db.iliad.insert({ pg : 164, line : "Scepticism is as much the result of knowledge, as knowledge is of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 165, line : "scepticism. To be content with what we at present know, is, for the most"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 166, line : "part, to shut our ears against conviction; since, from the very gradual"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 167, line : "character of our education, we must continually forget, and emancipate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 168, line : "ourselves from, knowledge previously acquired; we must set aside old"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 169, line : "notions and embrace fresh ones; and, as we learn, we must be daily"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 170, line : "unlearning something which it has cost us no small labour and anxiety to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 171, line : "acquire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 173, line : "And this difficulty attaches itself more closely to an age in which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 174, line : "progress has gained a strong ascendency over prejudice, and in which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 175, line : "persons and things are, day by day, finding their real level, in lieu of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 176, line : "their conventional value. The same principles which have swept away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 177, line : "traditional abuses, and which are making rapid havoc among the revenues of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 178, line : "sinecurists, and stripping the thin, tawdry veil from attractive"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 179, line : "superstitions, are working as actively in literature as in society. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 180, line : "credulity of one writer, or the partiality of another, finds as powerful a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 181, line : "touchstone and as wholesome a chastisement in the healthy scepticism of a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 182, line : "temperate class of antagonists, as the dreams of conservatism, or the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 183, line : "impostures of pluralist sinecures in the Church. History and tradition,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 184, line : "whether of ancient or comparatively recent times, are subjected to very"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 185, line : "different handling from that which the indulgence or credulity of former"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 186, line : "ages could allow. Mere statements are jealously watched, and the motives"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 187, line : "of the writer form as important an ingredient in the analysis of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 188, line : "history, as the facts he records. Probability is a powerful and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 189, line : "troublesome test; and it is by this troublesome standard that a large"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 190, line : "portion of historical evidence is sifted. Consistency is no less"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 191, line : "pertinacious and exacting in its demands. In brief, to write a history, we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 192, line : "must know more than mere facts. Human nature, viewed under an induction of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 193, line : "extended experience, is the best help to the criticism of human history."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 194, line : "Historical characters can only be estimated by the standard which human"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 195, line : "experience, whether actual or traditionary, has furnished. To form correct"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 196, line : "views of individuals we must regard them as forming parts of a great"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 197, line : "whole--we must measure them by their relation to the mass of beings by whom"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 198, line : "they are surrounded, and, in contemplating the incidents in their lives or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 199, line : "condition which tradition has handed down to us, we must rather consider"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 200, line : "the general bearing of the whole narrative, than the respective"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 201, line : "probability of its details."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 203, line : "It is unfortunate for us, that, of some of the greatest men, we know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 204, line : "least, and talk most. Homer, Socrates, and Shakespere(1) have, perhaps,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 205, line : "contributed more to the intellectual enlightenment of mankind than any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 206, line : "other three writers who could be named, and yet the history of all three"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 207, line : "has given rise to a boundless ocean of discussion, which has left us"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 208, line : "little save the option of choosing which theory or theories we will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 209, line : "follow. The personality of Shakespere is, perhaps, the only thing in which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 210, line : "critics will allow us to believe without controversy; but upon everything"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 211, line : "else, even down to the authorship of plays, there is more or less of doubt"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 212, line : "and uncertainty. Of Socrates we know as little as the contradictions of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 213, line : "Plato and Xenophon will allow us to know. He was one of the _dramatis"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 214, line : "personae_ in two dramas as unlike in principles as in style. He appears as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 215, line : "the enunciator of opinions as different in their tone as those of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 216, line : "writers who have handed them down. When we have read Plato _or_ Xenophon,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 217, line : "we think we know something of Socrates; when we have fairly read and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 218, line : "examined both, we feel convinced that we are something worse than"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 219, line : "ignorant."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 221, line : "It has been an easy, and a popular expedient, of late years, to deny the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 222, line : "personal or real existence of men and things whose life and condition were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 223, line : "too much for our belief. This system--which has often comforted the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 224, line : "religious sceptic, and substituted the consolations of Strauss for those"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 225, line : "of the New Testament--has been of incalculable value to the historical"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 226, line : "theorists of the last and present centuries. To question the existence of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 227, line : "Alexander the Great, would be a more excusable act, than to believe in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 228, line : "that of Romulus. To deny a fact related in Herodotus, because it is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 229, line : "inconsistent with a theory developed from an Assyrian inscription which no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 230, line : "two scholars read in the same way, is more pardonable, than to believe in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 231, line : "the good-natured old king whom the elegant pen of Florian has"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 232, line : "idealized--_Numa Pompilius._"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 234, line : "Scepticism has attained its culminating point with respect to Homer, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 235, line : "the state of our Homeric knowledge may be described as a free permission"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 236, line : "to believe any theory, provided we throw overboard all written tradition,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 237, line : "concerning the author or authors of the Iliad and Odyssey. What few"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 238, line : "authorities exist on the subject, are summarily dismissed, although the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 239, line : "arguments appear to run in a circle. \"This cannot be true, because it is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 240, line : "not true; and, that is not true, because it cannot be true.\" Such seems to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 241, line : "be the style, in which testimony upon testimony, statement upon statement,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 242, line : "is consigned to denial and oblivion."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 244, line : "It is, however, unfortunate that the professed biographies of Homer are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 245, line : "partly forgeries, partly freaks of ingenuity and imagination, in which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 246, line : "truth is the requisite most wanting. Before taking a brief review of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 247, line : "Homeric theory in its present conditions, some notice must be taken of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 248, line : "treatise on the Life of Homer which has been attributed to Herodotus."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 250, line : "According to this document, the city of Cumae in Ćolia, was, at an early"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 251, line : "period, the seat of frequent immigrations from various parts of Greece."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 252, line : "Among the immigrants was Menapolus, the son of Ithagenes. Although poor,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 253, line : "he married, and the result of the union was a girl named Critheis. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 254, line : "girl was left an orphan at an early age, under the guardianship of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 255, line : "Cleanax, of Argos. It is to the indiscretion of this maiden that we \"are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 256, line : "indebted for so much happiness.\" Homer was the first fruit of her juvenile"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 257, line : "frailty, and received the name of Melesigenes, from having been born near"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 258, line : "the river Meles, in Boeotia, whither Critheis had been transported in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 259, line : "order to save her reputation."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 261, line : "\"At this time,\" continues our narrative, \"there lived at Smyrna a man"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 262, line : "named Phemius, a teacher of literature and music, who, not being married,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 263, line : "engaged Critheis to manage his household, and spin the flax he received as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 264, line : "the price of his scholastic labours. So satisfactory was her performance"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 265, line : "of this task, and so modest her conduct, that he made proposals of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 266, line : "marriage, declaring himself, as a further inducement, willing to adopt her"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 267, line : "son, who, he asserted, would become a clever man, if he were carefully"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 268, line : "brought up.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 270, line : "They were married; careful cultivation ripened the talents which nature"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 271, line : "had bestowed, and Melesigenes soon surpassed his schoolfellows in every"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 272, line : "attainment, and, when older, rivalled his preceptor in wisdom. Phemius"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 273, line : "died, leaving him sole heir to his property, and his mother soon followed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 274, line : "Melesigenes carried on his adopted father's school with great success,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 275, line : "exciting the admiration not only of the inhabitants of Smyrna, but also of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 276, line : "the strangers whom the trade carried on there, especially in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 277, line : "exportation of corn, attracted to that city. Among these visitors, one"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 278, line : "Mentes, from Leucadia, the modern Santa Maura, who evinced a knowledge and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 279, line : "intelligence rarely found in those times, persuaded Melesigenes to close"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 280, line : "his school, and accompany him on his travels. He promised not only to pay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 281, line : "his expenses, but to furnish him with a further stipend, urging, that,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 282, line : "\"While he was yet young, it was fitting that he should see with his own"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 283, line : "eyes the countries and cities which might hereafter be the subjects of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 284, line : "discourses.\" Melesigenes consented, and set out with his patron,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 285, line : "\"examining all the curiosities of the countries they visited, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 286, line : "informing himself of everything by interrogating those whom he met.\" We"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 287, line : "may also suppose, that he wrote memoirs of all that he deemed worthy of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 288, line : "preservation(2) Having set sail from Tyrrhenia and Iberia, they reached"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 289, line : "Ithaca. Here Melesigenes, who had already suffered in his eyes, became"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 290, line : "much worse, and Mentes, who was about to leave for Leucadia, left him to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 291, line : "the medical superintendence of a friend of his, named Mentor, the son of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 292, line : "Alcinor. Under his hospitable and intelligent host, Melesigenes rapidly"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 293, line : "became acquainted with the legends respecting Ulysses, which afterwards"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 294, line : "formed the subject of the Odyssey. The inhabitants of Ithaca assert, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 295, line : "it was here that Melesigenes became blind, but the Colophomans make their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 296, line : "city the seat of that misfortune. He then returned to Smyrna, where he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 297, line : "applied himself to the study of poetry.(3)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 299, line : "But poverty soon drove him to Cumae. Having passed over the Hermaean"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 300, line : "plain, he arrived at Neon Teichos, the New Wall, a colony of Cumae. Here"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 301, line : "his misfortunes and poetical talent gained him the friendship of one"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 302, line : "Tychias, an armourer. \"And up to my time,\" continued the author, \"the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 303, line : "inhabitants showed the place where he used to sit when giving a recitation"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 304, line : "of his verses, and they greatly honoured the spot. Here also a poplar"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 305, line : "grew, which they said had sprung up ever since Melesigenes arrived\".(4)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 307, line : "But poverty still drove him on, and he went by way of Larissa, as being"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 308, line : "the most convenient road. Here, the Cumans say, he composed an epitaph on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 309, line : "Gordius, king of Phrygia, which has however, and with greater probability,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 310, line : "been attributed to Cleobulus of Lindus.(5)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 312, line : "Arrived at Cumae, he frequented the _converzationes_(6) of the old men,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 313, line : "and delighted all by the charms of his poetry. Encouraged by this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 314, line : "favourable reception, he declared that, if they would allow him a public"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 315, line : "maintenance, he would render their city most gloriously  renowned. They"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 316, line : "avowed their willingness to support him in the measure he proposed, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 317, line : "procured him an audience in the council. Having made the speech, with the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 318, line : "purport of which our author has forgotten to acquaint us, he retired, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 319, line : "left them to debate respecting the answer to be given to his proposal."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 321, line : "The greater part of the assembly seemed favourable to the poet's demand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 322, line : "but one man observed that \"if they were to feed _Homers,_ they would be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 323, line : "encumbered with a multitude of useless people.\" \"From this circumstance,\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 324, line : "says the writer, \"Melesigenes acquired the name of Homer, for the Cumans"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 325, line : "call blind men _Homers._\"(7) With a love of economy, which shows how"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 326, line : "similar the world has always been in its treatment of literary men, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 327, line : "pension was denied, and the poet vented his disappointment in a wish that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 328, line : "Cumoea might never produce a poet capable of giving it renown and glory."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 330, line : "At Phocoea, Homer was destined to experience another literary distress."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 331, line : "One Thestorides, who aimed at the reputation of poetical genius, kept"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 332, line : "Homer in his own house, and allowed him a pittance, on condition of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 333, line : "verses of the poet passing in his name. Having collected sufficient poetry"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 334, line : "to be profitable, Thestorides, like some would-be-literary publishers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 335, line : "neglected the man whose brains he had sucked, and left him. At his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 336, line : "departure, Homer is said to have observed: \"O Thestorides, of the many"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 337, line : "things hidden from the knowledge of man, nothing is more unintelligible"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 338, line : "than the human heart.\"(8)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 340, line : "Homer continued his career of difficulty and distress, until some Chian"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 341, line : "merchants, struck by the similarity of the verses they heard him recite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 342, line : "acquainted him with the fact that Thestorides was pursuing a profitable"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 343, line : "livelihood by the recital of the very same poems. This at once determined"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 344, line : "him to set out for Chios. No vessel happened then to be setting sail"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 345, line : "thither, but he found one ready to Start for Erythrae, a town of Ionia,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 346, line : "which faces that island, and he prevailed upon the seamen to allow him to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 347, line : "accompany them. Having embarked, he invoked a favourable wind, and prayed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 348, line : "that he might be able to expose the imposture of Thestorides, who, by his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 349, line : "breach of hospitality, had drawn down the wrath of Jove the Hospitable."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 351, line : "At Erythrae, Homer fortunately met with a person who had known him in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 352, line : "Phocoea, by whose assistance he at length, after some difficulty, reached"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 353, line : "the little hamlet of Pithys. Here he met with an adventure, which we will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 354, line : "continue in the words of our author. \"Having set out from Pithys, Homer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 355, line : "went on, attracted by the cries of some goats that were pasturing. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 356, line : "dogs barked on his approach, and he cried out. Glaucus (for that was the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 357, line : "name of the goat-herd) heard his voice, ran up quickly, called off his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 358, line : "dogs, and drove them away from Homer. For or some time he stood wondering"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 359, line : "how a blind man should have reached such a place alone, and what could be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 360, line : "his design in coming. He then went up to him, and inquired who he was, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 361, line : "how he had come to desolate places and untrodden spots, and of what he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 362, line : "stood in need. Homer, by recounting to him the whole history of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 363, line : "misfortunes, moved him with compassion; and he took him, and led him to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 364, line : "his cot, and having lit a fire, bade him sup.(9)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 366, line : "\"The dogs, instead of eating, kept barking at the stranger, according to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 367, line : "their usual habit. Whereupon Homer addressed Glaucus thus: O Glaucus, my"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 368, line : "friend, prythee attend to my behest. First give the dogs their supper at"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 369, line : "the doors of the hut: for so it is better, since, whilst they watch, nor"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 370, line : "thief nor wild beast will approach the fold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 372, line : "Glaucus was pleased with the advice, and marvelled at its author. Having"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 373, line : "finished supper, they banqueted(10) afresh on conversation, Homer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 374, line : "narrating his wanderings, and telling of the cities he had visited."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 376, line : "At length they retired to rest; but on the following morning, Glaucus"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 377, line : "resolved to go to his master, and acquaint him with his meeting with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 378, line : "Homer. Having left the goats in charge of a fellow-servant, he left Homer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 379, line : "at home, promising to return quickly. Having arrived at Bolissus, a place"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 380, line : "near the farm, and finding his mate, he told him the whole story"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 381, line : "respecting Homer and his journey. He paid little attention to what he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 382, line : "said, and blamed Glaucus for his stupidity in taking in and feeding maimed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 383, line : "and enfeebled persons. However, he bade him bring the stranger to him."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 385, line : "Glaucus told Homer what had taken place, and bade him follow him, assuring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 386, line : "him that good fortune would be the result. Conversation soon showed that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 387, line : "the stranger was a man of much cleverness and general knowledge, and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 388, line : "Chian persuaded him to remain, and to undertake the charge of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 389, line : "children.(11)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 391, line : "Besides the satisfaction of driving the impostor Thestorides from the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 392, line : "island, Homer enjoyed considerable success as a teacher. In the town of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 393, line : "Chios he established a school where he taught the precepts of poetry. \"To"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 394, line : "this day,\" says Chandler,(12) \"the most curious remain is that which has"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 395, line : "been named, without reason, the School of Homer. It is on the coast, at"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 396, line : "some distance from the city, northward, and appears to have been an open"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 397, line : "temple of Cybele, formed on the top of a rock. The shape is oval, and in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 398, line : "the centre is the image of the goddess, the head and an arm wanting. She"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 399, line : "is represented, as usual, sitting. The chair has a lion carved on each"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 400, line : "side, and on the back. The area is bounded by a low rim, or seat, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 401, line : "about five yards over. The whole is hewn out of the mountain, is rude,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 402, line : "indistinct, and probably of the most remote antiquity.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 404, line : "So successful was this school, that Homer realised a considerable fortune."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 405, line : "He married, and had two daughters, one of whom died single, the other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 406, line : "married a Chian."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 408, line : "The following passage betrays the same tendency to connect the personages"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 409, line : "of the poems with the history of the poet, which has already been"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 410, line : "mentioned:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 412, line : "\"In his poetical compositions Homer displays great gratitude towards"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 413, line : "Mentor of Ithaca, in the Odyssey, whose name he has inserted in his poem"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 414, line : "as the companion of Ulysses,(13) in return for the care taken of him when"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 415, line : "afflicted with blindness. He also testifies his gratitude to Phemius, who"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 416, line : "had given him both sustenance and instruction.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 418, line : "His celebrity continued to increase, and many persons advised him to visit"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 419, line : "Greece, whither his reputation had now extended. Having, it is said, made"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 420, line : "some additions to his poems calculated to please the vanity of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 421, line : "Athenians, of whose city he had hitherto made no mention,(14) he sent out"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 422, line : "for Samos. Here being recognized by a Samian, who had met with him in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 423, line : "Chios, he was handsomely received, and invited to join in celebrating the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 424, line : "Apaturian festival. He recited some verses, which gave great satisfaction,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 425, line : "and by singing the Eiresione at the New Moon festivals, he earned a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 426, line : "subsistence, visiting the houses of the rich, with whose children he was"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 427, line : "very popular."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 429, line : "In the spring he sailed for Athens, and arrived at the island of Ios, now"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 430, line : "Ino, where he fell extremely ill, and died. It is said that his death"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 431, line : "arose from vexation, at not having been able to unravel an enigma proposed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 432, line : "by some fishermen's children.(15)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 434, line : "Such is, in brief, the substance of the earliest life of Homer we possess,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 435, line : "and so broad are the evidences of its historical worthlessness, that it is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 436, line : "scarcely necessary to point them out in detail. Let us now consider some"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 437, line : "of the opinions to which a persevering, patient, and learned--but by no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 438, line : "means consistent--series of investigations has led. In doing so, I profess"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 439, line : "to bring forward statements, not to vouch for their reasonableness or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 440, line : "probability."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 442, line : "\"Homer appeared. The history of this poet and his works is lost in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 443, line : "doubtful obscurity, as is the history of many of the first minds who have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 444, line : "done honour to humanity, because they rose amidst darkness. The majestic"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 445, line : "stream of his song, blessing and fertilizing, flows like the Nile, through"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 446, line : "many lands and nations; and, like the sources of the Nile, its fountains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 447, line : "will ever remain concealed.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 449, line : "Such are the words in which one of the most judicious German critics has"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 450, line : "eloquently described the uncertainty in which the whole of the Homeric"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 451, line : "question is involved. With no less truth and feeling he proceeds:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 453, line : "\"It seems here of chief importance to expect no more than the nature of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 454, line : "things makes possible. If the period of tradition in history is the region"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 455, line : "of twilight, we should not expect in it perfect light. The creations of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 456, line : "genius always seem like miracles, because they are, for the most part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 457, line : "created far out of the reach of observation. If we were in possession of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 458, line : "all the historical testimonies, we never could wholly explain the origin"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 459, line : "of the Iliad and the Odyssey; for their origin, in all essential points,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 460, line : "must have remained the secret of the poet.\" (16)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 462, line : "From this criticism, which shows as much insight into the depths of human"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 463, line : "nature as into the minute wire-drawings of scholastic investigation, let"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 464, line : "us pass on to the main question at issue. Was Homer an individual?(17) or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 465, line : "were the Iliad and Odyssey the result of an ingenious arrangement of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 466, line : "fragments by earlier poets?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 468, line : "Well has Landor remarked: \"Some tell us there were twenty Homers; some"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 469, line : "deny that there was ever one. It were idle and foolish to shake the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 470, line : "contents of a vase, in order to let them settle at last. We are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 471, line : "perpetually labouring to destroy our delights, our composure, our devotion"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 472, line : "to superior power. Of all the animals on earth we least know what is good"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 473, line : "for us. My opinion is, that what is best for us is our admiration of good."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 474, line : "No man living venerates Homer more than I do.\" (18)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 476, line : "But, greatly as we admire the generous enthusiasm which rests contented"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 477, line : "with the poetry on which its best impulses had been nurtured and fostered,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 478, line : "without seeking to destroy the vividness of first impressions by minute"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 479, line : "analysis--our editorial office compels us to give some attention to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 480, line : "doubts and difficulties with which the Homeric question is beset, and to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 481, line : "entreat our reader, for a brief period, to prefer his judgment to his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 482, line : "imagination, and to condescend to dry details."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 484, line : "Before, however, entering into particulars respecting the question of this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 485, line : "unity of the Homeric poems, (at least of the Iliad,) I must express my"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 486, line : "sympathy with the sentiments expressed in the following remarks:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 488, line : "\"We cannot but think the universal admiration of its unity by the better,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 489, line : "the poetic age of Greece, almost conclusive testimony to its original"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 490, line : "composition. It was not till the age of the grammarians that its primitive"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 491, line : "integrity was called in question; nor is it injustice to assert, that the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 492, line : "minute and analytical spirit of a grammarian is not the best qualification"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 493, line : "for the profound feeling, the comprehensive conception of an harmonious"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 494, line : "whole. The most exquisite anatomist may be no judge of the symmetry of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 495, line : "human frame: and we would take the opinion of Chantrey or Westmacott on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 496, line : "the proportions and general beauty of a form, rather than that of Mr."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 497, line : "Brodie or Sir Astley Cooper."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 499, line : "\"There is some truth, though some malicious exaggeration, in the lines of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 500, line : "Pope.--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 502, line : "\"'The critic eye--that microscope of wit"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 503, line : "Sees hairs and pores, examines bit by bit,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 504, line : "How parts relate to parts, or they to whole"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 505, line : "The body's harmony, the beaming soul,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 506, line : "Are things which Kuster, Burmann, Wasse, shall see,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 507, line : "When man's whole frame is obvious to a flea.'\"(19)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 509, line : "Long was the time which elapsed before any one dreamt of questioning the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 510, line : "unity of the authorship of the Homeric poems. The grave and cautious"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 511, line : "Thucydides quoted without hesitation the Hymn to Apollo,(20) the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 512, line : "authenticity of which has been already disclaimed by modern critics."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 513, line : "Longinus, in an oft quoted passage, merely expressed an opinion touching"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 514, line : "the comparative inferiority of the Odyssey to the Iliad,(21) and, among a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 515, line : "mass of ancient authors, whose very names(22) it would be tedious to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 516, line : "detail, no suspicion of the personal non-existence of Homer ever arose. So"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 517, line : "far, the voice of antiquity seems to be in favour of our early ideas on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 518, line : "the subject; let us now see what are the discoveries to which more modern"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 519, line : "investigations lay claim."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 521, line : "At the end of the seventeenth century, doubts had begun to awaken on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 522, line : "subject, and we find Bentley remarking that \"Homer wrote a sequel of songs"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 523, line : "and rhapsodies, to be sung by himself, for small comings and good cheer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 524, line : "at festivals and other days of merriment. These loose songs were not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 525, line : "collected together, in the form of an epic poem, till about Peisistratus'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 526, line : "time, about five hundred years after.\"(23)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 528, line : "Two French writers--Hedelin and Perrault--avowed a similar scepticism on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 529, line : "subject; but it is in the \"Scienza Nuova\" of Battista Vico, that we first"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 530, line : "meet with the germ of the theory, subsequently defended by Wolf with so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 531, line : "much learning and acuteness. Indeed, it is with the Wolfian theory that we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 532, line : "have chiefly to deal, and with the following bold hypothesis, which we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 533, line : "will detail in the words of Grote(24)--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 535, line : "\"Half a century ago, the acute and valuable Prolegomena of F. A. Wolf,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 536, line : "turning to account the Venetian Scholia, which had then been recently"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 537, line : "published, first opened philosophical discussion as to the history of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 538, line : "Homeric text. A considerable part of that dissertation (though by no means"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 539, line : "the whole) is employed in vindicating the position, previously announced"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 540, line : "by Bentley, amongst others, that the separate constituent portions of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 541, line : "Iliad and Odyssey had not been cemented together into any compact body and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 542, line : "unchangeable order, until the days of Peisistratus, in the sixth century"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 543, line : "before Christ. As a step towards that conclusion, Wolf maintained that no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 544, line : "written copies of either poem could be shown to have existed during the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 545, line : "earlier times, to which their composition is referred; and that without"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 546, line : "writing, neither the perfect symmetry of so complicated a work could have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 547, line : "been originally conceived by any poet, nor, if realized by him,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 548, line : "transmitted with assurance to posterity. The absence of easy and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 549, line : "convenient writing, such as must be indispensably supposed for long"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 550, line : "manuscripts, among the early Greeks, was thus one of the points in Wolf's"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 551, line : "case against the primitive integrity of the Iliad and Odyssey. By Nitzsch,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 552, line : "and other leading opponents of Wolf, the connection of the one with the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 553, line : "other seems to have been accepted as he originally put it; and it has been"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 554, line : "considered incumbent on those who defended the ancient aggregate character"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 555, line : "of the Iliad and Odyssey, to maintain that they were written poems from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 556, line : "the beginning."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 558, line : "\"To me it appears, that the architectonic functions ascribed by Wolf to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 559, line : "Peisistratus and his associates, in reference to the Homeric poems, are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 560, line : "nowise admissible. But much would undoubtedly be gained towards that view"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 561, line : "of the question, if it could be shown, that, in order to controvert it, we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 562, line : "were driven to the necessity of admitting long written poems, in the ninth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 563, line : "century before the Christian aera. Few things, in my opinion, can be more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 564, line : "improbable; and Mr. Payne Knight, opposed as he is to the Wolfian"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 565, line : "hypothesis, admits this no less than Wolf himself. The traces of writing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 566, line : "in Greece, even in the seventh century before the Christian aera, are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 567, line : "exceedingly trifling. We have no remaining inscription earlier than the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 568, line : "fortieth Olympiad, and the early inscriptions are rude and unskilfully"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 569, line : "executed; nor can we even assure ourselves whether Archilochus, Simonides"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 570, line : "of Amorgus, Kallinus, Tyrtaeus, Xanthus, and the other early elegiac and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 571, line : "lyric poets, committed their compositions to writing, or at what time the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 572, line : "practice of doing so became familiar. The first positive ground which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 573, line : "authorizes us to presume the existence of a manuscript of Homer, is in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 574, line : "famous ordinance of Solon, with regard to the rhapsodies at the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 575, line : "Panathenaea: but for what length of time previously manuscripts had"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 576, line : "existed, we are unable to say."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 578, line : "\"Those who maintain the Homeric poems to have been written from the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 579, line : "beginning, rest their case, not upon positive proofs, nor yet upon the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 580, line : "existing habits of society with regard to poetry--for they admit generally"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 581, line : "that the Iliad and Odyssey were not read, but recited and heard,--but upon"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 582, line : "the supposed necessity that there must have been manuscripts to ensure the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 583, line : "preservation of the poems--the unassisted memory of reciters being neither"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 584, line : "sufficient nor trustworthy. But here we only escape a smaller difficulty"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 585, line : "by running into a greater; for the existence of trained bards, gifted with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 586, line : "extraordinary memory, (25) is far less astonishing than that of long"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 587, line : "manuscripts, in an age essentially non-reading and non-writing, and when"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 588, line : "even suitable instruments and materials for the process are not obvious."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 589, line : "Moreover, there is a strong positive reason for believing that the bard"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 590, line : "was under no necessity of refreshing his memory by consulting a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 591, line : "manuscript; for if such had been the fact, blindness would have been a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 592, line : "disqualification for the profession, which we know that it was not, as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 593, line : "well from the example of Demodokus, in the Odyssey, as from that of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 594, line : "blind bard of Chios, in the Hymn to the Delian Apollo, whom Thucydides, as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 595, line : "well as the general tenor of Grecian legend, identifies with Homer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 596, line : "himself. The author of that hymn, be he who he may, could never have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 597, line : "described a blind man as attaining the utmost perfection in his art, if he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 598, line : "had been conscious that the memory of the bard was only maintained by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 599, line : "constant reference to the manuscript in his chest.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 601, line : "The loss of the digamma, that _crux_ of critics, that quicksand upon which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 602, line : "even the acumen of Bentley was shipwrecked, seems to prove beyond a doubt,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 603, line : "that the pronunciation of the Greek language had undergone a considerable"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 604, line : "change. Now it is certainly difficult to suppose that the Homeric poems"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 605, line : "could have suffered by this change, had written copies been preserved. If"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 606, line : "Chaucer's poetry, for instance, had not been written, it could only have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 607, line : "come down to us in a softened form, more like the effeminate version of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 608, line : "Dryden, than the rough, quaint, noble original."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 610, line : "\"At what period,\" continues Grote, \"these poems, or indeed any other Greek"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 611, line : "poems, first began to be written, must be matter of conjecture, though"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 612, line : "there is ground for assurance that it was before the time of Solon. If, in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 613, line : "the absence of evidence, we may venture upon naming any more determinate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 614, line : "period, the question a once suggests itself, What were the purposes which,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 615, line : "in that state of society, a manuscript at its first commencement must have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 616, line : "been intended to answer? For whom was a written Iliad necessary? Not for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 617, line : "the rhapsodes; for with them it was not only planted in the memory, but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 618, line : "also interwoven with the feelings, and conceived in conjunction with all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 619, line : "those flexions and intonations of voice, pauses, and other oral artifices"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 620, line : "which were required for emphatic delivery, and which the naked manuscript"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 621, line : "could never reproduce. Not for the general public--they were accustomed to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 622, line : "receive it with its rhapsodic delivery, and with its accompaniments of a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 623, line : "solemn and crowded festival. The only persons for whom the written Iliad"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 624, line : "would be suitable would be a select few; studious and curious men; a class"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 625, line : "of readers capable of analyzing the complicated emotions which they had"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 626, line : "experienced as hearers in the crowd, and who would, on perusing the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 627, line : "written words, realize in their imaginations a sensible portion of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 628, line : "impression communicated by the reciter. Incredible as the statement may"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 629, line : "seem in an age like the present, there is in all early societies, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 630, line : "there was in early Greece, a time when no such reading class existed. If"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 631, line : "we could discover at what time such a class first began to be formed, we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 632, line : "should be able to make a guess at the time when the old epic poems were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 633, line : "first committed to writing. Now the period which may with the greatest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 634, line : "probability be fixed upon as having first witnessed the formation even of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 635, line : "the narrowest reading class in Greece, is the middle of the seventh"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 636, line : "century before the Christian aera (B.C. 660 to B.C. 630), the age of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 637, line : "Terpander, Kallinus, Archilochus, Simonides of Amorgus, &c. I ground this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 638, line : "supposition on the change then operated in the character and tendencies of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 639, line : "Grecian poetry and music--the elegiac and the iambic measures having been"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 640, line : "introduced as rivals to the primitive hexameter, and poetical compositions"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 641, line : "having been transferred from the epical past to the affairs of present and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 642, line : "real life. Such a change was important at a time when poetry was the only"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 643, line : "known mode of publication (to use a modern phrase not altogether suitable,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 644, line : "yet the nearest approaching to the sense). It argued a new way of looking"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 645, line : "at the old epical treasures of the people as well as a thirst for new"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 646, line : "poetical effect; and the men who stood forward in it, may well be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 647, line : "considered as desirous to study, and competent to criticize, from their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 648, line : "own individual point of view, the written words of the Homeric rhapsodies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 649, line : "just as we are told that Kallinus both noticed and eulogized the Thebais"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 650, line : "as the production of Homer. There seems, therefore, ground for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 651, line : "conjecturing that (for the use of this newly-formed and important, but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 652, line : "very narrow class), manuscripts of the Homeric poems and other old"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 653, line : "epics,--the Thebais and the Cypria, as well as the Iliad and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 654, line : "Odyssey,--began to be compiled towards the middle of the seventh century"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 655, line : "(B.C. 1); and the opening of Egypt to Grecian commerce, which took place"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 656, line : "about the same period, would furnish increased facilities for obtaining"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 657, line : "the requisite papyrus to write upon. A reading class, when once formed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 658, line : "would doubtless slowly increase, and the number of manuscripts along with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 659, line : "it; so that before the time of Solon, fifty years afterwards, both readers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 660, line : "and manuscripts, though still comparatively few, might have attained a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 661, line : "certain recognized authority, and formed a tribunal of reference against"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 662, line : "the carelessness of individual rhapsodes.\"(26)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 664, line : "But even Peisistratus has not been suffered to remain in possession of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 665, line : "credit, and we cannot help feeling the force of the following"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 666, line : "observations--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 669, line : "\"There are several incidental circumstances which, in our opinion,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 670, line : "throw some suspicion over the whole history of the Peisistratid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 671, line : "compilation, at least over the theory, that the Iliad was cast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 672, line : "into its present stately and harmonious form by the directions of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 673, line : "the Athenian ruler. If the great poets, who flourished at the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 674, line : "bright period of Grecian song, of which, alas! we have inherited"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 675, line : "little more than the fame, and the faint echo, if Stesichorus,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 676, line : "Anacreon, and Simonides were employed in the noble task of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 677, line : "compiling the Iliad and Odyssey, so much must have been done to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 678, line : "arrange, to connect, to harmonize, that it is almost incredible,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 679, line : "that stronger marks of Athenian manufacture should not remain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 680, line : "Whatever occasional anomalies may be detected, anomalies which no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 681, line : "doubt arise out of our own ignorance of the language of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 682, line : "Homeric age, however the irregular use of the digamma may have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 683, line : "perplexed our Bentleys, to whom the name of Helen is said to have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 684, line : "caused as much disquiet and distress as the fair one herself among"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 685, line : "the heroes of her age, however Mr. Knight may have failed in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 686, line : "reducing the Homeric language to its primitive form; however,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 687, line : "finally, the Attic dialect may not have assumed all its more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 688, line : "marked and distinguishing characteristics--still it is difficult to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 689, line : "suppose that the language, particularly in the joinings and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 690, line : "transitions, and connecting parts, should not more clearly betray"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 691, line : "the incongruity between the more ancient and modern forms of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 692, line : "expression. It is not quite in character with such a period to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 693, line : "imitate an antique style, in order to piece out an imperfect poem"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 694, line : "in the character of the original, as Sir Walter Scott has done in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 695, line : "his continuation of Sir Tristram."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 697, line : "\"If, however, not even such faint and indistinct traces of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 698, line : "Athenian compilation are discoverable in the language of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 699, line : "poems, the total absence of Athenian national feeling is perhaps"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 700, line : "no less worthy of observation. In later, and it may fairly be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 701, line : "suspected in earlier times, the Athenians were more than"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 702, line : "ordinarily jealous of the fame of their ancestors. But, amid all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 703, line : "the traditions of the glories of early Greece embodied in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 704, line : "Iliad, the Athenians play a most subordinate and insignificant"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 705, line : "part. Even the few passages which relate to their ancestors, Mr."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 706, line : "Knight suspects to be interpolations. It is possible, indeed, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 707, line : "in its leading outline, the Iliad may be true to historic fact,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 708, line : "that in the great maritime expedition of western Greece against"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 709, line : "the rival and half-kindred empire of the Laomedontiadae, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 710, line : "chieftain of Thessaly, from his valour and the number of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 711, line : "forces, may have been the most important ally of the Peloponnesian"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 712, line : "sovereign; the preeminent value of the ancient poetry on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 713, line : "Trojan war may thus have forced the national feeling of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 714, line : "Athenians to yield to their taste. The songs which spoke of their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 715, line : "own great ancestor were, no doubt, of far inferior sublimity and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 716, line : "popularity, or, at first sight, a Theseid would have been much"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 717, line : "more likely to have emanated from an Athenian synod of compilers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 718, line : "of ancient song, than an Achilleid or an Olysseid. Could France"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 719, line : "have given birth to a Tasso, Tancred would have been the hero of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 720, line : "the Jerusalem. If, however, the Homeric ballads, as they are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 721, line : "sometimes called, which related the wrath of Achilles, with all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 722, line : "its direful consequences, were so far superior to the rest of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 723, line : "poetic cycle, as to admit no rivalry,--it is still surprising, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 724, line : "throughout the whole poem the _callida junctura_ should never"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 725, line : "betray the workmanship of an Athenian hand, and that the national"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 726, line : "spirit of a race, who have at a later period not inaptly been"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 727, line : "compared to our self admiring neighbours, the French, should"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 728, line : "submit with lofty self denial to the almost total exclusion of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 729, line : "their own ancestors--or, at least, to the questionable dignity of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 730, line : "only having produced a leader tolerably skilled in the military"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 731, line : "tactics of his age.\"(27)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 734, line : "To return to the Wolfian theory. While it is to be confessed, that Wolf's"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 735, line : "objections to the primitive integrity of the Iliad and Odyssey have never"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 736, line : "been wholly got over, we cannot help discovering that they have failed to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 737, line : "enlighten us as to any substantial point, and that the difficulties with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 738, line : "which the whole subject is beset, are rather augmented than otherwise, if"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 739, line : "we admit his hypothesis. Nor is Lachmann's(28) modification of his theory"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 740, line : "any better. He divides the first twenty-two books of the Iliad into"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 741, line : "sixteen different songs, and treats as ridiculous the belief that their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 742, line : "amalgamation into one regular poem belongs to a period earlier than the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 743, line : "age of Peisistratus. This, as Grote observes, \"explains the gaps and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 744, line : "contradictions in the narrative, but it explains nothing else.\" Moreover,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 745, line : "we find no contradictions warranting this belief, and the so-called"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 746, line : "sixteen poets concur in getting rid of the following leading men in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 747, line : "first battle after the secession of Achilles: Elphenor, chief of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 748, line : "Euboeans; Tlepolemus, of the Rhodians; Pandarus, of the Lycians; Odius, of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 749, line : "the Halizonians; Pirous and Acamas, of the Thracians. None of these heroes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 750, line : "again make their appearance, and we can but agree with Colonel Mure, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 751, line : "\"it seems strange that any number of independent poets should have so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 752, line : "harmoniously dispensed with the services of all six in the sequel.\" The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 753, line : "discrepancy, by which Pylaemenes, who is represented as dead in the fifth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 754, line : "book, weeps at his son's funeral in the thirteenth, can only be regarded"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 755, line : "as the result of an interpolation."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 757, line : "Grote, although not very distinct in stating his own opinions on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 758, line : "subject, has done much to clearly show the incongruity of the Wolfian"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 759, line : "theory, and of Lachmann's modifications with the character of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 760, line : "Peisistratus. But he has also shown, and we think with equal success, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 761, line : "the two questions relative to the primitive unity of these poems, or,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 762, line : "supposing that impossible, the unison of these parts by Peisistratus, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 763, line : "not before his time, are essentially distinct. In short, \"a man may"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 764, line : "believe the Iliad to have been put together out of pre-existing songs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 765, line : "without recognising the age of Peisistratus as the period of its first"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 766, line : "compilation.\" The friends or literary _employes_ of Peisistratus must have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 767, line : "found an Iliad that was already ancient, and the silence of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 768, line : "Alexandrine critics respecting the Peisistratic \"recension,\" goes far to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 769, line : "prove, that, among the numerous manuscripts they examined, this was either"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 770, line : "wanting, or thought unworthy of attention."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 772, line : "\"Moreover,\" he continues, \"the whole tenor of the poems themselves"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 773, line : "confirms what is here remarked. There is nothing, either in the Iliad or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 774, line : "Odyssey, which savours of modernism, applying that term to the age of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 775, line : "Peisistratus--nothing which brings to our view the alterations brought"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 776, line : "about by two centuries, in the Greek language, the coined money, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 777, line : "habits of writing and reading, the despotisms and republican governments,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 778, line : "the close military array, the improved construction of ships, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 779, line : "Amphiktyonic convocations, the mutual frequentation of religious"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 780, line : "festivals, the Oriental and Egyptian veins of religion, &c., familiar to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 781, line : "the latter epoch. These alterations Onomakritus, and the other literary"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 782, line : "friends of Peisistratus, could hardly have failed to notice, even without"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 783, line : "design, had they then, for the first time, undertaken the task of piecing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 784, line : "together many self existent epics into one large aggregate. Everything in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 785, line : "the two great Homeric poems, both in substance and in language, belongs to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 786, line : "an age two or three centuries earlier than Peisistratus. Indeed, even the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 787, line : "interpolations (or those passages which, on the best grounds, are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 788, line : "pronounced to be such) betray no trace of the sixth century before Christ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 789, line : "and may well have been heard by Archilochus and Kallinus--in some cases"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 790, line : "even by Arktinus and Hesiod--as genuine Homeric matter(29) As far as the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 791, line : "evidences on the case, as well internal as external, enable us to judge,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 792, line : "we seem warranted in believing that the Iliad and Odyssey were recited"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 793, line : "substantially as they now stand (always allowing for paitial divergences"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 794, line : "of text and interpolations) in 776 B.C., our first trustworthy mark of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 795, line : "Grecian time; and this ancient date, let it be added, as it is the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 796, line : "best-authenticated fact, so it is also the most important attribute of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 797, line : "Homeric poems, considered in reference to Grecian history; for they thus"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 798, line : "afford us an insight into the anti-historical character of the Greeks,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 799, line : "enabling us to trace the subsequent forward march of the nation, and to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 800, line : "seize instructive contrasts between their former and their later"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 801, line : "condition.\"(30)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 803, line : "On the whole, I am inclined to believe, that the labours of Peisistratus"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 804, line : "were wholly of an editorial character, although, I must confess, that I"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 805, line : "can lay down nothing respecting the extent of his labours. At the same"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 806, line : "time, so far from believing that the composition or primary arrangement of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 807, line : "these poems, in their present form, was the work of Peisistratus, I am"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 808, line : "rather persuaded that the fine taste and elegant mind of that Athenian(31)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 809, line : "would lead him to preserve an ancient and traditional order of the poems,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 810, line : "rather than to patch and re-construct them according to a fanciful"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 811, line : "hypothesis. I will not repeat the many discussions respecting whether the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 812, line : "poems were written or not, or whether the art of writing was known in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 813, line : "time of their reputed author. Suffice it to say, that the more we read,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 814, line : "the less satisfied we are upon either subject."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 816, line : "I cannot, however, help thinking, that the story which attributes the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 817, line : "preservation of these poems to Lycurgus, is little else than a version of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 818, line : "the same story as that of Peisistratus, while its historical probability"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 819, line : "must be measured by that of many others relating to the Spartan Confucius."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 821, line : "I will conclude this sketch of the Homeric theories, with an attempt, made"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 822, line : "by an ingenious friend, to unite them into something like consistency. It"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 823, line : "is as follows:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 826, line : "\"No doubt the common soldiers of that age had, like the common"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 827, line : "sailors of some fifty years ago, some one qualified to 'discourse"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 828, line : "in excellent music' among them. Many of these, like those of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 829, line : "negroes in the United States, were extemporaneous, and allusive to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 830, line : "events passing around them. But what was passing around them? The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 831, line : "grand events of a spirit-stirring war; occurrences likely to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 832, line : "impress themselves, as the mystical legends of former times had"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 833, line : "done, upon their memory; besides which, a retentive memory was"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 834, line : "deemed a virtue of the first water, and was cultivated accordingly"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 835, line : "in those ancient times. Ballads at first, and down to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 836, line : "beginning of the war with Troy, were merely recitations, with an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 837, line : "intonation. Then followed a species of recitative, probably with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 838, line : "an intoned burden. Tune next followed, as it aided the memory"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 839, line : "considerably."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 841, line : "\"It was at this period, about four hundred years after the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 842, line : "that a poet flourished of the name of Melesigenes, or Moeonides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 843, line : "but most probably the former. He saw that these ballads might be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 844, line : "made of great utility to his purpose of writing a poem on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 845, line : "social position of Hellas, and, as a collection, he published"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 846, line : "these lays, connecting them by a tale of his own. This poem now"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 847, line : "exists, under the title of the 'Odyssea.' The author, however, did"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 848, line : "not affix his own name to the poem, which, in fact, was, great"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 849, line : "part of it, remodelled from the archaic dialect of Crete, in which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 850, line : "tongue the ballads were found by him. He therefore called it the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 851, line : "poem of Homeros, or the Collector; but this is rather a proof of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 852, line : "his modesty and talent, than of his mere drudging arrangement of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 853, line : "other people's ideas; for, as Grote has finely observed, arguing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 854, line : "for the unity of authorship, 'a great poet might have re-cast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 855, line : "pre-existing separate songs into one comprehensive whole; but no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 856, line : "mere arrangers or compilers would be competent to do so.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 858, line : "\"While employed on the wild legend of Odysseus, he met with a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 859, line : "ballad, recording the quarrel of Achilles and Agamemnon. His noble"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 860, line : "mind seized the hint that there presented itself, and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 861, line : "Achilleis(32) grew under his hand. Unity of design, however,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 862, line : "caused him to publish the poem under the same pseudonyme as his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 863, line : "former work: and the disjointed lays of the ancient bards were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 864, line : "joined together, like those relating to the Cid, into a chronicle"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 865, line : "history, named the Iliad. Melesigenes knew that the poem was"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 866, line : "destined to be a lasting one, and so it has proved; but, first,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 867, line : "the poems were destined to undergo many vicissitudes and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 868, line : "corruptions, by the people who took to singing them in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 869, line : "streets, assemblies, and agoras. However, Solon first, and then"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 870, line : "Peisistratus, and afterwards Aristoteles and others, revised the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 871, line : "poems, and restored the works of Melesigenes Homeros to their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 872, line : "original integrity in a great measure.\"(33)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 875, line : "Having thus given some general notion of the strange theories which have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 876, line : "developed themselves respecting this most interesting subject, I must"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 877, line : "still express my conviction as to the unity of the authorship of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 878, line : "Homeric poems. To deny that many corruptions and interpolations disfigure"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 879, line : "them, and that the intrusive hand of the poetasters may here and there"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 880, line : "have inflicted a wound more serious than the negligence of the copyist,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 881, line : "would be an absurd and captious assumption, but it is to a higher"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 882, line : "criticism that we must appeal, if we would either understand or enjoy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 883, line : "these poems. In maintaining the authenticity and personality of their one"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 884, line : "author, be he Homer or Melesigenes, _quocunque nomine vocari eum jus"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 885, line : "fasque sit,_ I feel conscious that, while the whole weight of historical"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 886, line : "evidence is against the hypothesis which would assign these great works to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 887, line : "a plurality of authors, the most powerful internal evidence, and that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 888, line : "which springs from the deepest and most immediate impulse of the soul,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 889, line : "also speaks eloquently to the contrary."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 891, line : "The minutiae of verbal criticism I am far from seeking to despise. Indeed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 892, line : "considering the character of some of my own books, such an attempt would"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 893, line : "be gross inconsistency. But, while I appreciate its importance in a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 894, line : "philological view, I am inclined to set little store on its aesthetic"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 895, line : "value, especially in poetry. Three parts of the emendations made upon"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 896, line : "poets are mere alterations, some of which, had they been suggested to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 897, line : "author by his Maecenas or Africanus, he would probably have adopted."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 898, line : "Moreover, those who are most exact in laying down rules of verbal"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 899, line : "criticism and interpretation, are often least competent to carry out their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 900, line : "own precepts. Grammarians are not poets by profession, but may be so _per"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 901, line : "accidens._ I do not at this moment remember two emendations on Homer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 902, line : "calculated to substantially improve the poetry of a passage, although a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 903, line : "mass of remarks, from Herodotus down to Loewe, have given us the history"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 904, line : "of a thousand minute points, without which our Greek knowledge would be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 905, line : "gloomy and jejune."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 907, line : "But it is not on words only that grammarians, mere grammarians, will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 908, line : "exercise their elaborate and often tiresome ingenuity. Binding down an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 909, line : "heroic or dramatic poet to the block upon which they have previously"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 910, line : "dissected his words and sentences, they proceed to use the axe and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 911, line : "pruning knife by wholesale, and inconsistent in everything but their wish"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 912, line : "to make out a case of unlawful affiliation, they cut out book after book,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 913, line : "passage after passage, till the author is reduced to a collection of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 914, line : "fragments, or till those, who fancied they possessed the works of some"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 915, line : "great man, find that they have been put off with a vile counterfeit got up"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 916, line : "at second hand. If we compare the theories of Knight, Wolf, Lachmann, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 917, line : "others, we shall feel better satisfied of the utter uncertainty of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 918, line : "criticism than of the apocryphal position of Homer. One rejects what"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 919, line : "another considers the turning-point of his theory. One cuts a supposed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 920, line : "knot by expunging what another would explain by omitting something else."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 922, line : "Nor is this morbid species of sagacity by any means to be looked upon as a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 923, line : "literary novelty. Justus Lipsius, a scholar of no ordinary skill, seems to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 924, line : "revel in the imaginary discovery, that the tragedies attributed to Seneca"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 925, line : "are by _four_ different authors.(34) Now, I will venture to assert, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 926, line : "these tragedies are so uniform, not only in their borrowed phraseology--a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 927, line : "phraseology with which writers like Boethius and Saxo Grammaticus were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 928, line : "more charmed than ourselves--in their freedom from real poetry, and last,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 929, line : "but not least, in an ultra-refined and consistent abandonment of good"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 930, line : "taste, that few writers of the present day would question the capabilities"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 931, line : "of the same gentleman, be he Seneca or not, to produce not only these, but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 932, line : "a great many more equally bad. With equal sagacity, Father Hardouin"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 933, line : "astonished the world with the startling announcement that the Ćneid of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 934, line : "Virgil, and the satires of Horace, were literary deceptions. Now, without"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 935, line : "wishing to say one word of disrespect against the industry and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 936, line : "learning--nay, the refined acuteness--which scholars, like Wolf, have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 937, line : "bestowed upon this subject, I must express my fears, that many of our"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 938, line : "modern Homeric theories will become matter for the surprise and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 939, line : "entertainment, rather than the instruction, of posterity. Nor can I help"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 940, line : "thinking, that the literary history of more recent times will account for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 941, line : "many points of difficulty in the transmission of the Iliad and Odyssey to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 942, line : "a period so remote from that of their first creation."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 944, line : "I have already expressed my belief that the labours of Peisistratus were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 945, line : "of a purely editorial character; and there seems no more reason why"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 946, line : "corrupt and imperfect editions of Homer may not have been abroad in his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 947, line : "day, than that the poems of Valerius Flaccus and Tibullus should have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 948, line : "given so much trouble to Poggio, Scaliger, and others. But, after all, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 949, line : "main fault in all the Homeric theories is, that they demand too great a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 950, line : "sacrifice of those feelings to which poetry most powerfully appeals, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 951, line : "which are its most fitting judges. The ingenuity which has sought to rob"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 952, line : "us of the name and existence of Homer, does too much violence to that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 953, line : "inward emotion, which makes our whole soul yearn with love and admiration"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 954, line : "for the blind bard of Chios. To believe the author of the Iliad a mere"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 955, line : "compiler, is to degrade the powers of human invention; to elevate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 956, line : "analytical judgment at the expense of the most ennobling impulses of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 957, line : "soul; and to forget the ocean in the contemplation of a polypus. There is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 958, line : "a catholicity, so to speak, in the very name of Homer. Our faith in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 959, line : "author of the Iliad may be a mistaken one, but as yet nobody has taught us"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 960, line : "a better."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 962, line : "While, however, I look upon the belief in Homer as one that has nature"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 963, line : "herself for its mainspring; while I can join with old Ennius in believing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 964, line : "in Homer as the ghost, who, like some patron saint, hovers round the bed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 965, line : "of the poet, and even bestows rare gifts from that wealth of imagination"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 966, line : "which a host of imitators could not exhaust,--still I am far from wishing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 967, line : "to deny that the author of these great poems found a rich fund of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 968, line : "tradition, a well-stocked mythical storehouse from whence he might derive"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 969, line : "both subject and embellishment. But it is one thing to _use_ existing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 970, line : "romances in the embellishment of a poem, another to patch up the poem"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 971, line : "itself from such materials. What consistency of style and execution can be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 972, line : "hoped for from such an attempt? or, rather, what bad taste and tedium will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 973, line : "not be the infallible result?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 975, line : "A blending of popular legends, and a free use of the songs of other bards,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 976, line : "are features perfectly consistent with poetical originality. In fact, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 977, line : "most original writer is still drawing upon outward impressions--nay, even"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 978, line : "his own thoughts are a kind of secondary agents which support and feed the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 979, line : "impulses of imagination. But unless there be some grand pervading"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 980, line : "principle--some invisible, yet most distinctly stamped archetypus of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 981, line : "great whole, a poem like the Iliad can never come to the birth. Traditions"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 982, line : "the most picturesque, episodes the most pathetic, local associations"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 983, line : "teeming with the thoughts of gods and great men, may crowd in one mighty"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 984, line : "vision, or reveal themselves in more substantial forms to the mind of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 985, line : "poet; but, except the power to create a grand whole, to which these shall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 986, line : "be but as details and embellishments, be present, we shall have nought but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 987, line : "a scrap-book, a parterre filled with flowers and weeds strangling each"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 988, line : "other in their wild redundancy: we shall have a cento of rags and tatters,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 989, line : "which will require little acuteness to detect."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 991, line : "Sensible as I am of the difficulty of disproving a negative, and aware as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 992, line : "I must be of the weighty grounds there are for opposing my belief, it"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 993, line : "still seems to me that the Homeric question is one that is reserved for a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 994, line : "higher criticism than it has often obtained. We are not by nature intended"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 995, line : "to know all things; still less, to compass the powers by which the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 996, line : "greatest blessings of life have been placed at our disposal. Were faith no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 997, line : "virtue, then we might indeed wonder why God willed our ignorance on any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 998, line : "matter. But we are too well taught the contrary lesson; and it seems as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 999, line : "though our faith should be especially tried touching the men and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1000, line : "events which have wrought most influence upon the condition of humanity."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1001, line : "And there is a kind of sacredness attached to the memory of the great and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1002, line : "the good, which seems to bid us repulse the scepticism which would"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1003, line : "allegorize their existence into a pleasing apologue, and measure the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1004, line : "giants of intellect by an homeopathic dynameter."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1006, line : "Long and habitual reading of Homer appears to familiarize our thoughts"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1007, line : "even to his incongruities; or rather, if we read in a right spirit and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1008, line : "with a heartfelt appreciation, we are too much dazzled, too deeply wrapped"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1009, line : "in admiration of the whole, to dwell upon the minute spots which mere"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1010, line : "analysis can discover. In reading an heroic poem we must transform"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1011, line : "ourselves into heroes of the time being, we in imagination must fight over"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1012, line : "the same battles, woo the same loves, burn with the same sense of injury,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1013, line : "as an Achilles or a Hector. And if we can but attain this degree of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1014, line : "enthusiasm (and less enthusiasm will scarcely suffice for the reading of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1015, line : "Homer), we shall feel that the poems of Homer are not only the work of one"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1016, line : "writer, but of the greatest writer that ever touched the hearts of men by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1017, line : "the power of song."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1019, line : "And it was this supposed unity of authorship which gave these poems their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1020, line : "powerful influence over the minds of the men of old. Heeren, who is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1021, line : "evidently little disposed in favour of modern theories, finely observes:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1024, line : "\"It was Homer who formed the character of the Greek nation. No"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1025, line : "poet has ever, as a poet, exercised a similar influence over his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1026, line : "countrymen. Prophets, lawgivers, and sages have formed the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1027, line : "character of other nations; it was reserved to a poet to form that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1028, line : "of the Greeks. This is a feature in their character which was not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1029, line : "wholly erased even in the period of their degeneracy. When"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1030, line : "lawgivers and sages appeared in Greece, the work of the poet had"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1031, line : "already been accomplished; and they paid homage to his superior"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1032, line : "genius. He held up before his nation the mirror, in which they"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1033, line : "were to behold the world of gods and heroes no less than of feeble"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1034, line : "mortals, and to behold them reflected with purity and truth. His"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1035, line : "poems are founded on the first feeling of human nature; on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1036, line : "love of children, wife, and country; on that passion which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1037, line : "outweighs all others, the love of glory. His songs were poured"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1038, line : "forth from a breast which sympathized with all the feelings of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1039, line : "man; and therefore they enter, and will continue to enter, every"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1040, line : "breast which cherishes the same sympathies. If it is granted to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1041, line : "his immortal spirit, from another heaven than any of which he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1042, line : "dreamed on earth, to look down on his race, to see the nations"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1043, line : "from the fields of Asia to the forests of Hercynia, performing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1044, line : "pilgrimages to the fountain which his magic wand caused to flow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1045, line : "if it is permitted to him to view the vast assemblage of grand, of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1046, line : "elevated, of glorious productions, which had been called into"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1047, line : "being by means of his songs; wherever his immortal spirit may"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1048, line : "reside, this alone would suffice to complete his happiness.\"(35)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1051, line : "Can we contemplate that ancient monument, on which the \"Apotheosis of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1052, line : "Homer\"(36) is depictured, and not feel how much of pleasing association,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1053, line : "how much that appeals most forcibly and most distinctly to our minds, is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1054, line : "lost by the admittance of any theory but our old tradition? The more we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1055, line : "read, and the more we think--think as becomes the readers of Homer,--the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1056, line : "more rooted becomes the conviction that the Father of Poetry gave us this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1057, line : "rich inheritance, whole and entire. Whatever were the means of its"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1058, line : "preservation, let us rather be thankful for the treasury of taste and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1059, line : "eloquence thus laid open to our use, than seek to make it a mere centre"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1060, line : "around which to drive a series of theories, whose wildness is only"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1061, line : "equalled by their inconsistency with each other."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1063, line : "As the hymns, and some other poems usually ascribed to Homer, are not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1064, line : "included in Pope's translation, I will content myself with a brief account"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1065, line : "of the Battle of the Frogs and Mice, from the pen of a writer who has done"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1066, line : "it full justice(37):--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1069, line : "\"This poem,\" says Coleridge, \"is a short mock-heroic of ancient"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1070, line : "date. The text varies in different editions, and is obviously"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1071, line : "disturbed and corrupt to a great degree; it is commonly said to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1072, line : "have been a juvenile essay of Homer's genius; others have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1073, line : "attributed it to the same Pigrees, mentioned above, and whose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1074, line : "reputation for humour seems to have invited the appropriation of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1075, line : "any piece of ancient wit, the author of which was uncertain; so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1076, line : "little did the Greeks, before the age of the Ptolemies, know or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1077, line : "care about that department of criticism employed in determining"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1078, line : "the genuineness of ancient writings. As to this little poem being"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1079, line : "a youthful prolusion of Homer, it seems sufficient to say that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1080, line : "from the beginning to the end it is a plain and palpable parody,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1081, line : "not only of the general spirit, but of the numerous passages of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1082, line : "the Iliad itself; and even, if no such intention to parody were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1083, line : "discernible in it, the objection would still remain, that to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1084, line : "suppose a work of mere burlesque to be the primary effort of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1085, line : "poetry in a simple age, seems to reverse that order in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1086, line : "development of national taste, which the history of every other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1087, line : "people in Europe, and of many in Asia, has almost ascertained to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1088, line : "be a law of the human mind; it is in a state of society much more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1089, line : "refined and permanent than that described in the Iliad, that any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1090, line : "popularity would attend such a ridicule of war and the gods as is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1091, line : "contained in this poem; and the fact of there having existed three"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1092, line : "other poems of the same kind attributed, for aught we can see,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1093, line : "with as much reason to Homer, is a strong inducement to believe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1094, line : "that none of them were of the Homeric age. Knight infers from the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1095, line : "usage of the word deltos, \"writing tablet,\" instead of diphthera,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1096, line : "\"skin,\" which, according to Herod. 5, 58, was the material"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1097, line : "employed by the Asiatic Greeks for that purpose, that this poem"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1098, line : "was another offspring of Attic ingenuity; and generally that the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1099, line : "familiar mention of the cock (v. 191) is a strong argument against"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1100, line : "so ancient a date for its composition.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1103, line : "Having thus given a brief account of the poems comprised in Pope's design,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1104, line : "I will now proceed to make a few remarks on his translation, and on my own"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1105, line : "purpose in the present edition."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1107, line : "Pope was not a Grecian. His whole education had been irregular, and his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1108, line : "earliest acquaintance with the poet was through the version of Ogilby. It"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1109, line : "is not too much to say that his whole work bears the impress of a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1110, line : "disposition to be satisfied with the general sense, rather than to dive"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1111, line : "deeply into the minute and delicate features of language. Hence his whole"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1112, line : "work is to be looked upon rather as an elegant paraphrase than a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1113, line : "translation. There are, to be sure, certain conventional anecdotes, which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1114, line : "prove that Pope consulted various friends, whose classical attainments"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1115, line : "were sounder than his own, during the undertaking; but it is probable that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1116, line : "these examinations were the result rather of the contradictory versions"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1117, line : "already existing, than of a desire to make a perfect transcript of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1118, line : "original. And in those days, what is called literal translation was less"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1119, line : "cultivated than at present. If something like the general sense could be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1120, line : "decorated with the easy gracefulness of a practised poet; if the charms of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1121, line : "metrical cadence and a pleasing fluency could be made consistent with a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1122, line : "fair interpretation of the poet's meaning, his _words_ were less jealously"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1123, line : "sought for, and those who could read so good a poem as Pope's Iliad had"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1124, line : "fair reason to be satisfied."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1126, line : "It would be absurd, therefore, to test Pope's translation by our own"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1127, line : "advancing knowledge of the original text. We must be content to look at it"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1128, line : "as a most delightful work in itself,--a work which is as much a part of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1129, line : "English literature as Homer himself is of Greek. We must not be torn from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1130, line : "our kindly associations with the old Iliad, that once was our most"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1131, line : "cherished companion, or our most looked-for prize, merely because"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1132, line : "Buttmann, Loewe, and Liddell have made us so much more accurate as to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1133, line : "amphikupellon being an adjective, and not a substantive. Far be it from us"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1134, line : "to defend the faults of Pope, especially when we think of Chapman's fine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1135, line : "bold, rough old English;--far be it from, us to hold up his translation as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1136, line : "what a translation of Homer _might_ be. But we can still dismiss Pope's"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1137, line : "Iliad to the hands of our readers, with the consciousness that they must"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1138, line : "have read a very great number of books before they have read its fellow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1140, line : "As to the Notes accompanying the present volume, they are drawn up without"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1141, line : "pretension, and mainly with the view of helping the general reader. Having"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1142, line : "some little time since translated all the works of Homer for another"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1143, line : "publisher, I might have brought a large amount of accumulated matter,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1144, line : "sometimes of a critical character, to bear upon the text. But Pope's"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1145, line : "version was no field for such a display; and my purpose was to touch"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1146, line : "briefly on antiquarian or mythological allusions, to notice occasionally"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1147, line : "_some_ departures from the original, and to give a few parallel passages"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1148, line : "from our English Homer, Milton. In the latter task I cannot pretend to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1149, line : "novelty, but I trust that my other annotations, while utterly disclaiming"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1150, line : "high scholastic views, will be found to convey as much as is wanted; at"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1151, line : "least, as far as the necessary limits of these volumes could be expected"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1152, line : "to admit. To write a commentary on Homer is not my present aim; but if I"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1153, line : "have made Pope's translation a little more entertaining and instructive to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1154, line : "a mass of miscellaneous readers, I shall consider my wishes satisfactorily"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1155, line : "accomplished."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1157, line : "THEODORE ALOIS BUCKLEY."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1159, line : "_Christ Church._"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1165, line : "POPE'S PREFACE TO THE ILIAD OF HOMER"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1168, line : "Homer is universally allowed to have had the greatest invention of any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1169, line : "writer whatever. The praise of judgment Virgil has justly contested with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1170, line : "him, and others may have their pretensions as to particular excellences;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1171, line : "but his invention remains yet unrivalled. Nor is it a wonder if he has"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1172, line : "ever been acknowledged the greatest of poets, who most excelled in that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1173, line : "which is the very foundation of poetry. It is the invention that, in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1174, line : "different degrees, distinguishes all great geniuses: the utmost stretch of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1175, line : "human study, learning, and industry, which masters everything besides, can"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1176, line : "never attain to this. It furnishes art with all her materials, and without"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1177, line : "it judgment itself can at best but \"steal wisely:\" for art is only like a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1178, line : "prudent steward that lives on managing the riches of nature. Whatever"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1179, line : "praises may be given to works of judgment, there is not even a single"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1180, line : "beauty in them to which the invention must not contribute: as in the most"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1181, line : "regular gardens, art can only reduce beauties of nature to more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1182, line : "regularity, and such a figure, which the common eye may better take in,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1183, line : "and is, therefore, more entertained with. And, perhaps, the reason why"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1184, line : "common critics are inclined to prefer a judicious and methodical genius to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1185, line : "a great and fruitful one, is, because they find it easier for themselves"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1186, line : "to pursue their observations through a uniform and bounded walk of art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1187, line : "than to comprehend the vast and various extent of nature."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1189, line : "Our author's work is a wild paradise, where, if we cannot see all the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1190, line : "beauties so distinctly as in an ordered garden, it is only because the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1191, line : "number of them is infinitely greater. It is like a copious nursery, which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1192, line : "contains the seeds and first productions of every kind, out of which those"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1193, line : "who followed him have but selected some particular plants, each according"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1194, line : "to his fancy, to cultivate and beautify. If some things are too luxuriant"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1195, line : "it is owing to the richness of the soil; and if others are not arrived to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1196, line : "perfection or maturity, it is only because they are overrun and oppressed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1197, line : "by those of a stronger nature."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1199, line : "It is to the strength of this amazing invention we are to attribute that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1200, line : "unequalled fire and rapture which is so forcible in Homer, that no man of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1201, line : "a true poetical spirit is master of himself while he reads him. What he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1202, line : "writes is of the most animated nature imaginable; every thing moves, every"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1203, line : "thing lives, and is put in action. If a council be called, or a battle"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1204, line : "fought, you are not coldly informed of what was said or done as from a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1205, line : "third person; the reader is hurried out of himself by the force of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1206, line : "poet's imagination, and turns in one place to a hearer, in another to a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1207, line : "spectator. The course of his verses resembles that of the army he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1208, line : "describes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1210, line : "Hoid' ar' isan hosei te puri chthon pasa nemoito."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1212, line : "\"They pour along like a fire that sweeps the whole earth before it.\" It"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1213, line : "is, however, remarkable, that his fancy, which is everywhere vigorous, is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1214, line : "not discovered immediately at the beginning of his poem in its fullest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1215, line : "splendour: it grows in the progress both upon himself and others, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1216, line : "becomes on fire, like a chariot-wheel, by its own rapidity. Exact"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1217, line : "disposition, just thought, correct elocution, polished numbers, may have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1218, line : "been found in a thousand; but this poetic fire, this \"vivida vis animi,\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1219, line : "in a very few. Even in works where all those are imperfect or neglected,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1220, line : "this can overpower criticism, and make us admire even while we disapprove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1221, line : "Nay, where this appears, though attended with absurdities, it brightens"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1222, line : "all the rubbish about it, till we see nothing but its own splendour. This"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1223, line : "fire is discerned in Virgil, but discerned as through a glass, reflected"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1224, line : "from Homer, more shining than fierce, but everywhere equal and constant:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1225, line : "in Lucan and Statius it bursts out in sudden, short, and interrupted"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1226, line : "flashes: In Milton it glows like a furnace kept up to an uncommon ardour"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1227, line : "by the force of art: in Shakspeare it strikes before we are aware, like an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1228, line : "accidental fire from heaven: but in Homer, and in him only, it burns"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1229, line : "everywhere clearly and everywhere irresistibly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1231, line : "I shall here endeavour to show how this vast invention exerts itself in a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1232, line : "manner superior to that of any poet through all the main constituent parts"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1233, line : "of his work: as it is the great and peculiar characteristic which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1234, line : "distinguishes him from all other authors."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1236, line : "This strong and ruling faculty was like a powerful star, which, in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1237, line : "violence of its course, drew all things within its vortex. It seemed not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1238, line : "enough to have taken in the whole circle of arts, and the whole compass of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1239, line : "nature, to supply his maxims and reflections; all the inward passions and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1240, line : "affections of mankind, to furnish his characters: and all the outward"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1241, line : "forms and images of things for his descriptions: but wanting yet an ampler"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1242, line : "sphere to expatiate in, he opened a new and boundless walk for his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1243, line : "imagination, and created a world for himself in the invention of fable."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1244, line : "That which Aristotle calls \"the soul of poetry,\" was first breathed into"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1245, line : "it by Homer, I shall begin with considering him in his part, as it is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1246, line : "naturally the first; and I speak of it both as it means the design of a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1247, line : "poem, and as it is taken for fiction."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1249, line : "Fable may be divided into the probable, the allegorical, and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1250, line : "marvellous. The probable fable is the recital of such actions as, though"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1251, line : "they did not happen, yet might, in the common course of nature; or of such"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1252, line : "as, though they did, became fables by the additional episodes and manner"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1253, line : "of telling them. Of this sort is the main story of an epic poem, \"The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1254, line : "return of Ulysses, the settlement of the Trojans in Italy,\" or the like."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1255, line : "That of the Iliad is the \"anger of Achilles,\" the most short and single"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1256, line : "subject that ever was chosen by any poet. Yet this he has supplied with a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1257, line : "vaster variety of incidents and events, and crowded with a greater number"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1258, line : "of councils, speeches, battles, and episodes of all kinds, than are to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1259, line : "found even in those poems whose schemes are of the utmost latitude and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1260, line : "irregularity. The action is hurried on with the most vehement spirit, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1261, line : "its whole duration employs not so much as fifty days. Virgil, for want of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1262, line : "so warm a genius, aided himself by taking in a more extensive subject, as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1263, line : "well as a greater length of time, and contracting the design of both"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1264, line : "Homer's poems into one, which is yet but a fourth part as large as his."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1265, line : "The other epic poets have used the same practice, but generally carried it"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1266, line : "so far as to superinduce a multiplicity of fables, destroy the unity of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1267, line : "action, and lose their readers in an unreasonable length of time. Nor is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1268, line : "it only in the main design that they have been unable to add to his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1269, line : "invention, but they have followed him in every episode and part of story."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1270, line : "If he has given a regular catalogue of an army, they all draw up their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1271, line : "forces in the same order. If he has funeral games for Patroclus, Virgil"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1272, line : "has the same for Anchises, and Statius (rather than omit them) destroys"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1273, line : "the unity of his actions for those of Archemorus. If Ulysses visit the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1274, line : "shades, the Ćneas of Virgil and Scipio of Silius are sent after him. If he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1275, line : "be detained from his return by the allurements of Calypso, so is Ćneas by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1276, line : "Dido, and Rinaldo by Armida. If Achilles be absent from the army on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1277, line : "score of a quarrel through half the poem, Rinaldo must absent himself just"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1278, line : "as long on the like account. If he gives his hero a suit of celestial"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1279, line : "armour, Virgil and Tasso make the same present to theirs. Virgil has not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1280, line : "only observed this close imitation of Homer, but, where he had not led the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1281, line : "way, supplied the want from other Greek authors. Thus the story of Sinon,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1282, line : "and the taking of Troy, was copied (says Macrobius) almost word for word"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1283, line : "from Pisander, as the loves of Dido and Ćneas are taken from those of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1284, line : "Medea and Jason in Apollonius, and several others in the same manner."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1286, line : "To proceed to the allegorical fable--If we reflect upon those innumerable"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1287, line : "knowledges, those secrets of nature and physical philosophy which Homer is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1288, line : "generally supposed to have wrapped up in his allegories, what a new and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1289, line : "ample scene of wonder may this consideration afford us! How fertile will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1290, line : "that imagination appear, which as able to clothe all the properties of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1291, line : "elements, the qualifications of the mind, the virtues and vices, in forms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1292, line : "and persons, and to introduce them into actions agreeable to the nature of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1293, line : "the things they shadowed! This is a field in which no succeeding poets"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1294, line : "could dispute with Homer, and whatever commendations have been allowed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1295, line : "them on this head, are by no means for their invention in having enlarged"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1296, line : "his circle, but for their judgment in having contracted it. For when the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1297, line : "mode of learning changed in the following ages, and science was delivered"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1298, line : "in a plainer manner, it then became as reasonable in the more modern poets"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1299, line : "to lay it aside, as it was in Homer to make use of it. And perhaps it was"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1300, line : "no unhappy circumstance for Virgil, that there was not in his time that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1301, line : "demand upon him of so great an invention as might be capable of furnishing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1302, line : "all those allegorical parts of a poem."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1304, line : "The marvellous fable includes whatever is supernatural, and especially the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1305, line : "machines of the gods. If Homer was not the first who introduced the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1306, line : "deities (as Herodotus imagines) into the religion of Greece, he seems the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1307, line : "first who brought them into a system of machinery for poetry, and such a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1308, line : "one as makes its greatest importance and dignity: for we find those"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1309, line : "authors who have been offended at the literal notion of the gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1310, line : "constantly laying their accusation against Homer as the chief support of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1311, line : "it. But whatever cause there might be to blame his machines in a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1312, line : "philosophical or religious view, they are so perfect in the poetic, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1313, line : "mankind have been ever since contented to follow them: none have been able"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1314, line : "to enlarge the sphere of poetry beyond the limits he has set: every"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1315, line : "attempt of this nature has proved unsuccessful; and after all the various"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1316, line : "changes of times and religions, his gods continue to this day the gods of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1317, line : "poetry."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1319, line : "We come now to the characters of his persons; and here we shall find no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1320, line : "author has ever drawn so many, with so visible and surprising a variety,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1321, line : "or given us such lively and affecting impressions of them. Every one has"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1322, line : "something so singularly his own, that no painter could have distinguished"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1323, line : "them more by their features, than the poet has by their manners. Nothing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1324, line : "can be more exact than the distinctions he has observed in the different"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1325, line : "degrees of virtues and vices. The single quality of courage is wonderfully"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1326, line : "diversified in the several characters of the Iliad. That of Achilles is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1327, line : "furious and intractable; that of Diomede forward, yet listening to advice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1328, line : "and subject to command; that of Ajax is heavy and self-confiding; of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1329, line : "Hector, active and vigilant: the courage of Agamemnon is inspirited by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1330, line : "love of empire and ambition; that of Menelaus mixed with softness and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1331, line : "tenderness for his people: we find in Idomeneus a plain direct soldier; in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1332, line : "Sarpedon a gallant and generous one. Nor is this judicious and astonishing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1333, line : "diversity to be found only in the principal quality which constitutes the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1334, line : "main of each character, but even in the under parts of it, to which he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1335, line : "takes care to give a tincture of that principal one. For example: the main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1336, line : "characters of Ulysses and Nestor consist in wisdom; and they are distinct"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1337, line : "in this, that the wisdom of one is artificial and various, of the other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1338, line : "natural, open, and regular. But they have, besides, characters of courage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1339, line : "and this quality also takes a different turn in each from the difference"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1340, line : "of his prudence; for one in the war depends still upon caution, the other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1341, line : "upon experience. It would be endless to produce instances of these kinds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1342, line : "The characters of Virgil are far from striking us in this open manner;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1343, line : "they lie, in a great degree, hidden and undistinguished; and, where they"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1344, line : "are marked most evidently affect us not in proportion to those of Homer."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1345, line : "His characters of valour are much alike; even that of Turnus seems no way"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1346, line : "peculiar, but, as it is, in a superior degree; and we see nothing that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1347, line : "differences the courage of Mnestheus from that of Sergestus, Cloanthus, or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1348, line : "the rest, In like manner it may be remarked of Statius's heroes, that an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1349, line : "air of impetuosity runs through them all; the same horrid and savage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1350, line : "courage appears in his Capaneus, Tydeus, Hippomedon, &c. They have a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1351, line : "parity of character, which makes them seem brothers of one family. I"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1352, line : "believe when the reader is led into this tract of reflection, if he will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1353, line : "pursue it through the epic and tragic writers, he will be convinced how"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1354, line : "infinitely superior, in this point, the invention of Homer was to that of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1355, line : "all others."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1357, line : "The speeches are to be considered as they flow from the characters; being"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1358, line : "perfect or defective as they agree or disagree with the manners, of those"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1359, line : "who utter them. As there is more variety of characters in the Iliad, so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1360, line : "there is of speeches, than in any other poem. \"Everything in it has"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1361, line : "manner\" (as Aristotle expresses it), that is, everything is acted or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1362, line : "spoken. It is hardly credible, in a work of such length, how small a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1363, line : "number of lines are employed in narration. In Virgil the dramatic part is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1364, line : "less in proportion to the narrative, and the speeches often consist of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1365, line : "general reflections or thoughts, which might be equally just in any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1366, line : "person's mouth upon the same occasion. As many of his persons have no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1367, line : "apparent characters, so many of his speeches escape being applied and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1368, line : "judged by the rule of propriety. We oftener think of the author himself"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1369, line : "when we read Virgil, than when we are engaged in Homer, all which are the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1370, line : "effects of a colder invention, that interests us less in the action"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1371, line : "described. Homer makes us hearers, and Virgil leaves us readers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1373, line : "If, in the next place, we take a view of the sentiments, the same"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1374, line : "presiding faculty is eminent in the sublimity and spirit of his thoughts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1375, line : "Longinus has given his opinion, that it was in this part Homer principally"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1376, line : "excelled. What were alone sufficient to prove the grandeur and excellence"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1377, line : "of his sentiments in general, is, that they have so remarkable a parity"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1378, line : "with those of the Scripture. Duport, in his Gnomologia Homerica, has"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1379, line : "collected innumerable instances of this sort. And it is with justice an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1380, line : "excellent modern writer allows, that if Virgil has not so many thoughts"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1381, line : "that are low and vulgar, he has not so many that are sublime and noble;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1382, line : "and that the Roman author seldom rises into very astonishing sentiments"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1383, line : "where he is not fired by the Iliad."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1385, line : "If we observe his descriptions, images, and similes, we shall find the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1386, line : "invention still predominant. To what else can we ascribe that vast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1387, line : "comprehension of images of every sort, where we see each circumstance of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1388, line : "art, and individual of nature, summoned together by the extent and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1389, line : "fecundity of his imagination to which all things, in their various views"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1390, line : "presented themselves in an instant, and had their impressions taken off to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1391, line : "perfection at a heat? Nay, he not only gives us the full prospects of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1392, line : "things, but several unexpected peculiarities and side views, unobserved by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1393, line : "any painter but Homer. Nothing is so surprising as the descriptions of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1394, line : "battles, which take up no less than half the Iliad, and are supplied with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1395, line : "so vast a variety of incidents, that no one bears a likeness to another;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1396, line : "such different kinds of deaths, that no two heroes are wounded in the same"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1397, line : "manner, and such a profusion of noble ideas, that every battle rises above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1398, line : "the last in greatness, horror, and confusion. It is certain there is not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1399, line : "near that number of images and descriptions in any epic poet, though every"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1400, line : "one has assisted himself with a great quantity out of him; and it is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1401, line : "evident of Virgil especially, that he has scarce any comparisons which are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1402, line : "not drawn from his master."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1404, line : "If we descend from hence to the expression, we see the bright imagination"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1405, line : "of Homer shining out in the most enlivened forms of it. We acknowledge him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1406, line : "the father of poetical diction; the first who taught that \"language of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1407, line : "gods\" to men. His expression is like the colouring of some great masters,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1408, line : "which discovers itself to be laid on boldly, and executed with rapidity."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1409, line : "It is, indeed, the strongest and most glowing imaginable, and touched with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1410, line : "the greatest spirit. Aristotle had reason to say, he was the only poet who"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1411, line : "had found out \"living words;\" there are in him more daring figures and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1412, line : "metaphors than in any good author whatever. An arrow is \"impatient\" to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1413, line : "on the wing, a weapon \"thirsts\" to drink the blood of an enemy, and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1414, line : "like, yet his expression is never too big for the sense, but justly great"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1415, line : "in proportion to it. It is the sentiment that swells and fills out the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1416, line : "diction, which rises with it, and forms itself about it, for in the same"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1417, line : "degree that a thought is warmer, an expression will be brighter, as that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1418, line : "is more strong, this will become more perspicuous; like glass in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1419, line : "furnace, which grows to a greater magnitude, and refines to a greater"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1420, line : "clearness, only as the breath within is more powerful, and the heat more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1421, line : "intense."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1423, line : "To throw his language more out of prose, Homer seems to have affected the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1424, line : "compound epithets. This was a sort of composition peculiarly proper to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1425, line : "poetry, not only as it heightened the diction, but as it assisted and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1426, line : "filled the numbers with greater sound and pomp, and likewise conduced in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1427, line : "some measure to thicken the images. On this last consideration I cannot"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1428, line : "but attribute these also to the fruitfulness of his invention, since (as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1429, line : "he has managed them) they are a sort of supernumerary pictures of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1430, line : "persons or things to which they were joined. We see the motion of Hector's"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1431, line : "plumes in the epithet Korythaiolos, the landscape of Mount Neritus in that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1432, line : "of Einosiphyllos, and so of others, which particular images could not have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1433, line : "been insisted upon so long as to express them in a description (though but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1434, line : "of a single line) without diverting the reader too much from the principal"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1435, line : "action or figure. As a metaphor is a short simile, one of these epithets"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1436, line : "is a short description."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1438, line : "Lastly, if we consider his versification, we shall be sensible what a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1439, line : "share of praise is due to his invention in that also. He was not satisfied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1440, line : "with his language as he found it settled in any one part of Greece, but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1441, line : "searched through its different dialects with this particular view, to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1442, line : "beautify and perfect his numbers he considered these as they had a greater"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1443, line : "mixture of vowels or consonants, and accordingly employed them as the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1444, line : "verse required either a greater smoothness or strength. What he most"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1445, line : "affected was the Ionic, which has a peculiar sweetness, from its never"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1446, line : "using contractions, and from its custom of resolving the diphthongs into"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1447, line : "two syllables, so as to make the words open themselves with a more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1448, line : "spreading and sonorous fluency. With this he mingled the Attic"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1449, line : "contractions, the broader Doric, and the feebler Ćolic, which often"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1450, line : "rejects its aspirate, or takes off its accent, and completed this variety"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1451, line : "by altering some letters with the licence of poetry. Thus his measures,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1452, line : "instead of being fetters to his sense, were always in readiness to run"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1453, line : "along with the warmth of his rapture, and even to give a further"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1454, line : "representation of his notions, in the correspondence of their sounds to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1455, line : "what they signified. Out of all these he has derived that harmony which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1456, line : "makes us confess he had not only the richest head, but the finest ear in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1457, line : "the world. This is so great a truth, that whoever will but consult the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1458, line : "tune of his verses, even without understanding them (with the same sort of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1459, line : "diligence as we daily see practised in the case of Italian operas), will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1460, line : "find more sweetness, variety, and majesty of sound, than in any other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1461, line : "language of poetry. The beauty of his numbers is allowed by the critics to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1462, line : "be copied but faintly by Virgil himself, though they are so just as to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1463, line : "ascribe it to the nature of the Latin tongue: indeed the Greek has some"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1464, line : "advantages both from the natural sound of its words, and the turn and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1465, line : "cadence of its verse, which agree with the genius of no other language."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1466, line : "Virgil was very sensible of this, and used the utmost diligence in working"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1467, line : "up a more intractable language to whatsoever graces it was capable of,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1468, line : "and, in particular, never failed to bring the sound of his line to a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1469, line : "beautiful agreement with its sense. If the Grecian poet has not been so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1470, line : "frequently celebrated on this account as the Roman, the only reason is,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1471, line : "that fewer critics have understood one language than the other. Dionysius"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1472, line : "of Halicarnassus has pointed out many of our author's beauties in this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1473, line : "kind, in his treatise of the Composition of Words. It suffices at present"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1474, line : "to observe of his numbers, that they flow with so much ease, as to make"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1475, line : "one imagine Homer had no other care than to transcribe as fast as the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1476, line : "Muses dictated, and, at the same time, with so much force and inspiriting"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1477, line : "vigour, that they awaken and raise us like the sound of a trumpet. They"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1478, line : "roll along as a plentiful river, always in motion, and always full; while"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1479, line : "we are borne away by a tide of verse, the most rapid, and yet the most"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1480, line : "smooth imaginable."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1482, line : "Thus on whatever side we contemplate Homer, what principally strikes us is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1483, line : "his invention. It is that which forms the character of each part of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1484, line : "work; and accordingly we find it to have made his fable more extensive and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1485, line : "copious than any other, his manners more lively and strongly marked, his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1486, line : "speeches more affecting and transported, his sentiments more warm and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1487, line : "sublime, his images and descriptions more full and animated, his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1488, line : "expression more raised and daring, and his numbers more rapid and various."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1489, line : "I hope, in what has been said of Virgil, with regard to any of these"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1490, line : "heads, I have no way derogated from his character. Nothing is more absurd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1491, line : "or endless, than the common method of comparing eminent writers by an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1492, line : "opposition of particular passages in them, and forming a judgment from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1493, line : "thence of their merit upon the whole. We ought to have a certain knowledge"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1494, line : "of the principal character and distinguishing excellence of each: it is in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1495, line : "that we are to consider him, and in proportion to his degree in that we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1496, line : "are to admire him. No author or man ever excelled all the world in more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1497, line : "than one faculty; and as Homer has done this in invention, Virgil has in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1498, line : "judgment. Not that we are to think that Homer wanted judgment, because"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1499, line : "Virgil had it in a more eminent degree; or that Virgil wanted invention,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1500, line : "because Homer possessed a larger share of it; each of these great authors"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1501, line : "had more of both than perhaps any man besides, and are only said to have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1502, line : "less in comparison with one another. Homer was the greater genius, Virgil"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1503, line : "the better artist. In one we most admire the man, in the other the work."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1504, line : "Homer hurries and transports us with a commanding impetuosity; Virgil"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1505, line : "leads us with an attractive majesty; Homer scatters with a generous"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1506, line : "profusion; Virgil bestows with a careful magnificence; Homer, like the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1507, line : "Nile, pours out his riches with a boundless overflow; Virgil, like a river"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1508, line : "in its banks, with a gentle and constant stream. When we behold their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1509, line : "battles, methinks the two poets resemble the heroes they celebrate. Homer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1510, line : "boundless and resistless as Achilles, bears all before him, and shines"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1511, line : "more and more as the tumult increases; Virgil, calmly daring, like Ćneas,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1512, line : "appears undisturbed in the midst of the action; disposes all about him,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1513, line : "and conquers with tranquillity. And when we look upon their machines,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1514, line : "Homer seems like his own Jupiter in his terrors, shaking Olympus,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1515, line : "scattering the lightnings, and firing the heavens: Virgil, like the same"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1516, line : "power in his benevolence, counselling with the gods, laying plans for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1517, line : "empires, and regularly ordering his whole creation."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1519, line : "But after all, it is with great parts, as with great virtues, they"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1520, line : "naturally border on some imperfection; and it is often hard to distinguish"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1521, line : "exactly where the virtue ends, or the fault begins. As prudence may"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1522, line : "sometimes sink to suspicion, so may a great judgment decline to coldness;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1523, line : "and as magnanimity may run up to profusion or extravagance, so may a great"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1524, line : "invention to redundancy or wildness. If we look upon Homer in this view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1525, line : "we shall perceive the chief objections against him to proceed from so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1526, line : "noble a cause as the excess of this faculty."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1528, line : "Among these we may reckon some of his marvellous fictions, upon which so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1529, line : "much criticism has been spent, as surpassing all the bounds of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1530, line : "probability. Perhaps it may be with great and superior souls, as with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1531, line : "gigantic bodies, which, exerting themselves with unusual strength, exceed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1532, line : "what is commonly thought the due proportion of parts, to become miracles"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1533, line : "in the whole; and, like the old heroes of that make, commit something near"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1534, line : "extravagance, amidst a series of glorious and inimitable performances."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1535, line : "Thus Homer has his \"speaking horses;\" and Virgil his \"myrtles distilling"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1536, line : "blood;\" where the latter has not so much as contrived the easy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1537, line : "intervention of a deity to save the probability."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1539, line : "It is owing to the same vast invention, that his similes have been thought"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1540, line : "too exuberant and full of circumstances. The force of this faculty is seen"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1541, line : "in nothing more, than in its inability to confine itself to that single"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1542, line : "circumstance upon which the comparison is grounded: it runs out into"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1543, line : "embellishments of additional images, which, however, are so managed as not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1544, line : "to overpower the main one. His similes are like pictures, where the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1545, line : "principal figure has not only its proportion given agreeable to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1546, line : "original, but is also set off with occasional ornaments and prospects. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1547, line : "same will account for his manner of heaping a number of comparisons"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1548, line : "together in one breath, when his fancy suggested to him at once so many"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1549, line : "various and correspondent images. The reader will easily extend this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1550, line : "observation to more objections of the same kind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1552, line : "If there are others which seem rather to charge him with a defect or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1553, line : "narrowness of genius, than an excess of it, those seeming defects will be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1554, line : "found upon examination to proceed wholly from the nature of the times he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1555, line : "lived in. Such are his grosser representations of the gods; and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1556, line : "vicious and imperfect manners of his heroes; but I must here speak a word"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1557, line : "of the latter, as it is a point generally carried into extremes, both by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1558, line : "the censurers and defenders of Homer. It must be a strange partiality to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1559, line : "antiquity, to think with Madame Dacier,(38) \"that those times and manners"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1560, line : "are so much the more excellent, as they are more contrary to ours.\" Who"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1561, line : "can be so prejudiced in their favour as to magnify the felicity of those"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1562, line : "ages, when a spirit of revenge and cruelty, joined with the practice of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1563, line : "rapine and robbery, reigned through the world: when no mercy was shown but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1564, line : "for the sake of lucre; when the greatest princes were put to the sword,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1565, line : "and their wives and daughters made slaves and concubines? On the other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1566, line : "side, I would not be so delicate as those modern critics, who are shocked"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1567, line : "at the servile offices and mean employments in which we sometimes see the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1568, line : "heroes of Homer engaged. There is a pleasure in taking a view of that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1569, line : "simplicity, in opposition to the luxury of succeeding ages: in beholding"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1570, line : "monarchs without their guards; princes tending their flocks, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1571, line : "princesses drawing water from the springs. When we read Homer, we ought to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1572, line : "reflect that we are reading the most ancient author in the heathen world;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1573, line : "and those who consider him in this light, will double their pleasure in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1574, line : "the perusal of him. Let them think they are growing acquainted with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1575, line : "nations and people that are now no more; that they are stepping almost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1576, line : "three thousand years back into the remotest antiquity, and entertaining"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1577, line : "themselves with a clear and surprising vision of things nowhere else to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1578, line : "found, the only true mirror of that ancient world. By this means alone"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1579, line : "their greatest obstacles will vanish; and what usually creates their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1580, line : "dislike, will become a satisfaction."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1582, line : "This consideration may further serve to answer for the constant use of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1583, line : "same epithets to his gods and heroes; such as the \"far-darting Phoebus,\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1584, line : "the \"blue-eyed Pallas,\" the \"swift-footed Achilles,\" &c., which some have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1585, line : "censured as impertinent, and tediously repeated. Those of the gods"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1586, line : "depended upon the powers and offices then believed to belong to them; and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1587, line : "had contracted a weight and veneration from the rites and solemn devotions"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1588, line : "in which they were used: they were a sort of attributes with which it was"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1589, line : "a matter of religion to salute them on all occasions, and which it was an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1590, line : "irreverence to omit. As for the epithets of great men, Mons. Boileau is of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1591, line : "opinion, that they were in the nature of surnames, and repeated as such;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1592, line : "for the Greeks having no names derived from their fathers, were obliged to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1593, line : "add some other distinction of each person; either naming his parents"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1594, line : "expressly, or his place of birth, profession, or the like: as Alexander"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1595, line : "the son of Philip, Herodotus of Halicarnassus, Diogenes the Cynic, &c."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1596, line : "Homer, therefore, complying with the custom of his country, used such"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1597, line : "distinctive additions as better agreed with poetry. And, indeed, we have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1598, line : "something parallel to these in modern times, such as the names of Harold"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1599, line : "Harefoot, Edmund Ironside, Edward Longshanks, Edward the Black Prince, &c."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1600, line : "If yet this be thought to account better for the propriety than for the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1601, line : "repetition, I shall add a further conjecture. Hesiod, dividing the world"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1602, line : "into its different ages, has placed a fourth age, between the brazen and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1603, line : "the iron one, of \"heroes distinct from other men; a divine race who fought"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1604, line : "at Thebes and Troy, are called demi-gods, and live by the care of Jupiter"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1605, line : "in the islands of the blessed.\" Now among the divine honours which were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1606, line : "paid them, they might have this also in common with the gods, not to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1607, line : "mentioned without the solemnity of an epithet, and such as might be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1608, line : "acceptable to them by celebrating their families, actions or qualities."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1610, line : "What other cavils have been raised against Homer, are such as hardly"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1611, line : "deserve a reply, but will yet be taken notice of as they occur in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1612, line : "course of the work. Many have been occasioned by an injudicious endeavour"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1613, line : "to exalt Virgil; which is much the same, as if one should think to raise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1614, line : "the superstructure by undermining the foundation: one would imagine, by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1615, line : "the whole course of their parallels, that these critics never so much as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1616, line : "heard of Homer's having written first; a consideration which whoever"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1617, line : "compares these two poets ought to have always in his eye. Some accuse him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1618, line : "for the same things which they overlook or praise in the other; as when"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1619, line : "they prefer the fable and moral of the Ćneis to those of the Iliad, for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1620, line : "the same reasons which might set the Odyssey above the Ćneis; as that the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1621, line : "hero is a wiser man, and the action of the one more beneficial to his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1622, line : "country than that of the other; or else they blame him for not doing what"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1623, line : "he never designed; as because Achilles is not as good and perfect a prince"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1624, line : "as Ćneas, when the very moral of his poem required a contrary character:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1625, line : "it is thus that Rapin judges in his comparison of Homer and Virgil. Others"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1626, line : "select those particular passages of Homer which are not so laboured as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1627, line : "some that Virgil drew out of them: this is the whole management of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1628, line : "Scaliger in his Poetics. Others quarrel with what they take for low and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1629, line : "mean expressions, sometimes through a false delicacy and refinement,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1630, line : "oftener from an ignorance of the graces of the original, and then triumph"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1631, line : "in the awkwardness of their own translations: this is the conduct of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1632, line : "Perrault in his Parallels. Lastly, there are others, who, pretending to a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1633, line : "fairer proceeding, distinguish between the personal merit of Homer, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1634, line : "that of his work; but when they come to assign the causes of the great"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1635, line : "reputation of the Iliad, they found it upon the ignorance of his times,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1636, line : "and the prejudice of those that followed: and in pursuance of this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1637, line : "principle, they make those accidents (such as the contention of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1638, line : "cities, &c.) to be the causes of his fame, which were in reality the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1639, line : "consequences of his merit. The same might as well be said of Virgil, or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1640, line : "any great author whose general character will infallibly raise many casual"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1641, line : "additions to their reputation. This is the method of Mons. de la Mott; who"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1642, line : "yet confesses upon the whole that in whatever age Homer had lived, he must"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1643, line : "have been the greatest poet of his nation, and that he may be said in his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1644, line : "sense to be the master even of those who surpassed him.(39)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1646, line : "In all these objections we see nothing that contradicts his title to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1647, line : "honour of the chief invention: and as long as this (which is indeed the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1648, line : "characteristic of poetry itself) remains unequalled by his followers, he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1649, line : "still continues superior to them. A cooler judgment may commit fewer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1650, line : "faults, and be more approved in the eyes of one sort of critics: but that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1651, line : "warmth of fancy will carry the loudest and most universal applauses which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1652, line : "holds the heart of a reader under the strongest enchantment. Homer not"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1653, line : "only appears the inventor of poetry, but excels all the inventors of other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1654, line : "arts, in this, that he has swallowed up the honour of those who succeeded"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1655, line : "him. What he has done admitted no increase, it only left room for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1656, line : "contraction or regulation. He showed all the stretch of fancy at once; and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1657, line : "if he has failed in some of his flights, it was but because he attempted"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1658, line : "everything. A work of this kind seems like a mighty tree, which rises from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1659, line : "the most vigorous seed, is improved with industry, flourishes, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1660, line : "produces the finest fruit: nature and art conspire to raise it; pleasure"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1661, line : "and profit join to make it valuable: and they who find the justest faults,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1662, line : "have only said that a few branches which run luxuriant through a richness"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1663, line : "of nature, might be lopped into form to give it a more regular appearance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1665, line : "Having now spoken of the beauties and defects of the original, it remains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1666, line : "to treat of the translation, with the same view to the chief"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1667, line : "characteristic. As far as that is seen in the main parts of the poem, such"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1668, line : "as the fable, manners, and sentiments, no translator can prejudice it but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1669, line : "by wilful omissions or contractions. As it also breaks out in every"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1670, line : "particular image, description, and simile, whoever lessens or too much"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1671, line : "softens those, takes off from this chief character. It is the first grand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1672, line : "duty of an interpreter to give his author entire and unmaimed; and for the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1673, line : "rest, the diction and versification only are his proper province, since"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1674, line : "these must be his own, but the others he is to take as he finds them."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1676, line : "It should then be considered what methods may afford some equivalent in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1677, line : "our language for the graces of these in the Greek. It is certain no"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1678, line : "literal translation can be just to an excellent original in a superior"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1679, line : "language: but it is a great mistake to imagine (as many have done) that a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1680, line : "rash paraphrase can make amends for this general defect; which is no less"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1681, line : "in danger to lose the spirit of an ancient, by deviating into the modern"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1682, line : "manners of expression. If there be sometimes a darkness, there is often a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1683, line : "light in antiquity, which nothing better preserves than a version almost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1684, line : "literal. I know no liberties one ought to take, but those which are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1685, line : "necessary to transfusing the spirit of the original, and supporting the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1686, line : "poetical style of the translation: and I will venture to say, there have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1687, line : "not been more men misled in former times by a servile, dull adherence to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1688, line : "the letter, than have been deluded in ours by a chimerical, insolent hope"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1689, line : "of raising and improving their author. It is not to be doubted, that the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1690, line : "fire of the poem is what a translator should principally regard, as it is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1691, line : "most likely to expire in his managing: however, it is his safest way to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1692, line : "content with preserving this to his utmost in the whole, without"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1693, line : "endeavouring to be more than he finds his author is, in any particular"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1694, line : "place. It is a great secret in writing, to know when to be plain, and when"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1695, line : "poetical and figurative; and it is what Homer will teach us, if we will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1696, line : "but follow modestly in his footsteps. Where his diction is bold and lofty,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1697, line : "let us raise ours as high as we can; but where his is plain and humble, we"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1698, line : "ought not to be deterred from imitating him by the fear of incurring the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1699, line : "censure of a mere English critic. Nothing that belongs to Homer seems to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1700, line : "have been more commonly mistaken than the just pitch of his style: some of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1701, line : "his translators having swelled into fustian in a proud confidence of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1702, line : "sublime; others sunk into flatness, in a cold and timorous notion of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1703, line : "simplicity. Methinks I see these different followers of Homer, some"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1704, line : "sweating and straining after him by violent leaps and bounds (the certain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1705, line : "signs of false mettle), others slowly and servilely creeping in his train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1706, line : "while the poet himself is all the time proceeding with an unaffected and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1707, line : "equal majesty before them. However, of the two extremes one could sooner"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1708, line : "pardon frenzy than frigidity; no author is to be envied for such"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1709, line : "commendations, as he may gain by that character of style, which his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1710, line : "friends must agree together to call simplicity, and the rest of the world"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1711, line : "will call dulness. There is a graceful and dignified simplicity, as well"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1712, line : "as a bold and sordid one; which differ as much from each other as the air"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1713, line : "of a plain man from that of a sloven: it is one thing to be tricked up,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1714, line : "and another not to be dressed at all. Simplicity is the mean between"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1715, line : "ostentation and rusticity."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1717, line : "This pure and noble simplicity is nowhere in such perfection as in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1718, line : "Scripture and our author. One may affirm, with all respect to the inspired"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1719, line : "writings, that the Divine Spirit made use of no other words but what were"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1720, line : "intelligible and common to men at that time, and in that part of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1721, line : "world; and, as Homer is the author nearest to those, his style must of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1722, line : "course bear a greater resemblance to the sacred books than that of any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1723, line : "other writer. This consideration (together with what has been observed of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1724, line : "the parity of some of his thoughts) may, methinks, induce a translator, on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1725, line : "the one hand, to give in to several of those general phrases and manners"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1726, line : "of expression, which have attained a veneration even in our language from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1727, line : "being used in the Old Testament; as, on the other, to avoid those which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1728, line : "have been appropriated to the Divinity, and in a manner consigned to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1729, line : "mystery and religion."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1731, line : "For a further preservation of this air of simplicity, a particular care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1732, line : "should be taken to express with all plainness those moral sentences and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1733, line : "proverbial speeches which are so numerous in this poet. They have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1734, line : "something venerable, and as I may say, oracular, in that unadorned gravity"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1735, line : "and shortness with which they are delivered: a grace which would be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1736, line : "utterly lost by endeavouring to give them what we call a more ingenious"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1737, line : "(that is, a more modern) turn in the paraphrase."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1739, line : "Perhaps the mixture of some Graecisms and old words after the manner of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1740, line : "Milton, if done without too much affectation, might not have an ill effect"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1741, line : "in a version of this particular work, which most of any other seems to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1742, line : "require a venerable, antique cast. But certainly the use of modern terms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1743, line : "of war and government, such as \"platoon, campaign, junto,\" or the like,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1744, line : "(into which some of his translators have fallen) cannot be allowable;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1745, line : "those only excepted without which it is impossible to treat the subjects"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1746, line : "in any living language."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1748, line : "There are two peculiarities in Homer's diction, which are a sort of marks"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1749, line : "or moles by which every common eye distinguishes him at first sight; those"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1750, line : "who are not his greatest admirers look upon them as defects, and those who"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1751, line : "are, seemed pleased with them as beauties. I speak of his compound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1752, line : "epithets, and of his repetitions. Many of the former cannot be done"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1753, line : "literally into English without destroying the purity of our language. I"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1754, line : "believe such should be retained as slide easily of themselves into an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1755, line : "English compound, without violence to the ear or to the received rules of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1756, line : "composition, as well as those which have received a sanction from the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1757, line : "authority of our best poets, and are become familiar through their use of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1758, line : "them; such as \"the cloud-compelling Jove,\" &c. As for the rest, whenever"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1759, line : "any can be as fully and significantly expressed in a single word as in a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1760, line : "compounded one, the course to be taken is obvious."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1762, line : "Some that cannot be so turned, as to preserve their full image by one or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1763, line : "two words, may have justice done them by circumlocution; as the epithet"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1764, line : "einosiphyllos to a mountain, would appear little or ridiculous translated"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1765, line : "literally \"leaf-shaking,\" but affords a majestic idea in the periphrasis:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1766, line : "\"the lofty mountain shakes his waving woods.\" Others that admit of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1767, line : "different significations, may receive an advantage from a judicious"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1768, line : "variation, according to the occasions on which they are introduced. For"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1769, line : "example, the epithet of Apollo, hekaebolos or \"far-shooting,\" is capable"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1770, line : "of two explications; one literal, in respect of the darts and bow, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1771, line : "ensigns of that god; the other allegorical, with regard to the rays of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1772, line : "sun; therefore, in such places where Apollo is represented as a god in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1773, line : "person, I would use the former interpretation; and where the effects of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1774, line : "the sun are described, I would make choice of the latter. Upon the whole,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1775, line : "it will be necessary to avoid that perpetual repetition of the same"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1776, line : "epithets which we find in Homer, and which, though it might be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1777, line : "accommodated (as has been already shown) to the ear of those times, is by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1778, line : "no means so to ours: but one may wait for opportunities of placing them,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1779, line : "where they derive an additional beauty from the occasions on which they"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1780, line : "are employed; and in doing this properly, a translator may at once show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1781, line : "his fancy and his judgment."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1783, line : "As for Homer's repetitions, we may divide them into three sorts: of whole"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1784, line : "narrations and speeches, of single sentences, and of one verse or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1785, line : "hemistitch. I hope it is not impossible to have such a regard to these, as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1786, line : "neither to lose so known a mark of the author on the one hand, nor to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1787, line : "offend the reader too much on the other. The repetition is not ungraceful"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1788, line : "in those speeches, where the dignity of the speaker renders it a sort of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1789, line : "insolence to alter his words; as in the messages from gods to men, or from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1790, line : "higher powers to inferiors in concerns of state, or where the ceremonial"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1791, line : "of religion seems to require it, in the solemn forms of prayers, oaths, or"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1792, line : "the like. In other cases, I believe the best rule is, to be guided by the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1793, line : "nearness, or distance, at which the repetitions are placed in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1794, line : "original: when they follow too close, one may vary the expression; but it"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1795, line : "is a question, whether a professed translator be authorized to omit any:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1796, line : "if they be tedious, the author is to answer for it."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1798, line : "It only remains to speak of the versification. Homer (as has been said) is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1799, line : "perpetually applying the sound to the sense, and varying it on every new"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1800, line : "subject. This is indeed one of the most exquisite beauties of poetry, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1801, line : "attainable by very few: I only know of Homer eminent for it in the Greek,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1802, line : "and Virgil in the Latin. I am sensible it is what may sometimes happen by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1803, line : "chance, when a writer is warm, and fully possessed of his image: however,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1804, line : "it may reasonably be believed they designed this, in whose verse it so"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1805, line : "manifestly appears in a superior degree to all others. Few readers have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1806, line : "the ear to be judges of it: but those who have, will see I have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1807, line : "endeavoured at this beauty."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1809, line : "Upon the whole, I must confess myself utterly incapable of doing justice"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1810, line : "to Homer. I attempt him in no other hope but that which one may entertain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1811, line : "without much vanity, of giving a more tolerable copy of him than any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1812, line : "entire translation in verse has yet done. We have only those of Chapman,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1813, line : "Hobbes, and Ogilby. Chapman has taken the advantage of an immeasurable"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1814, line : "length of verse, notwithstanding which, there is scarce any paraphrase"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1815, line : "more loose and rambling than his. He has frequent interpolations of four"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1816, line : "or six lines; and I remember one in the thirteenth book of the Odyssey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1817, line : "ver. 312, where he has spun twenty verses out of two. He is often mistaken"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1818, line : "in so bold a manner, that one might think he deviated on purpose, if he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1819, line : "did not in other places of his notes insist so much upon verbal trifles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1820, line : "He appears to have had a strong affectation of extracting new meanings out"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1821, line : "of his author; insomuch as to promise, in his rhyming preface, a poem of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1822, line : "the mysteries he had revealed in Homer; and perhaps he endeavoured to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1823, line : "strain the obvious sense to this end. His expression is involved in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1824, line : "fustian; a fault for which he was remarkable in his original writings, as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1825, line : "in the tragedy of Bussy d'Amboise, &c. In a word, the nature of the man"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1826, line : "may account for his whole performance; for he appears, from his preface"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1827, line : "and remarks, to have been of an arrogant turn, and an enthusiast in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1828, line : "poetry. His own boast, of having finished half the Iliad in less than"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1829, line : "fifteen weeks, shows with what negligence his version was performed. But"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1830, line : "that which is to be allowed him, and which very much contributed to cover"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1831, line : "his defects, is a daring fiery spirit that animates his translation, which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1832, line : "is something like what one might imagine Homer himself would have writ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1833, line : "before he arrived at years of discretion."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1835, line : "Hobbes has given us a correct explanation of the sense in general; but for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1836, line : "particulars and circumstances he continually lops them, and often omits"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1837, line : "the most beautiful. As for its being esteemed a close translation, I doubt"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1838, line : "not many have been led into that error by the shortness of it, which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1839, line : "proceeds not from his following the original line by line, but from the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1840, line : "contractions above mentioned. He sometimes omits whole similes and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1841, line : "sentences; and is now and then guilty of mistakes, into which no writer of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1842, line : "his learning could have fallen, but through carelessness. His poetry, as"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1843, line : "well as Ogilby's, is too mean for criticism."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1845, line : "It is a great loss to the poetical world that Mr. Dryden did not live to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1846, line : "translate the Iliad. He has left us only the first book, and a small part"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1847, line : "of the sixth; in which if he has in some places not truly interpreted the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1848, line : "sense, or preserved the antiquities, it ought to be excused on account of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1849, line : "the haste he was obliged to write in. He seems to have had too much regard"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1850, line : "to Chapman, whose words he sometimes copies, and has unhappily followed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1851, line : "him in passages where he wanders from the original. However, had he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1852, line : "translated the whole work, I would no more have attempted Homer after him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1853, line : "than Virgil: his version of whom (notwithstanding some human errors) is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1854, line : "the most noble and spirited translation I know in any language. But the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1855, line : "fate of great geniuses is like that of great ministers: though they are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1856, line : "confessedly the first in the commonwealth of letters, they must be envied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1857, line : "and calumniated only for being at the head of it."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1859, line : "That which, in my opinion, ought to be the endeavour of any one who"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1860, line : "translates Homer, is above all things to keep alive that spirit and fire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1861, line : "which makes his chief character: in particular places, where the sense can"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1862, line : "bear any doubt, to follow the strongest and most poetical, as most"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1863, line : "agreeing with that character; to copy him in all the variations of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1864, line : "style, and the different modulations of his numbers; to preserve, in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1865, line : "more active or descriptive parts, a warmth and elevation; in the more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1866, line : "sedate or narrative, a plainness and solemnity; in the speeches, a fulness"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1867, line : "and perspicuity; in the sentences, a shortness and gravity; not to neglect"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1868, line : "even the little figures and turns on the words, nor sometimes the very"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1869, line : "cast of the periods; neither to omit nor confound any rites or customs of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1870, line : "antiquity: perhaps too he ought to include the whole in a shorter compass"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1871, line : "than has hitherto been done by any translator who has tolerably preserved"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1872, line : "either the sense or poetry. What I would further recommend to him is, to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1873, line : "study his author rather from his own text, than from any commentaries, how"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1874, line : "learned soever, or whatever figure they may make in the estimation of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1875, line : "world; to consider him attentively in comparison with Virgil above all the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1876, line : "ancients, and with Milton above all the moderns. Next these, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1877, line : "Archbishop of Cambray's Telemachus may give him the truest idea of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1878, line : "spirit and turn of our author; and Bossu's admirable Treatise of the Epic"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1879, line : "Poem the justest notion of his design and conduct. But after all, with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1880, line : "whatever judgment and study a man may proceed, or with whatever happiness"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1881, line : "he may perform such a work, he must hope to please but a few; those only"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1882, line : "who have at once a taste of poetry, and competent learning. For to satisfy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1883, line : "such a want either, is not in the nature of this undertaking; since a mere"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1884, line : "modern wit can like nothing that is not modern, and a pedant nothing that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1885, line : "is not Greek."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1887, line : "What I have done is submitted to the public; from whose opinions I am"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1888, line : "prepared to learn; though I fear no judges so little as our best poets,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1889, line : "who are most sensible of the weight of this task. As for the worst,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1890, line : "whatever they shall please to say, they may give me some concern as they"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1891, line : "are unhappy men, but none as they are malignant writers. I was guided in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1892, line : "this translation by judgments very different from theirs, and by persons"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1893, line : "for whom they can have no kindness, if an old observation be true, that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1894, line : "the strongest antipathy in the world is that of fools to men of wit. Mr."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1895, line : "Addison was the first whose advice determined me to undertake this task;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1896, line : "who was pleased to write to me upon that occasion in such terms as I"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1897, line : "cannot repeat without vanity. I was obliged to Sir Richard Steele for a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1898, line : "very early recommendation of my undertaking to the public. Dr. Swift"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1899, line : "promoted my interest with that warmth with which he always serves his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1900, line : "friend. The humanity and frankness of Sir Samuel Garth are what I never"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1901, line : "knew wanting on any occasion. I must also acknowledge, with infinite"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1902, line : "pleasure, the many friendly offices, as well as sincere criticisms, of Mr."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1903, line : "Congreve, who had led me the way in translating some parts of Homer. I"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1904, line : "must add the names of Mr. Rowe, and Dr. Parnell, though I shall take a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1905, line : "further opportunity of doing justice to the last, whose good nature (to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1906, line : "give it a great panegyric), is no less extensive than his learning. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1907, line : "favour of these gentlemen is not entirely undeserved by one who bears them"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1908, line : "so true an affection. But what can I say of the honour so many of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1909, line : "great have done me; while the first names of the age appear as my"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1910, line : "subscribers, and the most distinguished patrons and ornaments of learning"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1911, line : "as my chief encouragers? Among these it is a particular pleasure to me to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1912, line : "find, that my highest obligations are to such who have done most honour to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1913, line : "the name of poet: that his grace the Duke of Buckingham was not displeased"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1914, line : "I should undertake the author to whom he has given (in his excellent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1915, line : "Essay), so complete a praise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1917, line : "\"Read Homer once, and you can read no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1918, line : "For all books else appear so mean, so poor,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1919, line : "Verse will seem prose: but still persist to read,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1920, line : "And Homer will be all the books you need.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1922, line : "That the Earl of Halifax was one of the first to favour me; of whom it is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1923, line : "hard to say whether the advancement of the polite arts is more owing to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1924, line : "his generosity or his example: that such a genius as my Lord Bolingbroke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1925, line : "not more distinguished in the great scenes of business, than in all the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1926, line : "useful and entertaining parts of learning, has not refused to be the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1927, line : "critic of these sheets, and the patron of their writer: and that the noble"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1928, line : "author of the tragedy of \"Heroic Love\" has continued his partiality to me,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1929, line : "from my writing pastorals to my attempting the Iliad. I cannot deny myself"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1930, line : "the pride of confessing, that I have had the advantage not only of their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1931, line : "advice for the conduct in general, but their correction of several"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1932, line : "particulars of this translation."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1934, line : "I could say a great deal of the pleasure of being distinguished by the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1935, line : "Earl of Carnarvon; but it is almost absurd to particularize any one"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1936, line : "generous action in a person whose whole life is a continued series of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1937, line : "them. Mr. Stanhope, the present secretary of state, will pardon my desire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1938, line : "of having it known that he was pleased to promote this affair. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1939, line : "particular zeal of Mr. Harcourt (the son of the late Lord Chancellor) gave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1940, line : "me a proof how much I am honoured in a share of his friendship. I must"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1941, line : "attribute to the same motive that of several others of my friends: to whom"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1942, line : "all acknowledgments are rendered unnecessary by the privileges of a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1943, line : "familiar correspondence; and I am satisfied I can no way better oblige men"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1944, line : "of their turn than by my silence."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1946, line : "In short, I have found more patrons than ever Homer wanted. He would have"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1947, line : "thought himself happy to have met the same favour at Athens that has been"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1948, line : "shown me by its learned rival, the University of Oxford. And I can hardly"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1949, line : "envy him those pompous honours he received after death, when I reflect on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1950, line : "the enjoyment of so many agreeable obligations, and easy friendships,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1951, line : "which make the satisfaction of life. This distinction is the more to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1952, line : "acknowledged, as it is shown to one whose pen has never gratified the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1953, line : "prejudices of particular parties, or the vanities of particular men."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1954, line : "Whatever the success may prove, I shall never repent of an undertaking in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1955, line : "which I have experienced the candour and friendship of so many persons of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1956, line : "merit; and in which I hope to pass some of those years of youth that are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1957, line : "generally lost in a circle of follies, after a manner neither wholly"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1958, line : "unuseful to others, nor disagreeable to myself."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1965, line : "THE ILIAD."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1971, line : "BOOK I."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1974, line : "ARGUMENT.(40)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1976, line : "THE CONTENTION OF ACHILLES AND AGAMEMNON."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1978, line : "In the war of Troy, the Greeks having sacked some of the neighbouring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1979, line : "towns, and taken from thence two beautiful captives, Chryseis and Briseis,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1980, line : "allotted the first to Agamemnon, and the last to Achilles. Chryses, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1981, line : "father of Chryseis, and priest of Apollo, comes to the Grecian camp to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1982, line : "ransom her; with which the action of the poem opens, in the tenth year of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1983, line : "the siege. The priest being refused, and insolently dismissed by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1984, line : "Agamemnon, entreats for vengeance from his god; who inflicts a pestilence"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1985, line : "on the Greeks. Achilles calls a council, and encourages Chalcas to declare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1986, line : "the cause of it; who attributes it to the refusal of Chryseis. The king,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1987, line : "being obliged to send back his captive, enters into a furious contest with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1988, line : "Achilles, which Nestor pacifies; however, as he had the absolute command"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1989, line : "of the army, he seizes on Briseis in revenge. Achilles in discontent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1990, line : "withdraws himself and his forces from the rest of the Greeks; and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1991, line : "complaining to Thetis, she supplicates Jupiter to render them sensible of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1992, line : "the wrong done to her son, by giving victory to the Trojans. Jupiter,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1993, line : "granting her suit, incenses Juno: between whom the debate runs high, till"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1994, line : "they are reconciled by the address of Vulcan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1996, line : "The time of two-and-twenty days is taken up in this book: nine during the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1997, line : "plague, one in the council and quarrel of the princes, and twelve for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1998, line : "Jupiter's stay with the Ćthiopians, at whose return Thetis prefers her"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 1999, line : "petition. The scene lies in the Grecian camp, then changes to Chrysa, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2000, line : "lastly to Olympus."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2002, line : "Achilles' wrath, to Greece the direful spring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2003, line : "Of woes unnumber'd, heavenly goddess, sing!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2004, line : "That wrath which hurl'd to Pluto's gloomy reign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2005, line : "The souls of mighty chiefs untimely slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2006, line : "Whose limbs unburied on the naked shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2007, line : "Devouring dogs and hungry vultures tore.(41)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2008, line : "Since great Achilles and Atrides strove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2009, line : "Such was the sovereign doom, and such the will of Jove!(42)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2011, line : "Declare, O Muse! in what ill-fated hour(43)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2012, line : "Sprung the fierce strife, from what offended power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2013, line : "Latona's son a dire contagion spread,(44)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2014, line : "And heap'd the camp with mountains of the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2015, line : "The king of men his reverent priest defied,(45)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2016, line : "And for the king's offence the people died."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2018, line : "For Chryses sought with costly gifts to gain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2019, line : "His captive daughter from the victor's chain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2020, line : "Suppliant the venerable father stands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2021, line : "Apollo's awful ensigns grace his hands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2022, line : "By these he begs; and lowly bending down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2023, line : "Extends the sceptre and the laurel crown"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2024, line : "He sued to all, but chief implored for grace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2025, line : "The brother-kings, of Atreus' royal race(46)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2027, line : "\"Ye kings and warriors! may your vows be crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2028, line : "And Troy's proud walls lie level with the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2029, line : "May Jove restore you when your toils are o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2030, line : "Safe to the pleasures of your native shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2031, line : "But, oh! relieve a wretched parent's pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2032, line : "And give Chryseis to these arms again;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2033, line : "If mercy fail, yet let my presents move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2034, line : "And dread avenging Phoebus, son of Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2036, line : "The Greeks in shouts their joint assent declare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2037, line : "The priest to reverence, and release the fair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2038, line : "Not so Atrides; he, with kingly pride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2039, line : "Repulsed the sacred sire, and thus replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2041, line : "\"Hence on thy life, and fly these hostile plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2042, line : "Nor ask, presumptuous, what the king detains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2043, line : "Hence, with thy laurel crown, and golden rod,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2044, line : "Nor trust too far those ensigns of thy god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2045, line : "Mine is thy daughter, priest, and shall remain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2046, line : "And prayers, and tears, and bribes, shall plead in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2047, line : "Till time shall rifle every youthful grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2048, line : "And age dismiss her from my cold embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2049, line : "In daily labours of the loom employ'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2050, line : "Or doom'd to deck the bed she once enjoy'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2051, line : "Hence then; to Argos shall the maid retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2052, line : "Far from her native soil and weeping sire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2054, line : "[Illustration: HOMER INVOKING THE MUSE.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2056, line : "HOMER INVOKING THE MUSE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2059, line : "The trembling priest along the shore return'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2060, line : "And in the anguish of a father mourn'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2061, line : "Disconsolate, not daring to complain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2062, line : "Silent he wander'd by the sounding main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2063, line : "Till, safe at distance, to his god he prays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2064, line : "The god who darts around the world his rays."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2066, line : "\"O Smintheus! sprung from fair Latona's line,(47)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2067, line : "Thou guardian power of Cilla the divine,(48)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2068, line : "Thou source of light! whom Tenedos adores,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2069, line : "And whose bright presence gilds thy Chrysa's shores."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2070, line : "If e'er with wreaths I hung thy sacred fane,(49)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2071, line : "Or fed the flames with fat of oxen slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2072, line : "God of the silver bow! thy shafts employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2073, line : "Avenge thy servant, and the Greeks destroy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2075, line : "Thus Chryses pray'd.--the favouring power attends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2076, line : "And from Olympus' lofty tops descends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2077, line : "Bent was his bow, the Grecian hearts to wound;(50)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2078, line : "Fierce as he moved, his silver shafts resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2079, line : "Breathing revenge, a sudden night he spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2080, line : "And gloomy darkness roll'd about his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2081, line : "The fleet in view, he twang'd his deadly bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2082, line : "And hissing fly the feather'd fates below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2083, line : "On mules and dogs the infection first began;(51)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2084, line : "And last, the vengeful arrows fix'd in man."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2085, line : "For nine long nights, through all the dusky air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2086, line : "The pyres, thick-flaming, shot a dismal glare."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2087, line : "But ere the tenth revolving day was run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2088, line : "Inspired by Juno, Thetis' godlike son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2089, line : "Convened to council all the Grecian train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2090, line : "For much the goddess mourn'd her heroes slain.(52)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2091, line : "The assembly seated, rising o'er the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2092, line : "Achilles thus the king of men address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2094, line : "\"Why leave we not the fatal Trojan shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2095, line : "And measure back the seas we cross'd before?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2096, line : "The plague destroying whom the sword would spare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2097, line : "'Tis time to save the few remains of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2098, line : "But let some prophet, or some sacred sage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2099, line : "Explore the cause of great Apollo's rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2100, line : "Or learn the wasteful vengeance to remove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2101, line : "By mystic dreams, for dreams descend from Jove.(53)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2102, line : "If broken vows this heavy curse have laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2103, line : "Let altars smoke, and hecatombs be paid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2104, line : "So Heaven, atoned, shall dying Greece restore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2105, line : "And Phoebus dart his burning shafts no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2107, line : "He said, and sat: when Chalcas thus replied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2108, line : "Chalcas the wise, the Grecian priest and guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2109, line : "That sacred seer, whose comprehensive view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2110, line : "The past, the present, and the future knew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2111, line : "Uprising slow, the venerable sage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2112, line : "Thus spoke the prudence and the fears of age:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2114, line : "\"Beloved of Jove, Achilles! would'st thou know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2115, line : "Why angry Phoebus bends his fatal bow?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2116, line : "First give thy faith, and plight a prince's word"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2117, line : "Of sure protection, by thy power and sword:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2118, line : "For I must speak what wisdom would conceal,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2119, line : "And truths, invidious to the great, reveal,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2120, line : "Bold is the task, when subjects, grown too wise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2121, line : "Instruct a monarch where his error lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2122, line : "For though we deem the short-lived fury past,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2123, line : "'Tis sure the mighty will revenge at last.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2124, line : "To whom Pelides:--\"From thy inmost soul"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2125, line : "Speak what thou know'st, and speak without control."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2126, line : "E'en by that god I swear who rules the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2127, line : "To whom thy hands the vows of Greece convey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2128, line : "And whose bless'd oracles thy lips declare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2129, line : "Long as Achilles breathes this vital air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2130, line : "No daring Greek, of all the numerous band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2131, line : "Against his priest shall lift an impious hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2132, line : "Not e'en the chief by whom our hosts are led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2133, line : "The king of kings, shall touch that sacred head.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2135, line : "Encouraged thus, the blameless man replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2136, line : "\"Nor vows unpaid, nor slighted sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2137, line : "But he, our chief, provoked the raging pest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2138, line : "Apollo's vengeance for his injured priest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2139, line : "Nor will the god's awaken'd fury cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2140, line : "But plagues shall spread, and funeral fires increase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2141, line : "Till the great king, without a ransom paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2142, line : "To her own Chrysa send the black-eyed maid.(54)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2143, line : "Perhaps, with added sacrifice and prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2144, line : "The priest may pardon, and the god may spare.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2146, line : "The prophet spoke: when with a gloomy frown"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2147, line : "The monarch started from his shining throne;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2148, line : "Black choler fill'd his breast that boil'd with ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2149, line : "And from his eye-balls flash'd the living fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2150, line : "\"Augur accursed! denouncing mischief still,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2151, line : "Prophet of plagues, for ever boding ill!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2152, line : "Still must that tongue some wounding message bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2153, line : "And still thy priestly pride provoke thy king?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2154, line : "For this are Phoebus' oracles explored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2155, line : "To teach the Greeks to murmur at their lord?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2156, line : "For this with falsehood is my honour stain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2157, line : "Is heaven offended, and a priest profaned;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2158, line : "Because my prize, my beauteous maid, I hold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2159, line : "And heavenly charms prefer to proffer'd gold?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2160, line : "A maid, unmatch'd in manners as in face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2161, line : "Skill'd in each art, and crown'd with every grace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2162, line : "Not half so dear were Clytaemnestra's charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2163, line : "When first her blooming beauties bless'd my arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2164, line : "Yet, if the gods demand her, let her sail;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2165, line : "Our cares are only for the public weal:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2166, line : "Let me be deem'd the hateful cause of all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2167, line : "And suffer, rather than my people fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2168, line : "The prize, the beauteous prize, I will resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2169, line : "So dearly valued, and so justly mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2170, line : "But since for common good I yield the fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2171, line : "My private loss let grateful Greece repair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2172, line : "Nor unrewarded let your prince complain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2173, line : "That he alone has fought and bled in vain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2174, line : "\"Insatiate king (Achilles thus replies),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2175, line : "Fond of the power, but fonder of the prize!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2176, line : "Would'st thou the Greeks their lawful prey should yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2177, line : "The due reward of many a well-fought field?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2179, line : "The spoils of cities razed and warriors slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2180, line : "We share with justice, as with toil we gain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2181, line : "But to resume whate'er thy avarice craves"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2182, line : "(That trick of tyrants) may be borne by slaves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2183, line : "Yet if our chief for plunder only fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2184, line : "The spoils of Ilion shall thy loss requite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2185, line : "Whene'er, by Jove's decree, our conquering powers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2186, line : "Shall humble to the dust her lofty towers.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2188, line : "Then thus the king: \"Shall I my prize resign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2189, line : "With tame content, and thou possess'd of thine?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2190, line : "Great as thou art, and like a god in fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2191, line : "Think not to rob me of a soldier's right."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2192, line : "At thy demand shall I restore the maid?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2193, line : "First let the just equivalent be paid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2194, line : "Such as a king might ask; and let it be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2195, line : "A treasure worthy her, and worthy me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2196, line : "Or grant me this, or with a monarch's claim"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2197, line : "This hand shall seize some other captive dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2198, line : "The mighty Ajax shall his prize resign;(55)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2199, line : "Ulysses' spoils, or even thy own, be mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2200, line : "The man who suffers, loudly may complain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2201, line : "And rage he may, but he shall rage in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2202, line : "But this when time requires.--It now remains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2203, line : "We launch a bark to plough the watery plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2204, line : "And waft the sacrifice to Chrysa's shores,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2205, line : "With chosen pilots, and with labouring oars."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2206, line : "Soon shall the fair the sable ship ascend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2207, line : "And some deputed prince the charge attend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2208, line : "This Creta's king, or Ajax shall fulfil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2209, line : "Or wise Ulysses see perform'd our will;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2210, line : "Or, if our royal pleasure shall ordain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2211, line : "Achilles' self conduct her o'er the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2212, line : "Let fierce Achilles, dreadful in his rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2213, line : "The god propitiate, and the pest assuage.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2215, line : "[Illustration: MARS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2217, line : "MARS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2220, line : "At this, Pelides, frowning stern, replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2221, line : "\"O tyrant, arm'd with insolence and pride!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2222, line : "Inglorious slave to interest, ever join'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2223, line : "With fraud, unworthy of a royal mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2224, line : "What generous Greek, obedient to thy word,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2225, line : "Shall form an ambush, or shall lift the sword?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2226, line : "What cause have I to war at thy decree?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2227, line : "The distant Trojans never injured me;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2228, line : "To Phthia's realms no hostile troops they led:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2229, line : "Safe in her vales my warlike coursers fed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2230, line : "Far hence removed, the hoarse-resounding main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2231, line : "And walls of rocks, secure my native reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2232, line : "Whose fruitful soil luxuriant harvests grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2233, line : "Rich in her fruits, and in her martial race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2234, line : "Hither we sail'd, a voluntary throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2235, line : "To avenge a private, not a public wrong:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2236, line : "What else to Troy the assembled nations draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2237, line : "But thine, ungrateful, and thy brother's cause?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2238, line : "Is this the pay our blood and toils deserve;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2239, line : "Disgraced and injured by the man we serve?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2240, line : "And darest thou threat to snatch my prize away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2241, line : "Due to the deeds of many a dreadful day?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2242, line : "A prize as small, O tyrant! match'd with thine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2243, line : "As thy own actions if compared to mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2244, line : "Thine in each conquest is the wealthy prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2245, line : "Though mine the sweat and danger of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2246, line : "Some trivial present to my ships I bear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2247, line : "Or barren praises pay the wounds of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2248, line : "But know, proud monarch, I'm thy slave no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2249, line : "My fleet shall waft me to Thessalia's shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2250, line : "Left by Achilles on the Trojan plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2251, line : "What spoils, what conquests, shall Atrides gain?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2253, line : "To this the king: \"Fly, mighty warrior! fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2254, line : "Thy aid we need not, and thy threats defy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2255, line : "There want not chiefs in such a cause to fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2256, line : "And Jove himself shall guard a monarch's right."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2257, line : "Of all the kings (the god's distinguish'd care)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2258, line : "To power superior none such hatred bear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2259, line : "Strife and debate thy restless soul employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2260, line : "And wars and horrors are thy savage joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2261, line : "If thou hast strength, 'twas Heaven that strength bestow'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2262, line : "For know, vain man! thy valour is from God."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2263, line : "Haste, launch thy vessels, fly with speed away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2264, line : "Rule thy own realms with arbitrary sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2265, line : "I heed thee not, but prize at equal rate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2266, line : "Thy short-lived friendship, and thy groundless hate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2267, line : "Go, threat thy earth-born Myrmidons:--but here(56)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2268, line : "'Tis mine to threaten, prince, and thine to fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2269, line : "Know, if the god the beauteous dame demand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2270, line : "My bark shall waft her to her native land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2271, line : "But then prepare, imperious prince! prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2272, line : "Fierce as thou art, to yield thy captive fair:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2273, line : "Even in thy tent I'll seize the blooming prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2274, line : "Thy loved Briseis with the radiant eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2275, line : "Hence shalt thou prove my might, and curse the hour"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2276, line : "Thou stood'st a rival of imperial power;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2277, line : "And hence, to all our hosts it shall be known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2278, line : "That kings are subject to the gods alone.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2280, line : "Achilles heard, with grief and rage oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2281, line : "His heart swell'd high, and labour'd in his breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2282, line : "Distracting thoughts by turns his bosom ruled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2283, line : "Now fired by wrath, and now by reason cool'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2284, line : "That prompts his hand to draw the deadly sword,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2285, line : "Force through the Greeks, and pierce their haughty lord;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2286, line : "This whispers soft his vengeance to control,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2287, line : "And calm the rising tempest of his soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2288, line : "Just as in anguish of suspense he stay'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2289, line : "While half unsheathed appear'd the glittering blade,(57)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2290, line : "Minerva swift descended from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2291, line : "Sent by the sister and the wife of Jove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2292, line : "(For both the princes claim'd her equal care);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2293, line : "Behind she stood, and by the golden hair"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2294, line : "Achilles seized; to him alone confess'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2295, line : "A sable cloud conceal'd her from the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2296, line : "He sees, and sudden to the goddess cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2297, line : "Known by the flames that sparkle from her eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2299, line : "[Illustration: MINERVA REPRESSING THE FURY OF ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2301, line : "MINERVA REPRESSING THE FURY OF ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2304, line : "\"Descends Minerva, in her guardian care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2305, line : "A heavenly witness of the wrongs I bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2306, line : "From Atreus' son?--Then let those eyes that view"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2307, line : "The daring crime, behold the vengeance too.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2309, line : "\"Forbear (the progeny of Jove replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2310, line : "To calm thy fury I forsake the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2311, line : "Let great Achilles, to the gods resign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2312, line : "To reason yield the empire o'er his mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2313, line : "By awful Juno this command is given;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2314, line : "The king and you are both the care of heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2315, line : "The force of keen reproaches let him feel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2316, line : "But sheathe, obedient, thy revenging steel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2317, line : "For I pronounce (and trust a heavenly power)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2318, line : "Thy injured honour has its fated hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2319, line : "When the proud monarch shall thy arms implores"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2320, line : "And bribe thy friendship with a boundless store."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2321, line : "Then let revenge no longer bear the sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2322, line : "Command thy passions, and the gods obey.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2324, line : "To her Pelides:--\"With regardful ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2325, line : "'Tis just, O goddess! I thy dictates hear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2326, line : "Hard as it is, my vengeance I suppress:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2327, line : "Those who revere the gods the gods will bless.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2328, line : "He said, observant of the blue-eyed maid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2329, line : "Then in the sheath return'd the shining blade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2330, line : "The goddess swift to high Olympus flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2331, line : "And joins the sacred senate of the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2333, line : "Nor yet the rage his boiling breast forsook,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2334, line : "Which thus redoubling on Atrides broke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2335, line : "\"O monster! mix'd of insolence and fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2336, line : "Thou dog in forehead, but in heart a deer!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2337, line : "When wert thou known in ambush'd fights to dare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2338, line : "Or nobly face the horrid front of war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2339, line : "'Tis ours, the chance of fighting fields to try;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2340, line : "Thine to look on, and bid the valiant die:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2341, line : "So much 'tis safer through the camp to go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2342, line : "And rob a subject, than despoil a foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2343, line : "Scourge of thy people, violent and base!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2344, line : "Sent in Jove's anger on a slavish race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2345, line : "Who, lost to sense of generous freedom past,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2346, line : "Are tamed to wrongs;--or this had been thy last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2347, line : "Now by this sacred sceptre hear me swear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2348, line : "Which never more shall leaves or blossoms bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2349, line : "Which sever'd from the trunk (as I from thee)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2350, line : "On the bare mountains left its parent tree;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2351, line : "This sceptre, form'd by temper'd steel to prove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2352, line : "An ensign of the delegates of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2353, line : "From whom the power of laws and justice springs"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2354, line : "(Tremendous oath! inviolate to kings);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2355, line : "By this I swear:--when bleeding Greece again"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2356, line : "Shall call Achilles, she shall call in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2357, line : "When, flush'd with slaughter, Hector comes to spread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2358, line : "The purpled shore with mountains of the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2359, line : "Then shall thou mourn the affront thy madness gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2360, line : "Forced to deplore when impotent to save:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2361, line : "Then rage in bitterness of soul to know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2362, line : "This act has made the bravest Greek thy foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2364, line : "He spoke; and furious hurl'd against the ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2365, line : "His sceptre starr'd with golden studs around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2366, line : "Then sternly silent sat. With like disdain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2367, line : "The raging king return'd his frowns again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2369, line : "To calm their passion with the words of age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2370, line : "Slow from his seat arose the Pylian sage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2371, line : "Experienced Nestor, in persuasion skill'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2372, line : "Words, sweet as honey, from his lips distill'd:(58)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2373, line : "Two generations now had pass'd away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2374, line : "Wise by his rules, and happy by his sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2375, line : "Two ages o'er his native realm he reign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2376, line : "And now the example of the third remain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2377, line : "All view'd with awe the venerable man;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2378, line : "Who thus with mild benevolence began:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2380, line : "\"What shame, what woe is this to Greece! what joy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2381, line : "To Troy's proud monarch, and the friends of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2382, line : "That adverse gods commit to stern debate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2383, line : "The best, the bravest, of the Grecian state."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2384, line : "Young as ye are, this youthful heat restrain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2385, line : "Nor think your Nestor's years and wisdom vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2386, line : "A godlike race of heroes once I knew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2387, line : "Such as no more these aged eyes shall view!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2388, line : "Lives there a chief to match Pirithous' fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2389, line : "Dryas the bold, or Ceneus' deathless name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2390, line : "Theseus, endued with more than mortal might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2391, line : "Or Polyphemus, like the gods in fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2392, line : "With these of old, to toils of battle bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2393, line : "In early youth my hardy days I led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2394, line : "Fired with the thirst which virtuous envy breeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2395, line : "And smit with love of honourable deeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2396, line : "Strongest of men, they pierced the mountain boar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2397, line : "Ranged the wild deserts red with monsters' gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2398, line : "And from their hills the shaggy Centaurs tore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2399, line : "Yet these with soft persuasive arts I sway'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2400, line : "When Nestor spoke, they listen'd and obey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2401, line : "If in my youth, even these esteem'd me wise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2402, line : "Do you, young warriors, hear my age advise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2403, line : "Atrides, seize not on the beauteous slave;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2404, line : "That prize the Greeks by common suffrage gave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2405, line : "Nor thou, Achilles, treat our prince with pride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2406, line : "Let kings be just, and sovereign power preside."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2407, line : "Thee, the first honours of the war adorn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2408, line : "Like gods in strength, and of a goddess born;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2409, line : "Him, awful majesty exalts above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2410, line : "The powers of earth, and sceptred sons of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2411, line : "Let both unite with well-consenting mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2412, line : "So shall authority with strength be join'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2413, line : "Leave me, O king! to calm Achilles' rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2414, line : "Rule thou thyself, as more advanced in age."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2415, line : "Forbid it, gods! Achilles should be lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2416, line : "The pride of Greece, and bulwark of our host.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2418, line : "This said, he ceased. The king of men replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2419, line : "\"Thy years are awful, and thy words are wise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2420, line : "But that imperious, that unconquer'd soul,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2421, line : "No laws can limit, no respect control."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2422, line : "Before his pride must his superiors fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2423, line : "His word the law, and he the lord of all?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2424, line : "Him must our hosts, our chiefs, ourself obey?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2425, line : "What king can bear a rival in his sway?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2426, line : "Grant that the gods his matchless force have given;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2427, line : "Has foul reproach a privilege from heaven?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2429, line : "Here on the monarch's speech Achilles broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2430, line : "And furious, thus, and interrupting spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2431, line : "\"Tyrant, I well deserved thy galling chain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2432, line : "To live thy slave, and still to serve in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2433, line : "Should I submit to each unjust decree:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2434, line : "Command thy vassals, but command not me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2435, line : "Seize on Briseis, whom the Grecians doom'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2436, line : "My prize of war, yet tamely see resumed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2437, line : "And seize secure; no more Achilles draws"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2438, line : "His conquering sword in any woman's cause."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2439, line : "The gods command me to forgive the past:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2440, line : "But let this first invasion be the last:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2441, line : "For know, thy blood, when next thou darest invade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2442, line : "Shall stream in vengeance on my reeking blade.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2444, line : "At this they ceased: the stern debate expired:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2445, line : "The chiefs in sullen majesty retired."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2447, line : "Achilles with Patroclus took his way"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2448, line : "Where near his tents his hollow vessels lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2449, line : "Meantime Atrides launch'd with numerous oars"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2450, line : "A well-rigg'd ship for Chrysa's sacred shores:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2451, line : "High on the deck was fair Chryseis placed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2452, line : "And sage Ulysses with the conduct graced:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2453, line : "Safe in her sides the hecatomb they stow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2454, line : "Then swiftly sailing, cut the liquid road."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2456, line : "The host to expiate next the king prepares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2457, line : "With pure lustrations, and with solemn prayers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2458, line : "Wash'd by the briny wave, the pious train(59)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2459, line : "Are cleansed; and cast the ablutions in the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2460, line : "Along the shore whole hecatombs were laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2461, line : "And bulls and goats to Phoebus' altars paid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2462, line : "The sable fumes in curling spires arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2463, line : "And waft their grateful odours to the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2465, line : "The army thus in sacred rites engaged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2466, line : "Atrides still with deep resentment raged."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2467, line : "To wait his will two sacred heralds stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2468, line : "Talthybius and Eurybates the good."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2469, line : "\"Haste to the fierce Achilles' tent (he cries),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2470, line : "Thence bear Briseis as our royal prize:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2471, line : "Submit he must; or if they will not part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2472, line : "Ourself in arms shall tear her from his heart.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2474, line : "The unwilling heralds act their lord's commands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2475, line : "Pensive they walk along the barren sands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2476, line : "Arrived, the hero in his tent they find,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2477, line : "With gloomy aspect on his arm reclined."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2478, line : "At awful distance long they silent stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2479, line : "Loth to advance, and speak their hard command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2480, line : "Decent confusion! This the godlike man"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2481, line : "Perceived, and thus with accent mild began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2483, line : "\"With leave and honour enter our abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2484, line : "Ye sacred ministers of men and gods!(60)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2485, line : "I know your message; by constraint you came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2486, line : "Not you, but your imperious lord I blame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2487, line : "Patroclus, haste, the fair Briseis bring;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2488, line : "Conduct my captive to the haughty king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2489, line : "But witness, heralds, and proclaim my vow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2490, line : "Witness to gods above, and men below!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2491, line : "But first, and loudest, to your prince declare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2492, line : "(That lawless tyrant whose commands you bear),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2493, line : "Unmoved as death Achilles shall remain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2494, line : "Though prostrate Greece shall bleed at every vein:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2495, line : "The raging chief in frantic passion lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2496, line : "Blind to himself, and useless to his host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2497, line : "Unskill'd to judge the future by the past,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2498, line : "In blood and slaughter shall repent at last.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2500, line : "[Illustration: THE DEPARTURE OF BRISEIS FROM THE TENT OF ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2502, line : "THE DEPARTURE OF BRISEIS FROM THE TENT OF ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2505, line : "Patroclus now the unwilling beauty brought;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2506, line : "She, in soft sorrows, and in pensive thought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2507, line : "Pass'd silent, as the heralds held her hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2508, line : "And of look'd back, slow-moving o'er the strand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2509, line : "Not so his loss the fierce Achilles bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2510, line : "But sad, retiring to the sounding shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2511, line : "O'er the wild margin of the deep he hung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2512, line : "That kindred deep from whence his mother sprung:(61)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2513, line : "There bathed in tears of anger and disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2514, line : "Thus loud lamented to the stormy main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2516, line : "\"O parent goddess! since in early bloom"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2517, line : "Thy son must fall, by too severe a doom;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2518, line : "Sure to so short a race of glory born,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2519, line : "Great Jove in justice should this span adorn:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2520, line : "Honour and fame at least the thunderer owed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2521, line : "And ill he pays the promise of a god,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2522, line : "If yon proud monarch thus thy son defies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2523, line : "Obscures my glories, and resumes my prize.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2525, line : "Far from the deep recesses of the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2526, line : "Where aged Ocean holds his watery reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2527, line : "The goddess-mother heard. The waves divide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2528, line : "And like a mist she rose above the tide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2529, line : "Beheld him mourning on the naked shores,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2530, line : "And thus the sorrows of his soul explores."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2531, line : "\"Why grieves my son? Thy anguish let me share;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2532, line : "Reveal the cause, and trust a parent's care.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2534, line : "He deeply sighing said: \"To tell my woe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2535, line : "Is but to mention what too well you know."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2536, line : "From Thebe, sacred to Apollo's name(62)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2537, line : "(Aetion's realm), our conquering army came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2538, line : "With treasure loaded and triumphant spoils,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2539, line : "Whose just division crown'd the soldier's toils;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2540, line : "But bright Chryseis, heavenly prize! was led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2541, line : "By vote selected, to the general's bed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2542, line : "The priest of Phoebus sought by gifts to gain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2543, line : "His beauteous daughter from the victor's chain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2544, line : "The fleet he reach'd, and, lowly bending down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2545, line : "Held forth the sceptre and the laurel crown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2546, line : "Intreating all; but chief implored for grace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2547, line : "The brother-kings of Atreus' royal race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2548, line : "The generous Greeks their joint consent declare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2549, line : "The priest to reverence, and release the fair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2550, line : "Not so Atrides: he, with wonted pride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2551, line : "The sire insulted, and his gifts denied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2552, line : "The insulted sire (his god's peculiar care)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2553, line : "To Phoebus pray'd, and Phoebus heard the prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2554, line : "A dreadful plague ensues: the avenging darts"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2555, line : "Incessant fly, and pierce the Grecian hearts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2556, line : "A prophet then, inspired by heaven, arose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2557, line : "And points the crime, and thence derives the woes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2558, line : "Myself the first the assembled chiefs incline"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2559, line : "To avert the vengeance of the power divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2560, line : "Then rising in his wrath, the monarch storm'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2561, line : "Incensed he threaten'd, and his threats perform'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2562, line : "The fair Chryseis to her sire was sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2563, line : "With offer'd gifts to make the god relent;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2564, line : "But now he seized Briseis' heavenly charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2565, line : "And of my valour's prize defrauds my arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2566, line : "Defrauds the votes of all the Grecian train;(63)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2567, line : "And service, faith, and justice, plead in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2568, line : "But, goddess! thou thy suppliant son attend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2569, line : "To high Olympus' shining court ascend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2570, line : "Urge all the ties to former service owed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2571, line : "And sue for vengeance to the thundering god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2572, line : "Oft hast thou triumph'd in the glorious boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2573, line : "That thou stood'st forth of all the ethereal host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2574, line : "When bold rebellion shook the realms above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2575, line : "The undaunted guard of cloud-compelling Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2576, line : "When the bright partner of his awful reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2577, line : "The warlike maid, and monarch of the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2578, line : "The traitor-gods, by mad ambition driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2579, line : "Durst threat with chains the omnipotence of Heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2580, line : "Then, call'd by thee, the monster Titan came"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2581, line : "(Whom gods Briareus, men Ćgeon name),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2582, line : "Through wondering skies enormous stalk'd along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2583, line : "Not he that shakes the solid earth so strong:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2584, line : "With giant-pride at Jove's high throne he stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2585, line : "And brandish'd round him all his hundred hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2586, line : "The affrighted gods confess'd their awful lord,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2587, line : "They dropp'd the fetters, trembled, and adored.(64)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2588, line : "This, goddess, this to his remembrance call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2589, line : "Embrace his knees, at his tribunal fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2590, line : "Conjure him far to drive the Grecian train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2591, line : "To hurl them headlong to their fleet and main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2592, line : "To heap the shores with copious death, and bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2593, line : "The Greeks to know the curse of such a king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2594, line : "Let Agamemnon lift his haughty head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2595, line : "O'er all his wide dominion of the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2596, line : "And mourn in blood that e'er he durst disgrace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2597, line : "The boldest warrior of the Grecian race.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2599, line : "[Illustration: THETIS CALLING BRIAREUS TO THE ASSISTANCE OF JUPITER.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2601, line : "THETIS CALLING BRIAREUS TO THE ASSISTANCE OF JUPITER."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2604, line : "\"Unhappy son! (fair Thetis thus replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2605, line : "While tears celestial trickle from her eyes)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2606, line : "Why have I borne thee with a mother's throes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2607, line : "To Fates averse, and nursed for future woes?(65)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2608, line : "So short a space the light of heaven to view!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2609, line : "So short a space! and fill'd with sorrow too!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2610, line : "O might a parent's careful wish prevail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2611, line : "Far, far from Ilion should thy vessels sail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2612, line : "And thou, from camps remote, the danger shun"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2613, line : "Which now, alas! too nearly threats my son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2614, line : "Yet (what I can) to move thy suit I'll go"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2615, line : "To great Olympus crown'd with fleecy snow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2616, line : "Meantime, secure within thy ships, from far"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2617, line : "Behold the field, not mingle in the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2618, line : "The sire of gods and all the ethereal train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2619, line : "On the warm limits of the farthest main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2620, line : "Now mix with mortals, nor disdain to grace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2621, line : "The feasts of Ćthiopia's blameless race,(66)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2622, line : "Twelve days the powers indulge the genial rite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2623, line : "Returning with the twelfth revolving light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2624, line : "Then will I mount the brazen dome, and move"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2625, line : "The high tribunal of immortal Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2627, line : "The goddess spoke: the rolling waves unclose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2628, line : "Then down the steep she plunged from whence she rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2629, line : "And left him sorrowing on the lonely coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2630, line : "In wild resentment for the fair he lost."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2632, line : "In Chrysa's port now sage Ulysses rode;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2633, line : "Beneath the deck the destined victims stow'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2634, line : "The sails they furl'd, they lash the mast aside,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2635, line : "And dropp'd their anchors, and the pinnace tied."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2636, line : "Next on the shore their hecatomb they land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2637, line : "Chryseis last descending on the strand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2638, line : "Her, thus returning from the furrow'd main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2639, line : "Ulysses led to Phoebus' sacred fane;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2640, line : "Where at his solemn altar, as the maid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2641, line : "He gave to Chryses, thus the hero said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2643, line : "\"Hail, reverend priest! to Phoebus' awful dome"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2644, line : "A suppliant I from great Atrides come:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2645, line : "Unransom'd, here receive the spotless fair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2646, line : "Accept the hecatomb the Greeks prepare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2647, line : "And may thy god who scatters darts around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2648, line : "Atoned by sacrifice, desist to wound.\"(67)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2650, line : "At this, the sire embraced the maid again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2651, line : "So sadly lost, so lately sought in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2652, line : "Then near the altar of the darting king,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2653, line : "Disposed in rank their hecatomb they bring;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2654, line : "With water purify their hands, and take"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2655, line : "The sacred offering of the salted cake;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2656, line : "While thus with arms devoutly raised in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2657, line : "And solemn voice, the priest directs his prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2659, line : "\"God of the silver bow, thy ear incline,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2660, line : "Whose power incircles Cilla the divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2661, line : "Whose sacred eye thy Tenedos surveys,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2662, line : "And gilds fair Chrysa with distinguish'd rays!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2663, line : "If, fired to vengeance at thy priest's request,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2664, line : "Thy direful darts inflict the raging pest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2665, line : "Once more attend! avert the wasteful woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2666, line : "And smile propitious, and unbend thy bow.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2668, line : "So Chryses pray'd. Apollo heard his prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2669, line : "And now the Greeks their hecatomb prepare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2670, line : "Between their horns the salted barley threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2671, line : "And, with their heads to heaven, the victims slew:(68)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2672, line : "The limbs they sever from the inclosing hide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2673, line : "The thighs, selected to the gods, divide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2674, line : "On these, in double cauls involved with art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2675, line : "The choicest morsels lay from every part."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2676, line : "The priest himself before his altar stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2677, line : "And burns the offering with his holy hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2678, line : "Pours the black wine, and sees the flames aspire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2679, line : "The youth with instruments surround the fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2680, line : "The thighs thus sacrificed, and entrails dress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2681, line : "The assistants part, transfix, and roast the rest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2682, line : "Then spread the tables, the repast prepare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2683, line : "Each takes his seat, and each receives his share."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2684, line : "When now the rage of hunger was repress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2685, line : "With pure libations they conclude the feast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2686, line : "The youths with wine the copious goblets crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2687, line : "And, pleased, dispense the flowing bowls around;(69)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2688, line : "With hymns divine the joyous banquet ends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2689, line : "The paeans lengthen'd till the sun descends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2690, line : "The Greeks, restored, the grateful notes prolong;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2691, line : "Apollo listens, and approves the song."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2693, line : "'Twas night; the chiefs beside their vessel lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2694, line : "Till rosy morn had purpled o'er the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2695, line : "Then launch, and hoist the mast: indulgent gales,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2696, line : "Supplied by Phoebus, fill the swelling sails;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2697, line : "The milk-white canvas bellying as they blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2698, line : "The parted ocean foams and roars below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2699, line : "Above the bounding billows swift they flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2700, line : "Till now the Grecian camp appear'd in view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2701, line : "Far on the beach they haul their bark to land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2702, line : "(The crooked keel divides the yellow sand,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2703, line : "Then part, where stretch'd along the winding bay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2704, line : "The ships and tents in mingled prospect lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2706, line : "But raging still, amidst his navy sat"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2707, line : "The stern Achilles, stedfast in his hate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2708, line : "Nor mix'd in combat, nor in council join'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2709, line : "But wasting cares lay heavy on his mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2710, line : "In his black thoughts revenge and slaughter roll,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2711, line : "And scenes of blood rise dreadful in his soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2713, line : "Twelve days were past, and now the dawning light"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2714, line : "The gods had summon'd to the Olympian height:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2715, line : "Jove, first ascending from the watery bowers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2716, line : "Leads the long order of ethereal powers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2717, line : "When, like the morning-mist in early day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2718, line : "Rose from the flood the daughter of the sea:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2719, line : "And to the seats divine her flight address'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2720, line : "There, far apart, and high above the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2721, line : "The thunderer sat; where old Olympus shrouds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2722, line : "His hundred heads in heaven, and props the clouds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2723, line : "Suppliant the goddess stood: one hand she placed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2724, line : "Beneath his beard, and one his knees embraced."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2725, line : "\"If e'er, O father of the gods! (she said)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2726, line : "My words could please thee, or my actions aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2727, line : "Some marks of honour on my son bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2728, line : "And pay in glory what in life you owe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2729, line : "Fame is at least by heavenly promise due"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2730, line : "To life so short, and now dishonour'd too."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2731, line : "Avenge this wrong, O ever just and wise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2732, line : "Let Greece be humbled, and the Trojans rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2733, line : "Till the proud king and all the Achaian race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2734, line : "Shall heap with honours him they now disgrace.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2736, line : "[Illustration: THETIS ENTREATING JUPITER TO HONOUR ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2738, line : "THETIS ENTREATING JUPITER TO HONOUR ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2741, line : "Thus Thetis spoke; but Jove in silence held"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2742, line : "The sacred counsels of his breast conceal'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2743, line : "Not so repulsed, the goddess closer press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2744, line : "Still grasp'd his knees, and urged the dear request."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2745, line : "\"O sire of gods and men! thy suppliant hear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2746, line : "Refuse, or grant; for what has Jove to fear?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2747, line : "Or oh! declare, of all the powers above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2748, line : "Is wretched Thetis least the care of Jove?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2750, line : "She said; and, sighing, thus the god replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2751, line : "Who rolls the thunder o'er the vaulted skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2753, line : "\"What hast thou ask'd? ah, why should Jove engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2754, line : "In foreign contests and domestic rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2755, line : "The gods' complaints, and Juno's fierce alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2756, line : "While I, too partial, aid the Trojan arms?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2757, line : "Go, lest the haughty partner of my sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2758, line : "With jealous eyes thy close access survey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2759, line : "But part in peace, secure thy prayer is sped:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2760, line : "Witness the sacred honours of our head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2761, line : "The nod that ratifies the will divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2762, line : "The faithful, fix'd, irrevocable sign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2763, line : "This seals thy suit, and this fulfils thy vows--\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2764, line : "He spoke, and awful bends his sable brows,(70)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2765, line : "Shakes his ambrosial curls, and gives the nod,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2766, line : "The stamp of fate and sanction of the god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2767, line : "High heaven with trembling the dread signal took,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2768, line : "And all Olympus to the centre shook.(71)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2770, line : "Swift to the seas profound the goddess flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2771, line : "Jove to his starry mansions in the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2772, line : "The shining synod of the immortals wait"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2773, line : "The coming god, and from their thrones of state"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2774, line : "Arising silent, wrapp'd in holy fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2775, line : "Before the majesty of heaven appear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2776, line : "Trembling they stand, while Jove assumes the throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2777, line : "All, but the god's imperious queen alone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2778, line : "Late had she view'd the silver-footed dame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2779, line : "And all her passions kindled into flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2780, line : "\"Say, artful manager of heaven (she cries),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2781, line : "Who now partakes the secrets of the skies?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2782, line : "Thy Juno knows not the decrees of fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2783, line : "In vain the partner of imperial state."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2784, line : "What favourite goddess then those cares divides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2785, line : "Which Jove in prudence from his consort hides?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2787, line : "To this the thunderer: \"Seek not thou to find"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2788, line : "The sacred counsels of almighty mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2789, line : "Involved in darkness likes the great decree,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2790, line : "Nor can the depths of fate be pierced by thee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2791, line : "What fits thy knowledge, thou the first shalt know;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2792, line : "The first of gods above, and men below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2793, line : "But thou, nor they, shall search the thoughts that roll"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2794, line : "Deep in the close recesses of my soul.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2796, line : "Full on the sire the goddess of the skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2797, line : "Roll'd the large orbs of her majestic eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2798, line : "And thus return'd:--\"Austere Saturnius, say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2799, line : "From whence this wrath, or who controls thy sway?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2800, line : "Thy boundless will, for me, remains in force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2801, line : "And all thy counsels take the destined course."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2802, line : "But 'tis for Greece I fear: for late was seen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2803, line : "In close consult, the silver-footed queen."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2804, line : "Jove to his Thetis nothing could deny,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2805, line : "Nor was the signal vain that shook the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2806, line : "What fatal favour has the goddess won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2807, line : "To grace her fierce, inexorable son?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2808, line : "Perhaps in Grecian blood to drench the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2809, line : "And glut his vengeance with my people slain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2811, line : "Then thus the god: \"O restless fate of pride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2812, line : "That strives to learn what heaven resolves to hide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2813, line : "Vain is the search, presumptuous and abhorr'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2814, line : "Anxious to thee, and odious to thy lord."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2815, line : "Let this suffice: the immutable decree"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2816, line : "No force can shake: what is, that ought to be."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2817, line : "Goddess, submit; nor dare our will withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2818, line : "But dread the power of this avenging hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2819, line : "The united strength of all the gods above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2820, line : "In vain resists the omnipotence of Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2822, line : "[Illustration: VULCAN.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2824, line : "VULCAN."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2827, line : "The thunderer spoke, nor durst the queen reply;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2828, line : "A reverent horror silenced all the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2829, line : "The feast disturb'd, with sorrow Vulcan saw"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2830, line : "His mother menaced, and the gods in awe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2831, line : "Peace at his heart, and pleasure his design,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2832, line : "Thus interposed the architect divine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2833, line : "\"The wretched quarrels of the mortal state"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2834, line : "Are far unworthy, gods! of your debate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2835, line : "Let men their days in senseless strife employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2836, line : "We, in eternal peace and constant joy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2837, line : "Thou, goddess-mother, with our sire comply,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2838, line : "Nor break the sacred union of the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2839, line : "Lest, roused to rage, he shake the bless'd abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2840, line : "Launch the red lightning, and dethrone the gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2841, line : "If you submit, the thunderer stands appeased;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2842, line : "The gracious power is willing to be pleased.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2844, line : "Thus Vulcan spoke: and rising with a bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2845, line : "The double bowl with sparkling nectar crown'd,(72)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2846, line : "Which held to Juno in a cheerful way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2847, line : "\"Goddess (he cried), be patient and obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2848, line : "Dear as you are, if Jove his arm extend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2849, line : "I can but grieve, unable to defend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2850, line : "What god so daring in your aid to move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2851, line : "Or lift his hand against the force of Jove?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2852, line : "Once in your cause I felt his matchless might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2853, line : "Hurl'd headlong down from the ethereal height;(73)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2854, line : "Toss'd all the day in rapid circles round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2855, line : "Nor till the sun descended touch'd the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2856, line : "Breathless I fell, in giddy motion lost;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2857, line : "The Sinthians raised me on the Lemnian coast;(74)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2859, line : "He said, and to her hands the goblet heaved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2860, line : "Which, with a smile, the white-arm'd queen received"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2861, line : "Then, to the rest he fill'd; and in his turn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2862, line : "Each to his lips applied the nectar'd urn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2863, line : "Vulcan with awkward grace his office plies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2864, line : "And unextinguish'd laughter shakes the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2866, line : "Thus the blest gods the genial day prolong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2867, line : "In feasts ambrosial, and celestial song.(75)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2868, line : "Apollo tuned the lyre; the Muses round"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2869, line : "With voice alternate aid the silver sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2870, line : "Meantime the radiant sun to mortal sight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2871, line : "Descending swift, roll'd down the rapid light:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2872, line : "Then to their starry domes the gods depart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2873, line : "The shining monuments of Vulcan's art:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2874, line : "Jove on his couch reclined his awful head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2875, line : "And Juno slumber'd on the golden bed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2877, line : "[Illustration: JUPITER.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2879, line : "JUPITER."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2882, line : "[Illustration: THE APOTHEOSIS OF HOMER.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2884, line : "THE APOTHEOSIS OF HOMER."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2890, line : "BOOK II."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2893, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2895, line : "THE TRIAL OF THE ARMY, AND CATALOGUE OF THE FORCES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2897, line : "Jupiter, in pursuance of the request of Thetis, sends a deceitful vision"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2898, line : "to Agamemnon, persuading him to lead the army to battle, in order to make"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2899, line : "the Greeks sensible of their want of Achilles. The general, who is deluded"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2900, line : "with the hopes of taking Troy without his assistance, but fears the army"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2901, line : "was discouraged by his absence, and the late plague, as well as by the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2902, line : "length of time, contrives to make trial of their disposition by a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2903, line : "stratagem. He first communicates his design to the princes in council,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2904, line : "that he would propose a return to the soldiers, and that they should put a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2905, line : "stop to them if the proposal was embraced. Then he assembles the whole"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2906, line : "host, and upon moving for a return to Greece, they unanimously agree to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2907, line : "it, and run to prepare the ships. They are detained by the management of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2908, line : "Ulysses, who chastises the insolence of Thersites. The assembly is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2909, line : "recalled, several speeches made on the occasion, and at length the advice"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2910, line : "of Nestor followed, which was to make a general muster of the troops, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2911, line : "to divide them into their several nations, before they proceeded to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2912, line : "battle. This gives occasion to the poet to enumerate all the forces of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2913, line : "Greeks and Trojans, and in a large catalogue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2915, line : "The time employed in this book consists not entirely of one day. The scene"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2916, line : "lies in the Grecian camp, and upon the sea-shore; towards the end it"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2917, line : "removes to Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2919, line : "Now pleasing sleep had seal'd each mortal eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2920, line : "Stretch'd in the tents the Grecian leaders lie:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2921, line : "The immortals slumber'd on their thrones above;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2922, line : "All, but the ever-wakeful eyes of Jove.(76)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2923, line : "To honour Thetis' son he bends his care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2924, line : "And plunge the Greeks in all the woes of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2925, line : "Then bids an empty phantom rise to sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2926, line : "And thus commands the vision of the night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2928, line : "\"Fly hence, deluding Dream! and light as air,(77)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2929, line : "To Agamemnon's ample tent repair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2930, line : "Bid him in arms draw forth the embattled train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2931, line : "Lead all his Grecians to the dusty plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2932, line : "Declare, e'en now 'tis given him to destroy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2933, line : "The lofty towers of wide-extended Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2934, line : "For now no more the gods with fate contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2935, line : "At Juno's suit the heavenly factions end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2936, line : "Destruction hangs o'er yon devoted wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2937, line : "And nodding Ilion waits the impending fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2939, line : "Swift as the word the vain illusion fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2940, line : "Descends, and hovers o'er Atrides' head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2941, line : "Clothed in the figure of the Pylian sage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2942, line : "Renown'd for wisdom, and revered for age:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2943, line : "Around his temples spreads his golden wing,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2944, line : "And thus the flattering dream deceives the king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2946, line : "[Illustration: JUPITER SENDING THE EVIL DREAM TO AGAMEMNON.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2948, line : "JUPITER SENDING THE EVIL DREAM TO AGAMEMNON."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2951, line : "\"Canst thou, with all a monarch's cares oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2952, line : "O Atreus' son! canst thou indulge the rest?(78)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2953, line : "Ill fits a chief who mighty nations guides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2954, line : "Directs in council, and in war presides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2955, line : "To whom its safety a whole people owes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2956, line : "To waste long nights in indolent repose.(79)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2957, line : "Monarch, awake! 'tis Jove's command I bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2958, line : "Thou, and thy glory, claim his heavenly care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2959, line : "In just array draw forth the embattled train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2960, line : "Lead all thy Grecians to the dusty plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2961, line : "E'en now, O king! 'tis given thee to destroy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2962, line : "The lofty towers of wide-extended Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2963, line : "For now no more the gods with fate contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2964, line : "At Juno's suit the heavenly factions end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2965, line : "Destruction hangs o'er yon devoted wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2966, line : "And nodding Ilion waits the impending fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2967, line : "Awake, but waking this advice approve,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2968, line : "And trust the vision that descends from Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2970, line : "The phantom said; then vanish'd from his sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2971, line : "Resolves to air, and mixes with the night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2972, line : "A thousand schemes the monarch's mind employ;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2973, line : "Elate in thought he sacks untaken Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2974, line : "Vain as he was, and to the future blind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2975, line : "Nor saw what Jove and secret fate design'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2976, line : "What mighty toils to either host remain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2977, line : "What scenes of grief, and numbers of the slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2978, line : "Eager he rises, and in fancy hears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2979, line : "The voice celestial murmuring in his ears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2980, line : "First on his limbs a slender vest he drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2981, line : "Around him next the regal mantle threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2982, line : "The embroider'd sandals on his feet were tied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2983, line : "The starry falchion glitter'd at his side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2984, line : "And last, his arm the massy sceptre loads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2985, line : "Unstain'd, immortal, and the gift of gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2987, line : "Now rosy Morn ascends the court of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2988, line : "Lifts up her light, and opens day above."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2989, line : "The king despatch'd his heralds with commands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2990, line : "To range the camp and summon all the bands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2991, line : "The gathering hosts the monarch's word obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2992, line : "While to the fleet Atrides bends his way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2993, line : "In his black ship the Pylian prince he found;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2994, line : "There calls a senate of the peers around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2995, line : "The assembly placed, the king of men express'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2996, line : "The counsels labouring in his artful breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2998, line : "\"Friends and confederates! with attentive ear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 2999, line : "Receive my words, and credit what you hear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3000, line : "Late as I slumber'd in the shades of night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3001, line : "A dream divine appear'd before my sight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3002, line : "Whose visionary form like Nestor came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3003, line : "The same in habit, and in mien the same.(80)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3004, line : "The heavenly phantom hover'd o'er my head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3005, line : "'And, dost thou sleep, O Atreus' son? (he said)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3006, line : "Ill fits a chief who mighty nations guides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3007, line : "Directs in council, and in war presides;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3008, line : "To whom its safety a whole people owes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3009, line : "To waste long nights in indolent repose."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3010, line : "Monarch, awake! 'tis Jove's command I bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3011, line : "Thou and thy glory claim his heavenly care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3012, line : "In just array draw forth the embattled train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3013, line : "And lead the Grecians to the dusty plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3014, line : "E'en now, O king! 'tis given thee to destroy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3015, line : "The lofty towers of wide-extended Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3016, line : "For now no more the gods with fate contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3017, line : "At Juno's suit the heavenly factions end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3018, line : "Destruction hangs o'er yon devoted wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3019, line : "And nodding Ilion waits the impending fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3021, line : "This hear observant, and the gods obey!'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3022, line : "The vision spoke, and pass'd in air away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3023, line : "Now, valiant chiefs! since heaven itself alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3024, line : "Unite, and rouse the sons of Greece to arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3025, line : "But first, with caution, try what yet they dare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3026, line : "Worn with nine years of unsuccessful war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3027, line : "To move the troops to measure back the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3028, line : "Be mine; and yours the province to detain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3030, line : "He spoke, and sat: when Nestor, rising said,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3031, line : "(Nestor, whom Pylos' sandy realms obey'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3032, line : "\"Princes of Greece, your faithful ears incline,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3033, line : "Nor doubt the vision of the powers divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3034, line : "Sent by great Jove to him who rules the host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3035, line : "Forbid it, heaven! this warning should be lost!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3036, line : "Then let us haste, obey the god's alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3037, line : "And join to rouse the sons of Greece to arms.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3039, line : "Thus spoke the sage: the kings without delay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3040, line : "Dissolve the council, and their chief obey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3041, line : "The sceptred rulers lead; the following host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3042, line : "Pour'd forth by thousands, darkens all the coast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3043, line : "As from some rocky cleft the shepherd sees"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3044, line : "Clustering in heaps on heaps the driving bees,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3045, line : "Rolling and blackening, swarms succeeding swarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3046, line : "With deeper murmurs and more hoarse alarms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3047, line : "Dusky they spread, a close embodied crowd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3048, line : "And o'er the vale descends the living cloud.(81)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3049, line : "So, from the tents and ships, a lengthen'd train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3050, line : "Spreads all the beach, and wide o'ershades the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3051, line : "Along the region runs a deafening sound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3052, line : "Beneath their footsteps groans the trembling ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3053, line : "Fame flies before the messenger of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3054, line : "And shining soars, and claps her wings above."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3055, line : "Nine sacred heralds now, proclaiming loud(82)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3056, line : "The monarch's will, suspend the listening crowd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3057, line : "Soon as the throngs in order ranged appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3058, line : "And fainter murmurs died upon the ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3059, line : "The king of kings his awful figure raised:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3060, line : "High in his hand the golden sceptre blazed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3061, line : "The golden sceptre, of celestial flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3062, line : "By Vulcan form'd, from Jove to Hermes came."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3063, line : "To Pelops he the immortal gift resign'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3064, line : "The immortal gift great Pelops left behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3065, line : "In Atreus' hand, which not with Atreus ends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3066, line : "To rich Thyestes next the prize descends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3067, line : "And now the mark of Agamemnon's reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3068, line : "Subjects all Argos, and controls the main.(83)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3070, line : "On this bright sceptre now the king reclined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3071, line : "And artful thus pronounced the speech design'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3072, line : "\"Ye sons of Mars, partake your leader's care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3073, line : "Heroes of Greece, and brothers of the war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3074, line : "Of partial Jove with justice I complain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3075, line : "And heavenly oracles believed in vain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3076, line : "A safe return was promised to our toils,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3077, line : "Renown'd, triumphant, and enrich'd with spoils."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3078, line : "Now shameful flight alone can save the host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3079, line : "Our blood, our treasure, and our glory lost."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3080, line : "So Jove decrees, resistless lord of all!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3081, line : "At whose command whole empires rise or fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3082, line : "He shakes the feeble props of human trust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3083, line : "And towns and armies humbles to the dust"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3084, line : "What shame to Greece a fruitful war to wage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3085, line : "Oh, lasting shame in every future age!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3086, line : "Once great in arms, the common scorn we grow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3087, line : "Repulsed and baffled by a feeble foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3088, line : "So small their number, that if wars were ceased,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3089, line : "And Greece triumphant held a general feast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3090, line : "All rank'd by tens, whole decades when they dine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3091, line : "Must want a Trojan slave to pour the wine.(84)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3092, line : "But other forces have our hopes o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3093, line : "And Troy prevails by armies not her own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3094, line : "Now nine long years of mighty Jove are run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3095, line : "Since first the labours of this war begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3096, line : "Our cordage torn, decay'd our vessels lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3097, line : "And scarce insure the wretched power to fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3098, line : "Haste, then, for ever leave the Trojan wall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3099, line : "Our weeping wives, our tender children call:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3100, line : "Love, duty, safety, summon us away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3101, line : "'Tis nature's voice, and nature we obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3102, line : "Our shatter'd barks may yet transport us o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3103, line : "Safe and inglorious, to our native shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3104, line : "Fly, Grecians, fly, your sails and oars employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3105, line : "And dream no more of heaven-defended Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3107, line : "His deep design unknown, the hosts approve"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3108, line : "Atrides' speech. The mighty numbers move."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3109, line : "So roll the billows to the Icarian shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3110, line : "From east and south when winds begin to roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3111, line : "Burst their dark mansions in the clouds, and sweep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3112, line : "The whitening surface of the ruffled deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3113, line : "And as on corn when western gusts descend,(85)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3114, line : "Before the blast the lofty harvests bend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3115, line : "Thus o'er the field the moving host appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3116, line : "With nodding plumes and groves of waving spears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3117, line : "The gathering murmur spreads, their trampling feet"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3118, line : "Beat the loose sands, and thicken to the fleet;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3119, line : "With long-resounding cries they urge the train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3120, line : "To fit the ships, and launch into the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3121, line : "They toil, they sweat, thick clouds of dust arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3122, line : "The doubling clamours echo to the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3123, line : "E'en then the Greeks had left the hostile plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3124, line : "And fate decreed the fall of Troy in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3125, line : "But Jove's imperial queen their flight survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3126, line : "And sighing thus bespoke the blue-eyed maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3128, line : "\"Shall then the Grecians fly! O dire disgrace!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3129, line : "And leave unpunish'd this perfidious race?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3130, line : "Shall Troy, shall Priam, and the adulterous spouse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3131, line : "In peace enjoy the fruits of broken vows?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3132, line : "And bravest chiefs, in Helen's quarrel slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3133, line : "Lie unrevenged on yon detested plain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3134, line : "No: let my Greeks, unmoved by vain alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3135, line : "Once more refulgent shine in brazen arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3136, line : "Haste, goddess, haste! the flying host detain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3137, line : "Nor let one sail be hoisted on the main.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3139, line : "Pallas obeys, and from Olympus' height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3140, line : "Swift to the ships precipitates her flight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3141, line : "Ulysses, first in public cares, she found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3142, line : "For prudent counsel like the gods renown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3143, line : "Oppress'd with generous grief the hero stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3144, line : "Nor drew his sable vessels to the flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3145, line : "\"And is it thus, divine Laertes' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3146, line : "Thus fly the Greeks (the martial maid begun),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3147, line : "Thus to their country bear their own disgrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3148, line : "And fame eternal leave to Priam's race?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3149, line : "Shall beauteous Helen still remain unfreed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3150, line : "Still unrevenged, a thousand heroes bleed!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3151, line : "Haste, generous Ithacus! prevent the shame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3152, line : "Recall your armies, and your chiefs reclaim."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3153, line : "Your own resistless eloquence employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3154, line : "And to the immortals trust the fall of Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3156, line : "The voice divine confess'd the warlike maid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3157, line : "Ulysses heard, nor uninspired obey'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3158, line : "Then meeting first Atrides, from his hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3159, line : "Received the imperial sceptre of command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3160, line : "Thus graced, attention and respect to gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3161, line : "He runs, he flies through all the Grecian train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3162, line : "Each prince of name, or chief in arms approved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3163, line : "He fired with praise, or with persuasion moved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3165, line : "\"Warriors like you, with strength and wisdom bless'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3166, line : "By brave examples should confirm the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3167, line : "The monarch's will not yet reveal'd appears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3168, line : "He tries our courage, but resents our fears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3169, line : "The unwary Greeks his fury may provoke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3170, line : "Not thus the king in secret council spoke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3171, line : "Jove loves our chief, from Jove his honour springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3172, line : "Beware! for dreadful is the wrath of kings.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3174, line : "But if a clamorous vile plebeian rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3175, line : "Him with reproof he check'd or tamed with blows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3176, line : "\"Be still, thou slave, and to thy betters yield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3177, line : "Unknown alike in council and in field!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3178, line : "Ye gods, what dastards would our host command!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3179, line : "Swept to the war, the lumber of a land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3180, line : "Be silent, wretch, and think not here allow'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3181, line : "That worst of tyrants, an usurping crowd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3182, line : "To one sole monarch Jove commits the sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3183, line : "His are the laws, and him let all obey.\"(86)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3185, line : "With words like these the troops Ulysses ruled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3186, line : "The loudest silenced, and the fiercest cool'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3187, line : "Back to the assembly roll the thronging train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3188, line : "Desert the ships, and pour upon the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3189, line : "Murmuring they move, as when old ocean roars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3190, line : "And heaves huge surges to the trembling shores;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3191, line : "The groaning banks are burst with bellowing sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3192, line : "The rocks remurmur and the deeps rebound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3193, line : "At length the tumult sinks, the noises cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3194, line : "And a still silence lulls the camp to peace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3195, line : "Thersites only clamour'd in the throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3196, line : "Loquacious, loud, and turbulent of tongue:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3197, line : "Awed by no shame, by no respect controll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3198, line : "In scandal busy, in reproaches bold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3199, line : "With witty malice studious to defame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3200, line : "Scorn all his joy, and laughter all his aim:--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3201, line : "But chief he gloried with licentious style"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3202, line : "To lash the great, and monarchs to revile."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3203, line : "His figure such as might his soul proclaim;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3204, line : "One eye was blinking, and one leg was lame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3205, line : "His mountain shoulders half his breast o'erspread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3206, line : "Thin hairs bestrew'd his long misshapen head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3207, line : "Spleen to mankind his envious heart possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3208, line : "And much he hated all, but most the best:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3209, line : "Ulysses or Achilles still his theme;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3210, line : "But royal scandal his delight supreme,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3211, line : "Long had he lived the scorn of every Greek,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3212, line : "Vex'd when he spoke, yet still they heard him speak."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3213, line : "Sharp was his voice; which in the shrillest tone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3214, line : "Thus with injurious taunts attack'd the throne."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3216, line : "\"Amidst the glories of so bright a reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3217, line : "What moves the great Atrides to complain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3218, line : "'Tis thine whate'er the warrior's breast inflames,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3219, line : "The golden spoil, and thine the lovely dames."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3220, line : "With all the wealth our wars and blood bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3221, line : "Thy tents are crowded and thy chests o'erflow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3222, line : "Thus at full ease in heaps of riches roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3223, line : "What grieves the monarch? Is it thirst of gold?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3224, line : "Say, shall we march with our unconquer'd powers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3225, line : "(The Greeks and I) to Ilion's hostile towers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3226, line : "And bring the race of royal bastards here,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3227, line : "For Troy to ransom at a price too dear?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3228, line : "But safer plunder thy own host supplies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3229, line : "Say, wouldst thou seize some valiant leader's prize?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3230, line : "Or, if thy heart to generous love be led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3231, line : "Some captive fair, to bless thy kingly bed?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3232, line : "Whate'er our master craves submit we must,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3233, line : "Plagued with his pride, or punish'd for his lust."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3234, line : "Oh women of Achaia; men no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3235, line : "Hence let us fly, and let him waste his store"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3236, line : "In loves and pleasures on the Phrygian shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3237, line : "We may be wanted on some busy day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3238, line : "When Hector comes: so great Achilles may:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3239, line : "From him he forced the prize we jointly gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3240, line : "From him, the fierce, the fearless, and the brave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3241, line : "And durst he, as he ought, resent that wrong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3242, line : "This mighty tyrant were no tyrant long.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3244, line : "Fierce from his seat at this Ulysses springs,(87)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3245, line : "In generous vengeance of the king of kings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3246, line : "With indignation sparkling in his eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3247, line : "He views the wretch, and sternly thus replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3249, line : "\"Peace, factious monster, born to vex the state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3250, line : "With wrangling talents form'd for foul debate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3251, line : "Curb that impetuous tongue, nor rashly vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3252, line : "And singly mad, asperse the sovereign reign."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3253, line : "Have we not known thee, slave! of all our host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3254, line : "The man who acts the least, upbraids the most?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3255, line : "Think not the Greeks to shameful flight to bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3256, line : "Nor let those lips profane the name of king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3257, line : "For our return we trust the heavenly powers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3258, line : "Be that their care; to fight like men be ours."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3259, line : "But grant the host with wealth the general load,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3260, line : "Except detraction, what hast thou bestow'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3261, line : "Suppose some hero should his spoils resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3262, line : "Art thou that hero, could those spoils be thine?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3263, line : "Gods! let me perish on this hateful shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3264, line : "And let these eyes behold my son no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3265, line : "If, on thy next offence, this hand forbear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3266, line : "To strip those arms thou ill deserv'st to wear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3267, line : "Expel the council where our princes meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3268, line : "And send thee scourged and howling through the fleet.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3270, line : "He said, and cowering as the dastard bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3271, line : "The weighty sceptre on his bank descends.(88)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3272, line : "On the round bunch the bloody tumours rise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3273, line : "The tears spring starting from his haggard eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3274, line : "Trembling he sat, and shrunk in abject fears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3275, line : "From his vile visage wiped the scalding tears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3276, line : "While to his neighbour each express'd his thought:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3278, line : "\"Ye gods! what wonders has Ulysses wrought!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3279, line : "What fruits his conduct and his courage yield!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3280, line : "Great in the council, glorious in the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3281, line : "Generous he rises in the crown's defence,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3282, line : "To curb the factious tongue of insolence,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3283, line : "Such just examples on offenders shown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3284, line : "Sedition silence, and assert the throne.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3286, line : "'Twas thus the general voice the hero praised,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3287, line : "Who, rising, high the imperial sceptre raised:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3288, line : "The blue-eyed Pallas, his celestial friend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3289, line : "(In form a herald,) bade the crowds attend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3290, line : "The expecting crowds in still attention hung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3291, line : "To hear the wisdom of his heavenly tongue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3292, line : "Then deeply thoughtful, pausing ere he spoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3293, line : "His silence thus the prudent hero broke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3295, line : "\"Unhappy monarch! whom the Grecian race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3296, line : "With shame deserting, heap with vile disgrace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3297, line : "Not such at Argos was their generous vow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3298, line : "Once all their voice, but ah! forgotten now:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3299, line : "Ne'er to return, was then the common cry,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3300, line : "Till Troy's proud structures should in ashes lie."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3301, line : "Behold them weeping for their native shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3302, line : "What could their wives or helpless children more?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3303, line : "What heart but melts to leave the tender train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3304, line : "And, one short month, endure the wintry main?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3305, line : "Few leagues removed, we wish our peaceful seat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3306, line : "When the ship tosses, and the tempests beat:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3307, line : "Then well may this long stay provoke their tears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3308, line : "The tedious length of nine revolving years."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3309, line : "Not for their grief the Grecian host I blame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3310, line : "But vanquish'd! baffled! oh, eternal shame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3311, line : "Expect the time to Troy's destruction given."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3312, line : "And try the faith of Chalcas and of heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3313, line : "What pass'd at Aulis, Greece can witness bear,(89)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3314, line : "And all who live to breathe this Phrygian air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3315, line : "Beside a fountain's sacred brink we raised"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3316, line : "Our verdant altars, and the victims blazed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3317, line : "'Twas where the plane-tree spread its shades around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3318, line : "The altars heaved; and from the crumbling ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3319, line : "A mighty dragon shot, of dire portent;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3320, line : "From Jove himself the dreadful sign was sent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3321, line : "Straight to the tree his sanguine spires he roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3322, line : "And curl'd around in many a winding fold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3323, line : "The topmost branch a mother-bird possess'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3324, line : "Eight callow infants fill'd the mossy nest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3325, line : "Herself the ninth; the serpent, as he hung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3326, line : "Stretch'd his black jaws and crush'd the crying young;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3327, line : "While hovering near, with miserable moan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3328, line : "The drooping mother wail'd her children gone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3329, line : "The mother last, as round the nest she flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3330, line : "Seized by the beating wing, the monster slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3331, line : "Nor long survived: to marble turn'd, he stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3332, line : "A lasting prodigy on Aulis' sands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3333, line : "Such was the will of Jove; and hence we dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3334, line : "Trust in his omen, and support the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3335, line : "For while around we gazed with wondering eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3336, line : "And trembling sought the powers with sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3337, line : "Full of his god, the reverend Chalcas cried,(90)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3338, line : "'Ye Grecian warriors! lay your fears aside."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3339, line : "This wondrous signal Jove himself displays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3340, line : "Of long, long labours, but eternal praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3341, line : "As many birds as by the snake were slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3342, line : "So many years the toils of Greece remain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3343, line : "But wait the tenth, for Ilion's fall decreed:'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3344, line : "Thus spoke the prophet, thus the Fates succeed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3345, line : "Obey, ye Grecians! with submission wait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3346, line : "Nor let your flight avert the Trojan fate.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3347, line : "He said: the shores with loud applauses sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3348, line : "The hollow ships each deafening shout rebound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3349, line : "Then Nestor thus--\"These vain debates forbear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3350, line : "Ye talk like children, not like heroes dare."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3351, line : "Where now are all your high resolves at last?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3352, line : "Your leagues concluded, your engagements past?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3353, line : "Vow'd with libations and with victims then,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3354, line : "Now vanish'd like their smoke: the faith of men!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3355, line : "While useless words consume the unactive hours,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3356, line : "No wonder Troy so long resists our powers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3357, line : "Rise, great Atrides! and with courage sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3358, line : "We march to war, if thou direct the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3359, line : "But leave the few that dare resist thy laws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3360, line : "The mean deserters of the Grecian cause,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3361, line : "To grudge the conquests mighty Jove prepares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3362, line : "And view with envy our successful wars."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3363, line : "On that great day, when first the martial train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3364, line : "Big with the fate of Ilion, plough'd the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3365, line : "Jove, on the right, a prosperous signal sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3366, line : "And thunder rolling shook the firmament."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3367, line : "Encouraged hence, maintain the glorious strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3368, line : "Till every soldier grasp a Phrygian wife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3369, line : "Till Helen's woes at full revenged appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3370, line : "And Troy's proud matrons render tear for tear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3371, line : "Before that day, if any Greek invite"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3372, line : "His country's troops to base, inglorious flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3373, line : "Stand forth that Greek! and hoist his sail to fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3374, line : "And die the dastard first, who dreads to die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3375, line : "But now, O monarch! all thy chiefs advise:(91)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3376, line : "Nor what they offer, thou thyself despise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3377, line : "Among those counsels, let not mine be vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3378, line : "In tribes and nations to divide thy train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3379, line : "His separate troops let every leader call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3380, line : "Each strengthen each, and all encourage all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3381, line : "What chief, or soldier, of the numerous band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3382, line : "Or bravely fights, or ill obeys command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3383, line : "When thus distinct they war, shall soon be known"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3384, line : "And what the cause of Ilion not o'erthrown;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3385, line : "If fate resists, or if our arms are slow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3386, line : "If gods above prevent, or men below.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3388, line : "To him the king: \"How much thy years excel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3389, line : "In arts of counsel, and in speaking well!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3390, line : "O would the gods, in love to Greece, decree"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3391, line : "But ten such sages as they grant in thee;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3392, line : "Such wisdom soon should Priam's force destroy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3393, line : "And soon should fall the haughty towers of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3394, line : "But Jove forbids, who plunges those he hates"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3395, line : "In fierce contention and in vain debates:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3396, line : "Now great Achilles from our aid withdraws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3397, line : "By me provoked; a captive maid the cause:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3398, line : "If e'er as friends we join, the Trojan wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3399, line : "Must shake, and heavy will the vengeance fall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3400, line : "But now, ye warriors, take a short repast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3401, line : "And, well refresh'd, to bloody conflict haste."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3402, line : "His sharpen'd spear let every Grecian wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3403, line : "And every Grecian fix his brazen shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3404, line : "Let all excite the fiery steeds of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3405, line : "And all for combat fit the rattling car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3406, line : "This day, this dreadful day, let each contend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3407, line : "No rest, no respite, till the shades descend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3408, line : "Till darkness, or till death, shall cover all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3409, line : "Let the war bleed, and let the mighty fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3410, line : "Till bathed in sweat be every manly breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3411, line : "With the huge shield each brawny arm depress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3412, line : "Each aching nerve refuse the lance to throw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3413, line : "And each spent courser at the chariot blow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3414, line : "Who dares, inglorious, in his ships to stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3415, line : "Who dares to tremble on this signal day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3416, line : "That wretch, too mean to fall by martial power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3417, line : "The birds shall mangle, and the dogs devour.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3419, line : "The monarch spoke; and straight a murmur rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3420, line : "Loud as the surges when the tempest blows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3421, line : "That dash'd on broken rocks tumultuous roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3422, line : "And foam and thunder on the stony shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3423, line : "Straight to the tents the troops dispersing bend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3424, line : "The fires are kindled, and the smokes ascend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3425, line : "With hasty feasts they sacrifice, and pray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3426, line : "To avert the dangers of the doubtful day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3427, line : "A steer of five years' age, large limb'd, and fed,(92)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3428, line : "To Jove's high altars Agamemnon led:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3429, line : "There bade the noblest of the Grecian peers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3430, line : "And Nestor first, as most advanced in years."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3431, line : "Next came Idomeneus,(93)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3432, line : "and Tydeus' son,(94)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3433, line : "Ajax the less, and Ajax Telamon;(95)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3434, line : "Then wise Ulysses in his rank was placed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3435, line : "And Menelaus came, unbid, the last.(96)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3436, line : "The chiefs surround the destined beast, and take"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3437, line : "The sacred offering of the salted cake:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3438, line : "When thus the king prefers his solemn prayer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3439, line : "\"O thou! whose thunder rends the clouded air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3440, line : "Who in the heaven of heavens hast fixed thy throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3441, line : "Supreme of gods! unbounded, and alone!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3442, line : "Hear! and before the burning sun descends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3443, line : "Before the night her gloomy veil extends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3444, line : "Low in the dust be laid yon hostile spires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3445, line : "Be Priam's palace sunk in Grecian fires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3446, line : "In Hector's breast be plunged this shining sword,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3447, line : "And slaughter'd heroes groan around their lord!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3449, line : "Thus prayed the chief: his unavailing prayer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3450, line : "Great Jove refused, and toss'd in empty air:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3451, line : "The God averse, while yet the fumes arose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3452, line : "Prepared new toils, and doubled woes on woes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3453, line : "Their prayers perform'd the chiefs the rite pursue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3454, line : "The barley sprinkled, and the victim slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3455, line : "The limbs they sever from the inclosing hide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3456, line : "The thighs, selected to the gods, divide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3457, line : "On these, in double cauls involved with art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3458, line : "The choicest morsels lie from every part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3459, line : "From the cleft wood the crackling flames aspire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3460, line : "While the fat victims feed the sacred fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3461, line : "The thighs thus sacrificed, and entrails dress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3462, line : "The assistants part, transfix, and roast the rest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3463, line : "Then spread the tables, the repast prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3464, line : "Each takes his seat, and each receives his share."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3465, line : "Soon as the rage of hunger was suppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3466, line : "The generous Nestor thus the prince address'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3468, line : "\"Now bid thy heralds sound the loud alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3469, line : "And call the squadrons sheathed in brazen arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3470, line : "Now seize the occasion, now the troops survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3471, line : "And lead to war when heaven directs the way.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3473, line : "He said; the monarch issued his commands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3474, line : "Straight the loud heralds call the gathering bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3475, line : "The chiefs inclose their king; the hosts divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3476, line : "In tribes and nations rank'd on either side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3477, line : "High in the midst the blue-eyed virgin flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3478, line : "From rank to rank she darts her ardent eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3479, line : "The dreadful aegis, Jove's immortal shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3480, line : "Blazed on her arm, and lighten'd all the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3481, line : "Round the vast orb a hundred serpents roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3482, line : "Form'd the bright fringe, and seem'd to burn in gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3483, line : "With this each Grecian's manly breast she warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3484, line : "Swells their bold hearts, and strings their nervous arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3485, line : "No more they sigh, inglorious, to return,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3486, line : "But breathe revenge, and for the combat burn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3488, line : "As on some mountain, through the lofty grove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3489, line : "The crackling flames ascend, and blaze above;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3490, line : "The fires expanding, as the winds arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3491, line : "Shoot their long beams, and kindle half the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3492, line : "So from the polish'd arms, and brazen shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3493, line : "A gleamy splendour flash'd along the fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3494, line : "Not less their number than the embodied cranes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3495, line : "Or milk-white swans in Asius' watery plains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3496, line : "That, o'er the windings of Cayster's springs,(97)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3497, line : "Stretch their long necks, and clap their rustling wings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3498, line : "Now tower aloft, and course in airy rounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3499, line : "Now light with noise; with noise the field resounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3500, line : "Thus numerous and confused, extending wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3501, line : "The legions crowd Scamander's flowery side;(98)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3502, line : "With rushing troops the plains are cover'd o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3503, line : "And thundering footsteps shake the sounding shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3504, line : "Along the river's level meads they stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3505, line : "Thick as in spring the flowers adorn the land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3506, line : "Or leaves the trees; or thick as insects play,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3507, line : "The wandering nation of a summer's day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3508, line : "That, drawn by milky steams, at evening hours,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3509, line : "In gather'd swarms surround the rural bowers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3510, line : "From pail to pail with busy murmur run"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3511, line : "The gilded legions, glittering in the sun."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3512, line : "So throng'd, so close, the Grecian squadrons stood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3513, line : "In radiant arms, and thirst for Trojan blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3514, line : "Each leader now his scatter'd force conjoins"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3515, line : "In close array, and forms the deepening lines."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3516, line : "Not with more ease the skilful shepherd-swain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3517, line : "Collects his flocks from thousands on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3518, line : "The king of kings, majestically tall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3519, line : "Towers o'er his armies, and outshines them all;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3520, line : "Like some proud bull, that round the pastures leads"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3521, line : "His subject herds, the monarch of the meads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3522, line : "Great as the gods, the exalted chief was seen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3523, line : "His strength like Neptune, and like Mars his mien;(99)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3524, line : "Jove o'er his eyes celestial glories spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3525, line : "And dawning conquest played around his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3527, line : "Say, virgins, seated round the throne divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3528, line : "All-knowing goddesses! immortal nine!(100)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3529, line : "Since earth's wide regions, heaven's umneasur'd height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3530, line : "And hell's abyss, hide nothing from your sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3531, line : "(We, wretched mortals! lost in doubts below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3532, line : "But guess by rumour, and but boast we know,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3533, line : "O say what heroes, fired by thirst of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3534, line : "Or urged by wrongs, to Troy's destruction came."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3535, line : "To count them all, demands a thousand tongues,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3536, line : "A throat of brass, and adamantine lungs."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3537, line : "Daughters of Jove, assist! inspired by you"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3538, line : "The mighty labour dauntless I pursue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3539, line : "What crowded armies, from what climes they bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3540, line : "Their names, their numbers, and their chiefs I sing."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3542, line : "THE CATALOGUE OF THE SHIPS.(101)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3544, line : "[Illustration: NEPTUNE.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3546, line : "NEPTUNE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3549, line : "The hardy warriors whom Boeotia bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3550, line : "Penelius, Leitus, Prothoenor, led:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3551, line : "With these Arcesilaus and Clonius stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3552, line : "Equal in arms, and equal in command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3553, line : "These head the troops that rocky Aulis yields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3554, line : "And Eteon's hills, and Hyrie's watery fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3555, line : "And Schoenos, Scholos, Graea near the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3556, line : "And Mycalessia's ample piny plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3557, line : "Those who in Peteon or Ilesion dwell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3558, line : "Or Harma where Apollo's prophet fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3559, line : "Heleon and Hyle, which the springs o'erflow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3560, line : "And Medeon lofty, and Ocalea low;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3561, line : "Or in the meads of Haliartus stray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3562, line : "Or Thespia sacred to the god of day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3563, line : "Onchestus, Neptune's celebrated groves;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3564, line : "Copae, and Thisbe, famed for silver doves;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3565, line : "For flocks Erythrae, Glissa for the vine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3566, line : "Platea green, and Nysa the divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3567, line : "And they whom Thebe's well-built walls inclose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3568, line : "Where Myde, Eutresis, Corone, rose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3569, line : "And Arne rich, with purple harvests crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3570, line : "And Anthedon, Boeotia's utmost bound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3571, line : "Full fifty ships they send, and each conveys"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3572, line : "Twice sixty warriors through the foaming seas.(102)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3574, line : "To these succeed Aspledon's martial train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3575, line : "Who plough the spacious Orchomenian plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3576, line : "Two valiant brothers rule the undaunted throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3577, line : "Ialmen and Ascalaphus the strong:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3578, line : "Sons of Astyoche, the heavenly fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3579, line : "Whose virgin charms subdued the god of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3580, line : "(In Actor's court as she retired to rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3581, line : "The strength of Mars the blushing maid compress'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3582, line : "Their troops in thirty sable vessels sweep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3583, line : "With equal oars, the hoarse-resounding deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3585, line : "The Phocians next in forty barks repair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3586, line : "Epistrophus and Schedius head the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3587, line : "From those rich regions where Cephisus leads"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3588, line : "His silver current through the flowery meads;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3589, line : "From Panopea, Chrysa the divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3590, line : "Where Anemoria's stately turrets shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3591, line : "Where Pytho, Daulis, Cyparissus stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3592, line : "And fair Lilaea views the rising flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3593, line : "These, ranged in order on the floating tide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3594, line : "Close, on the left, the bold Boeotians' side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3596, line : "Fierce Ajax led the Locrian squadrons on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3597, line : "Ajax the less, Oileus' valiant son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3598, line : "Skill'd to direct the flying dart aright;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3599, line : "Swift in pursuit, and active in the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3600, line : "Him, as their chief, the chosen troops attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3601, line : "Which Bessa, Thronus, and rich Cynos send;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3602, line : "Opus, Calliarus, and Scarphe's bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3603, line : "And those who dwell where pleasing Augia stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3604, line : "And where Boagrius floats the lowly lands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3605, line : "Or in fair Tarphe's sylvan seats reside:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3606, line : "In forty vessels cut the yielding tide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3608, line : "Euboea next her martial sons prepares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3609, line : "And sends the brave Abantes to the wars:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3610, line : "Breathing revenge, in arms they take their way"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3611, line : "From Chalcis' walls, and strong Eretria;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3612, line : "The Isteian fields for generous vines renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3613, line : "The fair Caristos, and the Styrian ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3614, line : "Where Dios from her towers o'erlooks the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3615, line : "And high Cerinthus views the neighbouring main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3616, line : "Down their broad shoulders falls a length of hair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3617, line : "Their hands dismiss not the long lance in air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3618, line : "But with protended spears in fighting fields"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3619, line : "Pierce the tough corslets and the brazen shields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3620, line : "Twice twenty ships transport the warlike bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3621, line : "Which bold Elphenor, fierce in arms, commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3623, line : "Full fifty more from Athens stem the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3624, line : "Led by Menestheus through the liquid plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3625, line : "(Athens the fair, where great Erectheus sway'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3626, line : "That owed his nurture to the blue-eyed maid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3627, line : "But from the teeming furrow took his birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3628, line : "The mighty offspring of the foodful earth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3629, line : "Him Pallas placed amidst her wealthy fane,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3630, line : "Adored with sacrifice and oxen slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3631, line : "Where, as the years revolve, her altars blaze,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3632, line : "And all the tribes resound the goddess' praise.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3633, line : "No chief like thee, Menestheus! Greece could yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3634, line : "To marshal armies in the dusty field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3635, line : "The extended wings of battle to display,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3636, line : "Or close the embodied host in firm array."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3637, line : "Nestor alone, improved by length of days,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3638, line : "For martial conduct bore an equal praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3640, line : "With these appear the Salaminian bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3641, line : "Whom the gigantic Telamon commands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3642, line : "In twelve black ships to Troy they steer their course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3643, line : "And with the great Athenians join their force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3645, line : "Next move to war the generous Argive train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3646, line : "From high Troezene, and Maseta's plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3647, line : "And fair Ćgina circled by the main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3648, line : "Whom strong Tyrinthe's lofty walls surround,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3649, line : "And Epidaure with viny harvests crown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3650, line : "And where fair Asinen and Hermoin show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3651, line : "Their cliffs above, and ample bay below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3652, line : "These by the brave Euryalus were led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3653, line : "Great Sthenelus, and greater Diomed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3654, line : "But chief Tydides bore the sovereign sway:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3655, line : "In fourscore barks they plough the watery way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3657, line : "The proud Mycene arms her martial powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3658, line : "Cleone, Corinth, with imperial towers,(103)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3659, line : "Fair Araethyrea, Ornia's fruitful plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3660, line : "And Ćgion, and Adrastus' ancient reign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3661, line : "And those who dwell along the sandy shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3662, line : "And where Pellene yields her fleecy store,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3663, line : "Where Helice and Hyperesia lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3664, line : "And Gonoessa's spires salute the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3665, line : "Great Agamemnon rules the numerous band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3666, line : "A hundred vessels in long order stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3667, line : "And crowded nations wait his dread command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3668, line : "High on the deck the king of men appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3669, line : "And his refulgent arms in triumph wears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3670, line : "Proud of his host, unrivall'd in his reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3671, line : "In silent pomp he moves along the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3673, line : "His brother follows, and to vengeance warms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3674, line : "The hardy Spartans, exercised in arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3675, line : "Phares and Brysia's valiant troops, and those"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3676, line : "Whom Lacedaemon's lofty hills inclose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3677, line : "Or Messe's towers for silver doves renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3678, line : "Amyclae, Laas, Augia's happy ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3679, line : "And those whom OEtylos' low walls contain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3680, line : "And Helos, on the margin of the main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3681, line : "These, o'er the bending ocean, Helen's cause,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3682, line : "In sixty ships with Menelaus draws:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3683, line : "Eager and loud from man to man he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3684, line : "Revenge and fury flaming in his eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3685, line : "While vainly fond, in fancy oft he hears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3686, line : "The fair one's grief, and sees her falling tears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3688, line : "In ninety sail, from Pylos' sandy coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3689, line : "Nestor the sage conducts his chosen host:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3690, line : "From Amphigenia's ever-fruitful land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3691, line : "Where Ćpy high, and little Pteleon stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3692, line : "Where beauteous Arene her structures shows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3693, line : "And Thryon's walls Alpheus' streams inclose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3694, line : "And Dorion, famed for Thamyris' disgrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3695, line : "Superior once of all the tuneful race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3696, line : "Till, vain of mortals' empty praise, he strove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3697, line : "To match the seed of cloud-compelling Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3698, line : "Too daring bard! whose unsuccessful pride"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3699, line : "The immortal Muses in their art defied."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3700, line : "The avenging Muses of the light of day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3701, line : "Deprived his eyes, and snatch'd his voice away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3702, line : "No more his heavenly voice was heard to sing,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3703, line : "His hand no more awaked the silver string."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3705, line : "Where under high Cyllene, crown'd with wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3706, line : "The shaded tomb of old Ćpytus stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3707, line : "From Ripe, Stratie, Tegea's bordering towns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3708, line : "The Phenean fields, and Orchomenian downs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3709, line : "Where the fat herds in plenteous pasture rove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3710, line : "And Stymphelus with her surrounding grove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3711, line : "Parrhasia, on her snowy cliffs reclined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3712, line : "And high Enispe shook by wintry wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3713, line : "And fair Mantinea's ever-pleasing site;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3714, line : "In sixty sail the Arcadian bands unite."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3715, line : "Bold Agapenor, glorious at their head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3716, line : "(Ancaeus' son) the mighty squadron led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3717, line : "Their ships, supplied by Agamemnon's care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3718, line : "Through roaring seas the wondering warriors bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3719, line : "The first to battle on the appointed plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3720, line : "But new to all the dangers of the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3722, line : "Those, where fair Elis and Buprasium join;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3723, line : "Whom Hyrmin, here, and Myrsinus confine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3724, line : "And bounded there, where o'er the valleys rose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3725, line : "The Olenian rock; and where Alisium flows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3726, line : "Beneath four chiefs (a numerous army) came:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3727, line : "The strength and glory of the Epean name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3728, line : "In separate squadrons these their train divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3729, line : "Each leads ten vessels through the yielding tide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3730, line : "One was Amphimachus, and Thalpius one;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3731, line : "(Eurytus' this, and that Teatus' son;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3732, line : "Diores sprung from Amarynceus' line;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3733, line : "And great Polyxenus, of force divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3735, line : "But those who view fair Elis o'er the seas"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3736, line : "From the blest islands of the Echinades,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3737, line : "In forty vessels under Meges move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3738, line : "Begot by Phyleus, the beloved of Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3739, line : "To strong Dulichium from his sire he fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3740, line : "And thence to Troy his hardy warriors led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3742, line : "Ulysses follow'd through the watery road,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3743, line : "A chief, in wisdom equal to a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3744, line : "With those whom Cephalenia's line inclosed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3745, line : "Or till their fields along the coast opposed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3746, line : "Or where fair Ithaca o'erlooks the floods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3747, line : "Where high Neritos shakes his waving woods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3748, line : "Where Ćgilipa's rugged sides are seen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3749, line : "Crocylia rocky, and Zacynthus green."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3750, line : "These in twelve galleys with vermilion prores,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3751, line : "Beneath his conduct sought the Phrygian shores."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3753, line : "Thoas came next, Andraemon's valiant son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3754, line : "From Pleuron's walls, and chalky Calydon,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3755, line : "And rough Pylene, and the Olenian steep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3756, line : "And Chalcis, beaten by the rolling deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3757, line : "He led the warriors from the Ćtolian shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3758, line : "For now the sons of OEneus were no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3759, line : "The glories of the mighty race were fled!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3760, line : "OEneus himself, and Meleager dead!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3761, line : "To Thoas' care now trust the martial train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3762, line : "His forty vessels follow through the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3764, line : "Next, eighty barks the Cretan king commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3765, line : "Of Gnossus, Lyctus, and Gortyna's bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3766, line : "And those who dwell where Rhytion's domes arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3767, line : "Or white Lycastus glitters to the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3768, line : "Or where by Phaestus silver Jardan runs;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3769, line : "Crete's hundred cities pour forth all her sons."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3770, line : "These march'd, Idomeneus, beneath thy care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3771, line : "And Merion, dreadful as the god of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3773, line : "Tlepolemus, the sun of Hercules,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3774, line : "Led nine swift vessels through the foamy seas,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3775, line : "From Rhodes, with everlasting sunshine bright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3776, line : "Jalyssus, Lindus, and Camirus white."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3777, line : "His captive mother fierce Alcides bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3778, line : "From Ephyr's walls and Selle's winding shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3779, line : "Where mighty towns in ruins spread the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3780, line : "And saw their blooming warriors early slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3781, line : "The hero, when to manly years he grew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3782, line : "Alcides' uncle, old Licymnius, slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3783, line : "For this, constrain'd to quit his native place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3784, line : "And shun the vengeance of the Herculean race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3785, line : "A fleet he built, and with a numerous train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3786, line : "Of willing exiles wander'd o'er the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3787, line : "Where, many seas and many sufferings past,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3788, line : "On happy Rhodes the chief arrived at last:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3789, line : "There in three tribes divides his native band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3790, line : "And rules them peaceful in a foreign land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3791, line : "Increased and prosper'd in their new abodes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3792, line : "By mighty Jove, the sire of men and gods;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3793, line : "With joy they saw the growing empire rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3794, line : "And showers of wealth descending from the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3796, line : "Three ships with Nireus sought the Trojan shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3797, line : "Nireus, whom Aglae to Charopus bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3798, line : "Nireus, in faultless shape and blooming grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3799, line : "The loveliest youth of all the Grecian race;(104)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3800, line : "Pelides only match'd his early charms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3801, line : "But few his troops, and small his strength in arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3803, line : "Next thirty galleys cleave the liquid plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3804, line : "Of those Calydnae's sea-girt isles contain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3805, line : "With them the youth of Nisyrus repair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3806, line : "Casus the strong, and Crapathus the fair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3807, line : "Cos, where Eurypylus possess'd the sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3808, line : "Till great Alcides made the realms obey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3809, line : "These Antiphus and bold Phidippus bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3810, line : "Sprung from the god by Thessalus the king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3812, line : "Now, Muse, recount Pelasgic Argos' powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3813, line : "From Alos, Alope, and Trechin's towers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3814, line : "From Phthia's spacious vales; and Hella, bless'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3815, line : "With female beauty far beyond the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3816, line : "Full fifty ships beneath Achilles' care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3817, line : "The Achaians, Myrmidons, Hellenians bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3818, line : "Thessalians all, though various in their name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3819, line : "The same their nation, and their chief the same."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3820, line : "But now inglorious, stretch'd along the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3821, line : "They hear the brazen voice of war no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3822, line : "No more the foe they face in dire array:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3823, line : "Close in his fleet the angry leader lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3824, line : "Since fair Briseis from his arms was torn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3825, line : "The noblest spoil from sack'd Lyrnessus borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3826, line : "Then, when the chief the Theban walls o'erthrew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3827, line : "And the bold sons of great Evenus slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3828, line : "There mourn'd Achilles, plunged in depth of care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3829, line : "But soon to rise in slaughter, blood, and war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3831, line : "To these the youth of Phylace succeed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3832, line : "Itona, famous for her fleecy breed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3833, line : "And grassy Pteleon deck'd with cheerful greens,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3834, line : "The bowers of Ceres, and the sylvan scenes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3835, line : "Sweet Pyrrhasus, with blooming flowerets crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3836, line : "And Antron's watery dens, and cavern'd ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3837, line : "These own'd, as chief, Protesilas the brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3838, line : "Who now lay silent in the gloomy grave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3839, line : "The first who boldly touch'd the Trojan shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3840, line : "And dyed a Phrygian lance with Grecian gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3841, line : "There lies, far distant from his native plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3842, line : "Unfinish'd his proud palaces remain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3843, line : "And his sad consort beats her breast in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3844, line : "His troops in forty ships Podarces led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3845, line : "Iphiclus' son, and brother to the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3846, line : "Nor he unworthy to command the host;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3847, line : "Yet still they mourn'd their ancient leader lost."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3849, line : "The men who Glaphyra's fair soil partake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3850, line : "Where hills incircle Boebe's lowly lake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3851, line : "Where Phaere hears the neighbouring waters fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3852, line : "Or proud Iolcus lifts her airy wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3853, line : "In ten black ships embark'd for Ilion's shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3854, line : "With bold Eumelus, whom Alceste bore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3855, line : "All Pelias' race Alceste far outshined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3856, line : "The grace and glory of the beauteous kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3858, line : "The troops Methone or Thaumacia yields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3859, line : "Olizon's rocks, or Meliboea's fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3860, line : "With Philoctetes sail'd whose matchless art"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3861, line : "From the tough bow directs the feather'd dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3862, line : "Seven were his ships; each vessel fifty row,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3863, line : "Skill'd in his science of the dart and bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3864, line : "But he lay raging on the Lemnian ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3865, line : "A poisonous hydra gave the burning wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3866, line : "There groan'd the chief in agonizing pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3867, line : "Whom Greece at length shall wish, nor wish in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3868, line : "His forces Medon led from Lemnos' shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3869, line : "Oileus' son, whom beauteous Rhena bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3871, line : "The OEchalian race, in those high towers contain'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3872, line : "Where once Eurytus in proud triumph reign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3873, line : "Or where her humbler turrets Tricca rears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3874, line : "Or where Ithome, rough with rocks, appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3875, line : "In thirty sail the sparkling waves divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3876, line : "Which Podalirius and Machaon guide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3877, line : "To these his skill their parent-god imparts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3878, line : "Divine professors of the healing arts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3880, line : "The bold Ormenian and Asterian bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3881, line : "In forty barks Eurypylus commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3882, line : "Where Titan hides his hoary head in snow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3883, line : "And where Hyperia's silver fountains flow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3884, line : "Thy troops, Argissa, Polypoetes leads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3885, line : "And Eleon, shelter'd by Olympus' shades,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3886, line : "Gyrtone's warriors; and where Orthe lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3887, line : "And Oloosson's chalky cliffs arise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3888, line : "Sprung from Pirithous of immortal race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3889, line : "The fruit of fair Hippodame's embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3890, line : "(That day, when hurl'd from Pelion's cloudy head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3891, line : "To distant dens the shaggy Centaurs fled)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3892, line : "With Polypoetes join'd in equal sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3893, line : "Leonteus leads, and forty ships obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3895, line : "In twenty sail the bold Perrhaebians came"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3896, line : "From Cyphus, Guneus was their leader's name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3897, line : "With these the Enians join'd, and those who freeze"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3898, line : "Where cold Dodona lifts her holy trees;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3899, line : "Or where the pleasing Titaresius glides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3900, line : "And into Peneus rolls his easy tides;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3901, line : "Yet o'er the silvery surface pure they flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3902, line : "The sacred stream unmix'd with streams below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3903, line : "Sacred and awful! from the dark abodes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3904, line : "Styx pours them forth, the dreadful oath of gods!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3906, line : "Last, under Prothous the Magnesians stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3907, line : "(Prothous the swift, of old Tenthredon's blood;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3908, line : "Who dwell where Pelion, crown'd with piny boughs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3909, line : "Obscures the glade, and nods his shaggy brows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3910, line : "Or where through flowery Tempe Peneus stray'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3911, line : "(The region stretch'd beneath his mighty shade:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3912, line : "In forty sable barks they stemm'd the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3913, line : "Such were the chiefs, and such the Grecian train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3915, line : "Say next, O Muse! of all Achaia breeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3916, line : "Who bravest fought, or rein'd the noblest steeds?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3917, line : "Eumelus' mares were foremost in the chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3918, line : "As eagles fleet, and of Pheretian race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3919, line : "Bred where Pieria's fruitful fountains flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3920, line : "And train'd by him who bears the silver bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3921, line : "Fierce in the fight their nostrils breathed a flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3922, line : "Their height, their colour, and their age the same;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3923, line : "O'er fields of death they whirl the rapid car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3924, line : "And break the ranks, and thunder through the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3925, line : "Ajax in arms the first renown acquired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3926, line : "While stern Achilles in his wrath retired:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3927, line : "(His was the strength that mortal might exceeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3928, line : "And his the unrivall'd race of heavenly steeds:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3929, line : "But Thetis' son now shines in arms no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3930, line : "His troops, neglected on the sandy shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3931, line : "In empty air their sportive javelins throw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3932, line : "Or whirl the disk, or bend an idle bow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3933, line : "Unstain'd with blood his cover'd chariots stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3934, line : "The immortal coursers graze along the strand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3935, line : "But the brave chiefs the inglorious life deplored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3936, line : "And, wandering o'er the camp, required their lord."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3938, line : "Now, like a deluge, covering all around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3939, line : "The shining armies sweep along the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3940, line : "Swift as a flood of fire, when storms arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3941, line : "Floats the wild field, and blazes to the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3942, line : "Earth groan'd beneath them; as when angry Jove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3943, line : "Hurls down the forky lightning from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3944, line : "On Arime when he the thunder throws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3945, line : "And fires Typhoeus with redoubled blows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3946, line : "Where Typhon, press'd beneath the burning load,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3947, line : "Still feels the fury of the avenging god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3949, line : "But various Iris, Jove's commands to bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3950, line : "Speeds on the wings of winds through liquid air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3951, line : "In Priam's porch the Trojan chiefs she found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3952, line : "The old consulting, and the youths around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3953, line : "Polites' shape, the monarch's son, she chose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3954, line : "Who from Ćsetes' tomb observed the foes,(105)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3955, line : "High on the mound; from whence in prospect lay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3956, line : "The fields, the tents, the navy, and the bay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3957, line : "In this dissembled form, she hastes to bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3958, line : "The unwelcome message to the Phrygian king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3960, line : "\"Cease to consult, the time for action calls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3961, line : "War, horrid war, approaches to your walls!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3962, line : "Assembled armies oft have I beheld;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3963, line : "But ne'er till now such numbers charged a field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3964, line : "Thick as autumnal leaves or driving sand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3965, line : "The moving squadrons blacken all the strand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3966, line : "Thou, godlike Hector! all thy force employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3967, line : "Assemble all the united bands of Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3968, line : "In just array let every leader call"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3969, line : "The foreign troops: this day demands them all!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3971, line : "The voice divine the mighty chief alarms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3972, line : "The council breaks, the warriors rush to arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3973, line : "The gates unfolding pour forth all their train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3974, line : "Nations on nations fill the dusky plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3975, line : "Men, steeds, and chariots, shake the trembling ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3976, line : "The tumult thickens, and the skies resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3978, line : "Amidst the plain, in sight of Ilion, stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3979, line : "A rising mount, the work of human hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3980, line : "(This for Myrinne's tomb the immortals know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3981, line : "Though call'd Bateia in the world below;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3982, line : "Beneath their chiefs in martial order here,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3983, line : "The auxiliar troops and Trojan hosts appear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3985, line : "The godlike Hector, high above the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3986, line : "Shakes his huge spear, and nods his plumy crest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3987, line : "In throngs around his native bands repair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3988, line : "And groves of lances glitter in the air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3990, line : "Divine Ćneas brings the Dardan race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3991, line : "Anchises' son, by Venus' stolen embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3992, line : "Born in the shades of Ida's secret grove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3993, line : "(A mortal mixing with the queen of love;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3994, line : "Archilochus and Acamas divide"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3995, line : "The warrior's toils, and combat by his side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3997, line : "Who fair Zeleia's wealthy valleys till,(106)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3998, line : "Fast by the foot of Ida's sacred hill,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 3999, line : "Or drink, Ćsepus, of thy sable flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4000, line : "Were led by Pandarus, of royal blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4001, line : "To whom his art Apollo deign'd to show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4002, line : "Graced with the presents of his shafts and bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4004, line : "From rich Apaesus and Adrestia's towers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4005, line : "High Teree's summits, and Pityea's bowers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4006, line : "From these the congregated troops obey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4007, line : "Young Amphius and Adrastus' equal sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4008, line : "Old Merops' sons; whom, skill'd in fates to come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4009, line : "The sire forewarn'd, and prophesied their doom:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4010, line : "Fate urged them on! the sire forewarn'd in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4011, line : "They rush'd to war, and perish'd on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4013, line : "From Practius' stream, Percote's pasture lands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4014, line : "And Sestos and Abydos' neighbouring strands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4015, line : "From great Arisba's walls and Selle's coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4016, line : "Asius Hyrtacides conducts his host:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4017, line : "High on his car he shakes the flowing reins,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4018, line : "His fiery coursers thunder o'er the plains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4020, line : "The fierce Pelasgi next, in war renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4021, line : "March from Larissa's ever-fertile ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4022, line : "In equal arms their brother leaders shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4023, line : "Hippothous bold, and Pyleus the divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4025, line : "Next Acamas and Pyrous lead their hosts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4026, line : "In dread array, from Thracia's wintry coasts;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4027, line : "Round the bleak realms where Hellespontus roars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4028, line : "And Boreas beats the hoarse-resounding shores."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4030, line : "With great Euphemus the Ciconians move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4031, line : "Sprung from Troezenian Ceus, loved by Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4033, line : "Pyraechmes the Paeonian troops attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4034, line : "Skill'd in the fight their crooked bows to bend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4035, line : "From Axius' ample bed he leads them on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4036, line : "Axius, that laves the distant Amydon,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4037, line : "Axius, that swells with all his neighbouring rills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4038, line : "And wide around the floating region fills."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4040, line : "The Paphlagonians Pylaemenes rules,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4041, line : "Where rich Henetia breeds her savage mules,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4042, line : "Where Erythinus' rising cliffs are seen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4043, line : "Thy groves of box, Cytorus! ever green,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4044, line : "And where Ćgialus and Cromna lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4045, line : "And lofty Sesamus invades the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4046, line : "And where Parthenius, roll'd through banks of flowers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4047, line : "Reflects her bordering palaces and bowers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4049, line : "Here march'd in arms the Halizonian band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4050, line : "Whom Odius and Epistrophus command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4051, line : "From those far regions where the sun refines"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4052, line : "The ripening silver in Alybean mines."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4054, line : "There mighty Chromis led the Mysian train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4055, line : "And augur Ennomus, inspired in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4056, line : "For stern Achilles lopp'd his sacred head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4057, line : "Roll'd down Scamander with the vulgar dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4059, line : "Phorcys and brave Ascanius here unite"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4060, line : "The Ascanian Phrygians, eager for the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4062, line : "Of those who round Maeonia's realms reside,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4063, line : "Or whom the vales in shades of Tmolus hide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4064, line : "Mestles and Antiphus the charge partake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4065, line : "Born on the banks of Gyges' silent lake."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4066, line : "There, from the fields where wild Maeander flows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4067, line : "High Mycale, and Latmos' shady brows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4068, line : "And proud Miletus, came the Carian throngs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4069, line : "With mingled clamours and with barbarous tongues.(107)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4070, line : "Amphimachus and Naustes guide the train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4071, line : "Naustes the bold, Amphimachus the vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4072, line : "Who, trick'd with gold, and glittering on his car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4073, line : "Rode like a woman to the field of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4074, line : "Fool that he was! by fierce Achilles slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4075, line : "The river swept him to the briny main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4076, line : "There whelm'd with waves the gaudy warrior lies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4077, line : "The valiant victor seized the golden prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4079, line : "The forces last in fair array succeed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4080, line : "Which blameless Glaucus and Sarpedon lead"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4081, line : "The warlike bands that distant Lycia yields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4082, line : "Where gulfy Xanthus foams along the fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4088, line : "BOOK III."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4091, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4093, line : "THE DUEL OF MENELAUS AND PARIS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4095, line : "The armies being ready to engage, a single combat is agreed upon between"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4096, line : "Menelaus and Paris (by the intervention of Hector) for the determination"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4097, line : "of the war. Iris is sent to call Helen to behold the fight. She leads her"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4098, line : "to the walls of Troy, where Priam sat with his counsellers observing the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4099, line : "Grecian leaders on the plain below, to whom Helen gives an account of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4100, line : "chief of them. The kings on either part take the solemn oath for the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4101, line : "conditions of the combat. The duel ensues; wherein Paris being overcome,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4102, line : "he is snatched away in a cloud by Venus, and transported to his apartment."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4103, line : "She then calls Helen from the walls, and brings the lovers together."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4104, line : "Agamemnon, on the part of the Grecians, demands the restoration of Helen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4105, line : "and the performance of the articles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4107, line : "The three-and-twentieth day still continues throughout this book. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4108, line : "scene is sometimes in the fields before Troy, and sometimes in Troy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4109, line : "itself."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4111, line : "Thus by their leaders' care each martial band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4112, line : "Moves into ranks, and stretches o'er the land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4113, line : "With shouts the Trojans, rushing from afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4114, line : "Proclaim their motions, and provoke the war"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4115, line : "So when inclement winters vex the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4116, line : "With piercing frosts, or thick-descending rain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4117, line : "To warmer seas the cranes embodied fly,(108)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4118, line : "With noise, and order, through the midway sky;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4119, line : "To pigmy nations wounds and death they bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4120, line : "And all the war descends upon the wing,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4121, line : "But silent, breathing rage, resolved and skill'd(109)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4122, line : "By mutual aids to fix a doubtful field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4123, line : "Swift march the Greeks: the rapid dust around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4124, line : "Darkening arises from the labour'd ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4125, line : "Thus from his flaggy wings when Notus sheds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4126, line : "A night of vapours round the mountain heads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4127, line : "Swift-gliding mists the dusky fields invade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4128, line : "To thieves more grateful than the midnight shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4129, line : "While scarce the swains their feeding flocks survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4130, line : "Lost and confused amidst the thicken'd day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4131, line : "So wrapp'd in gathering dust, the Grecian train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4132, line : "A moving cloud, swept on, and hid the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4134, line : "Now front to front the hostile armies stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4135, line : "Eager of fight, and only wait command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4136, line : "When, to the van, before the sons of fame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4137, line : "Whom Troy sent forth, the beauteous Paris came:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4138, line : "In form a god! the panther's speckled hide"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4139, line : "Flow'd o'er his armour with an easy pride:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4140, line : "His bended bow across his shoulders flung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4141, line : "His sword beside him negligently hung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4142, line : "Two pointed spears he shook with gallant grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4143, line : "And dared the bravest of the Grecian race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4145, line : "As thus, with glorious air and proud disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4146, line : "He boldly stalk'd, the foremost on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4147, line : "Him Menelaus, loved of Mars, espies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4148, line : "With heart elated, and with joyful eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4149, line : "So joys a lion, if the branching deer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4150, line : "Or mountain goat, his bulky prize, appear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4151, line : "Eager he seizes and devours the slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4152, line : "Press'd by bold youths and baying dogs in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4153, line : "Thus fond of vengeance, with a furious bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4154, line : "In clanging arms he leaps upon the ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4155, line : "From his high chariot: him, approaching near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4156, line : "The beauteous champion views with marks of fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4157, line : "Smit with a conscious sense, retires behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4158, line : "And shuns the fate he well deserved to find."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4159, line : "As when some shepherd, from the rustling trees(110)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4160, line : "Shot forth to view, a scaly serpent sees,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4161, line : "Trembling and pale, he starts with wild affright"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4162, line : "And all confused precipitates his flight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4163, line : "So from the king the shining warrior flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4164, line : "And plunged amid the thickest Trojans lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4166, line : "As godlike Hector sees the prince retreat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4167, line : "He thus upbraids him with a generous heat:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4168, line : "\"Unhappy Paris! but to women brave!(111)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4169, line : "So fairly form'd, and only to deceive!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4170, line : "Oh, hadst thou died when first thou saw'st the light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4171, line : "Or died at least before thy nuptial rite!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4172, line : "A better fate than vainly thus to boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4173, line : "And fly, the scandal of thy Trojan host."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4174, line : "Gods! how the scornful Greeks exult to see"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4175, line : "Their fears of danger undeceived in thee!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4176, line : "Thy figure promised with a martial air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4177, line : "But ill thy soul supplies a form so fair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4178, line : "In former days, in all thy gallant pride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4179, line : "When thy tall ships triumphant stemm'd the tide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4180, line : "When Greece beheld thy painted canvas flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4181, line : "And crowds stood wondering at the passing show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4182, line : "Say, was it thus, with such a baffled mien,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4183, line : "You met the approaches of the Spartan queen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4184, line : "Thus from her realm convey'd the beauteous prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4185, line : "And both her warlike lords outshined in Helen's eyes?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4186, line : "This deed, thy foes' delight, thy own disgrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4187, line : "Thy father's grief, and ruin of thy race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4188, line : "This deed recalls thee to the proffer'd fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4189, line : "Or hast thou injured whom thou dar'st not right?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4190, line : "Soon to thy cost the field would make thee know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4191, line : "Thou keep'st the consort of a braver foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4192, line : "Thy graceful form instilling soft desire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4193, line : "Thy curling tresses, and thy silver lyre,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4194, line : "Beauty and youth; in vain to these you trust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4195, line : "When youth and beauty shall be laid in dust:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4196, line : "Troy yet may wake, and one avenging blow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4197, line : "Crush the dire author of his country's woe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4199, line : "His silence here, with blushes, Paris breaks:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4200, line : "\"'Tis just, my brother, what your anger speaks:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4201, line : "But who like thee can boast a soul sedate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4202, line : "So firmly proof to all the shocks of fate?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4203, line : "Thy force, like steel, a temper'd hardness shows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4204, line : "Still edged to wound, and still untired with blows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4205, line : "Like steel, uplifted by some strenuous swain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4206, line : "With falling woods to strew the wasted plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4207, line : "Thy gifts I praise; nor thou despise the charms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4208, line : "With which a lover golden Venus arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4209, line : "Soft moving speech, and pleasing outward show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4210, line : "No wish can gain them, but the gods bestow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4211, line : "Yet, would'st thou have the proffer'd combat stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4212, line : "The Greeks and Trojans seat on either hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4213, line : "Then let a midway space our hosts divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4214, line : "And, on that stage of war, the cause be tried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4215, line : "By Paris there the Spartan king be fought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4216, line : "For beauteous Helen and the wealth she brought;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4217, line : "And who his rival can in arms subdue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4218, line : "His be the fair, and his the treasure too."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4219, line : "Thus with a lasting league your toils may cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4220, line : "And Troy possess her fertile fields in peace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4221, line : "Thus may the Greeks review their native shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4222, line : "Much famed for generous steeds, for beauty more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4224, line : "He said. The challenge Hector heard with joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4225, line : "Then with his spear restrain'd the youth of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4226, line : "Held by the midst, athwart; and near the foe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4227, line : "Advanced with steps majestically slow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4228, line : "While round his dauntless head the Grecians pour"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4229, line : "Their stones and arrows in a mingled shower."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4231, line : "Then thus the monarch, great Atrides, cried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4232, line : "\"Forbear, ye warriors! lay the darts aside:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4233, line : "A parley Hector asks, a message bears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4234, line : "We know him by the various plume he wears.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4235, line : "Awed by his high command the Greeks attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4236, line : "The tumult silence, and the fight suspend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4238, line : "While from the centre Hector rolls his eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4239, line : "On either host, and thus to both applies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4240, line : "\"Hear, all ye Trojan, all ye Grecian bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4241, line : "What Paris, author of the war, demands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4242, line : "Your shining swords within the sheath restrain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4243, line : "And pitch your lances in the yielding plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4244, line : "Here in the midst, in either army's sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4245, line : "He dares the Spartan king to single fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4246, line : "And wills that Helen and the ravish'd spoil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4247, line : "That caused the contest, shall reward the toil."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4248, line : "Let these the brave triumphant victor grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4249, line : "And different nations part in leagues of peace.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4251, line : "He spoke: in still suspense on either side"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4252, line : "Each army stood: the Spartan chief replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4254, line : "\"Me too, ye warriors, hear, whose fatal right"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4255, line : "A world engages in the toils of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4256, line : "To me the labour of the field resign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4257, line : "Me Paris injured; all the war be mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4258, line : "Fall he that must, beneath his rival's arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4259, line : "And live the rest, secure of future harms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4260, line : "Two lambs, devoted by your country's rite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4261, line : "To earth a sable, to the sun a white,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4262, line : "Prepare, ye Trojans! while a third we bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4263, line : "Select to Jove, the inviolable king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4264, line : "Let reverend Priam in the truce engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4265, line : "And add the sanction of considerate age;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4266, line : "His sons are faithless, headlong in debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4267, line : "And youth itself an empty wavering state;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4268, line : "Cool age advances, venerably wise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4269, line : "Turns on all hands its deep-discerning eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4270, line : "Sees what befell, and what may yet befall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4271, line : "Concludes from both, and best provides for all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4273, line : "The nations hear with rising hopes possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4274, line : "And peaceful prospects dawn in every breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4275, line : "Within the lines they drew their steeds around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4276, line : "And from their chariots issued on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4277, line : "Next, all unbuckling the rich mail they wore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4278, line : "Laid their bright arms along the sable shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4279, line : "On either side the meeting hosts are seen"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4280, line : "With lances fix'd, and close the space between."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4281, line : "Two heralds now, despatch'd to Troy, invite"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4282, line : "The Phrygian monarch to the peaceful rite."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4284, line : "Talthybius hastens to the fleet, to bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4285, line : "The lamb for Jove, the inviolable king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4287, line : "Meantime to beauteous Helen, from the skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4288, line : "The various goddess of the rainbow flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4289, line : "(Like fair Laodice in form and face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4290, line : "The loveliest nymph of Priam's royal race:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4291, line : "Her in the palace, at her loom she found;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4292, line : "The golden web her own sad story crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4293, line : "The Trojan wars she weaved (herself the prize)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4294, line : "And the dire triumphs of her fatal eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4295, line : "To whom the goddess of the painted bow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4296, line : "\"Approach, and view the wondrous scene below!(112)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4297, line : "Each hardy Greek, and valiant Trojan knight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4298, line : "So dreadful late, and furious for the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4299, line : "Now rest their spears, or lean upon their shields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4300, line : "Ceased is the war, and silent all the fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4301, line : "Paris alone and Sparta's king advance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4302, line : "In single fight to toss the beamy lance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4303, line : "Each met in arms, the fate of combat tries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4304, line : "Thy love the motive, and thy charms the prize.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4306, line : "This said, the many-coloured maid inspires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4307, line : "Her husband's love, and wakes her former fires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4308, line : "Her country, parents, all that once were dear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4309, line : "Rush to her thought, and force a tender tear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4310, line : "O'er her fair face a snowy veil she threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4311, line : "And, softly sighing, from the loom withdrew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4312, line : "Her handmaids, Clymene and Ćthra, wait"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4313, line : "Her silent footsteps to the Scaean gate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4315, line : "There sat the seniors of the Trojan race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4316, line : "(Old Priam's chiefs, and most in Priam's grace,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4317, line : "The king the first; Thymoetes at his side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4318, line : "Lampus and Clytius, long in council tried;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4319, line : "Panthus, and Hicetaon, once the strong;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4320, line : "And next, the wisest of the reverend throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4321, line : "Antenor grave, and sage Ucalegon,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4322, line : "Lean'd on the walls and bask'd before the sun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4323, line : "Chiefs, who no more in bloody fights engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4324, line : "But wise through time, and narrative with age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4325, line : "In summer days, like grasshoppers rejoice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4326, line : "A bloodless race, that send a feeble voice."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4327, line : "These, when the Spartan queen approach'd the tower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4328, line : "In secret own'd resistless beauty's power:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4329, line : "They cried, \"No wonder such celestial charms(113)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4330, line : "For nine long years have set the world in arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4331, line : "What winning graces! what majestic mien!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4332, line : "She moves a goddess, and she looks a queen!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4333, line : "Yet hence, O Heaven, convey that fatal face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4334, line : "And from destruction save the Trojan race.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4336, line : "The good old Priam welcomed her, and cried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4337, line : "\"Approach, my child, and grace thy father's side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4338, line : "See on the plain thy Grecian spouse appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4339, line : "The friends and kindred of thy former years."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4340, line : "No crime of thine our present sufferings draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4341, line : "Not thou, but Heaven's disposing will, the cause"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4342, line : "The gods these armies and this force employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4343, line : "The hostile gods conspire the fate of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4344, line : "But lift thy eyes, and say, what Greek is he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4345, line : "(Far as from hence these aged orbs can see)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4346, line : "Around whose brow such martial graces shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4347, line : "So tall, so awful, and almost divine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4348, line : "Though some of larger stature tread the green,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4349, line : "None match his grandeur and exalted mien:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4350, line : "He seems a monarch, and his country's pride.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4351, line : "Thus ceased the king, and thus the fair replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4353, line : "\"Before thy presence, father, I appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4354, line : "With conscious shame and reverential fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4355, line : "Ah! had I died, ere to these walk I fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4356, line : "False to my country, and my nuptial bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4357, line : "My brothers, friends, and daughter left behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4358, line : "False to them all, to Paris only kind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4359, line : "For this I mourn, till grief or dire disease"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4360, line : "Shall waste the form whose fault it was to please!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4361, line : "The king of kings, Atrides, you survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4362, line : "Great in the war, and great in arts of sway:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4363, line : "My brother once, before my days of shame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4364, line : "And oh! that still he bore a brother's name!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4366, line : "With wonder Priam view'd the godlike man,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4367, line : "Extoll'd the happy prince, and thus began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4368, line : "\"O bless'd Atrides! born to prosperous fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4369, line : "Successful monarch of a mighty state!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4370, line : "How vast thy empire! Of your matchless train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4371, line : "What numbers lost, what numbers yet remain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4372, line : "In Phrygia once were gallant armies known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4373, line : "In ancient time, when Otreus fill'd the throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4374, line : "When godlike Mygdon led their troops of horse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4375, line : "And I, to join them, raised the Trojan force:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4376, line : "Against the manlike Amazons we stood,(114)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4377, line : "And Sangar's stream ran purple with their blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4378, line : "But far inferior those, in martial grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4379, line : "And strength of numbers, to this Grecian race.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4381, line : "This said, once more he view'd the warrior train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4382, line : "\"What's he, whose arms lie scatter'd on the plain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4383, line : "Broad is his breast, his shoulders larger spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4384, line : "Though great Atrides overtops his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4385, line : "Nor yet appear his care and conduct small;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4386, line : "From rank to rank he moves, and orders all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4387, line : "The stately ram thus measures o'er the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4388, line : "And, master of the flock, surveys them round.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4390, line : "Then Helen thus: \"Whom your discerning eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4391, line : "Have singled out, is Ithacus the wise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4392, line : "A barren island boasts his glorious birth;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4393, line : "His fame for wisdom fills the spacious earth.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4395, line : "Antenor took the word, and thus began:(115)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4396, line : "\"Myself, O king! have seen that wondrous man"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4397, line : "When, trusting Jove and hospitable laws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4398, line : "To Troy he came, to plead the Grecian cause;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4399, line : "(Great Menelaus urged the same request;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4400, line : "My house was honour'd with each royal guest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4401, line : "I knew their persons, and admired their parts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4402, line : "Both brave in arms, and both approved in arts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4403, line : "Erect, the Spartan most engaged our view;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4404, line : "Ulysses seated, greater reverence drew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4405, line : "When Atreus' son harangued the listening train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4406, line : "Just was his sense, and his expression plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4407, line : "His words succinct, yet full, without a fault;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4408, line : "He spoke no more than just the thing he ought."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4409, line : "But when Ulysses rose, in thought profound,(116)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4410, line : "His modest eyes he fix'd upon the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4411, line : "As one unskill'd or dumb, he seem'd to stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4412, line : "Nor raised his head, nor stretch'd his sceptred hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4413, line : "But, when he speaks, what elocution flows!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4414, line : "Soft as the fleeces of descending snows,(117)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4415, line : "The copious accents fall, with easy art;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4416, line : "Melting they fall, and sink into the heart!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4417, line : "Wondering we hear, and fix'd in deep surprise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4418, line : "Our ears refute the censure of our eyes.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4420, line : "The king then ask'd (as yet the camp he view'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4421, line : "\"What chief is that, with giant strength endued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4422, line : "Whose brawny shoulders, and whose swelling chest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4423, line : "And lofty stature, far exceed the rest?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4424, line : "\"Ajax the great, (the beauteous queen replied,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4425, line : "Himself a host: the Grecian strength and pride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4426, line : "See! bold Idomeneus superior towers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4427, line : "Amid yon circle of his Cretan powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4428, line : "Great as a god! I saw him once before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4429, line : "With Menelaus on the Spartan shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4430, line : "The rest I know, and could in order name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4431, line : "All valiant chiefs, and men of mighty fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4432, line : "Yet two are wanting of the numerous train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4433, line : "Whom long my eyes have sought, but sought in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4434, line : "Castor and Pollux, first in martial force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4435, line : "One bold on foot, and one renown'd for horse."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4436, line : "My brothers these; the same our native shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4437, line : "One house contain'd us, as one mother bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4438, line : "Perhaps the chiefs, from warlike toils at ease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4439, line : "For distant Troy refused to sail the seas;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4440, line : "Perhaps their swords some nobler quarrel draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4441, line : "Ashamed to combat in their sister's cause.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4443, line : "So spoke the fair, nor knew her brothers' doom;(118)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4444, line : "Wrapt in the cold embraces of the tomb;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4445, line : "Adorn'd with honours in their native shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4446, line : "Silent they slept, and heard of wars no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4448, line : "Meantime the heralds, through the crowded town."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4449, line : "Bring the rich wine and destined victims down."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4450, line : "Idaeus' arms the golden goblets press'd,(119)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4451, line : "Who thus the venerable king address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4452, line : "\"Arise, O father of the Trojan state!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4453, line : "The nations call, thy joyful people wait"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4454, line : "To seal the truce, and end the dire debate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4455, line : "Paris, thy son, and Sparta's king advance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4456, line : "In measured lists to toss the weighty lance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4457, line : "And who his rival shall in arms subdue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4458, line : "His be the dame, and his the treasure too."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4459, line : "Thus with a lasting league our toils may cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4460, line : "And Troy possess her fertile fields in peace:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4461, line : "So shall the Greeks review their native shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4462, line : "Much famed for generous steeds, for beauty more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4464, line : "With grief he heard, and bade the chiefs prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4465, line : "To join his milk-white coursers to the car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4466, line : "He mounts the seat, Antenor at his side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4467, line : "The gentle steeds through Scaea's gates they guide:(120)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4468, line : "Next from the car descending on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4469, line : "Amid the Grecian host and Trojan train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4470, line : "Slow they proceed: the sage Ulysses then"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4471, line : "Arose, and with him rose the king of men."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4472, line : "On either side a sacred herald stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4473, line : "The wine they mix, and on each monarch's hands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4474, line : "Pour the full urn; then draws the Grecian lord"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4475, line : "His cutlass sheathed beside his ponderous sword;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4476, line : "From the sign'd victims crops the curling hair;(121)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4477, line : "The heralds part it, and the princes share;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4478, line : "Then loudly thus before the attentive bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4479, line : "He calls the gods, and spreads his lifted hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4481, line : "\"O first and greatest power! whom all obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4482, line : "Who high on Ida's holy mountain sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4483, line : "Eternal Jove! and you bright orb that roll"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4484, line : "From east to west, and view from pole to pole!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4485, line : "Thou mother Earth! and all ye living floods!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4486, line : "Infernal furies, and Tartarean gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4487, line : "Who rule the dead, and horrid woes prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4488, line : "For perjured kings, and all who falsely swear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4489, line : "Hear, and be witness. If, by Paris slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4490, line : "Great Menelaus press the fatal plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4491, line : "The dame and treasures let the Trojan keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4492, line : "And Greece returning plough the watery deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4493, line : "If by my brother's lance the Trojan bleed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4494, line : "Be his the wealth and beauteous dame decreed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4495, line : "The appointed fine let Ilion justly pay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4496, line : "And every age record the signal day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4497, line : "This if the Phrygians shall refuse to yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4498, line : "Arms must revenge, and Mars decide the field.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4500, line : "With that the chief the tender victims slew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4501, line : "And in the dust their bleeding bodies threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4502, line : "The vital spirit issued at the wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4503, line : "And left the members quivering on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4504, line : "From the same urn they drink the mingled wine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4505, line : "And add libations to the powers divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4506, line : "While thus their prayers united mount the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4507, line : "\"Hear, mighty Jove! and hear, ye gods on high!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4508, line : "And may their blood, who first the league confound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4509, line : "Shed like this wine, disdain the thirsty ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4510, line : "May all their consorts serve promiscuous lust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4511, line : "And all their lust be scatter'd as the dust!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4512, line : "Thus either host their imprecations join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4513, line : "Which Jove refused, and mingled with the wind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4515, line : "The rites now finish'd, reverend Priam rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4516, line : "And thus express'd a heart o'ercharged with woes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4517, line : "\"Ye Greeks and Trojans, let the chiefs engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4518, line : "But spare the weakness of my feeble age:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4519, line : "In yonder walls that object let me shun,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4520, line : "Nor view the danger of so dear a son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4521, line : "Whose arms shall conquer and what prince shall fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4522, line : "Heaven only knows; for heaven disposes all.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4524, line : "This said, the hoary king no longer stay'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4525, line : "But on his car the slaughter'd victims laid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4526, line : "Then seized the reins his gentle steeds to guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4527, line : "And drove to Troy, Antenor at his side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4529, line : "Bold Hector and Ulysses now dispose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4530, line : "The lists of combat, and the ground inclose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4531, line : "Next to decide, by sacred lots prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4532, line : "Who first shall launch his pointed spear in air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4533, line : "The people pray with elevated hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4534, line : "And words like these are heard through all the bands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4535, line : "\"Immortal Jove, high Heaven's superior lord,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4536, line : "On lofty Ida's holy mount adored!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4537, line : "Whoe'er involved us in this dire debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4538, line : "O give that author of the war to fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4539, line : "And shades eternal! let division cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4540, line : "And joyful nations join in leagues of peace.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4542, line : "With eyes averted Hector hastes to turn"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4543, line : "The lots of fight and shakes the brazen urn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4544, line : "Then, Paris, thine leap'd forth; by fatal chance"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4545, line : "Ordain'd the first to whirl the weighty lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4546, line : "Both armies sat the combat to survey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4547, line : "Beside each chief his azure armour lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4548, line : "And round the lists the generous coursers neigh."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4549, line : "The beauteous warrior now arrays for fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4550, line : "In gilded arms magnificently bright:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4551, line : "The purple cuishes clasp his thighs around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4552, line : "With flowers adorn'd, with silver buckles bound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4553, line : "Lycaon's corslet his fair body dress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4554, line : "Braced in and fitted to his softer breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4555, line : "A radiant baldric, o'er his shoulder tied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4556, line : "Sustain'd the sword that glitter'd at his side:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4557, line : "His youthful face a polish'd helm o'erspread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4558, line : "The waving horse-hair nodded on his head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4559, line : "His figured shield, a shining orb, he takes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4560, line : "And in his hand a pointed javelin shakes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4561, line : "With equal speed and fired by equal charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4562, line : "The Spartan hero sheathes his limbs in arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4564, line : "Now round the lists the admiring armies stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4565, line : "With javelins fix'd, the Greek and Trojan band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4566, line : "Amidst the dreadful vale, the chiefs advance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4567, line : "All pale with rage, and shake the threatening lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4568, line : "The Trojan first his shining javelin threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4569, line : "Full on Atrides' ringing shield it flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4570, line : "Nor pierced the brazen orb, but with a bound(122)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4571, line : "Leap'd from the buckler, blunted, on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4572, line : "Atrides then his massy lance prepares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4573, line : "In act to throw, but first prefers his prayers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4575, line : "\"Give me, great Jove! to punish lawless lust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4576, line : "And lay the Trojan gasping in the dust:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4577, line : "Destroy the aggressor, aid my righteous cause,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4578, line : "Avenge the breach of hospitable laws!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4579, line : "Let this example future times reclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4580, line : "And guard from wrong fair friendship's holy name.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4581, line : "Be said, and poised in air the javelin sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4582, line : "Through Paris' shield the forceful weapon went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4583, line : "His corslet pierces, and his garment rends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4584, line : "And glancing downward, near his flank descends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4585, line : "The wary Trojan, bending from the blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4586, line : "Eludes the death, and disappoints his foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4587, line : "But fierce Atrides waved his sword, and strook"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4588, line : "Full on his casque: the crested helmet shook;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4589, line : "The brittle steel, unfaithful to his hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4590, line : "Broke short: the fragments glitter'd on the sand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4591, line : "The raging warrior to the spacious skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4592, line : "Raised his upbraiding voice and angry eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4593, line : "\"Then is it vain in Jove himself to trust?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4594, line : "And is it thus the gods assist the just?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4595, line : "When crimes provoke us, Heaven success denies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4596, line : "The dart falls harmless, and the falchion flies.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4597, line : "Furious he said, and towards the Grecian crew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4598, line : "(Seized by the crest) the unhappy warrior drew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4599, line : "Struggling he followed, while the embroider'd thong"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4600, line : "That tied his helmet, dragg'd the chief along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4601, line : "Then had his ruin crown'd Atrides' joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4602, line : "But Venus trembled for the prince of Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4603, line : "Unseen she came, and burst the golden band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4604, line : "And left an empty helmet in his hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4605, line : "The casque, enraged, amidst the Greeks he threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4606, line : "The Greeks with smiles the polish'd trophy view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4607, line : "Then, as once more he lifts the deadly dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4608, line : "In thirst of vengeance, at his rival's heart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4609, line : "The queen of love her favour'd champion shrouds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4610, line : "(For gods can all things) in a veil of clouds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4611, line : "Raised from the field the panting youth she led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4612, line : "And gently laid him on the bridal bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4613, line : "With pleasing sweets his fainting sense renews,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4614, line : "And all the dome perfumes with heavenly dews."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4615, line : "Meantime the brightest of the female kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4616, line : "The matchless Helen, o'er the walls reclined;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4617, line : "To her, beset with Trojan beauties, came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4618, line : "In borrow'd form, the laughter-loving dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4619, line : "(She seem'd an ancient maid, well-skill'd to cull"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4620, line : "The snowy fleece, and wind the twisted wool.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4621, line : "The goddess softly shook her silken vest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4622, line : "That shed perfumes, and whispering thus address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4624, line : "[Illustration: VENUS, DISGUISED, INVITING HELEN TO THE CHAMBER OF PARIS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4626, line : "VENUS, DISGUISED, INVITING HELEN TO THE CHAMBER OF PARIS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4629, line : "\"Haste, happy nymph! for thee thy Paris calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4630, line : "Safe from the fight, in yonder lofty walls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4631, line : "Fair as a god; with odours round him spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4632, line : "He lies, and waits thee on the well-known bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4633, line : "Not like a warrior parted from the foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4634, line : "But some gay dancer in the public show.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4636, line : "She spoke, and Helen's secret soul was moved;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4637, line : "She scorn'd the champion, but the man she loved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4638, line : "Fair Venus' neck, her eyes that sparkled fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4639, line : "And breast, reveal'd the queen of soft desire.(123)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4640, line : "Struck with her presence, straight the lively red"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4641, line : "Forsook her cheek; and trembling, thus she said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4642, line : "\"Then is it still thy pleasure to deceive?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4643, line : "And woman's frailty always to believe!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4644, line : "Say, to new nations must I cross the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4645, line : "Or carry wars to some soft Asian plain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4646, line : "For whom must Helen break her second vow?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4647, line : "What other Paris is thy darling now?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4648, line : "Left to Atrides, (victor in the strife,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4649, line : "An odious conquest and a captive wife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4650, line : "Hence let me sail; and if thy Paris bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4651, line : "My absence ill, let Venus ease his care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4652, line : "A handmaid goddess at his side to wait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4653, line : "Renounce the glories of thy heavenly state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4654, line : "Be fix'd for ever to the Trojan shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4655, line : "His spouse, or slave; and mount the skies no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4656, line : "For me, to lawless love no longer led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4657, line : "I scorn the coward, and detest his bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4658, line : "Else should I merit everlasting shame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4659, line : "And keen reproach, from every Phrygian dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4660, line : "Ill suits it now the joys of love to know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4661, line : "Too deep my anguish, and too wild my woe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4663, line : "[Illustration: VENUS PRESENTING HELEN TO PARIS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4665, line : "VENUS PRESENTING HELEN TO PARIS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4668, line : "Then thus incensed, the Paphian queen replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4669, line : "\"Obey the power from whom thy glories rise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4670, line : "Should Venus leave thee, every charm must fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4671, line : "Fade from thy cheek, and languish in thy eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4672, line : "Cease to provoke me, lest I make thee more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4673, line : "The world's aversion, than their love before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4674, line : "Now the bright prize for which mankind engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4675, line : "Than, the sad victim, of the public rage.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4677, line : "At this, the fairest of her sex obey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4678, line : "And veil'd her blushes in a silken shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4679, line : "Unseen, and silent, from the train she moves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4680, line : "Led by the goddess of the Smiles and Loves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4681, line : "Arrived, and enter'd at the palace gate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4682, line : "The maids officious round their mistress wait;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4683, line : "Then, all dispersing, various tasks attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4684, line : "The queen and goddess to the prince ascend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4685, line : "Full in her Paris' sight, the queen of love"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4686, line : "Had placed the beauteous progeny of Jove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4687, line : "Where, as he view'd her charms, she turn'd away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4688, line : "Her glowing eyes, and thus began to say:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4690, line : "\"Is this the chief, who, lost to sense of shame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4691, line : "Late fled the field, and yet survives his fame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4692, line : "O hadst thou died beneath the righteous sword"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4693, line : "Of that brave man whom once I call'd my lord!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4694, line : "The boaster Paris oft desired the day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4695, line : "With Sparta's king to meet in single fray:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4696, line : "Go now, once more thy rival's rage excite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4697, line : "Provoke Atrides, and renew the fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4698, line : "Yet Helen bids thee stay, lest thou unskill'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4699, line : "Shouldst fall an easy conquest on the field.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4701, line : "The prince replies: \"Ah cease, divinely fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4702, line : "Nor add reproaches to the wounds I bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4703, line : "This day the foe prevail'd by Pallas' power:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4704, line : "We yet may vanquish in a happier hour:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4705, line : "There want not gods to favour us above;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4706, line : "But let the business of our life be love:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4707, line : "These softer moments let delights employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4708, line : "And kind embraces snatch the hasty joy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4709, line : "Not thus I loved thee, when from Sparta's shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4710, line : "My forced, my willing heavenly prize I bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4711, line : "When first entranced in Cranae's isle I lay,(124)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4712, line : "Mix'd with thy soul, and all dissolved away!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4713, line : "Thus having spoke, the enamour'd Phrygian boy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4714, line : "Rush'd to the bed, impatient for the joy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4715, line : "Him Helen follow'd slow with bashful charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4716, line : "And clasp'd the blooming hero in her arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4718, line : "While these to love's delicious rapture yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4719, line : "The stern Atrides rages round the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4720, line : "So some fell lion whom the woods obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4721, line : "Roars through the desert, and demands his prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4722, line : "Paris he seeks, impatient to destroy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4723, line : "But seeks in vain along the troops of Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4724, line : "Even those had yielded to a foe so brave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4725, line : "The recreant warrior, hateful as the grave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4726, line : "Then speaking thus, the king of kings arose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4727, line : "\"Ye Trojans, Dardans, all our generous foes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4728, line : "Hear and attest! from Heaven with conquest crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4729, line : "Our brother's arms the just success have found:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4730, line : "Be therefore now the Spartan wealth restor'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4731, line : "Let Argive Helen own her lawful lord;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4732, line : "The appointed fine let Ilion justly pay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4733, line : "And age to age record this signal day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4735, line : "He ceased; his army's loud applauses rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4736, line : "And the long shout runs echoing through the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4738, line : "[Illustration: VENUS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4740, line : "VENUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4743, line : "[Illustration: Map, titled \"Graeciae Antiquae\".]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4745, line : "Map, titled \"Graeciae Antiquae\"."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4751, line : "BOOK IV."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4754, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4756, line : "THE BREACH OF THE TRUCE, AND THE FIRST BATTLE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4758, line : "The gods deliberate in council concerning the Trojan war: they agree upon"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4759, line : "the continuation of it, and Jupiter sends down Minerva to break the truce."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4760, line : "She persuades Pandarus to aim an arrow at Menelaus, who is wounded, but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4761, line : "cured by Machaon. In the meantime some of the Trojan troops attack the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4762, line : "Greeks. Agamemnon is distinguished in all the parts of a good general; he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4763, line : "reviews the troops, and exhorts the leaders, some by praises and others by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4764, line : "reproof. Nestor is particularly celebrated for his military discipline."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4765, line : "The battle joins, and great numbers are slain on both sides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4767, line : "The same day continues through this as through the last book (as it does"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4768, line : "also through the two following, and almost to the end of the seventh"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4769, line : "book). The scene is wholly in the field before Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4771, line : "And now Olympus' shining gates unfold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4772, line : "The gods, with Jove, assume their thrones of gold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4773, line : "Immortal Hebe, fresh with bloom divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4774, line : "The golden goblet crowns with purple wine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4775, line : "While the full bowls flow round, the powers employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4776, line : "Their careful eyes on long-contended Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4778, line : "When Jove, disposed to tempt Saturnia's spleen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4779, line : "Thus waked the fury of his partial queen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4780, line : "\"Two powers divine the son of Atreus aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4781, line : "Imperial Juno, and the martial maid;(125)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4782, line : "But high in heaven they sit, and gaze from far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4783, line : "The tame spectators of his deeds of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4784, line : "Not thus fair Venus helps her favour'd knight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4785, line : "The queen of pleasures shares the toils of fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4786, line : "Each danger wards, and constant in her care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4787, line : "Saves in the moment of the last despair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4788, line : "Her act has rescued Paris' forfeit life,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4789, line : "Though great Atrides gain'd the glorious strife."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4790, line : "Then say, ye powers! what signal issue waits"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4791, line : "To crown this deed, and finish all the fates!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4792, line : "Shall Heaven by peace the bleeding kingdoms spare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4793, line : "Or rouse the furies, and awake the war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4794, line : "Yet, would the gods for human good provide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4795, line : "Atrides soon might gain his beauteous bride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4796, line : "Still Priam's walls in peaceful honours grow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4797, line : "And through his gates the crowding nations flow.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4799, line : "Thus while he spoke, the queen of heaven, enraged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4800, line : "And queen of war, in close consult engaged:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4801, line : "Apart they sit, their deep designs employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4802, line : "And meditate the future woes of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4803, line : "Though secret anger swell'd Minerva's breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4804, line : "The prudent goddess yet her wrath suppress'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4805, line : "But Juno, impotent of passion, broke"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4806, line : "Her sullen silence, and with fury spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4808, line : "[Illustration: THE COUNCIL OF THE GODS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4810, line : "THE COUNCIL OF THE GODS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4813, line : "\"Shall then, O tyrant of the ethereal reign!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4814, line : "My schemes, my labours, and my hopes be vain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4815, line : "Have I, for this, shook Ilion with alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4816, line : "Assembled nations, set two worlds in arms?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4817, line : "To spread the war, I flew from shore to shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4818, line : "The immortal coursers scarce the labour bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4819, line : "At length ripe vengeance o'er their heads impends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4820, line : "But Jove himself the faithless race defends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4821, line : "Loth as thou art to punish lawless lust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4822, line : "Not all the gods are partial and unjust.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4824, line : "The sire whose thunder shakes the cloudy skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4825, line : "Sighs from his inmost soul, and thus replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4826, line : "\"Oh lasting rancour! oh insatiate hate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4827, line : "To Phrygia's monarch, and the Phrygian state!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4828, line : "What high offence has fired the wife of Jove?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4829, line : "Can wretched mortals harm the powers above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4830, line : "That Troy, and Troy's whole race thou wouldst confound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4831, line : "And yon fair structures level with the ground!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4832, line : "Haste, leave the skies, fulfil thy stern desire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4833, line : "Burst all her gates, and wrap her walls in fire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4834, line : "Let Priam bleed! if yet you thirst for more,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4835, line : "Bleed all his sons, and Ilion float with gore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4836, line : "To boundless vengeance the wide realm be given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4837, line : "Till vast destruction glut the queen of heaven!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4838, line : "So let it be, and Jove his peace enjoy,(126)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4839, line : "When heaven no longer hears the name of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4840, line : "But should this arm prepare to wreak our hate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4841, line : "On thy loved realms, whose guilt demands their fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4842, line : "Presume not thou the lifted bolt to stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4843, line : "Remember Troy, and give the vengeance way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4844, line : "For know, of all the numerous towns that rise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4845, line : "Beneath the rolling sun and starry skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4846, line : "Which gods have raised, or earth-born men enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4847, line : "None stands so dear to Jove as sacred Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4848, line : "No mortals merit more distinguish'd grace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4849, line : "Than godlike Priam, or than Priam's race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4850, line : "Still to our name their hecatombs expire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4851, line : "And altars blaze with unextinguish'd fire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4853, line : "At this the goddess rolled her radiant eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4854, line : "Then on the Thunderer fix'd them, and replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4855, line : "\"Three towns are Juno's on the Grecian plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4856, line : "More dear than all the extended earth contains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4857, line : "Mycenae, Argos, and the Spartan wall;(127)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4859, line : "These thou mayst raze, nor I forbid their fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4860, line : "'Tis not in me the vengeance to remove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4861, line : "The crime's sufficient that they share my love."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4862, line : "Of power superior why should I complain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4863, line : "Resent I may, but must resent in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4864, line : "Yet some distinction Juno might require,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4865, line : "Sprung with thyself from one celestial sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4866, line : "A goddess born, to share the realms above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4867, line : "And styled the consort of the thundering Jove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4868, line : "Nor thou a wife and sister's right deny;(128)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4869, line : "Let both consent, and both by terms comply;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4870, line : "So shall the gods our joint decrees obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4871, line : "And heaven shall act as we direct the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4872, line : "See ready Pallas waits thy high commands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4873, line : "To raise in arms the Greek and Phrygian bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4874, line : "Their sudden friendship by her arts may cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4875, line : "And the proud Trojans first infringe the peace.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4877, line : "The sire of men and monarch of the sky"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4878, line : "The advice approved, and bade Minerva fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4879, line : "Dissolve the league, and all her arts employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4880, line : "To make the breach the faithless act of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4881, line : "Fired with the charge, she headlong urged her flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4882, line : "And shot like lightning from Olympus' height."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4883, line : "As the red comet, from Saturnius sent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4884, line : "To fright the nations with a dire portent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4885, line : "(A fatal sign to armies on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4886, line : "Or trembling sailors on the wintry main,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4887, line : "With sweeping glories glides along in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4888, line : "And shakes the sparkles from its blazing hair:(129)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4889, line : "Between both armies thus, in open sight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4890, line : "Shot the bright goddess in a trail of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4891, line : "With eyes erect the gazing hosts admire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4892, line : "The power descending, and the heavens on fire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4893, line : "\"The gods (they cried), the gods this signal sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4894, line : "And fate now labours with some vast event:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4895, line : "Jove seals the league, or bloodier scenes prepares;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4896, line : "Jove, the great arbiter of peace and wars.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4898, line : "They said, while Pallas through the Trojan throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4899, line : "(In shape a mortal,) pass'd disguised along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4900, line : "Like bold Laodocus, her course she bent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4901, line : "Who from Antenor traced his high descent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4902, line : "Amidst the ranks Lycaon's son she found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4903, line : "The warlike Pandarus, for strength renown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4904, line : "Whose squadrons, led from black Ćsepus' flood,(130)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4905, line : "With flaming shields in martial circle stood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4906, line : "To him the goddess: \"Phrygian! canst thou hear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4907, line : "A well-timed counsel with a willing ear?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4908, line : "What praise were thine, couldst thou direct thy dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4909, line : "Amidst his triumph, to the Spartan's heart?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4910, line : "What gifts from Troy, from Paris wouldst thou gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4911, line : "Thy country's foe, the Grecian glory slain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4912, line : "Then seize the occasion, dare the mighty deed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4913, line : "Aim at his breast, and may that aim succeed!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4914, line : "But first, to speed the shaft, address thy vow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4915, line : "To Lycian Phoebus with the silver bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4916, line : "And swear the firstlings of thy flock to pay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4917, line : "On Zelia's altars, to the god of day.\"(131)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4919, line : "He heard, and madly at the motion pleased,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4920, line : "His polish'd bow with hasty rashness seized."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4921, line : "'Twas form'd of horn, and smooth'd with artful toil:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4922, line : "A mountain goat resign'd the shining spoil."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4923, line : "Who pierced long since beneath his arrows bled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4924, line : "The stately quarry on the cliffs lay dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4925, line : "And sixteen palms his brow's large honours spread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4926, line : "The workmen join'd, and shaped the bended horns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4927, line : "And beaten gold each taper point adorns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4928, line : "This, by the Greeks unseen, the warrior bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4929, line : "Screen'd by the shields of his surrounding friends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4930, line : "There meditates the mark; and couching low,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4931, line : "Fits the sharp arrow to the well-strung bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4932, line : "One from a hundred feather'd deaths he chose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4933, line : "Fated to wound, and cause of future woes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4934, line : "Then offers vows with hecatombs to crown"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4935, line : "Apollo's altars in his native town."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4937, line : "Now with full force the yielding horn he bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4938, line : "Drawn to an arch, and joins the doubling ends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4939, line : "Close to his breast he strains the nerve below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4940, line : "Till the barb'd points approach the circling bow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4941, line : "The impatient weapon whizzes on the wing;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4942, line : "Sounds the tough horn, and twangs the quivering string."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4944, line : "But thee, Atrides! in that dangerous hour"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4945, line : "The gods forget not, nor thy guardian power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4946, line : "Pallas assists, and (weakened in its force)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4947, line : "Diverts the weapon from its destined course:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4948, line : "So from her babe, when slumber seals his eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4949, line : "The watchful mother wafts the envenom'd fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4950, line : "Just where his belt with golden buckles join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4951, line : "Where linen folds the double corslet lined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4952, line : "She turn'd the shaft, which, hissing from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4953, line : "Pass'd the broad belt, and through the corslet drove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4954, line : "The folds it pierced, the plaited linen tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4955, line : "And razed the skin, and drew the purple gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4956, line : "As when some stately trappings are decreed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4957, line : "To grace a monarch on his bounding steed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4958, line : "A nymph in Caria or Maeonia bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4959, line : "Stains the pure ivory with a lively red;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4960, line : "With equal lustre various colours vie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4961, line : "The shining whiteness, and the Tyrian dye:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4962, line : "So great Atrides! show'd thy sacred blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4963, line : "As down thy snowy thigh distill'd the streaming flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4964, line : "With horror seized, the king of men descried"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4965, line : "The shaft infix'd, and saw the gushing tide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4966, line : "Nor less the Spartan fear'd, before he found"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4967, line : "The shining barb appear above the wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4968, line : "Then, with a sigh, that heaved his manly breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4969, line : "The royal brother thus his grief express'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4970, line : "And grasp'd his hand; while all the Greeks around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4971, line : "With answering sighs return'd the plaintive sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4973, line : "\"Oh, dear as life! did I for this agree"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4974, line : "The solemn truce, a fatal truce to thee!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4975, line : "Wert thou exposed to all the hostile train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4976, line : "To fight for Greece, and conquer, to be slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4977, line : "The race of Trojans in thy ruin join,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4978, line : "And faith is scorn'd by all the perjured line."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4979, line : "Not thus our vows, confirm'd with wine and gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4980, line : "Those hands we plighted, and those oaths we swore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4981, line : "Shall all be vain: when Heaven's revenge is slow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4982, line : "Jove but prepares to strike the fiercer blow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4983, line : "The day shall come, that great avenging day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4984, line : "When Troy's proud glories in the dust shall lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4985, line : "When Priam's powers and Priam's self shall fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4986, line : "And one prodigious ruin swallow all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4987, line : "I see the god, already, from the pole"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4988, line : "Bare his red arm, and bid the thunder roll;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4989, line : "I see the Eternal all his fury shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4990, line : "And shake his aegis o'er their guilty head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4991, line : "Such mighty woes on perjured princes wait;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4992, line : "But thou, alas! deserv'st a happier fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4993, line : "Still must I mourn the period of thy days,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4994, line : "And only mourn, without my share of praise?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4995, line : "Deprived of thee, the heartless Greeks no more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4996, line : "Shall dream of conquests on the hostile shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4997, line : "Troy seized of Helen, and our glory lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4998, line : "Thy bones shall moulder on a foreign coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 4999, line : "While some proud Trojan thus insulting cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5000, line : "(And spurns the dust where Menelaus lies,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5001, line : "'Such are the trophies Greece from Ilion brings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5002, line : "And such the conquest of her king of kings!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5003, line : "Lo his proud vessels scatter'd o'er the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5004, line : "And unrevenged, his mighty brother slain.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5005, line : "Oh! ere that dire disgrace shall blast my fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5006, line : "O'erwhelm me, earth! and hide a monarch's shame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5008, line : "He said: a leader's and a brother's fears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5009, line : "Possess his soul, which thus the Spartan cheers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5010, line : "\"Let not thy words the warmth of Greece abate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5011, line : "The feeble dart is guiltless of my fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5012, line : "Stiff with the rich embroider'd work around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5013, line : "My varied belt repell'd the flying wound.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5015, line : "To whom the king: \"My brother and my friend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5016, line : "Thus, always thus, may Heaven thy life defend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5017, line : "Now seek some skilful hand, whose powerful art"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5018, line : "May stanch the effusion, and extract the dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5019, line : "Herald, be swift, and bid Machaon bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5020, line : "His speedy succour to the Spartan king;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5021, line : "Pierced with a winged shaft (the deed of Troy),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5022, line : "The Grecian's sorrow, and the Dardan's joy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5024, line : "With hasty zeal the swift Talthybius flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5025, line : "Through the thick files he darts his searching eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5026, line : "And finds Machaon, where sublime he stands(132)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5027, line : "In arms incircled with his native bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5028, line : "Then thus: \"Machaon, to the king repair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5029, line : "His wounded brother claims thy timely care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5030, line : "Pierced by some Lycian or Dardanian bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5031, line : "A grief to us, a triumph to the foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5033, line : "The heavy tidings grieved the godlike man"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5034, line : "Swift to his succour through the ranks he ran."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5035, line : "The dauntless king yet standing firm he found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5036, line : "And all the chiefs in deep concern around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5037, line : "Where to the steely point the reed was join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5038, line : "The shaft he drew, but left the head behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5039, line : "Straight the broad belt with gay embroidery graced,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5040, line : "He loosed; the corslet from his breast unbraced;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5041, line : "Then suck'd the blood, and sovereign balm infused,(133)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5042, line : "Which Chiron gave, and Ćsculapius used."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5044, line : "While round the prince the Greeks employ their care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5045, line : "The Trojans rush tumultuous to the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5046, line : "Once more they glitter in refulgent arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5047, line : "Once more the fields are fill'd with dire alarms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5048, line : "Nor had you seen the king of men appear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5049, line : "Confused, unactive, or surprised with fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5050, line : "But fond of glory, with severe delight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5051, line : "His beating bosom claim'd the rising fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5052, line : "No longer with his warlike steeds he stay'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5053, line : "Or press'd the car with polish'd brass inlaid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5054, line : "But left Eurymedon the reins to guide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5055, line : "The fiery coursers snorted at his side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5056, line : "On foot through all the martial ranks he moves"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5057, line : "And these encourages, and those reproves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5058, line : "\"Brave men!\" he cries, (to such who boldly dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5059, line : "Urge their swift steeds to face the coming war),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5060, line : "\"Your ancient valour on the foes approve;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5061, line : "Jove is with Greece, and let us trust in Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5062, line : "'Tis not for us, but guilty Troy, to dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5063, line : "Whose crimes sit heavy on her perjured head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5064, line : "Her sons and matrons Greece shall lead in chains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5065, line : "And her dead warriors strew the mournful plains.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5067, line : "Thus with new ardour he the brave inspires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5068, line : "Or thus the fearful with reproaches fires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5069, line : "\"Shame to your country, scandal of your kind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5070, line : "Born to the fate ye well deserve to find!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5071, line : "Why stand ye gazing round the dreadful plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5072, line : "Prepared for flight, but doom'd to fly in vain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5073, line : "Confused and panting thus, the hunted deer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5074, line : "Falls as he flies, a victim to his fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5075, line : "Still must ye wait the foes, and still retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5076, line : "Till yon tall vessels blaze with Trojan fire?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5077, line : "Or trust ye, Jove a valiant foe shall chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5078, line : "To save a trembling, heartless, dastard race?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5080, line : "This said, he stalk'd with ample strides along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5081, line : "To Crete's brave monarch and his martial throng;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5082, line : "High at their head he saw the chief appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5083, line : "And bold Meriones excite the rear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5084, line : "At this the king his generous joy express'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5085, line : "And clasp'd the warrior to his armed breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5086, line : "\"Divine Idomeneus! what thanks we owe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5087, line : "To worth like thine! what praise shall we bestow?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5088, line : "To thee the foremost honours are decreed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5089, line : "First in the fight and every graceful deed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5090, line : "For this, in banquets, when the generous bowls"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5091, line : "Restore our blood, and raise the warriors' souls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5092, line : "Though all the rest with stated rules we bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5093, line : "Unmix'd, unmeasured, are thy goblets crown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5094, line : "Be still thyself, in arms a mighty name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5095, line : "Maintain thy honours, and enlarge thy fame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5096, line : "To whom the Cretan thus his speech address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5097, line : "\"Secure of me, O king! exhort the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5098, line : "Fix'd to thy side, in every toil I share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5099, line : "Thy firm associate in the day of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5100, line : "But let the signal be this moment given;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5101, line : "To mix in fight is all I ask of Heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5102, line : "The field shall prove how perjuries succeed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5103, line : "And chains or death avenge the impious deed.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5105, line : "Charm'd with this heat, the king his course pursues,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5106, line : "And next the troops of either Ajax views:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5107, line : "In one firm orb the bands were ranged around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5108, line : "A cloud of heroes blacken'd all the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5109, line : "Thus from the lofty promontory's brow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5110, line : "A swain surveys the gathering storm below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5111, line : "Slow from the main the heavy vapours rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5112, line : "Spread in dim streams, and sail along the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5113, line : "Till black as night the swelling tempest shows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5114, line : "The cloud condensing as the west-wind blows:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5115, line : "He dreads the impending storm, and drives his flock"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5116, line : "To the close covert of an arching rock."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5118, line : "Such, and so thick, the embattled squadrons stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5119, line : "With spears erect, a moving iron wood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5120, line : "A shady light was shot from glimmering shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5121, line : "And their brown arms obscured the dusky fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5123, line : "\"O heroes! worthy such a dauntless train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5124, line : "Whose godlike virtue we but urge in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5125, line : "(Exclaim'd the king), who raise your eager bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5126, line : "With great examples, more than loud commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5127, line : "Ah! would the gods but breathe in all the rest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5128, line : "Such souls as burn in your exalted breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5129, line : "Soon should our arms with just success be crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5130, line : "And Troy's proud walls lie smoking on the ground.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5132, line : "Then to the next the general bends his course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5133, line : "(His heart exults, and glories in his force);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5134, line : "There reverend Nestor ranks his Pylian bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5135, line : "And with inspiring eloquence commands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5136, line : "With strictest order sets his train in arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5137, line : "The chiefs advises, and the soldiers warms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5138, line : "Alastor, Chromius, Haemon, round him wait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5139, line : "Bias the good, and Pelagon the great."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5140, line : "The horse and chariots to the front assign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5141, line : "The foot (the strength of war) he ranged behind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5142, line : "The middle space suspected troops supply,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5143, line : "Inclosed by both, nor left the power to fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5144, line : "He gives command to \"curb the fiery steed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5145, line : "Nor cause confusion, nor the ranks exceed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5146, line : "Before the rest let none too rashly ride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5147, line : "No strength nor skill, but just in time, be tried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5148, line : "The charge once made, no warrior turn the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5149, line : "But fight, or fall; a firm embodied train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5150, line : "He whom the fortune of the field shall cast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5151, line : "From forth his chariot, mount the next in haste;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5152, line : "Nor seek unpractised to direct the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5153, line : "Content with javelins to provoke the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5154, line : "Our great forefathers held this prudent course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5155, line : "Thus ruled their ardour, thus preserved their force;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5156, line : "By laws like these immortal conquests made,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5157, line : "And earth's proud tyrants low in ashes laid.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5159, line : "So spoke the master of the martial art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5160, line : "And touch'd with transport great Atrides' heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5161, line : "\"Oh! hadst thou strength to match thy brave desires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5162, line : "And nerves to second what thy soul inspires!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5163, line : "But wasting years, that wither human race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5164, line : "Exhaust thy spirits, and thy arms unbrace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5165, line : "What once thou wert, oh ever mightst thou be!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5166, line : "And age the lot of any chief but thee.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5168, line : "Thus to the experienced prince Atrides cried;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5169, line : "He shook his hoary locks, and thus replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5170, line : "\"Well might I wish, could mortal wish renew(134)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5171, line : "That strength which once in boiling youth I knew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5172, line : "Such as I was, when Ereuthalion, slain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5173, line : "Beneath this arm, fell prostrate on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5174, line : "But heaven its gifts not all at once bestows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5175, line : "These years with wisdom crowns, with action those:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5176, line : "The field of combat fits the young and bold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5177, line : "The solemn council best becomes the old:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5178, line : "To you the glorious conflict I resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5179, line : "Let sage advice, the palm of age, be mine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5181, line : "He said. With joy the monarch march'd before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5182, line : "And found Menestheus on the dusty shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5183, line : "With whom the firm Athenian phalanx stands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5184, line : "And next Ulysses, with his subject bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5185, line : "Remote their forces lay, nor knew so far"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5186, line : "The peace infringed, nor heard the sounds of war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5187, line : "The tumult late begun, they stood intent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5188, line : "To watch the motion, dubious of the event."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5189, line : "The king, who saw their squadrons yet unmoved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5190, line : "With hasty ardour thus the chiefs reproved:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5192, line : "\"Can Peleus' son forget a warrior's part."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5193, line : "And fears Ulysses, skill'd in every art?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5194, line : "Why stand you distant, and the rest expect"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5195, line : "To mix in combat which yourselves neglect?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5196, line : "From you 'twas hoped among the first to dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5197, line : "The shock of armies, and commence the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5198, line : "For this your names are call'd before the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5199, line : "To share the pleasures of the genial feast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5200, line : "And can you, chiefs! without a blush survey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5201, line : "Whole troops before you labouring in the fray?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5202, line : "Say, is it thus those honours you requite?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5203, line : "The first in banquets, but the last in fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5205, line : "Ulysses heard: the hero's warmth o'erspread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5206, line : "His cheek with blushes: and severe, he said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5207, line : "\"Take back the unjust reproach! Behold we stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5208, line : "Sheathed in bright arms, and but expect command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5209, line : "If glorious deeds afford thy soul delight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5210, line : "Behold me plunging in the thickest fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5211, line : "Then give thy warrior-chief a warrior's due,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5212, line : "Who dares to act whate'er thou dar'st to view.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5213, line : "Struck with his generous wrath, the king replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5215, line : "\"O great in action, and in council wise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5216, line : "With ours, thy care and ardour are the same,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5217, line : "Nor need I to commend, nor aught to blame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5218, line : "Sage as thou art, and learn'd in human kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5219, line : "Forgive the transport of a martial mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5220, line : "Haste to the fight, secure of just amends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5221, line : "The gods that make, shall keep the worthy, friends.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5223, line : "He said, and pass'd where great Tydides lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5224, line : "His steeds and chariots wedged in firm array;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5225, line : "(The warlike Sthenelus attends his side;)(135)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5226, line : "To whom with stern reproach the monarch cried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5227, line : "\"O son of Tydeus! (he, whose strength could tame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5228, line : "The bounding steed, in arms a mighty name)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5229, line : "Canst thou, remote, the mingling hosts descry,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5230, line : "With hands unactive, and a careless eye?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5231, line : "Not thus thy sire the fierce encounter fear'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5232, line : "Still first in front the matchless prince appear'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5233, line : "What glorious toils, what wonders they recite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5234, line : "Who view'd him labouring through the ranks of fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5235, line : "I saw him once, when gathering martial powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5236, line : "A peaceful guest, he sought Mycenae's towers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5237, line : "Armies he ask'd, and armies had been given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5238, line : "Not we denied, but Jove forbade from heaven;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5239, line : "While dreadful comets glaring from afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5240, line : "Forewarn'd the horrors of the Theban war.(136)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5241, line : "Next, sent by Greece from where Asopus flows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5242, line : "A fearless envoy, he approach'd the foes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5243, line : "Thebes' hostile walls unguarded and alone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5244, line : "Dauntless he enters, and demands the throne."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5245, line : "The tyrant feasting with his chiefs he found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5246, line : "And dared to combat all those chiefs around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5247, line : "Dared, and subdued before their haughty lord;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5248, line : "For Pallas strung his arm and edged his sword."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5249, line : "Stung with the shame, within the winding way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5250, line : "To bar his passage fifty warriors lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5251, line : "Two heroes led the secret squadron on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5252, line : "Mason the fierce, and hardy Lycophon;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5253, line : "Those fifty slaughter'd in the gloomy vale."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5254, line : "He spared but one to bear the dreadful tale,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5255, line : "Such Tydeus was, and such his martial fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5256, line : "Gods! how the son degenerates from the sire!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5258, line : "No words the godlike Diomed return'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5259, line : "But heard respectful, and in secret burn'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5260, line : "Not so fierce Capaneus' undaunted son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5261, line : "Stern as his sire, the boaster thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5263, line : "\"What needs, O monarch! this invidious praise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5264, line : "Ourselves to lessen, while our sire you raise?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5265, line : "Dare to be just, Atrides! and confess"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5266, line : "Our value equal, though our fury less."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5267, line : "With fewer troops we storm'd the Theban wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5268, line : "And happier saw the sevenfold city fall,(137)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5269, line : "In impious acts the guilty father died;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5270, line : "The sons subdued, for Heaven was on their side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5271, line : "Far more than heirs of all our parents' fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5272, line : "Our glories darken their diminish'd name.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5274, line : "To him Tydides thus: \"My friend, forbear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5275, line : "Suppress thy passion, and the king revere:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5276, line : "His high concern may well excuse this rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5277, line : "Whose cause we follow, and whose war we wage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5278, line : "His the first praise, were Ilion's towers o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5279, line : "And, if we fail, the chief disgrace his own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5280, line : "Let him the Greeks to hardy toils excite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5281, line : "'Tis ours to labour in the glorious fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5283, line : "He spoke, and ardent, on the trembling ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5284, line : "Sprung from his car: his ringing arms resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5285, line : "Dire was the clang, and dreadful from afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5286, line : "Of arm'd Tydides rushing to the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5287, line : "As when the winds, ascending by degrees,(138)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5288, line : "First move the whitening surface of the seas,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5289, line : "The billows float in order to the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5290, line : "The wave behind rolls on the wave before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5291, line : "Till, with the growing storm, the deeps arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5292, line : "Foam o'er the rocks, and thunder to the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5293, line : "So to the fight the thick battalions throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5294, line : "Shields urged on shields, and men drove men along"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5295, line : "Sedate and silent move the numerous bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5296, line : "No sound, no whisper, but the chief's commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5297, line : "Those only heard; with awe the rest obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5298, line : "As if some god had snatch'd their voice away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5299, line : "Not so the Trojans; from their host ascends"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5300, line : "A general shout that all the region rends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5301, line : "As when the fleecy flocks unnumber'd stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5302, line : "In wealthy folds, and wait the milker's hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5303, line : "The hollow vales incessant bleating fills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5304, line : "The lambs reply from all the neighbouring hills:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5305, line : "Such clamours rose from various nations round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5306, line : "Mix'd was the murmur, and confused the sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5307, line : "Each host now joins, and each a god inspires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5308, line : "These Mars incites, and those Minerva fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5309, line : "Pale flight around, and dreadful terror reign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5310, line : "And discord raging bathes the purple plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5311, line : "Discord! dire sister of the slaughtering power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5312, line : "Small at her birth, but rising every hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5313, line : "While scarce the skies her horrid head can bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5314, line : "She stalks on earth, and shakes the world around;(139)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5315, line : "The nations bleed, where'er her steps she turns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5316, line : "The groan still deepens, and the combat burns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5318, line : "Now shield with shield, with helmet helmet closed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5319, line : "To armour armour, lance to lance opposed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5320, line : "Host against host with shadowy squadrons drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5321, line : "The sounding darts in iron tempests flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5322, line : "Victors and vanquish'd join'd promiscuous cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5323, line : "And shrilling shouts and dying groans arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5324, line : "With streaming blood the slippery fields are dyed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5325, line : "And slaughter'd heroes swell the dreadful tide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5327, line : "As torrents roll, increased by numerous rills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5328, line : "With rage impetuous, down their echoing hills"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5329, line : "Rush to the vales, and pour'd along the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5330, line : "Roar through a thousand channels to the main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5331, line : "The distant shepherd trembling hears the sound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5332, line : "So mix both hosts, and so their cries rebound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5334, line : "The bold Antilochus the slaughter led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5335, line : "The first who struck a valiant Trojan dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5336, line : "At great Echepolus the lance arrives,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5337, line : "Razed his high crest, and through his helmet drives;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5338, line : "Warm'd in the brain the brazen weapon lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5339, line : "And shades eternal settle o'er his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5340, line : "So sinks a tower, that long assaults had stood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5341, line : "Of force and fire, its walls besmear'd with blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5342, line : "Him, the bold leader of the Abantian throng,(140)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5343, line : "Seized to despoil, and dragg'd the corpse along:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5344, line : "But while he strove to tug the inserted dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5345, line : "Agenor's javelin reach'd the hero's heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5346, line : "His flank, unguarded by his ample shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5347, line : "Admits the lance: he falls, and spurns the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5348, line : "The nerves, unbraced, support his limbs no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5349, line : "The soul comes floating in a tide of gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5350, line : "Trojans and Greeks now gather round the slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5351, line : "The war renews, the warriors bleed again:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5352, line : "As o'er their prey rapacious wolves engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5353, line : "Man dies on man, and all is blood and rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5355, line : "In blooming youth fair Simoisius fell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5356, line : "Sent by great Ajax to the shades of hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5357, line : "Fair Simoisius, whom his mother bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5358, line : "Amid the flocks on silver Simois' shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5359, line : "The nymph descending from the hills of Ide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5360, line : "To seek her parents on his flowery side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5361, line : "Brought forth the babe, their common care and joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5362, line : "And thence from Simois named the lovely boy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5363, line : "Short was his date! by dreadful Ajax slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5364, line : "He falls, and renders all their cares in vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5365, line : "So falls a poplar, that in watery ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5366, line : "Raised high the head, with stately branches crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5367, line : "(Fell'd by some artist with his shining steel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5368, line : "To shape the circle of the bending wheel,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5369, line : "Cut down it lies, tall, smooth, and largely spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5370, line : "With all its beauteous honours on its head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5371, line : "There, left a subject to the wind and rain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5372, line : "And scorch'd by suns, it withers on the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5373, line : "Thus pierced by Ajax, Simoisius lies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5374, line : "Stretch'd on the shore, and thus neglected dies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5376, line : "At Ajax, Antiphus his javelin threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5377, line : "The pointed lance with erring fury flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5378, line : "And Leucus, loved by wise Ulysses, slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5379, line : "He drops the corpse of Simoisius slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5380, line : "And sinks a breathless carcase on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5381, line : "This saw Ulysses, and with grief enraged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5382, line : "Strode where the foremost of the foes engaged;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5383, line : "Arm'd with his spear, he meditates the wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5384, line : "In act to throw; but cautious look'd around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5385, line : "Struck at his sight the Trojans backward drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5386, line : "And trembling heard the javelin as it flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5387, line : "A chief stood nigh, who from Abydos came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5388, line : "Old Priam's son, Democoon was his name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5389, line : "The weapon entered close above his ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5390, line : "Cold through his temples glides the whizzing spear;(141)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5391, line : "With piercing shrieks the youth resigns his breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5392, line : "His eye-balls darken with the shades of death;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5393, line : "Ponderous he falls; his clanging arms resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5394, line : "And his broad buckler rings against the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5396, line : "Seized with affright the boldest foes appear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5397, line : "E'en godlike Hector seems himself to fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5398, line : "Slow he gave way, the rest tumultuous fled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5399, line : "The Greeks with shouts press on, and spoil the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5400, line : "But Phoebus now from Ilion's towering height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5401, line : "Shines forth reveal'd, and animates the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5402, line : "\"Trojans, be bold, and force with force oppose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5403, line : "Your foaming steeds urge headlong on the foes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5404, line : "Nor are their bodies rocks, nor ribb'd with steel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5405, line : "Your weapons enter, and your strokes they feel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5406, line : "Have ye forgot what seem'd your dread before?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5407, line : "The great, the fierce Achilles fights no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5409, line : "Apollo thus from Ilion's lofty towers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5410, line : "Array'd in terrors, roused the Trojan powers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5411, line : "While war's fierce goddess fires the Grecian foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5412, line : "And shouts and thunders in the fields below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5413, line : "Then great Diores fell, by doom divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5414, line : "In vain his valour and illustrious line."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5415, line : "A broken rock the force of Pyrus threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5416, line : "(Who from cold Ćnus led the Thracian crew,)(142)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5417, line : "Full on his ankle dropp'd the ponderous stone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5418, line : "Burst the strong nerves, and crash'd the solid bone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5419, line : "Supine he tumbles on the crimson sands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5420, line : "Before his helpless friends, and native bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5421, line : "And spreads for aid his unavailing hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5422, line : "The foe rush'd furious as he pants for breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5423, line : "And through his navel drove the pointed death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5424, line : "His gushing entrails smoked upon the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5425, line : "And the warm life came issuing from the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5427, line : "His lance bold Thoas at the conqueror sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5428, line : "Deep in his breast above the pap it went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5429, line : "Amid the lungs was fix'd the winged wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5430, line : "And quivering in his heaving bosom stood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5431, line : "Till from the dying chief, approaching near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5432, line : "The Ćtolian warrior tugg'd his weighty spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5433, line : "Then sudden waved his flaming falchion round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5434, line : "And gash'd his belly with a ghastly wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5435, line : "The corpse now breathless on the bloody plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5436, line : "To spoil his arms the victor strove in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5437, line : "The Thracian bands against the victor press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5438, line : "A grove of lances glitter'd at his breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5439, line : "Stern Thoas, glaring with revengeful eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5440, line : "In sullen fury slowly quits the prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5442, line : "Thus fell two heroes; one the pride of Thrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5443, line : "And one the leader of the Epeian race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5444, line : "Death's sable shade at once o'ercast their eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5445, line : "In dust the vanquish'd and the victor lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5446, line : "With copious slaughter all the fields are red,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5447, line : "And heap'd with growing mountains of the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5449, line : "Had some brave chief this martial scene beheld,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5450, line : "By Pallas guarded through the dreadful field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5451, line : "Might darts be bid to turn their points away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5452, line : "And swords around him innocently play;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5453, line : "The war's whole art with wonder had he seen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5454, line : "And counted heroes where he counted men."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5456, line : "So fought each host, with thirst of glory fired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5457, line : "And crowds on crowds triumphantly expired."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5459, line : "[Illustration: Map of the Plain of Troy.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5461, line : "Map of the Plain of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5467, line : "BOOK V."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5470, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5472, line : "THE ACTS OF DIOMED."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5474, line : "Diomed, assisted by Pallas, performs wonders in this day's battle."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5475, line : "Pandarus wounds him with an arrow, but the goddess cures him, enables him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5476, line : "to discern gods from mortals, and prohibits him from contending with any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5477, line : "of the former, excepting Venus. Ćneas joins Pandarus to oppose him;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5478, line : "Pandarus is killed, and Ćneas in great danger but for the assistance of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5479, line : "Venus; who, as she is removing her son from the fight, is wounded on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5480, line : "hand by Diomed. Apollo seconds her in his rescue, and at length carries"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5481, line : "off Ćneas to Troy, where he is healed in the temple of Pergamus. Mars"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5482, line : "rallies the Trojans, and assists Hector to make a stand. In the meantime"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5483, line : "Ćneas is restored to the field, and they overthrow several of the Greeks;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5484, line : "among the rest Tlepolemus is slain by Sarpedon. Juno and Minerva descend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5485, line : "to resist Mars; the latter incites Diomed to go against that god; he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5486, line : "wounds him, and sends him groaning to heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5488, line : "The first battle continues through this book. The scene is the same as in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5489, line : "the former."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5491, line : "But Pallas now Tydides' soul inspires,(143)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5492, line : "Fills with her force, and warms with all her fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5493, line : "Above the Greeks his deathless fame to raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5494, line : "And crown her hero with distinguish'd praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5495, line : "High on his helm celestial lightnings play,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5496, line : "His beamy shield emits a living ray;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5497, line : "The unwearied blaze incessant streams supplies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5498, line : "Like the red star that fires the autumnal skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5499, line : "When fresh he rears his radiant orb to sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5500, line : "And, bathed in ocean, shoots a keener light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5501, line : "Such glories Pallas on the chief bestow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5502, line : "Such, from his arms, the fierce effulgence flow'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5503, line : "Onward she drives him, furious to engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5504, line : "Where the fight burns, and where the thickest rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5506, line : "The sons of Dares first the combat sought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5507, line : "A wealthy priest, but rich without a fault;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5508, line : "In Vulcan's fane the father's days were led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5509, line : "The sons to toils of glorious battle bred;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5510, line : "These singled from their troops the fight maintain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5511, line : "These, from their steeds, Tydides on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5512, line : "Fierce for renown the brother-chiefs draw near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5513, line : "And first bold Phegeus cast his sounding spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5514, line : "Which o'er the warrior's shoulder took its course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5515, line : "And spent in empty air its erring force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5516, line : "Not so, Tydides, flew thy lance in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5517, line : "But pierced his breast, and stretch'd him on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5518, line : "Seized with unusual fear, Idaeus fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5519, line : "Left the rich chariot, and his brother dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5520, line : "And had not Vulcan lent celestial aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5521, line : "He too had sunk to death's eternal shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5522, line : "But in a smoky cloud the god of fire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5523, line : "Preserved the son, in pity to the sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5524, line : "The steeds and chariot, to the navy led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5525, line : "Increased the spoils of gallant Diomed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5527, line : "Struck with amaze and shame, the Trojan crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5528, line : "Or slain, or fled, the sons of Dares view;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5529, line : "When by the blood-stain'd hand Minerva press'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5530, line : "The god of battles, and this speech address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5532, line : "\"Stern power of war! by whom the mighty fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5533, line : "Who bathe in blood, and shake the lofty wall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5534, line : "Let the brave chiefs their glorious toils divide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5535, line : "And whose the conquest, mighty Jove decide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5536, line : "While we from interdicted fields retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5537, line : "Nor tempt the wrath of heaven's avenging sire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5539, line : "Her words allay the impetuous warrior's heat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5540, line : "The god of arms and martial maid retreat;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5541, line : "Removed from fight, on Xanthus' flowery bounds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5542, line : "They sat, and listen'd to the dying sounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5544, line : "Meantime, the Greeks the Trojan race pursue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5545, line : "And some bold chieftain every leader slew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5546, line : "First Odius falls, and bites the bloody sand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5547, line : "His death ennobled by Atrides' hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5549, line : "As he to flight his wheeling car address'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5550, line : "The speedy javelin drove from back to breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5551, line : "In dust the mighty Halizonian lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5552, line : "His arms resound, the spirit wings its way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5554, line : "Thy fate was next, O Phaestus! doom'd to feel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5555, line : "The great Idomeneus' protended steel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5556, line : "Whom Borus sent (his son and only joy)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5557, line : "From fruitful Tarne to the fields of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5558, line : "The Cretan javelin reach'd him from afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5559, line : "And pierced his shoulder as he mounts his car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5560, line : "Back from the car he tumbles to the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5561, line : "And everlasting shades his eyes surround."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5563, line : "Then died Scamandrius, expert in the chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5564, line : "In woods and wilds to wound the savage race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5565, line : "Diana taught him all her sylvan arts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5566, line : "To bend the bow, and aim unerring darts:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5567, line : "But vainly here Diana's arts he tries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5568, line : "The fatal lance arrests him as he flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5569, line : "From Menelaus' arm the weapon sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5570, line : "Through his broad back and heaving bosom went:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5571, line : "Down sinks the warrior with a thundering sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5572, line : "His brazen armour rings against the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5574, line : "Next artful Phereclus untimely fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5575, line : "Bold Merion sent him to the realms of hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5576, line : "Thy father's skill, O Phereclus! was thine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5577, line : "The graceful fabric and the fair design;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5578, line : "For loved by Pallas, Pallas did impart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5579, line : "To him the shipwright's and the builder's art."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5580, line : "Beneath his hand the fleet of Paris rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5581, line : "The fatal cause of all his country's woes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5582, line : "But he, the mystic will of heaven unknown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5583, line : "Nor saw his country's peril, nor his own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5584, line : "The hapless artist, while confused he fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5585, line : "The spear of Merion mingled with the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5586, line : "Through his right hip, with forceful fury cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5587, line : "Between the bladder and the bone it pass'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5588, line : "Prone on his knees he falls with fruitless cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5589, line : "And death in lasting slumber seals his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5591, line : "From Meges' force the swift Pedaeus fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5592, line : "Antenor's offspring from a foreign bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5593, line : "Whose generous spouse, Theanor, heavenly fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5594, line : "Nursed the young stranger with a mother's care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5595, line : "How vain those cares! when Meges in the rear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5596, line : "Full in his nape infix'd the fatal spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5597, line : "Swift through his crackling jaws the weapon glides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5598, line : "And the cold tongue and grinning teeth divides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5600, line : "Then died Hypsenor, generous and divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5601, line : "Sprung from the brave Dolopion's mighty line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5602, line : "Who near adored Scamander made abode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5603, line : "Priest of the stream, and honoured as a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5604, line : "On him, amidst the flying numbers found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5605, line : "Eurypylus inflicts a deadly wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5606, line : "On his broad shoulders fell the forceful brand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5607, line : "Thence glancing downwards, lopp'd his holy hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5608, line : "Which stain'd with sacred blood the blushing sand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5609, line : "Down sunk the priest: the purple hand of death"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5610, line : "Closed his dim eye, and fate suppress'd his breath."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5612, line : "Thus toil'd the chiefs, in different parts engaged."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5613, line : "In every quarter fierce Tydides raged;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5614, line : "Amid the Greek, amid the Trojan train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5615, line : "Rapt through the ranks he thunders o'er the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5616, line : "Now here, now there, he darts from place to place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5617, line : "Pours on the rear, or lightens in their face."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5618, line : "Thus from high hills the torrents swift and strong"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5619, line : "Deluge whole fields, and sweep the trees along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5620, line : "Through ruin'd moles the rushing wave resounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5621, line : "O'erwhelm's the bridge, and bursts the lofty bounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5622, line : "The yellow harvests of the ripen'd year,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5623, line : "And flatted vineyards, one sad waste appear!(144)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5624, line : "While Jove descends in sluicy sheets of rain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5625, line : "And all the labours of mankind are vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5627, line : "So raged Tydides, boundless in his ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5628, line : "Drove armies back, and made all Troy retire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5629, line : "With grief the leader of the Lycian band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5630, line : "Saw the wide waste of his destructive hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5631, line : "His bended bow against the chief he drew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5632, line : "Swift to the mark the thirsty arrow flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5633, line : "Whose forky point the hollow breastplate tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5634, line : "Deep in his shoulder pierced, and drank the gore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5635, line : "The rushing stream his brazen armour dyed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5636, line : "While the proud archer thus exulting cried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5638, line : "\"Hither, ye Trojans, hither drive your steeds!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5639, line : "Lo! by our hand the bravest Grecian bleeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5640, line : "Not long the deathful dart he can sustain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5641, line : "Or Phoebus urged me to these fields in vain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5642, line : "So spoke he, boastful: but the winged dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5643, line : "Stopp'd short of life, and mock'd the shooter's art."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5644, line : "The wounded chief, behind his car retired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5645, line : "The helping hand of Sthenelus required;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5646, line : "Swift from his seat he leap'd upon the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5647, line : "And tugg'd the weapon from the gushing wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5648, line : "When thus the king his guardian power address'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5649, line : "The purple current wandering o'er his vest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5651, line : "\"O progeny of Jove! unconquer'd maid!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5652, line : "If e'er my godlike sire deserved thy aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5653, line : "If e'er I felt thee in the fighting field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5654, line : "Now, goddess, now, thy sacred succour yield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5655, line : "O give my lance to reach the Trojan knight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5656, line : "Whose arrow wounds the chief thou guard'st in fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5657, line : "And lay the boaster grovelling on the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5658, line : "That vaunts these eyes shall view the light no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5660, line : "Thus pray'd Tydides, and Minerva heard,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5661, line : "His nerves confirm'd, his languid spirits cheer'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5662, line : "He feels each limb with wonted vigour light;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5663, line : "His beating bosom claim'd the promised fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5664, line : "\"Be bold, (she cried), in every combat shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5665, line : "War be thy province, thy protection mine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5666, line : "Rush to the fight, and every foe control;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5667, line : "Wake each paternal virtue in thy soul:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5668, line : "Strength swells thy boiling breast, infused by me,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5669, line : "And all thy godlike father breathes in thee;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5670, line : "Yet more, from mortal mists I purge thy eyes,(145)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5671, line : "And set to view the warring deities."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5672, line : "These see thou shun, through all the embattled plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5673, line : "Nor rashly strive where human force is vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5674, line : "If Venus mingle in the martial band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5675, line : "Her shalt thou wound: so Pallas gives command.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5677, line : "With that, the blue-eyed virgin wing'd her flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5678, line : "The hero rush'd impetuous to the fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5679, line : "With tenfold ardour now invades the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5680, line : "Wild with delay, and more enraged by pain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5681, line : "As on the fleecy flocks when hunger calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5682, line : "Amidst the field a brindled lion falls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5683, line : "If chance some shepherd with a distant dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5684, line : "The savage wound, he rouses at the smart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5685, line : "He foams, he roars; the shepherd dares not stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5686, line : "But trembling leaves the scattering flocks a prey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5687, line : "Heaps fall on heaps; he bathes with blood the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5688, line : "Then leaps victorious o'er the lofty mound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5689, line : "Not with less fury stern Tydides flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5690, line : "And two brave leaders at an instant slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5691, line : "Astynous breathless fell, and by his side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5692, line : "His people's pastor, good Hypenor, died;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5693, line : "Astynous' breast the deadly lance receives,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5694, line : "Hypenor's shoulder his broad falchion cleaves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5695, line : "Those slain he left, and sprung with noble rage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5696, line : "Abas and Polyidus to engage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5697, line : "Sons of Eurydamus, who, wise and old,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5698, line : "Could fate foresee, and mystic dreams unfold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5699, line : "The youths return'd not from the doubtful plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5700, line : "And the sad father tried his arts in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5701, line : "No mystic dream could make their fates appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5702, line : "Though now determined by Tydides' spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5704, line : "Young Xanthus next, and Thoon felt his rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5705, line : "The joy and hope of Phaenops' feeble age:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5706, line : "Vast was his wealth, and these the only heirs"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5707, line : "Of all his labours and a life of cares."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5708, line : "Cold death o'ertakes them in their blooming years,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5709, line : "And leaves the father unavailing tears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5710, line : "To strangers now descends his heapy store,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5711, line : "The race forgotten, and the name no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5713, line : "Two sons of Priam in one chariot ride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5714, line : "Glittering in arms, and combat side by side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5715, line : "As when the lordly lion seeks his food"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5716, line : "Where grazing heifers range the lonely wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5717, line : "He leaps amidst them with a furious bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5718, line : "Bends their strong necks, and tears them to the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5719, line : "So from their seats the brother chiefs are torn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5720, line : "Their steeds and chariot to the navy borne."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5722, line : "With deep concern divine Ćneas view'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5723, line : "The foe prevailing, and his friends pursued;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5724, line : "Through the thick storm of singing spears he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5725, line : "Exploring Pandarus with careful eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5726, line : "At length he found Lycaon's mighty son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5727, line : "To whom the chief of Venus' race begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5729, line : "\"Where, Pandarus, are all thy honours now,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5730, line : "Thy winged arrows and unerring bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5731, line : "Thy matchless skill, thy yet unrivall'd fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5732, line : "And boasted glory of the Lycian name?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5733, line : "O pierce that mortal! if we mortal call"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5734, line : "That wondrous force by which whole armies fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5735, line : "Or god incensed, who quits the distant skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5736, line : "To punish Troy for slighted sacrifice;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5737, line : "(Which, oh avert from our unhappy state!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5738, line : "For what so dreadful as celestial hate)?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5739, line : "Whoe'er he be, propitiate Jove with prayer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5740, line : "If man, destroy; if god, entreat to spare.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5742, line : "To him the Lycian: \"Whom your eyes behold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5743, line : "If right I judge, is Diomed the bold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5744, line : "Such coursers whirl him o'er the dusty field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5745, line : "So towers his helmet, and so flames his shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5746, line : "If 'tis a god, he wears that chief's disguise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5747, line : "Or if that chief, some guardian of the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5748, line : "Involved in clouds, protects him in the fray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5749, line : "And turns unseen the frustrate dart away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5750, line : "I wing'd an arrow, which not idly fell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5751, line : "The stroke had fix'd him to the gates of hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5752, line : "And, but some god, some angry god withstands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5753, line : "His fate was due to these unerring hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5754, line : "Skill'd in the bow, on foot I sought the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5755, line : "Nor join'd swift horses to the rapid car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5756, line : "Ten polish'd chariots I possess'd at home,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5757, line : "And still they grace Lycaon's princely dome:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5758, line : "There veil'd in spacious coverlets they stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5759, line : "And twice ten coursers wait their lord's command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5760, line : "The good old warrior bade me trust to these,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5761, line : "When first for Troy I sail'd the sacred seas;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5762, line : "In fields, aloft, the whirling car to guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5763, line : "And through the ranks of death triumphant ride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5764, line : "But vain with youth, and yet to thrift inclined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5765, line : "I heard his counsels with unheedful mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5766, line : "And thought the steeds (your large supplies unknown)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5767, line : "Might fail of forage in the straiten'd town;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5768, line : "So took my bow and pointed darts in hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5769, line : "And left the chariots in my native land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5771, line : "\"Too late, O friend! my rashness I deplore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5772, line : "These shafts, once fatal, carry death no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5773, line : "Tydeus' and Atreus' sons their points have found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5774, line : "And undissembled gore pursued the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5775, line : "In vain they bleed: this unavailing bow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5776, line : "Serves, not to slaughter, but provoke the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5777, line : "In evil hour these bended horns I strung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5778, line : "And seized the quiver where it idly hung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5779, line : "Cursed be the fate that sent me to the field"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5780, line : "Without a warrior's arms, the spear and shield!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5781, line : "If e'er with life I quit the Trojan plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5782, line : "If e'er I see my spouse and sire again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5783, line : "This bow, unfaithful to my glorious aims,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5784, line : "Broke by my hand, shall feed the blazing flames.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5786, line : "To whom the leader of the Dardan race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5787, line : "\"Be calm, nor Phoebus' honour'd gift disgrace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5788, line : "The distant dart be praised, though here we need"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5789, line : "The rushing chariot and the bounding steed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5790, line : "Against yon hero let us bend our course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5791, line : "And, hand to hand, encounter force with force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5792, line : "Now mount my seat, and from the chariot's height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5793, line : "Observe my father's steeds, renown'd in fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5794, line : "Practised alike to turn, to stop, to chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5795, line : "To dare the shock, or urge the rapid race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5796, line : "Secure with these, through fighting fields we go;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5797, line : "Or safe to Troy, if Jove assist the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5798, line : "Haste, seize the whip, and snatch the guiding rein;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5799, line : "The warrior's fury let this arm sustain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5800, line : "Or, if to combat thy bold heart incline,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5801, line : "Take thou the spear, the chariot's care be mine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5803, line : "\"O prince! (Lycaon's valiant son replied)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5804, line : "As thine the steeds, be thine the task to guide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5805, line : "The horses, practised to their lord's command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5806, line : "Shall bear the rein, and answer to thy hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5807, line : "But, if, unhappy, we desert the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5808, line : "Thy voice alone can animate their flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5809, line : "Else shall our fates be number'd with the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5810, line : "And these, the victor's prize, in triumph led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5811, line : "Thine be the guidance, then: with spear and shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5812, line : "Myself will charge this terror of the field.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5814, line : "And now both heroes mount the glittering car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5815, line : "The bounding coursers rush amidst the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5816, line : "Their fierce approach bold Sthenelus espied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5817, line : "Who thus, alarm'd, to great Tydides cried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5819, line : "\"O friend! two chiefs of force immense I see,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5820, line : "Dreadful they come, and bend their rage on thee:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5821, line : "Lo the brave heir of old Lycaon's line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5822, line : "And great Ćneas, sprung from race divine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5823, line : "Enough is given to fame. Ascend thy car!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5824, line : "And save a life, the bulwark of our war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5826, line : "At this the hero cast a gloomy look,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5827, line : "Fix'd on the chief with scorn; and thus he spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5829, line : "\"Me dost thou bid to shun the coming fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5830, line : "Me wouldst thou move to base, inglorious flight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5831, line : "Know, 'tis not honest in my soul to fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5832, line : "Nor was Tydides born to tremble here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5833, line : "I hate the cumbrous chariot's slow advance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5834, line : "And the long distance of the flying lance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5835, line : "But while my nerves are strong, my force entire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5836, line : "Thus front the foe, and emulate my sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5837, line : "Nor shall yon steeds, that fierce to fight convey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5838, line : "Those threatening heroes, bear them both away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5839, line : "One chief at least beneath this arm shall die;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5840, line : "So Pallas tells me, and forbids to fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5841, line : "But if she dooms, and if no god withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5842, line : "That both shall fall by one victorious hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5843, line : "Then heed my words: my horses here detain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5844, line : "Fix'd to the chariot by the straiten'd rein;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5845, line : "Swift to Ćneas' empty seat proceed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5846, line : "And seize the coursers of ethereal breed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5847, line : "The race of those, which once the thundering god(146)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5848, line : "For ravish'd Ganymede on Tros bestow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5849, line : "The best that e'er on earth's broad surface run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5850, line : "Beneath the rising or the setting sun."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5851, line : "Hence great Anchises stole a breed unknown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5852, line : "By mortal mares, from fierce Laomedon:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5853, line : "Four of this race his ample stalls contain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5854, line : "And two transport Ćneas o'er the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5855, line : "These, were the rich immortal prize our own,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5856, line : "Through the wide world should make our glory known.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5858, line : "Thus while they spoke, the foe came furious on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5859, line : "And stern Lycaon's warlike race begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5861, line : "\"Prince, thou art met. Though late in vain assail'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5862, line : "The spear may enter where the arrow fail'd.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5864, line : "He said, then shook the ponderous lance, and flung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5865, line : "On his broad shield the sounding weapon rung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5866, line : "Pierced the tough orb, and in his cuirass hung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5867, line : "\"He bleeds! the pride of Greece! (the boaster cries,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5868, line : "Our triumph now, the mighty warrior lies!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5869, line : "\"Mistaken vaunter! (Diomed replied;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5870, line : "Thy dart has erred, and now my spear be tried;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5871, line : "Ye 'scape not both; one, headlong from his car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5872, line : "With hostile blood shall glut the god of war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5874, line : "He spoke, and rising hurl'd his forceful dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5875, line : "Which, driven by Pallas, pierced a vital part;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5876, line : "Full in his face it enter'd, and betwixt"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5877, line : "The nose and eye-ball the proud Lycian fix'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5878, line : "Crash'd all his jaws, and cleft the tongue within,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5879, line : "Till the bright point look'd out beneath the chin."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5880, line : "Headlong he falls, his helmet knocks the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5881, line : "Earth groans beneath him, and his arms resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5882, line : "The starting coursers tremble with affright;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5883, line : "The soul indignant seeks the realms of night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5885, line : "To guard his slaughter'd friend, Ćneas flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5886, line : "His spear extending where the carcase lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5887, line : "Watchful he wheels, protects it every way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5888, line : "As the grim lion stalks around his prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5889, line : "O'er the fall'n trunk his ample shield display'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5890, line : "He hides the hero with his mighty shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5891, line : "And threats aloud! the Greeks with longing eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5892, line : "Behold at distance, but forbear the prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5893, line : "Then fierce Tydides stoops; and from the fields"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5894, line : "Heaved with vast force, a rocky fragment wields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5895, line : "Not two strong men the enormous weight could raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5896, line : "Such men as live in these degenerate days:(147)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5897, line : "He swung it round; and, gathering strength to throw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5898, line : "Discharged the ponderous ruin at the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5899, line : "Where to the hip the inserted thigh unites,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5900, line : "Full on the bone the pointed marble lights;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5901, line : "Through both the tendons broke the rugged stone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5902, line : "And stripp'd the skin, and crack'd the solid bone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5903, line : "Sunk on his knees, and staggering with his pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5904, line : "His falling bulk his bended arm sustains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5905, line : "Lost in a dizzy mist the warrior lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5906, line : "A sudden cloud comes swimming o'er his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5907, line : "There the brave chief, who mighty numbers sway'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5908, line : "Oppress'd had sunk to death's eternal shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5909, line : "But heavenly Venus, mindful of the love"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5910, line : "She bore Anchises in the Idaean grove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5911, line : "His danger views with anguish and despair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5912, line : "And guards her offspring with a mother's care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5913, line : "About her much-loved son her arms she throws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5914, line : "Her arms whose whiteness match the falling snows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5915, line : "Screen'd from the foe behind her shining veil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5916, line : "The swords wave harmless, and the javelins fail;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5917, line : "Safe through the rushing horse, and feather'd flight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5918, line : "Of sounding shafts, she bears him from the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5920, line : "Nor Sthenelus, with unassisting hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5921, line : "Remain'd unheedful of his lord's commands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5922, line : "His panting steeds, removed from out the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5923, line : "He fix'd with straiten'd traces to the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5924, line : "Next, rushing to the Dardan spoil, detains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5925, line : "The heavenly coursers with the flowing manes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5926, line : "These in proud triumph to the fleet convey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5927, line : "No longer now a Trojan lord obey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5928, line : "That charge to bold Deipylus he gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5929, line : "(Whom most he loved, as brave men love the brave,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5930, line : "Then mounting on his car, resumed the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5931, line : "And follow'd where Tydides swept the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5933, line : "Meanwhile (his conquest ravished from his eyes)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5934, line : "The raging chief in chase of Venus flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5935, line : "No goddess she, commission'd to the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5936, line : "Like Pallas dreadful with her sable shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5937, line : "Or fierce Bellona thundering at the wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5938, line : "While flames ascend, and mighty ruins fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5939, line : "He knew soft combats suit the tender dame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5940, line : "New to the field, and still a foe to fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5941, line : "Through breaking ranks his furious course he bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5942, line : "And at the goddess his broad lance extends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5943, line : "Through her bright veil the daring weapon drove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5944, line : "The ambrosial veil which all the Graces wove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5945, line : "Her snowy hand the razing steel profaned,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5946, line : "And the transparent skin with crimson stain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5947, line : "From the clear vein a stream immortal flow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5948, line : "Such stream as issues from a wounded god;(148)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5949, line : "Pure emanation! uncorrupted flood!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5950, line : "Unlike our gross, diseased, terrestrial blood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5951, line : "(For not the bread of man their life sustains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5952, line : "Nor wine's inflaming juice supplies their veins:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5953, line : "With tender shrieks the goddess fill'd the place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5954, line : "And dropp'd her offspring from her weak embrace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5955, line : "Him Phoebus took: he casts a cloud around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5956, line : "The fainting chief, and wards the mortal wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5958, line : "Then with a voice that shook the vaulted skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5959, line : "The king insults the goddess as she flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5960, line : "\"Ill with Jove's daughter bloody fights agree,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5961, line : "The field of combat is no scene for thee:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5962, line : "Go, let thy own soft sex employ thy care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5963, line : "Go, lull the coward, or delude the fair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5964, line : "Taught by this stroke renounce the war's alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5965, line : "And learn to tremble at the name of arms.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5967, line : "Tydides thus. The goddess, seized with dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5968, line : "Confused, distracted, from the conflict fled."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5969, line : "To aid her, swift the winged Iris flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5970, line : "Wrapt in a mist above the warring crew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5971, line : "The queen of love with faded charms she found."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5972, line : "Pale was her cheek, and livid look'd the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5973, line : "To Mars, who sat remote, they bent their way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5974, line : "Far, on the left, with clouds involved he lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5975, line : "Beside him stood his lance, distain'd with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5976, line : "And, rein'd with gold, his foaming steeds before."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5977, line : "Low at his knee, she begg'd with streaming eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5978, line : "Her brother's car, to mount the distant skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5979, line : "And show'd the wound by fierce Tydides given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5980, line : "A mortal man, who dares encounter heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5981, line : "Stern Mars attentive hears the queen complain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5982, line : "And to her hand commits the golden rein;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5983, line : "She mounts the seat, oppress'd with silent woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5984, line : "Driven by the goddess of the painted bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5985, line : "The lash resounds, the rapid chariot flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5986, line : "And in a moment scales the lofty skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5987, line : "They stopp'd the car, and there the coursers stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5988, line : "Fed by fair Iris with ambrosial food;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5989, line : "Before her mother, love's bright queen appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5990, line : "O'erwhelmed with anguish, and dissolved in tears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5991, line : "She raised her in her arms, beheld her bleed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5992, line : "And ask'd what god had wrought this guilty deed?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5994, line : "[Illustration: VENUS, WOUNDED IN THE HAND, CONDUCTED BY IRIS TO MARS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5996, line : "VENUS, WOUNDED IN THE HAND, CONDUCTED BY IRIS TO MARS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 5999, line : "Then she: \"This insult from no god I found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6000, line : "An impious mortal gave the daring wound!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6001, line : "Behold the deed of haughty Diomed!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6002, line : "'Twas in the son's defence the mother bled."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6003, line : "The war with Troy no more the Grecians wage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6004, line : "But with the gods (the immortal gods) engage.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6006, line : "Dione then: \"Thy wrongs with patience bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6007, line : "And share those griefs inferior powers must share:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6008, line : "Unnumber'd woes mankind from us sustain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6009, line : "And men with woes afflict the gods again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6010, line : "The mighty Mars in mortal fetters bound,(149)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6011, line : "And lodged in brazen dungeons underground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6012, line : "Full thirteen moons imprison'd roar'd in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6013, line : "Otus and Ephialtes held the chain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6014, line : "Perhaps had perish'd had not Hermes' care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6015, line : "Restored the groaning god to upper air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6016, line : "Great Juno's self has borne her weight of pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6017, line : "The imperial partner of the heavenly reign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6018, line : "Amphitryon's son infix'd the deadly dart,(150)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6019, line : "And fill'd with anguish her immortal heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6020, line : "E'en hell's grim king Alcides' power confess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6021, line : "The shaft found entrance in his iron breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6022, line : "To Jove's high palace for a cure he fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6023, line : "Pierced in his own dominions of the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6024, line : "Where Paeon, sprinkling heavenly balm around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6025, line : "Assuaged the glowing pangs, and closed the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6026, line : "Rash, impious man! to stain the bless'd abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6027, line : "And drench his arrows in the blood of gods!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6029, line : "[Illustration: OTUS AND EPHIALTES HOLDING MARS CAPTIVE.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6031, line : "OTUS AND EPHIALTES HOLDING MARS CAPTIVE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6034, line : "\"But thou (though Pallas urged thy frantic deed),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6035, line : "Whose spear ill-fated makes a goddess bleed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6036, line : "Know thou, whoe'er with heavenly power contends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6037, line : "Short is his date, and soon his glory ends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6038, line : "From fields of death when late he shall retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6039, line : "No infant on his knees shall call him sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6040, line : "Strong as thou art, some god may yet be found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6041, line : "To stretch thee pale and gasping on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6042, line : "Thy distant wife, Ćgiale the fair,(151)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6043, line : "Starting from sleep with a distracted air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6044, line : "Shall rouse thy slaves, and her lost lord deplore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6045, line : "The brave, the great, the glorious now no more!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6047, line : "This said, she wiped from Venus' wounded palm"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6048, line : "The sacred ichor, and infused the balm."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6049, line : "Juno and Pallas with a smile survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6050, line : "And thus to Jove began the blue-eyed maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6052, line : "\"Permit thy daughter, gracious Jove! to tell"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6053, line : "How this mischance the Cyprian queen befell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6054, line : "As late she tried with passion to inflame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6055, line : "The tender bosom of a Grecian dame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6056, line : "Allured the fair, with moving thoughts of joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6057, line : "To quit her country for some youth of Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6058, line : "The clasping zone, with golden buckles bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6059, line : "Razed her soft hand with this lamented wound.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6061, line : "The sire of gods and men superior smiled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6062, line : "And, calling Venus, thus address'd his child:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6063, line : "\"Not these, O daughter are thy proper cares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6064, line : "Thee milder arts befit, and softer wars;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6065, line : "Sweet smiles are thine, and kind endearing charms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6066, line : "To Mars and Pallas leave the deeds of arms.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6068, line : "Thus they in heaven: while on the plain below"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6069, line : "The fierce Tydides charged his Dardan foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6070, line : "Flush'd with celestial blood pursued his way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6071, line : "And fearless dared the threatening god of day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6072, line : "Already in his hopes he saw him kill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6073, line : "Though screen'd behind Apollo's mighty shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6074, line : "Thrice rushing furious, at the chief he strook;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6075, line : "His blazing buckler thrice Apollo shook:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6076, line : "He tried the fourth: when, breaking from the cloud,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6077, line : "A more than mortal voice was heard aloud."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6079, line : "\"O son of Tydeus, cease! be wise and see"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6080, line : "How vast the difference of the gods and thee;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6081, line : "Distance immense! between the powers that shine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6082, line : "Above, eternal, deathless, and divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6083, line : "And mortal man! a wretch of humble birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6084, line : "A short-lived reptile in the dust of earth.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6086, line : "So spoke the god who darts celestial fires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6087, line : "He dreads his fury, and some steps retires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6088, line : "Then Phoebus bore the chief of Venus' race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6089, line : "To Troy's high fane, and to his holy place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6090, line : "Latona there and Phoebe heal'd the wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6091, line : "With vigour arm'd him, and with glory crown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6092, line : "This done, the patron of the silver bow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6093, line : "A phantom raised, the same in shape and show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6094, line : "With great Ćneas; such the form he bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6095, line : "And such in fight the radiant arms he wore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6096, line : "Around the spectre bloody wars are waged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6097, line : "And Greece and Troy with clashing shields engaged."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6098, line : "Meantime on Ilion's tower Apollo stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6099, line : "And calling Mars, thus urged the raging god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6101, line : "\"Stern power of arms, by whom the mighty fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6102, line : "Who bathest in blood, and shakest the embattled wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6103, line : "Rise in thy wrath! to hell's abhorr'd abodes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6104, line : "Despatch yon Greek, and vindicate the gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6105, line : "First rosy Venus felt his brutal rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6106, line : "Me next he charged, and dares all heaven engage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6107, line : "The wretch would brave high heaven's immortal sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6108, line : "His triple thunder, and his bolts of fire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6110, line : "The god of battle issues on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6111, line : "Stirs all the ranks, and fires the Trojan train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6112, line : "In form like Acamas, the Thracian guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6113, line : "Enraged to Troy's retiring chiefs he cried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6115, line : "\"How long, ye sons of Priam! will ye fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6116, line : "And unrevenged see Priam's people die?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6117, line : "Still unresisted shall the foe destroy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6118, line : "And stretch the slaughter to the gates of Troy?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6119, line : "Lo, brave Ćneas sinks beneath his wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6120, line : "Not godlike Hector more in arms renown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6121, line : "Haste all, and take the generous warrior's part."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6122, line : "He said;--new courage swell'd each hero's heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6123, line : "Sarpedon first his ardent soul express'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6124, line : "And, turn'd to Hector, these bold words address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6126, line : "\"Say, chief, is all thy ancient valour lost?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6127, line : "Where are thy threats, and where thy glorious boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6128, line : "That propp'd alone by Priam's race should stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6129, line : "Troy's sacred walls, nor need a foreign hand?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6130, line : "Now, now thy country calls her wonted friends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6131, line : "And the proud vaunt in just derision ends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6132, line : "Remote they stand while alien troops engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6133, line : "Like trembling hounds before the lion's rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6134, line : "Far distant hence I held my wide command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6135, line : "Where foaming Xanthus laves the Lycian land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6136, line : "With ample wealth (the wish of mortals) bless'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6137, line : "A beauteous wife, and infant at her breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6138, line : "With those I left whatever dear could be:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6139, line : "Greece, if she conquers, nothing wins from me;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6140, line : "Yet first in fight my Lycian bands I cheer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6141, line : "And long to meet this mighty man ye fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6142, line : "While Hector idle stands, nor bids the brave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6143, line : "Their wives, their infants, and their altars save."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6144, line : "Haste, warrior, haste! preserve thy threaten'd state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6145, line : "Or one vast burst of all-involving fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6146, line : "Full o'er your towers shall fall, and sweep away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6147, line : "Sons, sires, and wives, an undistinguish'd prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6148, line : "Rouse all thy Trojans, urge thy aids to fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6149, line : "These claim thy thoughts by day, thy watch by night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6150, line : "With force incessant the brave Greeks oppose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6151, line : "Such cares thy friends deserve, and such thy foes.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6153, line : "Stung to the heart the generous Hector hears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6154, line : "But just reproof with decent silence bears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6155, line : "From his proud car the prince impetuous springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6156, line : "On earth he leaps, his brazen armour rings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6157, line : "Two shining spears are brandish'd in his hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6158, line : "Thus arm'd, he animates his drooping bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6159, line : "Revives their ardour, turns their steps from flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6160, line : "And wakes anew the dying flames of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6161, line : "They turn, they stand; the Greeks their fury dare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6162, line : "Condense their powers, and wait the growing war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6164, line : "As when, on Ceres' sacred floor, the swain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6165, line : "Spreads the wide fan to clear the golden grain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6166, line : "And the light chaff, before the breezes borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6167, line : "Ascends in clouds from off the heapy corn;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6168, line : "The grey dust, rising with collected winds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6169, line : "Drives o'er the barn, and whitens all the hinds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6170, line : "So white with dust the Grecian host appears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6171, line : "From trampling steeds, and thundering charioteers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6172, line : "The dusky clouds from labour'd earth arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6173, line : "And roll in smoking volumes to the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6174, line : "Mars hovers o'er them with his sable shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6175, line : "And adds new horrors to the darken'd field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6176, line : "Pleased with his charge, and ardent to fulfil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6177, line : "In Troy's defence, Apollo's heavenly will:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6178, line : "Soon as from fight the blue-eyed maid retires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6179, line : "Each Trojan bosom with new warmth he fires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6180, line : "And now the god, from forth his sacred fane,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6181, line : "Produced Ćneas to the shouting train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6182, line : "Alive, unharm'd, with all his peers around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6183, line : "Erect he stood, and vigorous from his wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6184, line : "Inquiries none they made; the dreadful day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6185, line : "No pause of words admits, no dull delay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6186, line : "Fierce Discord storms, Apollo loud exclaims,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6187, line : "Fame calls, Mars thunders, and the field's in flames."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6189, line : "Stern Diomed with either Ajax stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6190, line : "And great Ulysses, bathed in hostile blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6191, line : "Embodied close, the labouring Grecian train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6192, line : "The fiercest shock of charging hosts sustain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6193, line : "Unmoved and silent, the whole war they wait"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6194, line : "Serenely dreadful, and as fix'd as fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6195, line : "So when the embattled clouds in dark array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6196, line : "Along the skies their gloomy lines display;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6197, line : "When now the North his boisterous rage has spent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6198, line : "And peaceful sleeps the liquid element:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6199, line : "The low-hung vapours, motionless and still,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6200, line : "Rest on the summits of the shaded hill;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6201, line : "Till the mass scatters as the winds arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6202, line : "Dispersed and broken through the ruffled skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6204, line : "Nor was the general wanting to his train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6205, line : "From troop to troop he toils through all the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6206, line : "\"Ye Greeks, be men! the charge of battle bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6207, line : "Your brave associates and yourselves revere!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6208, line : "Let glorious acts more glorious acts inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6209, line : "And catch from breast to breast the noble fire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6210, line : "On valour's side the odds of combat lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6211, line : "The brave live glorious, or lamented die;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6212, line : "The wretch who trembles in the field of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6213, line : "Meets death, and worse than death, eternal shame!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6215, line : "These words he seconds with his flying lance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6216, line : "To meet whose point was strong Deicoon's chance:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6217, line : "Ćneas' friend, and in his native place"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6218, line : "Honour'd and loved like Priam's royal race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6219, line : "Long had he fought the foremost in the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6220, line : "But now the monarch's lance transpierced his shield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6221, line : "His shield too weak the furious dart to stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6222, line : "Through his broad belt the weapon forced its way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6223, line : "The grisly wound dismiss'd his soul to hell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6224, line : "His arms around him rattled as he fell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6226, line : "Then fierce Ćneas, brandishing his blade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6227, line : "In dust Orsilochus and Crethon laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6228, line : "Whose sire Diocleus, wealthy, brave and great,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6229, line : "In well-built Pherae held his lofty seat:(152)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6230, line : "Sprung from Alpheus' plenteous stream, that yields"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6231, line : "Increase of harvests to the Pylian fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6232, line : "He got Orsilochus, Diocleus he,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6233, line : "And these descended in the third degree."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6234, line : "Too early expert in the martial toil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6235, line : "In sable ships they left their native soil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6236, line : "To avenge Atrides: now, untimely slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6237, line : "They fell with glory on the Phrygian plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6238, line : "So two young mountain lions, nursed with blood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6239, line : "In deep recesses of the gloomy wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6240, line : "Rush fearless to the plains, and uncontroll'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6241, line : "Depopulate the stalls and waste the fold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6242, line : "Till pierced at distance from their native den,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6243, line : "O'erpowered they fall beneath the force of men."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6244, line : "Prostrate on earth their beauteous bodies lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6245, line : "Like mountain firs, as tall and straight as they."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6246, line : "Great Menelaus views with pitying eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6247, line : "Lifts his bright lance, and at the victor flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6248, line : "Mars urged him on; yet, ruthless in his hate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6249, line : "The god but urged him to provoke his fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6250, line : "He thus advancing, Nestor's valiant son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6251, line : "Shakes for his danger, and neglects his own;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6252, line : "Struck with the thought, should Helen's lord be slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6253, line : "And all his country's glorious labours vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6254, line : "Already met, the threatening heroes stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6255, line : "The spears already tremble in their hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6256, line : "In rush'd Antilochus, his aid to bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6257, line : "And fall or conquer by the Spartan king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6258, line : "These seen, the Dardan backward turn'd his course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6259, line : "Brave as he was, and shunn'd unequal force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6260, line : "The breathless bodies to the Greeks they drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6261, line : "Then mix in combat, and their toils renew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6263, line : "First, Pylaemenes, great in battle, bled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6264, line : "Who sheathed in brass the Paphlagonians led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6265, line : "Atrides mark'd him where sublime he stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6266, line : "Fix'd in his throat the javelin drank his blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6267, line : "The faithful Mydon, as he turn'd from fight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6268, line : "His flying coursers, sunk to endless night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6269, line : "A broken rock by Nestor's son was thrown:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6270, line : "His bended arm received the falling stone;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6271, line : "From his numb'd hand the ivory-studded reins,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6272, line : "Dropp'd in the dust, are trail'd along the plains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6273, line : "Meanwhile his temples feel a deadly wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6274, line : "He groans in death, and ponderous sinks to ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6275, line : "Deep drove his helmet in the sands, and there"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6276, line : "The head stood fix'd, the quivering legs in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6277, line : "Till trampled flat beneath the coursers' feet:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6278, line : "The youthful victor mounts his empty seat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6279, line : "And bears the prize in triumph to the fleet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6281, line : "Great Hector saw, and, raging at the view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6282, line : "Pours on the Greeks: the Trojan troops pursue:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6283, line : "He fires his host with animating cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6284, line : "And brings along the furies of the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6285, line : "Mars, stern destroyer! and Bellona dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6286, line : "Flame in the front, and thunder at their head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6287, line : "This swells the tumult and the rage of fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6288, line : "That shakes a spear that casts a dreadful light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6289, line : "Where Hector march'd, the god of battles shined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6290, line : "Now storm'd before him, and now raged behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6292, line : "Tydides paused amidst his full career;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6293, line : "Then first the hero's manly breast knew fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6294, line : "As when some simple swain his cot forsakes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6295, line : "And wide through fens an unknown journey takes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6296, line : "If chance a swelling brook his passage stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6297, line : "And foam impervious 'cross the wanderer's way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6298, line : "Confused he stops, a length of country pass'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6299, line : "Eyes the rough waves, and tired, returns at last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6300, line : "Amazed no less the great Tydides stands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6301, line : "He stay'd, and turning thus address'd his bands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6303, line : "\"No wonder, Greeks! that all to Hector yield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6304, line : "Secure of favouring gods, he takes the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6305, line : "His strokes they second, and avert our spears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6306, line : "Behold where Mars in mortal arms appears!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6307, line : "Retire then, warriors, but sedate and slow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6308, line : "Retire, but with your faces to the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6309, line : "Trust not too much your unavailing might;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6310, line : "'Tis not with Troy, but with the gods ye fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6312, line : "Now near the Greeks the black battalions drew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6313, line : "And first two leaders valiant Hector slew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6314, line : "His force Anchialus and Mnesthes found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6315, line : "In every art of glorious war renown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6316, line : "In the same car the chiefs to combat ride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6317, line : "And fought united, and united died."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6318, line : "Struck at the sight, the mighty Ajax glows"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6319, line : "With thirst of vengeance, and assaults the foes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6320, line : "His massy spear with matchless fury sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6321, line : "Through Amphius' belt and heaving belly went;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6322, line : "Amphius Apaesus' happy soil possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6323, line : "With herds abounding, and with treasure bless'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6324, line : "But fate resistless from his country led"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6325, line : "The chief, to perish at his people's head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6326, line : "Shook with his fall his brazen armour rung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6327, line : "And fierce, to seize it, conquering Ajax sprung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6328, line : "Around his head an iron tempest rain'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6329, line : "A wood of spears his ample shield sustain'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6330, line : "Beneath one foot the yet warm corpse he press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6331, line : "And drew his javelin from the bleeding breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6332, line : "He could no more; the showering darts denied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6333, line : "To spoil his glittering arms, and plumy pride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6334, line : "Now foes on foes came pouring on the fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6335, line : "With bristling lances, and compacted shields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6336, line : "Till in the steely circle straiten'd round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6337, line : "Forced he gives way, and sternly quits the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6339, line : "While thus they strive, Tlepolemus the great,(153)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6340, line : "Urged by the force of unresisted fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6341, line : "Burns with desire Sarpedon's strength to prove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6342, line : "Alcides' offspring meets the son of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6343, line : "Sheathed in bright arms each adverse chief came on."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6344, line : "Jove's great descendant, and his greater son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6345, line : "Prepared for combat, ere the lance he toss'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6346, line : "The daring Rhodian vents his haughty boast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6348, line : "\"What brings this Lycian counsellor so far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6349, line : "To tremble at our arms, not mix in war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6350, line : "Know thy vain self, nor let their flattery move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6351, line : "Who style thee son of cloud-compelling Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6352, line : "How far unlike those chiefs of race divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6353, line : "How vast the difference of their deeds and thine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6354, line : "Jove got such heroes as my sire, whose soul"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6355, line : "No fear could daunt, nor earth nor hell control."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6356, line : "Troy felt his arm, and yon proud ramparts stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6357, line : "Raised on the ruins of his vengeful hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6358, line : "With six small ships, and but a slender train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6359, line : "He left the town a wide-deserted plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6360, line : "But what art thou, who deedless look'st around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6361, line : "While unrevenged thy Lycians bite the ground!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6362, line : "Small aid to Troy thy feeble force can be;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6363, line : "But wert thou greater, thou must yield to me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6364, line : "Pierced by my spear, to endless darkness go!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6365, line : "I make this present to the shades below.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6367, line : "The son of Hercules, the Rhodian guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6368, line : "Thus haughty spoke. The Lycian king replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6370, line : "\"Thy sire, O prince! o'erturn'd the Trojan state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6371, line : "Whose perjured monarch well deserved his fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6372, line : "Those heavenly steeds the hero sought so far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6373, line : "False he detain'd, the just reward of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6374, line : "Nor so content, the generous chief defied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6375, line : "With base reproaches and unmanly pride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6376, line : "But you, unworthy the high race you boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6377, line : "Shall raise my glory when thy own is lost:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6378, line : "Now meet thy fate, and by Sarpedon slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6379, line : "Add one more ghost to Pluto's gloomy reign.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6381, line : "He said: both javelins at an instant flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6382, line : "Both struck, both wounded, but Sarpedon's slew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6383, line : "Full in the boaster's neck the weapon stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6384, line : "Transfix'd his throat, and drank the vital blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6385, line : "The soul disdainful seeks the caves of night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6386, line : "And his seal'd eyes for ever lose the light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6388, line : "Yet not in vain, Tlepolemus, was thrown"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6389, line : "Thy angry lance; which piercing to the bone"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6390, line : "Sarpedon's thigh, had robb'd the chief of breath;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6391, line : "But Jove was present, and forbade the death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6392, line : "Borne from the conflict by his Lycian throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6393, line : "The wounded hero dragg'd the lance along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6394, line : "(His friends, each busied in his several part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6395, line : "Through haste, or danger, had not drawn the dart.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6396, line : "The Greeks with slain Tlepolemus retired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6397, line : "Whose fall Ulysses view'd, with fury fired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6398, line : "Doubtful if Jove's great son he should pursue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6399, line : "Or pour his vengeance on the Lycian crew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6400, line : "But heaven and fate the first design withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6401, line : "Nor this great death must grace Ulysses' hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6402, line : "Minerva drives him on the Lycian train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6403, line : "Alastor, Cronius, Halius, strew'd the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6404, line : "Alcander, Prytanis, Noemon fell:(154)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6405, line : "And numbers more his sword had sent to hell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6406, line : "But Hector saw; and, furious at the sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6407, line : "Rush'd terrible amidst the ranks of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6408, line : "With joy Sarpedon view'd the wish'd relief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6409, line : "And, faint, lamenting, thus implored the chief:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6411, line : "\"O suffer not the foe to bear away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6412, line : "My helpless corpse, an unassisted prey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6413, line : "If I, unbless'd, must see my son no more,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6414, line : "My much-loved consort, and my native shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6415, line : "Yet let me die in Ilion's sacred wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6416, line : "Troy, in whose cause I fell, shall mourn my fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6418, line : "He said, nor Hector to the chief replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6419, line : "But shakes his plume, and fierce to combat flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6420, line : "Swift as a whirlwind, drives the scattering foes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6421, line : "And dyes the ground with purple as he goes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6423, line : "Beneath a beech, Jove's consecrated shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6424, line : "His mournful friends divine Sarpedon laid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6425, line : "Brave Pelagon, his favourite chief, was nigh,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6426, line : "Who wrench'd the javelin from his sinewy thigh."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6427, line : "The fainting soul stood ready wing'd for flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6428, line : "And o'er his eye-balls swam the shades of night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6429, line : "But Boreas rising fresh, with gentle breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6430, line : "Recall'd his spirit from the gates of death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6432, line : "The generous Greeks recede with tardy pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6433, line : "Though Mars and Hector thunder in their face;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6434, line : "None turn their backs to mean ignoble flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6435, line : "Slow they retreat, and even retreating fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6436, line : "Who first, who last, by Mars' and Hector's hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6437, line : "Stretch'd in their blood, lay gasping on the sand?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6438, line : "Tenthras the great, Orestes the renown'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6439, line : "For managed steeds, and Trechus press'd the ground;,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6440, line : "Next OEnomaus and OEnops' offspring died;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6441, line : "Oresbius last fell groaning at their side:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6442, line : "Oresbius, in his painted mitre gay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6443, line : "In fat Boeotia held his wealthy sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6444, line : "Where lakes surround low Hyle's watery plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6445, line : "A prince and people studious of their gain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6447, line : "The carnage Juno from the skies survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6448, line : "And touch'd with grief bespoke the blue-eyed maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6449, line : "\"Oh, sight accursed! Shall faithless Troy prevail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6450, line : "And shall our promise to our people fail?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6451, line : "How vain the word to Menelaus given"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6452, line : "By Jove's great daughter and the queen of heaven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6453, line : "Beneath his arms that Priam's towers should fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6454, line : "If warring gods for ever guard the wall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6455, line : "Mars, red with slaughter, aids our hated foes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6456, line : "Haste, let us arm, and force with force oppose!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6458, line : "She spoke; Minerva burns to meet the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6459, line : "And now heaven's empress calls her blazing car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6460, line : "At her command rush forth the steeds divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6461, line : "Rich with immortal gold their trappings shine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6462, line : "Bright Hebe waits; by Hebe, ever young,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6463, line : "The whirling wheels are to the chariot hung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6464, line : "On the bright axle turns the bidden wheel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6465, line : "Of sounding brass; the polished axle steel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6466, line : "Eight brazen spokes in radiant order flame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6467, line : "The circles gold, of uncorrupted frame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6468, line : "Such as the heavens produce: and round the gold"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6469, line : "Two brazen rings of work divine were roll'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6470, line : "The bossy naves of sold silver shone;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6471, line : "Braces of gold suspend the moving throne:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6472, line : "The car, behind, an arching figure bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6473, line : "The bending concave form'd an arch before."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6474, line : "Silver the beam, the extended yoke was gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6475, line : "And golden reins the immortal coursers hold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6476, line : "Herself, impatient, to the ready car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6477, line : "The coursers joins, and breathes revenge and war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6479, line : "Pallas disrobes; her radiant veil untied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6480, line : "With flowers adorn'd, with art diversified,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6481, line : "(The laboured veil her heavenly fingers wove,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6482, line : "Flows on the pavement of the court of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6483, line : "Now heaven's dread arms her mighty limbs invest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6484, line : "Jove's cuirass blazes on her ample breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6485, line : "Deck'd in sad triumph for the mournful field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6486, line : "O'er her broad shoulders hangs his horrid shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6487, line : "Dire, black, tremendous! Round the margin roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6488, line : "A fringe of serpents hissing guards the gold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6489, line : "Here all the terrors of grim War appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6490, line : "Here rages Force, here tremble Flight and Fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6491, line : "Here storm'd Contention, and here Fury frown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6492, line : "And the dire orb portentous Gorgon crown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6493, line : "The massy golden helm she next assumes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6494, line : "That dreadful nods with four o'ershading plumes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6495, line : "So vast, the broad circumference contains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6496, line : "A hundred armies on a hundred plains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6497, line : "The goddess thus the imperial car ascends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6498, line : "Shook by her arm the mighty javelin bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6499, line : "Ponderous and huge; that when her fury burns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6500, line : "Proud tyrants humbles, and whole hosts o'erturns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6502, line : "Swift at the scourge the ethereal coursers fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6503, line : "While the smooth chariot cuts the liquid sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6504, line : "Heaven's gates spontaneous open to the powers,(155)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6505, line : "Heaven's golden gates, kept by the winged Hours;(156)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6506, line : "Commission'd in alternate watch they stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6507, line : "The sun's bright portals and the skies command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6508, line : "Involve in clouds the eternal gates of day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6509, line : "Or the dark barrier roll with ease away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6510, line : "The sounding hinges ring on either side"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6511, line : "The gloomy volumes, pierced with light, divide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6512, line : "The chariot mounts, where deep in ambient skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6513, line : "Confused, Olympus' hundred heads arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6514, line : "Where far apart the Thunderer fills his throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6515, line : "O'er all the gods superior and alone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6516, line : "There with her snowy hand the queen restrains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6517, line : "The fiery steeds, and thus to Jove complains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6519, line : "\"O sire! can no resentment touch thy soul?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6520, line : "Can Mars rebel, and does no thunder roll?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6521, line : "What lawless rage on yon forbidden plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6522, line : "What rash destruction! and what heroes slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6523, line : "Venus, and Phoebus with the dreadful bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6524, line : "Smile on the slaughter, and enjoy my woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6525, line : "Mad, furious power! whose unrelenting mind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6526, line : "No god can govern, and no justice bind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6527, line : "Say, mighty father! shall we scourge this pride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6528, line : "And drive from fight the impetuous homicide?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6530, line : "To whom assenting, thus the Thunderer said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6531, line : "\"Go! and the great Minerva be thy aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6532, line : "To tame the monster-god Minerva knows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6533, line : "And oft afflicts his brutal breast with woes.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6535, line : "He said; Saturnia, ardent to obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6536, line : "Lash'd her white steeds along the aerial way"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6537, line : "Swift down the steep of heaven the chariot rolls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6538, line : "Between the expanded earth and starry poles"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6539, line : "Far as a shepherd, from some point on high,(157)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6540, line : "O'er the wide main extends his boundless eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6541, line : "Through such a space of air, with thundering sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6542, line : "At every leap the immortal coursers bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6543, line : "Troy now they reach'd and touch'd those banks divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6544, line : "Where silver Simois and Scamander join"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6545, line : "There Juno stopp'd, and (her fair steeds unloosed)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6546, line : "Of air condensed a vapour circumfused"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6547, line : "For these, impregnate with celestial dew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6548, line : "On Simois, brink ambrosial herbage grew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6549, line : "Thence to relieve the fainting Argive throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6550, line : "Smooth as the sailing doves they glide along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6552, line : "The best and bravest of the Grecian band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6553, line : "(A warlike circle) round Tydides stand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6554, line : "Such was their look as lions bathed in blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6555, line : "Or foaming boars, the terror of the wood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6556, line : "Heaven's empress mingles with the mortal crowd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6557, line : "And shouts, in Stentor's sounding voice, aloud;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6558, line : "Stentor the strong, endued with brazen lungs,(158)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6559, line : "Whose throats surpass'd the force of fifty tongues."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6561, line : "\"Inglorious Argives! to your race a shame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6562, line : "And only men in figure and in name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6563, line : "Once from the walls your timorous foes engaged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6564, line : "While fierce in war divine Achilles raged;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6565, line : "Now issuing fearless they possess the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6566, line : "Now win the shores, and scarce the seas remain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6568, line : "Her speech new fury to their hearts convey'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6569, line : "While near Tydides stood the Athenian maid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6570, line : "The king beside his panting steeds she found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6571, line : "O'erspent with toil reposing on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6572, line : "To cool his glowing wound he sat apart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6573, line : "(The wound inflicted by the Lycian dart.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6574, line : "Large drops of sweat from all his limbs descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6575, line : "Beneath his ponderous shield his sinews bend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6576, line : "Whose ample belt, that o'er his shoulder lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6577, line : "He eased; and wash'd the clotted gore away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6578, line : "The goddess leaning o'er the bending yoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6579, line : "Beside his coursers, thus her silence broke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6581, line : "\"Degenerate prince! and not of Tydeus' kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6582, line : "Whose little body lodged a mighty mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6583, line : "Foremost he press'd in glorious toils to share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6584, line : "And scarce refrain'd when I forbade the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6585, line : "Alone, unguarded, once he dared to go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6586, line : "And feast, incircled by the Theban foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6587, line : "There braved, and vanquish'd, many a hardy knight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6588, line : "Such nerves I gave him, and such force in fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6589, line : "Thou too no less hast been my constant care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6590, line : "Thy hands I arm'd, and sent thee forth to war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6591, line : "But thee or fear deters, or sloth detains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6592, line : "No drop of all thy father warms thy veins.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6594, line : "The chief thus answered mild: \"Immortal maid!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6595, line : "I own thy presence, and confess thy aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6596, line : "Not fear, thou know'st, withholds me from the plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6597, line : "Nor sloth hath seized me, but thy word restrains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6598, line : "From warring gods thou bad'st me turn my spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6599, line : "And Venus only found resistance here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6600, line : "Hence, goddess! heedful of thy high commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6601, line : "Loth I gave way, and warn'd our Argive bands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6602, line : "For Mars, the homicide, these eyes beheld,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6603, line : "With slaughter red, and raging round the field.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6605, line : "Then thus Minerva:--\"Brave Tydides, hear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6606, line : "Not Mars himself, nor aught immortal, fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6607, line : "Full on the god impel thy foaming horse:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6608, line : "Pallas commands, and Pallas lends thee force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6609, line : "Rash, furious, blind, from these to those he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6610, line : "And every side of wavering combat tries;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6611, line : "Large promise makes, and breaks the promise made:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6612, line : "Now gives the Grecians, now the Trojans aid.\"(159)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6614, line : "She said, and to the steeds approaching near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6615, line : "Drew from his seat the martial charioteer."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6616, line : "The vigorous power the trembling car ascends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6617, line : "Fierce for revenge; and Diomed attends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6618, line : "The groaning axle bent beneath the load;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6619, line : "So great a hero, and so great a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6620, line : "She snatch'd the reins, she lash'd with all her force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6621, line : "And full on Mars impelled the foaming horse:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6622, line : "But first, to hide her heavenly visage, spread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6623, line : "Black Orcus' helmet o'er her radiant head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6625, line : "[Illustration: DIOMED CASTING HIS SPEAR AT MARS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6627, line : "DIOMED CASTING HIS SPEAR AT MARS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6630, line : "Just then gigantic Periphas lay slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6631, line : "The strongest warrior of the Ćtolian train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6632, line : "The god, who slew him, leaves his prostrate prize"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6633, line : "Stretch'd where he fell, and at Tydides flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6634, line : "Now rushing fierce, in equal arms appear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6635, line : "The daring Greek, the dreadful god of war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6636, line : "Full at the chief, above his courser's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6637, line : "From Mars's arm the enormous weapon fled:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6638, line : "Pallas opposed her hand, and caused to glance"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6639, line : "Far from the car the strong immortal lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6640, line : "Then threw the force of Tydeus' warlike son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6641, line : "The javelin hiss'd; the goddess urged it on:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6642, line : "Where the broad cincture girt his armour round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6643, line : "It pierced the god: his groin received the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6644, line : "From the rent skin the warrior tugs again"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6645, line : "The smoking steel. Mars bellows with the pain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6646, line : "Loud as the roar encountering armies yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6647, line : "When shouting millions shake the thundering field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6648, line : "Both armies start, and trembling gaze around;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6649, line : "And earth and heaven re-bellow to the sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6650, line : "As vapours blown by Auster's sultry breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6651, line : "Pregnant with plagues, and shedding seeds of death,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6652, line : "Beneath the rage of burning Sirius rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6653, line : "Choke the parch'd earth, and blacken all the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6654, line : "In such a cloud the god from combat driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6655, line : "High o'er the dusky whirlwind scales the heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6656, line : "Wild with his pain, he sought the bright abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6657, line : "There sullen sat beneath the sire of gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6658, line : "Show'd the celestial blood, and with a groan"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6659, line : "Thus pour'd his plaints before the immortal throne:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6661, line : "\"Can Jove, supine, flagitious facts survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6662, line : "And brook the furies of this daring day?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6663, line : "For mortal men celestial powers engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6664, line : "And gods on gods exert eternal rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6665, line : "From thee, O father! all these ills we bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6666, line : "And thy fell daughter with the shield and spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6667, line : "Thou gavest that fury to the realms of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6668, line : "Pernicious, wild, regardless of the right."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6669, line : "All heaven beside reveres thy sovereign sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6670, line : "Thy voice we hear, and thy behests obey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6671, line : "'Tis hers to offend, and even offending share"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6672, line : "Thy breast, thy counsels, thy distinguish'd care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6673, line : "So boundless she, and thou so partial grown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6674, line : "Well may we deem the wondrous birth thy own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6675, line : "Now frantic Diomed, at her command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6676, line : "Against the immortals lifts his raging hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6677, line : "The heavenly Venus first his fury found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6678, line : "Me next encountering, me he dared to wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6679, line : "Vanquish'd I fled; even I, the god of fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6680, line : "From mortal madness scarce was saved by flight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6681, line : "Else hadst thou seen me sink on yonder plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6682, line : "Heap'd round, and heaving under loads of slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6683, line : "Or pierced with Grecian darts, for ages lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6684, line : "Condemn'd to pain, though fated not to die.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6686, line : "Him thus upbraiding, with a wrathful look"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6687, line : "The lord of thunders view'd, and stern bespoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6688, line : "\"To me, perfidious! this lamenting strain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6689, line : "Of lawless force shall lawless Mars complain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6690, line : "Of all the gods who tread the spangled skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6691, line : "Thou most unjust, most odious in our eyes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6692, line : "Inhuman discord is thy dire delight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6693, line : "The waste of slaughter, and the rage of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6694, line : "No bounds, no law, thy fiery temper quells,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6695, line : "And all thy mother in thy soul rebels."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6696, line : "In vain our threats, in vain our power we use;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6697, line : "She gives the example, and her son pursues."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6698, line : "Yet long the inflicted pangs thou shall not mourn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6699, line : "Sprung since thou art from Jove, and heavenly-born."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6700, line : "Else, singed with lightning, hadst thou hence been thrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6701, line : "Where chain'd on burning rocks the Titans groan.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6703, line : "Thus he who shakes Olympus with his nod;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6704, line : "Then gave to Paeon's care the bleeding god.(160)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6705, line : "With gentle hand the balm he pour'd around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6706, line : "And heal'd the immortal flesh, and closed the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6707, line : "As when the fig's press'd juice, infused in cream,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6708, line : "To curds coagulates the liquid stream,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6709, line : "Sudden the fluids fix the parts combined;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6710, line : "Such, and so soon, the ethereal texture join'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6711, line : "Cleansed from the dust and gore, fair Hebe dress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6712, line : "His mighty limbs in an immortal vest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6713, line : "Glorious he sat, in majesty restored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6714, line : "Fast by the throne of heaven's superior lord."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6715, line : "Juno and Pallas mount the bless'd abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6716, line : "Their task perform'd, and mix among the gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6718, line : "[Illustration: JUNO.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6720, line : "JUNO."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6726, line : "BOOK VI."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6729, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6731, line : "THE EPISODES OF GLAUCUS AND DIOMED, AND OF HECTOR AND ANDROMACHE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6733, line : "The gods having left the field, the Grecians prevail. Helenus, the chief"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6734, line : "augur of Troy, commands Hector to return to the city, in order to appoint"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6735, line : "a solemn procession of the queen and the Trojan matrons to the temple of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6736, line : "Minerva, to entreat her to remove Diomed from the fight. The battle"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6737, line : "relaxing during the absence of Hector, Glaucus and Diomed have an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6738, line : "interview between the two armies; where, coming to the knowledge, of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6739, line : "friendship and hospitality passed between their ancestors, they make"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6740, line : "exchange of their arms. Hector, having performed the orders of Helenus,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6741, line : "prevails upon Paris to return to the battle, and, taking a tender leave of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6742, line : "his wife Andromache, hastens again to the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6744, line : "The scene is first in the field of battle, between the rivers Simois and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6745, line : "Scamander, and then changes to Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6747, line : "Now heaven forsakes the fight: the immortals yield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6748, line : "To human force and human skill the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6749, line : "Dark showers of javelins fly from foes to foes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6750, line : "Now here, now there, the tide of combat flows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6751, line : "While Troy's famed streams, that bound the deathful plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6752, line : "On either side, run purple to the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6754, line : "Great Ajax first to conquest led the way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6755, line : "Broke the thick ranks, and turn'd the doubtful day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6756, line : "The Thracian Acamas his falchion found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6757, line : "And hew'd the enormous giant to the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6758, line : "His thundering arm a deadly stroke impress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6759, line : "Where the black horse-hair nodded o'er his crest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6760, line : "Fix'd in his front the brazen weapon lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6761, line : "And seals in endless shades his swimming eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6762, line : "Next Teuthras' son distain'd the sands with blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6763, line : "Axylus, hospitable, rich, and good:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6764, line : "In fair Arisbe's walls (his native place)(161)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6765, line : "He held his seat! a friend to human race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6766, line : "Fast by the road, his ever-open door"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6767, line : "Obliged the wealthy, and relieved the poor."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6768, line : "To stern Tydides now he falls a prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6769, line : "No friend to guard him in the dreadful day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6770, line : "Breathless the good man fell, and by his side"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6771, line : "His faithful servant, old Calesius died."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6773, line : "By great Euryalus was Dresus slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6774, line : "And next he laid Opheltius on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6775, line : "Two twins were near, bold, beautiful, and young,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6776, line : "From a fair naiad and Bucolion sprung:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6777, line : "(Laomedon's white flocks Bucolion fed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6778, line : "That monarch's first-born by a foreign bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6779, line : "In secret woods he won the naiad's grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6780, line : "And two fair infants crown'd his strong embrace:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6781, line : "Here dead they lay in all their youthful charms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6782, line : "The ruthless victor stripp'd their shining arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6784, line : "Astyalus by Polypoetes fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6785, line : "Ulysses' spear Pidytes sent to hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6786, line : "By Teucer's shaft brave Aretaon bled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6787, line : "And Nestor's son laid stern Ablerus dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6788, line : "Great Agamemnon, leader of the brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6789, line : "The mortal wound of rich Elatus gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6790, line : "Who held in Pedasus his proud abode,(162)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6791, line : "And till'd the banks where silver Satnio flow'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6792, line : "Melanthius by Eurypylus was slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6793, line : "And Phylacus from Leitus flies in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6795, line : "Unbless'd Adrastus next at mercy lies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6796, line : "Beneath the Spartan spear, a living prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6797, line : "Scared with the din and tumult of the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6798, line : "His headlong steeds, precipitate in flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6799, line : "Rush'd on a tamarisk's strong trunk, and broke"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6800, line : "The shatter'd chariot from the crooked yoke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6801, line : "Wide o'er the field, resistless as the wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6802, line : "For Troy they fly, and leave their lord behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6803, line : "Prone on his face he sinks beside the wheel:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6804, line : "Atrides o'er him shakes his vengeful steel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6805, line : "The fallen chief in suppliant posture press'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6806, line : "The victor's knees, and thus his prayer address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6808, line : "\"O spare my youth, and for the life I owe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6809, line : "Large gifts of price my father shall bestow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6810, line : "When fame shall tell, that, not in battle slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6811, line : "Thy hollow ships his captive son detain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6812, line : "Rich heaps of brass shall in thy tent be told,(163)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6813, line : "And steel well-temper'd, and persuasive gold.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6815, line : "He said: compassion touch'd the hero's heart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6816, line : "He stood, suspended with the lifted dart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6817, line : "As pity pleaded for his vanquish'd prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6818, line : "Stern Agamemnon swift to vengeance flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6819, line : "And, furious, thus: \"Oh impotent of mind!(164)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6820, line : "Shall these, shall these Atrides' mercy find?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6821, line : "Well hast thou known proud Troy's perfidious land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6822, line : "And well her natives merit at thy hand!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6823, line : "Not one of all the race, nor sex, nor age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6824, line : "Shall save a Trojan from our boundless rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6825, line : "Ilion shall perish whole, and bury all;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6826, line : "Her babes, her infants at the breast, shall fall;(165)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6827, line : "A dreadful lesson of exampled fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6828, line : "To warn the nations, and to curb the great!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6830, line : "The monarch spoke; the words, with warmth address'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6831, line : "To rigid justice steel'd his brother's breast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6832, line : "Fierce from his knees the hapless chief he thrust;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6833, line : "The monarch's javelin stretch'd him in the dust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6834, line : "Then pressing with his foot his panting heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6835, line : "Forth from the slain he tugg'd the reeking dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6836, line : "Old Nestor saw, and roused the warrior's rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6837, line : "\"Thus, heroes! thus the vigorous combat wage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6838, line : "No son of Mars descend, for servile gains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6839, line : "To touch the booty, while a foe remains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6840, line : "Behold yon glittering host, your future spoil!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6841, line : "First gain the conquest, then reward the toil.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6843, line : "And now had Greece eternal fame acquired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6844, line : "And frighted Troy within her walls, retired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6845, line : "Had not sage Helenus her state redress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6846, line : "Taught by the gods that moved his sacred breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6847, line : "Where Hector stood, with great Ćneas join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6848, line : "The seer reveal'd the counsels of his mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6850, line : "\"Ye generous chiefs! on whom the immortals lay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6851, line : "The cares and glories of this doubtful day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6852, line : "On whom your aids, your country's hopes depend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6853, line : "Wise to consult, and active to defend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6854, line : "Here, at our gates, your brave efforts unite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6855, line : "Turn back the routed, and forbid the flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6856, line : "Ere yet their wives' soft arms the cowards gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6857, line : "The sport and insult of the hostile train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6858, line : "When your commands have hearten'd every band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6859, line : "Ourselves, here fix'd, will make the dangerous stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6860, line : "Press'd as we are, and sore of former fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6861, line : "These straits demand our last remains of might."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6862, line : "Meanwhile thou, Hector, to the town retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6863, line : "And teach our mother what the gods require:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6864, line : "Direct the queen to lead the assembled train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6865, line : "Of Troy's chief matrons to Minerva's fane;(166)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6866, line : "Unbar the sacred gates, and seek the power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6867, line : "With offer'd vows, in Ilion's topmost tower."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6868, line : "The largest mantle her rich wardrobes hold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6869, line : "Most prized for art, and labour'd o'er with gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6870, line : "Before the goddess' honour'd knees be spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6871, line : "And twelve young heifers to her altars led:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6872, line : "If so the power, atoned by fervent prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6873, line : "Our wives, our infants, and our city spare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6874, line : "And far avert Tydides' wasteful ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6875, line : "That mows whole troops, and makes all Troy retire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6876, line : "Not thus Achilles taught our hosts to dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6877, line : "Sprung though he was from more than mortal bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6878, line : "Not thus resistless ruled the stream of fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6879, line : "In rage unbounded, and unmatch'd in might.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6881, line : "Hector obedient heard: and, with a bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6882, line : "Leap'd from his trembling chariot to the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6883, line : "Through all his host inspiring force he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6884, line : "And bids the thunder of the battle rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6885, line : "With rage recruited the bold Trojans glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6886, line : "And turn the tide of conflict on the foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6887, line : "Fierce in the front he shakes two dazzling spears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6888, line : "All Greece recedes, and 'midst her triumphs fears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6889, line : "Some god, they thought, who ruled the fate of wars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6890, line : "Shot down avenging from the vault of stars."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6892, line : "Then thus aloud: \"Ye dauntless Dardans, hear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6893, line : "And you whom distant nations send to war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6894, line : "Be mindful of the strength your fathers bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6895, line : "Be still yourselves, and Hector asks no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6896, line : "One hour demands me in the Trojan wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6897, line : "To bid our altars flame, and victims fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6898, line : "Nor shall, I trust, the matrons' holy train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6899, line : "And reverend elders, seek the gods in vain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6901, line : "This said, with ample strides the hero pass'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6902, line : "The shield's large orb behind his shoulder cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6903, line : "His neck o'ershading, to his ankle hung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6904, line : "And as he march'd the brazen buckler rung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6906, line : "Now paused the battle (godlike Hector gone),(167)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6907, line : "Where daring Glaucus and great Tydeus' son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6908, line : "Between both armies met: the chiefs from far"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6909, line : "Observed each other, and had mark'd for war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6910, line : "Near as they drew, Tydides thus began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6912, line : "\"What art thou, boldest of the race of man?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6913, line : "Our eyes till now that aspect ne'er beheld,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6914, line : "Where fame is reap'd amid the embattled field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6915, line : "Yet far before the troops thou dar'st appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6916, line : "And meet a lance the fiercest heroes fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6917, line : "Unhappy they, and born of luckless sires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6918, line : "Who tempt our fury when Minerva fires!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6919, line : "But if from heaven, celestial, thou descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6920, line : "Know with immortals we no more contend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6921, line : "Not long Lycurgus view'd the golden light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6922, line : "That daring man who mix'd with gods in fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6923, line : "Bacchus, and Bacchus' votaries, he drove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6924, line : "With brandish'd steel, from Nyssa's sacred grove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6925, line : "Their consecrated spears lay scatter'd round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6926, line : "With curling vines and twisted ivy bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6927, line : "While Bacchus headlong sought the briny flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6928, line : "And Thetis' arms received the trembling god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6929, line : "Nor fail'd the crime the immortals' wrath to move;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6930, line : "(The immortals bless'd with endless ease above;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6931, line : "Deprived of sight by their avenging doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6932, line : "Cheerless he breathed, and wander'd in the gloom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6933, line : "Then sunk unpitied to the dire abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6934, line : "A wretch accursed, and hated by the gods!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6935, line : "I brave not heaven: but if the fruits of earth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6936, line : "Sustain thy life, and human be thy birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6937, line : "Bold as thou art, too prodigal of breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6938, line : "Approach, and enter the dark gates of death.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6940, line : "\"What, or from whence I am, or who my sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6941, line : "(Replied the chief,) can Tydeus' son inquire?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6942, line : "Like leaves on trees the race of man is found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6943, line : "Now green in youth, now withering on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6944, line : "Another race the following spring supplies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6945, line : "They fall successive, and successive rise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6946, line : "So generations in their course decay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6947, line : "So flourish these, when those are pass'd away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6948, line : "But if thou still persist to search my birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6949, line : "Then hear a tale that fills the spacious earth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6951, line : "\"A city stands on Argos' utmost bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6952, line : "(Argos the fair, for warlike steeds renown'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6953, line : "Aeolian Sisyphus, with wisdom bless'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6954, line : "In ancient time the happy wall possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6955, line : "Then call'd Ephyre: Glaucus was his son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6956, line : "Great Glaucus, father of Bellerophon,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6957, line : "Who o'er the sons of men in beauty shined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6958, line : "Loved for that valour which preserves mankind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6959, line : "Then mighty Praetus Argos' sceptre sway'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6960, line : "Whose hard commands Bellerophon obey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6961, line : "With direful jealousy the monarch raged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6962, line : "And the brave prince in numerous toils engaged."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6963, line : "For him Antaea burn'd with lawless flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6964, line : "And strove to tempt him from the paths of fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6965, line : "In vain she tempted the relentless youth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6966, line : "Endued with wisdom, sacred fear, and truth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6967, line : "Fired at his scorn the queen to Praetus fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6968, line : "And begg'd revenge for her insulted bed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6969, line : "Incensed he heard, resolving on his fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6970, line : "But hospitable laws restrain'd his hate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6971, line : "To Lycia the devoted youth he sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6972, line : "With tablets seal'd, that told his dire intent.(168)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6973, line : "Now bless'd by every power who guards the good,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6974, line : "The chief arrived at Xanthus' silver flood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6975, line : "There Lycia's monarch paid him honours due,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6976, line : "Nine days he feasted, and nine bulls he slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6977, line : "But when the tenth bright morning orient glow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6978, line : "The faithful youth his monarch's mandate show'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6979, line : "The fatal tablets, till that instant seal'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6980, line : "The deathful secret to the king reveal'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6981, line : "First, dire Chimaera's conquest was enjoin'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6982, line : "A mingled monster of no mortal kind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6983, line : "Behind, a dragon's fiery tail was spread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6984, line : "A goat's rough body bore a lion's head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6985, line : "Her pitchy nostrils flaky flames expire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6986, line : "Her gaping throat emits infernal fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6988, line : "\"This pest he slaughter'd, (for he read the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6989, line : "And trusted heaven's informing prodigies,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6990, line : "Then met in arms the Solymaean crew,(169)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6991, line : "(Fiercest of men,) and those the warrior slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6992, line : "Next the bold Amazons' whole force defied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6993, line : "And conquer'd still, for heaven was on his side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6995, line : "\"Nor ended here his toils: his Lycian foes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6996, line : "At his return, a treacherous ambush rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6997, line : "With levell'd spears along the winding shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 6998, line : "There fell they breathless, and return'd no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7000, line : "\"At length the monarch, with repentant grief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7001, line : "Confess'd the gods, and god-descended chief;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7002, line : "His daughter gave, the stranger to detain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7003, line : "With half the honours of his ample reign:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7004, line : "The Lycians grant a chosen space of ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7005, line : "With woods, with vineyards, and with harvests crown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7006, line : "There long the chief his happy lot possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7007, line : "With two brave sons and one fair daughter bless'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7008, line : "(Fair e'en in heavenly eyes: her fruitful love"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7009, line : "Crown'd with Sarpedon's birth the embrace of Jove;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7010, line : "But when at last, distracted in his mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7011, line : "Forsook by heaven, forsaking humankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7012, line : "Wide o'er the Aleian field he chose to stray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7013, line : "A long, forlorn, uncomfortable way!(170)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7014, line : "Woes heap'd on woes consumed his wasted heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7015, line : "His beauteous daughter fell by Phoebe's dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7016, line : "His eldest born by raging Mars was slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7017, line : "In combat on the Solymaean plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7018, line : "Hippolochus survived: from him I came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7019, line : "The honour'd author of my birth and name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7020, line : "By his decree I sought the Trojan town;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7021, line : "By his instructions learn to win renown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7022, line : "To stand the first in worth as in command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7023, line : "To add new honours to my native land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7024, line : "Before my eyes my mighty sires to place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7025, line : "And emulate the glories of our race.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7027, line : "He spoke, and transport fill'd Tydides' heart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7028, line : "In earth the generous warrior fix'd his dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7029, line : "Then friendly, thus the Lycian prince address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7030, line : "\"Welcome, my brave hereditary guest!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7031, line : "Thus ever let us meet, with kind embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7032, line : "Nor stain the sacred friendship of our race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7033, line : "Know, chief, our grandsires have been guests of old;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7034, line : "OEneus the strong, Bellerophon the bold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7035, line : "Our ancient seat his honour'd presence graced,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7036, line : "Where twenty days in genial rites he pass'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7037, line : "The parting heroes mutual presents left;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7038, line : "A golden goblet was thy grandsire's gift;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7039, line : "OEneus a belt of matchless work bestowed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7040, line : "That rich with Tyrian dye refulgent glow'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7041, line : "(This from his pledge I learn'd, which, safely stored"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7042, line : "Among my treasures, still adorns my board:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7043, line : "For Tydeus left me young, when Thebe's wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7044, line : "Beheld the sons of Greece untimely fall.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7045, line : "Mindful of this, in friendship let us join;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7046, line : "If heaven our steps to foreign lands incline,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7047, line : "My guest in Argos thou, and I in Lycia thine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7048, line : "Enough of Trojans to this lance shall yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7049, line : "In the full harvest of yon ample field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7050, line : "Enough of Greeks shall dye thy spear with gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7051, line : "But thou and Diomed be foes no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7052, line : "Now change we arms, and prove to either host"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7053, line : "We guard the friendship of the line we boast.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7055, line : "Thus having said, the gallant chiefs alight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7056, line : "Their hands they join, their mutual faith they plight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7057, line : "Brave Glaucus then each narrow thought resign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7058, line : "(Jove warm'd his bosom, and enlarged his mind,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7059, line : "For Diomed's brass arms, of mean device,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7060, line : "For which nine oxen paid, (a vulgar price,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7061, line : "He gave his own, of gold divinely wrought,(171)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7062, line : "A hundred beeves the shining purchase bought."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7064, line : "Meantime the guardian of the Trojan state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7065, line : "Great Hector, enter'd at the Scaean gate.(172)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7066, line : "Beneath the beech-tree's consecrated shades,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7067, line : "The Trojan matrons and the Trojan maids"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7068, line : "Around him flock'd, all press'd with pious care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7069, line : "For husbands, brothers, sons, engaged in war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7070, line : "He bids the train in long procession go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7071, line : "And seek the gods, to avert the impending woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7072, line : "And now to Priam's stately courts he came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7073, line : "Rais'd on arch'd columns of stupendous frame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7074, line : "O'er these a range of marble structure runs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7075, line : "The rich pavilions of his fifty sons,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7076, line : "In fifty chambers lodged: and rooms of state,(173)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7077, line : "Opposed to those, where Priam's daughters sate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7078, line : "Twelve domes for them and their loved spouses shone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7079, line : "Of equal beauty, and of polish'd stone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7080, line : "Hither great Hector pass'd, nor pass'd unseen"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7081, line : "Of royal Hecuba, his mother-queen."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7082, line : "(With her Laodice, whose beauteous face"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7083, line : "Surpass'd the nymphs of Troy's illustrious race.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7084, line : "Long in a strict embrace she held her son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7085, line : "And press'd his hand, and tender thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7087, line : "\"O Hector! say, what great occasion calls"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7088, line : "My son from fight, when Greece surrounds our walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7089, line : "Com'st thou to supplicate the almighty power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7090, line : "With lifted hands, from Ilion's lofty tower?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7091, line : "Stay, till I bring the cup with Bacchus crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7092, line : "In Jove's high name, to sprinkle on the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7093, line : "And pay due vows to all the gods around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7094, line : "Then with a plenteous draught refresh thy soul,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7095, line : "And draw new spirits from the generous bowl;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7096, line : "Spent as thou art with long laborious fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7097, line : "The brave defender of thy country's right.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7099, line : "\"Far hence be Bacchus' gifts; (the chief rejoin'd;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7100, line : "Inflaming wine, pernicious to mankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7101, line : "Unnerves the limbs, and dulls the noble mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7102, line : "Let chiefs abstain, and spare the sacred juice"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7103, line : "To sprinkle to the gods, its better use."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7104, line : "By me that holy office were profaned;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7105, line : "Ill fits it me, with human gore distain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7106, line : "To the pure skies these horrid hands to raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7107, line : "Or offer heaven's great Sire polluted praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7108, line : "You, with your matrons, go! a spotless train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7109, line : "And burn rich odours in Minerva's fane."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7110, line : "The largest mantle your full wardrobes hold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7111, line : "Most prized for art, and labour'd o'er with gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7112, line : "Before the goddess' honour'd knees be spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7113, line : "And twelve young heifers to her altar led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7114, line : "So may the power, atoned by fervent prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7115, line : "Our wives, our infants, and our city spare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7116, line : "And far avert Tydides' wasteful ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7117, line : "Who mows whole troops, and makes all Troy retire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7118, line : "Be this, O mother, your religious care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7119, line : "I go to rouse soft Paris to the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7120, line : "If yet not lost to all the sense of shame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7121, line : "The recreant warrior hear the voice of fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7122, line : "Oh, would kind earth the hateful wretch embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7123, line : "That pest of Troy, that ruin of our race!(174)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7124, line : "Deep to the dark abyss might he descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7125, line : "Troy yet should flourish, and my sorrows end.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7127, line : "This heard, she gave command: and summon'd came"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7128, line : "Each noble matron and illustrious dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7129, line : "The Phrygian queen to her rich wardrobe went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7130, line : "Where treasured odours breathed a costly scent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7131, line : "There lay the vestures of no vulgar art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7132, line : "Sidonian maids embroider'd every part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7133, line : "Whom from soft Sidon youthful Paris bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7134, line : "With Helen touching on the Tyrian shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7135, line : "Here, as the queen revolved with careful eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7136, line : "The various textures and the various dyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7137, line : "She chose a veil that shone superior far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7138, line : "And glow'd refulgent as the morning star."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7139, line : "Herself with this the long procession leads;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7140, line : "The train majestically slow proceeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7141, line : "Soon as to Ilion's topmost tower they come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7142, line : "And awful reach the high Palladian dome,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7143, line : "Antenor's consort, fair Theano, waits"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7144, line : "As Pallas' priestess, and unbars the gates."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7145, line : "With hands uplifted and imploring eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7146, line : "They fill the dome with supplicating cries."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7147, line : "The priestess then the shining veil displays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7148, line : "Placed on Minerva's knees, and thus she prays:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7150, line : "\"Oh awful goddess! ever-dreadful maid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7151, line : "Troy's strong defence, unconquer'd Pallas, aid!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7152, line : "Break thou Tydides' spear, and let him fall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7153, line : "Prone on the dust before the Trojan wall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7154, line : "So twelve young heifers, guiltless of the yoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7155, line : "Shall fill thy temple with a grateful smoke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7156, line : "But thou, atoned by penitence and prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7157, line : "Ourselves, our infants, and our city spare!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7158, line : "So pray'd the priestess in her holy fane;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7159, line : "So vow'd the matrons, but they vow'd in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7161, line : "While these appear before the power with prayers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7162, line : "Hector to Paris' lofty dome repairs.(175)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7163, line : "Himself the mansion raised, from every part"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7164, line : "Assembling architects of matchless art."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7165, line : "Near Priam's court and Hector's palace stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7166, line : "The pompous structure, and the town commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7167, line : "A spear the hero bore of wondrous strength,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7168, line : "Of full ten cubits was the lance's length,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7169, line : "The steely point with golden ringlets join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7170, line : "Before him brandish'd, at each motion shined"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7171, line : "Thus entering, in the glittering rooms he found"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7172, line : "His brother-chief, whose useless arms lay round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7173, line : "His eyes delighting with their splendid show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7174, line : "Brightening the shield, and polishing the bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7175, line : "Beside him Helen with her virgins stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7176, line : "Guides their rich labours, and instructs their hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7178, line : "Him thus inactive, with an ardent look"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7179, line : "The prince beheld, and high-resenting spoke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7180, line : "\"Thy hate to Troy, is this the time to show?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7181, line : "(O wretch ill-fated, and thy country's foe!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7182, line : "Paris and Greece against us both conspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7183, line : "Thy close resentment, and their vengeful ire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7184, line : "For thee great Ilion's guardian heroes fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7185, line : "Till heaps of dead alone defend her wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7186, line : "For thee the soldier bleeds, the matron mourns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7187, line : "And wasteful war in all its fury burns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7188, line : "Ungrateful man! deserves not this thy care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7189, line : "Our troops to hearten, and our toils to share?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7190, line : "Rise, or behold the conquering flames ascend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7191, line : "And all the Phrygian glories at an end.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7193, line : "\"Brother, 'tis just, (replied the beauteous youth,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7194, line : "Thy free remonstrance proves thy worth and truth:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7195, line : "Yet charge my absence less, O generous chief!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7196, line : "On hate to Troy, than conscious shame and grief:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7197, line : "Here, hid from human eyes, thy brother sate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7198, line : "And mourn'd, in secret, his and Ilion's fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7199, line : "'Tis now enough; now glory spreads her charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7200, line : "And beauteous Helen calls her chief to arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7201, line : "Conquest to-day my happier sword may bless,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7202, line : "'Tis man's to fight, but heaven's to give success."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7203, line : "But while I arm, contain thy ardent mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7204, line : "Or go, and Paris shall not lag behind.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7206, line : "[Illustration: HECTOR CHIDING PARIS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7208, line : "HECTOR CHIDING PARIS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7211, line : "He said, nor answer'd Priam's warlike son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7212, line : "When Helen thus with lowly grace begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7214, line : "\"Oh, generous brother! (if the guilty dame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7215, line : "That caused these woes deserve a sister's name!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7216, line : "Would heaven, ere all these dreadful deeds were done,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7217, line : "The day that show'd me to the golden sun"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7218, line : "Had seen my death! why did not whirlwinds bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7219, line : "The fatal infant to the fowls of air?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7220, line : "Why sunk I not beneath the whelming tide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7221, line : "And midst the roarings of the waters died?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7222, line : "Heaven fill'd up all my ills, and I accursed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7223, line : "Bore all, and Paris of those ills the worst."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7224, line : "Helen at least a braver spouse might claim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7225, line : "Warm'd with some virtue, some regard of fame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7226, line : "Now tired with toils, thy fainting limbs recline,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7227, line : "With toils, sustain'd for Paris' sake and mine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7228, line : "The gods have link'd our miserable doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7229, line : "Our present woe, and infamy to come:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7230, line : "Wide shall it spread, and last through ages long,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7231, line : "Example sad! and theme of future song.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7233, line : "The chief replied: \"This time forbids to rest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7234, line : "The Trojan bands, by hostile fury press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7235, line : "Demand their Hector, and his arm require;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7236, line : "The combat urges, and my soul's on fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7237, line : "Urge thou thy knight to march where glory calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7238, line : "And timely join me, ere I leave the walls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7239, line : "Ere yet I mingle in the direful fray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7240, line : "My wife, my infant, claim a moment's stay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7241, line : "This day (perhaps the last that sees me here)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7242, line : "Demands a parting word, a tender tear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7243, line : "This day, some god who hates our Trojan land"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7244, line : "May vanquish Hector by a Grecian hand.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7246, line : "He said, and pass'd with sad presaging heart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7247, line : "To seek his spouse, his soul's far dearer part;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7248, line : "At home he sought her, but he sought in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7249, line : "She, with one maid of all her menial train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7250, line : "Had hence retired; and with her second joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7251, line : "The young Astyanax, the hope of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7252, line : "Pensive she stood on Ilion's towery height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7253, line : "Beheld the war, and sicken'd at the sight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7254, line : "There her sad eyes in vain her lord explore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7255, line : "Or weep the wounds her bleeding country bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7257, line : "But he who found not whom his soul desired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7258, line : "Whose virtue charm'd him as her beauty fired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7259, line : "Stood in the gates, and ask'd \"what way she bent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7260, line : "Her parting step? If to the fane she went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7261, line : "Where late the mourning matrons made resort;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7262, line : "Or sought her sisters in the Trojan court?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7263, line : "\"Not to the court, (replied the attendant train,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7264, line : "Nor mix'd with matrons to Minerva's fane:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7265, line : "To Ilion's steepy tower she bent her way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7266, line : "To mark the fortunes of the doubtful day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7267, line : "Troy fled, she heard, before the Grecian sword;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7268, line : "She heard, and trembled for her absent lord:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7269, line : "Distracted with surprise, she seem'd to fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7270, line : "Fear on her cheek, and sorrow m her eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7271, line : "The nurse attended with her infant boy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7272, line : "The young Astyanax, the hope of Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7274, line : "Hector this heard, return'd without delay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7275, line : "Swift through the town he trod his former way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7276, line : "Through streets of palaces, and walks of state;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7277, line : "And met the mourner at the Scaean gate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7278, line : "With haste to meet him sprung the joyful fair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7279, line : "His blameless wife, Aetion's wealthy heir:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7280, line : "(Cilician Thebe great Aetion sway'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7281, line : "And Hippoplacus' wide extended shade:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7282, line : "The nurse stood near, in whose embraces press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7283, line : "His only hope hung smiling at her breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7284, line : "Whom each soft charm and early grace adorn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7285, line : "Fair as the new-born star that gilds the morn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7286, line : "To this loved infant Hector gave the name"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7287, line : "Scamandrius, from Scamander's honour'd stream;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7288, line : "Astyanax the Trojans call'd the boy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7289, line : "From his great father, the defence of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7290, line : "Silent the warrior smiled, and pleased resign'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7291, line : "To tender passions all his mighty mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7292, line : "His beauteous princess cast a mournful look,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7293, line : "Hung on his hand, and then dejected spoke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7294, line : "Her bosom laboured with a boding sigh,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7295, line : "And the big tear stood trembling in her eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7297, line : "[Illustration: THE MEETING OF HECTOR AND ANDROMACHE.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7299, line : "THE MEETING OF HECTOR AND ANDROMACHE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7302, line : "\"Too daring prince! ah, whither dost thou run?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7303, line : "Ah, too forgetful of thy wife and son!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7304, line : "And think'st thou not how wretched we shall be,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7305, line : "A widow I, a helpless orphan he?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7306, line : "For sure such courage length of life denies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7307, line : "And thou must fall, thy virtue's sacrifice."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7308, line : "Greece in her single heroes strove in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7309, line : "Now hosts oppose thee, and thou must be slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7310, line : "O grant me, gods, ere Hector meets his doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7311, line : "All I can ask of heaven, an early tomb!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7312, line : "So shall my days in one sad tenor run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7313, line : "And end with sorrows as they first begun."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7314, line : "No parent now remains my griefs to share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7315, line : "No father's aid, no mother's tender care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7316, line : "The fierce Achilles wrapt our walls in fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7317, line : "Laid Thebe waste, and slew my warlike sire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7318, line : "His fate compassion in the victor bred;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7319, line : "Stern as he was, he yet revered the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7320, line : "His radiant arms preserved from hostile spoil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7321, line : "And laid him decent on the funeral pile;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7322, line : "Then raised a mountain where his bones were burn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7323, line : "The mountain-nymphs the rural tomb adorn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7324, line : "Jove's sylvan daughters bade their elms bestow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7325, line : "A barren shade, and in his honour grow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7327, line : "\"By the same arm my seven brave brothers fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7328, line : "In one sad day beheld the gates of hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7329, line : "While the fat herds and snowy flocks they fed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7330, line : "Amid their fields the hapless heroes bled!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7331, line : "My mother lived to wear the victor's bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7332, line : "The queen of Hippoplacia's sylvan lands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7333, line : "Redeem'd too late, she scarce beheld again"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7334, line : "Her pleasing empire and her native plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7335, line : "When ah! oppress'd by life-consuming woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7336, line : "She fell a victim to Diana's bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7338, line : "\"Yet while my Hector still survives, I see"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7339, line : "My father, mother, brethren, all, in thee:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7340, line : "Alas! my parents, brothers, kindred, all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7341, line : "Once more will perish, if my Hector fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7342, line : "Thy wife, thy infant, in thy danger share:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7343, line : "Oh, prove a husband's and a father's care!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7344, line : "That quarter most the skilful Greeks annoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7345, line : "Where yon wild fig-trees join the wall of Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7346, line : "Thou, from this tower defend the important post;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7347, line : "There Agamemnon points his dreadful host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7348, line : "That pass Tydides, Ajax, strive to gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7349, line : "And there the vengeful Spartan fires his train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7350, line : "Thrice our bold foes the fierce attack have given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7351, line : "Or led by hopes, or dictated from heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7352, line : "Let others in the field their arms employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7353, line : "But stay my Hector here, and guard his Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7355, line : "The chief replied: \"That post shall be my care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7356, line : "Not that alone, but all the works of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7357, line : "How would the sons of Troy, in arms renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7358, line : "And Troy's proud dames, whose garments sweep the ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7359, line : "Attaint the lustre of my former name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7360, line : "Should Hector basely quit the field of fame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7361, line : "My early youth was bred to martial pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7362, line : "My soul impels me to the embattled plains!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7363, line : "Let me be foremost to defend the throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7364, line : "And guard my father's glories, and my own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7366, line : "\"Yet come it will, the day decreed by fates!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7367, line : "(How my heart trembles while my tongue relates!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7368, line : "The day when thou, imperial Troy! must bend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7369, line : "And see thy warriors fall, thy glories end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7370, line : "And yet no dire presage so wounds my mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7371, line : "My mother's death, the ruin of my kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7372, line : "Not Priam's hoary hairs defiled with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7373, line : "Not all my brothers gasping on the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7374, line : "As thine, Andromache! Thy griefs I dread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7375, line : "I see thee trembling, weeping, captive led!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7376, line : "In Argive looms our battles to design,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7377, line : "And woes, of which so large a part was thine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7378, line : "To bear the victor's hard commands, or bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7379, line : "The weight of waters from Hyperia's spring."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7380, line : "There while you groan beneath the load of life,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7381, line : "They cry, 'Behold the mighty Hector's wife!'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7382, line : "Some haughty Greek, who lives thy tears to see,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7383, line : "Imbitters all thy woes, by naming me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7384, line : "The thoughts of glory past, and present shame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7385, line : "A thousand griefs shall waken at the name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7386, line : "May I lie cold before that dreadful day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7387, line : "Press'd with a load of monumental clay!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7388, line : "Thy Hector, wrapt in everlasting sleep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7389, line : "Shall neither hear thee sigh, nor see thee weep.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7391, line : "Thus having spoke, the illustrious chief of Troy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7392, line : "Stretch'd his fond arms to clasp the lovely boy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7393, line : "The babe clung crying to his nurse's breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7394, line : "Scared at the dazzling helm, and nodding crest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7395, line : "With secret pleasure each fond parent smiled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7396, line : "And Hector hasted to relieve his child,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7397, line : "The glittering terrors from his brows unbound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7398, line : "And placed the beaming helmet on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7399, line : "Then kiss'd the child, and, lifting high in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7400, line : "Thus to the gods preferr'd a father's prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7402, line : "\"O thou! whose glory fills the ethereal throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7403, line : "And all ye deathless powers! protect my son!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7404, line : "Grant him, like me, to purchase just renown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7405, line : "To guard the Trojans, to defend the crown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7406, line : "Against his country's foes the war to wage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7407, line : "And rise the Hector of the future age!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7408, line : "So when triumphant from successful toils"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7409, line : "Of heroes slain he bears the reeking spoils,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7410, line : "Whole hosts may hail him with deserved acclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7411, line : "And say, 'This chief transcends his father's fame:'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7412, line : "While pleased amidst the general shouts of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7413, line : "His mother's conscious heart o'erflows with joy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7415, line : "He spoke, and fondly gazing on her charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7416, line : "Restored the pleasing burden to her arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7417, line : "Soft on her fragrant breast the babe she laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7418, line : "Hush'd to repose, and with a smile survey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7419, line : "The troubled pleasure soon chastised by fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7420, line : "She mingled with a smile a tender tear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7421, line : "The soften'd chief with kind compassion view'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7422, line : "And dried the falling drops, and thus pursued:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7424, line : "\"Andromache! my soul's far better part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7425, line : "Why with untimely sorrows heaves thy heart?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7426, line : "No hostile hand can antedate my doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7427, line : "Till fate condemns me to the silent tomb."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7428, line : "Fix'd is the term to all the race of earth;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7429, line : "And such the hard condition of our birth:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7430, line : "No force can then resist, no flight can save,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7431, line : "All sink alike, the fearful and the brave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7432, line : "No more--but hasten to thy tasks at home,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7433, line : "There guide the spindle, and direct the loom:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7434, line : "Me glory summons to the martial scene,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7435, line : "The field of combat is the sphere for men."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7436, line : "Where heroes war, the foremost place I claim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7437, line : "The first in danger as the first in fame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7439, line : "Thus having said, the glorious chief resumes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7440, line : "His towery helmet, black with shading plumes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7441, line : "His princess parts with a prophetic sigh,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7442, line : "Unwilling parts, and oft reverts her eye"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7443, line : "That stream'd at every look; then, moving slow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7444, line : "Sought her own palace, and indulged her woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7445, line : "There, while her tears deplored the godlike man,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7446, line : "Through all her train the soft infection ran;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7447, line : "The pious maids their mingled sorrows shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7448, line : "And mourn the living Hector, as the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7450, line : "But now, no longer deaf to honour's call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7451, line : "Forth issues Paris from the palace wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7452, line : "In brazen arms that cast a gleamy ray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7453, line : "Swift through the town the warrior bends his way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7454, line : "The wanton courser thus with reins unbound(176)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7455, line : "Breaks from his stall, and beats the trembling ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7456, line : "Pamper'd and proud, he seeks the wonted tides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7457, line : "And laves, in height of blood his shining sides;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7458, line : "His head now freed, he tosses to the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7459, line : "His mane dishevell'd o'er his shoulders flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7460, line : "He snuffs the females in the distant plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7461, line : "And springs, exulting, to his fields again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7462, line : "With equal triumph, sprightly, bold, and gay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7463, line : "In arms refulgent as the god of day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7464, line : "The son of Priam, glorying in his might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7465, line : "Rush'd forth with Hector to the fields of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7467, line : "And now, the warriors passing on the way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7468, line : "The graceful Paris first excused his stay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7469, line : "To whom the noble Hector thus replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7470, line : "\"O chief! in blood, and now in arms, allied!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7471, line : "Thy power in war with justice none contest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7472, line : "Known is thy courage, and thy strength confess'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7473, line : "What pity sloth should seize a soul so brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7474, line : "Or godlike Paris live a woman's slave!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7475, line : "My heart weeps blood at what the Trojans say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7476, line : "And hopes thy deeds shall wipe the stain away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7477, line : "Haste then, in all their glorious labours share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7478, line : "For much they suffer, for thy sake, in war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7479, line : "These ills shall cease, whene'er by Jove's decree"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7480, line : "We crown the bowl to heaven and liberty:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7481, line : "While the proud foe his frustrate triumphs mourns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7482, line : "And Greece indignant through her seas returns.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7484, line : "[Illustration: BOWS AND BOW CASE.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7486, line : "BOWS AND BOW CASE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7489, line : "[Illustration: IRIS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7491, line : "IRIS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7497, line : "BOOK VII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7500, line : "ARGUMENT"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7502, line : "THE SINGLE COMBAT OF HECTOR AND AJAX."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7504, line : "The battle renewing with double ardour upon the return of Hector, Minerva"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7505, line : "is under apprehensions for the Greeks. Apollo, seeing her descend from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7506, line : "Olympus, joins her near the Scaean gate. They agree to put off the general"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7507, line : "engagement for that day, and incite Hector to challenge the Greeks to a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7508, line : "single combat. Nine of the princes accepting the challenge, the lot is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7509, line : "cast and falls upon Ajax. These heroes, after several attacks, are parted"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7510, line : "by the night. The Trojans calling a council, Antenor purposes the delivery"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7511, line : "of Helen to the Greeks, to which Paris will not consent, but offers to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7512, line : "restore them her riches. Priam sends a herald to make this offer, and to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7513, line : "demand a truce for burning the dead, the last of which only is agreed to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7514, line : "by Agamemnon. When the funerals are performed, the Greeks, pursuant to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7515, line : "advice of Nestor, erect a fortification to protect their fleet and camp,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7516, line : "flanked with towers, and defended by a ditch and palisades. Neptune"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7517, line : "testifies his jealousy at this work, but is pacified by a promise from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7518, line : "Jupiter. Both armies pass the night in feasting but Jupiter disheartens"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7519, line : "the Trojans with thunder, and other signs of his wrath."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7521, line : "The three and twentieth day ends with the duel of Hector and Ajax, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7522, line : "next day the truce is agreed; another is taken up in the funeral rites of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7523, line : "the slain and one more in building the fortification before the ships. So"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7524, line : "that somewhat about three days is employed in this book. The scene lies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7525, line : "wholly in the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7527, line : "So spoke the guardian of the Trojan state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7528, line : "Then rush'd impetuous through the Scaean gate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7529, line : "Him Paris follow'd to the dire alarms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7530, line : "Both breathing slaughter, both resolved in arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7531, line : "As when to sailors labouring through the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7532, line : "That long have heaved the weary oar in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7533, line : "Jove bids at length the expected gales arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7534, line : "The gales blow grateful, and the vessel flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7535, line : "So welcome these to Troy's desiring train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7536, line : "The bands are cheer'd, the war awakes again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7538, line : "Bold Paris first the work of death begun"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7539, line : "On great Menestheus, Areithous' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7540, line : "Sprung from the fair Philomeda's embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7541, line : "The pleasing Arne was his native place."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7542, line : "Then sunk Eioneus to the shades below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7543, line : "Beneath his steely casque he felt the blow(177)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7544, line : "Full on his neck, from Hector's weighty hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7545, line : "And roll'd, with limbs relax'd, along the land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7546, line : "By Glaucus' spear the bold Iphmous bleeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7547, line : "Fix'd in the shoulder as he mounts his steeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7548, line : "Headlong he tumbles: his slack nerves unbound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7549, line : "Drop the cold useless members on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7551, line : "When now Minerva saw her Argives slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7552, line : "From vast Olympus to the gleaming plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7553, line : "Fierce she descends: Apollo marked her flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7554, line : "Nor shot less swift from Ilion's towery height."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7555, line : "Radiant they met, beneath the beechen shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7556, line : "When thus Apollo to the blue-eyed maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7558, line : "\"What cause, O daughter of Almighty Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7559, line : "Thus wings thy progress from the realms above?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7560, line : "Once more impetuous dost thou bend thy way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7561, line : "To give to Greece the long divided day?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7562, line : "Too much has Troy already felt thy hate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7563, line : "Now breathe thy rage, and hush the stern debate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7564, line : "This day, the business of the field suspend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7565, line : "War soon shall kindle, and great Ilion bend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7566, line : "Since vengeful goddesses confederate join"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7567, line : "To raze her walls, though built by hands divine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7569, line : "To whom the progeny of Jove replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7570, line : "\"I left, for this, the council of the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7571, line : "But who shall bid conflicting hosts forbear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7572, line : "What art shall calm the furious sons of war?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7573, line : "To her the god: \"Great Hector's soul incite"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7574, line : "To dare the boldest Greek to single fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7575, line : "Till Greece, provoked, from all her numbers show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7576, line : "A warrior worthy to be Hector's foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7578, line : "At this agreed, the heavenly powers withdrew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7579, line : "Sage Helenus their secret counsels knew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7580, line : "Hector, inspired, he sought: to him address'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7581, line : "Thus told the dictates of his sacred breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7582, line : "\"O son of Priam! let thy faithful ear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7583, line : "Receive my words: thy friend and brother hear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7584, line : "Go forth persuasive, and a while engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7585, line : "The warring nations to suspend their rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7586, line : "Then dare the boldest of the hostile train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7587, line : "To mortal combat on the listed plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7588, line : "For not this day shall end thy glorious date;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7589, line : "The gods have spoke it, and their voice is fate.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7591, line : "He said: the warrior heard the word with joy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7592, line : "Then with his spear restrain'd the youth of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7593, line : "Held by the midst athwart. On either hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7594, line : "The squadrons part; the expecting Trojans stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7595, line : "Great Agamemnon bids the Greeks forbear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7596, line : "They breathe, and hush the tumult of the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7597, line : "The Athenian maid, and glorious god of day,(178)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7598, line : "With silent joy the settling hosts survey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7599, line : "In form of vultures, on the beech's height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7600, line : "They sit conceal'd, and wait the future fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7602, line : "The thronging troops obscure the dusky fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7603, line : "Horrid with bristling spears, and gleaming shields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7604, line : "As when a general darkness veils the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7605, line : "(Soft Zephyr curling the wide wat'ry plain,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7606, line : "The waves scarce heave, the face of ocean sleeps,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7607, line : "And a still horror saddens all the deeps;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7608, line : "Thus in thick orders settling wide around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7609, line : "At length composed they sit, and shade the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7610, line : "Great Hector first amidst both armies broke"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7611, line : "The solemn silence, and their powers bespoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7613, line : "\"Hear, all ye Trojan, all ye Grecian bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7614, line : "What my soul prompts, and what some god commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7615, line : "Great Jove, averse our warfare to compose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7616, line : "O'erwhelms the nations with new toils and woes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7617, line : "War with a fiercer tide once more returns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7618, line : "Till Ilion falls, or till yon navy burns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7619, line : "You then, O princes of the Greeks! appear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7620, line : "'Tis Hector speaks, and calls the gods to hear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7621, line : "From all your troops select the boldest knight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7622, line : "And him, the boldest, Hector dares to fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7623, line : "Here if I fall, by chance of battle slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7624, line : "Be his my spoil, and his these arms remain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7625, line : "But let my body, to my friends return'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7626, line : "By Trojan hands and Trojan flames be burn'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7627, line : "And if Apollo, in whose aid I trust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7628, line : "Shall stretch your daring champion in the dust;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7629, line : "If mine the glory to despoil the foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7630, line : "On Phoebus' temple I'll his arms bestow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7631, line : "The breathless carcase to your navy sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7632, line : "Greece on the shore shall raise a monument;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7633, line : "Which when some future mariner surveys,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7634, line : "Wash'd by broad Hellespont's resounding seas,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7635, line : "Thus shall he say, 'A valiant Greek lies there,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7636, line : "By Hector slain, the mighty man of war,'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7637, line : "The stone shall tell your vanquish'd hero's name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7638, line : "And distant ages learn the victor's fame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7640, line : "This fierce defiance Greece astonish'd heard,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7641, line : "Blush'd to refuse, and to accept it fear'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7642, line : "Stern Menelaus first the silence broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7643, line : "And, inly groaning, thus opprobrious spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7645, line : "\"Women of Greece! O scandal of your race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7646, line : "Whose coward souls your manly form disgrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7647, line : "How great the shame, when every age shall know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7648, line : "That not a Grecian met this noble foe!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7649, line : "Go then! resolve to earth, from whence ye grew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7650, line : "A heartless, spiritless, inglorious crew!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7651, line : "Be what ye seem, unanimated clay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7652, line : "Myself will dare the danger of the day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7653, line : "'Tis man's bold task the generous strife to try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7654, line : "But in the hands of God is victory.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7656, line : "These words scarce spoke, with generous ardour press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7657, line : "His manly limbs in azure arms he dress'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7658, line : "That day, Atrides! a superior hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7659, line : "Had stretch'd thee breathless on the hostile strand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7660, line : "But all at once, thy fury to compose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7661, line : "The kings of Greece, an awful band, arose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7662, line : "Even he their chief, great Agamemnon, press'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7663, line : "Thy daring hand, and this advice address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7664, line : "\"Whither, O Menelaus! wouldst thou run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7665, line : "And tempt a fate which prudence bids thee shun?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7666, line : "Grieved though thou art, forbear the rash design;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7667, line : "Great Hectors arm is mightier far than thine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7668, line : "Even fierce Achilles learn'd its force to fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7669, line : "And trembling met this dreadful son of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7670, line : "Sit thou secure, amidst thy social band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7671, line : "Greece in our cause shall arm some powerful hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7672, line : "The mightiest warrior of the Achaian name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7673, line : "Though bold and burning with desire of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7674, line : "Content the doubtful honour might forego,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7675, line : "So great the danger, and so brave the foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7677, line : "He said, and turn'd his brother's vengeful mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7678, line : "He stoop'd to reason, and his rage resign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7679, line : "No longer bent to rush on certain harms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7680, line : "His joyful friends unbrace his azure arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7682, line : "He from whose lips divine persuasion flows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7683, line : "Grave Nestor, then, in graceful act arose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7684, line : "Thus to the kings he spoke: \"What grief, what shame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7685, line : "Attend on Greece, and all the Grecian name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7686, line : "How shall, alas! her hoary heroes mourn"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7687, line : "Their sons degenerate, and their race a scorn!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7688, line : "What tears shall down thy silvery beard be roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7689, line : "O Peleus, old in arms, in wisdom old!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7690, line : "Once with what joy the generous prince would hear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7691, line : "Of every chief who fought this glorious war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7692, line : "Participate their fame, and pleased inquire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7693, line : "Each name, each action, and each hero's sire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7694, line : "Gods! should he see our warriors trembling stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7695, line : "And trembling all before one hostile hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7696, line : "How would he lift his aged arms on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7697, line : "Lament inglorious Greece, and beg to die!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7698, line : "Oh! would to all the immortal powers above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7699, line : "Minerva, Phoebus, and almighty Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7700, line : "Years might again roll back, my youth renew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7701, line : "And give this arm the spring which once it knew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7702, line : "When fierce in war, where Jardan's waters fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7703, line : "I led my troops to Phea's trembling wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7704, line : "And with the Arcadian spears my prowess tried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7705, line : "Where Celadon rolls down his rapid tide.(179)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7706, line : "There Ereuthalion braved us in the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7707, line : "Proud Areithous' dreadful arms to wield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7708, line : "Great Areithous, known from shore to shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7709, line : "By the huge, knotted, iron mace he bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7710, line : "No lance he shook, nor bent the twanging bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7711, line : "But broke, with this, the battle of the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7712, line : "Him not by manly force Lycurgus slew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7713, line : "Whose guileful javelin from the thicket flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7714, line : "Deep in a winding way his breast assailed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7715, line : "Nor aught the warrior's thundering mace avail'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7716, line : "Supine he fell: those arms which Mars before"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7717, line : "Had given the vanquish'd, now the victor bore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7718, line : "But when old age had dimm'd Lycurgus' eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7719, line : "To Ereuthalion he consign'd the prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7720, line : "Furious with this he crush'd our levell'd bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7721, line : "And dared the trial of the strongest hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7722, line : "Nor could the strongest hands his fury stay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7723, line : "All saw, and fear'd, his huge tempestuous sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7724, line : "Till I, the youngest of the host, appear'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7725, line : "And, youngest, met whom all our army fear'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7726, line : "I fought the chief: my arms Minerva crown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7727, line : "Prone fell the giant o'er a length of ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7728, line : "What then I was, O were your Nestor now!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7729, line : "Not Hector's self should want an equal foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7730, line : "But, warriors, you that youthful vigour boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7731, line : "The flower of Greece, the examples of our host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7732, line : "Sprung from such fathers, who such numbers sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7733, line : "Can you stand trembling, and desert the day?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7735, line : "His warm reproofs the listening kings inflame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7736, line : "And nine, the noblest of the Grecian name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7737, line : "Up-started fierce: but far before the rest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7738, line : "The king of men advanced his dauntless breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7739, line : "Then bold Tydides, great in arms, appear'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7740, line : "And next his bulk gigantic Ajax rear'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7741, line : "Oileus follow'd; Idomen was there,(180)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7742, line : "And Merion, dreadful as the god of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7743, line : "With these Eurypylus and Thoas stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7744, line : "And wise Ulysses closed the daring band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7745, line : "All these, alike inspired with noble rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7746, line : "Demand the fight. To whom the Pylian sage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7748, line : "\"Lest thirst of glory your brave souls divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7749, line : "What chief shall combat, let the gods decide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7750, line : "Whom heaven shall choose, be his the chance to raise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7751, line : "His country's fame, his own immortal praise.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7753, line : "The lots produced, each hero signs his own:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7754, line : "Then in the general's helm the fates are thrown,(181)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7755, line : "The people pray, with lifted eyes and hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7756, line : "And vows like these ascend from all the bands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7757, line : "\"Grant, thou Almighty! in whose hand is fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7758, line : "A worthy champion for the Grecian state:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7759, line : "This task let Ajax or Tydides prove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7760, line : "Or he, the king of kings, beloved by Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7761, line : "Old Nestor shook the casque. By heaven inspired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7762, line : "Leap'd forth the lot, of every Greek desired."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7763, line : "This from the right to left the herald bears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7764, line : "Held out in order to the Grecian peers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7765, line : "Each to his rival yields the mark unknown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7766, line : "Till godlike Ajax finds the lot his own;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7767, line : "Surveys the inscription with rejoicing eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7768, line : "Then casts before him, and with transport cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7770, line : "\"Warriors! I claim the lot, and arm with joy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7771, line : "Be mine the conquest of this chief of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7772, line : "Now while my brightest arms my limbs invest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7773, line : "To Saturn's son be all your vows address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7774, line : "But pray in secret, lest the foes should hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7775, line : "And deem your prayers the mean effect of fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7776, line : "Said I in secret? No, your vows declare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7777, line : "In such a voice as fills the earth and air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7778, line : "Lives there a chief whom Ajax ought to dread?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7779, line : "Ajax, in all the toils of battle bred!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7780, line : "From warlike Salamis I drew my birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7781, line : "And, born to combats, fear no force on earth.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7783, line : "He said. The troops with elevated eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7784, line : "Implore the god whose thunder rends the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7785, line : "\"O father of mankind, superior lord!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7786, line : "On lofty Ida's holy hill adored:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7787, line : "Who in the highest heaven hast fix'd thy throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7788, line : "Supreme of gods! unbounded and alone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7789, line : "Grant thou, that Telamon may bear away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7790, line : "The praise and conquest of this doubtful day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7791, line : "Or, if illustrious Hector be thy care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7792, line : "That both may claim it, and that both may share.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7794, line : "Now Ajax braced his dazzling armour on;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7795, line : "Sheathed in bright steel the giant-warrior shone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7796, line : "He moves to combat with majestic pace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7797, line : "So stalks in arms the grisly god of Thrace,(182)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7798, line : "When Jove to punish faithless men prepares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7799, line : "And gives whole nations to the waste of wars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7800, line : "Thus march'd the chief, tremendous as a god;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7801, line : "Grimly he smiled; earth trembled as he strode:(183)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7802, line : "His massy javelin quivering in his hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7803, line : "He stood, the bulwark of the Grecian band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7804, line : "Through every Argive heart new transport ran;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7805, line : "All Troy stood trembling at the mighty man:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7806, line : "Even Hector paused; and with new doubt oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7807, line : "Felt his great heart suspended in his breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7808, line : "'Twas vain to seek retreat, and vain to fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7809, line : "Himself had challenged, and the foe drew near."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7811, line : "Stern Telamon behind his ample shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7812, line : "As from a brazen tower, o'erlook'd the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7813, line : "Huge was its orb, with seven thick folds o'ercast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7814, line : "Of tough bull-hides; of solid brass the last,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7815, line : "(The work of Tychius, who in Hyle dwell'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7816, line : "And in all arts of armoury excell'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7817, line : "This Ajax bore before his manly breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7818, line : "And, threatening, thus his adverse chief address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7820, line : "\"Hector! approach my arm, and singly know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7821, line : "What strength thou hast, and what the Grecian foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7822, line : "Achilles shuns the fight; yet some there are,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7823, line : "Not void of soul, and not unskill'd in war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7824, line : "Let him, unactive on the sea-beat shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7825, line : "Indulge his wrath, and aid our arms no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7826, line : "Whole troops of heroes Greece has yet to boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7827, line : "And sends thee one, a sample of her host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7828, line : "Such as I am, I come to prove thy might;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7829, line : "No more--be sudden, and begin the fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7831, line : "\"O son of Telamon, thy country's pride!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7832, line : "(To Ajax thus the Trojan prince replied)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7833, line : "Me, as a boy, or woman, wouldst thou fright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7834, line : "New to the field, and trembling at the fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7835, line : "Thou meet'st a chief deserving of thy arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7836, line : "To combat born, and bred amidst alarms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7837, line : "I know to shift my ground, remount the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7838, line : "Turn, charge, and answer every call of war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7839, line : "To right, to left, the dexterous lance I wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7840, line : "And bear thick battle on my sounding shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7841, line : "But open be our fight, and bold each blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7842, line : "I steal no conquest from a noble foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7844, line : "He said, and rising, high above the field"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7845, line : "Whirl'd the long lance against the sevenfold shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7846, line : "Full on the brass descending from above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7847, line : "Through six bull-hides the furious weapon drove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7848, line : "Till in the seventh it fix'd. Then Ajax threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7849, line : "Through Hector's shield the forceful javelin flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7850, line : "His corslet enters, and his garment rends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7851, line : "And glancing downwards, near his flank descends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7852, line : "The wary Trojan shrinks, and bending low"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7853, line : "Beneath his buckler, disappoints the blow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7854, line : "From their bored shields the chiefs their javelins drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7855, line : "Then close impetuous, and the charge renew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7856, line : "Fierce as the mountain-lions bathed in blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7857, line : "Or foaming boars, the terror of the wood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7858, line : "At Ajax, Hector his long lance extends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7859, line : "The blunted point against the buckler bends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7860, line : "But Ajax, watchful as his foe drew near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7861, line : "Drove through the Trojan targe the knotty spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7862, line : "It reach'd his neck, with matchless strength impell'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7863, line : "Spouts the black gore, and dims his shining shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7864, line : "Yet ceased not Hector thus; but stooping down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7865, line : "In his strong hand up-heaved a flinty stone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7866, line : "Black, craggy, vast: to this his force he bends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7867, line : "Full on the brazen boss the stone descends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7868, line : "The hollow brass resounded with the shock:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7869, line : "Then Ajax seized the fragment of a rock,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7870, line : "Applied each nerve, and swinging round on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7871, line : "With force tempestuous, let the ruin fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7872, line : "The huge stone thundering through his buckler broke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7873, line : "His slacken'd knees received the numbing stroke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7874, line : "Great Hector falls extended on the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7875, line : "His bulk supporting on the shatter'd shield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7876, line : "Nor wanted heavenly aid: Apollo's might"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7877, line : "Confirm'd his sinews, and restored to fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7878, line : "And now both heroes their broad falchions drew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7879, line : "In flaming circles round their heads they flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7880, line : "But then by heralds' voice the word was given."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7881, line : "The sacred ministers of earth and heaven:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7882, line : "Divine Talthybius, whom the Greeks employ."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7883, line : "And sage Idaeus on the part of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7884, line : "Between the swords their peaceful sceptres rear'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7885, line : "And first Idaeus' awful voice was heard:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7887, line : "[Illustration: HECTOR AND AJAX SEPARATED BY THE HERALDS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7889, line : "HECTOR AND AJAX SEPARATED BY THE HERALDS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7892, line : "\"Forbear, my sons! your further force to prove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7893, line : "Both dear to men, and both beloved of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7894, line : "To either host your matchless worth is known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7895, line : "Each sounds your praise, and war is all your own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7896, line : "But now the Night extends her awful shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7897, line : "The goddess parts you; be the night obey'd.\"(184)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7899, line : "To whom great Ajax his high soul express'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7900, line : "\"O sage! to Hector be these words address'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7901, line : "Let him, who first provoked our chiefs to fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7902, line : "Let him demand the sanction of the night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7903, line : "If first he ask'd it, I content obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7904, line : "And cease the strife when Hector shows the way.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7906, line : "\"O first of Greeks! (his noble foe rejoin'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7907, line : "Whom heaven adorns, superior to thy kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7908, line : "With strength of body, and with worth of mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7909, line : "Now martial law commands us to forbear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7910, line : "Hereafter we shall meet in glorious war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7911, line : "Some future day shall lengthen out the strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7912, line : "And let the gods decide of death or life!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7913, line : "Since, then, the night extends her gloomy shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7914, line : "And heaven enjoins it, be the night obey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7915, line : "Return, brave Ajax, to thy Grecian friends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7916, line : "And joy the nations whom thy arm defends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7917, line : "As I shall glad each chief, and Trojan wife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7918, line : "Who wearies heaven with vows for Hector's life."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7919, line : "But let us, on this memorable day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7920, line : "Exchange some gift: that Greece and Troy may say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7921, line : "'Not hate, but glory, made these chiefs contend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7922, line : "And each brave foe was in his soul a friend.'\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7924, line : "With that, a sword with stars of silver graced,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7925, line : "The baldric studded, and the sheath enchased,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7926, line : "He gave the Greek. The generous Greek bestow'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7927, line : "A radiant belt that rich with purple glow'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7928, line : "Then with majestic grace they quit the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7929, line : "This seeks the Grecian, that the Phrygian train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7931, line : "The Trojan bands returning Hector wait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7932, line : "And hail with joy the Champion of their state;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7933, line : "Escaped great Ajax, they survey him round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7934, line : "Alive, unarm'd, and vigorous from his wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7935, line : "To Troy's high gates the godlike man they bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7936, line : "Their present triumph, as their late despair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7938, line : "But Ajax, glorying in his hardy deed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7939, line : "The well-arm'd Greeks to Agamemnon lead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7940, line : "A steer for sacrifice the king design'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7941, line : "Of full five years, and of the nobler kind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7942, line : "The victim falls; they strip the smoking hide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7943, line : "The beast they quarter, and the joints divide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7944, line : "Then spread the tables, the repast prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7945, line : "Each takes his seat, and each receives his share."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7946, line : "The king himself (an honorary sign)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7947, line : "Before great Ajax placed the mighty chine.(185)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7948, line : "When now the rage of hunger was removed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7949, line : "Nestor, in each persuasive art approved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7950, line : "The sage whose counsels long had sway'd the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7951, line : "In words like these his prudent thought express'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7953, line : "\"How dear, O kings! this fatal day has cost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7954, line : "What Greeks are perish'd! what a people lost!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7955, line : "What tides of blood have drench'd Scamander's shore!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7956, line : "What crowds of heroes sunk to rise no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7957, line : "Then hear me, chief! nor let the morrow's light"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7958, line : "Awake thy squadrons to new toils of fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7959, line : "Some space at least permit the war to breathe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7960, line : "While we to flames our slaughter'd friends bequeath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7961, line : "From the red field their scatter'd bodies bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7962, line : "And nigh the fleet a funeral structure rear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7963, line : "So decent urns their snowy bones may keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7964, line : "And pious children o'er their ashes weep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7965, line : "Here, where on one promiscuous pile they blazed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7966, line : "High o'er them all a general tomb be raised;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7967, line : "Next, to secure our camp and naval powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7968, line : "Raise an embattled wall, with lofty towers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7969, line : "From space to space be ample gates around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7970, line : "For passing chariots; and a trench profound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7971, line : "So Greece to combat shall in safety go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7972, line : "Nor fear the fierce incursions of the foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7973, line : "'Twas thus the sage his wholesome counsel moved;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7974, line : "The sceptred kings of Greece his words approved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7976, line : "Meanwhile, convened at Priam's palace-gate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7977, line : "The Trojan peers in nightly council sate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7978, line : "A senate void of order, as of choice:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7979, line : "Their hearts were fearful, and confused their voice."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7980, line : "Antenor, rising, thus demands their ear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7981, line : "\"Ye Trojans, Dardans, and auxiliars, hear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7982, line : "'Tis heaven the counsel of my breast inspires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7983, line : "And I but move what every god requires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7984, line : "Let Sparta's treasures be this hour restored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7985, line : "And Argive Helen own her ancient lord."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7986, line : "The ties of faith, the sworn alliance, broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7987, line : "Our impious battles the just gods provoke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7988, line : "As this advice ye practise, or reject,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7989, line : "So hope success, or dread the dire effect.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7991, line : "The senior spoke and sate. To whom replied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7992, line : "The graceful husband of the Spartan bride:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7993, line : "\"Cold counsels, Trojan, may become thy years"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7994, line : "But sound ungrateful in a warrior's ears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7995, line : "Old man, if void of fallacy or art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7996, line : "Thy words express the purpose of thy heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7997, line : "Thou, in thy time, more sound advice hast given;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7998, line : "But wisdom has its date, assign'd by heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 7999, line : "Then hear me, princes of the Trojan name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8000, line : "Their treasures I'll restore, but not the dame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8001, line : "My treasures too, for peace, I will resign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8002, line : "But be this bright possession ever mine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8004, line : "'Twas then, the growing discord to compose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8005, line : "Slow from his seat the reverend Priam rose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8006, line : "His godlike aspect deep attention drew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8007, line : "He paused, and these pacific words ensue:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8009, line : "\"Ye Trojans, Dardans, and auxiliar bands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8010, line : "Now take refreshment as the hour demands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8011, line : "Guard well the walls, relieve the watch of night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8012, line : "Till the new sun restores the cheerful light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8013, line : "Then shall our herald, to the Atrides sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8014, line : "Before their ships proclaim my son's intent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8015, line : "Next let a truce be ask'd, that Troy may burn"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8016, line : "Her slaughter'd heroes, and their bones inurn;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8017, line : "That done, once more the fate of war be tried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8018, line : "And whose the conquest, mighty Jove decide!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8020, line : "The monarch spoke: the warriors snatch'd with haste"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8021, line : "(Each at his post in arms) a short repast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8022, line : "Soon as the rosy morn had waked the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8023, line : "To the black ships Idaeus bent his way;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8024, line : "There, to the sons of Mars, in council found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8025, line : "He raised his voice: the host stood listening round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8027, line : "\"Ye sons of Atreus, and ye Greeks, give ear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8028, line : "The words of Troy, and Troy's great monarch, hear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8029, line : "Pleased may ye hear (so heaven succeed my prayers)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8030, line : "What Paris, author of the war, declares."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8031, line : "The spoils and treasures he to Ilion bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8032, line : "(Oh had he perish'd ere they touch'd our shore!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8033, line : "He proffers injured Greece: with large increase"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8034, line : "Of added Trojan wealth to buy the peace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8035, line : "But to restore the beauteous bride again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8036, line : "This Greece demands, and Troy requests in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8037, line : "Next, O ye chiefs! we ask a truce to burn"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8038, line : "Our slaughter'd heroes, and their bones inurn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8039, line : "That done, once more the fate of war be tried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8040, line : "And whose the conquest, mighty Jove decide!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8042, line : "The Greeks gave ear, but none the silence broke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8043, line : "At length Tydides rose, and rising spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8044, line : "\"Oh, take not, friends! defrauded of your fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8045, line : "Their proffer'd wealth, nor even the Spartan dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8046, line : "Let conquest make them ours: fate shakes their wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8047, line : "And Troy already totters to her fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8049, line : "The admiring chiefs, and all the Grecian name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8050, line : "With general shouts return'd him loud acclaim."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8051, line : "Then thus the king of kings rejects the peace:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8052, line : "\"Herald! in him thou hear'st the voice of Greece"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8053, line : "For what remains; let funeral flames be fed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8054, line : "With heroes' corps: I war not with the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8055, line : "Go search your slaughtered chiefs on yonder plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8056, line : "And gratify the manes of the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8057, line : "Be witness, Jove, whose thunder rolls on high!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8058, line : "He said, and rear'd his sceptre to the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8060, line : "To sacred Troy, where all her princes lay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8061, line : "To wait the event, the herald bent his way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8062, line : "He came, and standing in the midst, explain'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8063, line : "The peace rejected, but the truce obtain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8064, line : "Straight to their several cares the Trojans move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8065, line : "Some search the plains, some fell the sounding grove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8066, line : "Nor less the Greeks, descending on the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8067, line : "Hew'd the green forests, and the bodies bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8068, line : "And now from forth the chambers of the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8069, line : "To shed his sacred light on earth again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8070, line : "Arose the golden chariot of the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8071, line : "And tipp'd the mountains with a purple ray."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8072, line : "In mingled throngs the Greek and Trojan train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8073, line : "Through heaps of carnage search'd the mournful plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8074, line : "Scarce could the friend his slaughter'd friend explore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8075, line : "With dust dishonour'd, and deformed with gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8076, line : "The wounds they wash'd, their pious tears they shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8077, line : "And, laid along their cars, deplored the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8078, line : "Sage Priam check'd their grief: with silent haste"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8079, line : "The bodies decent on the piles were placed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8080, line : "With melting hearts the cold remains they burn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8081, line : "And, sadly slow, to sacred Troy return'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8082, line : "Nor less the Greeks their pious sorrows shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8083, line : "And decent on the pile dispose the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8084, line : "The cold remains consume with equal care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8085, line : "And slowly, sadly, to their fleet repair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8086, line : "Now, ere the morn had streak'd with reddening light"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8087, line : "The doubtful confines of the day and night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8088, line : "About the dying flames the Greeks appear'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8089, line : "And round the pile a general tomb they rear'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8090, line : "Then, to secure the camp and naval powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8091, line : "They raised embattled walls with lofty towers:(186)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8092, line : "From space to space were ample gates around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8093, line : "For passing chariots, and a trench profound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8094, line : "Of large extent; and deep in earth below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8095, line : "Strong piles infix'd stood adverse to the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8097, line : "So toil'd the Greeks: meanwhile the gods above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8098, line : "In shining circle round their father Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8099, line : "Amazed beheld the wondrous works of man:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8100, line : "Then he, whose trident shakes the earth, began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8102, line : "\"What mortals henceforth shall our power adore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8103, line : "Our fanes frequent, our oracles implore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8104, line : "If the proud Grecians thus successful boast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8105, line : "Their rising bulwarks on the sea-beat coast?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8106, line : "See the long walls extending to the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8107, line : "No god consulted, and no victim slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8108, line : "Their fame shall fill the world's remotest ends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8109, line : "Wide as the morn her golden beam extends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8110, line : "While old Laomedon's divine abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8111, line : "Those radiant structures raised by labouring gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8112, line : "Shall, razed and lost, in long oblivion sleep.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8113, line : "Thus spoke the hoary monarch of the deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8115, line : "The almighty Thunderer with a frown replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8116, line : "That clouds the world, and blackens half the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8117, line : "\"Strong god of ocean! thou, whose rage can make"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8118, line : "The solid earth's eternal basis shake!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8119, line : "What cause of fear from mortal works could move(187)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8120, line : "The meanest subject of our realms above?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8121, line : "Where'er the sun's refulgent rays are cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8122, line : "Thy power is honour'd, and thy fame shall last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8123, line : "But yon proud work no future age shall view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8124, line : "No trace remain where once the glory grew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8125, line : "The sapp'd foundations by thy force shall fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8126, line : "And, whelm'd beneath the waves, drop the huge wall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8127, line : "Vast drifts of sand shall change the former shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8128, line : "The ruin vanish'd, and the name no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8130, line : "Thus they in heaven: while, o'er the Grecian train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8131, line : "The rolling sun descending to the main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8132, line : "Beheld the finish'd work. Their bulls they slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8133, line : "Back from the tents the savoury vapour flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8134, line : "And now the fleet, arrived from Lemnos' strands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8135, line : "With Bacchus' blessings cheered the generous bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8136, line : "Of fragrant wines the rich Eunaeus sent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8137, line : "A thousant measures to the royal tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8138, line : "(Eunaeus, whom Hypsipyle of yore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8139, line : "To Jason, shepherd of his people, bore,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8140, line : "The rest they purchased at their proper cost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8141, line : "And well the plenteous freight supplied the host:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8142, line : "Each, in exchange, proportion'd treasures gave;(188)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8143, line : "Some, brass or iron; some, an ox, or slave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8144, line : "All night they feast, the Greek and Trojan powers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8145, line : "Those on the fields, and these within their towers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8146, line : "But Jove averse the signs of wrath display'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8147, line : "And shot red lightnings through the gloomy shade:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8148, line : "Humbled they stood; pale horror seized on all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8149, line : "While the deep thunder shook the aerial hall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8150, line : "Each pour'd to Jove before the bowl was crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8151, line : "And large libations drench'd the thirsty ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8152, line : "Then late, refresh'd with sleep from toils of fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8153, line : "Enjoy'd the balmy blessings of the night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8155, line : "[Illustration: GREEK AMPHORA--WINE VESSELS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8157, line : "GREEK AMPHORA--WINE VESSELS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8163, line : "BOOK VIII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8166, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8168, line : "THE SECOND BATTLE, AND THE DISTRESS OF THE GREEKS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8170, line : "Jupiter assembles a council of the deities, and threatens them with the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8171, line : "pains of Tartarus if they assist either side: Minerva only obtains of him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8172, line : "that she may direct the Greeks by her counsels.(189) his balances the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8173, line : "fates of both, and affrights the Greeks with his thunders and lightnings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8174, line : "Nestor alone continues in the field in great danger: Diomed relieves him;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8175, line : "whose exploits, and those of Hector, are excellently described. Juno"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8176, line : "endeavours to animate Neptune to the assistance of the Greeks, but in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8177, line : "vain. The acts of Teucer, who is at length wounded by Hector, and carried"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8178, line : "off. Juno and Minerva prepare to aid the Grecians, but are restrained by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8179, line : "Iris, sent from Jupiter. The night puts an end to the battle. Hector"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8180, line : "continues in the field, (the Greeks being driven to their fortifications"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8181, line : "before the ships,) and gives orders to keep the watch all night in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8182, line : "camp, to prevent the enemy from re-embarking and escaping by flight. They"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8183, line : "kindle fires through all the fields, and pass the night under arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8185, line : "The time of seven and twenty days is employed from the opening of the poem"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8186, line : "to the end of this book. The scene here (except of the celestial machines)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8187, line : "lies in the field towards the seashore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8189, line : "Aurora now, fair daughter of the dawn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8190, line : "Sprinkled with rosy light the dewy lawn;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8191, line : "When Jove convened the senate of the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8192, line : "Where high Olympus' cloudy tops arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8193, line : "The sire of gods his awful silence broke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8194, line : "The heavens attentive trembled as he spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8196, line : "\"Celestial states! immortal gods! give ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8197, line : "Hear our decree, and reverence what ye hear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8198, line : "The fix'd decree which not all heaven can move;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8199, line : "Thou, fate! fulfil it! and, ye powers, approve!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8200, line : "What god but enters yon forbidden field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8201, line : "Who yields assistance, or but wills to yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8202, line : "Back to the skies with shame he shall be driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8203, line : "Gash'd with dishonest wounds, the scorn of heaven;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8204, line : "Or far, oh far, from steep Olympus thrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8205, line : "Low in the dark Tartarean gulf shall groan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8206, line : "With burning chains fix'd to the brazen floors,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8207, line : "And lock'd by hell's inexorable doors;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8208, line : "As deep beneath the infernal centre hurl'd,(190)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8209, line : "As from that centre to the ethereal world."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8210, line : "Let him who tempts me, dread those dire abodes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8211, line : "And know, the Almighty is the god of gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8212, line : "League all your forces, then, ye powers above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8213, line : "Join all, and try the omnipotence of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8214, line : "Let down our golden everlasting chain(191)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8215, line : "Whose strong embrace holds heaven, and earth, and main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8216, line : "Strive all, of mortal and immortal birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8217, line : "To drag, by this, the Thunderer down to earth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8218, line : "Ye strive in vain! if I but stretch this hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8219, line : "I heave the gods, the ocean, and the land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8220, line : "I fix the chain to great Olympus' height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8221, line : "And the vast world hangs trembling in my sight!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8222, line : "For such I reign, unbounded and above;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8223, line : "And such are men, and gods, compared to Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8225, line : "The all-mighty spoke, nor durst the powers reply:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8226, line : "A reverend horror silenced all the sky;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8227, line : "Trembling they stood before their sovereign's look;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8228, line : "At length his best-beloved, the power of wisdom, spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8230, line : "\"O first and greatest! God, by gods adored"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8231, line : "We own thy might, our father and our lord!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8232, line : "But, ah! permit to pity human state:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8233, line : "If not to help, at least lament their fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8234, line : "From fields forbidden we submiss refrain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8235, line : "With arms unaiding mourn our Argives slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8236, line : "Yet grant my counsels still their breasts may move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8237, line : "Or all must perish in the wrath of Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8239, line : "The cloud-compelling god her suit approved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8240, line : "And smiled superior on his best beloved;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8241, line : "Then call'd his coursers, and his chariot took;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8242, line : "The stedfast firmament beneath them shook:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8243, line : "Rapt by the ethereal steeds the chariot roll'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8244, line : "Brass were their hoofs, their curling manes of gold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8245, line : "Of heaven's undrossy gold the gods array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8246, line : "Refulgent, flash'd intolerable day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8247, line : "High on the throne he shines: his coursers fly"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8248, line : "Between the extended earth and starry sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8249, line : "But when to Ida's topmost height he came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8250, line : "(Fair nurse of fountains, and of savage game,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8251, line : "Where o'er her pointed summits proudly raised,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8252, line : "His fane breathed odours, and his altar blazed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8253, line : "There, from his radiant car, the sacred sire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8254, line : "Of gods and men released the steeds of fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8255, line : "Blue ambient mists the immortal steeds embraced;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8256, line : "High on the cloudy point his seat he placed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8257, line : "Thence his broad eye the subject world surveys,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8258, line : "The town, and tents, and navigable seas."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8260, line : "Now had the Grecians snatch'd a short repast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8261, line : "And buckled on their shining arms with haste."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8262, line : "Troy roused as soon; for on this dreadful day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8263, line : "The fate of fathers, wives, and infants lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8264, line : "The gates unfolding pour forth all their train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8265, line : "Squadrons on squadrons cloud the dusky plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8266, line : "Men, steeds, and chariots shake the trembling ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8267, line : "The tumult thickens, and the skies resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8268, line : "And now with shouts the shocking armies closed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8269, line : "To lances lances, shields to shields opposed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8270, line : "Host against host with shadowy legends drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8271, line : "The sounding darts in iron tempests flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8272, line : "Victors and vanquish'd join promiscuous cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8273, line : "Triumphant shouts and dying groans arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8274, line : "With streaming blood the slippery fields are dyed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8275, line : "And slaughter'd heroes swell the dreadful tide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8276, line : "Long as the morning beams, increasing bright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8277, line : "O'er heaven's clear azure spread the sacred light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8278, line : "Commutual death the fate of war confounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8279, line : "Each adverse battle gored with equal wounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8280, line : "But when the sun the height of heaven ascends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8281, line : "The sire of gods his golden scales suspends,(192)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8282, line : "With equal hand: in these explored the fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8283, line : "Of Greece and Troy, and poised the mighty weight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8284, line : "Press'd with its load, the Grecian balance lies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8285, line : "Low sunk on earth, the Trojan strikes the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8286, line : "Then Jove from Ida's top his horrors spreads;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8287, line : "The clouds burst dreadful o'er the Grecian heads;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8288, line : "Thick lightnings flash; the muttering thunder rolls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8289, line : "Their strength he withers, and unmans their souls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8290, line : "Before his wrath the trembling hosts retire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8291, line : "The gods in terrors, and the skies on fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8292, line : "Nor great Idomeneus that sight could bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8293, line : "Nor each stern Ajax, thunderbolts of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8294, line : "Nor he, the king of war, the alarm sustain'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8295, line : "Nestor alone, amidst the storm remain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8296, line : "Unwilling he remain'd, for Paris' dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8297, line : "Had pierced his courser in a mortal part;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8298, line : "Fix'd in the forehead, where the springing man"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8299, line : "Curl'd o'er the brow, it stung him to the brain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8300, line : "Mad with his anguish, he begins to rear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8301, line : "Paw with his hoofs aloft, and lash the air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8302, line : "Scarce had his falchion cut the reins, and freed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8303, line : "The encumber'd chariot from the dying steed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8304, line : "When dreadful Hector, thundering through the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8305, line : "Pour'd to the tumult on his whirling car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8306, line : "That day had stretch'd beneath his matchless hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8307, line : "The hoary monarch of the Pylian band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8308, line : "But Diomed beheld; from forth the crowd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8309, line : "He rush'd, and on Ulysses call'd aloud:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8311, line : "\"Whither, oh whither does Ulysses run?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8312, line : "Oh, flight unworthy great Laertes' son!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8313, line : "Mix'd with the vulgar shall thy fate be found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8314, line : "Pierced in the back, a vile, dishonest wound?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8315, line : "Oh turn and save from Hector's direful rage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8316, line : "The glory of the Greeks, the Pylian sage.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8317, line : "His fruitless words are lost unheard in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8318, line : "Ulysses seeks the ships, and shelters there."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8319, line : "But bold Tydides to the rescue goes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8320, line : "A single warrior midst a host of foes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8321, line : "Before the coursers with a sudden spring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8322, line : "He leap'd, and anxious thus bespoke the king:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8324, line : "\"Great perils, father! wait the unequal fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8325, line : "These younger champions will oppress thy might."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8326, line : "Thy veins no more with ancient vigour glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8327, line : "Weak is thy servant, and thy coursers slow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8328, line : "Then haste, ascend my seat, and from the car"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8329, line : "Observe the steeds of Tros, renown'd in war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8330, line : "Practised alike to turn, to stop, to chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8331, line : "To dare the fight, or urge the rapid race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8332, line : "These late obey'd Ćneas' guiding rein;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8333, line : "Leave thou thy chariot to our faithful train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8334, line : "With these against yon Trojans will we go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8335, line : "Nor shall great Hector want an equal foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8336, line : "Fierce as he is, even he may learn to fear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8337, line : "The thirsty fury of my flying spear.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8339, line : "Thus said the chief; and Nestor, skill'd in war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8340, line : "Approves his counsel, and ascends the car:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8341, line : "The steeds he left, their trusty servants hold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8342, line : "Eurymedon, and Sthenelus the bold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8343, line : "The reverend charioteer directs the course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8344, line : "And strains his aged arm to lash the horse."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8345, line : "Hector they face; unknowing how to fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8346, line : "Fierce he drove on; Tydides whirl'd his spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8347, line : "The spear with erring haste mistook its way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8348, line : "But plunged in Eniopeus' bosom lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8349, line : "His opening hand in death forsakes the rein;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8350, line : "The steeds fly back: he falls, and spurns the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8351, line : "Great Hector sorrows for his servant kill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8352, line : "Yet unrevenged permits to press the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8353, line : "Till, to supply his place and rule the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8354, line : "Rose Archeptolemus, the fierce in war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8355, line : "And now had death and horror cover'd all;(193)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8356, line : "Like timorous flocks the Trojans in their wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8357, line : "Inclosed had bled: but Jove with awful sound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8358, line : "Roll'd the big thunder o'er the vast profound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8359, line : "Full in Tydides' face the lightning flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8360, line : "The ground before him flamed with sulphur blue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8361, line : "The quivering steeds fell prostrate at the sight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8362, line : "And Nestor's trembling hand confess'd his fright:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8363, line : "He dropp'd the reins: and, shook with sacred dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8364, line : "Thus, turning, warn'd the intrepid Diomed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8366, line : "\"O chief! too daring in thy friend's defence"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8367, line : "Retire advised, and urge the chariot hence."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8368, line : "This day, averse, the sovereign of the skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8369, line : "Assists great Hector, and our palm denies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8370, line : "Some other sun may see the happier hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8371, line : "When Greece shall conquer by his heavenly power."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8372, line : "'Tis not in man his fix'd decree to move:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8373, line : "The great will glory to submit to Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8375, line : "\"O reverend prince! (Tydides thus replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8376, line : "Thy years are awful, and thy words are wise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8377, line : "But ah, what grief! should haughty Hector boast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8378, line : "I fled inglorious to the guarded coast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8379, line : "Before that dire disgrace shall blast my fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8380, line : "O'erwhelm me, earth; and hide a warrior's shame!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8381, line : "To whom Gerenian Nestor thus replied:(194)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8382, line : "\"Gods! can thy courage fear the Phrygian's pride?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8383, line : "Hector may vaunt, but who shall heed the boast?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8384, line : "Not those who felt thy arm, the Dardan host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8385, line : "Nor Troy, yet bleeding in her heroes lost;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8386, line : "Not even a Phrygian dame, who dreads the sword"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8387, line : "That laid in dust her loved, lamented lord.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8388, line : "He said, and, hasty, o'er the gasping throng"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8389, line : "Drives the swift steeds: the chariot smokes along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8390, line : "The shouts of Trojans thicken in the wind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8391, line : "The storm of hissing javelins pours behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8392, line : "Then with a voice that shakes the solid skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8393, line : "Pleased, Hector braves the warrior as he flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8394, line : "\"Go, mighty hero! graced above the rest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8395, line : "In seats of council and the sumptuous feast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8396, line : "Now hope no more those honours from thy train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8397, line : "Go less than woman, in the form of man!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8398, line : "To scale our walls, to wrap our towers in flames,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8399, line : "To lead in exile the fair Phrygian dames,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8400, line : "Thy once proud hopes, presumptuous prince! are fled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8401, line : "This arm shall reach thy heart, and stretch thee dead.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8403, line : "Now fears dissuade him, and now hopes invite."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8404, line : "To stop his coursers, and to stand the fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8405, line : "Thrice turn'd the chief, and thrice imperial Jove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8406, line : "On Ida's summits thunder'd from above."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8407, line : "Great Hector heard; he saw the flashing light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8408, line : "(The sign of conquest,) and thus urged the fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8410, line : "\"Hear, every Trojan, Lycian, Dardan band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8411, line : "All famed in war, and dreadful hand to hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8412, line : "Be mindful of the wreaths your arms have won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8413, line : "Your great forefathers' glories, and your own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8414, line : "Heard ye the voice of Jove? Success and fame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8415, line : "Await on Troy, on Greece eternal shame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8416, line : "In vain they skulk behind their boasted wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8417, line : "Weak bulwarks; destined by this arm to fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8418, line : "High o'er their slighted trench our steeds shall bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8419, line : "And pass victorious o'er the levell'd mound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8420, line : "Soon as before yon hollow ships we stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8421, line : "Fight each with flames, and toss the blazing brand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8422, line : "Till, their proud navy wrapt in smoke and fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8423, line : "All Greece, encompass'd, in one blaze expires.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8425, line : "Furious he said; then bending o'er the yoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8426, line : "Encouraged his proud steeds, while thus he spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8428, line : "\"Now, Xanthus, Ćthon, Lampus, urge the chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8429, line : "And thou, Podargus! prove thy generous race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8430, line : "Be fleet, be fearless, this important day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8431, line : "And all your master's well-spent care repay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8432, line : "For this, high-fed, in plenteous stalls ye stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8433, line : "Served with pure wheat, and by a princess' hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8434, line : "For this my spouse, of great Aetion's line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8435, line : "So oft has steep'd the strengthening grain in wine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8436, line : "Now swift pursue, now thunder uncontroll'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8437, line : "Give me to seize rich Nestor's shield of gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8438, line : "From Tydeus' shoulders strip the costly load,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8439, line : "Vulcanian arms, the labour of a god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8440, line : "These if we gain, then victory, ye powers!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8441, line : "This night, this glorious night, the fleet is ours!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8443, line : "That heard, deep anguish stung Saturnia's soul;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8444, line : "She shook her throne, that shook the starry pole:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8445, line : "And thus to Neptune: \"Thou, whose force can make"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8446, line : "The stedfast earth from her foundations shake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8447, line : "Seest thou the Greeks by fates unjust oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8448, line : "Nor swells thy heart in that immortal breast?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8449, line : "Yet Ćgae, Helice, thy power obey,(195)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8450, line : "And gifts unceasing on thine altars lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8451, line : "Would all the deities of Greece combine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8452, line : "In vain the gloomy Thunderer might repine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8453, line : "Sole should he sit, with scarce a god to friend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8454, line : "And see his Trojans to the shades descend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8455, line : "Such be the scene from his Idaean bower;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8456, line : "Ungrateful prospect to the sullen power!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8458, line : "Neptune with wrath rejects the rash design:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8459, line : "\"What rage, what madness, furious queen! is thine?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8460, line : "I war not with the highest. All above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8461, line : "Submit and tremble at the hand of Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8463, line : "Now godlike Hector, to whose matchless might"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8464, line : "Jove gave the glory of the destined fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8465, line : "Squadrons on squadrons drives, and fills the fields"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8466, line : "With close-ranged chariots, and with thicken'd shields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8467, line : "Where the deep trench in length extended lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8468, line : "Compacted troops stand wedged in firm array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8469, line : "A dreadful front! they shake the brands, and threat"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8470, line : "With long-destroying flames the hostile fleet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8471, line : "The king of men, by Juno's self inspired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8472, line : "Toil'd through the tents, and all his army fired."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8473, line : "Swift as he moved, he lifted in his hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8474, line : "His purple robe, bright ensign of command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8475, line : "High on the midmost bark the king appear'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8476, line : "There, from Ulysses' deck, his voice was heard:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8477, line : "To Ajax and Achilles reach'd the sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8478, line : "Whose distant ships the guarded navy bound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8479, line : "\"O Argives! shame of human race! (he cried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8480, line : "The hollow vessels to his voice replied,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8481, line : "Where now are all your glorious boasts of yore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8482, line : "Your hasty triumphs on the Lemnian shore?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8483, line : "Each fearless hero dares a hundred foes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8484, line : "While the feast lasts, and while the goblet flows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8485, line : "But who to meet one martial man is found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8486, line : "When the fight rages, and the flames surround?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8487, line : "O mighty Jove! O sire of the distress'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8488, line : "Was ever king like me, like me oppress'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8489, line : "With power immense, with justice arm'd in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8490, line : "My glory ravish'd, and my people slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8491, line : "To thee my vows were breathed from every shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8492, line : "What altar smoked not with our victims' gore?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8493, line : "With fat of bulls I fed the constant flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8494, line : "And ask'd destruction to the Trojan name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8495, line : "Now, gracious god! far humbler our demand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8496, line : "Give these at least to 'scape from Hector's hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8497, line : "And save the relics of the Grecian land!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8499, line : "Thus pray'd the king, and heaven's great father heard"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8500, line : "His vows, in bitterness of soul preferr'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8501, line : "The wrath appeased, by happy signs declares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8502, line : "And gives the people to their monarch's prayers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8503, line : "His eagle, sacred bird of heaven! he sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8504, line : "A fawn his talons truss'd, (divine portent!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8505, line : "High o'er the wondering hosts he soar'd above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8506, line : "Who paid their vows to Panomphaean Jove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8507, line : "Then let the prey before his altar fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8508, line : "The Greeks beheld, and transport seized on all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8509, line : "Encouraged by the sign, the troops revive,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8510, line : "And fierce on Troy with doubled fury drive."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8511, line : "Tydides first, of all the Grecian force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8512, line : "O'er the broad ditch impell'd his foaming horse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8513, line : "Pierced the deep ranks, their strongest battle tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8514, line : "And dyed his javelin red with Trojan gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8515, line : "Young Agelaus (Phradmon was his sire)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8516, line : "With flying coursers shunn'd his dreadful ire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8517, line : "Struck through the back, the Phrygian fell oppress'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8518, line : "The dart drove on, and issued at his breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8519, line : "Headlong he quits the car: his arms resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8520, line : "His ponderous buckler thunders on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8521, line : "Forth rush a tide of Greeks, the passage freed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8522, line : "The Atridae first, the Ajaces next succeed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8523, line : "Meriones, like Mars in arms renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8524, line : "And godlike Idomen, now passed the mound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8525, line : "Evaemon's son next issues to the foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8526, line : "And last young Teucer with his bended bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8527, line : "Secure behind the Telamonian shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8528, line : "The skilful archer wide survey'd the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8529, line : "With every shaft some hostile victim slew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8530, line : "Then close beneath the sevenfold orb withdrew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8531, line : "The conscious infant so, when fear alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8532, line : "Retires for safety to the mother's arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8533, line : "Thus Ajax guards his brother in the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8534, line : "Moves as he moves, and turns the shining shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8535, line : "Who first by Teucer's mortal arrows bled?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8536, line : "Orsilochus; then fell Ormenus dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8537, line : "The godlike Lycophon next press'd the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8538, line : "With Chromius, Daetor, Ophelestes slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8539, line : "Bold Hamopaon breathless sunk to ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8540, line : "The bloody pile great Melanippus crown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8541, line : "Heaps fell on heaps, sad trophies of his art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8542, line : "A Trojan ghost attending every dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8543, line : "Great Agamemnon views with joyful eye"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8544, line : "The ranks grow thinner as his arrows fly:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8545, line : "\"O youth forever dear! (the monarch cried)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8546, line : "Thus, always thus, thy early worth be tried;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8547, line : "Thy brave example shall retrieve our host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8548, line : "Thy country's saviour, and thy father's boast!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8549, line : "Sprung from an alien's bed thy sire to grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8550, line : "The vigorous offspring of a stolen embrace:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8551, line : "Proud of his boy, he own'd the generous flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8552, line : "And the brave son repays his cares with fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8553, line : "Now hear a monarch's vow: If heaven's high powers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8554, line : "Give me to raze Troy's long-defended towers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8555, line : "Whatever treasures Greece for me design,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8556, line : "The next rich honorary gift be thine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8557, line : "Some golden tripod, or distinguished car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8558, line : "With coursers dreadful in the ranks of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8559, line : "Or some fair captive, whom thy eyes approve,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8560, line : "Shall recompense the warrior's toils with love.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8562, line : "To this the chief: \"With praise the rest inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8563, line : "Nor urge a soul already fill'd with fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8564, line : "What strength I have, be now in battle tried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8565, line : "Till every shaft in Phrygian blood be dyed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8566, line : "Since rallying from our wall we forced the foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8567, line : "Still aim'd at Hector have I bent my bow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8568, line : "Eight forky arrows from this hand have fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8569, line : "And eight bold heroes by their points lie dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8570, line : "But sure some god denies me to destroy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8571, line : "This fury of the field, this dog of Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8573, line : "He said, and twang'd the string. The weapon flies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8574, line : "At Hector's breast, and sings along the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8575, line : "He miss'd the mark; but pierced Gorgythio's heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8576, line : "And drench'd in royal blood the thirsty dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8577, line : "(Fair Castianira, nymph of form divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8578, line : "This offspring added to king Priam's line.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8579, line : "As full-blown poppies, overcharged with rain,(196)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8580, line : "Decline the head, and drooping kiss the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8581, line : "So sinks the youth: his beauteous head, depress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8582, line : "Beneath his helmet, drops upon his breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8583, line : "Another shaft the raging archer drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8584, line : "That other shaft with erring fury flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8585, line : "(From Hector, Phoebus turn'd the flying wound,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8586, line : "Yet fell not dry or guiltless to the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8587, line : "Thy breast, brave Archeptolemus! it tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8588, line : "And dipp'd its feathers in no vulgar gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8589, line : "Headlong he falls: his sudden fall alarms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8590, line : "The steeds, that startle at his sounding arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8591, line : "Hector with grief his charioteer beheld"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8592, line : "All pale and breathless on the sanguine field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8593, line : "Then bids Cebriones direct the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8594, line : "Quits his bright car, and issues on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8595, line : "Dreadful he shouts: from earth a stone he took,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8596, line : "And rush'd on Teucer with the lifted rock."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8597, line : "The youth already strain'd the forceful yew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8598, line : "The shaft already to his shoulder drew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8599, line : "The feather in his hand, just wing'd for flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8600, line : "Touch'd where the neck and hollow chest unite;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8601, line : "There, where the juncture knits the channel bone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8602, line : "The furious chief discharged the craggy stone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8603, line : "The bow-string burst beneath the ponderous blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8604, line : "And his numb'd hand dismiss'd his useless bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8605, line : "He fell: but Ajax his broad shield display'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8606, line : "And screen'd his brother with the mighty shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8607, line : "Till great Alaster, and Mecistheus, bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8608, line : "The batter'd archer groaning to the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8610, line : "Troy yet found grace before the Olympian sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8611, line : "He arm'd their hands, and fill'd their breasts with fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8612, line : "The Greeks repulsed, retreat behind their wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8613, line : "Or in the trench on heaps confusedly fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8614, line : "First of the foe, great Hector march'd along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8615, line : "With terror clothed, and more than mortal strong."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8616, line : "As the bold hound, that gives the lion chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8617, line : "With beating bosom, and with eager pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8618, line : "Hangs on his haunch, or fastens on his heels,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8619, line : "Guards as he turns, and circles as he wheels;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8620, line : "Thus oft the Grecians turn'd, but still they flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8621, line : "Thus following, Hector still the hindmost slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8622, line : "When flying they had pass'd the trench profound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8623, line : "And many a chief lay gasping on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8624, line : "Before the ships a desperate stand they made,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8625, line : "And fired the troops, and called the gods to aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8626, line : "Fierce on his rattling chariot Hector came:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8627, line : "His eyes like Gorgon shot a sanguine flame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8628, line : "That wither'd all their host: like Mars he stood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8629, line : "Dire as the monster, dreadful as the god!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8630, line : "Their strong distress the wife of Jove survey'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8631, line : "Then pensive thus, to war's triumphant maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8633, line : "\"O daughter of that god, whose arm can wield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8634, line : "The avenging bolt, and shake the sable shield!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8635, line : "Now, in this moment of her last despair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8636, line : "Shall wretched Greece no more confess our care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8637, line : "Condemn'd to suffer the full force of fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8638, line : "And drain the dregs of heaven's relentless hate?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8639, line : "Gods! shall one raging hand thus level all?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8640, line : "What numbers fell! what numbers yet shall fall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8641, line : "What power divine shall Hector's wrath assuage?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8642, line : "Still swells the slaughter, and still grows the rage!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8644, line : "So spake the imperial regent of the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8645, line : "To whom the goddess with the azure eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8647, line : "\"Long since had Hector stain'd these fields with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8648, line : "Stretch'd by some Argive on his native shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8649, line : "But he above, the sire of heaven, withstands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8650, line : "Mocks our attempts, and slights our just demands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8651, line : "The stubborn god, inflexible and hard,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8652, line : "Forgets my service and deserved reward:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8653, line : "Saved I, for this, his favourite son distress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8654, line : "By stern Eurystheus with long labours press'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8655, line : "He begg'd, with tears he begg'd, in deep dismay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8656, line : "I shot from heaven, and gave his arm the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8657, line : "Oh had my wisdom known this dire event,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8658, line : "When to grim Pluto's gloomy gates he went;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8659, line : "The triple dog had never felt his chain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8660, line : "Nor Styx been cross'd, nor hell explored in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8661, line : "Averse to me of all his heaven of gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8662, line : "At Thetis' suit the partial Thunderer nods;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8663, line : "To grace her gloomy, fierce, resenting son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8664, line : "My hopes are frustrate, and my Greeks undone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8665, line : "Some future day, perhaps, he may be moved"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8666, line : "To call his blue-eyed maid his best beloved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8667, line : "Haste, launch thy chariot, through yon ranks to ride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8668, line : "Myself will arm, and thunder at thy side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8669, line : "Then, goddess! say, shall Hector glory then?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8670, line : "(That terror of the Greeks, that man of men)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8671, line : "When Juno's self, and Pallas shall appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8672, line : "All dreadful in the crimson walks of war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8673, line : "What mighty Trojan then, on yonder shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8674, line : "Expiring, pale, and terrible no more,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8675, line : "Shall feast the fowls, and glut the dogs with gore?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8677, line : "She ceased, and Juno rein'd the steeds with care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8678, line : "(Heaven's awful empress, Saturn's other heir:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8679, line : "Pallas, meanwhile, her various veil unbound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8680, line : "With flowers adorn'd, with art immortal crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8681, line : "The radiant robe her sacred fingers wove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8682, line : "Floats in rich waves, and spreads the court of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8683, line : "Her father's arms her mighty limbs invest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8684, line : "His cuirass blazes on her ample breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8685, line : "The vigorous power the trembling car ascends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8686, line : "Shook by her arm, the massy javelin bends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8687, line : "Huge, ponderous, strong! that when her fury burns"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8688, line : "Proud tyrants humbles, and whole hosts o'erturns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8690, line : "Saturnia lends the lash; the coursers fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8691, line : "Smooth glides the chariot through the liquid sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8692, line : "Heaven's gates spontaneous open to the powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8693, line : "Heaven's golden gates, kept by the winged Hours."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8694, line : "Commission'd in alternate watch they stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8695, line : "The sun's bright portals and the skies command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8696, line : "Close, or unfold, the eternal gates of day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8697, line : "Bar heaven with clouds, or roll those clouds away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8698, line : "The sounding hinges ring, the clouds divide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8699, line : "Prone down the steep of heaven their course they guide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8700, line : "But Jove, incensed, from Ida's top survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8701, line : "And thus enjoin'd the many-colour'd maid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8703, line : "[Illustration: JUNO AND MINERVA GOING TO ASSIST THE GREEKS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8705, line : "JUNO AND MINERVA GOING TO ASSIST THE GREEKS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8708, line : "\"Thaumantia! mount the winds, and stop their car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8709, line : "Against the highest who shall wage the war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8710, line : "If furious yet they dare the vain debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8711, line : "Thus have I spoke, and what I speak is fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8712, line : "Their coursers crush'd beneath the wheels shall lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8713, line : "Their car in fragments, scatter'd o'er the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8714, line : "My lightning these rebellious shall confound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8715, line : "And hurl them flaming, headlong, to the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8716, line : "Condemn'd for ten revolving years to weep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8717, line : "The wounds impress'd by burning thunder deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8718, line : "So shall Minerva learn to fear our ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8719, line : "Nor dare to combat hers and nature's sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8720, line : "For Juno, headstrong and imperious still,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8721, line : "She claims some title to transgress our will.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8723, line : "Swift as the wind, the various-colour'd maid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8724, line : "From Ida's top her golden wings display'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8725, line : "To great Olympus' shining gate she flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8726, line : "There meets the chariot rushing down the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8727, line : "Restrains their progress from the bright abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8728, line : "And speaks the mandate of the sire of gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8730, line : "\"What frenzy goddesses! what rage can move"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8731, line : "Celestial minds to tempt the wrath of Jove?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8732, line : "Desist, obedient to his high command:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8733, line : "This is his word; and know his word shall stand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8734, line : "His lightning your rebellion shall confound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8735, line : "And hurl ye headlong, flaming, to the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8736, line : "Your horses crush'd beneath the wheels shall lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8737, line : "Your car in fragments scatter'd o'er the sky;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8738, line : "Yourselves condemn'd ten rolling years to weep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8739, line : "The wounds impress'd by burning thunder deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8740, line : "So shall Minerva learn to fear his ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8741, line : "Nor dare to combat hers and nature's sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8742, line : "For Juno, headstrong and imperious still,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8743, line : "She claims some title to transgress his will:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8744, line : "But thee, what desperate insolence has driven"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8745, line : "To lift thy lance against the king of heaven?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8747, line : "Then, mounting on the pinions of the wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8748, line : "She flew; and Juno thus her rage resign'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8750, line : "\"O daughter of that god, whose arm can wield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8751, line : "The avenging bolt, and shake the dreadful shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8752, line : "No more let beings of superior birth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8753, line : "Contend with Jove for this low race of earth;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8754, line : "Triumphant now, now miserably slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8755, line : "They breathe or perish as the fates ordain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8756, line : "But Jove's high counsels full effect shall find;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8757, line : "And, ever constant, ever rule mankind.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8759, line : "She spoke, and backward turn'd her steeds of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8760, line : "Adorn'd with manes of gold, and heavenly bright."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8761, line : "The Hours unloosed them, panting as they stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8762, line : "And heap'd their mangers with ambrosial food."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8763, line : "There tied, they rest in high celestial stalls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8764, line : "The chariot propp'd against the crystal walls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8765, line : "The pensive goddesses, abash'd, controll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8766, line : "Mix with the gods, and fill their seats of gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8768, line : "[Illustration: THE HOURS TAKING THE HORSES FROM JUNO'S CAR.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8770, line : "THE HOURS TAKING THE HORSES FROM JUNO'S CAR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8773, line : "And now the Thunderer meditates his flight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8774, line : "From Ida's summits to the Olympian height."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8775, line : "Swifter than thought, the wheels instinctive fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8776, line : "Flame through the vast of air, and reach the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8777, line : "'Twas Neptune's charge his coursers to unbrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8778, line : "And fix the car on its immortal base;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8779, line : "There stood the chariot, beaming forth its rays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8780, line : "Till with a snowy veil he screen'd the blaze."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8781, line : "He, whose all-conscious eyes the world behold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8782, line : "The eternal Thunderer sat, enthroned in gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8783, line : "High heaven the footstool of his feet he makes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8784, line : "And wide beneath him all Olympus shakes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8785, line : "Trembling afar the offending powers appear'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8786, line : "Confused and silent, for his frown they fear'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8787, line : "He saw their soul, and thus his word imparts:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8788, line : "\"Pallas and Juno! say, why heave your hearts?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8789, line : "Soon was your battle o'er: proud Troy retired"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8790, line : "Before your face, and in your wrath expired."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8791, line : "But know, whoe'er almighty power withstand!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8792, line : "Unmatch'd our force, unconquer'd is our hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8793, line : "Who shall the sovereign of the skies control?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8794, line : "Not all the gods that crown the starry pole."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8795, line : "Your hearts shall tremble, if our arms we take,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8796, line : "And each immortal nerve with horror shake."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8797, line : "For thus I speak, and what I speak shall stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8798, line : "What power soe'er provokes our lifted hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8799, line : "On this our hill no more shall hold his place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8800, line : "Cut off, and exiled from the ethereal race.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8802, line : "Juno and Pallas grieving hear the doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8803, line : "But feast their souls on Ilion's woes to come."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8804, line : "Though secret anger swell'd Minerva's breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8805, line : "The prudent goddess yet her wrath repress'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8806, line : "But Juno, impotent of rage, replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8807, line : "\"What hast thou said, O tyrant of the skies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8808, line : "Strength and omnipotence invest thy throne;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8809, line : "'Tis thine to punish; ours to grieve alone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8810, line : "For Greece we grieve, abandon'd by her fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8811, line : "To drink the dregs of thy unmeasured hate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8812, line : "From fields forbidden we submiss refrain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8813, line : "With arms unaiding see our Argives slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8814, line : "Yet grant our counsels still their breasts may move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8815, line : "Lest all should perish in the rage of Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8817, line : "The goddess thus; and thus the god replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8818, line : "Who swells the clouds, and blackens all the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8820, line : "\"The morning sun, awaked by loud alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8821, line : "Shall see the almighty Thunderer in arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8822, line : "What heaps of Argives then shall load the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8823, line : "Those radiant eyes shall view, and view in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8824, line : "Nor shall great Hector cease the rage of fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8825, line : "The navy flaming, and thy Greeks in flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8826, line : "Even till the day when certain fates ordain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8827, line : "That stern Achilles (his Patroclus slain)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8828, line : "Shall rise in vengeance, and lay waste the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8829, line : "For such is fate, nor canst thou turn its course"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8830, line : "With all thy rage, with all thy rebel force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8831, line : "Fly, if thy wilt, to earth's remotest bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8832, line : "Where on her utmost verge the seas resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8833, line : "Where cursed Iapetus and Saturn dwell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8834, line : "Fast by the brink, within the streams of hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8835, line : "No sun e'er gilds the gloomy horrors there;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8836, line : "No cheerful gales refresh the lazy air:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8837, line : "There arm once more the bold Titanian band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8838, line : "And arm in vain; for what I will, shall stand.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8840, line : "Now deep in ocean sunk the lamp of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8841, line : "And drew behind the cloudy veil of night:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8842, line : "The conquering Trojans mourn his beams decay'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8843, line : "The Greeks rejoicing bless the friendly shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8845, line : "The victors keep the field; and Hector calls"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8846, line : "A martial council near the navy walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8847, line : "These to Scamander's bank apart he led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8848, line : "Where thinly scatter'd lay the heaps of dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8849, line : "The assembled chiefs, descending on the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8850, line : "Attend his order, and their prince surround."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8851, line : "A massy spear he bore of mighty strength,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8852, line : "Of full ten cubits was the lance's length;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8853, line : "The point was brass, refulgent to behold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8854, line : "Fix'd to the wood with circling rings of gold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8855, line : "The noble Hector on his lance reclined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8856, line : "And, bending forward, thus reveal'd his mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8858, line : "\"Ye valiant Trojans, with attention hear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8859, line : "Ye Dardan bands, and generous aids, give ear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8860, line : "This day, we hoped, would wrap in conquering flame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8861, line : "Greece with her ships, and crown our toils with fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8862, line : "But darkness now, to save the cowards, falls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8863, line : "And guards them trembling in their wooden walls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8864, line : "Obey the night, and use her peaceful hours"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8865, line : "Our steeds to forage, and refresh our powers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8866, line : "Straight from the town be sheep and oxen sought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8867, line : "And strengthening bread and generous wine be brought"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8868, line : "Wide o'er the field, high blazing to the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8869, line : "Let numerous fires the absent sun supply,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8870, line : "The flaming piles with plenteous fuel raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8871, line : "Till the bright morn her purple beam displays;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8872, line : "Lest, in the silence and the shades of night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8873, line : "Greece on her sable ships attempt her flight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8874, line : "Not unmolested let the wretches gain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8875, line : "Their lofty decks, or safely cleave the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8876, line : "Some hostile wound let every dart bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8877, line : "Some lasting token of the Phrygian foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8878, line : "Wounds, that long hence may ask their spouses' care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8879, line : "And warn their children from a Trojan war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8880, line : "Now through the circuit of our Ilion wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8881, line : "Let sacred heralds sound the solemn call;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8882, line : "To bid the sires with hoary honours crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8883, line : "And beardless youths, our battlements surround."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8884, line : "Firm be the guard, while distant lie our powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8885, line : "And let the matrons hang with lights the towers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8886, line : "Lest, under covert of the midnight shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8887, line : "The insidious foe the naked town invade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8888, line : "Suffice, to-night, these orders to obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8889, line : "A nobler charge shall rouse the dawning day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8890, line : "The gods, I trust, shall give to Hector's hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8891, line : "From these detested foes to free the land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8892, line : "Who plough'd, with fates averse, the watery way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8893, line : "For Trojan vultures a predestined prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8894, line : "Our common safety must be now the care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8895, line : "But soon as morning paints the fields of air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8896, line : "Sheathed in bright arms let every troop engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8897, line : "And the fired fleet behold the battle rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8898, line : "Then, then shall Hector and Tydides prove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8899, line : "Whose fates are heaviest in the scales of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8900, line : "To-morrow's light (O haste the glorious morn!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8901, line : "Shall see his bloody spoils in triumph borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8902, line : "With this keen javelin shall his breast be gored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8903, line : "And prostrate heroes bleed around their lord."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8904, line : "Certain as this, oh! might my days endure,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8905, line : "From age inglorious, and black death secure;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8906, line : "So might my life and glory know no bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8907, line : "Like Pallas worshipp'd, like the sun renown'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8908, line : "As the next dawn, the last they shall enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8909, line : "Shall crush the Greeks, and end the woes of Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8911, line : "The leader spoke. From all his host around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8912, line : "Shouts of applause along the shores resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8913, line : "Each from the yoke the smoking steeds untied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8914, line : "And fix'd their headstalls to his chariot-side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8915, line : "Fat sheep and oxen from the town are led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8916, line : "With generous wine, and all-sustaining bread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8917, line : "Full hecatombs lay burning on the shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8918, line : "The winds to heaven the curling vapours bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8919, line : "Ungrateful offering to the immortal powers!(197)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8920, line : "Whose wrath hung heavy o'er the Trojan towers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8921, line : "Nor Priam nor his sons obtain'd their grace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8922, line : "Proud Troy they hated, and her guilty race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8924, line : "The troops exulting sat in order round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8925, line : "And beaming fires illumined all the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8926, line : "As when the moon, refulgent lamp of night,(198)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8927, line : "O'er heaven's pure azure spreads her sacred light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8928, line : "When not a breath disturbs the deep serene,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8929, line : "And not a cloud o'ercasts the solemn scene,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8930, line : "Around her throne the vivid planets roll,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8931, line : "And stars unnumber'd gild the glowing pole,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8932, line : "O'er the dark trees a yellower verdure shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8933, line : "And tip with silver every mountain's head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8934, line : "Then shine the vales, the rocks in prospect rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8935, line : "A flood of glory bursts from all the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8936, line : "The conscious swains, rejoicing in the sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8937, line : "Eye the blue vault, and bless the useful light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8938, line : "So many flames before proud Ilion blaze,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8939, line : "And lighten glimmering Xanthus with their rays."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8940, line : "The long reflections of the distant fires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8941, line : "Gleam on the walls, and tremble on the spires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8942, line : "A thousand piles the dusky horrors gild,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8943, line : "And shoot a shady lustre o'er the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8944, line : "Full fifty guards each flaming pile attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8945, line : "Whose umber'd arms, by fits, thick flashes send,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8946, line : "Loud neigh the coursers o'er their heaps of corn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8947, line : "And ardent warriors wait the rising morn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8949, line : "[Illustration: THE SHIELD OF ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8951, line : "THE SHIELD OF ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8957, line : "BOOK IX."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8960, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8962, line : "THE EMBASSY TO ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8964, line : "Agamemnon, after the last day's defeat, proposes to the Greeks to quit the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8965, line : "siege, and return to their country. Diomed opposes this, and Nestor"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8966, line : "seconds him, praising his wisdom and resolution. He orders the guard to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8967, line : "strengthened, and a council summoned to deliberate what measures are to be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8968, line : "followed in this emergency. Agamemnon pursues this advice, and Nestor"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8969, line : "further prevails upon him to send ambassadors to Achilles, in order to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8970, line : "move him to a reconciliation. Ulysses and Ajax are made choice of, who are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8971, line : "accompanied by old Phoenix. They make, each of them, very moving and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8972, line : "pressing speeches, but are rejected with roughness by Achilles, who"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8973, line : "notwithstanding retains Phoenix in his tent. The ambassadors return"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8974, line : "unsuccessfully to the camp, and the troops betake themselves to sleep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8976, line : "This book, and the next following, take up the space of one night, which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8977, line : "is the twenty-seventh from the beginning of the poem. The scene lies on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8978, line : "the sea-shore, the station of the Grecian ships."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8980, line : "Thus joyful Troy maintain'd the watch of night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8981, line : "While fear, pale comrade of inglorious flight,(199)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8982, line : "And heaven-bred horror, on the Grecian part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8983, line : "Sat on each face, and sadden'd every heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8984, line : "As from its cloudy dungeon issuing forth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8985, line : "A double tempest of the west and north"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8986, line : "Swells o'er the sea, from Thracia's frozen shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8987, line : "Heaps waves on waves, and bids the Ćgean roar:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8988, line : "This way and that the boiling deeps are toss'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8989, line : "Such various passions urged the troubled host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8990, line : "Great Agamemnon grieved above the rest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8991, line : "Superior sorrows swell'd his royal breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8992, line : "Himself his orders to the heralds bears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8993, line : "To bid to council all the Grecian peers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8994, line : "But bid in whispers: these surround their chief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8995, line : "In solemn sadness and majestic grief."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8996, line : "The king amidst the mournful circle rose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8997, line : "Down his wan cheek a briny torrent flows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8998, line : "So silent fountains, from a rock's tall head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 8999, line : "In sable streams soft-trickling waters shed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9000, line : "With more than vulgar grief he stood oppress'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9001, line : "Words, mix'd with sighs, thus bursting from his breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9003, line : "\"Ye sons of Greece! partake your leader's care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9004, line : "Fellows in arms and princes of the war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9005, line : "Of partial Jove too justly we complain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9006, line : "And heavenly oracles believed in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9007, line : "A safe return was promised to our toils,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9008, line : "With conquest honour'd and enrich'd with spoils:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9009, line : "Now shameful flight alone can save the host;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9010, line : "Our wealth, our people, and our glory lost."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9011, line : "So Jove decrees, almighty lord of all!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9012, line : "Jove, at whose nod whole empires rise or fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9013, line : "Who shakes the feeble props of human trust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9014, line : "And towers and armies humbles to the dust."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9015, line : "Haste then, for ever quit these fatal fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9016, line : "Haste to the joys our native country yields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9017, line : "Spread all your canvas, all your oars employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9018, line : "Nor hope the fall of heaven-defended Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9020, line : "He said: deep silence held the Grecian band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9021, line : "Silent, unmov'd in dire dismay they stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9022, line : "A pensive scene! till Tydeus' warlike son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9023, line : "Roll'd on the king his eyes, and thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9024, line : "\"When kings advise us to renounce our fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9025, line : "First let him speak who first has suffer'd shame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9026, line : "If I oppose thee, prince! thy wrath withhold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9027, line : "The laws of council bid my tongue be bold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9028, line : "Thou first, and thou alone, in fields of fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9029, line : "Durst brand my courage, and defame my might:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9030, line : "Nor from a friend the unkind reproach appear'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9031, line : "The Greeks stood witness, all our army heard."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9032, line : "The gods, O chief! from whom our honours spring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9033, line : "The gods have made thee but by halves a king:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9034, line : "They gave thee sceptres, and a wide command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9035, line : "They gave dominion o'er the seas and land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9036, line : "The noblest power that might the world control"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9037, line : "They gave thee not--a brave and virtuous soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9038, line : "Is this a general's voice, that would suggest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9039, line : "Fears like his own to every Grecian breast?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9040, line : "Confiding in our want of worth, he stands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9041, line : "And if we fly, 'tis what our king commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9042, line : "Go thou, inglorious! from the embattled plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9043, line : "Ships thou hast store, and nearest to the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9044, line : "A noble care the Grecians shall employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9045, line : "To combat, conquer, and extirpate Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9046, line : "Here Greece shall stay; or, if all Greece retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9047, line : "Myself shall stay, till Troy or I expire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9048, line : "Myself, and Sthenelus, will fight for fame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9049, line : "God bade us fight, and 'twas with God we came.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9051, line : "He ceased; the Greeks loud acclamations raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9052, line : "And voice to voice resounds Tydides' praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9053, line : "Wise Nestor then his reverend figure rear'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9054, line : "He spoke: the host in still attention heard:(200)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9056, line : "\"O truly great! in whom the gods have join'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9057, line : "Such strength of body with such force of mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9058, line : "In conduct, as in courage, you excel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9059, line : "Still first to act what you advise so well."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9060, line : "These wholesome counsels which thy wisdom moves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9061, line : "Applauding Greece with common voice approves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9062, line : "Kings thou canst blame; a bold but prudent youth:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9063, line : "And blame even kings with praise, because with truth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9064, line : "And yet those years that since thy birth have run"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9065, line : "Would hardly style thee Nestor's youngest son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9066, line : "Then let me add what yet remains behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9067, line : "A thought unfinish'd in that generous mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9068, line : "Age bids me speak! nor shall the advice I bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9069, line : "Distaste the people, or offend the king:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9071, line : "\"Cursed is the man, and void of law and right,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9072, line : "Unworthy property, unworthy light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9073, line : "Unfit for public rule, or private care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9074, line : "That wretch, that monster, who delights in war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9075, line : "Whose lust is murder, and whose horrid joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9076, line : "To tear his country, and his kind destroy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9077, line : "This night, refresh and fortify thy train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9078, line : "Between the trench and wall let guards remain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9079, line : "Be that the duty of the young and bold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9080, line : "But thou, O king, to council call the old;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9081, line : "Great is thy sway, and weighty are thy cares;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9082, line : "Thy high commands must spirit all our wars."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9083, line : "With Thracian wines recruit thy honour'd guests,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9084, line : "For happy counsels flow from sober feasts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9085, line : "Wise, weighty counsels aid a state distress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9086, line : "And such a monarch as can choose the best."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9087, line : "See what a blaze from hostile tents aspires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9088, line : "How near our fleet approach the Trojan fires!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9089, line : "Who can, unmoved, behold the dreadful light?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9090, line : "What eye beholds them, and can close to-night?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9091, line : "This dreadful interval determines all;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9092, line : "To-morrow, Troy must flame, or Greece must fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9094, line : "Thus spoke the hoary sage: the rest obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9095, line : "Swift through the gates the guards direct their way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9096, line : "His son was first to pass the lofty mound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9097, line : "The generous Thrasymed, in arms renown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9098, line : "Next him, Ascalaphus, Ialmen, stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9099, line : "The double offspring of the warrior-god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9100, line : "Deipyrus, Aphareus, Merion join,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9101, line : "And Lycomed of Creon's noble line."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9102, line : "Seven were the leaders of the nightly bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9103, line : "And each bold chief a hundred spears commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9104, line : "The fires they light, to short repasts they fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9105, line : "Some line the trench, and others man the wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9107, line : "The king of men, on public counsels bent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9108, line : "Convened the princes in his ample tent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9109, line : "Each seized a portion of the kingly feast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9110, line : "But stay'd his hand when thirst and hunger ceased."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9111, line : "Then Nestor spoke, for wisdom long approved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9112, line : "And slowly rising, thus the council moved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9114, line : "\"Monarch of nations! whose superior sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9115, line : "Assembled states, and lords of earth obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9116, line : "The laws and sceptres to thy hand are given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9117, line : "And millions own the care of thee and Heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9118, line : "O king! the counsels of my age attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9119, line : "With thee my cares begin, with thee must end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9120, line : "Thee, prince! it fits alike to speak and hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9121, line : "Pronounce with judgment, with regard give ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9122, line : "To see no wholesome motion be withstood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9123, line : "And ratify the best for public good."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9124, line : "Nor, though a meaner give advice, repine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9125, line : "But follow it, and make the wisdom thine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9126, line : "Hear then a thought, not now conceived in haste,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9127, line : "At once my present judgment and my past."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9128, line : "When from Pelides' tent you forced the maid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9129, line : "I first opposed, and faithful, durst dissuade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9130, line : "But bold of soul, when headlong fury fired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9131, line : "You wronged the man, by men and gods admired:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9132, line : "Now seek some means his fatal wrath to end,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9133, line : "With prayers to move him, or with gifts to bend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9135, line : "To whom the king. \"With justice hast thou shown"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9136, line : "A prince's faults, and I with reason own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9137, line : "That happy man, whom Jove still honours most,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9138, line : "Is more than armies, and himself a host."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9139, line : "Bless'd in his love, this wondrous hero stands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9140, line : "Heaven fights his war, and humbles all our bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9141, line : "Fain would my heart, which err'd through frantic rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9142, line : "The wrathful chief and angry gods assuage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9143, line : "If gifts immense his mighty soul can bow,(201)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9144, line : "Hear, all ye Greeks, and witness what I vow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9145, line : "Ten weighty talents of the purest gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9146, line : "And twice ten vases of refulgent mould:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9147, line : "Seven sacred tripods, whose unsullied frame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9148, line : "Yet knows no office, nor has felt the flame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9149, line : "Twelve steeds unmatch'd in fleetness and in force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9150, line : "And still victorious in the dusty course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9151, line : "(Rich were the man whose ample stores exceed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9152, line : "The prizes purchased by their winged speed;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9153, line : "Seven lovely captives of the Lesbian line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9154, line : "Skill'd in each art, unmatch'd in form divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9155, line : "The same I chose for more than vulgar charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9156, line : "When Lesbos sank beneath the hero's arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9157, line : "All these, to buy his friendship, shall be paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9158, line : "And join'd with these the long-contested maid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9159, line : "With all her charms, Briseis I resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9160, line : "And solemn swear those charms were never mine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9161, line : "Untouch'd she stay'd, uninjured she removes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9162, line : "Pure from my arms, and guiltless of my loves,(202)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9163, line : "These instant shall be his; and if the powers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9164, line : "Give to our arms proud Ilion's hostile towers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9165, line : "Then shall he store (when Greece the spoil divides)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9166, line : "With gold and brass his loaded navy's sides:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9167, line : "Besides, full twenty nymphs of Trojan race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9168, line : "With copious love shall crown his warm embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9169, line : "Such as himself will choose; who yield to none,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9170, line : "Or yield to Helen's heavenly charms alone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9171, line : "Yet hear me further: when our wars are o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9172, line : "If safe we land on Argos' fruitful shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9173, line : "There shall he live my son, our honours share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9174, line : "And with Orestes' self divide my care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9175, line : "Yet more--three daughters in my court are bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9176, line : "And each well worthy of a royal bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9177, line : "Laodice and Iphigenia fair,(203)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9178, line : "And bright Chrysothemis with golden hair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9179, line : "Her let him choose whom most his eyes approve,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9180, line : "I ask no presents, no reward for love:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9181, line : "Myself will give the dower; so vast a store"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9182, line : "As never father gave a child before."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9183, line : "Seven ample cities shall confess his sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9184, line : "Him Enope, and Pherae him obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9185, line : "Cardamyle with ample turrets crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9186, line : "And sacred Pedasus for vines renown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9187, line : "Ćpea fair, the pastures Hira yields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9188, line : "And rich Antheia with her flowery fields:(204)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9189, line : "The whole extent to Pylos' sandy plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9190, line : "Along the verdant margin of the main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9191, line : "There heifers graze, and labouring oxen toil;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9192, line : "Bold are the men, and generous is the soil;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9193, line : "There shall he reign, with power and justice crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9194, line : "And rule the tributary realms around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9195, line : "All this I give, his vengeance to control,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9196, line : "And sure all this may move his mighty soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9197, line : "Pluto, the grisly god, who never spares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9198, line : "Who feels no mercy, and who hears no prayers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9199, line : "Lives dark and dreadful in deep hell's abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9200, line : "And mortals hate him, as the worst of gods"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9201, line : "Great though he be, it fits him to obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9202, line : "Since more than his my years, and more my sway.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9204, line : "[Illustration: PLUTO.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9206, line : "PLUTO."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9209, line : "The monarch thus. The reverend Nestor then:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9210, line : "\"Great Agamemnon! glorious king of men!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9211, line : "Such are thy offers as a prince may take,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9212, line : "And such as fits a generous king to make."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9213, line : "Let chosen delegates this hour be sent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9214, line : "(Myself will name them) to Pelides' tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9215, line : "Let Phoenix lead, revered for hoary age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9216, line : "Great Ajax next, and Ithacus the sage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9217, line : "Yet more to sanctify the word you send,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9218, line : "Let Hodius and Eurybates attend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9219, line : "Now pray to Jove to grant what Greece demands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9220, line : "Pray in deep silence,(205) and with purest hands.\"(206)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9222, line : "[Illustration: THE EMBASSY TO ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9224, line : "THE EMBASSY TO ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9227, line : "He said; and all approved. The heralds bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9228, line : "The cleansing water from the living spring."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9229, line : "The youth with wine the sacred goblets crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9230, line : "And large libations drench'd the sands around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9231, line : "The rite perform'd, the chiefs their thirst allay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9232, line : "Then from the royal tent they take their way;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9233, line : "Wise Nestor turns on each his careful eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9234, line : "Forbids to offend, instructs them to apply;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9235, line : "Much he advised them all, Ulysses most,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9236, line : "To deprecate the chief, and save the host."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9237, line : "Through the still night they march, and hear the roar"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9238, line : "Of murmuring billows on the sounding shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9239, line : "To Neptune, ruler of the seas profound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9240, line : "Whose liquid arms the mighty globe surround,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9241, line : "They pour forth vows, their embassy to bless,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9242, line : "And calm the rage of stern Ćacides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9243, line : "And now, arrived, where on the sandy bay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9244, line : "The Myrmidonian tents and vessels lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9245, line : "Amused at ease, the godlike man they found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9246, line : "Pleased with the solemn harp's harmonious sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9247, line : "(The well wrought harp from conquered Thebae came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9248, line : "Of polish'd silver was its costly frame.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9249, line : "With this he soothes his angry soul, and sings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9250, line : "The immortal deeds of heroes and of kings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9251, line : "Patroclus only of the royal train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9252, line : "Placed in his tent, attends the lofty strain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9253, line : "Full opposite he sat, and listen'd long,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9254, line : "In silence waiting till he ceased the song."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9255, line : "Unseen the Grecian embassy proceeds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9256, line : "To his high tent; the great Ulysses leads."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9257, line : "Achilles starting, as the chiefs he spied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9258, line : "Leap'd from his seat, and laid the harp aside."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9259, line : "With like surprise arose Menoetius' son:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9260, line : "Pelides grasp'd their hands, and thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9262, line : "\"Princes, all hail! whatever brought you here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9263, line : "Or strong necessity, or urgent fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9264, line : "Welcome, though Greeks! for not as foes ye came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9265, line : "To me more dear than all that bear the name.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9267, line : "With that, the chiefs beneath his roof he led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9268, line : "And placed in seats with purple carpets spread."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9269, line : "Then thus--\"Patroclus, crown a larger bowl,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9270, line : "Mix purer wine, and open every soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9271, line : "Of all the warriors yonder host can send,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9272, line : "Thy friend most honours these, and these thy friend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9274, line : "He said: Patroclus o'er the blazing fire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9275, line : "Heaps in a brazen vase three chines entire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9276, line : "The brazen vase Automedon sustains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9277, line : "Which flesh of porker, sheep, and goat contains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9278, line : "Achilles at the genial feast presides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9279, line : "The parts transfixes, and with skill divides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9280, line : "Meanwhile Patroclus sweats, the fire to raise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9281, line : "The tent is brighten'd with the rising blaze:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9282, line : "Then, when the languid flames at length subside,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9283, line : "He strows a bed of glowing embers wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9284, line : "Above the coals the smoking fragments turns"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9285, line : "And sprinkles sacred salt from lifted urns;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9286, line : "With bread the glittering canisters they load,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9287, line : "Which round the board Menoetius' son bestow'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9288, line : "Himself, opposed to Ulysses full in sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9289, line : "Each portion parts, and orders every rite."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9290, line : "The first fat offering to the immortals due,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9291, line : "Amidst the greedy flames Patroclus threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9292, line : "Then each, indulging in the social feast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9293, line : "His thirst and hunger soberly repress'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9294, line : "That done, to Phoenix Ajax gave the sign:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9295, line : "Not unperceived; Ulysses crown'd with wine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9296, line : "The foaming bowl, and instant thus began,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9297, line : "His speech addressing to the godlike man."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9299, line : "\"Health to Achilles! happy are thy guests!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9300, line : "Not those more honour'd whom Atrides feasts:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9301, line : "Though generous plenty crown thy loaded boards,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9302, line : "That, Agamemnon's regal tent affords;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9303, line : "But greater cares sit heavy on our souls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9304, line : "Nor eased by banquets or by flowing bowls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9305, line : "What scenes of slaughter in yon fields appear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9306, line : "The dead we mourn, and for the living fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9307, line : "Greece on the brink of fate all doubtful stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9308, line : "And owns no help but from thy saving hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9309, line : "Troy and her aids for ready vengeance call;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9310, line : "Their threatening tents already shade our wall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9311, line : "Hear how with shouts their conquest they proclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9312, line : "And point at every ship their vengeful flame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9313, line : "For them the father of the gods declares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9314, line : "Theirs are his omens, and his thunder theirs."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9315, line : "See, full of Jove, avenging Hector rise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9316, line : "See! heaven and earth the raging chief defies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9317, line : "What fury in his breast, what lightning in his eyes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9318, line : "He waits but for the morn, to sink in flame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9319, line : "The ships, the Greeks, and all the Grecian name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9320, line : "Heavens! how my country's woes distract my mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9321, line : "Lest Fate accomplish all his rage design'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9322, line : "And must we, gods! our heads inglorious lay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9323, line : "In Trojan dust, and this the fatal day?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9324, line : "Return, Achilles: oh return, though late,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9325, line : "To save thy Greeks, and stop the course of Fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9326, line : "If in that heart or grief or courage lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9327, line : "Rise to redeem; ah, yet to conquer, rise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9328, line : "The day may come, when, all our warriors slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9329, line : "That heart shall melt, that courage rise in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9330, line : "Regard in time, O prince divinely brave!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9331, line : "Those wholesome counsels which thy father gave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9332, line : "When Peleus in his aged arms embraced"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9333, line : "His parting son, these accents were his last:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9335, line : "\"'My child! with strength, with glory, and success,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9336, line : "Thy arms may Juno and Minerva bless!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9337, line : "Trust that to Heaven: but thou, thy cares engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9338, line : "To calm thy passions, and subdue thy rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9339, line : "From gentler manners let thy glory grow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9340, line : "And shun contention, the sure source of woe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9341, line : "That young and old may in thy praise combine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9342, line : "The virtues of humanity be thine--'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9343, line : "This now-despised advice thy father gave;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9344, line : "Ah! check thy anger; and be truly brave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9345, line : "If thou wilt yield to great Atrides' prayers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9346, line : "Gifts worthy thee his royal hand prepares;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9347, line : "If not--but hear me, while I number o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9348, line : "The proffer'd presents, an exhaustless store."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9349, line : "Ten weighty talents of the purest gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9350, line : "And twice ten vases of refulgent mould;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9351, line : "Seven sacred tripods, whose unsullied frame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9352, line : "Yet knows no office, nor has felt the flame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9353, line : "Twelve steeds unmatched in fleetness and in force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9354, line : "And still victorious in the dusty course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9355, line : "(Rich were the man, whose ample stores exceed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9356, line : "The prizes purchased by their winged speed;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9357, line : "Seven lovely captives of the Lesbian line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9358, line : "Skill'd in each art, unmatch'd in form divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9359, line : "The same he chose for more than vulgar charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9360, line : "When Lesbos sank beneath thy conquering arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9361, line : "All these, to buy thy friendship shall be paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9362, line : "And, join'd with these, the long-contested maid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9363, line : "With all her charms, Briseis he'll resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9364, line : "And solemn swear those charms were only thine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9365, line : "Untouch'd she stay'd, uninjured she removes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9366, line : "Pure from his arms, and guiltless of his loves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9367, line : "These instant shall be thine; and if the powers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9368, line : "Give to our arms proud Ilion's hostile towers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9369, line : "Then shalt thou store (when Greece the spoil divides)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9370, line : "With gold and brass thy loaded navy's sides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9371, line : "Besides, full twenty nymphs of Trojan race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9372, line : "With copious love shall crown thy warm embrace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9373, line : "Such as thyself shall chose; who yield to none,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9374, line : "Or yield to Helen's heavenly charms alone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9375, line : "Yet hear me further: when our wars are o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9376, line : "If safe we land on Argos' fruitful shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9377, line : "There shalt thou live his son, his honour share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9378, line : "And with Orestes' self divide his care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9379, line : "Yet more--three daughters in his court are bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9380, line : "And each well worthy of a royal bed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9381, line : "Laodice and Iphigenia fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9382, line : "And bright Chrysothemis with golden hair:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9383, line : "Her shalt thou wed whom most thy eyes approve;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9384, line : "He asks no presents, no reward for love:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9385, line : "Himself will give the dower; so vast a store"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9386, line : "As never father gave a child before."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9387, line : "Seven ample cities shall confess thy sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9388, line : "The Enope and Pherae thee obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9389, line : "Cardamyle with ample turrets crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9390, line : "And sacred Pedasus, for vines renown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9391, line : "Ćpea fair, the pastures Hira yields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9392, line : "And rich Antheia with her flowery fields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9393, line : "The whole extent to Pylos' sandy plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9394, line : "Along the verdant margin of the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9395, line : "There heifers graze, and labouring oxen toil;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9396, line : "Bold are the men, and generous is the soil."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9397, line : "There shalt thou reign, with power and justice crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9398, line : "And rule the tributary realms around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9399, line : "Such are the proffers which this day we bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9400, line : "Such the repentance of a suppliant king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9401, line : "But if all this, relentless, thou disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9402, line : "If honour and if interest plead in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9403, line : "Yet some redress to suppliant Greece afford,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9404, line : "And be, amongst her guardian gods, adored."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9405, line : "If no regard thy suffering country claim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9406, line : "Hear thy own glory, and the voice of fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9407, line : "For now that chief, whose unresisted ire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9408, line : "Made nations tremble, and whole hosts retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9409, line : "Proud Hector, now, the unequal fight demands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9410, line : "And only triumphs to deserve thy hands.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9412, line : "Then thus the goddess-born: \"Ulysses, hear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9413, line : "A faithful speech, that knows nor art nor fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9414, line : "What in my secret soul is understood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9415, line : "My tongue shall utter, and my deeds make good."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9416, line : "Let Greece then know, my purpose I retain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9417, line : "Nor with new treaties vex my peace in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9418, line : "Who dares think one thing, and another tell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9419, line : "My heart detests him as the gates of hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9421, line : "\"Then thus in short my fix'd resolves attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9422, line : "Which nor Atrides nor his Greeks can bend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9423, line : "Long toils, long perils in their cause I bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9424, line : "But now the unfruitful glories charm no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9425, line : "Fight or not fight, a like reward we claim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9426, line : "The wretch and hero find their prize the same."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9427, line : "Alike regretted in the dust he lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9428, line : "Who yields ignobly, or who bravely dies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9429, line : "Of all my dangers, all my glorious pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9430, line : "A life of labours, lo! what fruit remains?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9431, line : "As the bold bird her helpless young attends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9432, line : "From danger guards them, and from want defends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9433, line : "In search of prey she wings the spacious air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9434, line : "And with the untasted food supplies her care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9435, line : "For thankless Greece such hardships have I braved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9436, line : "Her wives, her infants, by my labours saved;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9437, line : "Long sleepless nights in heavy arms I stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9438, line : "And sweat laborious days in dust and blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9439, line : "I sack'd twelve ample cities on the main,(207)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9440, line : "And twelve lay smoking on the Trojan plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9441, line : "Then at Atrides' haughty feet were laid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9442, line : "The wealth I gathered, and the spoils I made."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9443, line : "Your mighty monarch these in peace possess'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9444, line : "Some few my soldiers had, himself the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9445, line : "Some present, too, to every prince was paid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9446, line : "And every prince enjoys the gift he made:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9447, line : "I only must refund, of all his train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9448, line : "See what pre-eminence our merits gain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9449, line : "My spoil alone his greedy soul delights:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9450, line : "My spouse alone must bless his lustful nights:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9451, line : "The woman, let him (as he may) enjoy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9452, line : "But what's the quarrel, then, of Greece to Troy?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9453, line : "What to these shores the assembled nations draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9454, line : "What calls for vengeance but a woman's cause?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9455, line : "Are fair endowments and a beauteous face"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9456, line : "Beloved by none but those of Atreus' race?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9457, line : "The wife whom choice and passion doth approve,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9458, line : "Sure every wise and worthy man will love."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9459, line : "Nor did my fair one less distinction claim;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9460, line : "Slave as she was, my soul adored the dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9461, line : "Wrong'd in my love, all proffers I disdain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9462, line : "Deceived for once, I trust not kings again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9463, line : "Ye have my answer--what remains to do,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9464, line : "Your king, Ulysses, may consult with you."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9465, line : "What needs he the defence this arm can make?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9466, line : "Has he not walls no human force can shake?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9467, line : "Has he not fenced his guarded navy round"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9468, line : "With piles, with ramparts, and a trench profound?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9469, line : "And will not these (the wonders he has done)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9470, line : "Repel the rage of Priam's single son?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9471, line : "There was a time ('twas when for Greece I fought)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9472, line : "When Hector's prowess no such wonders wrought;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9473, line : "He kept the verge of Troy, nor dared to wait"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9474, line : "Achilles' fury at the Scaean gate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9475, line : "He tried it once, and scarce was saved by fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9476, line : "But now those ancient enmities are o'er;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9477, line : "To-morrow we the favouring gods implore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9478, line : "Then shall you see our parting vessels crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9479, line : "And hear with oars the Hellespont resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9480, line : "The third day hence shall Pthia greet our sails,(208)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9481, line : "If mighty Neptune send propitious gales;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9482, line : "Pthia to her Achilles shall restore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9483, line : "The wealth he left for this detested shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9484, line : "Thither the spoils of this long war shall pass,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9485, line : "The ruddy gold, the steel, and shining brass:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9486, line : "My beauteous captives thither I'll convey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9487, line : "And all that rests of my unravish'd prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9488, line : "One only valued gift your tyrant gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9489, line : "And that resumed--the fair Lyrnessian slave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9490, line : "Then tell him: loud, that all the Greeks may hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9491, line : "And learn to scorn the wretch they basely fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9492, line : "(For arm'd in impudence, mankind he braves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9493, line : "And meditates new cheats on all his slaves;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9494, line : "Though shameless as he is, to face these eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9495, line : "Is what he dares not: if he dares he dies;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9496, line : "Tell him, all terms, all commerce I decline,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9497, line : "Nor share his council, nor his battle join;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9498, line : "For once deceiv'd, was his; but twice were mine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9499, line : "No--let the stupid prince, whom Jove deprives"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9500, line : "Of sense and justice, run where frenzy drives;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9501, line : "His gifts are hateful: kings of such a kind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9502, line : "Stand but as slaves before a noble mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9503, line : "Not though he proffer'd all himself possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9504, line : "And all his rapine could from others wrest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9505, line : "Not all the golden tides of wealth that crown"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9506, line : "The many-peopled Orchomenian town;(209)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9507, line : "Not all proud Thebes' unrivall'd walls contain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9508, line : "The world's great empress on the Egyptian plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9509, line : "(That spreads her conquests o'er a thousand states,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9510, line : "And pours her heroes through a hundred gates,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9511, line : "Two hundred horsemen and two hundred cars"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9512, line : "From each wide portal issuing to the wars);(210)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9513, line : "Though bribes were heap'd on bribes, in number more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9514, line : "Than dust in fields, or sands along the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9515, line : "Should all these offers for my friendship call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9516, line : "'Tis he that offers, and I scorn them all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9517, line : "Atrides' daughter never shall be led"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9518, line : "(An ill-match'd consort) to Achilles' bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9519, line : "Like golden Venus though she charm'd the heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9520, line : "And vied with Pallas in the works of art;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9521, line : "Some greater Greek let those high nuptials grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9522, line : "I hate alliance with a tyrant's race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9523, line : "If heaven restore me to my realms with life,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9524, line : "The reverend Peleus shall elect my wife;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9525, line : "Thessalian nymphs there are of form divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9526, line : "And kings that sue to mix their blood with mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9527, line : "Bless'd in kind love, my years shall glide away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9528, line : "Content with just hereditary sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9529, line : "There, deaf for ever to the martial strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9530, line : "Enjoy the dear prerogative of life."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9531, line : "Life is not to be bought with heaps of gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9532, line : "Not all Apollo's Pythian treasures hold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9533, line : "Or Troy once held, in peace and pride of sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9534, line : "Can bribe the poor possession of a day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9535, line : "Lost herds and treasures we by arms regain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9536, line : "And steeds unrivall'd on the dusty plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9537, line : "But from our lips the vital spirit fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9538, line : "Returns no more to wake the silent dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9539, line : "My fates long since by Thetis were disclosed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9540, line : "And each alternate, life or fame, proposed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9541, line : "Here, if I stay, before the Trojan town,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9542, line : "Short is my date, but deathless my renown:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9543, line : "If I return, I quit immortal praise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9544, line : "For years on years, and long-extended days."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9545, line : "Convinced, though late, I find my fond mistake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9546, line : "And warn the Greeks the wiser choice to make;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9547, line : "To quit these shores, their native seats enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9548, line : "Nor hope the fall of heaven-defended Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9549, line : "Jove's arm display'd asserts her from the skies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9550, line : "Her hearts are strengthen'd, and her glories rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9551, line : "Go then to Greece, report our fix'd design;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9552, line : "Bid all your counsels, all your armies join,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9553, line : "Let all your forces, all your arts conspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9554, line : "To save the ships, the troops, the chiefs, from fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9555, line : "One stratagem has fail'd, and others will:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9556, line : "Ye find, Achilles is unconquer'd still."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9557, line : "Go then--digest my message as ye may--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9558, line : "But here this night let reverend Phoenix stay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9559, line : "His tedious toils and hoary hairs demand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9560, line : "A peaceful death in Pthia's friendly land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9561, line : "But whether he remain or sail with me,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9562, line : "His age be sacred, and his will be free.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9564, line : "[Illustration: GREEK GALLEY.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9566, line : "GREEK GALLEY."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9569, line : "The son of Peleus ceased: the chiefs around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9570, line : "In silence wrapt, in consternation drown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9571, line : "Attend the stern reply. Then Phoenix rose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9572, line : "(Down his white beard a stream of sorrow flows;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9573, line : "And while the fate of suffering Greece he mourn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9574, line : "With accent weak these tender words return'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9576, line : "[Illustration: PROSERPINE.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9578, line : "PROSERPINE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9581, line : "\"Divine Achilles! wilt thou then retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9582, line : "And leave our hosts in blood, our fleets on fire?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9583, line : "If wrath so dreadful fill thy ruthless mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9584, line : "How shall thy friend, thy Phoenix, stay behind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9585, line : "The royal Peleus, when from Pthia's coast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9586, line : "He sent thee early to the Achaian host;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9587, line : "Thy youth as then in sage debates unskill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9588, line : "And new to perils of the direful field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9589, line : "He bade me teach thee all the ways of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9590, line : "To shine in councils, and in camps to dare."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9591, line : "Never, ah, never let me leave thy side!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9592, line : "No time shall part us, and no fate divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9593, line : "Not though the god, that breathed my life, restore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9594, line : "The bloom I boasted, and the port I bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9595, line : "When Greece of old beheld my youthful flames"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9596, line : "(Delightful Greece, the land of lovely dames),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9597, line : "My father faithless to my mother's arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9598, line : "Old as he was, adored a stranger's charms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9599, line : "I tried what youth could do (at her desire)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9600, line : "To win the damsel, and prevent my sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9601, line : "My sire with curses loads my hated head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9602, line : "And cries, 'Ye furies! barren be his bed.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9603, line : "Infernal Jove, the vengeful fiends below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9604, line : "And ruthless Proserpine, confirm'd his vow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9605, line : "Despair and grief distract my labouring mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9606, line : "Gods! what a crime my impious heart design'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9607, line : "I thought (but some kind god that thought suppress'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9608, line : "To plunge the poniard in my father's breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9609, line : "Then meditate my flight: my friends in vain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9610, line : "With prayers entreat me, and with force detain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9611, line : "On fat of rams, black bulls, and brawny swine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9612, line : "They daily feast, with draughts of fragrant wine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9613, line : "Strong guards they placed, and watch'd nine nights entire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9614, line : "The roofs and porches flamed with constant fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9615, line : "The tenth, I forced the gates, unseen of all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9616, line : "And, favour'd by the night, o'erleap'd the wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9617, line : "My travels thence through spacious Greece extend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9618, line : "In Phthia's court at last my labours end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9619, line : "Your sire received me, as his son caress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9620, line : "With gifts enrich'd, and with possessions bless'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9621, line : "The strong Dolopians thenceforth own'd my reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9622, line : "And all the coast that runs along the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9623, line : "By love to thee his bounties I repaid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9624, line : "And early wisdom to thy soul convey'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9625, line : "Great as thou art, my lessons made thee brave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9626, line : "A child I took thee, but a hero gave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9627, line : "Thy infant breast a like affection show'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9628, line : "Still in my arms (an ever-pleasing load)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9629, line : "Or at my knee, by Phoenix wouldst thou stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9630, line : "No food was grateful but from Phoenix' hand.(211)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9631, line : "I pass my watchings o'er thy helpless years,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9632, line : "The tender labours, the compliant cares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9633, line : "The gods (I thought) reversed their hard decree,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9634, line : "And Phoenix felt a father's joys in thee:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9635, line : "Thy growing virtues justified my cares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9636, line : "And promised comfort to my silver hairs."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9637, line : "Now be thy rage, thy fatal rage, resign'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9638, line : "A cruel heart ill suits a manly mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9639, line : "The gods (the only great, and only wise)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9640, line : "Are moved by offerings, vows, and sacrifice;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9641, line : "Offending man their high compassion wins,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9642, line : "And daily prayers atone for daily sins."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9643, line : "Prayers are Jove's daughters, of celestial race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9644, line : "Lame are their feet, and wrinkled is their face;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9645, line : "With humble mien, and with dejected eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9646, line : "Constant they follow, where injustice flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9647, line : "Injustice swift, erect, and unconfined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9648, line : "Sweeps the wide earth, and tramples o'er mankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9649, line : "While Prayers, to heal her wrongs, move slow behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9650, line : "Who hears these daughters of almighty Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9651, line : "For him they mediate to the throne above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9652, line : "When man rejects the humble suit they make,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9653, line : "The sire revenges for the daughters' sake;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9654, line : "From Jove commission'd, fierce injustice then"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9655, line : "Descends to punish unrelenting men."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9656, line : "O let not headlong passion bear the sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9657, line : "These reconciling goddesses obey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9658, line : "Due honours to the seed of Jove belong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9659, line : "Due honours calm the fierce, and bend the strong."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9660, line : "Were these not paid thee by the terms we bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9661, line : "Were rage still harbour'd in the haughty king;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9662, line : "Nor Greece nor all her fortunes should engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9663, line : "Thy friend to plead against so just a rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9664, line : "But since what honour asks the general sends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9665, line : "And sends by those whom most thy heart commends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9666, line : "The best and noblest of the Grecian train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9667, line : "Permit not these to sue, and sue in vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9668, line : "Let me (my son) an ancient fact unfold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9669, line : "A great example drawn from times of old;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9670, line : "Hear what our fathers were, and what their praise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9671, line : "Who conquer'd their revenge in former days."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9673, line : "\"Where Calydon on rocky mountains stands(212)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9674, line : "Once fought the Ćtolian and Curetian bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9675, line : "To guard it those; to conquer, these advance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9676, line : "And mutual deaths were dealt with mutual chance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9677, line : "The silver Cynthia bade contention rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9678, line : "In vengeance of neglected sacrifice;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9679, line : "On OEneus fields she sent a monstrous boar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9680, line : "That levell'd harvests, and whole forests tore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9681, line : "This beast (when many a chief his tusks had slain)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9682, line : "Great Meleager stretch'd along the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9683, line : "Then, for his spoils, a new debate arose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9684, line : "The neighbour nations thence commencing foes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9685, line : "Strong as they were, the bold Curetes fail'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9686, line : "While Meleager's thundering arm prevail'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9687, line : "Till rage at length inflamed his lofty breast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9688, line : "(For rage invades the wisest and the best)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9690, line : "\"Cursed by Althaea, to his wrath he yields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9691, line : "And in his wife's embrace forgets the fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9692, line : "(She from Marpessa sprung, divinely fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9693, line : "And matchless Idas, more than man in war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9694, line : "The god of day adored the mother's charms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9695, line : "Against the god the father bent his arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9696, line : "The afflicted pair, their sorrows to proclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9697, line : "From Cleopatra changed their daughter's name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9698, line : "And call'd Alcyone; a name to show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9699, line : "The father's grief, the mourning mother's woe.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9700, line : "To her the chief retired from stern debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9701, line : "But found no peace from fierce Althaea's hate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9702, line : "Althaea's hate the unhappy warrior drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9703, line : "Whose luckless hand his royal uncle slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9704, line : "She beat the ground, and call'd the powers beneath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9705, line : "On her own son to wreak her brother's death;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9706, line : "Hell heard her curses from the realms profound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9707, line : "And the red fiends that walk the nightly round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9708, line : "In vain Ćtolia her deliverer waits,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9709, line : "War shakes her walls, and thunders at her gates."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9710, line : "She sent ambassadors, a chosen band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9711, line : "Priests of the gods, and elders of the land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9712, line : "Besought the chief to save the sinking state:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9713, line : "Their prayers were urgent, and their proffers great:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9714, line : "(Full fifty acres of the richest ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9715, line : "Half pasture green, and half with vineyards crown'd:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9716, line : "His suppliant father, aged OEneus, came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9717, line : "His sisters follow'd; even the vengeful dame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9718, line : "Althaea, sues; his friends before him fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9719, line : "He stands relentless, and rejects them all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9720, line : "Meanwhile the victor's shouts ascend the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9721, line : "The walls are scaled; the rolling flames arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9722, line : "At length his wife (a form divine) appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9723, line : "With piercing cries, and supplicating tears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9724, line : "She paints the horrors of a conquer'd town,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9725, line : "The heroes slain, the palaces o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9726, line : "The matrons ravish'd, the whole race enslaved:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9727, line : "The warrior heard, he vanquish'd, and he saved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9728, line : "The Ćtolians, long disdain'd, now took their turn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9729, line : "And left the chief their broken faith to mourn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9730, line : "Learn hence, betimes to curb pernicious ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9731, line : "Nor stay till yonder fleets ascend in fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9732, line : "Accept the presents; draw thy conquering sword;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9733, line : "And be amongst our guardian gods adored.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9735, line : "Thus he: the stern Achilles thus replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9736, line : "\"My second father, and my reverend guide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9737, line : "Thy friend, believe me, no such gifts demands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9738, line : "And asks no honours from a mortal's hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9739, line : "Jove honours me, and favours my designs;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9740, line : "His pleasure guides me, and his will confines;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9741, line : "And here I stay (if such his high behest)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9742, line : "While life's warm spirit beats within my breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9743, line : "Yet hear one word, and lodge it in thy heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9744, line : "No more molest me on Atrides' part:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9745, line : "Is it for him these tears are taught to flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9746, line : "For him these sorrows? for my mortal foe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9747, line : "A generous friendship no cold medium knows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9748, line : "Burns with one love, with one resentment glows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9749, line : "One should our interests and our passions be;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9750, line : "My friend must hate the man that injures me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9751, line : "Do this, my Phoenix, 'tis a generous part;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9752, line : "And share my realms, my honours, and my heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9753, line : "Let these return: our voyage, or our stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9754, line : "Rest undetermined till the dawning day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9756, line : "He ceased; then order'd for the sage's bed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9757, line : "A warmer couch with numerous carpets spread."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9758, line : "With that, stern Ajax his long silence broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9759, line : "And thus, impatient, to Ulysses spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9761, line : "\"Hence let us go--why waste we time in vain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9762, line : "See what effect our low submissions gain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9763, line : "Liked or not liked, his words we must relate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9764, line : "The Greeks expect them, and our heroes wait."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9765, line : "Proud as he is, that iron heart retains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9766, line : "Its stubborn purpose, and his friends disdains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9767, line : "Stern and unpitying! if a brother bleed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9768, line : "On just atonement, we remit the deed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9769, line : "A sire the slaughter of his son forgives;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9770, line : "The price of blood discharged, the murderer lives:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9771, line : "The haughtiest hearts at length their rage resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9772, line : "And gifts can conquer every soul but thine.(213)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9773, line : "The gods that unrelenting breast have steel'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9774, line : "And cursed thee with a mind that cannot yield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9775, line : "One woman-slave was ravish'd from thy arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9776, line : "Lo, seven are offer'd, and of equal charms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9777, line : "Then hear, Achilles! be of better mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9778, line : "Revere thy roof, and to thy guests be kind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9779, line : "And know the men of all the Grecian host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9780, line : "Who honour worth, and prize thy valour most.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9782, line : "\"O soul of battles, and thy people's guide!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9783, line : "(To Ajax thus the first of Greeks replied)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9784, line : "Well hast thou spoke; but at the tyrant's name"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9785, line : "My rage rekindles, and my soul's on flame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9786, line : "'Tis just resentment, and becomes the brave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9787, line : "Disgraced, dishonour'd, like the vilest slave!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9788, line : "Return, then, heroes! and our answer bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9789, line : "The glorious combat is no more my care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9790, line : "Not till, amidst yon sinking navy slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9791, line : "The blood of Greeks shall dye the sable main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9792, line : "Not till the flames, by Hector's fury thrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9793, line : "Consume your vessels, and approach my own;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9794, line : "Just there, the impetuous homicide shall stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9795, line : "There cease his battle, and there feel our hand.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9797, line : "This said, each prince a double goblet crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9798, line : "And cast a large libation on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9799, line : "Then to their vessels, through the gloomy shades,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9800, line : "The chiefs return; divine Ulysses leads."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9801, line : "Meantime Achilles' slaves prepared a bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9802, line : "With fleeces, carpets, and soft linen spread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9803, line : "There, till the sacred morn restored the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9804, line : "In slumber sweet the reverend Phoenix lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9805, line : "But in his inner tent, an ampler space,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9806, line : "Achilles slept; and in his warm embrace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9807, line : "Fair Diomede of the Lesbian race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9808, line : "Last, for Patroclus was the couch prepared,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9809, line : "Whose nightly joys the beauteous Iphis shared;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9810, line : "Achilles to his friend consign'd her charms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9811, line : "When Scyros fell before his conquering arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9813, line : "And now the elected chiefs whom Greece had sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9814, line : "Pass'd through the hosts, and reach'd the royal tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9815, line : "Then rising all, with goblets in their hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9816, line : "The peers and leaders of the Achaian bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9817, line : "Hail'd their return: Atrides first begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9819, line : "\"Say what success? divine Laertes' son!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9820, line : "Achilles' high resolves declare to all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9821, line : "\"Returns the chief, or must our navy fall?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9823, line : "\"Great king of nations! (Ithacus replied)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9824, line : "Fix'd is his wrath, unconquer'd is his pride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9825, line : "He slights thy friendship, thy proposals scorns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9826, line : "And, thus implored, with fiercer fury burns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9827, line : "To save our army, and our fleets to free,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9828, line : "Is not his care; but left to Greece and thee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9829, line : "Your eyes shall view, when morning paints the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9830, line : "Beneath his oars the whitening billows fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9831, line : "Us too he bids our oars and sails employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9832, line : "Nor hope the fall of heaven-protected Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9833, line : "For Jove o'ershades her with his arm divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9834, line : "Inspires her war, and bids her glory shine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9835, line : "Such was his word: what further he declared,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9836, line : "These sacred heralds and great Ajax heard."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9837, line : "But Phoenix in his tent the chief retains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9838, line : "Safe to transport him to his native plains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9839, line : "When morning dawns; if other he decree,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9840, line : "His age is sacred, and his choice is free.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9842, line : "Ulysses ceased: the great Achaian host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9843, line : "With sorrow seized, in consternation lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9844, line : "Attend the stern reply. Tydides broke"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9845, line : "The general silence, and undaunted spoke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9846, line : "\"Why should we gifts to proud Achilles send,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9847, line : "Or strive with prayers his haughty soul to bend?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9848, line : "His country's woes he glories to deride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9849, line : "And prayers will burst that swelling heart with pride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9850, line : "Be the fierce impulse of his rage obey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9851, line : "Our battles let him or desert or aid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9852, line : "Then let him arm when Jove or he think fit:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9853, line : "That, to his madness, or to Heaven commit:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9854, line : "What for ourselves we can, is always ours;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9855, line : "This night, let due repast refresh our powers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9856, line : "(For strength consists in spirits and in blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9857, line : "And those are owed to generous wine and food;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9858, line : "But when the rosy messenger of day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9859, line : "Strikes the blue mountains with her golden ray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9860, line : "Ranged at the ships, let all our squadrons shine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9861, line : "In flaming arms, a long-extended line:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9862, line : "In the dread front let great Atrides stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9863, line : "The first in danger, as in high command.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9865, line : "Shouts of acclaim the listening heroes raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9866, line : "Then each to Heaven the due libations pays;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9867, line : "Till sleep, descending o'er the tents, bestows"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9868, line : "The grateful blessings of desired repose.\"(214)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9870, line : "[Illustration: ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9872, line : "ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9878, line : "BOOK X."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9881, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9883, line : "THE NIGHT-ADVENTURE OF DIOMED AND ULYSSES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9885, line : "Upon the refusal of Achilles to return to the army, the distress of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9886, line : "Agamemnon is described in the most lively manner. He takes no rest that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9887, line : "night, but passes through the camp, awaking the leaders, and contriving"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9888, line : "all possible methods for the public safety. Menelaus, Nestor, Ulysses, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9889, line : "Diomed are employed in raising the rest of the captains. They call a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9890, line : "council of war, and determine to send scouts into the enemies' camp, to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9891, line : "learn their posture, and discover their intentions. Diomed undertakes this"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9892, line : "hazardous enterprise, and makes choice of Ulysses for his companion. In"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9893, line : "their passage they surprise Dolon, whom Hector had sent on a like design"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9894, line : "to the camp of the Grecians. From him they are informed of the situation"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9895, line : "of the Trojan and auxiliary forces, and particularly of Rhesus, and the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9896, line : "Thracians who were lately arrived. They pass on with success; kill Rhesus,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9897, line : "with several of his officers, and seize the famous horses of that prince,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9898, line : "with which they return in triumph to the camp."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9900, line : "The same night continues; the scene lies in the two camps."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9902, line : "All night the chiefs before their vessels lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9903, line : "And lost in sleep the labours of the day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9904, line : "All but the king: with various thoughts oppress'd,(215)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9905, line : "His country's cares lay rolling in his breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9906, line : "As when by lightnings Jove's ethereal power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9907, line : "Foretels the rattling hail, or weighty shower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9908, line : "Or sends soft snows to whiten all the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9909, line : "Or bids the brazen throat of war to roar;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9910, line : "By fits one flash succeeds as one expires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9911, line : "And heaven flames thick with momentary fires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9912, line : "So bursting frequent from Atrides' breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9913, line : "Sighs following sighs his inward fears confess'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9914, line : "Now o'er the fields, dejected, he surveys"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9915, line : "From thousand Trojan fires the mounting blaze;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9916, line : "Hears in the passing wind their music blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9917, line : "And marks distinct the voices of the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9918, line : "Now looking backwards to the fleet and coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9919, line : "Anxious he sorrows for the endangered host."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9920, line : "He rends his hair, in sacrifice to Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9921, line : "And sues to him that ever lives above:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9922, line : "Inly he groans; while glory and despair"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9923, line : "Divide his heart, and wage a double war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9925, line : "A thousand cares his labouring breast revolves;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9926, line : "To seek sage Nestor now the chief resolves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9927, line : "With him, in wholesome counsels, to debate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9928, line : "What yet remains to save the afflicted state."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9929, line : "He rose, and first he cast his mantle round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9930, line : "Next on his feet the shining sandals bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9931, line : "A lion's yellow spoils his back conceal'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9932, line : "His warlike hand a pointed javelin held."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9933, line : "Meanwhile his brother, press'd with equal woes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9934, line : "Alike denied the gifts of soft repose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9935, line : "Laments for Greece, that in his cause before"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9936, line : "So much had suffer'd and must suffer more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9937, line : "A leopard's spotted hide his shoulders spread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9938, line : "A brazen helmet glitter'd on his head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9939, line : "Thus (with a javelin in his hand) he went"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9940, line : "To wake Atrides in the royal tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9941, line : "Already waked, Atrides he descried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9942, line : "His armour buckling at his vessel's side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9943, line : "Joyful they met; the Spartan thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9944, line : "\"Why puts my brother his bright armour on?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9945, line : "Sends he some spy, amidst these silent hours,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9946, line : "To try yon camp, and watch the Trojan powers?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9947, line : "But say, what hero shall sustain that task?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9948, line : "Such bold exploits uncommon courage ask;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9949, line : "Guideless, alone, through night's dark shade to go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9950, line : "And midst a hostile camp explore the foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9952, line : "To whom the king: \"In such distress we stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9953, line : "No vulgar counsel our affairs demand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9954, line : "Greece to preserve, is now no easy part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9955, line : "But asks high wisdom, deep design, and art."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9956, line : "For Jove, averse, our humble prayer denies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9957, line : "And bows his head to Hector's sacrifice."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9958, line : "What eye has witness'd, or what ear believed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9959, line : "In one great day, by one great arm achieved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9960, line : "Such wondrous deeds as Hector's hand has done,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9961, line : "And we beheld, the last revolving sun"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9962, line : "What honours the beloved of Jove adorn!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9963, line : "Sprung from no god, and of no goddess born;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9964, line : "Yet such his acts, as Greeks unborn shall tell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9965, line : "And curse the battle where their fathers fell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9967, line : "\"Now speed thy hasty course along the fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9968, line : "There call great Ajax, and the prince of Crete;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9969, line : "Ourself to hoary Nestor will repair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9970, line : "To keep the guards on duty be his care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9971, line : "(For Nestor's influence best that quarter guides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9972, line : "Whose son with Merion, o'er the watch presides.\")"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9973, line : "To whom the Spartan: \"These thy orders borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9974, line : "Say, shall I stay, or with despatch return?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9975, line : "\"There shall thou stay, (the king of men replied,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9976, line : "Else may we miss to meet, without a guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9977, line : "The paths so many, and the camp so wide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9978, line : "Still, with your voice the slothful soldiers raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9979, line : "Urge by their fathers' fame their future praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9980, line : "Forget we now our state and lofty birth;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9981, line : "Not titles here, but works, must prove our worth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9982, line : "To labour is the lot of man below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9983, line : "And when Jove gave us life, he gave us woe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9985, line : "This said, each parted to his several cares:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9986, line : "The king to Nestor's sable ship repairs;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9987, line : "The sage protector of the Greeks he found"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9988, line : "Stretch'd in his bed with all his arms around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9989, line : "The various-colour'd scarf, the shield he rears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9990, line : "The shining helmet, and the pointed spears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9991, line : "The dreadful weapons of the warrior's rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9992, line : "That, old in arms, disdain'd the peace of age."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9993, line : "Then, leaning on his hand his watchful head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9994, line : "The hoary monarch raised his eyes and said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9996, line : "\"What art thou, speak, that on designs unknown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9997, line : "While others sleep, thus range the camp alone;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9998, line : "Seek'st thou some friend or nightly sentinel?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 9999, line : "Stand off, approach not, but thy purpose tell.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10001, line : "\"O son of Neleus, (thus the king rejoin'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10002, line : "Pride of the Greeks, and glory of thy kind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10003, line : "Lo, here the wretched Agamemnon stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10004, line : "The unhappy general of the Grecian bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10005, line : "Whom Jove decrees with daily cares to bend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10006, line : "And woes, that only with his life shall end!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10007, line : "Scarce can my knees these trembling limbs sustain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10008, line : "And scarce my heart support its load of pain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10009, line : "No taste of sleep these heavy eyes have known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10010, line : "Confused, and sad, I wander thus alone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10011, line : "With fears distracted, with no fix'd design;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10012, line : "And all my people's miseries are mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10013, line : "If aught of use thy waking thoughts suggest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10014, line : "(Since cares, like mine, deprive thy soul of rest,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10015, line : "Impart thy counsel, and assist thy friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10016, line : "Now let us jointly to the trench descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10017, line : "At every gate the fainting guard excite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10018, line : "Tired with the toils of day and watch of night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10019, line : "Else may the sudden foe our works invade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10020, line : "So near, and favour'd by the gloomy shade.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10022, line : "To him thus Nestor: \"Trust the powers above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10023, line : "Nor think proud Hector's hopes confirm'd by Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10024, line : "How ill agree the views of vain mankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10025, line : "And the wise counsels of the eternal mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10026, line : "Audacious Hector, if the gods ordain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10027, line : "That great Achilles rise and rage again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10028, line : "What toils attend thee, and what woes remain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10029, line : "Lo, faithful Nestor thy command obeys;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10030, line : "The care is next our other chiefs to raise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10031, line : "Ulysses, Diomed, we chiefly need;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10032, line : "Meges for strength, Oileus famed for speed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10033, line : "Some other be despatch'd of nimbler feet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10034, line : "To those tall ships, remotest of the fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10035, line : "Where lie great Ajax and the king of Crete.(216)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10036, line : "To rouse the Spartan I myself decree;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10037, line : "Dear as he is to us, and dear to thee,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10038, line : "Yet must I tax his sloth, that claims no share"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10039, line : "With his great brother in his martial care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10040, line : "Him it behoved to every chief to sue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10041, line : "Preventing every part perform'd by you;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10042, line : "For strong necessity our toils demands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10043, line : "Claims all our hearts, and urges all our hands.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10045, line : "To whom the king: \"With reverence we allow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10046, line : "Thy just rebukes, yet learn to spare them now:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10047, line : "My generous brother is of gentle kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10048, line : "He seems remiss, but bears a valiant mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10049, line : "Through too much deference to our sovereign sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10050, line : "Content to follow when we lead the way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10051, line : "But now, our ills industrious to prevent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10052, line : "Long ere the rest he rose, and sought my tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10053, line : "The chiefs you named, already at his call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10054, line : "Prepare to meet us near the navy-wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10055, line : "Assembling there, between the trench and gates,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10056, line : "Near the night-guards, our chosen council waits.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10058, line : "\"Then none (said Nestor) shall his rule withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10059, line : "For great examples justify command.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10060, line : "With that, the venerable warrior rose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10061, line : "The shining greaves his manly legs enclose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10062, line : "His purple mantle golden buckles join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10063, line : "Warm with the softest wool, and doubly lined."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10064, line : "Then rushing from his tent, he snatch'd in haste"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10065, line : "His steely lance, that lighten'd as he pass'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10066, line : "The camp he traversed through the sleeping crowd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10067, line : "Stopp'd at Ulysses' tent, and call'd aloud."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10068, line : "Ulysses, sudden as the voice was sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10069, line : "Awakes, starts up, and issues from his tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10070, line : "\"What new distress, what sudden cause of fright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10071, line : "Thus leads you wandering in the silent night?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10072, line : "\"O prudent chief! (the Pylian sage replied)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10073, line : "Wise as thou art, be now thy wisdom tried:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10074, line : "Whatever means of safety can be sought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10075, line : "Whatever counsels can inspire our thought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10076, line : "Whatever methods, or to fly or fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10077, line : "All, all depend on this important night!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10078, line : "He heard, return'd, and took his painted shield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10079, line : "Then join'd the chiefs, and follow'd through the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10080, line : "Without his tent, bold Diomed they found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10081, line : "All sheathed in arms, his brave companions round:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10082, line : "Each sunk in sleep, extended on the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10083, line : "His head reclining on his bossy shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10084, line : "A wood of spears stood by, that, fix'd upright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10085, line : "Shot from their flashing points a quivering light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10086, line : "A bull's black hide composed the hero's bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10087, line : "A splendid carpet roll'd beneath his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10088, line : "Then, with his foot, old Nestor gently shakes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10089, line : "The slumbering chief, and in these words awakes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10091, line : "\"Rise, son of Tydeus! to the brave and strong"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10092, line : "Rest seems inglorious, and the night too long."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10093, line : "But sleep'st thou now, when from yon hill the foe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10094, line : "Hangs o'er the fleet, and shades our walls below?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10096, line : "At this, soft slumber from his eyelids fled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10097, line : "The warrior saw the hoary chief, and said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10098, line : "\"Wondrous old man! whose soul no respite knows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10099, line : "Though years and honours bid thee seek repose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10100, line : "Let younger Greeks our sleeping warriors wake;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10101, line : "Ill fits thy age these toils to undertake.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10102, line : "\"My friend, (he answered,) generous is thy care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10103, line : "These toils, my subjects and my sons might bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10104, line : "Their loyal thoughts and pious love conspire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10105, line : "To ease a sovereign and relieve a sire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10106, line : "But now the last despair surrounds our host;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10107, line : "No hour must pass, no moment must be lost;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10108, line : "Each single Greek, in this conclusive strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10109, line : "Stands on the sharpest edge of death or life:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10110, line : "Yet, if my years thy kind regard engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10111, line : "Employ thy youth as I employ my age;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10112, line : "Succeed to these my cares, and rouse the rest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10113, line : "He serves me most, who serves his country best.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10115, line : "This said, the hero o'er his shoulders flung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10116, line : "A lion's spoils, that to his ankles hung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10117, line : "Then seized his ponderous lance, and strode along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10118, line : "Meges the bold, with Ajax famed for speed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10119, line : "The warrior roused, and to the entrenchments lead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10121, line : "And now the chiefs approach the nightly guard;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10122, line : "A wakeful squadron, each in arms prepared:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10123, line : "The unwearied watch their listening leaders keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10124, line : "And, couching close, repel invading sleep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10125, line : "So faithful dogs their fleecy charge maintain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10126, line : "With toil protected from the prowling train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10127, line : "When the gaunt lioness, with hunger bold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10128, line : "Springs from the mountains toward the guarded fold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10129, line : "Through breaking woods her rustling course they hear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10130, line : "Loud, and more loud, the clamours strike their ear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10131, line : "Of hounds and men: they start, they gaze around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10132, line : "Watch every side, and turn to every sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10133, line : "Thus watch'd the Grecians, cautious of surprise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10134, line : "Each voice, each motion, drew their ears and eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10135, line : "Each step of passing feet increased the affright;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10136, line : "And hostile Troy was ever full in sight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10137, line : "Nestor with joy the wakeful band survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10138, line : "And thus accosted through the gloomy shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10139, line : "\"'Tis well, my sons! your nightly cares employ;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10140, line : "Else must our host become the scorn of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10141, line : "Watch thus, and Greece shall live.\" The hero said;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10142, line : "Then o'er the trench the following chieftains led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10143, line : "His son, and godlike Merion, march'd behind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10144, line : "(For these the princes to their council join'd)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10145, line : "The trenches pass'd, the assembled kings around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10146, line : "In silent state the consistory crown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10147, line : "A place there was, yet undefiled with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10148, line : "The spot where Hector stopp'd his rage before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10149, line : "When night descending, from his vengeful hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10150, line : "Reprieved the relics of the Grecian band:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10151, line : "(The plain beside with mangled corps was spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10152, line : "And all his progress mark'd by heaps of dead:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10153, line : "There sat the mournful kings: when Neleus' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10154, line : "The council opening, in these words begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10156, line : "\"Is there (said he) a chief so greatly brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10157, line : "His life to hazard, and his country save?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10158, line : "Lives there a man, who singly dares to go"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10159, line : "To yonder camp, or seize some straggling foe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10160, line : "Or favour'd by the night approach so near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10161, line : "Their speech, their counsels, and designs to hear?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10162, line : "If to besiege our navies they prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10163, line : "Or Troy once more must be the seat of war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10164, line : "This could he learn, and to our peers recite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10165, line : "And pass unharm'd the dangers of the night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10166, line : "What fame were his through all succeeding days,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10167, line : "While Phoebus shines, or men have tongues to praise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10168, line : "What gifts his grateful country would bestow!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10169, line : "What must not Greece to her deliverer owe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10170, line : "A sable ewe each leader should provide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10171, line : "With each a sable lambkin by her side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10172, line : "At every rite his share should be increased,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10173, line : "And his the foremost honours of the feast.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10175, line : "Fear held them mute: alone, untaught to fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10176, line : "Tydides spoke--\"The man you seek is here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10177, line : "Through yon black camps to bend my dangerous way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10178, line : "Some god within commands, and I obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10179, line : "But let some other chosen warrior join,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10180, line : "To raise my hopes, and second my design."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10181, line : "By mutual confidence and mutual aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10182, line : "Great deeds are done, and great discoveries made;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10183, line : "The wise new prudence from the wise acquire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10184, line : "And one brave hero fans another's fire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10186, line : "Contending leaders at the word arose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10187, line : "Each generous breast with emulation glows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10188, line : "So brave a task each Ajax strove to share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10189, line : "Bold Merion strove, and Nestor's valiant heir;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10190, line : "The Spartan wish'd the second place to gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10191, line : "And great Ulysses wish'd, nor wish'd in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10192, line : "Then thus the king of men the contest ends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10193, line : "\"Thou first of warriors, and thou best of friends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10194, line : "Undaunted Diomed! what chief to join"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10195, line : "In this great enterprise, is only thine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10196, line : "Just be thy choice, without affection made;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10197, line : "To birth, or office, no respect be paid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10198, line : "Let worth determine here.\" The monarch spake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10199, line : "And inly trembled for his brother's sake."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10201, line : "\"Then thus (the godlike Diomed rejoin'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10202, line : "My choice declares the impulse of my mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10203, line : "How can I doubt, while great Ulysses stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10204, line : "To lend his counsels and assist our hands?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10205, line : "A chief, whose safety is Minerva's care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10206, line : "So famed, so dreadful, in the works of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10207, line : "Bless'd in his conduct, I no aid require;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10208, line : "Wisdom like his might pass through flames of fire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10210, line : "\"It fits thee not, before these chiefs of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10211, line : "(Replied the sage,) to praise me, or to blame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10212, line : "Praise from a friend, or censure from a foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10213, line : "Are lost on hearers that our merits know."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10214, line : "But let us haste--Night rolls the hours away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10215, line : "The reddening orient shows the coming day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10216, line : "The stars shine fainter on the ethereal plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10217, line : "And of night's empire but a third remains.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10219, line : "Thus having spoke, with generous ardour press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10220, line : "In arms terrific their huge limbs they dress'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10221, line : "A two-edged falchion Thrasymed the brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10222, line : "And ample buckler, to Tydides gave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10223, line : "Then in a leathern helm he cased his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10224, line : "Short of its crest, and with no plume o'erspread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10225, line : "(Such as by youths unused to arms are worn:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10226, line : "No spoils enrich it, and no studs adorn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10227, line : "Next him Ulysses took a shining sword,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10228, line : "A bow and quiver, with bright arrows stored:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10229, line : "A well-proved casque, with leather braces bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10230, line : "(Thy gift, Meriones,) his temples crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10231, line : "Soft wool within; without, in order spread,(217)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10232, line : "A boar's white teeth grinn'd horrid o'er his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10233, line : "This from Amyntor, rich Ormenus' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10234, line : "Autolycus by fraudful rapine won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10235, line : "And gave Amphidamas; from him the prize"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10236, line : "Molus received, the pledge of social ties;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10237, line : "The helmet next by Merion was possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10238, line : "And now Ulysses' thoughtful temples press'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10239, line : "Thus sheathed in arms, the council they forsake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10240, line : "And dark through paths oblique their progress take."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10241, line : "Just then, in sign she favour'd their intent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10242, line : "A long-wing'd heron great Minerva sent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10243, line : "This, though surrounding shades obscured their view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10244, line : "By the shrill clang and whistling wings they knew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10245, line : "As from the right she soar'd, Ulysses pray'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10246, line : "Hail'd the glad omen, and address'd the maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10248, line : "\"O daughter of that god whose arm can wield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10249, line : "The avenging bolt, and shake the dreadful shield!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10250, line : "O thou! for ever present in my way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10251, line : "Who all my motions, all my toils survey!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10252, line : "Safe may we pass beneath the gloomy shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10253, line : "Safe by thy succour to our ships convey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10254, line : "And let some deed this signal night adorn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10255, line : "To claim the tears of Trojans yet unborn.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10257, line : "Then godlike Diomed preferr'd his prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10258, line : "\"Daughter of Jove, unconquer'd Pallas! hear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10259, line : "Great queen of arms, whose favour Tydeus won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10260, line : "As thou defend'st the sire, defend the son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10261, line : "When on Ćsopus' banks the banded powers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10262, line : "Of Greece he left, and sought the Theban towers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10263, line : "Peace was his charge; received with peaceful show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10264, line : "He went a legate, but return'd a foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10265, line : "Then help'd by thee, and cover'd by thy shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10266, line : "He fought with numbers, and made numbers yield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10267, line : "So now be present, O celestial maid!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10268, line : "So still continue to the race thine aid!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10269, line : "A youthful steer shall fall beneath the stroke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10270, line : "Untamed, unconscious of the galling yoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10271, line : "With ample forehead, and with spreading horns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10272, line : "Whose taper tops refulgent gold adorns.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10273, line : "The heroes pray'd, and Pallas from the skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10274, line : "Accords their vow, succeeds their enterprise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10275, line : "Now, like two lions panting for the prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10276, line : "With dreadful thoughts they trace the dreary way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10277, line : "Through the black horrors of the ensanguined plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10278, line : "Through dust, through blood, o'er arms, and hills of slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10280, line : "Nor less bold Hector, and the sons of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10281, line : "On high designs the wakeful hours employ;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10282, line : "The assembled peers their lofty chief enclosed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10283, line : "Who thus the counsels of his breast proposed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10285, line : "\"What glorious man, for high attempts prepared,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10286, line : "Dares greatly venture for a rich reward?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10287, line : "Of yonder fleet a bold discovery make,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10288, line : "What watch they keep, and what resolves they take?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10289, line : "If now subdued they meditate their flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10290, line : "And, spent with toil, neglect the watch of night?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10291, line : "His be the chariot that shall please him most,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10292, line : "Of all the plunder of the vanquish'd host;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10293, line : "His the fair steeds that all the rest excel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10294, line : "And his the glory to have served so well.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10296, line : "A youth there was among the tribes of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10297, line : "Dolon his name, Eumedes' only boy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10298, line : "(Five girls beside the reverend herald told.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10299, line : "Rich was the son in brass, and rich in gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10300, line : "Not bless'd by nature with the charms of face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10301, line : "But swift of foot, and matchless in the race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10302, line : "\"Hector! (he said) my courage bids me meet"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10303, line : "This high achievement, and explore the fleet:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10304, line : "But first exalt thy sceptre to the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10305, line : "And swear to grant me the demanded prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10306, line : "The immortal coursers, and the glittering car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10307, line : "That bear Pelides through the ranks of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10308, line : "Encouraged thus, no idle scout I go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10309, line : "Fulfil thy wish, their whole intention know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10310, line : "Even to the royal tent pursue my way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10311, line : "And all their counsels, all their aims betray.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10313, line : "The chief then heaved the golden sceptre high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10314, line : "Attesting thus the monarch of the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10315, line : "\"Be witness thou! immortal lord of all!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10316, line : "Whose thunder shakes the dark aerial hall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10317, line : "By none but Dolon shall this prize be borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10318, line : "And him alone the immortal steeds adorn.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10320, line : "Thus Hector swore: the gods were call'd in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10321, line : "But the rash youth prepares to scour the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10322, line : "Across his back the bended bow he flung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10323, line : "A wolf's grey hide around his shoulders hung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10324, line : "A ferret's downy fur his helmet lined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10325, line : "And in his hand a pointed javelin shined."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10326, line : "Then (never to return) he sought the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10327, line : "And trod the path his feet must tread no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10328, line : "Scarce had he pass'd the steeds and Trojan throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10329, line : "(Still bending forward as he coursed along,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10330, line : "When, on the hollow way, the approaching tread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10331, line : "Ulysses mark'd, and thus to Diomed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10333, line : "\"O friend! I hear some step of hostile feet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10334, line : "Moving this way, or hastening to the fleet;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10335, line : "Some spy, perhaps, to lurk beside the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10336, line : "Or nightly pillager that strips the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10337, line : "Yet let him pass, and win a little space;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10338, line : "Then rush behind him, and prevent his pace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10339, line : "But if too swift of foot he flies before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10340, line : "Confine his course along the fleet and shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10341, line : "Betwixt the camp and him our spears employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10342, line : "And intercept his hoped return to Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10344, line : "With that they stepp'd aside, and stoop'd their head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10345, line : "(As Dolon pass'd,) behind a heap of dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10346, line : "Along the path the spy unwary flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10347, line : "Soft, at just distance, both the chiefs pursue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10348, line : "So distant they, and such the space between,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10349, line : "As when two teams of mules divide the green,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10350, line : "(To whom the hind like shares of land allows,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10351, line : "When now new furrows part the approaching ploughs."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10352, line : "Now Dolon, listening, heard them as they pass'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10353, line : "Hector (he thought) had sent, and check'd his haste,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10354, line : "Till scarce at distance of a javelin's throw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10355, line : "No voice succeeding, he perceived the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10356, line : "As when two skilful hounds the leveret wind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10357, line : "Or chase through woods obscure the trembling hind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10358, line : "Now lost, now seen, they intercept his way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10359, line : "And from the herd still turn the flying prey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10360, line : "So fast, and with such fears, the Trojan flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10361, line : "So close, so constant, the bold Greeks pursue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10362, line : "Now almost on the fleet the dastard falls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10363, line : "And mingles with the guards that watch the walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10364, line : "When brave Tydides stopp'd; a gen'rous thought"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10365, line : "(Inspired by Pallas) in his bosom wrought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10366, line : "Lest on the foe some forward Greek advance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10367, line : "And snatch the glory from his lifted lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10368, line : "Then thus aloud: \"Whoe'er thou art, remain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10369, line : "This javelin else shall fix thee to the plain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10370, line : "He said, and high in air the weapon cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10371, line : "Which wilful err'd, and o'er his shoulder pass'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10372, line : "Then fix'd in earth. Against the trembling wood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10373, line : "The wretch stood propp'd, and quiver'd as he stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10374, line : "A sudden palsy seized his turning head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10375, line : "His loose teeth chatter'd, and his colour fled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10376, line : "The panting warriors seize him as he stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10377, line : "And with unmanly tears his life demands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10379, line : "\"O spare my youth, and for the breath I owe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10380, line : "Large gifts of price my father shall bestow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10381, line : "Vast heaps of brass shall in your ships be told,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10382, line : "And steel well-temper'd and refulgent gold.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10384, line : "To whom Ulysses made this wise reply:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10385, line : "\"Whoe'er thou art, be bold, nor fear to die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10386, line : "What moves thee, say, when sleep has closed the sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10387, line : "To roam the silent fields in dead of night?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10388, line : "Cam'st thou the secrets of our camp to find,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10389, line : "By Hector prompted, or thy daring mind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10390, line : "Or art some wretch by hopes of plunder led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10391, line : "Through heaps of carnage, to despoil the dead?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10393, line : "Then thus pale Dolon, with a fearful look:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10394, line : "(Still, as he spoke, his limbs with horror shook:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10395, line : "\"Hither I came, by Hector's words deceived;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10396, line : "Much did he promise, rashly I believed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10397, line : "No less a bribe than great Achilles' car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10398, line : "And those swift steeds that sweep the ranks of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10399, line : "Urged me, unwilling, this attempt to make;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10400, line : "To learn what counsels, what resolves you take:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10401, line : "If now subdued, you fix your hopes on flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10402, line : "And, tired with toils, neglect the watch of night.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10404, line : "\"Bold was thy aim, and glorious was the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10405, line : "(Ulysses, with a scornful smile, replies,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10406, line : "Far other rulers those proud steeds demand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10407, line : "And scorn the guidance of a vulgar hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10408, line : "Even great Achilles scarce their rage can tame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10409, line : "Achilles sprung from an immortal dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10410, line : "But say, be faithful, and the truth recite!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10411, line : "Where lies encamp'd the Trojan chief to-night?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10412, line : "Where stand his coursers? in what quarter sleep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10413, line : "Their other princes? tell what watch they keep:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10414, line : "Say, since this conquest, what their counsels are;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10415, line : "Or here to combat, from their city far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10416, line : "Or back to Ilion's walls transfer the war?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10418, line : "Ulysses thus, and thus Eumedes' son:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10419, line : "\"What Dolon knows, his faithful tongue shall own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10420, line : "Hector, the peers assembling in his tent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10421, line : "A council holds at Ilus' monument."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10422, line : "No certain guards the nightly watch partake;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10423, line : "Where'er yon fires ascend, the Trojans wake:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10424, line : "Anxious for Troy, the guard the natives keep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10425, line : "Safe in their cares, the auxiliar forces sleep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10426, line : "Whose wives and infants, from the danger far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10427, line : "Discharge their souls of half the fears of war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10429, line : "\"Then sleep those aids among the Trojan train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10430, line : "(Inquired the chief,) or scattered o'er the plain?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10431, line : "To whom the spy: \"Their powers they thus dispose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10432, line : "The Paeons, dreadful with their bended bows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10433, line : "The Carians, Caucons, the Pelasgian host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10434, line : "And Leleges, encamp along the coast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10435, line : "Not distant far, lie higher on the land"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10436, line : "The Lycian, Mysian, and Maeonian band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10437, line : "And Phrygia's horse, by Thymbras' ancient wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10438, line : "The Thracians utmost, and apart from all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10439, line : "These Troy but lately to her succour won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10440, line : "Led on by Rhesus, great Eioneus' son:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10441, line : "I saw his coursers in proud triumph go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10442, line : "Swift as the wind, and white as winter-snow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10443, line : "Rich silver plates his shining car infold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10444, line : "His solid arms, refulgent, flame with gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10445, line : "No mortal shoulders suit the glorious load,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10446, line : "Celestial panoply, to grace a god!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10447, line : "Let me, unhappy, to your fleet be borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10448, line : "Or leave me here, a captive's fate to mourn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10449, line : "In cruel chains, till your return reveal"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10450, line : "The truth or falsehood of the news I tell.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10452, line : "To this Tydides, with a gloomy frown:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10453, line : "\"Think not to live, though all the truth be shown:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10454, line : "Shall we dismiss thee, in some future strife"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10455, line : "To risk more bravely thy now forfeit life?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10456, line : "Or that again our camps thou may'st explore?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10457, line : "No--once a traitor, thou betray'st no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10459, line : "Sternly he spoke, and as the wretch prepared"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10460, line : "With humble blandishment to stroke his beard,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10461, line : "Like lightning swift the wrathful falchion flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10462, line : "Divides the neck, and cuts the nerves in two;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10463, line : "One instant snatch'd his trembling soul to hell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10464, line : "The head, yet speaking, mutter'd as it fell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10465, line : "The furry helmet from his brow they tear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10466, line : "The wolf's grey hide, the unbended bow and spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10467, line : "These great Ulysses lifting to the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10468, line : "To favouring Pallas dedicates the prize:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10470, line : "\"Great queen of arms, receive this hostile spoil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10471, line : "And let the Thracian steeds reward our toil;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10472, line : "Thee, first of all the heavenly host, we praise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10473, line : "O speed our labours, and direct our ways!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10474, line : "This said, the spoils, with dropping gore defaced,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10475, line : "High on a spreading tamarisk he placed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10476, line : "Then heap'd with reeds and gathered boughs the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10477, line : "To guide their footsteps to the place again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10479, line : "Through the still night they cross the devious fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10480, line : "Slippery with blood, o'er arms and heaps of shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10481, line : "Arriving where the Thracian squadrons lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10482, line : "And eased in sleep the labours of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10483, line : "Ranged in three lines they view the prostrate band:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10484, line : "The horses yoked beside each warrior stand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10485, line : "Their arms in order on the ground reclined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10486, line : "Through the brown shade the fulgid weapons shined:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10487, line : "Amidst lay Rhesus, stretch'd in sleep profound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10488, line : "And the white steeds behind his chariot bound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10489, line : "The welcome sight Ulysses first descries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10490, line : "And points to Diomed the tempting prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10491, line : "\"The man, the coursers, and the car behold!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10492, line : "Described by Dolon, with the arms of gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10493, line : "Now, brave Tydides! now thy courage try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10494, line : "Approach the chariot, and the steeds untie;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10495, line : "Or if thy soul aspire to fiercer deeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10496, line : "Urge thou the slaughter, while I seize the steeds.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10498, line : "Pallas (this said) her hero's bosom warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10499, line : "Breathed in his heart, and strung his nervous arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10500, line : "Where'er he pass'd, a purple stream pursued"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10501, line : "His thirsty falchion, fat with hostile blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10502, line : "Bathed all his footsteps, dyed the fields with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10503, line : "And a low groan remurmur'd through the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10504, line : "So the grim lion, from his nightly den,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10505, line : "O'erleaps the fences, and invades the pen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10506, line : "On sheep or goats, resistless in his way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10507, line : "He falls, and foaming rends the guardless prey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10508, line : "Nor stopp'd the fury of his vengeful hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10509, line : "Till twelve lay breathless of the Thracian band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10510, line : "Ulysses following, as his partner slew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10511, line : "Back by the foot each slaughter'd warrior drew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10512, line : "The milk-white coursers studious to convey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10513, line : "Safe to the ships, he wisely cleared the way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10514, line : "Lest the fierce steeds, not yet to battles bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10515, line : "Should start, and tremble at the heaps of dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10516, line : "Now twelve despatch'd, the monarch last they found;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10517, line : "Tydides' falchion fix'd him to the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10518, line : "Just then a deathful dream Minerva sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10519, line : "A warlike form appear'd before his tent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10520, line : "Whose visionary steel his bosom tore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10521, line : "So dream'd the monarch, and awaked no more.(218)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10523, line : "Ulysses now the snowy steeds detains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10524, line : "And leads them, fasten'd by the silver reins;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10525, line : "These, with his bow unbent, he lash'd along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10526, line : "(The scourge forgot, on Rhesus' chariot hung;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10527, line : "Then gave his friend the signal to retire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10528, line : "But him, new dangers, new achievements fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10529, line : "Doubtful he stood, or with his reeking blade"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10530, line : "To send more heroes to the infernal shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10531, line : "Drag off the car where Rhesus' armour lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10532, line : "Or heave with manly force, and lift away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10533, line : "While unresolved the son of Tydeus stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10534, line : "Pallas appears, and thus her chief commands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10536, line : "\"Enough, my son; from further slaughter cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10537, line : "Regard thy safety, and depart in peace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10538, line : "Haste to the ships, the gotten spoils enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10539, line : "Nor tempt too far the hostile gods of Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10541, line : "The voice divine confess'd the martial maid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10542, line : "In haste he mounted, and her word obey'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10543, line : "The coursers fly before Ulysses' bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10544, line : "Swift as the wind, and white as winter-snow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10546, line : "Not unobserved they pass'd: the god of light"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10547, line : "Had watch'd his Troy, and mark'd Minerva's flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10548, line : "Saw Tydeus' son with heavenly succour bless'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10549, line : "And vengeful anger fill'd his sacred breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10550, line : "Swift to the Trojan camp descends the power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10551, line : "And wakes Hippocoon in the morning-hour;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10552, line : "(On Rhesus' side accustom'd to attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10553, line : "A faithful kinsman, and instructive friend;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10554, line : "He rose, and saw the field deform'd with blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10555, line : "An empty space where late the coursers stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10556, line : "The yet-warm Thracians panting on the coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10557, line : "For each he wept, but for his Rhesus most:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10558, line : "Now while on Rhesus' name he calls in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10559, line : "The gathering tumult spreads o'er all the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10560, line : "On heaps the Trojans rush, with wild affright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10561, line : "And wondering view the slaughters of the night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10563, line : "Meanwhile the chiefs, arriving at the shade"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10564, line : "Where late the spoils of Hector's spy were laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10565, line : "Ulysses stopp'd; to him Tydides bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10566, line : "The trophy, dropping yet with Dolon's gore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10567, line : "Then mounts again; again their nimbler feet"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10568, line : "The coursers ply, and thunder towards the fleet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10570, line : "[Illustration: DIOMED AND ULYSSES RETURNING WITH THE SPOILS OF RHESUS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10572, line : "DIOMED AND ULYSSES RETURNING WITH THE SPOILS OF RHESUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10575, line : "Old Nestor first perceived the approaching sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10576, line : "Bespeaking thus the Grecian peers around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10577, line : "\"Methinks the noise of trampling steeds I hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10578, line : "Thickening this way, and gathering on my ear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10579, line : "Perhaps some horses of the Trojan breed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10580, line : "(So may, ye gods! my pious hopes succeed)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10581, line : "The great Tydides and Ulysses bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10582, line : "Return'd triumphant with this prize of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10583, line : "Yet much I fear (ah, may that fear be vain!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10584, line : "The chiefs outnumber'd by the Trojan train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10585, line : "Perhaps, even now pursued, they seek the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10586, line : "Or, oh! perhaps those heroes are no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10588, line : "Scarce had he spoke, when, lo! the chiefs appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10589, line : "And spring to earth; the Greeks dismiss their fear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10590, line : "With words of friendship and extended hands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10591, line : "They greet the kings; and Nestor first demands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10593, line : "\"Say thou, whose praises all our host proclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10594, line : "Thou living glory of the Grecian name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10595, line : "Say whence these coursers? by what chance bestow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10596, line : "The spoil of foes, or present of a god?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10597, line : "Not those fair steeds, so radiant and so gay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10598, line : "That draw the burning chariot of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10599, line : "Old as I am, to age I scorn to yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10600, line : "And daily mingle in the martial field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10601, line : "But sure till now no coursers struck my sight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10602, line : "Like these, conspicuous through the ranks of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10603, line : "Some god, I deem, conferred the glorious prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10604, line : "Bless'd as ye are, and favourites of the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10605, line : "The care of him who bids the thunder roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10606, line : "And her, whose fury bathes the world with gore.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10608, line : "\"Father! not so, (sage Ithacus rejoin'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10609, line : "The gifts of heaven are of a nobler kind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10610, line : "Of Thracian lineage are the steeds ye view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10611, line : "Whose hostile king the brave Tydides slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10612, line : "Sleeping he died, with all his guards around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10613, line : "And twelve beside lay gasping on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10614, line : "These other spoils from conquer'd Dolon came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10615, line : "A wretch, whose swiftness was his only fame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10616, line : "By Hector sent our forces to explore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10617, line : "He now lies headless on the sandy shore.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10619, line : "Then o'er the trench the bounding coursers flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10620, line : "The joyful Greeks with loud acclaim pursue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10621, line : "Straight to Tydides' high pavilion borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10622, line : "The matchless steeds his ample stalls adorn:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10623, line : "The neighing coursers their new fellows greet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10624, line : "And the full racks are heap'd with generous wheat."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10625, line : "But Dolon's armour, to his ships convey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10626, line : "High on the painted stern Ulysses laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10627, line : "A trophy destin'd to the blue-eyed maid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10629, line : "Now from nocturnal sweat and sanguine stain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10630, line : "They cleanse their bodies in the neighb'ring main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10631, line : "Then in the polished bath, refresh'd from toil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10632, line : "Their joints they supple with dissolving oil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10633, line : "In due repast indulge the genial hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10634, line : "And first to Pallas the libations pour:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10635, line : "They sit, rejoicing in her aid divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10636, line : "And the crown'd goblet foams with floods of wine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10642, line : "BOOK XI."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10645, line : "ARGUMENT"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10647, line : "THE THIRD BATTLE, AND THE ACTS OF AGAMEMNON."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10649, line : "Agamemnon, having armed himself, leads the Grecians to battle; Hector"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10650, line : "prepares the Trojans to receive them, while Jupiter, Juno, and Minerva"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10651, line : "give the signals of war. Agamemnon bears all before him and Hector is"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10652, line : "commanded by Jupiter (who sends Iris for that purpose) to decline the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10653, line : "engagement, till the king shall be wounded and retire from the field. He"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10654, line : "then makes a great slaughter of the enemy. Ulysses and Diomed put a stop"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10655, line : "to him for a time but the latter, being wounded by Paris, is obliged to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10656, line : "desert his companion, who is encompassed by the Trojans, wounded, and in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10657, line : "the utmost danger, till Menelaus and Ajax rescue him. Hector comes against"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10658, line : "Ajax, but that hero alone opposes multitudes, and rallies the Greeks. In"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10659, line : "the meantime Machaon, in the other wing of the army, is pierced with an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10660, line : "arrow by Paris, and carried from the fight in Nestor's chariot. Achilles"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10661, line : "(who overlooked the action from his ship) sent Patroclus to inquire which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10662, line : "of the Greeks was wounded in that manner; Nestor entertains him in his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10663, line : "tent with an account of the accidents of the day, and a long recital of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10664, line : "some former wars which he remembered, tending to put Patroclus upon"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10665, line : "persuading Achilles to fight for his countrymen, or at least to permit him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10666, line : "to do it, clad in Achilles' armour. Patroclus, on his return, meets"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10667, line : "Eurypylus also wounded, and assists him in that distress."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10669, line : "This book opens with the eight and-twentieth day of the poem, and the same"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10670, line : "day, with its various actions and adventures is extended through the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10671, line : "twelfth, thirteenth, fourteenth, fifteenth, sixteenth, seventeenth, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10672, line : "part of the eighteenth books. The scene lies in the field near the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10673, line : "monument of Ilus."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10675, line : "The saffron morn, with early blushes spread,(219)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10676, line : "Now rose refulgent from Tithonus' bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10677, line : "With new-born day to gladden mortal sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10678, line : "And gild the courts of heaven with sacred light:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10679, line : "When baleful Eris, sent by Jove's command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10680, line : "The torch of discord blazing in her hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10681, line : "Through the red skies her bloody sign extends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10682, line : "And, wrapt in tempests, o'er the fleet descends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10683, line : "High on Ulysses' bark her horrid stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10684, line : "She took, and thunder'd through the seas and land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10686, line : "Even Ajax and Achilles heard the sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10687, line : "Whose ships, remote, the guarded navy bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10688, line : "Thence the black fury through the Grecian throng"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10689, line : "With horror sounds the loud Orthian song:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10690, line : "The navy shakes, and at the dire alarms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10691, line : "Each bosom boils, each warrior starts to arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10692, line : "No more they sigh, inglorious to return,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10693, line : "But breathe revenge, and for the combat burn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10695, line : "[Illustration: THE DESCENT OF DISCORD.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10697, line : "THE DESCENT OF DISCORD."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10700, line : "The king of men his hardy host inspires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10701, line : "With loud command, with great example fires!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10702, line : "Himself first rose, himself before the rest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10703, line : "His mighty limbs in radiant armour dress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10704, line : "And first he cased his manly legs around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10705, line : "In shining greaves with silver buckles bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10706, line : "The beaming cuirass next adorn'd his breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10707, line : "The same which once king Cinyras possess'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10708, line : "(The fame of Greece and her assembled host"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10709, line : "Had reach'd that monarch on the Cyprian coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10710, line : "'Twas then, the friendship of the chief to gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10711, line : "This glorious gift he sent, nor sent in vain:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10712, line : "Ten rows of azure steel the work infold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10713, line : "Twice ten of tin, and twelve of ductile gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10714, line : "Three glittering dragons to the gorget rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10715, line : "Whose imitated scales against the skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10716, line : "Reflected various light, and arching bow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10717, line : "Like colour'd rainbows o'er a showery cloud"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10718, line : "(Jove's wondrous bow, of three celestial dies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10719, line : "Placed as a sign to man amidst the skies)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10720, line : "A radiant baldric, o'er his shoulder tied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10721, line : "Sustain'd the sword that glitter'd at his side:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10722, line : "Gold was the hilt, a silver sheath encased"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10723, line : "The shining blade, and golden hangers graced."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10724, line : "His buckler's mighty orb was next display'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10725, line : "That round the warrior cast a dreadful shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10726, line : "Ten zones of brass its ample brim surround,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10727, line : "And twice ten bosses the bright convex crown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10728, line : "Tremendous Gorgon frown'd upon its field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10729, line : "And circling terrors fill'd the expressive shield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10730, line : "Within its concave hung a silver thong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10731, line : "On which a mimic serpent creeps along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10732, line : "His azure length in easy waves extends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10733, line : "Till in three heads the embroider'd monster ends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10734, line : "Last o'er his brows his fourfold helm he placed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10735, line : "With nodding horse-hair formidably graced;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10736, line : "And in his hands two steely javelins wields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10737, line : "That blaze to heaven, and lighten all the fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10739, line : "That instant Juno, and the martial maid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10740, line : "In happy thunders promised Greece their aid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10741, line : "High o'er the chief they clash'd their arms in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10742, line : "And, leaning from the clouds, expect the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10744, line : "Close to the limits of the trench and mound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10745, line : "The fiery coursers to their chariots bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10746, line : "The squires restrain'd: the foot, with those who wield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10747, line : "The lighter arms, rush forward to the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10748, line : "To second these, in close array combined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10749, line : "The squadrons spread their sable wings behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10750, line : "Now shouts and tumults wake the tardy sun,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10751, line : "As with the light the warriors' toils begun."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10752, line : "Even Jove, whose thunder spoke his wrath, distill'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10753, line : "Red drops of blood o'er all the fatal field;(220)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10754, line : "The woes of men unwilling to survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10755, line : "And all the slaughters that must stain the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10757, line : "Near Ilus' tomb, in order ranged around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10758, line : "The Trojan lines possess'd the rising ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10759, line : "There wise Polydamas and Hector stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10760, line : "Ćneas, honour'd as a guardian god;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10761, line : "Bold Polybus, Agenor the divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10762, line : "The brother-warriors of Antenor's line:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10763, line : "With youthful Acamas, whose beauteous face"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10764, line : "And fair proportion match'd the ethereal race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10765, line : "Great Hector, cover'd with his spacious shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10766, line : "Plies all the troops, and orders all the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10767, line : "As the red star now shows his sanguine fires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10768, line : "Through the dark clouds, and now in night retires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10769, line : "Thus through the ranks appear'd the godlike man,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10770, line : "Plunged in the rear, or blazing in the van;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10771, line : "While streamy sparkles, restless as he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10772, line : "Flash from his arms, as lightning from the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10773, line : "As sweating reapers in some wealthy field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10774, line : "Ranged in two bands, their crooked weapons wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10775, line : "Bear down the furrows, till their labours meet;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10776, line : "Thick fall the heapy harvests at their feet:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10777, line : "So Greece and Troy the field of war divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10778, line : "And falling ranks are strow'd on every side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10779, line : "None stoop'd a thought to base inglorious flight;(221)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10780, line : "But horse to horse, and man to man they fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10781, line : "Not rabid wolves more fierce contest their prey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10782, line : "Each wounds, each bleeds, but none resign the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10783, line : "Discord with joy the scene of death descries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10784, line : "And drinks large slaughter at her sanguine eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10785, line : "Discord alone, of all the immortal train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10786, line : "Swells the red horrors of this direful plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10787, line : "The gods in peace their golden mansions fill,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10788, line : "Ranged in bright order on the Olympian hill:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10789, line : "But general murmurs told their griefs above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10790, line : "And each accused the partial will of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10791, line : "Meanwhile apart, superior, and alone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10792, line : "The eternal Monarch, on his awful throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10793, line : "Wrapt in the blaze of boundless glory sate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10794, line : "And fix'd, fulfill'd the just decrees of fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10795, line : "On earth he turn'd his all-considering eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10796, line : "And mark'd the spot where Ilion's towers arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10797, line : "The sea with ships, the fields with armies spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10798, line : "The victor's rage, the dying, and the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10800, line : "Thus while the morning-beams, increasing bright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10801, line : "O'er heaven's pure azure spread the glowing light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10802, line : "Commutual death the fate of war confounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10803, line : "Each adverse battle gored with equal wounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10804, line : "But now (what time in some sequester'd vale"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10805, line : "The weary woodman spreads his sparing meal,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10806, line : "When his tired arms refuse the axe to rear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10807, line : "And claim a respite from the sylvan war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10808, line : "But not till half the prostrate forests lay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10809, line : "Stretch'd in long ruin, and exposed to day)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10810, line : "Then, nor till then, the Greeks' impulsive might"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10811, line : "Pierced the black phalanx, and let in the light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10812, line : "Great Agamemnon then the slaughter led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10813, line : "And slew Bienor at his people's head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10814, line : "Whose squire Oileus, with a sudden spring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10815, line : "Leap'd from the chariot to revenge his king;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10816, line : "But in his front he felt the fatal wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10817, line : "Which pierced his brain, and stretch'd him on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10818, line : "Atrides spoil'd, and left them on the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10819, line : "Vain was their youth, their glittering armour vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10820, line : "Now soil'd with dust, and naked to the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10821, line : "Their snowy limbs and beauteous bodies lie."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10823, line : "Two sons of Priam next to battle move,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10824, line : "The product, one of marriage, one of love:(222)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10825, line : "In the same car the brother-warriors ride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10826, line : "This took the charge to combat, that to guide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10827, line : "Far other task, than when they wont to keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10828, line : "On Ida's tops, their father's fleecy sheep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10829, line : "These on the mountains once Achilles found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10830, line : "And captive led, with pliant osiers bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10831, line : "Then to their sire for ample sums restored;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10832, line : "But now to perish by Atrides' sword:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10833, line : "Pierced in the breast the base-born Isus bleeds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10834, line : "Cleft through the head his brother's fate succeeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10835, line : "Swift to the spoil the hasty victor falls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10836, line : "And, stript, their features to his mind recalls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10837, line : "The Trojans see the youths untimely die,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10838, line : "But helpless tremble for themselves, and fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10839, line : "So when a lion ranging o'er the lawns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10840, line : "Finds, on some grassy lair, the couching fawns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10841, line : "Their bones he cracks, their reeking vitals draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10842, line : "And grinds the quivering flesh with bloody jaws;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10843, line : "The frighted hind beholds, and dares not stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10844, line : "But swift through rustling thickets bursts her way;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10845, line : "All drown'd in sweat, the panting mother flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10846, line : "And the big tears roll trickling from her eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10848, line : "Amidst the tumult of the routed train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10849, line : "The sons of false Antimachus were slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10850, line : "He who for bribes his faithless counsels sold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10851, line : "And voted Helen's stay for Paris' gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10852, line : "Atrides mark'd, as these their safety sought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10853, line : "And slew the children for the father's fault;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10854, line : "Their headstrong horse unable to restrain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10855, line : "They shook with fear, and dropp'd the silken rein;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10856, line : "Then in the chariot on their knees they fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10857, line : "And thus with lifted hands for mercy call:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10859, line : "\"O spare our youth, and for the life we owe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10860, line : "Antimachus shall copious gifts bestow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10861, line : "Soon as he hears, that, not in battle slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10862, line : "The Grecian ships his captive sons detain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10863, line : "Large heaps of brass in ransom shall be told,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10864, line : "And steel well-tempered, and persuasive gold.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10866, line : "These words, attended with the flood of tears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10867, line : "The youths address'd to unrelenting ears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10868, line : "The vengeful monarch gave this stern reply:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10869, line : "\"If from Antimachus ye spring, ye die;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10870, line : "The daring wretch who once in council stood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10871, line : "To shed Ulysses' and my brother's blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10872, line : "For proffer'd peace! and sues his seed for grace?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10873, line : "No, die, and pay the forfeit of your race.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10875, line : "This said, Pisander from the car he cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10876, line : "And pierced his breast: supine he breathed his last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10877, line : "His brother leap'd to earth; but, as he lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10878, line : "The trenchant falchion lopp'd his hands away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10879, line : "His sever'd head was toss'd among the throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10880, line : "And, rolling, drew a bloody train along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10881, line : "Then, where the thickest fought, the victor flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10882, line : "The king's example all his Greeks pursue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10883, line : "Now by the foot the flying foot were slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10884, line : "Horse trod by horse, lay foaming on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10885, line : "From the dry fields thick clouds of dust arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10886, line : "Shade the black host, and intercept the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10887, line : "The brass-hoof'd steeds tumultuous plunge and bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10888, line : "And the thick thunder beats the labouring ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10889, line : "Still slaughtering on, the king of men proceeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10890, line : "The distanced army wonders at his deeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10891, line : "As when the winds with raging flames conspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10892, line : "And o'er the forests roll the flood of fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10893, line : "In blazing heaps the grove's old honours fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10894, line : "And one refulgent ruin levels all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10895, line : "Before Atrides' rage so sinks the foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10896, line : "Whole squadrons vanish, and proud heads lie low."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10897, line : "The steeds fly trembling from his waving sword,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10898, line : "And many a car, now lighted of its lord,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10899, line : "Wide o'er the field with guideless fury rolls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10900, line : "Breaking their ranks, and crushing out their souls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10901, line : "While his keen falchion drinks the warriors' lives;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10902, line : "More grateful, now, to vultures than their wives!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10904, line : "Perhaps great Hector then had found his fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10905, line : "But Jove and destiny prolong'd his date."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10906, line : "Safe from the darts, the care of heaven he stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10907, line : "Amidst alarms, and death, and dust, and blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10909, line : "Now past the tomb where ancient Ilus lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10910, line : "Through the mid field the routed urge their way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10911, line : "Where the wild figs the adjoining summit crown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10912, line : "The path they take, and speed to reach the town."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10913, line : "As swift, Atrides with loud shouts pursued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10914, line : "Hot with his toil, and bathed in hostile blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10915, line : "Now near the beech-tree, and the Scaean gates,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10916, line : "The hero halts, and his associates waits."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10917, line : "Meanwhile on every side around the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10918, line : "Dispersed, disorder'd, fly the Trojan train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10919, line : "So flies a herd of beeves, that hear dismay'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10920, line : "The lion's roaring through the midnight shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10921, line : "On heaps they tumble with successless haste;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10922, line : "The savage seizes, draws, and rends the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10923, line : "Not with less fury stern Atrides flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10924, line : "Still press'd the rout, and still the hindmost slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10925, line : "Hurl'd from their cars the bravest chiefs are kill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10926, line : "And rage, and death, and carnage load the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10928, line : "Now storms the victor at the Trojan wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10929, line : "Surveys the towers, and meditates their fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10930, line : "But Jove descending shook the Idaean hills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10931, line : "And down their summits pour'd a hundred rills:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10932, line : "The unkindled lightning in his hand he took,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10933, line : "And thus the many-coloured maid bespoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10935, line : "\"Iris, with haste thy golden wings display,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10936, line : "To godlike Hector this our word convey--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10937, line : "While Agamemnon wastes the ranks around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10938, line : "Fights in the front, and bathes with blood the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10939, line : "Bid him give way; but issue forth commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10940, line : "And trust the war to less important hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10941, line : "But when, or wounded by the spear or dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10942, line : "That chief shall mount his chariot, and depart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10943, line : "Then Jove shall string his arm, and fire his breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10944, line : "Then to her ships shall flying Greece be press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10945, line : "Till to the main the burning sun descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10946, line : "And sacred night her awful shade extend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10948, line : "He spoke, and Iris at his word obey'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10949, line : "On wings of winds descends the various maid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10950, line : "The chief she found amidst the ranks of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10951, line : "Close to the bulwarks, on his glittering car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10952, line : "The goddess then: \"O son of Priam, hear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10953, line : "From Jove I come, and his high mandate bear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10954, line : "While Agamemnon wastes the ranks around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10955, line : "Fights in the front, and bathes with blood the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10956, line : "Abstain from fight; yet issue forth commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10957, line : "And trust the war to less important hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10958, line : "But when, or wounded by the spear or dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10959, line : "The chief shall mount his chariot, and depart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10960, line : "Then Jove shall string thy arm, and fire thy breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10961, line : "Then to her ships shall flying Greece be press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10962, line : "Till to the main the burning sun descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10963, line : "And sacred night her awful shade extend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10965, line : "She said, and vanish'd. Hector, with a bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10966, line : "Springs from his chariot on the trembling ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10967, line : "In clanging arms: he grasps in either hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10968, line : "A pointed lance, and speeds from band to band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10969, line : "Revives their ardour, turns their steps from flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10970, line : "And wakes anew the dying flames of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10971, line : "They stand to arms: the Greeks their onset dare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10972, line : "Condense their powers, and wait the coming war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10973, line : "New force, new spirit, to each breast returns;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10974, line : "The fight renew'd with fiercer fury burns:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10975, line : "The king leads on: all fix on him their eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10976, line : "And learn from him to conquer, or to die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10978, line : "Ye sacred nine! celestial Muses! tell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10979, line : "Who faced him first, and by his prowess fell?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10980, line : "The great Iphidamas, the bold and young,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10981, line : "From sage Antenor and Theano sprung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10982, line : "Whom from his youth his grandsire Cisseus bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10983, line : "And nursed in Thrace where snowy flocks are fed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10984, line : "Scarce did the down his rosy cheeks invest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10985, line : "And early honour warm his generous breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10986, line : "When the kind sire consign'd his daughter's charms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10987, line : "(Theano's sister) to his youthful arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10988, line : "But call'd by glory to the wars of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10989, line : "He leaves untasted the first fruits of joy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10990, line : "From his loved bride departs with melting eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10991, line : "And swift to aid his dearer country flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10992, line : "With twelve black ships he reach'd Percope's strand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10993, line : "Thence took the long laborious march by land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10994, line : "Now fierce for fame, before the ranks he springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10995, line : "Towering in arms, and braves the king of kings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10996, line : "Atrides first discharged the missive spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10997, line : "The Trojan stoop'd, the javelin pass'd in air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10998, line : "Then near the corslet, at the monarch's heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 10999, line : "With all his strength, the youth directs his dart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11000, line : "But the broad belt, with plates of silver bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11001, line : "The point rebated, and repell'd the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11002, line : "Encumber'd with the dart, Atrides stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11003, line : "Till, grasp'd with force, he wrench'd it from his hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11004, line : "At once his weighty sword discharged a wound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11005, line : "Full on his neck, that fell'd him to the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11006, line : "Stretch'd in the dust the unhappy warrior lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11007, line : "And sleep eternal seals his swimming eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11008, line : "Oh worthy better fate! oh early slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11009, line : "Thy country's friend; and virtuous, though in vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11010, line : "No more the youth shall join his consort's side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11011, line : "At once a virgin, and at once a bride!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11012, line : "No more with presents her embraces meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11013, line : "Or lay the spoils of conquest at her feet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11014, line : "On whom his passion, lavish of his store,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11015, line : "Bestow'd so much, and vainly promised more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11016, line : "Unwept, uncover'd, on the plain he lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11017, line : "While the proud victor bore his arms away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11019, line : "Coon, Antenor's eldest hope, was nigh:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11020, line : "Tears, at the sight, came starting from his eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11021, line : "While pierced with grief the much-loved youth he view'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11022, line : "And the pale features now deform'd with blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11023, line : "Then, with his spear, unseen, his time he took,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11024, line : "Aim'd at the king, and near his elbow strook."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11025, line : "The thrilling steel transpierced the brawny part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11026, line : "And through his arm stood forth the barbed dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11027, line : "Surprised the monarch feels, yet void of fear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11028, line : "On Coon rushes with his lifted spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11029, line : "His brother's corpse the pious Trojan draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11030, line : "And calls his country to assert his cause;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11031, line : "Defends him breathless on the sanguine field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11032, line : "And o'er the body spreads his ample shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11033, line : "Atrides, marking an unguarded part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11034, line : "Transfix'd the warrior with his brazen dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11035, line : "Prone on his brother's bleeding breast he lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11036, line : "The monarch's falchion lopp'd his head away:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11037, line : "The social shades the same dark journey go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11038, line : "And join each other in the realms below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11040, line : "The vengeful victor rages round the fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11041, line : "With every weapon art or fury yields:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11042, line : "By the long lance, the sword, or ponderous stone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11043, line : "Whole ranks are broken, and whole troops o'erthrown."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11044, line : "This, while yet warm distill'd the purple flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11045, line : "But when the wound grew stiff with clotted blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11046, line : "Then grinding tortures his strong bosom rend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11047, line : "Less keen those darts the fierce Ilythiae send:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11048, line : "(The powers that cause the teeming matron's throes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11049, line : "Sad mothers of unutterable woes!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11050, line : "Stung with the smart, all-panting with the pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11051, line : "He mounts the car, and gives his squire the rein;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11052, line : "Then with a voice which fury made more strong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11053, line : "And pain augmented, thus exhorts the throng:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11055, line : "\"O friends! O Greeks! assert your honours won;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11056, line : "Proceed, and finish what this arm begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11057, line : "Lo! angry Jove forbids your chief to stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11058, line : "And envies half the glories of the day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11060, line : "He said: the driver whirls his lengthful thong;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11061, line : "The horses fly; the chariot smokes along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11062, line : "Clouds from their nostrils the fierce coursers blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11063, line : "And from their sides the foam descends in snow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11064, line : "Shot through the battle in a moment's space,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11065, line : "The wounded monarch at his tent they place."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11067, line : "No sooner Hector saw the king retired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11068, line : "But thus his Trojans and his aids he fired:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11069, line : "\"Hear, all ye Dardan, all ye Lycian race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11070, line : "Famed in close fight, and dreadful face to face:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11071, line : "Now call to mind your ancient trophies won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11072, line : "Your great forefathers' virtues, and your own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11073, line : "Behold, the general flies! deserts his powers!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11074, line : "Lo, Jove himself declares the conquest ours!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11075, line : "Now on yon ranks impel your foaming steeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11076, line : "And, sure of glory, dare immortal deeds.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11078, line : "With words like these the fiery chief alarms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11079, line : "His fainting host, and every bosom warms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11080, line : "As the bold hunter cheers his hounds to tear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11081, line : "The brindled lion, or the tusky bear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11082, line : "With voice and hand provokes their doubting heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11083, line : "And springs the foremost with his lifted dart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11084, line : "So godlike Hector prompts his troops to dare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11085, line : "Nor prompts alone, but leads himself the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11086, line : "On the black body of the foe he pours;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11087, line : "As from the cloud's deep bosom, swell'd with showers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11088, line : "A sudden storm the purple ocean sweeps,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11089, line : "Drives the wild waves, and tosses all the deeps."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11090, line : "Say, Muse! when Jove the Trojan's glory crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11091, line : "Beneath his arm what heroes bit the ground?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11092, line : "Assaeus, Dolops, and Autonous died,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11093, line : "Opites next was added to their side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11094, line : "Then brave Hipponous, famed in many a fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11095, line : "Opheltius, Orus, sunk to endless night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11096, line : "Ćsymnus, Agelaus; all chiefs of name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11097, line : "The rest were vulgar deaths unknown to fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11098, line : "As when a western whirlwind, charged with storms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11099, line : "Dispels the gather'd clouds that Notus forms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11100, line : "The gust continued, violent and strong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11101, line : "Rolls sable clouds in heaps on heaps along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11102, line : "Now to the skies the foaming billows rears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11103, line : "Now breaks the surge, and wide the bottom bares:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11104, line : "Thus, raging Hector, with resistless hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11105, line : "O'erturns, confounds, and scatters all their bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11106, line : "Now the last ruin the whole host appals;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11107, line : "Now Greece had trembled in her wooden walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11108, line : "But wise Ulysses call'd Tydides forth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11109, line : "His soul rekindled, and awaked his worth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11110, line : "\"And stand we deedless, O eternal shame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11111, line : "Till Hector's arm involve the ships in flame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11112, line : "Haste, let us join, and combat side by side.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11113, line : "The warrior thus, and thus the friend replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11115, line : "\"No martial toil I shun, no danger fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11116, line : "Let Hector come; I wait his fury here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11117, line : "But Jove with conquest crowns the Trojan train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11118, line : "And, Jove our foe, all human force is vain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11120, line : "He sigh'd; but, sighing, raised his vengeful steel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11121, line : "And from his car the proud Thymbraeus fell:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11122, line : "Molion, the charioteer, pursued his lord,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11123, line : "His death ennobled by Ulysses' sword."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11124, line : "There slain, they left them in eternal night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11125, line : "Then plunged amidst the thickest ranks of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11126, line : "So two wild boars outstrip the following hounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11127, line : "Then swift revert, and wounds return for wounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11128, line : "Stern Hector's conquests in the middle plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11129, line : "Stood check'd awhile, and Greece respired again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11131, line : "The sons of Merops shone amidst the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11132, line : "Towering they rode in one refulgent car:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11133, line : "In deep prophetic arts their father skill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11134, line : "Had warn'd his children from the Trojan field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11135, line : "Fate urged them on: the father warn'd in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11136, line : "They rush'd to fight, and perish'd on the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11137, line : "Their breasts no more the vital spirit warms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11138, line : "The stern Tydides strips their shining arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11139, line : "Hypirochus by great Ulysses dies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11140, line : "And rich Hippodamus becomes his prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11141, line : "Great Jove from Ide with slaughter fills his sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11142, line : "And level hangs the doubtful scale of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11143, line : "By Tydeus' lance Agastrophus was slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11144, line : "The far-famed hero of Paeonian strain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11145, line : "Wing'd with his fears, on foot he strove to fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11146, line : "His steeds too distant, and the foe too nigh:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11147, line : "Through broken orders, swifter than the wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11148, line : "He fled, but flying left his life behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11149, line : "This Hector sees, as his experienced eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11150, line : "Traverse the files, and to the rescue flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11151, line : "Shouts, as he pass'd, the crystal regions rend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11152, line : "And moving armies on his march attend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11153, line : "Great Diomed himself was seized with fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11154, line : "And thus bespoke his brother of the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11156, line : "\"Mark how this way yon bending squadrons yield!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11157, line : "The storm rolls on, and Hector rules the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11158, line : "Here stand his utmost force.\"--The warrior said;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11159, line : "Swift at the word his ponderous javelin fled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11160, line : "Nor miss'd its aim, but where the plumage danced"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11161, line : "Razed the smooth cone, and thence obliquely glanced."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11162, line : "Safe in his helm (the gift of Phoebus' hands)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11163, line : "Without a wound the Trojan hero stands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11164, line : "But yet so stunn'd, that, staggering on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11165, line : "His arm and knee his sinking bulk sustain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11166, line : "O'er his dim sight the misty vapours rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11167, line : "And a short darkness shades his swimming eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11168, line : "Tydides followed to regain his lance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11169, line : "While Hector rose, recover'd from the trance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11170, line : "Remounts his car, and herds amidst the crowd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11171, line : "The Greek pursues him, and exults aloud:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11172, line : "\"Once more thank Phoebus for thy forfeit breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11173, line : "Or thank that swiftness which outstrips the death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11174, line : "Well by Apollo are thy prayers repaid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11175, line : "And oft that partial power has lent his aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11176, line : "Thou shall not long the death deserved withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11177, line : "If any god assist Tydides' hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11178, line : "Fly then, inglorious! but thy flight, this day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11179, line : "Whole hecatombs of Trojan ghosts shall pay,\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11181, line : "Him, while he triumph'd, Paris eyed from far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11182, line : "(The spouse of Helen, the fair cause of war;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11183, line : "Around the fields his feather'd shafts he sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11184, line : "From ancient Ilus' ruin'd monument:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11185, line : "Behind the column placed, he bent his bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11186, line : "And wing'd an arrow at the unwary foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11187, line : "Just as he stoop'd, Agastrophus's crest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11188, line : "To seize, and drew the corslet from his breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11189, line : "The bowstring twang'd; nor flew the shaft in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11190, line : "But pierced his foot, and nail'd it to the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11191, line : "The laughing Trojan, with a joyful spring."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11192, line : "Leaps from his ambush, and insults the king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11194, line : "\"He bleeds! (he cries) some god has sped my dart!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11195, line : "Would the same god had fix'd it in his heart!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11196, line : "So Troy, relieved from that wide-wasting hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11197, line : "Should breathe from slaughter and in combat stand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11198, line : "Whose sons now tremble at his darted spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11199, line : "As scatter'd lambs the rushing lion fear.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11201, line : "He dauntless thus: \"Thou conqueror of the fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11202, line : "Thou woman-warrior with the curling hair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11203, line : "Vain archer! trusting to the distant dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11204, line : "Unskill'd in arms to act a manly part!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11205, line : "Thou hast but done what boys or women can;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11206, line : "Such hands may wound, but not incense a man."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11207, line : "Nor boast the scratch thy feeble arrow gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11208, line : "A coward's weapon never hurts the brave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11209, line : "Not so this dart, which thou may'st one day feel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11210, line : "Fate wings its flight, and death is on the steel:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11211, line : "Where this but lights, some noble life expires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11212, line : "Its touch makes orphans, bathes the cheeks of sires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11213, line : "Steeps earth in purple, gluts the birds of air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11214, line : "And leaves such objects as distract the fair.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11215, line : "Ulysses hastens with a trembling heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11216, line : "Before him steps, and bending draws the dart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11217, line : "Forth flows the blood; an eager pang succeeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11218, line : "Tydides mounts, and to the navy speeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11220, line : "Now on the field Ulysses stands alone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11221, line : "The Greeks all fled, the Trojans pouring on;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11222, line : "But stands collected in himself, and whole,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11223, line : "And questions thus his own unconquer'd soul:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11225, line : "\"What further subterfuge, what hopes remain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11226, line : "What shame, inglorious if I quit the plain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11227, line : "What danger, singly if I stand the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11228, line : "My friends all scatter'd, all the foes around?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11229, line : "Yet wherefore doubtful? let this truth suffice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11230, line : "The brave meets danger, and the coward flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11231, line : "To die or conquer, proves a hero's heart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11232, line : "And, knowing this, I know a soldier's part.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11234, line : "Such thoughts revolving in his careful breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11235, line : "Near, and more near, the shady cohorts press'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11236, line : "These, in the warrior, their own fate enclose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11237, line : "And round him deep the steely circle grows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11238, line : "So fares a boar whom all the troop surrounds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11239, line : "Of shouting huntsmen and of clamorous hounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11240, line : "He grinds his ivory tusks; he foams with ire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11241, line : "His sanguine eye-balls glare with living fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11242, line : "By these, by those, on every part is plied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11243, line : "And the red slaughter spreads on every side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11244, line : "Pierced through the shoulder, first Deiopis fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11245, line : "Next Ennomus and Thoon sank to hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11246, line : "Chersidamas, beneath the navel thrust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11247, line : "Falls prone to earth, and grasps the bloody dust."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11248, line : "Charops, the son of Hippasus, was near;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11249, line : "Ulysses reach'd him with the fatal spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11250, line : "But to his aid his brother Socus flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11251, line : "Socus the brave, the generous, and the wise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11252, line : "Near as he drew, the warrior thus began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11254, line : "\"O great Ulysses! much-enduring man!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11255, line : "Not deeper skill'd in every martial sleight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11256, line : "Than worn to toils, and active in the fight!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11257, line : "This day two brothers shall thy conquest grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11258, line : "And end at once the great Hippasian race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11259, line : "Or thou beneath this lance must press the field.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11260, line : "He said, and forceful pierced his spacious shield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11261, line : "Through the strong brass the ringing javelin thrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11262, line : "Plough'd half his side, and bared it to the bone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11263, line : "By Pallas' care, the spear, though deep infix'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11264, line : "Stopp'd short of life, nor with his entrails mix'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11266, line : "The wound not mortal wise Ulysses knew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11267, line : "Then furious thus (but first some steps withdrew):"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11268, line : "\"Unhappy man! whose death our hands shall grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11269, line : "Fate calls thee hence and finish'd is thy race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11270, line : "Nor longer check my conquests on the foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11271, line : "But, pierced by this, to endless darkness go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11272, line : "And add one spectre to the realms below!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11274, line : "He spoke, while Socus, seized with sudden fright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11275, line : "Trembling gave way, and turn'd his back to flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11276, line : "Between his shoulders pierced the following dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11277, line : "And held its passage through the panting heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11278, line : "Wide in his breast appear'd the grisly wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11279, line : "He falls; his armour rings against the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11280, line : "Then thus Ulysses, gazing on the slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11281, line : "\"Famed son of Hippasus! there press the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11282, line : "There ends thy narrow span assign'd by fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11283, line : "Heaven owes Ulysses yet a longer date."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11284, line : "Ah, wretch! no father shall thy corpse compose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11285, line : "Thy dying eyes no tender mother close;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11286, line : "But hungry birds shall tear those balls away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11287, line : "And hovering vultures scream around their prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11288, line : "Me Greece shall honour, when I meet my doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11289, line : "With solemn funerals and a lasting tomb.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11291, line : "Then raging with intolerable smart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11292, line : "He writhes his body, and extracts the dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11293, line : "The dart a tide of spouting gore pursued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11294, line : "And gladden'd Troy with sight of hostile blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11295, line : "Now troops on troops the fainting chief invade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11296, line : "Forced he recedes, and loudly calls for aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11297, line : "Thrice to its pitch his lofty voice he rears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11298, line : "The well-known voice thrice Menelaus hears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11299, line : "Alarm'd, to Ajax Telamon he cried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11300, line : "Who shares his labours, and defends his side:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11301, line : "\"O friend! Ulysses' shouts invade my ear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11302, line : "Distressed he seems, and no assistance near;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11303, line : "Strong as he is, yet one opposed to all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11304, line : "Oppress'd by multitudes, the best may fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11305, line : "Greece robb'd of him must bid her host despair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11306, line : "And feel a loss not ages can repair.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11308, line : "Then, where the cry directs, his course he bends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11309, line : "Great Ajax, like the god of war, attends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11310, line : "The prudent chief in sore distress they found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11311, line : "With bands of furious Trojans compass'd round.(223)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11312, line : "As when some huntsman, with a flying spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11313, line : "From the blind thicket wounds a stately deer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11314, line : "Down his cleft side, while fresh the blood distils,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11315, line : "He bounds aloft, and scuds from hills to hills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11316, line : "Till life's warm vapour issuing through the wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11317, line : "Wild mountain-wolves the fainting beast surround:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11318, line : "Just as their jaws his prostrate limbs invade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11319, line : "The lion rushes through the woodland shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11320, line : "The wolves, though hungry, scour dispersed away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11321, line : "The lordly savage vindicates his prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11322, line : "Ulysses thus, unconquer'd by his pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11323, line : "A single warrior half a host sustains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11324, line : "But soon as Ajax leaves his tower-like shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11325, line : "The scattered crowds fly frighted o'er the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11326, line : "Atrides' arm the sinking hero stays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11327, line : "And, saved from numbers, to his car conveys."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11329, line : "Victorious Ajax plies the routed crew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11330, line : "And first Doryclus, Priam's son, he slew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11331, line : "On strong Pandocus next inflicts a wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11332, line : "And lays Lysander bleeding on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11333, line : "As when a torrent, swell'd with wintry rains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11334, line : "Pours from the mountains o'er the deluged plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11335, line : "And pines and oaks, from their foundations torn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11336, line : "A country's ruins! to the seas are borne:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11337, line : "Fierce Ajax thus o'erwhelms the yielding throng;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11338, line : "Men, steeds, and chariots, roll in heaps along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11340, line : "But Hector, from this scene of slaughter far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11341, line : "Raged on the left, and ruled the tide of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11342, line : "Loud groans proclaim his progress through the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11343, line : "And deep Scamander swells with heaps of slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11344, line : "There Nestor and Idomeneus oppose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11345, line : "The warrior's fury; there the battle glows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11346, line : "There fierce on foot, or from the chariot's height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11347, line : "His sword deforms the beauteous ranks of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11348, line : "The spouse of Helen, dealing darts around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11349, line : "Had pierced Machaon with a distant wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11350, line : "In his right shoulder the broad shaft appear'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11351, line : "And trembling Greece for her physician fear'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11352, line : "To Nestor then Idomeneus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11353, line : "\"Glory of Greece, old Neleus' valiant son!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11354, line : "Ascend thy chariot, haste with speed away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11355, line : "And great Machaon to the ships convey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11356, line : "A wise physician skill'd our wounds to heal,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11357, line : "Is more than armies to the public weal.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11358, line : "Old Nestor mounts the seat; beside him rode"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11359, line : "The wounded offspring of the healing god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11360, line : "He lends the lash; the steeds with sounding feet"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11361, line : "Shake the dry field, and thunder toward the fleet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11363, line : "But now Cebriones, from Hector's car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11364, line : "Survey'd the various fortune of the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11365, line : "\"While here (he cried) the flying Greeks are slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11366, line : "Trojans on Trojans yonder load the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11367, line : "Before great Ajax see the mingled throng"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11368, line : "Of men and chariots driven in heaps along!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11369, line : "I know him well, distinguish'd o'er the field"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11370, line : "By the broad glittering of the sevenfold shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11371, line : "Thither, O Hector, thither urge thy steeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11372, line : "There danger calls, and there the combat bleeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11373, line : "There horse and foot in mingled deaths unite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11374, line : "And groans of slaughter mix with shouts of fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11376, line : "Thus having spoke, the driver's lash resounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11377, line : "Swift through the ranks the rapid chariot bounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11378, line : "Stung by the stroke, the coursers scour the fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11379, line : "O'er heaps of carcases, and hills of shields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11380, line : "The horses' hoofs are bathed in heroes' gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11381, line : "And, dashing, purple all the car before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11382, line : "The groaning axle sable drops distils,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11383, line : "And mangled carnage clogs the rapid wheels."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11384, line : "Here Hector, plunging through the thickest fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11385, line : "Broke the dark phalanx, and let in the light:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11386, line : "(By the long lance, the sword, or ponderous stone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11387, line : "The ranks he scatter'd and the troops o'erthrown:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11388, line : "Ajax he shuns, through all the dire debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11389, line : "And fears that arm whose force he felt so late."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11390, line : "But partial Jove, espousing Hector's part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11391, line : "Shot heaven-bred horror through the Grecian's heart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11392, line : "Confused, unnerved in Hector's presence grown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11393, line : "Amazed he stood, with terrors not his own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11394, line : "O'er his broad back his moony shield he threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11395, line : "And, glaring round, by tardy steps withdrew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11396, line : "Thus the grim lion his retreat maintains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11397, line : "Beset with watchful dogs, and shouting swains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11398, line : "Repulsed by numbers from the nightly stalls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11399, line : "Though rage impels him, and though hunger calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11400, line : "Long stands the showering darts, and missile fires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11401, line : "Then sourly slow the indignant beast retires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11402, line : "So turn'd stern Ajax, by whole hosts repell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11403, line : "While his swoln heart at every step rebell'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11405, line : "As the slow beast, with heavy strength endued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11406, line : "In some wide field by troops of boys pursued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11407, line : "Though round his sides a wooden tempest rain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11408, line : "Crops the tall harvest, and lays waste the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11409, line : "Thick on his hide the hollow blows resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11410, line : "The patient animal maintains his ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11411, line : "Scarce from the field with all their efforts chased,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11412, line : "And stirs but slowly when he stirs at last:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11413, line : "On Ajax thus a weight of Trojans hung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11414, line : "The strokes redoubled on his buckler rung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11415, line : "Confiding now in bulky strength he stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11416, line : "Now turns, and backward bears the yielding bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11417, line : "Now stiff recedes, yet hardly seems to fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11418, line : "And threats his followers with retorted eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11419, line : "Fix'd as the bar between two warring powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11420, line : "While hissing darts descend in iron showers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11421, line : "In his broad buckler many a weapon stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11422, line : "Its surface bristled with a quivering wood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11423, line : "And many a javelin, guiltless on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11424, line : "Marks the dry dust, and thirsts for blood in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11425, line : "But bold Eurypylus his aid imparts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11426, line : "And dauntless springs beneath a cloud of darts;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11427, line : "Whose eager javelin launch'd against the foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11428, line : "Great Apisaon felt the fatal blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11429, line : "From his torn liver the red current flow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11430, line : "And his slack knees desert their dying load."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11431, line : "The victor rushing to despoil the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11432, line : "From Paris' bow a vengeful arrow fled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11433, line : "Fix'd in his nervous thigh the weapon stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11434, line : "Fix'd was the point, but broken was the wood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11435, line : "Back to the lines the wounded Greek retired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11436, line : "Yet thus retreating, his associates fired:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11438, line : "\"What god, O Grecians! has your hearts dismay'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11439, line : "Oh, turn to arms; 'tis Ajax claims your aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11440, line : "This hour he stands the mark of hostile rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11441, line : "And this the last brave battle he shall wage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11442, line : "Haste, join your forces; from the gloomy grave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11443, line : "The warrior rescue, and your country save.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11444, line : "Thus urged the chief: a generous troop appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11445, line : "Who spread their bucklers, and advance their spears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11446, line : "To guard their wounded friend: while thus they stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11447, line : "With pious care, great Ajax joins the band:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11448, line : "Each takes new courage at the hero's sight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11449, line : "The hero rallies, and renews the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11451, line : "Thus raged both armies like conflicting fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11452, line : "While Nestor's chariot far from fight retires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11453, line : "His coursers steep'd in sweat, and stain'd with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11454, line : "The Greeks' preserver, great Machaon, bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11455, line : "That hour Achilles, from the topmost height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11456, line : "Of his proud fleet, o'erlook'd the fields of fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11457, line : "His feasted eyes beheld around the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11458, line : "The Grecian rout, the slaying, and the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11459, line : "His friend Machaon singled from the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11460, line : "A transient pity touch'd his vengeful breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11461, line : "Straight to Menoetius' much-loved son he sent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11462, line : "Graceful as Mars, Patroclus quits his tent;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11463, line : "In evil hour! Then fate decreed his doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11464, line : "And fix'd the date of all his woes to come."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11466, line : "\"Why calls my friend? thy loved injunctions lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11467, line : "Whate'er thy will, Patroclus shall obey.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11469, line : "\"O first of friends! (Pelides thus replied)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11470, line : "Still at my heart, and ever at my side!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11471, line : "The time is come, when yon despairing host"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11472, line : "Shall learn the value of the man they lost:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11473, line : "Now at my knees the Greeks shall pour their moan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11474, line : "And proud Atrides tremble on his throne."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11475, line : "Go now to Nestor, and from him be taught"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11476, line : "What wounded warrior late his chariot brought:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11477, line : "For, seen at distance, and but seen behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11478, line : "His form recall'd Machaon to my mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11479, line : "Nor could I, through yon cloud, discern his face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11480, line : "The coursers pass'd me with so swift a pace.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11482, line : "The hero said. His friend obey'd with haste,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11483, line : "Through intermingled ships and tents he pass'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11484, line : "The chiefs descending from their car he found:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11485, line : "The panting steeds Eurymedon unbound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11486, line : "The warriors standing on the breezy shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11487, line : "To dry their sweat, and wash away the gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11488, line : "Here paused a moment, while the gentle gale"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11489, line : "Convey'd that freshness the cool seas exhale;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11490, line : "Then to consult on farther methods went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11491, line : "And took their seats beneath the shady tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11492, line : "The draught prescribed, fair Hecamede prepares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11493, line : "Arsinous' daughter, graced with golden hairs:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11494, line : "(Whom to his aged arms, a royal slave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11495, line : "Greece, as the prize of Nestor's wisdom gave:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11496, line : "A table first with azure feet she placed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11497, line : "Whose ample orb a brazen charger graced;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11498, line : "Honey new-press'd, the sacred flour of wheat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11499, line : "And wholesome garlic, crown'd the savoury treat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11500, line : "Next her white hand an antique goblet brings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11501, line : "A goblet sacred to the Pylian kings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11502, line : "From eldest times: emboss'd with studs of gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11503, line : "Two feet support it, and four handles hold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11504, line : "On each bright handle, bending o'er the brink,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11505, line : "In sculptured gold, two turtles seem to drink:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11506, line : "A massy weight, yet heaved with ease by him,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11507, line : "When the brisk nectar overlook'd the brim."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11508, line : "Temper'd in this, the nymph of form divine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11509, line : "Pours a large portion of the Pramnian wine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11510, line : "With goat's-milk cheese a flavourous taste bestows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11511, line : "And last with flour the smiling surface strows:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11512, line : "This for the wounded prince the dame prepares:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11513, line : "The cordial beverage reverend Nestor shares:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11514, line : "Salubrious draughts the warriors' thirst allay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11515, line : "And pleasing conference beguiles the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11517, line : "Meantime Patroclus, by Achilles sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11518, line : "Unheard approached, and stood before the tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11519, line : "Old Nestor, rising then, the hero led"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11520, line : "To his high seat: the chief refused and said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11522, line : "\"'Tis now no season for these kind delays;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11523, line : "The great Achilles with impatience stays."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11524, line : "To great Achilles this respect I owe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11525, line : "Who asks, what hero, wounded by the foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11526, line : "Was borne from combat by thy foaming steeds?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11527, line : "With grief I see the great Machaon bleeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11528, line : "This to report, my hasty course I bend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11529, line : "Thou know'st the fiery temper of my friend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11530, line : "\"Can then the sons of Greece (the sage rejoin'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11531, line : "Excite compassion in Achilles' mind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11532, line : "Seeks he the sorrows of our host to know?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11533, line : "This is not half the story of our woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11534, line : "Tell him, not great Machaon bleeds alone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11535, line : "Our bravest heroes in the navy groan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11536, line : "Ulysses, Agamemnon, Diomed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11537, line : "And stern Eurypylus, already bleed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11538, line : "But, ah! what flattering hopes I entertain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11539, line : "Achilles heeds not, but derides our pain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11540, line : "Even till the flames consume our fleet he stays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11541, line : "And waits the rising of the fatal blaze."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11542, line : "Chief after chief the raging foe destroys;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11543, line : "Calm he looks on, and every death enjoys."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11544, line : "Now the slow course of all-impairing time"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11545, line : "Unstrings my nerves, and ends my manly prime;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11546, line : "Oh! had I still that strength my youth possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11547, line : "When this bold arm the Epeian powers oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11548, line : "The bulls of Elis in glad triumph led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11549, line : "And stretch'd the great Itymonaeus dead!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11550, line : "Then from my fury fled the trembling swains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11551, line : "And ours was all the plunder of the plains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11552, line : "Fifty white flocks, full fifty herds of swine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11553, line : "As many goats, as many lowing kine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11554, line : "And thrice the number of unrivall'd steeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11555, line : "All teeming females, and of generous breeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11556, line : "These, as my first essay of arms, I won;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11557, line : "Old Neleus gloried in his conquering son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11558, line : "Thus Elis forced, her long arrears restored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11559, line : "And shares were parted to each Pylian lord."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11560, line : "The state of Pyle was sunk to last despair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11561, line : "When the proud Elians first commenced the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11562, line : "For Neleus' sons Alcides' rage had slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11563, line : "Of twelve bold brothers, I alone remain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11564, line : "Oppress'd, we arm'd; and now this conquest gain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11565, line : "My sire three hundred chosen sheep obtain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11566, line : "(That large reprisal he might justly claim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11567, line : "For prize defrauded, and insulted fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11568, line : "When Elis' monarch, at the public course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11569, line : "Detain'd his chariot, and victorious horse.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11570, line : "The rest the people shared; myself survey'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11571, line : "The just partition, and due victims paid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11572, line : "Three days were past, when Elis rose to war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11573, line : "With many a courser, and with many a car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11574, line : "The sons of Actor at their army's head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11575, line : "(Young as they were) the vengeful squadrons led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11576, line : "High on the rock fair Thryoessa stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11577, line : "Our utmost frontier on the Pylian lands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11578, line : "Not far the streams of famed Alphaeus flow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11579, line : "The stream they pass'd, and pitch'd their tents below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11580, line : "Pallas, descending in the shades of night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11581, line : "Alarms the Pylians and commands the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11582, line : "Each burns for fame, and swells with martial pride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11583, line : "Myself the foremost; but my sire denied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11584, line : "Fear'd for my youth, exposed to stern alarms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11585, line : "And stopp'd my chariot, and detain'd my arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11586, line : "My sire denied in vain: on foot I fled"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11587, line : "Amidst our chariots; for the goddess led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11589, line : "\"Along fair Arene's delightful plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11590, line : "Soft Minyas rolls his waters to the main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11591, line : "There, horse and foot, the Pylian troops unite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11592, line : "And sheathed in arms, expect the dawning light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11593, line : "Thence, ere the sun advanced his noon-day flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11594, line : "To great Alphaeus' sacred source we came."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11595, line : "There first to Jove our solemn rites were paid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11596, line : "An untamed heifer pleased the blue-eyed maid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11597, line : "A bull, Alphaeus; and a bull was slain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11598, line : "To the blue monarch of the watery main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11599, line : "In arms we slept, beside the winding flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11600, line : "While round the town the fierce Epeians stood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11601, line : "Soon as the sun, with all-revealing ray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11602, line : "Flamed in the front of Heaven, and gave the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11603, line : "Bright scenes of arms, and works of war appear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11604, line : "The nations meet; there Pylos, Elis here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11605, line : "The first who fell, beneath my javelin bled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11606, line : "King Augias' son, and spouse of Agamede:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11607, line : "(She that all simples' healing virtues knew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11608, line : "And every herb that drinks the morning dew:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11609, line : "I seized his car, the van of battle led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11610, line : "The Epeians saw, they trembled, and they fled."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11611, line : "The foe dispersed, their bravest warrior kill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11612, line : "Fierce as the whirlwind now I swept the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11613, line : "Full fifty captive chariots graced my train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11614, line : "Two chiefs from each fell breathless to the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11615, line : "Then Actor's sons had died, but Neptune shrouds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11616, line : "The youthful heroes in a veil of clouds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11617, line : "O'er heapy shields, and o'er the prostrate throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11618, line : "Collecting spoils, and slaughtering all along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11619, line : "Through wide Buprasian fields we forced the foes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11620, line : "Where o'er the vales the Olenian rocks arose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11621, line : "Till Pallas stopp'd us where Alisium flows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11622, line : "Even there the hindmost of the rear I slay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11623, line : "And the same arm that led concludes the day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11624, line : "Then back to Pyle triumphant take my way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11625, line : "There to high Jove were public thanks assign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11626, line : "As first of gods; to Nestor, of mankind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11627, line : "Such then I was, impell'd by youthful blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11628, line : "So proved my valour for my country's good."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11630, line : "\"Achilles with unactive fury glows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11631, line : "And gives to passion what to Greece he owes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11632, line : "How shall he grieve, when to the eternal shade"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11633, line : "Her hosts shall sink, nor his the power to aid!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11634, line : "0 friend! my memory recalls the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11635, line : "When, gathering aids along the Grecian sea,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11636, line : "I, and Ulysses, touch'd at Phthia's port,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11637, line : "And entered Peleus' hospitable court."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11638, line : "A bull to Jove he slew in sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11639, line : "And pour'd libations on the flaming thighs."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11640, line : "Thyself, Achilles, and thy reverend sire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11641, line : "Menoetius, turn'd the fragments on the fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11642, line : "Achilles sees us, to the feast invites;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11643, line : "Social we sit, and share the genial rites."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11644, line : "We then explained the cause on which we came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11645, line : "Urged you to arms, and found you fierce for fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11646, line : "Your ancient fathers generous precepts gave;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11647, line : "Peleus said only this:--'My son! be brave.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11648, line : "Menoetius thus: 'Though great Achilles shine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11649, line : "In strength superior, and of race divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11650, line : "Yet cooler thoughts thy elder years attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11651, line : "Let thy just counsels aid, and rule thy friend.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11652, line : "Thus spoke your father at Thessalia's court:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11653, line : "Words now forgot, though now of vast import."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11654, line : "Ah! try the utmost that a friend can say:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11655, line : "Such gentle force the fiercest minds obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11656, line : "Some favouring god Achilles' heart may move;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11657, line : "Though deaf to glory, he may yield to love."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11658, line : "If some dire oracle his breast alarm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11659, line : "If aught from Heaven withhold his saving arm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11660, line : "Some beam of comfort yet on Greece may shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11661, line : "If thou but lead the Myrmidonian line;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11662, line : "Clad in Achilles' arms, if thou appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11663, line : "Proud Troy may tremble, and desist from war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11664, line : "Press'd by fresh forces, her o'er-labour'd train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11665, line : "Shall seek their walls, and Greece respire again.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11667, line : "This touch'd his generous heart, and from the tent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11668, line : "Along the shore with hasty strides he went;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11669, line : "Soon as he came, where, on the crowded strand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11670, line : "The public mart and courts of justice stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11671, line : "Where the tall fleet of great Ulysses lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11672, line : "And altars to the guardian gods arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11673, line : "There, sad, he met the brave Euaemon's son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11674, line : "Large painful drops from all his members run;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11675, line : "An arrow's head yet rooted in his wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11676, line : "The sable blood in circles mark'd the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11677, line : "As faintly reeling he confess'd the smart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11678, line : "Weak was his pace, but dauntless was his heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11679, line : "Divine compassion touch'd Patroclus' breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11680, line : "Who, sighing, thus his bleeding friend address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11682, line : "\"Ah, hapless leaders of the Grecian host!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11683, line : "Thus must ye perish on a barbarous coast?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11684, line : "Is this your fate, to glut the dogs with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11685, line : "Far from your friends, and from your native shore?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11686, line : "Say, great Eurypylus! shall Greece yet stand?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11687, line : "Resists she yet the raging Hector's hand?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11688, line : "Or are her heroes doom'd to die with shame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11689, line : "And this the period of our wars and fame?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11691, line : "Eurypylus replies: \"No more, my friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11692, line : "Greece is no more! this day her glories end;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11693, line : "Even to the ships victorious Troy pursues,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11694, line : "Her force increasing as her toil renews."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11695, line : "Those chiefs, that used her utmost rage to meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11696, line : "Lie pierced with wounds, and bleeding in the fleet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11697, line : "But, thou, Patroclus! act a friendly part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11698, line : "Lead to my ships, and draw this deadly dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11699, line : "With lukewarm water wash the gore away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11700, line : "With healing balms the raging smart allay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11701, line : "Such as sage Chiron, sire of pharmacy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11702, line : "Once taught Achilles, and Achilles thee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11703, line : "Of two famed surgeons, Podalirius stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11704, line : "This hour surrounded by the Trojan bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11705, line : "And great Machaon, wounded in his tent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11706, line : "Now wants that succour which so oft he lent.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11708, line : "To him the chief: \"What then remains to do?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11709, line : "The event of things the gods alone can view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11710, line : "Charged by Achilles' great command I fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11711, line : "And bear with haste the Pylian king's reply:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11712, line : "But thy distress this instant claims relief.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11713, line : "He said, and in his arms upheld the chief."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11714, line : "The slaves their master's slow approach survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11715, line : "And hides of oxen on the floor display'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11716, line : "There stretch'd at length the wounded hero lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11717, line : "Patroclus cut the forky steel away:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11718, line : "Then in his hands a bitter root he bruised;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11719, line : "The wound he wash'd, the styptic juice infused."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11720, line : "The closing flesh that instant ceased to glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11721, line : "The wound to torture, and the blood to flow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11723, line : "[Illustration: HERCULES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11725, line : "HERCULES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11731, line : "BOOK XII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11734, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11736, line : "THE BATTLE AT THE GRECIAN WALL."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11738, line : "The Greeks having retired into their intrenchments, Hector attempts to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11739, line : "force them; but it proving impossible to pass the ditch, Polydamas advises"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11740, line : "to quit their chariots, and manage the attack on foot. The Trojans follow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11741, line : "his counsel; and having divided their army into five bodies of foot, begin"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11742, line : "the assault. But upon the signal of an eagle with a serpent in his talons,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11743, line : "which appeared on the left hand of the Trojans, Polydamas endeavours to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11744, line : "withdraw them again. This Hector opposes, and continues the attack; in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11745, line : "which, after many actions, Sarpedon makes the first breach in the wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11746, line : "Hector also, casting a stone of vast size, forces open one of the gates,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11747, line : "and enters at the head of his troops, who victoriously pursue the Grecians"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11748, line : "even to their ships."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11750, line : "While thus the hero's pious cares attend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11751, line : "The cure and safety of his wounded friend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11752, line : "Trojans and Greeks with clashing shields engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11753, line : "And mutual deaths are dealt with mutual rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11754, line : "Nor long the trench or lofty walls oppose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11755, line : "With gods averse the ill-fated works arose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11756, line : "Their powers neglected, and no victim slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11757, line : "The walls were raised, the trenches sunk in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11759, line : "Without the gods, how short a period stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11760, line : "The proudest monument of mortal hands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11761, line : "This stood while Hector and Achilles raged."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11762, line : "While sacred Troy the warring hosts engaged;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11763, line : "But when her sons were slain, her city burn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11764, line : "And what survived of Greece to Greece return'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11765, line : "Then Neptune and Apollo shook the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11766, line : "Then Ida's summits pour'd their watery store;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11767, line : "Rhesus and Rhodius then unite their rills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11768, line : "Caresus roaring down the stony hills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11769, line : "Ćsepus, Granicus, with mingled force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11770, line : "And Xanthus foaming from his fruitful source;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11771, line : "And gulfy Simois, rolling to the main(224)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11772, line : "Helmets, and shields, and godlike heroes slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11773, line : "These, turn'd by Phoebus from their wonted ways,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11774, line : "Deluged the rampire nine continual days;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11775, line : "The weight of waters saps the yielding wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11776, line : "And to the sea the floating bulwarks fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11777, line : "Incessant cataracts the Thunderer pours,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11778, line : "And half the skies descend in sluicy showers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11779, line : "The god of ocean, marching stern before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11780, line : "With his huge trident wounds the trembling shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11781, line : "Vast stones and piles from their foundation heaves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11782, line : "And whelms the smoky ruin in the waves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11783, line : "Now smooth'd with sand, and levell'd by the flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11784, line : "No fragment tells where once the wonder stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11785, line : "In their old bounds the rivers roll again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11786, line : "Shine 'twixt the hills, or wander o'er the plain.(225)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11788, line : "But this the gods in later times perform;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11789, line : "As yet the bulwark stood, and braved the storm;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11790, line : "The strokes yet echoed of contending powers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11791, line : "War thunder'd at the gates, and blood distain'd the towers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11792, line : "Smote by the arm of Jove with dire dismay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11793, line : "Close by their hollow ships the Grecians lay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11794, line : "Hector's approach in every wind they hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11795, line : "And Hector's fury every moment fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11796, line : "He, like a whirlwind, toss'd the scattering throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11797, line : "Mingled the troops, and drove the field along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11798, line : "So 'midst the dogs and hunters' daring bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11799, line : "Fierce of his might, a boar or lion stands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11800, line : "Arm'd foes around a dreadful circle form,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11801, line : "And hissing javelins rain an iron storm:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11802, line : "His powers untamed, their bold assault defy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11803, line : "And where he turns the rout disperse or die:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11804, line : "He foams, he glares, he bounds against them all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11805, line : "And if he falls, his courage makes him fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11806, line : "With equal rage encompass'd Hector glows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11807, line : "Exhorts his armies, and the trenches shows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11808, line : "The panting steeds impatient fury breathe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11809, line : "And snort and tremble at the gulf beneath;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11810, line : "Just at the brink they neigh, and paw the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11811, line : "And the turf trembles, and the skies resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11812, line : "Eager they view'd the prospect dark and deep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11813, line : "Vast was the leap, and headlong hung the steep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11814, line : "The bottom bare, (a formidable show!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11815, line : "And bristled thick with sharpen'd stakes below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11816, line : "The foot alone this strong defence could force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11817, line : "And try the pass impervious to the horse."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11818, line : "This saw Polydamas; who, wisely brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11819, line : "Restrain'd great Hector, and this counsel gave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11821, line : "\"O thou, bold leader of the Trojan bands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11822, line : "And you, confederate chiefs from foreign lands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11823, line : "What entrance here can cumbrous chariots find,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11824, line : "The stakes beneath, the Grecian walls behind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11825, line : "No pass through those, without a thousand wounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11826, line : "No space for combat in yon narrow bounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11827, line : "Proud of the favours mighty Jove has shown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11828, line : "On certain dangers we too rashly run:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11829, line : "If 'tis will our haughty foes to tame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11830, line : "Oh may this instant end the Grecian name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11831, line : "Here, far from Argos, let their heroes fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11832, line : "And one great day destroy and bury all!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11833, line : "But should they turn, and here oppress our train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11834, line : "What hopes, what methods of retreat remain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11835, line : "Wedged in the trench, by our own troops confused,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11836, line : "In one promiscuous carnage crush'd and bruised,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11837, line : "All Troy must perish, if their arms prevail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11838, line : "Nor shall a Trojan live to tell the tale."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11839, line : "Hear then, ye warriors! and obey with speed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11840, line : "Back from the trenches let your steeds be led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11841, line : "Then all alighting, wedged in firm array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11842, line : "Proceed on foot, and Hector lead the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11843, line : "So Greece shall stoop before our conquering power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11844, line : "And this (if Jove consent) her fatal hour.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11846, line : "[Illustration: POLYDAMAS ADVISING HECTOR.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11848, line : "POLYDAMAS ADVISING HECTOR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11851, line : "This counsel pleased: the godlike Hector sprung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11852, line : "Swift from his seat; his clanging armour rung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11853, line : "The chief's example follow'd by his train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11854, line : "Each quits his car, and issues on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11855, line : "By orders strict the charioteers enjoin'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11856, line : "Compel the coursers to their ranks behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11857, line : "The forces part in five distinguish'd bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11858, line : "And all obey their several chiefs' commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11859, line : "The best and bravest in the first conspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11860, line : "Pant for the fight, and threat the fleet with fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11861, line : "Great Hector glorious in the van of these,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11862, line : "Polydamas, and brave Cebriones."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11863, line : "Before the next the graceful Paris shines,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11864, line : "And bold Alcathous, and Agenor joins."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11865, line : "The sons of Priam with the third appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11866, line : "Deiphobus, and Helenas the seer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11867, line : "In arms with these the mighty Asius stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11868, line : "Who drew from Hyrtacus his noble blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11869, line : "And whom Arisba's yellow coursers bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11870, line : "The coursers fed on Selle's winding shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11871, line : "Antenor's sons the fourth battalion guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11872, line : "And great Ćneas, born on fountful Ide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11873, line : "Divine Sarpedon the last band obey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11874, line : "Whom Glaucus and Asteropaeus aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11875, line : "Next him, the bravest, at their army's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11876, line : "But he more brave than all the hosts he led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11878, line : "Now with compacted shields in close array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11879, line : "The moving legions speed their headlong way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11880, line : "Already in their hopes they fire the fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11881, line : "And see the Grecians gasping at their feet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11883, line : "While every Trojan thus, and every aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11884, line : "The advice of wise Polydamas obey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11885, line : "Asius alone, confiding in his car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11886, line : "His vaunted coursers urged to meet the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11887, line : "Unhappy hero! and advised in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11888, line : "Those wheels returning ne'er shall mark the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11889, line : "No more those coursers with triumphant joy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11890, line : "Restore their master to the gates of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11891, line : "Black death attends behind the Grecian wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11892, line : "And great Idomeneus shall boast thy fall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11893, line : "Fierce to the left he drives, where from the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11894, line : "The flying Grecians strove their ships to gain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11895, line : "Swift through the wall their horse and chariots pass'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11896, line : "The gates half-open'd to receive the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11897, line : "Thither, exulting in his force, he flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11898, line : "His following host with clamours rend the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11899, line : "To plunge the Grecians headlong in the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11900, line : "Such their proud hopes; but all their hopes were vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11902, line : "To guard the gates, two mighty chiefs attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11903, line : "Who from the Lapiths' warlike race descend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11904, line : "This Polypoetes, great Perithous' heir,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11905, line : "And that Leonteus, like the god of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11906, line : "As two tall oaks, before the wall they rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11907, line : "Their roots in earth, their heads amidst the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11908, line : "Whose spreading arms with leafy honours crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11909, line : "Forbid the tempest, and protect the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11910, line : "High on the hills appears their stately form,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11911, line : "And their deep roots for ever brave the storm."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11912, line : "So graceful these, and so the shock they stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11913, line : "Of raging Asius, and his furious band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11914, line : "Orestes, Acamas, in front appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11915, line : "And OEnomaus and Thoon close the rear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11916, line : "In vain their clamours shake the ambient fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11917, line : "In vain around them beat their hollow shields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11918, line : "The fearless brothers on the Grecians call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11919, line : "To guard their navies, and defend the wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11920, line : "Even when they saw Troy's sable troops impend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11921, line : "And Greece tumultuous from her towers descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11922, line : "Forth from the portals rush'd the intrepid pair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11923, line : "Opposed their breasts, and stood themselves the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11924, line : "So two wild boars spring furious from their den,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11925, line : "Roused with the cries of dogs and voice of men;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11926, line : "On every side the crackling trees they tear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11927, line : "And root the shrubs, and lay the forest bare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11928, line : "They gnash their tusks, with fire their eye-balls roll,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11929, line : "Till some wide wound lets out their mighty soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11930, line : "Around their heads the whistling javelins sung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11931, line : "With sounding strokes their brazen targets rung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11932, line : "Fierce was the fight, while yet the Grecian powers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11933, line : "Maintain'd the walls, and mann'd the lofty towers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11934, line : "To save their fleet their last efforts they try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11935, line : "And stones and darts in mingled tempests fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11937, line : "As when sharp Boreas blows abroad, and brings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11938, line : "The dreary winter on his frozen wings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11939, line : "Beneath the low-hung clouds the sheets of snow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11940, line : "Descend, and whiten all the fields below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11941, line : "So fast the darts on either army pour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11942, line : "So down the rampires rolls the rocky shower:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11943, line : "Heavy, and thick, resound the batter'd shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11944, line : "And the deaf echo rattles round the fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11946, line : "With shame repulsed, with grief and fury driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11947, line : "The frantic Asius thus accuses Heaven:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11948, line : "\"In powers immortal who shall now believe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11949, line : "Can those too flatter, and can Jove deceive?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11950, line : "What man could doubt but Troy's victorious power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11951, line : "Should humble Greece, and this her fatal hour?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11952, line : "But like when wasps from hollow crannies drive,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11953, line : "To guard the entrance of their common hive,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11954, line : "Darkening the rock, while with unwearied wings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11955, line : "They strike the assailants, and infix their stings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11956, line : "A race determined, that to death contend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11957, line : "So fierce these Greeks their last retreats defend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11958, line : "Gods! shall two warriors only guard their gates,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11959, line : "Repel an army, and defraud the fates?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11961, line : "These empty accents mingled with the wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11962, line : "Nor moved great Jove's unalterable mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11963, line : "To godlike Hector and his matchless might"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11964, line : "Was owed the glory of the destined fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11965, line : "Like deeds of arms through all the forts were tried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11966, line : "And all the gates sustain'd an equal tide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11967, line : "Through the long walls the stony showers were heard,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11968, line : "The blaze of flames, the flash of arms appear'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11969, line : "The spirit of a god my breast inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11970, line : "To raise each act to life, and sing with fire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11971, line : "While Greece unconquer'd kept alive the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11972, line : "Secure of death, confiding in despair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11973, line : "And all her guardian gods, in deep dismay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11974, line : "With unassisting arms deplored the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11976, line : "Even yet the dauntless Lapithae maintain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11977, line : "The dreadful pass, and round them heap the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11978, line : "First Damasus, by Polypoetes' steel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11979, line : "Pierced through his helmet's brazen visor, fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11980, line : "The weapon drank the mingled brains and gore!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11981, line : "The warrior sinks, tremendous now no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11982, line : "Next Ormenus and Pylon yield their breath:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11983, line : "Nor less Leonteus strews the field with death;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11984, line : "First through the belt Hippomachus he gored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11985, line : "Then sudden waved his unresisted sword:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11986, line : "Antiphates, as through the ranks he broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11987, line : "The falchion struck, and fate pursued the stroke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11988, line : "Iamenus, Orestes, Menon, bled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11989, line : "And round him rose a monument of dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11990, line : "Meantime, the bravest of the Trojan crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11991, line : "Bold Hector and Polydamas, pursue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11992, line : "Fierce with impatience on the works to fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11993, line : "And wrap in rolling flames the fleet and wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11994, line : "These on the farther bank now stood and gazed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11995, line : "By Heaven alarm'd, by prodigies amazed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11996, line : "A signal omen stopp'd the passing host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11997, line : "Their martial fury in their wonder lost."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11998, line : "Jove's bird on sounding pinions beat the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 11999, line : "A bleeding serpent of enormous size,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12000, line : "His talons truss'd; alive, and curling round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12001, line : "He stung the bird, whose throat received the wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12002, line : "Mad with the smart, he drops the fatal prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12003, line : "In airy circles wings his painful way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12004, line : "Floats on the winds, and rends the heaven with cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12005, line : "Amidst the host the fallen serpent lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12006, line : "They, pale with terror, mark its spires unroll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12007, line : "And Jove's portent with beating hearts behold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12008, line : "Then first Polydamas the silence broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12009, line : "Long weigh'd the signal, and to Hector spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12011, line : "\"How oft, my brother, thy reproach I bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12012, line : "For words well meant, and sentiments sincere?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12013, line : "True to those counsels which I judge the best,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12014, line : "I tell the faithful dictates of my breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12015, line : "To speak his thoughts is every freeman's right,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12016, line : "In peace, in war, in council, and in fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12017, line : "And all I move, deferring to thy sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12018, line : "But tends to raise that power which I obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12019, line : "Then hear my words, nor may my words be vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12020, line : "Seek not this day the Grecian ships to gain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12021, line : "For sure, to warn us, Jove his omen sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12022, line : "And thus my mind explains its clear event:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12023, line : "The victor eagle, whose sinister flight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12024, line : "Retards our host, and fills our hearts with fright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12025, line : "Dismiss'd his conquest in the middle skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12026, line : "Allow'd to seize, but not possess the prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12027, line : "Thus, though we gird with fires the Grecian fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12028, line : "Though these proud bulwalks tumble at our feet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12029, line : "Toils unforeseen, and fiercer, are decreed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12030, line : "More woes shall follow, and more heroes bleed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12031, line : "So bodes my soul, and bids me thus advise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12032, line : "For thus a skilful seer would read the skies.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12034, line : "To him then Hector with disdain return'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12035, line : "(Fierce as he spoke, his eyes with fury burn'd:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12036, line : "\"Are these the faithful counsels of thy tongue?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12037, line : "Thy will is partial, not thy reason wrong:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12038, line : "Or if the purpose of thy heart thou vent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12039, line : "Sure heaven resumes the little sense it lent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12040, line : "What coward counsels would thy madness move"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12041, line : "Against the word, the will reveal'd of Jove?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12042, line : "The leading sign, the irrevocable nod,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12043, line : "And happy thunders of the favouring god,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12044, line : "These shall I slight, and guide my wavering mind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12045, line : "By wandering birds that flit with every wind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12046, line : "Ye vagrants of the sky! your wings extend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12047, line : "Or where the suns arise, or where descend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12048, line : "To right, to left, unheeded take your way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12049, line : "While I the dictates of high heaven obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12050, line : "Without a sign his sword the brave man draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12051, line : "And asks no omen but his country's cause."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12052, line : "But why should'st thou suspect the war's success?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12053, line : "None fears it more, as none promotes it less:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12054, line : "Though all our chiefs amidst yon ships expire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12055, line : "Trust thy own cowardice to escape their fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12056, line : "Troy and her sons may find a general grave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12057, line : "But thou canst live, for thou canst be a slave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12058, line : "Yet should the fears that wary mind suggests"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12059, line : "Spread their cold poison through our soldiers' breasts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12060, line : "My javelin can revenge so base a part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12061, line : "And free the soul that quivers in thy heart.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12063, line : "Furious he spoke, and, rushing to the wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12064, line : "Calls on his host; his host obey the call;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12065, line : "With ardour follow where their leader flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12066, line : "Redoubling clamours thunder in the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12067, line : "Jove breathes a whirlwind from the hills of Ide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12068, line : "And drifts of dust the clouded navy hide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12069, line : "He fills the Greeks with terror and dismay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12070, line : "And gives great Hector the predestined day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12071, line : "Strong in themselves, but stronger in his aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12072, line : "Close to the works their rigid siege they laid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12073, line : "In vain the mounds and massy beams defend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12074, line : "While these they undermine, and those they rend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12075, line : "Upheaved the piles that prop the solid wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12076, line : "And heaps on heaps the smoky ruins fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12077, line : "Greece on her ramparts stands the fierce alarms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12078, line : "The crowded bulwarks blaze with waving arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12079, line : "Shield touching shield, a long refulgent row;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12080, line : "Whence hissing darts, incessant, rain below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12081, line : "The bold Ajaces fly from tower to tower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12082, line : "And rouse, with flame divine, the Grecian power."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12083, line : "The generous impulse every Greek obeys;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12084, line : "Threats urge the fearful; and the valiant, praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12086, line : "\"Fellows in arms! whose deeds are known to fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12087, line : "And you, whose ardour hopes an equal name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12088, line : "Since not alike endued with force or art;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12089, line : "Behold a day when each may act his part!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12090, line : "A day to fire the brave, and warm the cold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12091, line : "To gain new glories, or augment the old."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12092, line : "Urge those who stand, and those who faint, excite;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12093, line : "Drown Hector's vaunts in loud exhorts of fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12094, line : "Conquest, not safety, fill the thoughts of all;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12095, line : "Seek not your fleet, but sally from the wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12096, line : "So Jove once more may drive their routed train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12097, line : "And Troy lie trembling in her walls again.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12099, line : "Their ardour kindles all the Grecian powers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12100, line : "And now the stones descend in heavier showers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12101, line : "As when high Jove his sharp artillery forms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12102, line : "And opes his cloudy magazine of storms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12103, line : "In winter's bleak un comfortable reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12104, line : "A snowy inundation hides the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12105, line : "He stills the winds, and bids the skies to sleep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12106, line : "Then pours the silent tempest thick and deep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12107, line : "And first the mountain-tops are cover'd o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12108, line : "Then the green fields, and then the sandy shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12109, line : "Bent with the weight, the nodding woods are seen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12110, line : "And one bright waste hides all the works of men:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12111, line : "The circling seas, alone absorbing all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12112, line : "Drink the dissolving fleeces as they fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12113, line : "So from each side increased the stony rain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12114, line : "And the white ruin rises o'er the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12116, line : "Thus godlike Hector and his troops contend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12117, line : "To force the ramparts, and the gates to rend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12118, line : "Nor Troy could conquer, nor the Greeks would yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12119, line : "Till great Sarpedon tower'd amid the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12120, line : "For mighty Jove inspired with martial flame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12121, line : "His matchless son, and urged him on to fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12122, line : "In arms he shines, conspicuous from afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12123, line : "And bears aloft his ample shield in air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12124, line : "Within whose orb the thick bull-hides were roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12125, line : "Ponderous with brass, and bound with ductile gold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12126, line : "And while two pointed javelins arm his hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12127, line : "Majestic moves along, and leads his Lycian bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12129, line : "So press'd with hunger, from the mountain's brow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12130, line : "Descends a lion on the flocks below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12131, line : "So stalks the lordly savage o'er the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12132, line : "In sullen majesty, and stern disdain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12133, line : "In vain loud mastiffs bay him from afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12134, line : "And shepherds gall him with an iron war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12135, line : "Regardless, furious, he pursues his way;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12136, line : "He foams, he roars, he rends the panting prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12138, line : "Resolved alike, divine Sarpedon glows"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12139, line : "With generous rage that drives him on the foes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12140, line : "He views the towers, and meditates their fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12141, line : "To sure destruction dooms the aspiring wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12142, line : "Then casting on his friend an ardent look,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12143, line : "Fired with the thirst of glory, thus he spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12145, line : "\"Why boast we, Glaucus! our extended reign,(226)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12146, line : "Where Xanthus' streams enrich the Lycian plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12147, line : "Our numerous herds that range the fruitful field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12148, line : "And hills where vines their purple harvest yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12149, line : "Our foaming bowls with purer nectar crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12150, line : "Our feasts enhanced with music's sprightly sound?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12151, line : "Why on those shores are we with joy survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12152, line : "Admired as heroes, and as gods obey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12153, line : "Unless great acts superior merit prove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12154, line : "And vindicate the bounteous powers above?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12155, line : "'Tis ours, the dignity they give to grace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12156, line : "The first in valour, as the first in place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12157, line : "That when with wondering eyes our martial bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12158, line : "Behold our deeds transcending our commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12159, line : "Such, they may cry, deserve the sovereign state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12160, line : "Whom those that envy dare not imitate!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12161, line : "Could all our care elude the gloomy grave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12162, line : "Which claims no less the fearful and the brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12163, line : "For lust of fame I should not vainly dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12164, line : "In fighting fields, nor urge thy soul to war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12165, line : "But since, alas! ignoble age must come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12166, line : "Disease, and death's inexorable doom"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12167, line : "The life, which others pay, let us bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12168, line : "And give to fame what we to nature owe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12169, line : "Brave though we fall, and honour'd if we live,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12170, line : "Or let us glory gain, or glory give!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12172, line : "He said; his words the listening chief inspire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12173, line : "With equal warmth, and rouse the warrior's fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12174, line : "The troops pursue their leaders with delight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12175, line : "Rush to the foe, and claim the promised fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12176, line : "Menestheus from on high the storm beheld"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12177, line : "Threatening the fort, and blackening in the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12178, line : "Around the walls he gazed, to view from far"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12179, line : "What aid appear'd to avert the approaching war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12180, line : "And saw where Teucer with the Ajaces stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12181, line : "Of fight insatiate, prodigal of blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12182, line : "In vain he calls; the din of helms and shields"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12183, line : "Rings to the skies, and echoes through the fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12184, line : "The brazen hinges fly, the walls resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12185, line : "Heaven trembles, roar the mountains, thunders all the ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12186, line : "Then thus to Thoos: \"Hence with speed (he said),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12187, line : "And urge the bold Ajaces to our aid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12188, line : "Their strength, united, best may help to bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12189, line : "The bloody labours of the doubtful war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12190, line : "Hither the Lycian princes bend their course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12191, line : "The best and bravest of the hostile force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12192, line : "But if too fiercely there the foes contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12193, line : "Let Telamon, at least, our towers defend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12194, line : "And Teucer haste with his unerring bow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12195, line : "To share the danger, and repel the foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12197, line : "Swift, at the word, the herald speeds along"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12198, line : "The lofty ramparts, through the martial throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12199, line : "And finds the heroes bathed in sweat and gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12200, line : "Opposed in combat on the dusty shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12201, line : "\"Ye valiant leaders of our warlike bands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12202, line : "Your aid (said Thoos) Peteus' son demands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12203, line : "Your strength, united, best may help to bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12204, line : "The bloody labours of the doubtful war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12205, line : "Thither the Lycian princes bend their course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12206, line : "The best and bravest of the hostile force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12207, line : "But if too fiercely, here, the foes contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12208, line : "At least, let Telamon those towers defend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12209, line : "And Teucer haste with his unerring bow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12210, line : "To share the danger, and repel the foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12212, line : "Straight to the fort great Ajax turn'd his care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12213, line : "And thus bespoke his brothers of the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12214, line : "\"Now, valiant Lycomede! exert your might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12215, line : "And, brave Oileus, prove your force in fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12216, line : "To you I trust the fortune of the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12217, line : "Till by this arm the foe shall be repell'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12218, line : "That done, expect me to complete the day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12219, line : "Then with his sevenfold shield he strode away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12220, line : "With equal steps bold Teucer press'd the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12221, line : "Whose fatal bow the strong Pandion bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12223, line : "High on the walls appear'd the Lycian powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12224, line : "Like some black tempest gathering round the towers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12225, line : "The Greeks, oppress'd, their utmost force unite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12226, line : "Prepared to labour in the unequal fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12227, line : "The war renews, mix'd shouts and groans arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12228, line : "Tumultuous clamour mounts, and thickens in the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12229, line : "Fierce Ajax first the advancing host invades,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12230, line : "And sends the brave Epicles to the shades,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12231, line : "Sarpedon's friend. Across the warrior's way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12232, line : "Rent from the walls, a rocky fragment lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12233, line : "In modern ages not the strongest swain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12234, line : "Could heave the unwieldy burden from the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12235, line : "He poised, and swung it round; then toss'd on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12236, line : "It flew with force, and labour'd up the sky;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12237, line : "Full on the Lycian's helmet thundering down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12238, line : "The ponderous ruin crush'd his batter'd crown."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12239, line : "As skilful divers from some airy steep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12240, line : "Headlong descend, and shoot into the deep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12241, line : "So falls Epicles; then in groans expires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12242, line : "And murmuring to the shades the soul retires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12244, line : "While to the ramparts daring Glaucus drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12245, line : "From Teucer's hand a winged arrow flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12246, line : "The bearded shaft the destined passage found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12247, line : "And on his naked arm inflicts a wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12248, line : "The chief, who fear'd some foe's insulting boast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12249, line : "Might stop the progress of his warlike host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12250, line : "Conceal'd the wound, and, leaping from his height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12251, line : "Retired reluctant from the unfinish'd fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12252, line : "Divine Sarpedon with regret beheld"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12253, line : "Disabled Glaucus slowly quit the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12254, line : "His beating breast with generous ardour glows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12255, line : "He springs to fight, and flies upon the foes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12256, line : "Alcmaon first was doom'd his force to feel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12257, line : "Deep in his breast he plunged the pointed steel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12258, line : "Then from the yawning wound with fury tore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12259, line : "The spear, pursued by gushing streams of gore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12260, line : "Down sinks the warrior with a thundering sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12261, line : "His brazen armour rings against the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12263, line : "Swift to the battlement the victor flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12264, line : "Tugs with full force, and every nerve applies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12265, line : "It shakes; the ponderous stones disjointed yield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12266, line : "The rolling ruins smoke along the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12267, line : "A mighty breach appears; the walls lie bare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12268, line : "And, like a deluge, rushes in the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12269, line : "At once bold Teucer draws the twanging bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12270, line : "And Ajax sends his javelin at the foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12271, line : "Fix'd in his belt the feather'd weapon stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12272, line : "And through his buckler drove the trembling wood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12273, line : "But Jove was present in the dire debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12274, line : "To shield his offspring, and avert his fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12275, line : "The prince gave back, not meditating flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12276, line : "But urging vengeance, and severer fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12277, line : "Then raised with hope, and fired with glory's charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12278, line : "His fainting squadrons to new fury warms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12279, line : "\"O where, ye Lycians, is the strength you boast?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12280, line : "Your former fame and ancient virtue lost!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12281, line : "The breach lies open, but your chief in vain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12282, line : "Attempts alone the guarded pass to gain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12283, line : "Unite, and soon that hostile fleet shall fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12284, line : "The force of powerful union conquers all.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12286, line : "This just rebuke inflamed the Lycian crew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12287, line : "They join, they thicken, and the assault renew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12288, line : "Unmoved the embodied Greeks their fury dare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12289, line : "And fix'd support the weight of all the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12290, line : "Nor could the Greeks repel the Lycian powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12291, line : "Nor the bold Lycians force the Grecian towers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12292, line : "As on the confines of adjoining grounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12293, line : "Two stubborn swains with blows dispute their bounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12294, line : "They tug, they sweat; but neither gain, nor yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12295, line : "One foot, one inch, of the contended field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12296, line : "Thus obstinate to death, they fight, they fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12297, line : "Nor these can keep, nor those can win the wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12298, line : "Their manly breasts are pierced with many a wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12299, line : "Loud strokes are heard, and rattling arms resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12300, line : "The copious slaughter covers all the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12301, line : "And the high ramparts drip with human gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12303, line : "As when two scales are charged with doubtful loads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12304, line : "From side to side the trembling balance nods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12305, line : "(While some laborious matron, just and poor,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12306, line : "With nice exactness weighs her woolly store,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12307, line : "Till poised aloft, the resting beam suspends"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12308, line : "Each equal weight; nor this, nor that, descends:(227)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12309, line : "So stood the war, till Hector's matchless might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12310, line : "With fates prevailing, turn'd the scale of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12311, line : "Fierce as a whirlwind up the walls he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12312, line : "And fires his host with loud repeated cries."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12313, line : "\"Advance, ye Trojans! lend your valiant hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12314, line : "Haste to the fleet, and toss the blazing brands!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12315, line : "They hear, they run; and, gathering at his call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12316, line : "Raise scaling engines, and ascend the wall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12317, line : "Around the works a wood of glittering spears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12318, line : "Shoots up, and all the rising host appears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12319, line : "A ponderous stone bold Hector heaved to throw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12320, line : "Pointed above, and rough and gross below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12321, line : "Not two strong men the enormous weight could raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12322, line : "Such men as live in these degenerate days:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12323, line : "Yet this, as easy as a swain could bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12324, line : "The snowy fleece, he toss'd, and shook in air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12325, line : "For Jove upheld, and lighten'd of its load"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12326, line : "The unwieldy rock, the labour of a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12327, line : "Thus arm'd, before the folded gates he came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12328, line : "Of massy substance, and stupendous frame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12329, line : "With iron bars and brazen hinges strong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12330, line : "On lofty beams of solid timber hung:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12331, line : "Then thundering through the planks with forceful sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12332, line : "Drives the sharp rock; the solid beams give way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12333, line : "The folds are shatter'd; from the crackling door"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12334, line : "Leap the resounding bars, the flying hinges roar."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12335, line : "Now rushing in, the furious chief appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12336, line : "Gloomy as night! and shakes two shining spears:(228)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12337, line : "A dreadful gleam from his bright armour came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12338, line : "And from his eye-balls flash'd the living flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12339, line : "He moves a god, resistless in his course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12340, line : "And seems a match for more than mortal force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12341, line : "Then pouring after, through the gaping space,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12342, line : "A tide of Trojans flows, and fills the place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12343, line : "The Greeks behold, they tremble, and they fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12344, line : "The shore is heap'd with death, and tumult rends the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12346, line : "[Illustration: GREEK ALTAR.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12348, line : "GREEK ALTAR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12354, line : "BOOK XIII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12357, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12359, line : "THE FOURTH BATTLE CONTINUED, IN WHICH NEPTUNE ASSISTS THE GREEKS: THE ACTS"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12360, line : "OF IDOMENEUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12362, line : "Neptune, concerned for the loss of the Grecians, upon seeing the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12363, line : "fortification forced by Hector, (who had entered the gate near the station"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12364, line : "of the Ajaces,) assumes the shape of Calchas, and inspires those heroes to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12365, line : "oppose him: then, in the form of one of the generals, encourages the other"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12366, line : "Greeks who had retired to their vessels. The Ajaces form their troops in a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12367, line : "close phalanx, and put a stop to Hector and the Trojans. Several deeds of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12368, line : "valour are performed; Meriones, losing his spear in the encounter, repairs"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12369, line : "to seek another at the tent of Idomeneus: this occasions a conversation"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12370, line : "between those two warriors, who return together to the battle. Idomeneus"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12371, line : "signalizes his courage above the rest; he kills Othryoneus, Asius, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12372, line : "Alcathous: Deiphobus and Ćneas march against him, and at length Idomeneus"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12373, line : "retires. Menelaus wounds Helenus, and kills Pisander. The Trojans are"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12374, line : "repulsed on the left wing; Hector still keeps his ground against the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12375, line : "Ajaces, till, being galled by the Locrian slingers and archers, Polydamas"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12376, line : "advises to call a council of war: Hector approves of his advice, but goes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12377, line : "first to rally the Trojans; upbraids Paris, rejoins Polydamas, meets Ajax"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12378, line : "again, and renews the attack."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12380, line : "The eight-and-twentieth day still continues. The scene is between the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12381, line : "Grecian wall and the sea-shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12383, line : "When now the Thunderer on the sea-beat coast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12384, line : "Had fix'd great Hector and his conquering host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12385, line : "He left them to the fates, in bloody fray"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12386, line : "To toil and struggle through the well-fought day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12387, line : "Then turn'd to Thracia from the field of fight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12388, line : "Those eyes that shed insufferable light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12389, line : "To where the Mysians prove their martial force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12390, line : "And hardy Thracians tame the savage horse;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12391, line : "And where the far-famed Hippomolgian strays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12392, line : "Renown'd for justice and for length of days;(229)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12393, line : "Thrice happy race! that, innocent of blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12394, line : "From milk, innoxious, seek their simple food:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12395, line : "Jove sees delighted; and avoids the scene"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12396, line : "Of guilty Troy, of arms, and dying men:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12397, line : "No aid, he deems, to either host is given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12398, line : "While his high law suspends the powers of Heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12400, line : "Meantime the monarch of the watery main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12401, line : "Observed the Thunderer, nor observed in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12402, line : "In Samothracia, on a mountain's brow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12403, line : "Whose waving woods o'erhung the deeps below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12404, line : "He sat; and round him cast his azure eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12405, line : "Where Ida's misty tops confusedly rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12406, line : "Below, fair Ilion's glittering spires were seen;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12407, line : "The crowded ships and sable seas between."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12408, line : "There, from the crystal chambers of the main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12409, line : "Emerged, he sat, and mourn'd his Argives slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12410, line : "At Jove incensed, with grief and fury stung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12411, line : "Prone down the rocky steep he rush'd along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12412, line : "Fierce as he pass'd, the lofty mountains nod,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12413, line : "The forest shakes; earth trembled as he trod,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12414, line : "And felt the footsteps of the immortal god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12415, line : "From realm to realm three ample strides he took,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12416, line : "And, at the fourth, the distant Ćgae shook."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12418, line : "Far in the bay his shining palace stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12419, line : "Eternal frame! not raised by mortal hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12420, line : "This having reach'd, his brass-hoof'd steeds he reins,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12421, line : "Fleet as the winds, and deck'd with golden manes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12422, line : "Refulgent arms his mighty limbs infold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12423, line : "Immortal arms of adamant and gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12424, line : "He mounts the car, the golden scourge applies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12425, line : "He sits superior, and the chariot flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12426, line : "His whirling wheels the glassy surface sweep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12427, line : "The enormous monsters rolling o'er the deep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12428, line : "Gambol around him on the watery way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12429, line : "And heavy whales in awkward measures play;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12430, line : "The sea subsiding spreads a level plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12431, line : "Exults, and owns the monarch of the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12432, line : "The parting waves before his coursers fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12433, line : "The wondering waters leave his axle dry."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12435, line : "Deep in the liquid regions lies a cave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12436, line : "Between where Tenedos the surges lave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12437, line : "And rocky Imbrus breaks the rolling wave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12438, line : "There the great ruler of the azure round"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12439, line : "Stopp'd his swift chariot, and his steeds unbound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12440, line : "Fed with ambrosial herbage from his hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12441, line : "And link'd their fetlocks with a golden band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12442, line : "Infrangible, immortal: there they stay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12443, line : "The father of the floods pursues his way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12444, line : "Where, like a tempest, darkening heaven around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12445, line : "Or fiery deluge that devours the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12446, line : "The impatient Trojans, in a gloomy throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12447, line : "Embattled roll'd, as Hector rush'd along:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12448, line : "To the loud tumult and the barbarous cry"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12449, line : "The heavens re-echo, and the shores reply:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12450, line : "They vow destruction to the Grecian name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12451, line : "And in their hopes the fleets already flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12453, line : "But Neptune, rising from the seas profound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12454, line : "The god whose earthquakes rock the solid ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12455, line : "Now wears a mortal form; like Calchas seen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12456, line : "Such his loud voice, and such his manly mien;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12457, line : "His shouts incessant every Greek inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12458, line : "But most the Ajaces, adding fire to fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12460, line : "[Illustration: NEPTUNE RISING FROM THE SEA.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12462, line : "NEPTUNE RISING FROM THE SEA."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12465, line : "\"'Tis yours, O warriors, all our hopes to raise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12466, line : "Oh recollect your ancient worth and praise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12467, line : "'Tis yours to save us, if you cease to fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12468, line : "Flight, more than shameful, is destructive here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12469, line : "On other works though Troy with fury fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12470, line : "And pour her armies o'er our batter'd wall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12471, line : "There Greece has strength: but this, this part o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12472, line : "Her strength were vain; I dread for you alone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12473, line : "Here Hector rages like the force of fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12474, line : "Vaunts of his gods, and calls high Jove his sire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12475, line : "If yet some heavenly power your breast excite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12476, line : "Breathe in your hearts, and string your arms to fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12477, line : "Greece yet may live, her threaten'd fleet maintain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12478, line : "And Hector's force, and Jove's own aid, be vain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12480, line : "Then with his sceptre, that the deep controls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12481, line : "He touch'd the chiefs, and steel'd their manly souls:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12482, line : "Strength, not their own, the touch divine imparts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12483, line : "Prompts their light limbs, and swells their daring hearts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12484, line : "Then, as a falcon from the rocky height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12485, line : "Her quarry seen, impetuous at the sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12486, line : "Forth-springing instant, darts herself from high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12487, line : "Shoots on the wing, and skims along the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12488, line : "Such, and so swift, the power of ocean flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12489, line : "The wide horizon shut him from their view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12491, line : "The inspiring god Oileus' active son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12492, line : "Perceived the first, and thus to Telamon:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12494, line : "\"Some god, my friend, some god in human form"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12495, line : "Favouring descends, and wills to stand the storm."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12496, line : "Not Calchas this, the venerable seer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12497, line : "Short as he turned, I saw the power appear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12498, line : "I mark'd his parting, and the steps he trod;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12499, line : "His own bright evidence reveals a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12500, line : "Even now some energy divine I share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12501, line : "And seem to walk on wings, and tread in air!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12503, line : "\"With equal ardour (Telamon returns)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12504, line : "My soul is kindled, and my bosom burns;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12505, line : "New rising spirits all my force alarm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12506, line : "Lift each impatient limb, and brace my arm."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12507, line : "This ready arm, unthinking, shakes the dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12508, line : "The blood pours back, and fortifies my heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12509, line : "Singly, methinks, yon towering chief I meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12510, line : "And stretch the dreadful Hector at my feet.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12512, line : "Full of the god that urged their burning breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12513, line : "The heroes thus their mutual warmth express'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12514, line : "Neptune meanwhile the routed Greeks inspired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12515, line : "Who, breathless, pale, with length of labours tired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12516, line : "Pant in the ships; while Troy to conquest calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12517, line : "And swarms victorious o'er their yielding walls:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12518, line : "Trembling before the impending storm they lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12519, line : "While tears of rage stand burning in their eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12520, line : "Greece sunk they thought, and this their fatal hour;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12521, line : "But breathe new courage as they feel the power."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12522, line : "Teucer and Leitus first his words excite;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12523, line : "Then stern Peneleus rises to the fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12524, line : "Thoas, Deipyrus, in arms renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12525, line : "And Merion next, the impulsive fury found;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12526, line : "Last Nestor's son the same bold ardour takes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12527, line : "While thus the god the martial fire awakes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12529, line : "\"Oh lasting infamy, oh dire disgrace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12530, line : "To chiefs of vigorous youth, and manly race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12531, line : "I trusted in the gods, and you, to see"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12532, line : "Brave Greece victorious, and her navy free:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12533, line : "Ah, no--the glorious combat you disclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12534, line : "And one black day clouds all her former fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12535, line : "Heavens! what a prodigy these eyes survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12536, line : "Unseen, unthought, till this amazing day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12537, line : "Fly we at length from Troy's oft-conquer'd bands?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12538, line : "And falls our fleet by such inglorious hands?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12539, line : "A rout undisciplined, a straggling train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12540, line : "Not born to glories of the dusty plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12541, line : "Like frighted fawns from hill to hill pursued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12542, line : "A prey to every savage of the wood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12543, line : "Shall these, so late who trembled at your name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12544, line : "Invade your camps, involve your ships in flame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12545, line : "A change so shameful, say, what cause has wrought?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12546, line : "The soldiers' baseness, or the general's fault?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12547, line : "Fools! will ye perish for your leader's vice;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12548, line : "The purchase infamy, and life the price?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12549, line : "'Tis not your cause, Achilles' injured fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12550, line : "Another's is the crime, but yours the shame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12551, line : "Grant that our chief offend through rage or lust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12552, line : "Must you be cowards, if your king's unjust?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12553, line : "Prevent this evil, and your country save:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12554, line : "Small thought retrieves the spirits of the brave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12555, line : "Think, and subdue! on dastards dead to fame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12556, line : "I waste no anger, for they feel no shame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12557, line : "But you, the pride, the flower of all our host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12558, line : "My heart weeps blood to see your glory lost!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12559, line : "Nor deem this day, this battle, all you lose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12560, line : "A day more black, a fate more vile, ensues."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12561, line : "Let each reflect, who prizes fame or breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12562, line : "On endless infamy, on instant death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12563, line : "For, lo! the fated time, the appointed shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12564, line : "Hark! the gates burst, the brazen barriers roar!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12565, line : "Impetuous Hector thunders at the wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12566, line : "The hour, the spot, to conquer, or to fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12568, line : "These words the Grecians' fainting hearts inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12569, line : "And listening armies catch the godlike fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12570, line : "Fix'd at his post was each bold Ajax found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12571, line : "With well-ranged squadrons strongly circled round:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12572, line : "So close their order, so disposed their fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12573, line : "As Pallas' self might view with fix'd delight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12574, line : "Or had the god of war inclined his eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12575, line : "The god of war had own'd a just surprise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12576, line : "A chosen phalanx, firm, resolved as fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12577, line : "Descending Hector and his battle wait."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12578, line : "An iron scene gleams dreadful o'er the fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12579, line : "Armour in armour lock'd, and shields in shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12580, line : "Spears lean on spears, on targets targets throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12581, line : "Helms stuck to helms, and man drove man along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12582, line : "The floating plumes unnumber'd wave above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12583, line : "As when an earthquake stirs the nodding grove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12584, line : "And levell'd at the skies with pointing rays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12585, line : "Their brandish'd lances at each motion blaze."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12587, line : "Thus breathing death, in terrible array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12588, line : "The close compacted legions urged their way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12589, line : "Fierce they drove on, impatient to destroy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12590, line : "Troy charged the first, and Hector first of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12591, line : "As from some mountain's craggy forehead torn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12592, line : "A rock's round fragment flies, with fury borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12593, line : "(Which from the stubborn stone a torrent rends,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12594, line : "Precipitate the ponderous mass descends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12595, line : "From steep to steep the rolling ruin bounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12596, line : "At every shock the crackling wood resounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12597, line : "Still gathering force, it smokes; and urged amain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12598, line : "Whirls, leaps, and thunders down, impetuous to the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12599, line : "There stops--so Hector. Their whole force he proved,(230)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12600, line : "Resistless when he raged, and, when he stopp'd, unmoved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12602, line : "On him the war is bent, the darts are shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12603, line : "And all their falchions wave around his head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12604, line : "Repulsed he stands, nor from his stand retires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12605, line : "But with repeated shouts his army fires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12606, line : "\"Trojans! be firm; this arm shall make your way"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12607, line : "Through yon square body, and that black array:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12608, line : "Stand, and my spear shall rout their scattering power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12609, line : "Strong as they seem, embattled like a tower;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12610, line : "For he that Juno's heavenly bosom warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12611, line : "The first of gods, this day inspires our arms.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12613, line : "He said; and roused the soul in every breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12614, line : "Urged with desire of fame, beyond the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12615, line : "Forth march'd Deiphobus; but, marching, held"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12616, line : "Before his wary steps his ample shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12617, line : "Bold Merion aim'd a stroke (nor aim'd it wide);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12618, line : "The glittering javelin pierced the tough bull-hide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12619, line : "But pierced not through: unfaithful to his hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12620, line : "The point broke short, and sparkled in the sand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12621, line : "The Trojan warrior, touch'd with timely fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12622, line : "On the raised orb to distance bore the spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12623, line : "The Greek, retreating, mourn'd his frustrate blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12624, line : "And cursed the treacherous lance that spared a foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12625, line : "Then to the ships with surly speed he went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12626, line : "To seek a surer javelin in his tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12628, line : "Meanwhile with rising rage the battle glows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12629, line : "The tumult thickens, and the clamour grows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12630, line : "By Teucer's arm the warlike Imbrius bleeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12631, line : "The son of Mentor, rich in generous steeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12632, line : "Ere yet to Troy the sons of Greece were led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12633, line : "In fair Pedaeus' verdant pastures bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12634, line : "The youth had dwelt, remote from war's alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12635, line : "And blest in bright Medesicaste's arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12636, line : "(This nymph, the fruit of Priam's ravish'd joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12637, line : "Allied the warrior to the house of Troy:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12638, line : "To Troy, when glory call'd his arms, he came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12639, line : "And match'd the bravest of her chiefs in fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12640, line : "With Priam's sons, a guardian of the throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12641, line : "He lived, beloved and honour'd as his own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12642, line : "Him Teucer pierced between the throat and ear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12643, line : "He groans beneath the Telamonian spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12644, line : "As from some far-seen mountain's airy crown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12645, line : "Subdued by steel, a tall ash tumbles down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12646, line : "And soils its verdant tresses on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12647, line : "So falls the youth; his arms the fall resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12648, line : "Then Teucer rushing to despoil the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12649, line : "From Hector's hand a shining javelin fled:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12650, line : "He saw, and shunn'd the death; the forceful dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12651, line : "Sung on, and pierced Amphimachus's heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12652, line : "Cteatus' son, of Neptune's forceful line;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12653, line : "Vain was his courage, and his race divine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12654, line : "Prostrate he falls; his clanging arms resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12655, line : "And his broad buckler thunders on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12656, line : "To seize his beamy helm the victor flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12657, line : "And just had fastened on the dazzling prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12658, line : "When Ajax' manly arm a javelin flung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12659, line : "Full on the shield's round boss the weapon rung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12660, line : "He felt the shock, nor more was doom'd to feel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12661, line : "Secure in mail, and sheath'd in shining steel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12662, line : "Repulsed he yields; the victor Greeks obtain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12663, line : "The spoils contested, and bear off the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12664, line : "Between the leaders of the Athenian line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12665, line : "(Stichius the brave, Menestheus the divine,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12666, line : "Deplored Amphimachus, sad object! lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12667, line : "Imbrius remains the fierce Ajaces' prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12668, line : "As two grim lions bear across the lawn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12669, line : "Snatch'd from devouring hounds, a slaughter'd fawn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12670, line : "In their fell jaws high-lifting through the wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12671, line : "And sprinkling all the shrubs with drops of blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12672, line : "So these, the chief: great Ajax from the dead"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12673, line : "Strips his bright arms; Oileus lops his head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12674, line : "Toss'd like a ball, and whirl'd in air away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12675, line : "At Hector's feet the gory visage lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12677, line : "The god of ocean, fired with stern disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12678, line : "And pierced with sorrow for his grandson slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12679, line : "Inspires the Grecian hearts, confirms their hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12680, line : "And breathes destruction on the Trojan bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12681, line : "Swift as a whirlwind rushing to the fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12682, line : "He finds the lance-famed Idomen of Crete,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12683, line : "His pensive brow the generous care express'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12684, line : "With which a wounded soldier touch'd his breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12685, line : "Whom in the chance of war a javelin tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12686, line : "And his sad comrades from the battle bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12687, line : "Him to the surgeons of the camp he sent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12688, line : "That office paid, he issued from his tent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12689, line : "Fierce for the fight: to whom the god begun,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12690, line : "In Thoas' voice, Andraemon's valiant son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12691, line : "Who ruled where Calydon's white rocks arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12692, line : "And Pleuron's chalky cliffs emblaze the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12694, line : "\"Where's now the imperious vaunt, the daring boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12695, line : "Of Greece victorious, and proud Ilion lost?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12697, line : "To whom the king: \"On Greece no blame be thrown;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12698, line : "Arms are her trade, and war is all her own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12699, line : "Her hardy heroes from the well-fought plains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12700, line : "Nor fear withholds, nor shameful sloth detains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12701, line : "'Tis heaven, alas! and Jove's all-powerful doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12702, line : "That far, far distant from our native home"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12703, line : "Wills us to fall inglorious! Oh, my friend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12704, line : "Once foremost in the fight, still prone to lend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12705, line : "Or arms or counsels, now perform thy best,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12706, line : "And what thou canst not singly, urge the rest.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12708, line : "Thus he: and thus the god whose force can make"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12709, line : "The solid globe's eternal basis shake:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12710, line : "\"Ah! never may he see his native land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12711, line : "But feed the vultures on this hateful strand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12712, line : "Who seeks ignobly in his ships to stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12713, line : "Nor dares to combat on this signal day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12714, line : "For this, behold! in horrid arms I shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12715, line : "And urge thy soul to rival acts with mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12716, line : "Together let us battle on the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12717, line : "Two, not the worst; nor even this succour vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12718, line : "Not vain the weakest, if their force unite;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12719, line : "But ours, the bravest have confess'd in fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12721, line : "This said, he rushes where the combat burns;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12722, line : "Swift to his tent the Cretan king returns:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12723, line : "From thence, two javelins glittering in his hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12724, line : "And clad in arms that lighten'd all the strand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12725, line : "Fierce on the foe the impetuous hero drove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12726, line : "Like lightning bursting from the arm of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12727, line : "Which to pale man the wrath of heaven declares,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12728, line : "Or terrifies the offending world with wars;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12729, line : "In streamy sparkles, kindling all the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12730, line : "From pole to pole the trail of glory flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12731, line : "Thus his bright armour o'er the dazzled throng"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12732, line : "Gleam'd dreadful, as the monarch flash'd along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12734, line : "Him, near his tent, Meriones attends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12735, line : "Whom thus he questions: \"Ever best of friends!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12736, line : "O say, in every art of battle skill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12737, line : "What holds thy courage from so brave a field?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12738, line : "On some important message art thou bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12739, line : "Or bleeds my friend by some unhappy wound?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12740, line : "Inglorious here, my soul abhors to stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12741, line : "And glows with prospects of th' approaching day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12743, line : "\"O prince! (Meriones replies) whose care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12744, line : "Leads forth the embattled sons of Crete to war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12745, line : "This speaks my grief: this headless lance I wield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12746, line : "The rest lies rooted in a Trojan shield.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12748, line : "To whom the Cretan: \"Enter, and receive"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12749, line : "The wonted weapons; those my tent can give;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12750, line : "Spears I have store, (and Trojan lances all,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12751, line : "That shed a lustre round the illumined wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12752, line : "Though I, disdainful of the distant war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12753, line : "Nor trust the dart, nor aim the uncertain spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12754, line : "Yet hand to hand I fight, and spoil the slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12755, line : "And thence these trophies, and these arms I gain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12756, line : "Enter, and see on heaps the helmets roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12757, line : "And high-hung spears, and shields that flame with gold.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12759, line : "\"Nor vain (said Merion) are our martial toils;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12760, line : "We too can boast of no ignoble spoils:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12761, line : "But those my ship contains; whence distant far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12762, line : "I fight conspicuous in the van of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12763, line : "What need I more? If any Greek there be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12764, line : "Who knows not Merion, I appeal to thee.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12766, line : "To this, Idomeneus: \"The fields of fight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12767, line : "Have proved thy valour, and unconquer'd might:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12768, line : "And were some ambush for the foes design'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12769, line : "Even there thy courage would not lag behind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12770, line : "In that sharp service, singled from the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12771, line : "The fear of each, or valour, stands confess'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12772, line : "No force, no firmness, the pale coward shows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12773, line : "He shifts his place: his colour comes and goes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12774, line : "A dropping sweat creeps cold on every part;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12775, line : "Against his bosom beats his quivering heart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12776, line : "Terror and death in his wild eye-balls stare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12777, line : "With chattering teeth he stands, and stiffening hair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12778, line : "And looks a bloodless image of despair!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12779, line : "Not so the brave--still dauntless, still the same,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12780, line : "Unchanged his colour, and unmoved his frame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12781, line : "Composed his thought, determined is his eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12782, line : "And fix'd his soul, to conquer or to die:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12783, line : "If aught disturb the tenour of his breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12784, line : "'Tis but the wish to strike before the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12786, line : "\"In such assays thy blameless worth is known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12787, line : "And every art of dangerous war thy own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12788, line : "By chance of fight whatever wounds you bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12789, line : "Those wounds were glorious all, and all before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12790, line : "Such as may teach, 'twas still thy brave delight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12791, line : "T'oppose thy bosom where thy foremost fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12792, line : "But why, like infants, cold to honour's charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12793, line : "Stand we to talk, when glory calls to arms?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12794, line : "Go--from my conquer'd spears the choicest take,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12795, line : "And to their owners send them nobly back.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12797, line : "Swift at the word bold Merion snatch'd a spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12798, line : "And, breathing slaughter, follow'd to the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12799, line : "So Mars armipotent invades the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12800, line : "(The wide destroyer of the race of man,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12801, line : "Terror, his best-beloved son, attends his course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12802, line : "Arm'd with stern boldness, and enormous force;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12803, line : "The pride of haughty warriors to confound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12804, line : "And lay the strength of tyrants on the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12805, line : "From Thrace they fly, call'd to the dire alarms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12806, line : "Of warring Phlegyans, and Ephyrian arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12807, line : "Invoked by both, relentless they dispose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12808, line : "To these glad conquest, murderous rout to those."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12809, line : "So march'd the leaders of the Cretan train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12810, line : "And their bright arms shot horror o'er the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12812, line : "Then first spake Merion: \"Shall we join the right,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12813, line : "Or combat in the centre of the fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12814, line : "Or to the left our wonted succour lend?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12815, line : "Hazard and fame all parts alike attend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12817, line : "\"Not in the centre (Idomen replied:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12818, line : "Our ablest chieftains the main battle guide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12819, line : "Each godlike Ajax makes that post his care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12820, line : "And gallant Teucer deals destruction there,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12821, line : "Skill'd or with shafts to gall the distant field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12822, line : "Or bear close battle on the sounding shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12823, line : "These can the rage of haughty Hector tame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12824, line : "Safe in their arms, the navy fears no flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12825, line : "Till Jove himself descends, his bolts to shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12826, line : "And hurl the blazing ruin at our head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12827, line : "Great must he be, of more than human birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12828, line : "Nor feed like mortals on the fruits of earth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12829, line : "Him neither rocks can crush, nor steel can wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12830, line : "Whom Ajax fells not on the ensanguined ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12831, line : "In standing fight he mates Achilles' force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12832, line : "Excell'd alone in swiftness in the course."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12833, line : "Then to the left our ready arms apply,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12834, line : "And live with glory, or with glory die.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12836, line : "He said: and Merion to th' appointed place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12837, line : "Fierce as the god of battles, urged his pace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12838, line : "Soon as the foe the shining chiefs beheld"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12839, line : "Rush like a fiery torrent o'er the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12840, line : "Their force embodied in a tide they pour;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12841, line : "The rising combat sounds along the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12842, line : "As warring winds, in Sirius' sultry reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12843, line : "From different quarters sweep the sandy plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12844, line : "On every side the dusty whirlwinds rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12845, line : "And the dry fields are lifted to the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12846, line : "Thus by despair, hope, rage, together driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12847, line : "Met the black hosts, and, meeting, darken'd heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12848, line : "All dreadful glared the iron face of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12849, line : "Bristled with upright spears, that flash'd afar;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12850, line : "Dire was the gleam of breastplates, helms, and shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12851, line : "And polish'd arms emblazed the flaming fields:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12852, line : "Tremendous scene! that general horror gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12853, line : "But touch'd with joy the bosoms of the brave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12855, line : "Saturn's great sons in fierce contention vied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12856, line : "And crowds of heroes in their anger died."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12857, line : "The sire of earth and heaven, by Thetis won"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12858, line : "To crown with glory Peleus' godlike son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12859, line : "Will'd not destruction to the Grecian powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12860, line : "But spared awhile the destined Trojan towers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12861, line : "While Neptune, rising from his azure main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12862, line : "Warr'd on the king of heaven with stern disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12863, line : "And breathed revenge, and fired the Grecian train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12864, line : "Gods of one source, of one ethereal race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12865, line : "Alike divine, and heaven their native place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12866, line : "But Jove the greater; first-born of the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12867, line : "And more than men, or gods, supremely wise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12868, line : "For this, of Jove's superior might afraid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12869, line : "Neptune in human form conceal'd his aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12870, line : "These powers enfold the Greek and Trojan train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12871, line : "In war and discord's adamantine chain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12872, line : "Indissolubly strong: the fatal tie"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12873, line : "Is stretch'd on both, and close compell'd they die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12875, line : "Dreadful in arms, and grown in combats grey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12876, line : "The bold Idomeneus controls the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12877, line : "First by his hand Othryoneus was slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12878, line : "Swell'd with false hopes, with mad ambition vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12879, line : "Call'd by the voice of war to martial fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12880, line : "From high Cabesus' distant walls he came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12881, line : "Cassandra's love he sought, with boasts of power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12882, line : "And promised conquest was the proffer'd dower."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12883, line : "The king consented, by his vaunts abused;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12884, line : "The king consented, but the fates refused."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12885, line : "Proud of himself, and of the imagined bride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12886, line : "The field he measured with a larger stride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12887, line : "Him as he stalk'd, the Cretan javelin found;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12888, line : "Vain was his breastplate to repel the wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12889, line : "His dream of glory lost, he plunged to hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12890, line : "His arms resounded as the boaster fell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12891, line : "The great Idomeneus bestrides the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12892, line : "\"And thus (he cries) behold thy promise sped!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12893, line : "Such is the help thy arms to Ilion bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12894, line : "And such the contract of the Phrygian king!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12895, line : "Our offers now, illustrious prince! receive;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12896, line : "For such an aid what will not Argos give?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12897, line : "To conquer Troy, with ours thy forces join,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12898, line : "And count Atrides' fairest daughter thine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12899, line : "Meantime, on further methods to advise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12900, line : "Come, follow to the fleet thy new allies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12901, line : "There hear what Greece has on her part to say.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12902, line : "He spoke, and dragg'd the gory corse away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12903, line : "This Asius view'd, unable to contain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12904, line : "Before his chariot warring on the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12905, line : "(His crowded coursers, to his squire consign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12906, line : "Impatient panted on his neck behind:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12907, line : "To vengeance rising with a sudden spring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12908, line : "He hoped the conquest of the Cretan king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12909, line : "The wary Cretan, as his foe drew near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12910, line : "Full on his throat discharged the forceful spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12911, line : "Beneath the chin the point was seen to glide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12912, line : "And glitter'd, extant at the further side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12913, line : "As when the mountain-oak, or poplar tall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12914, line : "Or pine, fit mast for some great admiral,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12915, line : "Groans to the oft-heaved axe, with many a wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12916, line : "Then spreads a length of ruin o'er the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12917, line : "So sunk proud Asius in that dreadful day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12918, line : "And stretch'd before his much-loved coursers lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12919, line : "He grinds the dust distain'd with streaming gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12920, line : "And, fierce in death, lies foaming on the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12921, line : "Deprived of motion, stiff with stupid fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12922, line : "Stands all aghast his trembling charioteer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12923, line : "Nor shuns the foe, nor turns the steeds away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12924, line : "But falls transfix'd, an unresisting prey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12925, line : "Pierced by Antilochus, he pants beneath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12926, line : "The stately car, and labours out his breath."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12927, line : "Thus Asius' steeds (their mighty master gone)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12928, line : "Remain the prize of Nestor's youthful son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12930, line : "Stabb'd at the sight, Deiphobus drew nigh,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12931, line : "And made, with force, the vengeful weapon fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12932, line : "The Cretan saw; and, stooping, caused to glance"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12933, line : "From his slope shield the disappointed lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12934, line : "Beneath the spacious targe, (a blazing round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12935, line : "Thick with bull-hides and brazen orbits bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12936, line : "On his raised arm by two strong braces stay'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12937, line : "He lay collected in defensive shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12938, line : "O'er his safe head the javelin idly sung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12939, line : "And on the tinkling verge more faintly rung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12940, line : "Even then the spear the vigorous arm confess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12941, line : "And pierced, obliquely, king Hypsenor's breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12942, line : "Warm'd in his liver, to the ground it bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12943, line : "The chief, his people's guardian now no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12945, line : "\"Not unattended (the proud Trojan cries)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12946, line : "Nor unrevenged, lamented Asius lies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12947, line : "For thee, through hell's black portals stand display'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12948, line : "This mate shall joy thy melancholy shade.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12950, line : "Heart-piercing anguish, at the haughty boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12951, line : "Touch'd every Greek, but Nestor's son the most."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12952, line : "Grieved as he was, his pious arms attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12953, line : "And his broad buckler shields his slaughter'd friend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12954, line : "Till sad Mecistheus and Alastor bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12955, line : "His honour'd body to the tented shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12957, line : "Nor yet from fight Idomeneus withdraws;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12958, line : "Resolved to perish in his country's cause,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12959, line : "Or find some foe, whom heaven and he shall doom"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12960, line : "To wail his fate in death's eternal gloom."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12961, line : "He sees Alcathous in the front aspire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12962, line : "Great Ćsyetes was the hero's sire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12963, line : "His spouse Hippodame, divinely fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12964, line : "Anchises' eldest hope, and darling care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12965, line : "Who charm'd her parents' and her husband's heart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12966, line : "With beauty, sense, and every work of art:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12967, line : "He once of Ilion's youth the loveliest boy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12968, line : "The fairest she of all the fair of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12969, line : "By Neptune now the hapless hero dies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12970, line : "Who covers with a cloud those beauteous eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12971, line : "And fetters every limb: yet bent to meet"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12972, line : "His fate he stands; nor shuns the lance of Crete."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12973, line : "Fix'd as some column, or deep-rooted oak,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12974, line : "While the winds sleep; his breast received the stroke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12975, line : "Before the ponderous stroke his corslet yields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12976, line : "Long used to ward the death in fighting fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12977, line : "The riven armour sends a jarring sound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12978, line : "His labouring heart heaves with so strong a bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12979, line : "The long lance shakes, and vibrates in the wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12980, line : "Fast flowing from its source, as prone he lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12981, line : "Life's purple tide impetuous gush'd away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12983, line : "Then Idomen, insulting o'er the slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12984, line : "\"Behold, Deiphobus! nor vaunt in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12985, line : "See! on one Greek three Trojan ghosts attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12986, line : "This, my third victim, to the shades I send."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12987, line : "Approaching now thy boasted might approve,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12988, line : "And try the prowess of the seed of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12989, line : "From Jove, enamour'd of a mortal dame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12990, line : "Great Minos, guardian of his country, came:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12991, line : "Deucalion, blameless prince, was Minos' heir;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12992, line : "His first-born I, the third from Jupiter:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12993, line : "O'er spacious Crete, and her bold sons, I reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12994, line : "And thence my ships transport me through the main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12995, line : "Lord of a host, o'er all my host I shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12996, line : "A scourge to thee, thy father, and thy line.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12998, line : "The Trojan heard; uncertain or to meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 12999, line : "Alone, with venturous arms the king of Crete,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13000, line : "Or seek auxiliar force; at length decreed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13001, line : "To call some hero to partake the deed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13002, line : "Forthwith Ćneas rises to his thought:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13003, line : "For him in Troy's remotest lines he sought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13004, line : "Where he, incensed at partial Priam, stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13005, line : "And sees superior posts in meaner hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13006, line : "To him, ambitious of so great an aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13007, line : "The bold Deiphobus approach'd, and said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13009, line : "\"Now, Trojan prince, employ thy pious arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13010, line : "If e'er thy bosom felt fair honour's charms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13011, line : "Alcathous dies, thy brother and thy friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13012, line : "Come, and the warrior's loved remains defend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13013, line : "Beneath his cares thy early youth was train'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13014, line : "One table fed you, and one roof contain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13015, line : "This deed to fierce Idomeneus we owe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13016, line : "Haste, and revenge it on th' insulting foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13018, line : "Ćneas heard, and for a space resign'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13019, line : "To tender pity all his manly mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13020, line : "Then rising in his rage, he burns to fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13021, line : "The Greek awaits him with collected might."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13022, line : "As the fell boar, on some rough mountain's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13023, line : "Arm'd with wild terrors, and to slaughter bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13024, line : "When the loud rustics rise, and shout from far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13025, line : "Attends the tumult, and expects the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13026, line : "O'er his bent back the bristly horrors rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13027, line : "Fires stream in lightning from his sanguine eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13028, line : "His foaming tusks both dogs and men engage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13029, line : "But most his hunters rouse his mighty rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13030, line : "So stood Idomeneus, his javelin shook,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13031, line : "And met the Trojan with a lowering look."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13032, line : "Antilochus, Deipyrus, were near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13033, line : "The youthful offspring of the god of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13034, line : "Merion, and Aphareus, in field renown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13035, line : "To these the warrior sent his voice around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13036, line : "\"Fellows in arms! your timely aid unite;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13037, line : "Lo, great Ćneas rushes to the fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13038, line : "Sprung from a god, and more than mortal bold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13039, line : "He fresh in youth, and I in arms grown old."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13040, line : "Else should this hand, this hour decide the strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13041, line : "The great dispute, of glory, or of life.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13043, line : "He spoke, and all, as with one soul, obey'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13044, line : "Their lifted bucklers cast a dreadful shade"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13045, line : "Around the chief. Ćneas too demands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13046, line : "Th' assisting forces of his native bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13047, line : "Paris, Deiphobus, Agenor, join;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13048, line : "(Co-aids and captains of the Trojan line;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13049, line : "In order follow all th' embodied train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13050, line : "Like Ida's flocks proceeding o'er the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13051, line : "Before his fleecy care, erect and bold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13052, line : "Stalks the proud ram, the father of the bold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13053, line : "With joy the swain surveys them, as he leads"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13054, line : "To the cool fountains, through the well-known meads:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13055, line : "So joys Ćneas, as his native band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13056, line : "Moves on in rank, and stretches o'er the land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13058, line : "Round dread Alcathous now the battle rose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13059, line : "On every side the steely circle grows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13060, line : "Now batter'd breast-plates and hack'd helmets ring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13061, line : "And o'er their heads unheeded javelins sing."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13062, line : "Above the rest, two towering chiefs appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13063, line : "There great Idomeneus, Ćneas here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13064, line : "Like gods of war, dispensing fate, they stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13065, line : "And burn'd to drench the ground with mutual blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13066, line : "The Trojan weapon whizz'd along in air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13067, line : "The Cretan saw, and shunn'd the brazen spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13068, line : "Sent from an arm so strong, the missive wood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13069, line : "Stuck deep in earth, and quiver'd where it stood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13070, line : "But OEnomas received the Cretan's stroke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13071, line : "The forceful spear his hollow corslet broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13072, line : "It ripp'd his belly with a ghastly wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13073, line : "And roll'd the smoking entrails on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13074, line : "Stretch'd on the plain, he sobs away his breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13075, line : "And, furious, grasps the bloody dust in death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13076, line : "The victor from his breast the weapon tears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13077, line : "His spoils he could not, for the shower of spears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13078, line : "Though now unfit an active war to wage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13079, line : "Heavy with cumbrous arms, stiff with cold age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13080, line : "His listless limbs unable for the course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13081, line : "In standing fight he yet maintains his force;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13082, line : "Till faint with labour, and by foes repell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13083, line : "His tired slow steps he drags from off the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13084, line : "Deiphobus beheld him as he pass'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13085, line : "And, fired with hate, a parting javelin cast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13086, line : "The javelin err'd, but held its course along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13087, line : "And pierced Ascalaphus, the brave and young:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13088, line : "The son of Mars fell gasping on the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13089, line : "And gnash'd the dust, all bloody with his wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13091, line : "Nor knew the furious father of his fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13092, line : "High-throned amidst the great Olympian hall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13093, line : "On golden clouds th' immortal synod sate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13094, line : "Detain'd from bloody war by Jove and Fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13096, line : "Now, where in dust the breathless hero lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13097, line : "For slain Ascalaphus commenced the fray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13098, line : "Deiphobus to seize his helmet flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13099, line : "And from his temples rends the glittering prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13100, line : "Valiant as Mars, Meriones drew near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13101, line : "And on his loaded arm discharged his spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13102, line : "He drops the weight, disabled with the pain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13103, line : "The hollow helmet rings against the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13104, line : "Swift as a vulture leaping on his prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13105, line : "From his torn arm the Grecian rent away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13106, line : "The reeking javelin, and rejoin'd his friends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13107, line : "His wounded brother good Polites tends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13108, line : "Around his waist his pious arms he threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13109, line : "And from the rage of battle gently drew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13110, line : "Him his swift coursers, on his splendid car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13111, line : "Rapt from the lessening thunder of the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13112, line : "To Troy they drove him, groaning from the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13113, line : "And sprinkling, as he pass'd, the sands with gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13115, line : "Meanwhile fresh slaughter bathes the sanguine ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13116, line : "Heaps fall on heaps, and heaven and earth resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13117, line : "Bold Aphareus by great Ćneas bled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13118, line : "As toward the chief he turn'd his daring head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13119, line : "He pierced his throat; the bending head, depress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13120, line : "Beneath his helmet, nods upon his breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13121, line : "His shield reversed o'er the fallen warrior lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13122, line : "And everlasting slumber seals his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13123, line : "Antilochus, as Thoon turn'd him round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13124, line : "Transpierced his back with a dishonest wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13125, line : "The hollow vein, that to the neck extends"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13126, line : "Along the chine, his eager javelin rends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13127, line : "Supine he falls, and to his social train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13128, line : "Spreads his imploring arms, but spreads in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13129, line : "Th' exulting victor, leaping where he lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13130, line : "From his broad shoulders tore the spoils away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13131, line : "His time observed; for closed by foes around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13132, line : "On all sides thick the peals of arms resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13133, line : "His shield emboss'd the ringing storm sustains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13134, line : "But he impervious and untouch'd remains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13135, line : "(Great Neptune's care preserved from hostile rage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13136, line : "This youth, the joy of Nestor's glorious age.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13137, line : "In arms intrepid, with the first he fought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13138, line : "Faced every foe, and every danger sought;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13139, line : "His winged lance, resistless as the wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13140, line : "Obeys each motion of the master's mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13141, line : "Restless it flies, impatient to be free,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13142, line : "And meditates the distant enemy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13143, line : "The son of Asius, Adamas, drew near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13144, line : "And struck his target with the brazen spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13145, line : "Fierce in his front: but Neptune wards the blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13146, line : "And blunts the javelin of th' eluded foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13147, line : "In the broad buckler half the weapon stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13148, line : "Splinter'd on earth flew half the broken wood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13149, line : "Disarm'd, he mingled in the Trojan crew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13150, line : "But Merion's spear o'ertook him as he flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13151, line : "Deep in the belly's rim an entrance found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13152, line : "Where sharp the pang, and mortal is the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13153, line : "Bending he fell, and doubled to the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13154, line : "Lay panting. Thus an ox in fetters tied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13155, line : "While death's strong pangs distend his labouring side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13156, line : "His bulk enormous on the field displays;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13157, line : "His heaving heart beats thick as ebbing life decays."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13158, line : "The spear the conqueror from his body drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13159, line : "And death's dim shadows swarm before his view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13160, line : "Next brave Deipyrus in dust was laid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13161, line : "King Helenus waved high the Thracian blade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13162, line : "And smote his temples with an arm so strong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13163, line : "The helm fell off, and roll'd amid the throng:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13164, line : "There for some luckier Greek it rests a prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13165, line : "For dark in death the godlike owner lies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13166, line : "Raging with grief, great Menelaus burns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13167, line : "And fraught with vengeance, to the victor turns:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13168, line : "That shook the ponderous lance, in act to throw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13169, line : "And this stood adverse with the bended bow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13170, line : "Full on his breast the Trojan arrow fell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13171, line : "But harmless bounded from the plated steel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13172, line : "As on some ample barn's well harden'd floor,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13173, line : "(The winds collected at each open door,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13174, line : "While the broad fan with force is whirl'd around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13175, line : "Light leaps the golden grain, resulting from the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13176, line : "So from the steel that guards Atrides' heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13177, line : "Repell'd to distance flies the bounding dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13178, line : "Atrides, watchful of the unwary foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13179, line : "Pierced with his lance the hand that grasp'd the bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13180, line : "And nailed it to the yew: the wounded hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13181, line : "Trail'd the long lance that mark'd with blood the sand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13182, line : "But good Agenor gently from the wound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13183, line : "The spear solicits, and the bandage bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13184, line : "A sling's soft wool, snatch'd from a soldier's side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13185, line : "At once the tent and ligature supplied."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13187, line : "Behold! Pisander, urged by fate's decree,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13188, line : "Springs through the ranks to fall, and fall by thee,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13189, line : "Great Menelaus! to enchance thy fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13190, line : "High-towering in the front, the warrior came."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13191, line : "First the sharp lance was by Atrides thrown;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13192, line : "The lance far distant by the winds was blown."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13193, line : "Nor pierced Pisander through Atrides' shield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13194, line : "Pisander's spear fell shiver'd on the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13195, line : "Not so discouraged, to the future blind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13196, line : "Vain dreams of conquest swell his haughty mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13197, line : "Dauntless he rushes where the Spartan lord"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13198, line : "Like lightning brandish'd his far beaming sword."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13199, line : "His left arm high opposed the shining shield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13200, line : "His right beneath, the cover'd pole-axe held;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13201, line : "(An olive's cloudy grain the handle made,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13202, line : "Distinct with studs, and brazen was the blade;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13203, line : "This on the helm discharged a noble blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13204, line : "The plume dropp'd nodding to the plain below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13205, line : "Shorn from the crest. Atrides waved his steel:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13206, line : "Deep through his front the weighty falchion fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13207, line : "The crashing bones before its force gave way;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13208, line : "In dust and blood the groaning hero lay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13209, line : "Forced from their ghastly orbs, and spouting gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13210, line : "The clotted eye-balls tumble on the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13211, line : "And fierce Atrides spurn'd him as he bled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13212, line : "Tore off his arms, and, loud-exulting, said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13214, line : "\"Thus, Trojans, thus, at length be taught to fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13215, line : "O race perfidious, who delight in war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13216, line : "Already noble deeds ye have perform'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13217, line : "A princess raped transcends a navy storm'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13218, line : "In such bold feats your impious might approve,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13219, line : "Without th' assistance, or the fear of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13220, line : "The violated rites, the ravish'd dame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13221, line : "Our heroes slaughter'd and our ships on flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13222, line : "Crimes heap'd on crimes, shall bend your glory down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13223, line : "And whelm in ruins yon flagitious town."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13224, line : "O thou, great father! lord of earth and skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13225, line : "Above the thought of man, supremely wise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13226, line : "If from thy hand the fates of mortals flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13227, line : "From whence this favour to an impious foe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13228, line : "A godless crew, abandon'd and unjust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13229, line : "Still breathing rapine, violence, and lust?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13230, line : "The best of things, beyond their measure, cloy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13231, line : "Sleep's balmy blessing, love's endearing joy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13232, line : "The feast, the dance; whate'er mankind desire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13233, line : "Even the sweet charms of sacred numbers tire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13234, line : "But Troy for ever reaps a dire delight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13235, line : "In thirst of slaughter, and in lust of fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13237, line : "This said, he seized (while yet the carcase heaved)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13238, line : "The bloody armour, which his train received:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13239, line : "Then sudden mix'd among the warring crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13240, line : "And the bold son of Pylaemenes slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13241, line : "Harpalion had through Asia travell'd far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13242, line : "Following his martial father to the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13243, line : "Through filial love he left his native shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13244, line : "Never, ah, never to behold it more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13245, line : "His unsuccessful spear he chanced to fling"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13246, line : "Against the target of the Spartan king;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13247, line : "Thus of his lance disarm'd, from death he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13248, line : "And turns around his apprehensive eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13249, line : "Him, through the hip transpiercing as he fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13250, line : "The shaft of Merion mingled with the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13251, line : "Beneath the bone the glancing point descends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13252, line : "And, driving down, the swelling bladder rends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13253, line : "Sunk in his sad companions' arms he lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13254, line : "And in short pantings sobb'd his soul away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13255, line : "(Like some vile worm extended on the ground;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13256, line : "While life's red torrent gush'd from out the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13258, line : "Him on his car the Paphlagonian train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13259, line : "In slow procession bore from off the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13260, line : "The pensive father, father now no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13261, line : "Attends the mournful pomp along the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13262, line : "And unavailing tears profusely shed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13263, line : "And, unrevenged, deplored his offspring dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13265, line : "Paris from far the moving sight beheld,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13266, line : "With pity soften'd and with fury swell'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13267, line : "His honour'd host, a youth of matchless grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13268, line : "And loved of all the Paphlagonian race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13269, line : "With his full strength he bent his angry bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13270, line : "And wing'd the feather'd vengeance at the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13271, line : "A chief there was, the brave Euchenor named,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13272, line : "For riches much, and more for virtue famed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13273, line : "Who held his seat in Corinth's stately town;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13274, line : "Polydus' son, a seer of old renown."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13275, line : "Oft had the father told his early doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13276, line : "By arms abroad, or slow disease at home:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13277, line : "He climb'd his vessel, prodigal of breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13278, line : "And chose the certain glorious path to death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13279, line : "Beneath his ear the pointed arrow went;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13280, line : "The soul came issuing at the narrow vent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13281, line : "His limbs, unnerved, drop useless on the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13282, line : "And everlasting darkness shades him round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13284, line : "Nor knew great Hector how his legions yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13285, line : "(Wrapp'd in the cloud and tumult of the field:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13286, line : "Wide on the left the force of Greece commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13287, line : "And conquest hovers o'er th' Achaian bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13288, line : "With such a tide superior virtue sway'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13289, line : "And he that shakes the solid earth gave aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13290, line : "But in the centre Hector fix'd remain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13291, line : "Where first the gates were forced, and bulwarks gain'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13292, line : "There, on the margin of the hoary deep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13293, line : "(Their naval station where the Ajaces keep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13294, line : "And where low walls confine the beating tides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13295, line : "Whose humble barrier scarce the foe divides;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13296, line : "Where late in fight both foot and horse engaged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13297, line : "And all the thunder of the battle raged,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13298, line : "There join'd, the whole Boeotian strength remains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13299, line : "The proud Iaonians with their sweeping trains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13300, line : "Locrians and Phthians, and th' Epaean force;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13301, line : "But join'd, repel not Hector's fiery course."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13302, line : "The flower of Athens, Stichius, Phidas, led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13303, line : "Bias and great Menestheus at their head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13304, line : "Meges the strong the Epaean bands controll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13305, line : "And Dracius prudent, and Amphion bold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13306, line : "The Phthians, Medon, famed for martial might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13307, line : "And brave Podarces, active in the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13308, line : "This drew from Phylacus his noble line;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13309, line : "Iphiclus' son: and that (Oileus) thine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13310, line : "(Young Ajax' brother, by a stolen embrace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13311, line : "He dwelt far distant from his native place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13312, line : "By his fierce step-dame from his father's reign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13313, line : "Expell'd and exiled for her brother slain:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13314, line : "These rule the Phthians, and their arms employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13315, line : "Mix'd with Boeotians, on the shores of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13317, line : "Now side by side, with like unwearied care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13318, line : "Each Ajax laboured through the field of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13319, line : "So when two lordly bulls, with equal toil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13320, line : "Force the bright ploughshare through the fallow soil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13321, line : "Join'd to one yoke, the stubborn earth they tear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13322, line : "And trace large furrows with the shining share;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13323, line : "O'er their huge limbs the foam descends in snow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13324, line : "And streams of sweat down their sour foreheads flow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13325, line : "A train of heroes followed through the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13326, line : "Who bore by turns great Ajax' sevenfold shield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13327, line : "Whene'er he breathed, remissive of his might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13328, line : "Tired with the incessant slaughters of the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13329, line : "No following troops his brave associate grace:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13330, line : "In close engagement an unpractised race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13331, line : "The Locrian squadrons nor the javelin wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13332, line : "Nor bear the helm, nor lift the moony shield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13333, line : "But skill'd from far the flying shaft to wing,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13334, line : "Or whirl the sounding pebble from the sling,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13335, line : "Dexterous with these they aim a certain wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13336, line : "Or fell the distant warrior to the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13337, line : "Thus in the van the Telamonian train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13338, line : "Throng'd in bright arms, a pressing fight maintain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13339, line : "Far in the rear the Locrian archers lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13340, line : "Whose stones and arrows intercept the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13341, line : "The mingled tempest on the foes they pour;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13342, line : "Troy's scattering orders open to the shower."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13344, line : "Now had the Greeks eternal fame acquired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13345, line : "And the gall'd Ilians to their walls retired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13346, line : "But sage Polydamas, discreetly brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13347, line : "Address'd great Hector, and this counsel gave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13349, line : "\"Though great in all, thou seem'st averse to lend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13350, line : "Impartial audience to a faithful friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13351, line : "To gods and men thy matchless worth is known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13352, line : "And every art of glorious war thy own;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13353, line : "But in cool thought and counsel to excel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13354, line : "How widely differs this from warring well!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13355, line : "Content with what the bounteous gods have given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13356, line : "Seek not alone to engross the gifts of Heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13357, line : "To some the powers of bloody war belong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13358, line : "To some sweet music and the charm of song;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13359, line : "To few, and wondrous few, has Jove assign'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13360, line : "A wise, extensive, all-considering mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13361, line : "Their guardians these, the nations round confess,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13362, line : "And towns and empires for their safety bless."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13363, line : "If Heaven have lodged this virtue in my breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13364, line : "Attend, O Hector! what I judge the best,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13365, line : "See, as thou mov'st, on dangers dangers spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13366, line : "And war's whole fury burns around thy head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13367, line : "Behold! distress'd within yon hostile wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13368, line : "How many Trojans yield, disperse, or fall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13369, line : "What troops, out-number'd, scarce the war maintain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13370, line : "And what brave heroes at the ships lie slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13371, line : "Here cease thy fury: and, the chiefs and kings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13372, line : "Convoked to council, weigh the sum of things."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13373, line : "Whether (the gods succeeding our desires)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13374, line : "To yon tall ships to bear the Trojan fires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13375, line : "Or quit the fleet, and pass unhurt away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13376, line : "Contented with the conquest of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13377, line : "I fear, I fear, lest Greece, not yet undone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13378, line : "Pay the large debt of last revolving sun;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13379, line : "Achilles, great Achilles, yet remains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13380, line : "On yonder decks, and yet o'erlooks the plains!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13382, line : "The counsel pleased; and Hector, with a bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13383, line : "Leap'd from his chariot on the trembling ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13384, line : "Swift as he leap'd his clanging arms resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13385, line : "\"To guard this post (he cried) thy art employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13386, line : "And here detain the scatter'd youth of Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13387, line : "Where yonder heroes faint, I bend my way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13388, line : "And hasten back to end the doubtful day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13390, line : "This said, the towering chief prepares to go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13391, line : "Shakes his white plumes that to the breezes flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13392, line : "And seems a moving mountain topp'd with snow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13393, line : "Through all his host, inspiring force, he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13394, line : "And bids anew the martial thunder rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13395, line : "To Panthus' son, at Hector's high command"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13396, line : "Haste the bold leaders of the Trojan band:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13397, line : "But round the battlements, and round the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13398, line : "For many a chief he look'd, but look'd in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13399, line : "Deiphobus, nor Helenus the seer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13400, line : "Nor Asius' son, nor Asius' self appear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13401, line : "For these were pierced with many a ghastly wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13402, line : "Some cold in death, some groaning on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13403, line : "Some low in dust, (a mournful object) lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13404, line : "High on the wall some breathed their souls away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13406, line : "Far on the left, amid the throng he found"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13407, line : "(Cheering the troops, and dealing deaths around)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13408, line : "The graceful Paris; whom, with fury moved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13409, line : "Opprobrious thus, th' impatient chief reproved:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13411, line : "\"Ill-fated Paris! slave to womankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13412, line : "As smooth of face as fraudulent of mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13413, line : "Where is Deiphobus, where Asius gone?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13414, line : "The godlike father, and th' intrepid son?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13415, line : "The force of Helenus, dispensing fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13416, line : "And great Othryoneus, so fear'd of late?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13417, line : "Black fate hang's o'er thee from th' avenging gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13418, line : "Imperial Troy from her foundations nods;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13419, line : "Whelm'd in thy country's ruin shalt thou fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13420, line : "And one devouring vengeance swallow all.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13422, line : "When Paris thus: \"My brother and my friend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13423, line : "Thy warm impatience makes thy tongue offend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13424, line : "In other battles I deserved thy blame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13425, line : "Though then not deedless, nor unknown to fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13426, line : "But since yon rampart by thy arms lay low,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13427, line : "I scatter'd slaughter from my fatal bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13428, line : "The chiefs you seek on yonder shore lie slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13429, line : "Of all those heroes, two alone remain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13430, line : "Deiphobus, and Helenus the seer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13431, line : "Each now disabled by a hostile spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13432, line : "Go then, successful, where thy soul inspires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13433, line : "This heart and hand shall second all thy fires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13434, line : "What with this arm I can, prepare to know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13435, line : "Till death for death be paid, and blow for blow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13436, line : "But 'tis not ours, with forces not our own"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13437, line : "To combat: strength is of the gods alone.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13438, line : "These words the hero's angry mind assuage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13439, line : "Then fierce they mingle where the thickest rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13440, line : "Around Polydamas, distain'd with blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13441, line : "Cebrion, Phalces, stern Orthaeus stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13442, line : "Palmus, with Polypoetes the divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13443, line : "And two bold brothers of Hippotion's line"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13444, line : "(Who reach'd fair Ilion, from Ascania far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13445, line : "The former day; the next engaged in war)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13446, line : "As when from gloomy clouds a whirlwind springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13447, line : "That bears Jove's thunder on its dreadful wings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13448, line : "Wide o'er the blasted fields the tempest sweeps;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13449, line : "Then, gather'd, settles on the hoary deeps;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13450, line : "The afflicted deeps tumultuous mix and roar;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13451, line : "The waves behind impel the waves before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13452, line : "Wide rolling, foaming high, and tumbling to the shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13453, line : "Thus rank on rank, the thick battalions throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13454, line : "Chief urged on chief, and man drove man along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13455, line : "Far o'er the plains, in dreadful order bright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13456, line : "The brazen arms reflect a beamy light:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13457, line : "Full in the blazing van great Hector shined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13458, line : "Like Mars commission'd to confound mankind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13459, line : "Before him flaming his enormous shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13460, line : "Like the broad sun, illumined all the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13461, line : "His nodding helm emits a streamy ray;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13462, line : "His piercing eyes through all the battle stray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13463, line : "And, while beneath his targe he flash'd along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13464, line : "Shot terrors round, that wither'd e'en the strong."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13466, line : "Thus stalk'd he, dreadful; death was in his look:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13467, line : "Whole nations fear'd; but not an Argive shook."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13468, line : "The towering Ajax, with an ample stride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13469, line : "Advanced the first, and thus the chief defied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13471, line : "\"Hector! come on; thy empty threats forbear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13472, line : "'Tis not thy arm, 'tis thundering Jove we fear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13473, line : "The skill of war to us not idly given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13474, line : "Lo! Greece is humbled, not by Troy, but Heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13475, line : "Vain are the hopes that haughty mind imparts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13476, line : "To force our fleet: the Greeks have hands and hearts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13477, line : "Long ere in flames our lofty navy fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13478, line : "Your boasted city, and your god-built wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13479, line : "Shall sink beneath us, smoking on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13480, line : "And spread a long unmeasured ruin round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13481, line : "The time shall come, when, chased along the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13482, line : "Even thou shalt call on Jove, and call in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13483, line : "Even thou shalt wish, to aid thy desperate course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13484, line : "The wings of falcons for thy flying horse;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13485, line : "Shalt run, forgetful of a warrior's fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13486, line : "While clouds of friendly dust conceal thy shame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13488, line : "As thus he spoke, behold, in open view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13489, line : "On sounding wings a dexter eagle flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13490, line : "To Jove's glad omen all the Grecians rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13491, line : "And hail, with shouts, his progress through the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13492, line : "Far-echoing clamours bound from side to side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13493, line : "They ceased; and thus the chief of Troy replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13495, line : "\"From whence this menace, this insulting strain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13496, line : "Enormous boaster! doom'd to vaunt in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13497, line : "So may the gods on Hector life bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13498, line : "(Not that short life which mortals lead below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13499, line : "But such as those of Jove's high lineage born,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13500, line : "The blue-eyed maid, or he that gilds the morn,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13501, line : "As this decisive day shall end the fame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13502, line : "Of Greece, and Argos be no more a name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13503, line : "And thou, imperious! if thy madness wait"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13504, line : "The lance of Hector, thou shalt meet thy fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13505, line : "That giant-corse, extended on the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13506, line : "Shall largely feast the fowls with fat and gore.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13508, line : "He said; and like a lion stalk'd along:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13509, line : "With shouts incessant earth and ocean rung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13510, line : "Sent from his following host: the Grecian train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13511, line : "With answering thunders fill'd the echoing plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13512, line : "A shout that tore heaven's concave, and, above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13513, line : "Shook the fix'd splendours of the throne of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13515, line : "[Illustration: GREEK EARRINGS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13517, line : "GREEK EARRINGS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13523, line : "BOOK XIV."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13526, line : "ARGUMENT.(231)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13528, line : "JUNO DECEIVES JUPITER BY THE GIRDLE OF VENUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13530, line : "Nestor, sitting at the table with Machaon, is alarmed with the increasing"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13531, line : "clamour of war, and hastens to Agamemnon; on his way he meets that prince"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13532, line : "with Diomed and Ulysses, whom he informs of the extremity of the danger."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13533, line : "Agamemnon proposes to make their escape by night, which Ulysses"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13534, line : "withstands; to which Diomed adds his advice, that, wounded as they were,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13535, line : "they should go forth and encourage the army with their presence, which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13536, line : "advice is pursued. Juno, seeing the partiality of Jupiter to the Trojans,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13537, line : "forms a design to over-reach him: she sets off her charms with the utmost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13538, line : "care, and (the more surely to enchant him) obtains the magic girdle of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13539, line : "Venus. She then applies herself to the god of sleep, and, with some"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13540, line : "difficulty, persuades him to seal the eyes of Jupiter: this done, she goes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13541, line : "to mount Ida, where the god, at first sight, is ravished with her beauty,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13542, line : "sinks in her embraces, and is laid asleep. Neptune takes advantage of his"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13543, line : "slumber, and succours the Greeks: Hector is struck to the ground with a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13544, line : "prodigious stone by Ajax, and carried off from the battle: several actions"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13545, line : "succeed, till the Trojans, much distressed, are obliged to give way: the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13546, line : "lesser Ajax signalizes himself in a particular manner."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13548, line : "But not the genial feast, nor flowing bowl,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13549, line : "Could charm the cares of Nestor's watchful soul;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13550, line : "His startled ears the increasing cries attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13551, line : "Then thus, impatient, to his wounded friend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13553, line : "\"What new alarm, divine Machaon, say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13554, line : "What mix'd events attend this mighty day?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13555, line : "Hark! how the shouts divide, and how they meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13556, line : "And now come full, and thicken to the fleet!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13557, line : "Here with the cordial draught dispel thy care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13558, line : "Let Hecamede the strengthening bath prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13559, line : "Refresh thy wound, and cleanse the clotted gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13560, line : "While I the adventures of the day explore.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13562, line : "He said: and, seizing Thrasymedes' shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13563, line : "(His valiant offspring,) hasten'd to the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13564, line : "(That day the son his father's buckler bore;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13565, line : "Then snatch'd a lance, and issued from the door."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13566, line : "Soon as the prospect open'd to his view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13567, line : "His wounded eyes the scene of sorrow knew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13568, line : "Dire disarray! the tumult of the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13569, line : "The wall in ruins, and the Greeks in flight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13570, line : "As when old ocean's silent surface sleeps,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13571, line : "The waves just heaving on the purple deeps:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13572, line : "While yet the expected tempest hangs on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13573, line : "Weighs down the cloud, and blackens in the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13574, line : "The mass of waters will no wind obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13575, line : "Jove sends one gust, and bids them roll away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13576, line : "While wavering counsels thus his mind engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13577, line : "Fluctuates in doubtful thought the Pylian sage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13578, line : "To join the host, or to the general haste;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13579, line : "Debating long, he fixes on the last:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13580, line : "Yet, as he moves, the sight his bosom warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13581, line : "The field rings dreadful with the clang of arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13582, line : "The gleaming falchions flash, the javelins fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13583, line : "Blows echo blows, and all or kill or die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13585, line : "Him, in his march, the wounded princes meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13586, line : "By tardy steps ascending from the fleet:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13587, line : "The king of men, Ulysses the divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13588, line : "And who to Tydeus owes his noble line.(232)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13589, line : "(Their ships at distance from the battle stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13590, line : "In lines advanced along the shelving strand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13591, line : "Whose bay, the fleet unable to contain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13592, line : "At length; beside the margin of the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13593, line : "Rank above rank, the crowded ships they moor:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13594, line : "Who landed first, lay highest on the shore.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13595, line : "Supported on the spears, they took their way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13596, line : "Unfit to fight, but anxious for the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13597, line : "Nestor's approach alarm'd each Grecian breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13598, line : "Whom thus the general of the host address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13600, line : "\"O grace and glory of the Achaian name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13601, line : "What drives thee, Nestor, from the field of fame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13602, line : "Shall then proud Hector see his boast fulfill'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13603, line : "Our fleets in ashes, and our heroes kill'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13604, line : "Such was his threat, ah! now too soon made good,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13605, line : "On many a Grecian bosom writ in blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13606, line : "Is every heart inflamed with equal rage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13607, line : "Against your king, nor will one chief engage?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13608, line : "And have I lived to see with mournful eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13609, line : "In every Greek a new Achilles rise?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13611, line : "Gerenian Nestor then: \"So fate has will'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13612, line : "And all-confirming time has fate fulfill'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13613, line : "Not he that thunders from the aerial bower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13614, line : "Not Jove himself, upon the past has power."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13615, line : "The wall, our late inviolable bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13616, line : "And best defence, lies smoking on the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13617, line : "Even to the ships their conquering arms extend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13618, line : "And groans of slaughter'd Greeks to heaven ascend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13619, line : "On speedy measures then employ your thought"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13620, line : "In such distress! if counsel profit aught:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13621, line : "Arms cannot much: though Mars our souls incite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13622, line : "These gaping wounds withhold us from the fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13624, line : "To him the monarch: \"That our army bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13625, line : "That Troy triumphant our high fleet ascends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13626, line : "And that the rampart, late our surest trust"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13627, line : "And best defence, lies smoking in the dust;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13628, line : "All this from Jove's afflictive hand we bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13629, line : "Who, far from Argos, wills our ruin here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13630, line : "Past are the days when happier Greece was blest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13631, line : "And all his favour, all his aid confess'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13632, line : "Now heaven averse, our hands from battle ties,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13633, line : "And lifts the Trojan glory to the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13634, line : "Cease we at length to waste our blood in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13635, line : "And launch what ships lie nearest to the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13636, line : "Leave these at anchor, till the coming night:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13637, line : "Then, if impetuous Troy forbear the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13638, line : "Bring all to sea, and hoist each sail for flight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13639, line : "Better from evils, well foreseen, to run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13640, line : "Than perish in the danger we may shun.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13642, line : "Thus he. The sage Ulysses thus replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13643, line : "While anger flash'd from his disdainful eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13644, line : "\"What shameful words (unkingly as thou art)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13645, line : "Fall from that trembling tongue and timorous heart?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13646, line : "Oh were thy sway the curse of meaner powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13647, line : "And thou the shame of any host but ours!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13648, line : "A host, by Jove endued with martial might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13649, line : "And taught to conquer, or to fall in fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13650, line : "Adventurous combats and bold wars to wage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13651, line : "Employ'd our youth, and yet employs our age."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13652, line : "And wilt thou thus desert the Trojan plain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13653, line : "And have whole streams of blood been spilt in vain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13654, line : "In such base sentence if thou couch thy fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13655, line : "Speak it in whispers, lest a Greek should hear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13656, line : "Lives there a man so dead to fame, who dares"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13657, line : "To think such meanness, or the thought declares?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13658, line : "And comes it even from him whose sovereign sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13659, line : "The banded legions of all Greece obey?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13660, line : "Is this a general's voice that calls to flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13661, line : "While war hangs doubtful, while his soldiers fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13662, line : "What more could Troy? What yet their fate denies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13663, line : "Thou givest the foe: all Greece becomes their prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13664, line : "No more the troops (our hoisted sails in view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13665, line : "Themselves abandon'd) shall the fight pursue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13666, line : "But thy ships flying, with despair shall see;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13667, line : "And owe destruction to a prince like thee.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13669, line : "\"Thy just reproofs (Atrides calm replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13670, line : "Like arrows pierce me, for thy words are wise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13671, line : "Unwilling as I am to lose the host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13672, line : "I force not Greece to quit this hateful coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13673, line : "Glad I submit, whoe'er, or young, or old,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13674, line : "Aught, more conducive to our weal, unfold.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13676, line : "Tydides cut him short, and thus began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13677, line : "\"Such counsel if you seek, behold the man"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13678, line : "Who boldly gives it, and what he shall say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13679, line : "Young though he be, disdain not to obey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13680, line : "A youth, who from the mighty Tydeus springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13681, line : "May speak to councils and assembled kings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13682, line : "Hear then in me the great OEnides' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13683, line : "Whose honoured dust (his race of glory run)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13684, line : "Lies whelm'd in ruins of the Theban wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13685, line : "Brave in his life, and glorious in his fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13686, line : "With three bold sons was generous Prothous bless'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13687, line : "Who Pleuron's walls and Calydon possess'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13688, line : "Melas and Agrius, but (who far surpass'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13689, line : "The rest in courage) OEneus was the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13690, line : "From him, my sire. From Calydon expell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13691, line : "He pass'd to Argos, and in exile dwell'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13692, line : "The monarch's daughter there (so Jove ordain'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13693, line : "He won, and flourish'd where Adrastus reign'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13694, line : "There, rich in fortune's gifts, his acres till'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13695, line : "Beheld his vines their liquid harvest yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13696, line : "And numerous flocks that whiten'd all the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13697, line : "Such Tydeus was, the foremost once in fame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13698, line : "Nor lives in Greece a stranger to his name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13699, line : "Then, what for common good my thoughts inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13700, line : "Attend, and in the son respect the sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13701, line : "Though sore of battle, though with wounds oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13702, line : "Let each go forth, and animate the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13703, line : "Advance the glory which he cannot share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13704, line : "Though not partaker, witness of the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13705, line : "But lest new wounds on wounds o'erpower us quite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13706, line : "Beyond the missile javelin's sounding flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13707, line : "Safe let us stand; and, from the tumult far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13708, line : "Inspire the ranks, and rule the distant war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13710, line : "He added not: the listening kings obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13711, line : "Slow moving on; Atrides leads the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13712, line : "The god of ocean (to inflame their rage)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13713, line : "Appears a warrior furrowed o'er with age;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13714, line : "Press'd in his own, the general's hand he took,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13715, line : "And thus the venerable hero spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13717, line : "\"Atrides! lo! with what disdainful eye"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13718, line : "Achilles sees his country's forces fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13719, line : "Blind, impious man! whose anger is his guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13720, line : "Who glories in unutterable pride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13721, line : "So may he perish, so may Jove disclaim"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13722, line : "The wretch relentless, and o'erwhelm with shame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13723, line : "But Heaven forsakes not thee: o'er yonder sands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13724, line : "Soon shall thou view the scattered Trojan bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13725, line : "Fly diverse; while proud kings, and chiefs renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13726, line : "Driven heaps on heaps, with clouds involved around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13727, line : "Of rolling dust, their winged wheels employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13728, line : "To hide their ignominious heads in Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13730, line : "He spoke, then rush'd amid the warrior crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13731, line : "And sent his voice before him as he flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13732, line : "Loud, as the shout encountering armies yield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13733, line : "When twice ten thousand shake the labouring field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13734, line : "Such was the voice, and such the thundering sound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13735, line : "Of him whose trident rends the solid ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13736, line : "Each Argive bosom beats to meet the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13737, line : "And grisly war appears a pleasing sight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13739, line : "Meantime Saturnia from Olympus' brow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13740, line : "High-throned in gold, beheld the fields below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13741, line : "With joy the glorious conflict she survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13742, line : "Where her great brother gave the Grecians aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13743, line : "But placed aloft, on Ida's shady height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13744, line : "She sees her Jove, and trembles at the sight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13745, line : "Jove to deceive, what methods shall she try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13746, line : "What arts, to blind his all-beholding eye?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13747, line : "At length she trusts her power; resolved to prove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13748, line : "The old, yet still successful, cheat of love;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13749, line : "Against his wisdom to oppose her charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13750, line : "And lull the lord of thunders in her arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13752, line : "Swift to her bright apartment she repairs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13753, line : "Sacred to dress and beauty's pleasing cares:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13754, line : "With skill divine had Vulcan form'd the bower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13755, line : "Safe from access of each intruding power."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13756, line : "Touch'd with her secret key, the doors unfold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13757, line : "Self-closed, behind her shut the valves of gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13758, line : "Here first she bathes; and round her body pours"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13759, line : "Soft oils of fragrance, and ambrosial showers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13760, line : "The winds, perfumed, the balmy gale convey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13761, line : "Through heaven, through earth, and all the aerial way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13762, line : "Spirit divine! whose exhalation greets"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13763, line : "The sense of gods with more than mortal sweets."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13764, line : "Thus while she breathed of heaven, with decent pride"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13765, line : "Her artful hands the radiant tresses tied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13766, line : "Part on her head in shining ringlets roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13767, line : "Part o'er her shoulders waved like melted gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13768, line : "Around her next a heavenly mantle flow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13769, line : "That rich with Pallas' labour'd colours glow'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13770, line : "Large clasps of gold the foldings gather'd round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13771, line : "A golden zone her swelling bosom bound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13772, line : "Far-beaming pendants tremble in her ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13773, line : "Each gem illumined with a triple star."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13774, line : "Then o'er her head she cast a veil more white"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13775, line : "Than new-fallen snow, and dazzling as the light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13776, line : "Last her fair feet celestial sandals grace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13777, line : "Thus issuing radiant with majestic pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13778, line : "Forth from the dome the imperial goddess moves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13779, line : "And calls the mother of the smiles and loves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13781, line : "\"How long (to Venus thus apart she cried)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13782, line : "Shall human strife celestial minds divide?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13783, line : "Ah yet, will Venus aid Saturnia's joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13784, line : "And set aside the cause of Greece and Troy?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13786, line : "\"Let heaven's dread empress (Cytheraea said)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13787, line : "Speak her request, and deem her will obey'd.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13789, line : "\"Then grant me (said the queen) those conquering charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13790, line : "That power, which mortals and immortals warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13791, line : "That love, which melts mankind in fierce desires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13792, line : "And burns the sons of heaven with sacred fires!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13794, line : "\"For lo! I haste to those remote abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13795, line : "Where the great parents, (sacred source of gods!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13796, line : "Ocean and Tethys their old empire keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13797, line : "On the last limits of the land and deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13798, line : "In their kind arms my tender years were past;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13799, line : "What time old Saturn, from Olympus cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13800, line : "Of upper heaven to Jove resign'd the reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13801, line : "Whelm'd under the huge mass of earth and main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13802, line : "For strife, I hear, has made the union cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13803, line : "Which held so long that ancient pair in peace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13804, line : "What honour, and what love, shall I obtain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13805, line : "If I compose those fatal feuds again;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13806, line : "Once more their minds in mutual ties engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13807, line : "And, what my youth has owed, repay their age!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13809, line : "She said. With awe divine, the queen of love"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13810, line : "Obey'd the sister and the wife of Jove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13811, line : "And from her fragrant breast the zone embraced,(233)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13812, line : "With various skill and high embroidery graced."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13813, line : "In this was every art, and every charm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13814, line : "To win the wisest, and the coldest warm:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13815, line : "Fond love, the gentle vow, the gay desire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13816, line : "The kind deceit, the still-reviving fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13817, line : "Persuasive speech, and the more persuasive sighs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13818, line : "Silence that spoke, and eloquence of eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13819, line : "This on her hand the Cyprian Goddess laid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13820, line : "\"Take this, and with it all thy wish;\" she said."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13821, line : "With smiles she took the charm; and smiling press'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13822, line : "The powerful cestus to her snowy breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13824, line : "Then Venus to the courts of Jove withdrew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13825, line : "Whilst from Olympus pleased Saturnia flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13826, line : "O'er high Pieria thence her course she bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13827, line : "O'er fair Emathia's ever-pleasing shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13828, line : "O'er Hemus' hills with snows eternal crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13829, line : "Nor once her flying foot approach'd the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13830, line : "Then taking wing from Athos' lofty steep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13831, line : "She speeds to Lemnos o'er the rolling deep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13832, line : "And seeks the cave of Death's half-brother, Sleep.(234)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13834, line : "\"Sweet pleasing Sleep! (Saturnia thus began)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13835, line : "Who spread'st thy empire o'er each god and man;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13836, line : "If e'er obsequious to thy Juno's will,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13837, line : "O power of slumbers! hear, and favour still."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13838, line : "Shed thy soft dews on Jove's immortal eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13839, line : "While sunk in love's entrancing joys he lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13840, line : "A splendid footstool, and a throne, that shine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13841, line : "With gold unfading, Somnus, shall be thine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13842, line : "The work of Vulcan; to indulge thy ease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13843, line : "When wine and feasts thy golden humours please.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13845, line : "\"Imperial dame (the balmy power replies),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13846, line : "Great Saturn's heir, and empress of the skies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13847, line : "O'er other gods I spread my easy chain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13848, line : "The sire of all, old Ocean, owns my reign."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13849, line : "And his hush'd waves lie silent on the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13850, line : "But how, unbidden, shall I dare to steep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13851, line : "Jove's awful temples in the dew of sleep?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13852, line : "Long since, too venturous, at thy bold command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13853, line : "On those eternal lids I laid my hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13854, line : "What time, deserting Ilion's wasted plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13855, line : "His conquering son, Alcides, plough'd the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13856, line : "When lo! the deeps arise, the tempests roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13857, line : "And drive the hero to the Coan shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13858, line : "Great Jove, awaking, shook the blest abodes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13859, line : "With rising wrath, and tumbled gods on gods;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13860, line : "Me chief he sought, and from the realms on high"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13861, line : "Had hurl'd indignant to the nether sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13862, line : "But gentle Night, to whom I fled for aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13863, line : "(The friend of earth and heaven,) her wings display'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13864, line : "Impower'd the wrath of gods and men to tame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13865, line : "Even Jove revered the venerable dame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13867, line : "\"Vain are thy fears (the queen of heaven replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13868, line : "And, speaking, rolls her large majestic eyes);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13869, line : "Think'st thou that Troy has Jove's high favour won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13870, line : "Like great Alcides, his all-conquering son?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13871, line : "Hear, and obey the mistress of the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13872, line : "Nor for the deed expect a vulgar prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13873, line : "For know, thy loved-one shall be ever thine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13874, line : "The youngest Grace, Pasithae the divine.\"(235)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13876, line : "\"Swear then (he said) by those tremendous floods"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13877, line : "That roar through hell, and bind the invoking gods:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13878, line : "Let the great parent earth one hand sustain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13879, line : "And stretch the other o'er the sacred main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13880, line : "Call the black Titans, that with Chronos dwell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13881, line : "To hear and witness from the depths of hell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13882, line : "That she, my loved-one, shall be ever mine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13883, line : "The youngest Grace, Pasithae the divine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13885, line : "The queen assents, and from the infernal bowers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13886, line : "Invokes the sable subtartarean powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13887, line : "And those who rule the inviolable floods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13888, line : "Whom mortals name the dread Titanian gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13890, line : "[Illustration: SLEEP ESCAPING FROM THE WRATH OF JUPITER.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13892, line : "SLEEP ESCAPING FROM THE WRATH OF JUPITER."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13895, line : "Then swift as wind, o'er Lemnos' smoky isle"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13896, line : "They wing their way, and Imbrus' sea-beat soil;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13897, line : "Through air, unseen, involved in darkness glide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13898, line : "And light on Lectos, on the point of Ide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13899, line : "(Mother of savages, whose echoing hills"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13900, line : "Are heard resounding with a hundred rills:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13901, line : "Fair Ida trembles underneath the god;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13902, line : "Hush'd are her mountains, and her forests nod."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13903, line : "There on a fir, whose spiry branches rise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13904, line : "To join its summit to the neighbouring skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13905, line : "Dark in embowering shade, conceal'd from sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13906, line : "Sat Sleep, in likeness of the bird of night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13907, line : "(Chalcis his name by those of heavenly birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13908, line : "But call'd Cymindis by the race of earth.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13910, line : "To Ida's top successful Juno flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13911, line : "Great Jove surveys her with desiring eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13912, line : "The god, whose lightning sets the heavens on fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13913, line : "Through all his bosom feels the fierce desire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13914, line : "Fierce as when first by stealth he seized her charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13915, line : "Mix'd with her soul, and melted in her arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13916, line : "Fix'd on her eyes he fed his eager look,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13917, line : "Then press'd her hand, and thus with transport spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13919, line : "\"Why comes my goddess from the ethereal sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13920, line : "And not her steeds and flaming chariot nigh?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13922, line : "Then she--\"I haste to those remote abodes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13923, line : "Where the great parents of the deathless gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13924, line : "The reverend Ocean and gray Tethys, reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13925, line : "On the last limits of the land and main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13926, line : "I visit these, to whose indulgent cares"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13927, line : "I owe the nursing of my tender years:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13928, line : "For strife, I hear, has made that union cease"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13929, line : "Which held so long that ancient pair in peace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13930, line : "The steeds, prepared my chariot to convey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13931, line : "O'er earth and seas, and through the aerial way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13932, line : "Wait under Ide: of thy superior power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13933, line : "To ask consent, I leave the Olympian bower;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13934, line : "Nor seek, unknown to thee, the sacred cells"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13935, line : "Deep under seas, where hoary Ocean dwells.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13937, line : "\"For that (said Jove) suffice another day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13938, line : "But eager love denies the least delay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13939, line : "Let softer cares the present hour employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13940, line : "And be these moments sacred all to joy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13941, line : "Ne'er did my soul so strong a passion prove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13942, line : "Or for an earthly, or a heavenly love:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13943, line : "Not when I press'd Ixion's matchless dame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13944, line : "Whence rose Pirithous like the gods in fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13945, line : "Not when fair Danae felt the shower of gold"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13946, line : "Stream into life, whence Perseus brave and bold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13947, line : "Not thus I burn'd for either Theban dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13948, line : "(Bacchus from this, from that Alcides came:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13949, line : "Nor Phoenix' daughter, beautiful and young,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13950, line : "Whence godlike Rhadamanth and Minos sprung.(236)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13951, line : "Not thus I burn'd for fair Latona's face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13952, line : "Nor comelier Ceres' more majestic grace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13953, line : "Not thus even for thyself I felt desire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13954, line : "As now my veins receive the pleasing fire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13956, line : "He spoke; the goddess with the charming eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13957, line : "Glows with celestial red, and thus replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13958, line : "\"Is this a scene for love? On Ida's height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13959, line : "Exposed to mortal and immortal sight!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13960, line : "Our joys profaned by each familiar eye;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13961, line : "The sport of heaven, and fable of the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13962, line : "How shall I e'er review the blest abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13963, line : "Or mix among the senate of the gods?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13964, line : "Shall I not think, that, with disorder'd charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13965, line : "All heaven beholds me recent from thy arms?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13966, line : "With skill divine has Vulcan form'd thy bower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13967, line : "Sacred to love and to the genial hour;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13968, line : "If such thy will, to that recess retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13969, line : "In secret there indulge thy soft desire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13971, line : "She ceased; and, smiling with superior love,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13972, line : "Thus answer'd mild the cloud-compelling Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13973, line : "\"Nor god nor mortal shall our joys behold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13974, line : "Shaded with clouds, and circumfused in gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13975, line : "Not even the sun, who darts through heaven his rays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13976, line : "And whose broad eye the extended earth surveys.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13978, line : "Gazing he spoke, and, kindling at the view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13979, line : "His eager arms around the goddess threw."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13980, line : "Glad Earth perceives, and from her bosom pours"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13981, line : "Unbidden herbs and voluntary flowers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13982, line : "Thick new-born violets a soft carpet spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13983, line : "And clustering lotos swell'd the rising bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13984, line : "And sudden hyacinths the turf bestrow,(237)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13985, line : "And flamy crocus made the mountain glow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13986, line : "There golden clouds conceal the heavenly pair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13987, line : "Steep'd in soft joys and circumfused with air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13988, line : "Celestial dews, descending o'er the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13989, line : "Perfume the mount, and breathe ambrosia round:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13990, line : "At length, with love and sleep's soft power oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13991, line : "The panting thunderer nods, and sinks to rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13993, line : "Now to the navy borne on silent wings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13994, line : "To Neptune's ear soft Sleep his message brings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13995, line : "Beside him sudden, unperceived, he stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13996, line : "And thus with gentle words address'd the god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13998, line : "\"Now, Neptune! now, the important hour employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 13999, line : "To check a while the haughty hopes of Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14000, line : "While Jove yet rests, while yet my vapours shed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14001, line : "The golden vision round his sacred head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14002, line : "For Juno's love, and Somnus' pleasing ties,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14003, line : "Have closed those awful and eternal eyes.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14004, line : "Thus having said, the power of slumber flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14005, line : "On human lids to drop the balmy dew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14006, line : "Neptune, with zeal increased, renews his care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14007, line : "And towering in the foremost ranks of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14008, line : "Indignant thus--\"Oh once of martial fame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14009, line : "O Greeks! if yet ye can deserve the name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14010, line : "This half-recover'd day shall Troy obtain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14011, line : "Shall Hector thunder at your ships again?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14012, line : "Lo! still he vaunts, and threats the fleet with fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14013, line : "While stern Achilles in his wrath retires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14014, line : "One hero's loss too tamely you deplore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14015, line : "Be still yourselves, and ye shall need no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14016, line : "Oh yet, if glory any bosom warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14017, line : "Brace on your firmest helms, and stand to arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14018, line : "His strongest spear each valiant Grecian wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14019, line : "Each valiant Grecian seize his broadest shield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14020, line : "Let to the weak the lighter arms belong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14021, line : "The ponderous targe be wielded by the strong."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14022, line : "Thus arm'd, not Hector shall our presence stay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14023, line : "Myself, ye Greeks! myself will lead the way.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14025, line : "[Illustration: GREEK SHIELD.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14027, line : "GREEK SHIELD."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14030, line : "The troops assent; their martial arms they change:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14031, line : "The busy chiefs their banded legions range."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14032, line : "The kings, though wounded, and oppress'd with pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14033, line : "With helpful hands themselves assist the train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14034, line : "The strong and cumbrous arms the valiant wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14035, line : "The weaker warrior takes a lighter shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14036, line : "Thus sheath'd in shining brass, in bright array"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14037, line : "The legions march, and Neptune leads the way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14038, line : "His brandish'd falchion flames before their eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14039, line : "Like lightning flashing through the frighted skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14040, line : "Clad in his might, the earth-shaking power appears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14041, line : "Pale mortals tremble, and confess their fears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14043, line : "Troy's great defender stands alone unawed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14044, line : "Arms his proud host, and dares oppose a god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14045, line : "And lo! the god, and wondrous man, appear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14046, line : "The sea's stern ruler there, and Hector here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14047, line : "The roaring main, at her great master's call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14048, line : "Rose in huge ranks, and form'd a watery wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14049, line : "Around the ships: seas hanging o'er the shores,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14050, line : "Both armies join: earth thunders, ocean roars."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14051, line : "Not half so loud the bellowing deeps resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14052, line : "When stormy winds disclose the dark profound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14053, line : "Less loud the winds that from the Ćolian hall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14054, line : "Roar through the woods, and make whole forests fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14055, line : "Less loud the woods, when flames in torrents pour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14056, line : "Catch the dry mountain, and its shades devour;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14057, line : "With such a rage the meeting hosts are driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14058, line : "And such a clamour shakes the sounding heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14059, line : "The first bold javelin, urged by Hector's force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14060, line : "Direct at Ajax' bosom winged its course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14061, line : "But there no pass the crossing belts afford,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14062, line : "(One braced his shield, and one sustain'd his sword.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14063, line : "Then back the disappointed Trojan drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14064, line : "And cursed the lance that unavailing flew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14065, line : "But 'scaped not Ajax; his tempestuous hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14066, line : "A ponderous stone upheaving from the sand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14067, line : "(Where heaps laid loose beneath the warrior's feet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14068, line : "Or served to ballast, or to prop the fleet,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14069, line : "Toss'd round and round, the missive marble flings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14070, line : "On the razed shield the fallen ruin rings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14071, line : "Full on his breast and throat with force descends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14072, line : "Nor deaden'd there its giddy fury spends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14073, line : "But whirling on, with many a fiery round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14074, line : "Smokes in the dust, and ploughs into the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14075, line : "As when the bolt, red-hissing from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14076, line : "Darts on the consecrated plant of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14077, line : "The mountain-oak in flaming ruin lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14078, line : "Black from the blow, and smokes of sulphur rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14079, line : "Stiff with amaze the pale beholders stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14080, line : "And own the terrors of the almighty hand!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14081, line : "So lies great Hector prostrate on the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14082, line : "His slacken'd hand deserts the lance it bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14083, line : "His following shield the fallen chief o'erspread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14084, line : "Beneath his helmet dropp'd his fainting head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14085, line : "His load of armour, sinking to the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14086, line : "Clanks on the field, a dead and hollow sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14087, line : "Loud shouts of triumph fill the crowded plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14088, line : "Greece sees, in hope, Troy's great defender slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14089, line : "All spring to seize him; storms of arrows fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14090, line : "And thicker javelins intercept the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14091, line : "In vain an iron tempest hisses round;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14092, line : "He lies protected, and without a wound.(238)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14093, line : "Polydamas, Agenor the divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14094, line : "The pious warrior of Anchises' line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14095, line : "And each bold leader of the Lycian band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14096, line : "With covering shields (a friendly circle) stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14097, line : "His mournful followers, with assistant care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14098, line : "The groaning hero to his chariot bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14099, line : "His foaming coursers, swifter than the wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14100, line : "Speed to the town, and leave the war behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14102, line : "When now they touch'd the mead's enamell'd side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14103, line : "Where gentle Xanthus rolls his easy tide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14104, line : "With watery drops the chief they sprinkle round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14105, line : "Placed on the margin of the flowery ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14106, line : "Raised on his knees, he now ejects the gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14107, line : "Now faints anew, low-sinking on the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14108, line : "By fits he breathes, half views the fleeting skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14109, line : "And seals again, by fits, his swimming eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14111, line : "Soon as the Greeks the chief's retreat beheld,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14112, line : "With double fury each invades the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14113, line : "Oilean Ajax first his javelin sped,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14114, line : "Pierced by whose point the son of Enops bled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14115, line : "(Satnius the brave, whom beauteous Neis bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14116, line : "Amidst her flocks on Satnio's silver shore;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14117, line : "Struck through the belly's rim, the warrior lies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14118, line : "Supine, and shades eternal veil his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14119, line : "An arduous battle rose around the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14120, line : "By turns the Greeks, by turns the Trojans bled."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14122, line : "Fired with revenge, Polydamas drew near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14123, line : "And at Prothoenor shook the trembling spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14124, line : "The driving javelin through his shoulder thrust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14125, line : "He sinks to earth, and grasps the bloody dust."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14126, line : "\"Lo thus (the victor cries) we rule the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14127, line : "And thus their arms the race of Panthus wield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14128, line : "From this unerring hand there flies no dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14129, line : "But bathes its point within a Grecian heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14130, line : "Propp'd on that spear to which thou owest thy fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14131, line : "Go, guide thy darksome steps to Pluto's dreary hall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14133, line : "He said, and sorrow touch'd each Argive breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14134, line : "The soul of Ajax burn'd above the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14135, line : "As by his side the groaning warrior fell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14136, line : "At the fierce foe he launch'd his piercing steel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14137, line : "The foe, reclining, shunn'd the flying death;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14138, line : "But fate, Archilochus, demands thy breath:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14139, line : "Thy lofty birth no succour could impart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14140, line : "The wings of death o'ertook thee on the dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14141, line : "Swift to perform heaven's fatal will, it fled"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14142, line : "Full on the juncture of the neck and head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14143, line : "And took the joint, and cut the nerves in twain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14144, line : "The dropping head first tumbled on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14145, line : "So just the stroke, that yet the body stood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14146, line : "Erect, then roll'd along the sands in blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14148, line : "\"Here, proud Polydamas, here turn thy eyes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14149, line : "(The towering Ajax loud-insulting cries:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14150, line : "Say, is this chief extended on the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14151, line : "A worthy vengeance for Prothoenor slain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14152, line : "Mark well his port! his figure and his face"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14153, line : "Nor speak him vulgar, nor of vulgar race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14154, line : "Some lines, methinks, may make his lineage known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14155, line : "Antenor's brother, or perhaps his son.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14157, line : "He spake, and smiled severe, for well he knew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14158, line : "The bleeding youth: Troy sadden'd at the view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14159, line : "But furious Acamas avenged his cause;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14160, line : "As Promachus his slaughtered brother draws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14161, line : "He pierced his heart--\"Such fate attends you all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14162, line : "Proud Argives! destined by our arms to fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14163, line : "Not Troy alone, but haughty Greece, shall share"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14164, line : "The toils, the sorrows, and the wounds of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14165, line : "Behold your Promachus deprived of breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14166, line : "A victim owed to my brave brother's death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14167, line : "Not unappeased he enters Pluto's gate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14168, line : "Who leaves a brother to revenge his fate.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14170, line : "Heart-piercing anguish struck the Grecian host,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14171, line : "But touch'd the breast of bold Peneleus most;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14172, line : "At the proud boaster he directs his course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14173, line : "The boaster flies, and shuns superior force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14174, line : "But young Ilioneus received the spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14175, line : "Ilioneus, his father's only care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14176, line : "(Phorbas the rich, of all the Trojan train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14177, line : "Whom Hermes loved, and taught the arts of gain:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14178, line : "Full in his eye the weapon chanced to fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14179, line : "And from the fibres scoop'd the rooted ball,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14180, line : "Drove through the neck, and hurl'd him to the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14181, line : "He lifts his miserable arms in vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14182, line : "Swift his broad falchion fierce Peneleus spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14183, line : "And from the spouting shoulders struck his head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14184, line : "To earth at once the head and helmet fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14185, line : "The lance, yet sticking through the bleeding eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14186, line : "The victor seized; and, as aloft he shook"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14187, line : "The gory visage, thus insulting spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14189, line : "\"Trojans! your great Ilioneus behold!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14190, line : "Haste, to his father let the tale be told:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14191, line : "Let his high roofs resound with frantic woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14192, line : "Such as the house of Promachus must know;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14193, line : "Let doleful tidings greet his mother's ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14194, line : "Such as to Promachus' sad spouse we bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14195, line : "When we victorious shall to Greece return,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14196, line : "And the pale matron in our triumphs mourn.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14198, line : "Dreadful he spoke, then toss'd the head on high;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14199, line : "The Trojans hear, they tremble, and they fly:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14200, line : "Aghast they gaze around the fleet and wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14201, line : "And dread the ruin that impends on all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14203, line : "Daughters of Jove! that on Olympus shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14204, line : "Ye all-beholding, all-recording nine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14205, line : "O say, when Neptune made proud Ilion yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14206, line : "What chief, what hero first embrued the field?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14207, line : "Of all the Grecians what immortal name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14208, line : "And whose bless'd trophies, will ye raise to fame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14210, line : "Thou first, great Ajax! on the unsanguined plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14211, line : "Laid Hyrtius, leader of the Mysian train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14212, line : "Phalces and Mermer, Nestor's son o'erthrew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14213, line : "Bold Merion, Morys and Hippotion slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14214, line : "Strong Periphaetes and Prothoon bled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14215, line : "By Teucer's arrows mingled with the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14216, line : "Pierced in the flank by Menelaus' steel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14217, line : "His people's pastor, Hyperenor fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14218, line : "Eternal darkness wrapp'd the warrior round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14219, line : "And the fierce soul came rushing through the wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14220, line : "But stretch'd in heaps before Oileus' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14221, line : "Fall mighty numbers, mighty numbers run;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14222, line : "Ajax the less, of all the Grecian race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14223, line : "Skill'd in pursuit, and swiftest in the chase."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14225, line : "[Illustration: BACCHUS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14227, line : "BACCHUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14233, line : "BOOK XV."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14236, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14238, line : "THE FIFTH BATTLE AT THE SHIPS; AND THE ACTS OF AJAX."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14240, line : "Jupiter, awaking, sees the Trojans repulsed from the trenches, Hector in a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14241, line : "swoon, and Neptune at the head of the Greeks: he is highly incensed at the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14242, line : "artifice of Juno, who appeases him by her submissions; she is then sent to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14243, line : "Iris and Apollo. Juno, repairing to the assembly of the gods, attempts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14244, line : "with extraordinary address, to incense them against Jupiter; in particular"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14245, line : "she touches Mars with a violent resentment; he is ready to take arms, but"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14246, line : "is prevented by Minerva. Iris and Apollo obey the orders of Jupiter; Iris"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14247, line : "commands Neptune to leave the battle, to which, after much reluctance and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14248, line : "passion, he consents. Apollo reinspires Hector with vigour, brings him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14249, line : "back to the battle, marches before him with his aegis, and turns the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14250, line : "fortune of the fight. He breaks down great part of the Grecian wall: the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14251, line : "Trojans rush in, and attempt to fire the first line of the fleet, but are,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14252, line : "as yet, repelled by the greater Ajax with a prodigious slaughter."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14254, line : "Now in swift flight they pass the trench profound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14255, line : "And many a chief lay gasping on the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14256, line : "Then stopp'd and panted, where the chariots lie"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14257, line : "Fear on their cheek, and horror in their eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14258, line : "Meanwhile, awaken'd from his dream of love,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14259, line : "On Ida's summit sat imperial Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14260, line : "Round the wide fields he cast a careful view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14261, line : "There saw the Trojans fly, the Greeks pursue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14262, line : "These proud in arms, those scatter'd o'er the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14263, line : "And, 'midst the war, the monarch of the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14264, line : "Not far, great Hector on the dust he spies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14265, line : "(His sad associates round with weeping eyes,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14266, line : "Ejecting blood, and panting yet for breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14267, line : "His senses wandering to the verge of death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14268, line : "The god beheld him with a pitying look,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14269, line : "And thus, incensed, to fraudful Juno spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14271, line : "\"O thou, still adverse to the eternal will,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14272, line : "For ever studious in promoting ill!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14273, line : "Thy arts have made the godlike Hector yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14274, line : "And driven his conquering squadrons from the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14275, line : "Canst thou, unhappy in thy wiles, withstand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14276, line : "Our power immense, and brave the almighty hand?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14277, line : "Hast thou forgot, when, bound and fix'd on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14278, line : "From the vast concave of the spangled sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14279, line : "I hung thee trembling in a golden chain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14280, line : "And all the raging gods opposed in vain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14281, line : "Headlong I hurl'd them from the Olympian hall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14282, line : "Stunn'd in the whirl, and breathless with the fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14283, line : "For godlike Hercules these deeds were done,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14284, line : "Nor seem'd the vengeance worthy such a son:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14285, line : "When, by thy wiles induced, fierce Boreas toss'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14286, line : "The shipwreck'd hero on the Coan coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14287, line : "Him through a thousand forms of death I bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14288, line : "And sent to Argos, and his native shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14289, line : "Hear this, remember, and our fury dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14290, line : "Nor pull the unwilling vengeance on thy head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14291, line : "Lest arts and blandishments successless prove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14292, line : "Thy soft deceits, and well-dissembled love.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14294, line : "The Thunderer spoke: imperial Juno mourn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14295, line : "And, trembling, these submissive words return'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14297, line : "\"By every oath that powers immortal ties,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14298, line : "The foodful earth and all-infolding skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14299, line : "By thy black waves, tremendous Styx! that flow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14300, line : "Through the drear realms of gliding ghosts below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14301, line : "By the dread honours of thy sacred head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14302, line : "And that unbroken vow, our virgin bed!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14303, line : "Not by my arts the ruler of the main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14304, line : "Steeps Troy in blood, and ranges round the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14305, line : "By his own ardour, his own pity sway'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14306, line : "To help his Greeks, he fought and disobey'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14307, line : "Else had thy Juno better counsels given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14308, line : "And taught submission to the sire of heaven.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14310, line : "\"Think'st thou with me? fair empress of the skies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14311, line : "(The immortal father with a smile replies;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14312, line : "Then soon the haughty sea-god shall obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14313, line : "Nor dare to act but when we point the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14314, line : "If truth inspires thy tongue, proclaim our will"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14315, line : "To yon bright synod on the Olympian hill;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14316, line : "Our high decree let various Iris know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14317, line : "And call the god that bears the silver bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14318, line : "Let her descend, and from the embattled plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14319, line : "Command the sea-god to his watery reign:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14320, line : "While Phoebus hastes great Hector to prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14321, line : "To rise afresh, and once more wake the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14322, line : "His labouring bosom re-inspires with breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14323, line : "And calls his senses from the verge of death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14324, line : "Greece chased by Troy, even to Achilles' fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14325, line : "Shall fall by thousands at the hero's feet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14326, line : "He, not untouch'd with pity, to the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14327, line : "Shall send Patroclus, but shall send in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14328, line : "What youths he slaughters under Ilion's walls!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14329, line : "Even my loved son, divine Sarpedon, falls!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14330, line : "Vanquish'd at last by Hector's lance he lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14331, line : "Then, nor till then, shall great Achilles rise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14332, line : "And lo! that instant, godlike Hector dies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14333, line : "From that great hour the war's whole fortune turns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14334, line : "Pallas assists, and lofty Ilion burns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14335, line : "Not till that day shall Jove relax his rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14336, line : "Nor one of all the heavenly host engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14337, line : "In aid of Greece. The promise of a god"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14338, line : "I gave, and seal'd it with the almighty nod,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14339, line : "Achilles' glory to the stars to raise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14340, line : "Such was our word, and fate the word obeys.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14342, line : "The trembling queen (the almighty order given)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14343, line : "Swift from the Idaean summit shot to heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14344, line : "As some wayfaring man, who wanders o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14345, line : "In thought a length of lands he trod before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14346, line : "Sends forth his active mind from place to place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14347, line : "Joins hill to dale, and measures space with space:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14348, line : "So swift flew Juno to the bless'd abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14349, line : "If thought of man can match the speed of gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14350, line : "There sat the powers in awful synod placed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14351, line : "They bow'd, and made obeisance as she pass'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14352, line : "Through all the brazen dome: with goblets crown'd(239)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14353, line : "They hail her queen; the nectar streams around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14354, line : "Fair Themis first presents the golden bowl,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14355, line : "And anxious asks what cares disturb her soul?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14357, line : "To whom the white-arm'd goddess thus replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14358, line : "\"Enough thou know'st the tyrant of the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14359, line : "Severely bent his purpose to fulfil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14360, line : "Unmoved his mind, and unrestrain'd his will."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14361, line : "Go thou, the feasts of heaven attend thy call;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14362, line : "Bid the crown'd nectar circle round the hall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14363, line : "But Jove shall thunder through the ethereal dome"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14364, line : "Such stern decrees, such threaten'd woes to come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14365, line : "As soon shall freeze mankind with dire surprise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14366, line : "And damp the eternal banquets of the skies.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14368, line : "The goddess said, and sullen took her place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14369, line : "Black horror sadden'd each celestial face."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14370, line : "To see the gathering grudge in every breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14371, line : "Smiles on her lips a spleenful joy express'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14372, line : "While on her wrinkled front, and eyebrow bent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14373, line : "Sat stedfast care, and lowering discontent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14374, line : "Thus she proceeds--\"Attend, ye powers above!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14375, line : "But know, 'tis madness to contest with Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14376, line : "Supreme he sits; and sees, in pride of sway."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14377, line : "Your vassal godheads grudgingly obey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14378, line : "Fierce in the majesty of power controls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14379, line : "Shakes all the thrones of heaven, and bends the poles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14380, line : "Submiss, immortals! all he wills, obey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14381, line : "And thou, great Mars, begin and show the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14382, line : "Behold Ascalaphus! behold him die,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14383, line : "But dare not murmur, dare not vent a sigh;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14384, line : "Thy own loved boasted offspring lies o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14385, line : "If that loved boasted offspring be thy own.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14387, line : "Stern Mars, with anguish for his slaughter'd son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14388, line : "Smote his rebelling breast, and fierce begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14389, line : "\"Thus then, immortals! thus shall Mars obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14390, line : "Forgive me, gods, and yield my vengeance way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14391, line : "Descending first to yon forbidden plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14392, line : "The god of battles dares avenge the slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14393, line : "Dares, though the thunder bursting o'er my head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14394, line : "Should hurl me blazing on those heaps of dead.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14396, line : "With that he gives command to Fear and Flight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14397, line : "To join his rapid coursers for the fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14398, line : "Then grim in arms, with hasty vengeance flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14399, line : "Arms that reflect a radiance through the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14400, line : "And now had Jove, by bold rebellion driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14401, line : "Discharged his wrath on half the host of heaven;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14402, line : "But Pallas, springing through the bright abode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14403, line : "Starts from her azure throne to calm the god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14404, line : "Struck for the immortal race with timely fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14405, line : "From frantic Mars she snatch'd the shield and spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14406, line : "Then the huge helmet lifting from his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14407, line : "Thus to the impetuous homicide she said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14409, line : "\"By what wild passion, furious! art thou toss'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14410, line : "Striv'st thou with Jove? thou art already lost."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14411, line : "Shall not the Thunderer's dread command restrain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14412, line : "And was imperial Juno heard in vain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14413, line : "Back to the skies wouldst thou with shame be driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14414, line : "And in thy guilt involve the host of heaven?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14415, line : "Ilion and Greece no more should Jove engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14416, line : "The skies would yield an ampler scene of rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14417, line : "Guilty and guiltless find an equal fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14418, line : "And one vast ruin whelm the Olympian state."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14419, line : "Cease then thy offspring's death unjust to call;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14420, line : "Heroes as great have died, and yet shall fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14421, line : "Why should heaven's law with foolish man comply"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14422, line : "Exempted from the race ordain'd to die?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14424, line : "This menace fix'd the warrior to his throne;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14425, line : "Sullen he sat, and curb'd the rising groan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14426, line : "Then Juno call'd (Jove's orders to obey)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14427, line : "The winged Iris, and the god of day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14428, line : "\"Go wait the Thunderer's will (Saturnia cried)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14429, line : "On yon tall summit of the fountful Ide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14430, line : "There in the father's awful presence stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14431, line : "Receive, and execute his dread command.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14433, line : "She said, and sat; the god that gilds the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14434, line : "And various Iris, wing their airy way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14435, line : "Swift as the wind, to Ida's hills they came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14436, line : "(Fair nurse of fountains, and of savage game)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14437, line : "There sat the eternal; he whose nod controls"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14438, line : "The trembling world, and shakes the steady poles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14439, line : "Veil'd in a mist of fragrance him they found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14440, line : "With clouds of gold and purple circled round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14441, line : "Well-pleased the Thunderer saw their earnest care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14442, line : "And prompt obedience to the queen of air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14443, line : "Then (while a smile serenes his awful brow)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14444, line : "Commands the goddess of the showery bow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14446, line : "\"Iris! descend, and what we here ordain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14447, line : "Report to yon mad tyrant of the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14448, line : "Bid him from fight to his own deeps repair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14449, line : "Or breathe from slaughter in the fields of air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14450, line : "If he refuse, then let him timely weigh"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14451, line : "Our elder birthright, and superior sway."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14452, line : "How shall his rashness stand the dire alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14453, line : "If heaven's omnipotence descend in arms?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14454, line : "Strives he with me, by whom his power was given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14455, line : "And is there equal to the lord of heaven?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14457, line : "The all-mighty spoke; the goddess wing'd her flight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14458, line : "To sacred Ilion from the Idaean height."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14459, line : "Swift as the rattling hail, or fleecy snows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14460, line : "Drive through the skies, when Boreas fiercely blows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14461, line : "So from the clouds descending Iris falls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14462, line : "And to blue Neptune thus the goddess calls:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14464, line : "\"Attend the mandate of the sire above!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14465, line : "In me behold the messenger of Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14466, line : "He bids thee from forbidden wars repair"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14467, line : "To thine own deeps, or to the fields of air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14468, line : "This if refused, he bids thee timely weigh"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14469, line : "His elder birthright, and superior sway."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14470, line : "How shall thy rashness stand the dire alarms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14471, line : "If heaven's omnipotence descend in arms?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14472, line : "Striv'st thou with him by whom all power is given?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14473, line : "And art thou equal to the lord of heaven?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14475, line : "\"What means the haughty sovereign of the skies?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14476, line : "(The king of ocean thus, incensed, replies;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14477, line : "Rule as he will his portion'd realms on high;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14478, line : "No vassal god, nor of his train, am I."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14479, line : "Three brother deities from Saturn came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14480, line : "And ancient Rhea, earth's immortal dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14481, line : "Assign'd by lot, our triple rule we know;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14482, line : "Infernal Pluto sways the shades below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14483, line : "O'er the wide clouds, and o'er the starry plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14484, line : "Ethereal Jove extends his high domain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14485, line : "My court beneath the hoary waves I keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14486, line : "And hush the roarings of the sacred deep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14487, line : "Olympus, and this earth, in common lie:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14488, line : "What claim has here the tyrant of the sky?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14489, line : "Far in the distant clouds let him control,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14490, line : "And awe the younger brothers of the pole;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14491, line : "There to his children his commands be given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14492, line : "The trembling, servile, second race of heaven.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14494, line : "\"And must I then (said she), O sire of floods!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14495, line : "Bear this fierce answer to the king of gods?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14496, line : "Correct it yet, and change thy rash intent;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14497, line : "A noble mind disdains not to repent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14498, line : "To elder brothers guardian fiends are given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14499, line : "To scourge the wretch insulting them and heaven.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14501, line : "\"Great is the profit (thus the god rejoin'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14502, line : "When ministers are blest with prudent mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14503, line : "Warn'd by thy words, to powerful Jove I yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14504, line : "And quit, though angry, the contended field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14505, line : "Not but his threats with justice I disclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14506, line : "The same our honours, and our birth the same."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14507, line : "If yet, forgetful of his promise given"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14508, line : "To Hermes, Pallas, and the queen of heaven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14509, line : "To favour Ilion, that perfidious place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14510, line : "He breaks his faith with half the ethereal race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14511, line : "Give him to know, unless the Grecian train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14512, line : "Lay yon proud structures level with the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14513, line : "Howe'er the offence by other gods be pass'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14514, line : "The wrath of Neptune shall for ever last.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14516, line : "Thus speaking, furious from the field he strode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14517, line : "And plunged into the bosom of the flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14518, line : "The lord of thunders, from his lofty height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14519, line : "Beheld, and thus bespoke the source of light:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14521, line : "\"Behold! the god whose liquid arms are hurl'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14522, line : "Around the globe, whose earthquakes rock the world,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14523, line : "Desists at length his rebel-war to wage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14524, line : "Seeks his own seas, and trembles at our rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14525, line : "Else had my wrath, heaven's thrones all shaking round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14526, line : "Burn'd to the bottom of his seas profound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14527, line : "And all the gods that round old Saturn dwell"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14528, line : "Had heard the thunders to the deeps of hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14529, line : "Well was the crime, and well the vengeance spared;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14530, line : "Even power immense had found such battle hard."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14531, line : "Go thou, my son! the trembling Greeks alarm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14532, line : "Shake my broad aegis on thy active arm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14533, line : "Be godlike Hector thy peculiar care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14534, line : "Swell his bold heart, and urge his strength to war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14535, line : "Let Ilion conquer, till the Achaian train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14536, line : "Fly to their ships and Hellespont again:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14537, line : "Then Greece shall breathe from toils.\" The godhead said;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14538, line : "His will divine the son of Jove obey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14539, line : "Not half so swift the sailing falcon flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14540, line : "That drives a turtle through the liquid skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14541, line : "As Phoebus, shooting from the Idaean brow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14542, line : "Glides down the mountain to the plain below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14543, line : "There Hector seated by the stream he sees,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14544, line : "His sense returning with the coming breeze;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14545, line : "Again his pulses beat, his spirits rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14546, line : "Again his loved companions meet his eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14547, line : "Jove thinking of his pains, they pass'd away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14548, line : "To whom the god who gives the golden day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14550, line : "\"Why sits great Hector from the field so far?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14551, line : "What grief, what wound, withholds thee from the war?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14553, line : "The fainting hero, as the vision bright"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14554, line : "Stood shining o'er him, half unseal'd his sight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14556, line : "\"What blest immortal, with commanding breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14557, line : "Thus wakens Hector from the sleep of death?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14558, line : "Has fame not told, how, while my trusty sword"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14559, line : "Bathed Greece in slaughter, and her battle gored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14560, line : "The mighty Ajax with a deadly blow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14561, line : "Had almost sunk me to the shades below?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14562, line : "Even yet, methinks, the gliding ghosts I spy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14563, line : "And hell's black horrors swim before my eye.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14565, line : "To him Apollo: \"Be no more dismay'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14566, line : "See, and be strong! the Thunderer sends thee aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14567, line : "Behold! thy Phoebus shall his arms employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14568, line : "Phoebus, propitious still to thee and Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14569, line : "Inspire thy warriors then with manly force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14570, line : "And to the ships impel thy rapid horse:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14571, line : "Even I will make thy fiery coursers way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14572, line : "And drive the Grecians headlong to the sea.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14574, line : "Thus to bold Hector spoke the son of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14575, line : "And breathed immortal ardour from above."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14576, line : "As when the pamper'd steed, with reins unbound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14577, line : "Breaks from his stall, and pours along the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14578, line : "With ample strokes he rushes to the flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14579, line : "To bathe his sides, and cool his fiery blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14580, line : "His head, now freed, he tosses to the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14581, line : "His mane dishevell'd o'er his shoulders flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14582, line : "He snuffs the females in the well-known plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14583, line : "And springs, exulting, to his fields again:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14584, line : "Urged by the voice divine, thus Hector flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14585, line : "Full of the god; and all his hosts pursue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14586, line : "As when the force of men and dogs combined"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14587, line : "Invade the mountain goat, or branching hind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14588, line : "Far from the hunter's rage secure they lie"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14589, line : "Close in the rock, (not fated yet to die)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14590, line : "When lo! a lion shoots across the way!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14591, line : "They fly: at once the chasers and the prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14592, line : "So Greece, that late in conquering troops pursued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14593, line : "And mark'd their progress through the ranks in blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14594, line : "Soon as they see the furious chief appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14595, line : "Forget to vanquish, and consent to fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14597, line : "Thoas with grief observed his dreadful course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14598, line : "Thoas, the bravest of the Ćtolian force;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14599, line : "Skill'd to direct the javelin's distant flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14600, line : "And bold to combat in the standing fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14601, line : "Not more in councils famed for solid sense,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14602, line : "Than winning words and heavenly eloquence."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14603, line : "\"Gods! what portent (he cried) these eyes invades?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14604, line : "Lo! Hector rises from the Stygian shades!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14605, line : "We saw him, late, by thundering Ajax kill'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14606, line : "What god restores him to the frighted field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14607, line : "And not content that half of Greece lie slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14608, line : "Pours new destruction on her sons again?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14609, line : "He comes not, Jove! without thy powerful will;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14610, line : "Lo! still he lives, pursues, and conquers still!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14611, line : "Yet hear my counsel, and his worst withstand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14612, line : "The Greeks' main body to the fleet command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14613, line : "But let the few whom brisker spirits warm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14614, line : "Stand the first onset, and provoke the storm."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14615, line : "Thus point your arms; and when such foes appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14616, line : "Fierce as he is, let Hector learn to fear.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14618, line : "The warrior spoke; the listening Greeks obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14619, line : "Thickening their ranks, and form a deep array."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14621, line : "Each Ajax, Teucer, Merion gave command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14622, line : "The valiant leader of the Cretan band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14623, line : "And Mars-like Meges: these the chiefs excite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14624, line : "Approach the foe, and meet the coming fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14625, line : "Behind, unnumber'd multitudes attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14626, line : "To flank the navy, and the shores defend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14627, line : "Full on the front the pressing Trojans bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14628, line : "And Hector first came towering to the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14629, line : "Phoebus himself the rushing battle led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14630, line : "A veil of clouds involved his radiant head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14631, line : "High held before him, Jove's enormous shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14632, line : "Portentous shone, and shaded all the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14633, line : "Vulcan to Jove the immortal gift consign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14634, line : "To scatter hosts and terrify mankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14635, line : "The Greeks expect the shock, the clamours rise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14636, line : "From different parts, and mingle in the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14637, line : "Dire was the hiss of darts, by heroes flung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14638, line : "And arrows leaping from the bow-string sung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14639, line : "These drink the life of generous warriors slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14640, line : "Those guiltless fall, and thirst for blood in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14641, line : "As long as Phoebus bore unmoved the shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14642, line : "Sat doubtful conquest hovering o'er the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14643, line : "But when aloft he shakes it in the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14644, line : "Shouts in their ears, and lightens in their eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14645, line : "Deep horror seizes every Grecian breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14646, line : "Their force is humbled, and their fear confess'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14647, line : "So flies a herd of oxen, scatter'd wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14648, line : "No swain to guard them, and no day to guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14649, line : "When two fell lions from the mountain come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14650, line : "And spread the carnage through the shady gloom."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14651, line : "Impending Phoebus pours around them fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14652, line : "And Troy and Hector thunder in the rear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14653, line : "Heaps fall on heaps: the slaughter Hector leads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14654, line : "First great Arcesilas, then Stichius bleeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14655, line : "One to the bold Boeotians ever dear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14656, line : "And one Menestheus' friend and famed compeer."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14657, line : "Medon and Iasus, Ćneas sped;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14658, line : "This sprang from Phelus, and the Athenians led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14659, line : "But hapless Medon from Oileus came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14660, line : "Him Ajax honour'd with a brother's name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14661, line : "Though born of lawless love: from home expell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14662, line : "A banish'd man, in Phylace he dwell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14663, line : "Press'd by the vengeance of an angry wife;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14664, line : "Troy ends at last his labours and his life."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14665, line : "Mecystes next Polydamas o'erthrew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14666, line : "And thee, brave Clonius, great Agenor slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14667, line : "By Paris, Deiochus inglorious dies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14668, line : "Pierced through the shoulder as he basely flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14669, line : "Polites' arm laid Echius on the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14670, line : "Stretch'd on one heap, the victors spoil the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14671, line : "The Greeks dismay'd, confused, disperse or fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14672, line : "Some seek the trench, some skulk behind the wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14673, line : "While these fly trembling, others pant for breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14674, line : "And o'er the slaughter stalks gigantic death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14675, line : "On rush'd bold Hector, gloomy as the night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14676, line : "Forbids to plunder, animates the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14677, line : "Points to the fleet: \"For, by the gods! who flies,(240)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14678, line : "Who dares but linger, by this hand he dies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14679, line : "No weeping sister his cold eye shall close,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14680, line : "No friendly hand his funeral pyre compose."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14681, line : "Who stops to plunder at this signal hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14682, line : "The birds shall tear him, and the dogs devour.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14683, line : "Furious he said; the smarting scourge resounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14684, line : "The coursers fly; the smoking chariot bounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14685, line : "The hosts rush on; loud clamours shake the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14686, line : "The horses thunder, earth and ocean roar!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14687, line : "Apollo, planted at the trench's bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14688, line : "Push'd at the bank: down sank the enormous mound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14689, line : "Roll'd in the ditch the heapy ruin lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14690, line : "A sudden road! a long and ample way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14691, line : "O'er the dread fosse (a late impervious space)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14692, line : "Now steeds, and men, and cars tumultuous pass."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14693, line : "The wondering crowds the downward level trod;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14694, line : "Before them flamed the shield, and march'd the god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14695, line : "Then with his hand he shook the mighty wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14696, line : "And lo! the turrets nod, the bulwarks fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14697, line : "Easy as when ashore an infant stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14698, line : "And draws imagined houses in the sands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14699, line : "The sportive wanton, pleased with some new play,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14700, line : "Sweeps the slight works and fashion'd domes away:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14701, line : "Thus vanish'd at thy touch, the towers and walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14702, line : "The toil of thousands in a moment falls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14704, line : "The Grecians gaze around with wild despair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14705, line : "Confused, and weary all the powers with prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14706, line : "Exhort their men, with praises, threats, commands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14707, line : "And urge the gods, with voices, eyes, and hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14708, line : "Experienced Nestor chief obtests the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14709, line : "And weeps his country with a father's eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14711, line : "\"O Jove! if ever, on his native shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14712, line : "One Greek enrich'd thy shrine with offer'd gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14713, line : "If e'er, in hope our country to behold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14714, line : "We paid the fattest firstlings of the fold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14715, line : "If e'er thou sign'st our wishes with thy nod:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14716, line : "Perform the promise of a gracious god!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14717, line : "This day preserve our navies from the flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14718, line : "And save the relics of the Grecian name.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14720, line : "Thus prayed the sage: the eternal gave consent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14721, line : "And peals of thunder shook the firmament."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14722, line : "Presumptuous Troy mistook the accepting sign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14723, line : "And catch'd new fury at the voice divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14724, line : "As, when black tempests mix the seas and skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14725, line : "The roaring deeps in watery mountains rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14726, line : "Above the sides of some tall ship ascend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14727, line : "Its womb they deluge, and its ribs they rend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14728, line : "Thus loudly roaring, and o'erpowering all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14729, line : "Mount the thick Trojans up the Grecian wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14730, line : "Legions on legions from each side arise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14731, line : "Thick sound the keels; the storm of arrows flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14732, line : "Fierce on the ships above, the cars below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14733, line : "These wield the mace, and those the javelin throw."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14735, line : "While thus the thunder of the battle raged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14736, line : "And labouring armies round the works engaged,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14737, line : "Still in the tent Patroclus sat to tend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14738, line : "The good Eurypylus, his wounded friend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14739, line : "He sprinkles healing balms, to anguish kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14740, line : "And adds discourse, the medicine of the mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14741, line : "But when he saw, ascending up the fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14742, line : "Victorious Troy; then, starting from his seat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14743, line : "With bitter groans his sorrows he express'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14744, line : "He wrings his hands, he beats his manly breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14745, line : "\"Though yet thy state require redress (he cries)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14746, line : "Depart I must: what horrors strike my eyes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14747, line : "Charged with Achilles' high command I go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14748, line : "A mournful witness of this scene of woe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14749, line : "I haste to urge him by his country's care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14750, line : "To rise in arms, and shine again in war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14751, line : "Perhaps some favouring god his soul may bend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14752, line : "The voice is powerful of a faithful friend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14754, line : "He spoke; and, speaking, swifter than the wind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14755, line : "Sprung from the tent, and left the war behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14756, line : "The embodied Greeks the fierce attack sustain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14757, line : "But strive, though numerous, to repulse in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14758, line : "Nor could the Trojans, through that firm array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14759, line : "Force to the fleet and tents the impervious way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14760, line : "As when a shipwright, with Palladian art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14761, line : "Smooths the rough wood, and levels every part;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14762, line : "With equal hand he guides his whole design,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14763, line : "By the just rule, and the directing line:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14764, line : "The martial leaders, with like skill and care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14765, line : "Preserved their line, and equal kept the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14766, line : "Brave deeds of arms through all the ranks were tried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14767, line : "And every ship sustained an equal tide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14768, line : "At one proud bark, high-towering o'er the fleet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14769, line : "Ajax the great, and godlike Hector meet;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14770, line : "For one bright prize the matchless chiefs contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14771, line : "Nor this the ships can fire, nor that defend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14772, line : "One kept the shore, and one the vessel trod;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14773, line : "That fix'd as fate, this acted by a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14774, line : "The son of Clytius in his daring hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14775, line : "The deck approaching, shakes a flaming brand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14776, line : "But, pierced by Telamon's huge lance, expires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14777, line : "Thundering he falls, and drops the extinguish'd fires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14778, line : "Great Hector view'd him with a sad survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14779, line : "As stretch'd in dust before the stern he lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14780, line : "\"Oh! all of Trojan, all of Lycian race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14781, line : "Stand to your arms, maintain this arduous space:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14782, line : "Lo! where the son of royal Clytius lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14783, line : "Ah, save his arms, secure his obsequies!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14785, line : "This said, his eager javelin sought the foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14786, line : "But Ajax shunn'd the meditated blow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14787, line : "Not vainly yet the forceful lance was thrown;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14788, line : "It stretch'd in dust unhappy Lycophron:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14789, line : "An exile long, sustain'd at Ajax' board,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14790, line : "A faithful servant to a foreign lord;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14791, line : "In peace, and war, for ever at his side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14792, line : "Near his loved master, as he lived, he died."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14793, line : "From the high poop he tumbles on the sand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14794, line : "And lies a lifeless load along the land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14795, line : "With anguish Ajax views the piercing sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14796, line : "And thus inflames his brother to the fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14798, line : "\"Teucer, behold! extended on the shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14799, line : "Our friend, our loved companion! now no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14800, line : "Dear as a parent, with a parent's care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14801, line : "To fight our wars he left his native air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14802, line : "This death deplored, to Hector's rage we owe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14803, line : "Revenge, revenge it on the cruel foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14804, line : "Where are those darts on which the fates attend?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14805, line : "And where the bow which Phoebus taught to bend?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14807, line : "Impatient Teucer, hastening to his aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14808, line : "Before the chief his ample bow display'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14809, line : "The well-stored quiver on his shoulders hung:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14810, line : "Then hiss'd his arrow, and the bowstring sung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14811, line : "Clytus, Pisenor's son, renown'd in fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14812, line : "(To thee, Polydamas! an honour'd name)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14813, line : "Drove through the thickest of the embattled plains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14814, line : "The startling steeds, and shook his eager reins."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14815, line : "As all on glory ran his ardent mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14816, line : "The pointed death arrests him from behind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14817, line : "Through his fair neck the thrilling arrow flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14818, line : "In youth's first bloom reluctantly he dies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14819, line : "Hurl'd from the lofty seat, at distance far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14820, line : "The headlong coursers spurn his empty car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14821, line : "Till sad Polydamas the steeds restrain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14822, line : "And gave, Astynous, to thy careful hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14823, line : "Then, fired to vengeance, rush'd amidst the foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14824, line : "Rage edged his sword, and strengthen'd every blow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14826, line : "Once more bold Teucer, in his country's cause,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14827, line : "At Hector's breast a chosen arrow draws:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14828, line : "And had the weapon found the destined way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14829, line : "Thy fall, great Trojan! had renown'd that day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14830, line : "But Hector was not doom'd to perish then:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14831, line : "The all-wise disposer of the fates of men"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14832, line : "(Imperial Jove) his present death withstands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14833, line : "Nor was such glory due to Teucer's hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14834, line : "At its full stretch as the tough string he drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14835, line : "Struck by an arm unseen, it burst in two;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14836, line : "Down dropp'd the bow: the shaft with brazen head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14837, line : "Fell innocent, and on the dust lay dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14838, line : "The astonish'd archer to great Ajax cries;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14839, line : "\"Some god prevents our destined enterprise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14840, line : "Some god, propitious to the Trojan foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14841, line : "Has, from my arm unfailing, struck the bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14842, line : "And broke the nerve my hands had twined with art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14843, line : "Strong to impel the flight of many a dart.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14845, line : "\"Since heaven commands it (Ajax made reply)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14846, line : "Dismiss the bow, and lay thy arrows by:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14847, line : "Thy arms no less suffice the lance to wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14848, line : "And quit the quiver for the ponderous shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14849, line : "In the first ranks indulge thy thirst of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14850, line : "Thy brave example shall the rest inflame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14851, line : "Fierce as they are, by long successes vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14852, line : "To force our fleet, or even a ship to gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14853, line : "Asks toil, and sweat, and blood: their utmost might"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14854, line : "Shall find its match--No more: 'tis ours to fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14856, line : "Then Teucer laid his faithless bow aside;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14857, line : "The fourfold buckler o'er his shoulder tied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14858, line : "On his brave head a crested helm he placed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14859, line : "With nodding horse-hair formidably graced;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14860, line : "A dart, whose point with brass refulgent shines,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14861, line : "The warrior wields; and his great brother joins."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14863, line : "This Hector saw, and thus express'd his joy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14864, line : "\"Ye troops of Lycia, Dardanus, and Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14865, line : "Be mindful of yourselves, your ancient fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14866, line : "And spread your glory with the navy's flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14867, line : "Jove is with us; I saw his hand, but now,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14868, line : "From the proud archer strike his vaunted bow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14869, line : "Indulgent Jove! how plain thy favours shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14870, line : "When happy nations bear the marks divine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14871, line : "How easy then, to see the sinking state"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14872, line : "Of realms accursed, deserted, reprobate!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14873, line : "Such is the fate of Greece, and such is ours:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14874, line : "Behold, ye warriors, and exert your powers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14875, line : "Death is the worst; a fate which all must try;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14876, line : "And for our country, 'tis a bliss to die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14877, line : "The gallant man, though slain in fight he be,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14878, line : "Yet leaves his nation safe, his children free;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14879, line : "Entails a debt on all the grateful state;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14880, line : "His own brave friends shall glory in his fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14881, line : "His wife live honour'd, all his race succeed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14882, line : "And late posterity enjoy the deed!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14884, line : "This roused the soul in every Trojan breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14885, line : "The godlike Ajax next his Greeks address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14887, line : "\"How long, ye warriors of the Argive race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14888, line : "(To generous Argos what a dire disgrace!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14889, line : "How long on these cursed confines will ye lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14890, line : "Yet undetermined, or to live or die?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14891, line : "What hopes remain, what methods to retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14892, line : "If once your vessels catch the Trojan fire?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14893, line : "Make how the flames approach, how near they fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14894, line : "How Hector calls, and Troy obeys his call!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14895, line : "Not to the dance that dreadful voice invites,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14896, line : "It calls to death, and all the rage of fights."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14897, line : "'Tis now no time for wisdom or debates;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14898, line : "To your own hands are trusted all your fates;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14899, line : "And better far in one decisive strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14900, line : "One day should end our labour or our life,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14901, line : "Than keep this hard-got inch of barren sands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14902, line : "Still press'd, and press'd by such inglorious hands.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14904, line : "The listening Grecians feel their leader's flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14905, line : "And every kindling bosom pants for fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14906, line : "Then mutual slaughters spread on either side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14907, line : "By Hector here the Phocian Schedius died;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14908, line : "There, pierced by Ajax, sunk Laodamas,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14909, line : "Chief of the foot, of old Antenor's race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14910, line : "Polydamas laid Otus on the sand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14911, line : "The fierce commander of the Epeian band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14912, line : "His lance bold Meges at the victor threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14913, line : "The victor, stooping, from the death withdrew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14914, line : "(That valued life, O Phoebus! was thy care)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14915, line : "But Croesmus' bosom took the flying spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14916, line : "His corpse fell bleeding on the slippery shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14917, line : "His radiant arms triumphant Meges bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14918, line : "Dolops, the son of Lampus, rushes on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14919, line : "Sprung from the race of old Laomedon,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14920, line : "And famed for prowess in a well-fought field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14921, line : "He pierced the centre of his sounding shield:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14922, line : "But Meges, Phyleus' ample breastplate wore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14923, line : "(Well-known in fight on Selle's winding shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14924, line : "For king Euphetes gave the golden mail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14925, line : "Compact, and firm with many a jointed scale)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14926, line : "Which oft, in cities storm'd, and battles won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14927, line : "Had saved the father, and now saves the son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14928, line : "Full at the Trojan's head he urged his lance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14929, line : "Where the high plumes above the helmet dance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14930, line : "New ting'd with Tyrian dye: in dust below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14931, line : "Shorn from the crest, the purple honours glow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14932, line : "Meantime their fight the Spartan king survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14933, line : "And stood by Meges' side a sudden aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14934, line : "Through Dolops' shoulder urged his forceful dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14935, line : "Which held its passage through the panting heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14936, line : "And issued at his breast. With thundering sound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14937, line : "The warrior falls, extended on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14938, line : "In rush the conquering Greeks to spoil the slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14939, line : "But Hector's voice excites his kindred train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14940, line : "The hero most, from Hicetaon sprung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14941, line : "Fierce Melanippus, gallant, brave, and young."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14942, line : "He (ere to Troy the Grecians cross'd the main)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14943, line : "Fed his large oxen on Percote's plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14944, line : "But when oppress'd, his country claim'd his care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14945, line : "Return'd to Ilion, and excell'd in war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14946, line : "For this, in Priam's court, he held his place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14947, line : "Beloved no less than Priam's royal race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14948, line : "Him Hector singled, as his troops he led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14949, line : "And thus inflamed him, pointing to the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14951, line : "\"Lo, Melanippus! lo, where Dolops lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14952, line : "And is it thus our royal kinsman dies?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14953, line : "O'ermatch'd he falls; to two at once a prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14954, line : "And lo! they bear the bloody arms away!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14955, line : "Come on--a distant war no longer wage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14956, line : "But hand to hand thy country's foes engage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14957, line : "Till Greece at once, and all her glory end;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14958, line : "Or Ilion from her towery height descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14959, line : "Heaved from the lowest stone; and bury all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14960, line : "In one sad sepulchre, one common fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14962, line : "Hector (this said) rush'd forward on the foes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14963, line : "With equal ardour Melanippus glows:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14964, line : "Then Ajax thus--\"O Greeks! respect your fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14965, line : "Respect yourselves, and learn an honest shame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14966, line : "Let mutual reverence mutual warmth inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14967, line : "And catch from breast to breast the noble fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14968, line : "On valour's side the odds of combat lie;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14969, line : "The brave live glorious, or lamented die;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14970, line : "The wretch that trembles in the field of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14971, line : "Meets death, and worse than death, eternal shame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14973, line : "His generous sense he not in vain imparts;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14974, line : "It sunk, and rooted in the Grecian hearts:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14975, line : "They join, they throng, they thicken at his call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14976, line : "And flank the navy with a brazen wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14977, line : "Shields touching shields, in order blaze above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14978, line : "And stop the Trojans, though impell'd by Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14979, line : "The fiery Spartan first, with loud applause."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14980, line : "Warms the bold son of Nestor in his cause."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14981, line : "\"Is there (he said) in arms a youth like you,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14982, line : "So strong to fight, so active to pursue?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14983, line : "Why stand you distant, nor attempt a deed?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14984, line : "Lift the bold lance, and make some Trojan bleed.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14986, line : "He said; and backward to the lines retired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14987, line : "Forth rush'd the youth with martial fury fired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14988, line : "Beyond the foremost ranks; his lance he threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14989, line : "And round the black battalions cast his view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14990, line : "The troops of Troy recede with sudden fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14991, line : "While the swift javelin hiss'd along in air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14992, line : "Advancing Melanippus met the dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14993, line : "With his bold breast, and felt it in his heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14994, line : "Thundering he falls; his falling arms resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14995, line : "And his broad buckler rings against the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14996, line : "The victor leaps upon his prostrate prize:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14997, line : "Thus on a roe the well-breath'd beagle flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14998, line : "And rends his side, fresh-bleeding with the dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 14999, line : "The distant hunter sent into his heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15000, line : "Observing Hector to the rescue flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15001, line : "Bold as he was, Antilochus withdrew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15002, line : "So when a savage, ranging o'er the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15003, line : "Has torn the shepherd's dog, or shepherd's swain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15004, line : "While conscious of the deed, he glares around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15005, line : "And hears the gathering multitude resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15006, line : "Timely he flies the yet-untasted food,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15007, line : "And gains the friendly shelter of the wood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15008, line : "So fears the youth; all Troy with shouts pursue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15009, line : "While stones and darts in mingled tempest flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15010, line : "But enter'd in the Grecian ranks, he turns"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15011, line : "His manly breast, and with new fury burns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15013, line : "Now on the fleet the tides of Trojans drove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15014, line : "Fierce to fulfil the stern decrees of Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15015, line : "The sire of gods, confirming Thetis' prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15016, line : "The Grecian ardour quench'd in deep despair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15017, line : "But lifts to glory Troy's prevailing bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15018, line : "Swells all their hearts, and strengthens all their hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15019, line : "On Ida's top he waits with longing eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15020, line : "To view the navy blazing to the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15021, line : "Then, nor till then, the scale of war shall turn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15022, line : "The Trojans fly, and conquer'd Ilion burn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15023, line : "These fates revolved in his almighty mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15024, line : "He raises Hector to the work design'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15025, line : "Bids him with more than mortal fury glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15026, line : "And drives him, like a lightning, on the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15027, line : "So Mars, when human crimes for vengeance call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15028, line : "Shakes his huge javelin, and whole armies fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15029, line : "Not with more rage a conflagration rolls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15030, line : "Wraps the vast mountains, and involves the poles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15031, line : "He foams with wrath; beneath his gloomy brow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15032, line : "Like fiery meteors his red eye-balls glow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15033, line : "The radiant helmet on his temple burns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15034, line : "Waves when he nods, and lightens as he turns:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15035, line : "For Jove his splendour round the chief had thrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15036, line : "And cast the blaze of both the hosts on one."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15037, line : "Unhappy glories! for his fate was near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15038, line : "Due to stern Pallas, and Pelides' spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15039, line : "Yet Jove deferr'd the death he was to pay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15040, line : "And gave what fate allow'd, the honours of a day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15042, line : "Now all on fire for fame, his breast, his eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15043, line : "Burn at each foe, and single every prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15044, line : "Still at the closest ranks, the thickest fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15045, line : "He points his ardour, and exerts his might."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15046, line : "The Grecian phalanx, moveless as a tower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15047, line : "On all sides batter'd, yet resists his power:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15048, line : "So some tall rock o'erhangs the hoary main,(241)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15049, line : "By winds assail'd, by billows beat in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15050, line : "Unmoved it hears, above, the tempest blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15051, line : "And sees the watery mountains break below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15052, line : "Girt in surrounding flames, he seems to fall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15053, line : "Like fire from Jove, and bursts upon them all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15054, line : "Bursts as a wave that from the cloud impends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15055, line : "And, swell'd with tempests, on the ship descends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15056, line : "White are the decks with foam; the winds aloud"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15057, line : "Howl o'er the masts, and sing through every shroud:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15058, line : "Pale, trembling, tired, the sailors freeze with fears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15059, line : "And instant death on every wave appears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15060, line : "So pale the Greeks the eyes of Hector meet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15061, line : "The chief so thunders, and so shakes the fleet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15063, line : "As when a lion, rushing from his den,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15064, line : "Amidst the plain of some wide-water'd fen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15065, line : "(Where numerous oxen, as at ease they feed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15066, line : "At large expatiate o'er the ranker mead)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15067, line : "Leaps on the herds before the herdsman's eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15068, line : "The trembling herdsman far to distance flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15069, line : "Some lordly bull (the rest dispersed and fled)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15070, line : "He singles out; arrests, and lays him dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15071, line : "Thus from the rage of Jove-like Hector flew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15072, line : "All Greece in heaps; but one he seized, and slew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15073, line : "Mycenian Periphes, a mighty name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15074, line : "In wisdom great, in arms well known to fame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15075, line : "The minister of stern Eurystheus' ire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15076, line : "Against Alcides, Copreus was his sire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15077, line : "The son redeem'd the honours of the race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15078, line : "A son as generous as the sire was base;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15079, line : "O'er all his country's youth conspicuous far"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15080, line : "In every virtue, or of peace or war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15081, line : "But doom'd to Hector's stronger force to yield!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15082, line : "Against the margin of his ample shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15083, line : "He struck his hasty foot: his heels up-sprung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15084, line : "Supine he fell; his brazen helmet rung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15085, line : "On the fallen chief the invading Trojan press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15086, line : "And plunged the pointed javelin in his breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15087, line : "His circling friends, who strove to guard too late"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15088, line : "The unhappy hero, fled, or shared his fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15090, line : "Chased from the foremost line, the Grecian train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15091, line : "Now man the next, receding toward the main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15092, line : "Wedged in one body at the tents they stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15093, line : "Wall'd round with sterns, a gloomy, desperate band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15094, line : "Now manly shame forbids the inglorious flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15095, line : "Now fear itself confines them to the fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15096, line : "Man courage breathes in man; but Nestor most"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15097, line : "(The sage preserver of the Grecian host)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15098, line : "Exhorts, adjures, to guard these utmost shores;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15099, line : "And by their parents, by themselves implores."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15101, line : "\"Oh friends! be men: your generous breasts inflame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15102, line : "With mutual honour, and with mutual shame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15103, line : "Think of your hopes, your fortunes; all the care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15104, line : "Your wives, your infants, and your parents share:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15105, line : "Think of each living father's reverend head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15106, line : "Think of each ancestor with glory dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15107, line : "Absent, by me they speak, by me they sue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15108, line : "They ask their safety, and their fame, from you:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15109, line : "The gods their fates on this one action lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15110, line : "And all are lost, if you desert the day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15112, line : "He spoke, and round him breathed heroic fires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15113, line : "Minerva seconds what the sage inspires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15114, line : "The mist of darkness Jove around them threw"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15115, line : "She clear'd, restoring all the war to view;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15116, line : "A sudden ray shot beaming o'er the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15117, line : "And show'd the shores, the navy, and the main:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15118, line : "Hector they saw, and all who fly, or fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15119, line : "The scene wide-opening to the blaze of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15120, line : "First of the field great Ajax strikes their eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15121, line : "His port majestic, and his ample size:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15122, line : "A ponderous mace with studs of iron crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15123, line : "Full twenty cubits long, he swings around;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15124, line : "Nor fights, like others, fix'd to certain stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15125, line : "But looks a moving tower above the bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15126, line : "High on the decks with vast gigantic stride,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15127, line : "The godlike hero stalks from side to side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15128, line : "So when a horseman from the watery mead"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15129, line : "(Skill'd in the manage of the bounding steed)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15130, line : "Drives four fair coursers, practised to obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15131, line : "To some great city through the public way;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15132, line : "Safe in his art, as side by side they run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15133, line : "He shifts his seat, and vaults from one to one;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15134, line : "And now to this, and now to that he flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15135, line : "Admiring numbers follow with their eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15137, line : "From ship to ship thus Ajax swiftly flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15138, line : "No less the wonder of the warring crew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15139, line : "As furious, Hector thunder'd threats aloud,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15140, line : "And rush'd enraged before the Trojan crowd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15141, line : "Then swift invades the ships, whose beaky prores"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15142, line : "Lay rank'd contiguous on the bending shores;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15143, line : "So the strong eagle from his airy height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15144, line : "Who marks the swans' or cranes' embodied flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15145, line : "Stoops down impetuous, while they light for food,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15146, line : "And, stooping, darkens with his wings the flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15147, line : "Jove leads him on with his almighty hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15148, line : "And breathes fierce spirits in his following band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15149, line : "The warring nations meet, the battle roars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15150, line : "Thick beats the combat on the sounding prores."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15151, line : "Thou wouldst have thought, so furious was their fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15152, line : "No force could tame them, and no toil could tire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15153, line : "As if new vigour from new fights they won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15154, line : "And the long battle was but then begun."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15155, line : "Greece, yet unconquer'd, kept alive the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15156, line : "Secure of death, confiding in despair:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15157, line : "Troy in proud hopes already view'd the main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15158, line : "Bright with the blaze, and red with heroes slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15159, line : "Like strength is felt from hope, and from despair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15160, line : "And each contends, as his were all the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15162, line : "\"Twas thou, bold Hector! whose resistless hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15163, line : "First seized a ship on that contested strand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15164, line : "The same which dead Protesilaus bore,(242)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15165, line : "The first that touch'd the unhappy Trojan shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15166, line : "For this in arms the warring nations stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15167, line : "And bathed their generous breasts with mutual blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15168, line : "No room to poise the lance or bend the bow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15169, line : "But hand to hand, and man to man, they grow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15170, line : "Wounded, they wound; and seek each other's hearts"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15171, line : "With falchions, axes, swords, and shorten'd darts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15172, line : "The falchions ring, shields rattle, axes sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15173, line : "Swords flash in air, or glitter on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15174, line : "With streaming blood the slippery shores are dyed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15175, line : "And slaughter'd heroes swell the dreadful tide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15177, line : "Still raging, Hector with his ample hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15178, line : "Grasps the high stern, and gives this loud command:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15180, line : "[Illustration: AJAX DEFENDING THE GREEK SHIPS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15182, line : "AJAX DEFENDING THE GREEK SHIPS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15185, line : "\"Haste, bring the flames! that toil of ten long years"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15186, line : "Is finished; and the day desired appears!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15187, line : "This happy day with acclamations greet,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15188, line : "Bright with destruction of yon hostile fleet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15189, line : "The coward-counsels of a timorous throng"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15190, line : "Of reverend dotards check'd our glory long:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15191, line : "Too long Jove lull'd us with lethargic charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15192, line : "But now in peals of thunder calls to arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15193, line : "In this great day he crowns our full desires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15194, line : "Wakes all our force, and seconds all our fires.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15196, line : "He spoke--the warriors at his fierce command"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15197, line : "Pour a new deluge on the Grecian band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15198, line : "Even Ajax paused, (so thick the javelins fly,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15199, line : "Stepp'd back, and doubted or to live or die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15200, line : "Yet, where the oars are placed, he stands to wait"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15201, line : "What chief approaching dares attempt his fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15202, line : "Even to the last his naval charge defends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15203, line : "Now shakes his spear, now lifts, and now protends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15204, line : "Even yet, the Greeks with piercing shouts inspires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15205, line : "Amidst attacks, and deaths, and darts, and fires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15207, line : "\"O friends! O heroes! names for ever dear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15208, line : "Once sons of Mars, and thunderbolts of war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15209, line : "Ah! yet be mindful of your old renown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15210, line : "Your great forefathers' virtues and your own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15211, line : "What aids expect you in this utmost strait?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15212, line : "What bulwarks rising between you and fate?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15213, line : "No aids, no bulwarks your retreat attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15214, line : "No friends to help, no city to defend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15215, line : "This spot is all you have, to lose or keep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15216, line : "There stand the Trojans, and here rolls the deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15217, line : "'Tis hostile ground you tread; your native lands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15218, line : "Far, far from hence: your fates are in your hands.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15220, line : "Raging he spoke; nor further wastes his breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15221, line : "But turns his javelin to the work of death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15222, line : "Whate'er bold Trojan arm'd his daring hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15223, line : "Against the sable ships, with flaming brands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15224, line : "So well the chief his naval weapon sped,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15225, line : "The luckless warrior at his stern lay dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15226, line : "Full twelve, the boldest, in a moment fell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15227, line : "Sent by great Ajax to the shades of hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15229, line : "[Illustration: CASTOR AND POLLUX.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15231, line : "CASTOR AND POLLUX."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15237, line : "BOOK XVI."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15240, line : "ARGUMENT"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15242, line : "THE SIXTH BATTLE, THE ACTS AND DEATH OF PATROCLUS"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15244, line : "Patroclus (in pursuance of the request of Nestor in the eleventh book)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15245, line : "entreats Achilles to suffer him to go to the assistance of the Greeks with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15246, line : "Achilles' troops and armour. He agrees to it, but at the same time charges"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15247, line : "him to content himself with rescuing the fleet, without further pursuit of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15248, line : "the enemy. The armour, horses, soldiers, and officers are described."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15249, line : "Achilles offers a libation for the success of his friend, after which"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15250, line : "Patroclus leads the Myrmidons to battle. The Trojans, at the sight of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15251, line : "Patroclus in Achilles' armour, taking him for that hero, are cast into the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15252, line : "uttermost consternation; he beats them off from the vessels, Hector"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15253, line : "himself flies, Sarpedon is killed, though Jupiter was averse to his fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15254, line : "Several other particulars of the battle are described; in the heat of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15255, line : "which, Patroclus, neglecting the orders of Achilles, pursues the foe to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15256, line : "the walls of Troy, where Apollo repulses and disarms him, Euphorbus wounds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15257, line : "him, and Hector kills him, which concludes the book."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15259, line : "So warr'd both armies on the ensanguined shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15260, line : "While the black vessels smoked with human gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15261, line : "Meantime Patroclus to Achilles flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15262, line : "The streaming tears fall copious from his eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15263, line : "Not faster, trickling to the plains below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15264, line : "From the tall rock the sable waters flow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15265, line : "Divine Pelides, with compassion moved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15266, line : "Thus spoke, indulgent, to his best beloved:(243)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15268, line : "\"Patroclus, say, what grief thy bosom bears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15269, line : "That flows so fast in these unmanly tears?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15270, line : "No girl, no infant whom the mother keeps"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15271, line : "From her loved breast, with fonder passion weeps;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15272, line : "Not more the mother's soul, that infant warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15273, line : "Clung to her knees, and reaching at her arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15274, line : "Than thou hast mine! Oh tell me, to what end"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15275, line : "Thy melting sorrows thus pursue thy friend?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15277, line : "\"Griev'st thou for me, or for, my martial band?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15278, line : "Or come sad tidings from our native land?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15279, line : "Our fathers live (our first, most tender care),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15280, line : "Thy good Menoetius breathes the vital air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15281, line : "And hoary Peleus yet extends his days;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15282, line : "Pleased in their age to hear their children's praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15283, line : "Or may some meaner cause thy pity claim?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15284, line : "Perhaps yon relics of the Grecian name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15285, line : "Doom'd in their ships to sink by fire and sword,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15286, line : "And pay the forfeit of their haughty lord?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15287, line : "Whate'er the cause, reveal thy secret care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15288, line : "And speak those sorrows which a friend would share.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15289, line : "A sigh that instant from his bosom broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15290, line : "Another follow'd, and Patroclus spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15292, line : "\"Let Greece at length with pity touch thy breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15293, line : "Thyself a Greek; and, once, of Greeks the best!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15294, line : "Lo! every chief that might her fate prevent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15295, line : "Lies pierced with wounds, and bleeding in his tent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15296, line : "Eurypylus, Tydides, Atreus' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15297, line : "And wise Ulysses, at the navy groan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15298, line : "More for their country's wounds than for their own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15299, line : "Their pain soft arts of pharmacy can ease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15300, line : "Thy breast alone no lenitives appease."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15301, line : "May never rage like thine my soul enslave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15302, line : "O great in vain! unprofitably brave!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15303, line : "Thy country slighted in her last distress,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15304, line : "What friend, what man, from thee shall hope redress?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15305, line : "No--men unborn, and ages yet behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15306, line : "Shall curse that fierce, that unforgiving mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15308, line : "\"O man unpitying! if of man thy race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15309, line : "But sure thou spring'st not from a soft embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15310, line : "Nor ever amorous hero caused thy birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15311, line : "Nor ever tender goddess brought thee forth:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15312, line : "Some rugged rock's hard entrails gave thee form,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15313, line : "And raging seas produced thee in a storm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15314, line : "A soul well suiting that tempestuous kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15315, line : "So rough thy manners, so untamed thy mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15317, line : "\"If some dire oracle thy breast alarm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15318, line : "If aught from Jove, or Thetis, stop thy arm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15319, line : "Some beam of comfort yet on Greece may shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15320, line : "If I but lead the Myrmidonian line:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15321, line : "Clad in thy dreadful arms if I appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15322, line : "Proud Troy shall tremble, and desert the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15323, line : "Without thy person Greece shall win the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15324, line : "And thy mere image chase her foes away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15325, line : "Press'd by fresh forces, her o'erlabour'd train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15326, line : "Shall quit the ships, and Greece respire again.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15327, line : "Thus, blind to fate! with supplicating breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15328, line : "Thou begg'st his arms, and in his arms thy death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15329, line : "Unfortunately good! a boding sigh"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15330, line : "Thy friend return'd; and with it, this reply:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15331, line : "\"Patroclus! thy Achilles knows no fears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15332, line : "Nor words from Jove nor oracles he hears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15333, line : "Nor aught a mother's caution can suggest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15334, line : "The tyrant's pride lies rooted in my breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15335, line : "My wrongs, my wrongs, my constant thought engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15336, line : "Those, my sole oracles, inspire my rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15337, line : "I made him tyrant: gave him power to wrong"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15338, line : "Even my: I felt it; and shall feel it long."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15339, line : "The maid, my black-eyed maid, he forced away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15340, line : "Due to the toils of many a well-fought day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15341, line : "Due to my conquest of her father's reign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15342, line : "Due to the votes of all the Grecian train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15343, line : "From me he forced her; me, the bold and brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15344, line : "Disgraced, dishonour'd, like the meanest slave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15345, line : "But bear we this--the wrongs I grieve are past;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15346, line : "'Tis time our fury should relent at last:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15347, line : "I fix'd its date; the day I wish'd appears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15348, line : "How Hector to my ships his battle bears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15349, line : "The flames my eyes, the shouts invade my ears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15350, line : "Go then, Patroclus! court fair honour's charms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15351, line : "In Troy's famed fields, and in Achilles' arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15352, line : "Lead forth my martial Myrmidons to fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15353, line : "Go save the fleets, and conquer in my right."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15354, line : "See the thin relics of their baffled band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15355, line : "At the last edge of yon deserted land!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15356, line : "Behold all Ilion on their ships descends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15357, line : "How the cloud blackens, how the storm impends!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15358, line : "It was not thus, when, at my sight amazed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15359, line : "Troy saw and trembled, as this helmet blazed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15360, line : "Had not the injurious king our friendship lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15361, line : "Yon ample trench had buried half her host."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15362, line : "No camps, no bulwarks now the Trojans fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15363, line : "Those are not dreadful, no Achilles there;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15364, line : "No longer flames the lance of Tydeus' son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15365, line : "No more your general calls his heroes on:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15366, line : "Hector, alone, I hear; his dreadful breath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15367, line : "Commands your slaughter, or proclaims your death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15368, line : "Yet now, Patroclus, issue to the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15369, line : "Now save the ships, the rising fires restrain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15370, line : "And give the Greeks to visit Greece again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15371, line : "But heed my words, and mark a friend's command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15372, line : "Who trusts his fame and honours in thy hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15373, line : "And from thy deeds expects the Achaian host"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15374, line : "Shall render back the beauteous maid he lost:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15375, line : "Rage uncontroll'd through all the hostile crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15376, line : "But touch not Hector, Hector is my due."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15377, line : "Though Jove in thunder should command the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15378, line : "Be just, consult my glory, and forbear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15379, line : "The fleet once saved, desist from further chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15380, line : "Nor lead to Ilion's walls the Grecian race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15381, line : "Some adverse god thy rashness may destroy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15382, line : "Some god, like Phoebus, ever kind to Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15383, line : "Let Greece, redeem'd from this destructive strait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15384, line : "Do her own work; and leave the rest to fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15385, line : "O! would to all the immortal powers above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15386, line : "Apollo, Pallas, and almighty Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15387, line : "That not one Trojan might be left alive,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15388, line : "And not a Greek of all the race survive:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15389, line : "Might only we the vast destruction shun,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15390, line : "And only we destroy the accursed town!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15391, line : "Such conference held the chiefs; while on the strand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15392, line : "Great Jove with conquest crown'd the Trojan band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15393, line : "Ajax no more the sounding storm sustain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15394, line : "So thick the darts an iron tempest rain'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15395, line : "On his tired arm the weighty buckler hung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15396, line : "His hollow helm with falling javelins rung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15397, line : "His breath, in quick short pantings, comes and goes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15398, line : "And painful sweat from all his members flows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15399, line : "Spent and o'erpower'd, he barely breathes at most;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15400, line : "Yet scarce an army stirs him from his post;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15401, line : "Dangers on dangers all around him glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15402, line : "And toil to toil, and woe succeeds to woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15404, line : "Say, Muses, throned above the starry frame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15405, line : "How first the navy blazed with Trojan flame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15407, line : "Stern Hector waved his sword, and standing near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15408, line : "Where furious Ajax plied his ashen spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15409, line : "Full on the lance a stroke so justly sped,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15410, line : "That the broad falchion lopp'd its brazen head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15411, line : "His pointless spear the warrior shakes in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15412, line : "The brazen head falls sounding on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15413, line : "Great Ajax saw, and own'd the hand divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15414, line : "Confessing Jove, and trembling at the sign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15415, line : "Warn'd he retreats. Then swift from all sides pour"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15416, line : "The hissing brands; thick streams the fiery shower;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15417, line : "O'er the high stern the curling volumes rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15418, line : "And sheets of rolling smoke involve the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15420, line : "Divine Achilles view'd the rising flames,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15421, line : "And smote his thigh, and thus aloud exclaims:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15422, line : "\"Arm, arm, Patroclus! Lo, the blaze aspires!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15423, line : "The glowing ocean reddens with the fires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15424, line : "Arm, ere our vessels catch the spreading flame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15425, line : "Arm, ere the Grecians be no more a name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15426, line : "I haste to bring the troops.\"--The hero said;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15427, line : "The friend with ardour and with joy obey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15429, line : "He cased his limbs in brass; and first around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15430, line : "His manly legs, with silver buckles bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15431, line : "The clasping greaves; then to his breast applies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15432, line : "The flaming cuirass of a thousand dyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15433, line : "Emblazed with studs of gold his falchion shone"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15434, line : "In the rich belt, as in a starry zone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15435, line : "Achilles' shield his ample shoulders spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15436, line : "Achilles' helmet nodded o'er his head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15437, line : "Adorn'd in all his terrible array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15438, line : "He flash'd around intolerable day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15439, line : "Alone untouch'd, Pelides' javelin stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15440, line : "Not to be poised but by Pelides' hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15441, line : "From Pelion's shady brow the plant entire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15442, line : "Old Chiron rent, and shaped it for his sire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15443, line : "Whose son's great arm alone the weapon wields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15444, line : "The death of heroes, and the dread of fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15446, line : "[Illustration: Buckles.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15448, line : "Buckles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15451, line : "The brave Automedon (an honour'd name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15452, line : "The second to his lord in love and fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15453, line : "In peace his friend, and partner of the war)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15454, line : "The winged coursers harness'd to the car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15455, line : "Xanthus and Balius, of immortal breed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15456, line : "Sprung from the wind, and like the wind in speed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15457, line : "Whom the wing'd harpy, swift Podarge, bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15458, line : "By Zephyr pregnant on the breezy shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15459, line : "Swift Pedasus was added to their side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15460, line : "(Once great Aetion's, now Achilles' pride)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15461, line : "Who, like in strength, in swiftness, and in grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15462, line : "A mortal courser match'd the immortal race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15464, line : "Achilles speeds from tent to tent, and warms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15465, line : "His hardy Myrmidons to blood and arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15466, line : "All breathing death, around the chief they stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15467, line : "A grim, terrific, formidable band:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15468, line : "Grim as voracious wolves, that seek the springs(244)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15469, line : "When scalding thirst their burning bowels wrings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15470, line : "When some tall stag, fresh-slaughtered in the wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15471, line : "Has drench'd their wide insatiate throats with blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15472, line : "To the black fount they rush, a hideous throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15473, line : "With paunch distended, and with lolling tongue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15474, line : "Fire fills their eye, their black jaws belch the gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15475, line : "And gorged with slaughter still they thirst for more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15476, line : "Like furious, rush'd the Myrmidonian crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15477, line : "Such their dread strength, and such their deathful view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15479, line : "High in the midst the great Achilles stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15480, line : "Directs their order, and the war commands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15481, line : "He, loved of Jove, had launch'd for Ilion's shores"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15482, line : "Full fifty vessels, mann'd with fifty oars:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15483, line : "Five chosen leaders the fierce bands obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15484, line : "Himself supreme in valour, as in sway."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15486, line : "First march'd Menestheus, of celestial birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15487, line : "Derived from thee, whose waters wash the earth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15488, line : "Divine Sperchius! Jove-descended flood!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15489, line : "A mortal mother mixing with a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15490, line : "Such was Menestheus, but miscall'd by fame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15491, line : "The son of Borus, that espoused the dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15493, line : "Eudorus next; whom Polymele the gay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15494, line : "Famed in the graceful dance, produced to-day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15495, line : "Her, sly Cellenius loved: on her would gaze,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15496, line : "As with swift step she form'd the running maze:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15497, line : "To her high chamber from Diana's quire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15498, line : "The god pursued her, urged, and crown'd his fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15499, line : "The son confess'd his father's heavenly race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15500, line : "And heir'd his mother's swiftness in the chase."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15501, line : "Strong Echecleus, bless'd in all those charms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15502, line : "That pleased a god, succeeded to her arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15503, line : "Not conscious of those loves, long hid from fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15504, line : "With gifts of price he sought and won the dame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15505, line : "Her secret offspring to her sire she bare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15506, line : "Her sire caress'd him with a parent's care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15508, line : "Pisander follow'd; matchless in his art"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15509, line : "To wing the spear, or aim the distant dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15510, line : "No hand so sure of all the Emathian line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15511, line : "Or if a surer, great Patroclus! thine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15513, line : "The fourth by Phoenix' grave command was graced,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15514, line : "Laerces' valiant offspring led the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15516, line : "Soon as Achilles with superior care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15517, line : "Had call'd the chiefs, and order'd all the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15518, line : "This stern remembrance to his troops he gave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15519, line : "\"Ye far-famed Myrmidons, ye fierce and brave!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15520, line : "Think with what threats you dared the Trojan throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15521, line : "Think what reproach these ears endured so long;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15522, line : "'Stern son of Peleus, (thus ye used to say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15523, line : "While restless, raging, in your ships you lay)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15524, line : "Oh nursed with gall, unknowing how to yield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15525, line : "Whose rage defrauds us of so famed a field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15526, line : "If that dire fury must for ever burn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15527, line : "What make we here? Return, ye chiefs, return!'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15528, line : "Such were your words--Now, warriors! grieve no more,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15529, line : "Lo there the Trojans; bathe your swords in gore!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15530, line : "This day shall give you all your soul demands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15531, line : "Glut all your hearts, and weary all your hands!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15533, line : "[Illustration: DIANA.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15535, line : "DIANA."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15538, line : "Thus while he roused the fire in every breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15539, line : "Close and more close the listening cohorts press'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15540, line : "Ranks wedged in ranks; of arms a steely ring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15541, line : "Still grows, and spreads, and thickens round the king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15542, line : "As when a circling wall the builder forms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15543, line : "Of strength defensive against wind and storms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15544, line : "Compacted stones the thickening work compose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15545, line : "And round him wide the rising structure grows:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15546, line : "So helm to helm, and crest to crest they throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15547, line : "Shield urged on shield, and man drove man along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15548, line : "Thick, undistinguish'd plumes, together join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15549, line : "Float in one sea, and wave before the wind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15551, line : "Far o'er the rest in glittering pomp appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15552, line : "There bold Automedon, Patroclus here;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15553, line : "Brothers in arms, with equal fury fired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15554, line : "Two friends, two bodies with one soul inspired."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15556, line : "But mindful of the gods, Achilles went"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15557, line : "To the rich coffer in his shady tent;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15558, line : "There lay on heaps his various garments roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15559, line : "And costly furs, and carpets stiff with gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15560, line : "(The presents of the silver-footed dame)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15561, line : "From thence he took a bowl, of antique frame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15562, line : "Which never man had stained with ruddy wine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15563, line : "Nor raised in offerings to the power divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15564, line : "But Peleus' son; and Peleus' son to none"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15565, line : "Had raised in offerings, but to Jove alone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15566, line : "This tinged with sulphur, sacred first to flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15567, line : "He purged; and wash'd it in the running stream."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15568, line : "Then cleansed his hands; and fixing for a space"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15569, line : "His eyes on heaven, his feet upon the place"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15570, line : "Of sacrifice, the purple draught he pour'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15571, line : "Forth in the midst; and thus the god implored:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15573, line : "\"O thou supreme! high-throned all height above!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15574, line : "O great Pelasgic, Dodonaean Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15575, line : "Who 'midst surrounding frosts, and vapours chill,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15576, line : "Presid'st on bleak Dodona's vocal hill:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15577, line : "(Whose groves the Selli, race austere! surround,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15578, line : "Their feet unwash'd, their slumbers on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15579, line : "Who hear, from rustling oaks, thy dark decrees;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15580, line : "And catch the fates, low-whispered in the breeze;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15581, line : "Hear, as of old! Thou gav'st, at Thetis' prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15582, line : "Glory to me, and to the Greeks despair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15583, line : "Lo, to the dangers of the fighting field"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15584, line : "The best, the dearest of my friends, I yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15585, line : "Though still determined, to my ships confined;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15586, line : "Patroclus gone, I stay but half behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15587, line : "Oh! be his guard thy providential care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15588, line : "Confirm his heart, and string his arm to war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15589, line : "Press'd by his single force let Hector see"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15590, line : "His fame in arms not owing all to me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15591, line : "But when the fleets are saved from foes and fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15592, line : "Let him with conquest and renown retire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15593, line : "Preserve his arms, preserve his social train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15594, line : "And safe return him to these eyes again!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15596, line : "Great Jove consents to half the chief's request,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15597, line : "But heaven's eternal doom denies the rest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15598, line : "To free the fleet was granted to his prayer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15599, line : "His safe return, the winds dispersed in air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15600, line : "Back to his tent the stern Achilles flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15601, line : "And waits the combat with impatient eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15603, line : "Meanwhile the troops beneath Patroclus' care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15604, line : "Invade the Trojans, and commence the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15605, line : "As wasps, provoked by children in their play,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15606, line : "Pour from their mansions by the broad highway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15607, line : "In swarms the guiltless traveller engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15608, line : "Whet all their stings, and call forth all their rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15609, line : "All rise in arms, and, with a general cry,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15610, line : "Assert their waxen domes, and buzzing progeny."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15611, line : "Thus from the tents the fervent legion swarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15612, line : "So loud their clamours, and so keen their arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15613, line : "Their rising rage Patroclus' breath inspires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15614, line : "Who thus inflames them with heroic fires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15616, line : "\"O warriors, partners of Achilles' praise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15617, line : "Be mindful of your deeds in ancient days;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15618, line : "Your godlike master let your acts proclaim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15619, line : "And add new glories to his mighty name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15620, line : "Think your Achilles sees you fight: be brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15621, line : "And humble the proud monarch whom you save.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15623, line : "Joyful they heard, and kindling as he spoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15624, line : "Flew to the fleet, involved in fire and smoke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15625, line : "From shore to shore the doubling shouts resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15626, line : "The hollow ships return a deeper sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15627, line : "The war stood still, and all around them gazed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15628, line : "When great Achilles' shining armour blazed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15629, line : "Troy saw, and thought the dread Achilles nigh,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15630, line : "At once they see, they tremble, and they fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15632, line : "Then first thy spear, divine Patroclus! flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15633, line : "Where the war raged, and where the tumult grew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15634, line : "Close to the stern of that famed ship which bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15635, line : "Unbless'd Protesilaus to Ilion's shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15636, line : "The great Paeonian, bold Pyrechmes stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15637, line : "(Who led his bands from Axius' winding flood;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15638, line : "His shoulder-blade receives the fatal wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15639, line : "The groaning warrior pants upon the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15640, line : "His troops, that see their country's glory slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15641, line : "Fly diverse, scatter'd o'er the distant plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15642, line : "Patroclus' arm forbids the spreading fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15643, line : "And from the half-burn'd ship proud Troy retires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15644, line : "Clear'd from the smoke the joyful navy lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15645, line : "In heaps on heaps the foe tumultuous flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15646, line : "Triumphant Greece her rescued decks ascends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15647, line : "And loud acclaim the starry region rends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15648, line : "So when thick clouds enwrap the mountain's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15649, line : "O'er heaven's expanse like one black ceiling spread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15650, line : "Sudden the Thunderer, with a flashing ray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15651, line : "Bursts through the darkness, and lets down the day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15652, line : "The hills shine out, the rocks in prospect rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15653, line : "And streams, and vales, and forests, strike the eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15654, line : "The smiling scene wide opens to the sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15655, line : "And all the unmeasured ether flames with light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15657, line : "But Troy repulsed, and scatter'd o'er the plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15658, line : "Forced from the navy, yet the fight maintains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15659, line : "Now every Greek some hostile hero slew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15660, line : "But still the foremost, bold Patroclus flew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15661, line : "As Areilycus had turn'd him round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15662, line : "Sharp in his thigh he felt the piercing wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15663, line : "The brazen-pointed spear, with vigour thrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15664, line : "The thigh transfix'd, and broke the brittle bone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15665, line : "Headlong he fell. Next, Thoas was thy chance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15666, line : "Thy breast, unarm'd, received the Spartan lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15667, line : "Phylides' dart (as Amphidus drew nigh)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15668, line : "His blow prevented, and transpierced his thigh,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15669, line : "Tore all the brawn, and rent the nerves away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15670, line : "In darkness, and in death, the warrior lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15672, line : "In equal arms two sons of Nestor stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15673, line : "And two bold brothers of the Lycian band:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15674, line : "By great Antilochus, Atymnius dies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15675, line : "Pierced in the flank, lamented youth! he lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15676, line : "Kind Maris, bleeding in his brother's wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15677, line : "Defends the breathless carcase on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15678, line : "Furious he flies, his murderer to engage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15679, line : "But godlike Thrasimed prevents his rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15680, line : "Between his arm and shoulder aims a blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15681, line : "His arm falls spouting on the dust below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15682, line : "He sinks, with endless darkness cover'd o'er:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15683, line : "And vents his soul, effused with gushing gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15685, line : "Slain by two brothers, thus two brothers bleed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15686, line : "Sarpedon's friends, Amisodarus' seed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15687, line : "Amisodarus, who, by Furies led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15688, line : "The bane of men, abhorr'd Chimaera bred;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15689, line : "Skill'd in the dart in vain, his sons expire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15690, line : "And pay the forfeit of their guilty sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15692, line : "Stopp'd in the tumult Cleobulus lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15693, line : "Beneath Oileus' arm, a living prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15694, line : "A living prize not long the Trojan stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15695, line : "The thirsty falchion drank his reeking blood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15696, line : "Plunged in his throat the smoking weapon lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15697, line : "Black death, and fate unpitying, seal his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15699, line : "Amid the ranks, with mutual thirst of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15700, line : "Lycon the brave, and fierce Peneleus came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15701, line : "In vain their javelins at each other flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15702, line : "Now, met in arms, their eager swords they drew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15703, line : "On the plumed crest of his Boeotian foe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15704, line : "The daring Lycon aim'd a noble blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15705, line : "The sword broke short; but his, Peneleus sped"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15706, line : "Full on the juncture of the neck and head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15707, line : "The head, divided by a stroke so just,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15708, line : "Hung by the skin; the body sunk to dust."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15710, line : "O'ertaken Neamas by Merion bleeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15711, line : "Pierced through the shoulder as he mounts his steeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15712, line : "Back from the car he tumbles to the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15713, line : "His swimming eyes eternal shades surround."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15715, line : "Next Erymas was doom'd his fate to feel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15716, line : "His open'd mouth received the Cretan steel:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15717, line : "Beneath the brain the point a passage tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15718, line : "Crash'd the thin bones, and drown'd the teeth in gore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15719, line : "His mouth, his eyes, his nostrils, pour a flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15720, line : "He sobs his soul out in the gush of blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15722, line : "As when the flocks neglected by the swain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15723, line : "Or kids, or lambs, lie scatter'd o'er the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15724, line : "A troop of wolves the unguarded charge survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15725, line : "And rend the trembling, unresisting prey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15726, line : "Thus on the foe the Greeks impetuous came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15727, line : "Troy fled, unmindful of her former fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15729, line : "But still at Hector godlike Ajax aim'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15730, line : "Still, pointed at his breast, his javelin flamed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15731, line : "The Trojan chief, experienced in the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15732, line : "O'er his broad shoulders spread the massy shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15733, line : "Observed the storm of darts the Grecians pour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15734, line : "And on his buckler caught the ringing shower:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15735, line : "He sees for Greece the scale of conquest rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15736, line : "Yet stops, and turns, and saves his loved allies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15738, line : "As when the hand of Jove a tempest forms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15739, line : "And rolls the cloud to blacken heaven with storms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15740, line : "Dark o'er the fields the ascending vapour flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15741, line : "And shades the sun, and blots the golden skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15742, line : "So from the ships, along the dusky plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15743, line : "Dire Flight and Terror drove the Trojan train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15744, line : "Even Hector fled; through heads of disarray"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15745, line : "The fiery coursers forced their lord away:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15746, line : "While far behind his Trojans fall confused;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15747, line : "Wedged in the trench, in one vast carnage bruised:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15748, line : "Chariots on chariots roll: the clashing spokes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15749, line : "Shock; while the madding steeds break short their yokes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15750, line : "In vain they labour up the steepy mound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15751, line : "Their charioteers lie foaming on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15752, line : "Fierce on the rear, with shouts Patroclus flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15753, line : "Tumultuous clamour fills the fields and skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15754, line : "Thick drifts of dust involve their rapid flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15755, line : "Clouds rise on clouds, and heaven is snatch'd from sight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15756, line : "The affrighted steeds their dying lords cast down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15757, line : "Scour o'er the fields, and stretch to reach the town."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15758, line : "Loud o'er the rout was heard the victor's cry,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15759, line : "Where the war bleeds, and where the thickest die,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15760, line : "Where horse and arms, and chariots he o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15761, line : "And bleeding heroes under axles groan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15762, line : "No stop, no check, the steeds of Peleus knew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15763, line : "From bank to bank the immortal coursers flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15764, line : "High-bounding o'er the fosse, the whirling car"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15765, line : "Smokes through the ranks, o'ertakes the flying war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15766, line : "And thunders after Hector; Hector flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15767, line : "Patroclus shakes his lance; but fate denies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15768, line : "Not with less noise, with less impetuous force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15769, line : "The tide of Trojans urge their desperate course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15770, line : "Than when in autumn Jove his fury pours,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15771, line : "And earth is loaden with incessant showers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15772, line : "(When guilty mortals break the eternal laws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15773, line : "Or judges, bribed, betray the righteous cause;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15774, line : "From their deep beds he bids the rivers rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15775, line : "And opens all the flood-gates of the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15776, line : "The impetuous torrents from their hills obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15777, line : "Whole fields are drown'd, and mountains swept away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15778, line : "Loud roars the deluge till it meets the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15779, line : "And trembling man sees all his labours vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15781, line : "And now the chief (the foremost troops repell'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15782, line : "Back to the ships his destined progress held,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15783, line : "Bore down half Troy in his resistless way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15784, line : "And forced the routed ranks to stand the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15785, line : "Between the space where silver Simois flows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15786, line : "Where lay the fleets, and where the rampires rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15787, line : "All grim in dust and blood Patroclus stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15788, line : "And turns the slaughter on the conquering bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15789, line : "First Pronous died beneath his fiery dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15790, line : "Which pierced below the shield his valiant heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15791, line : "Thestor was next, who saw the chief appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15792, line : "And fell the victim of his coward fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15793, line : "Shrunk up he sat, with wild and haggard eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15794, line : "Nor stood to combat, nor had force to fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15795, line : "Patroclus mark'd him as he shunn'd the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15796, line : "And with unmanly tremblings shook the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15797, line : "And dropp'd the flowing reins. Him 'twixt the jaws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15798, line : "The javelin sticks, and from the chariot draws."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15799, line : "As on a rock that overhangs the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15800, line : "An angler, studious of the line and cane,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15801, line : "Some mighty fish draws panting to the shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15802, line : "Not with less ease the barbed javelin bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15803, line : "The gaping dastard; as the spear was shook,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15804, line : "He fell, and life his heartless breast forsook."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15806, line : "Next on Eryalus he flies; a stone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15807, line : "Large as a rock, was by his fury thrown:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15808, line : "Full on his crown the ponderous fragment flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15809, line : "And burst the helm, and cleft the head in two:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15810, line : "Prone to the ground the breathless warrior fell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15811, line : "And death involved him with the shades of hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15812, line : "Then low in dust Epaltes, Echius, lie;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15813, line : "Ipheas, Evippus, Polymelus, die;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15814, line : "Amphoterus and Erymas succeed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15815, line : "And last Tlepolemus and Pyres bleed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15816, line : "Where'er he moves, the growing slaughters spread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15817, line : "In heaps on heaps a monument of dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15819, line : "When now Sarpedon his brave friends beheld"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15820, line : "Grovelling in dust, and gasping on the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15821, line : "With this reproach his flying host he warms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15822, line : "\"Oh stain to honour! oh disgrace to arms!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15823, line : "Forsake, inglorious, the contended plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15824, line : "This hand unaided shall the war sustain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15825, line : "The task be mine this hero's strength to try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15826, line : "Who mows whole troops, and makes an army fly.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15828, line : "He spake: and, speaking, leaps from off the car:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15829, line : "Patroclus lights, and sternly waits the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15830, line : "As when two vultures on the mountain's height"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15831, line : "Stoop with resounding pinions to the fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15832, line : "They cuff, they tear, they raise a screaming cry;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15833, line : "The desert echoes, and the rocks reply:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15834, line : "The warriors thus opposed in arms, engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15835, line : "With equal clamours, and with equal rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15837, line : "Jove view'd the combat: whose event foreseen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15838, line : "He thus bespoke his sister and his queen:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15839, line : "\"The hour draws on; the destinies ordain,(245)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15840, line : "My godlike son shall press the Phrygian plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15841, line : "Already on the verge of death he stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15842, line : "His life is owed to fierce Patroclus' hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15843, line : "What passions in a parent's breast debate!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15844, line : "Say, shall I snatch him from impending fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15845, line : "And send him safe to Lycia, distant far"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15846, line : "From all the dangers and the toils of war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15847, line : "Or to his doom my bravest offspring yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15848, line : "And fatten, with celestial blood, the field?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15850, line : "Then thus the goddess with the radiant eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15851, line : "\"What words are these, O sovereign of the skies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15852, line : "Short is the date prescribed to mortal man;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15853, line : "Shall Jove for one extend the narrow span,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15854, line : "Whose bounds were fix'd before his race began?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15855, line : "How many sons of gods, foredoom'd to death,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15856, line : "Before proud Ilion must resign their breath!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15857, line : "Were thine exempt, debate would rise above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15858, line : "And murmuring powers condemn their partial Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15859, line : "Give the bold chief a glorious fate in fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15860, line : "And when the ascending soul has wing'd her flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15861, line : "Let Sleep and Death convey, by thy command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15862, line : "The breathless body to his native land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15863, line : "His friends and people, to his future praise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15864, line : "A marble tomb and pyramid shall raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15865, line : "And lasting honours to his ashes give;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15866, line : "His fame ('tis all the dead can have) shall live.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15868, line : "She said: the cloud-compeller, overcome,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15869, line : "Assents to fate, and ratifies the doom."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15870, line : "Then touch'd with grief, the weeping heavens distill'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15871, line : "A shower of blood o'er all the fatal field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15872, line : "The god, his eyes averting from the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15873, line : "Laments his son, predestined to be slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15874, line : "Far from the Lycian shores, his happy native reign."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15875, line : "Now met in arms, the combatants appear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15876, line : "Each heaved the shield, and poised the lifted spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15877, line : "From strong Patroclus' hand the javelin fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15878, line : "And pass'd the groin of valiant Thrasymed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15879, line : "The nerves unbraced no more his bulk sustain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15880, line : "He falls, and falling bites the bloody plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15881, line : "Two sounding darts the Lycian leader threw:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15882, line : "The first aloof with erring fury flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15883, line : "The next transpierced Achilles' mortal steed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15884, line : "The generous Pedasus of Theban breed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15885, line : "Fix'd in the shoulder's joint, he reel'd around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15886, line : "Roll'd in the bloody dust, and paw'd the slippery ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15887, line : "His sudden fall the entangled harness broke;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15888, line : "Each axle crackled, and the chariot shook:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15889, line : "When bold Automedon, to disengage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15890, line : "The starting coursers, and restrain their rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15891, line : "Divides the traces with his sword, and freed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15892, line : "The encumbered chariot from the dying steed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15893, line : "The rest move on, obedient to the rein:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15894, line : "The car rolls slowly o'er the dusty plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15896, line : "The towering chiefs to fiercer fight advance:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15897, line : "And first Sarpedon whirl'd his weighty lance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15898, line : "Which o'er the warrior's shoulder took its course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15899, line : "And spent in empty air its dying force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15900, line : "Not so Patroclus' never-erring dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15901, line : "Aim'd at his breast it pierced a mortal part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15902, line : "Where the strong fibres bind the solid heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15903, line : "Then as the mountain oak, or poplar tall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15904, line : "Or pine (fit mast for some great admiral)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15905, line : "Nods to the axe, till with a groaning sound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15906, line : "It sinks, and spreads its honours on the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15907, line : "Thus fell the king; and laid on earth supine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15908, line : "Before his chariot stretch'd his form divine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15909, line : "He grasp'd the dust distain'd with streaming gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15910, line : "And, pale in death, lay groaning on the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15911, line : "So lies a bull beneath the lion's paws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15912, line : "While the grim savage grinds with foamy jaws"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15913, line : "The trembling limbs, and sucks the smoking blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15914, line : "Deep groans, and hollow roars, rebellow through the wood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15916, line : "Then to the leader of the Lycian band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15917, line : "The dying chief address'd his last command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15918, line : "\"Glaucus, be bold; thy task be first to dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15919, line : "The glorious dangers of destructive war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15920, line : "To lead my troops, to combat at their head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15921, line : "Incite the living, and supply the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15922, line : "Tell them, I charged them with my latest breath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15923, line : "Not unrevenged to bear Sarpedon's death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15924, line : "What grief, what shame, must Glaucus undergo,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15925, line : "If these spoil'd arms adorn a Grecian foe!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15926, line : "Then as a friend, and as a warrior fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15927, line : "Defend my body, conquer in my right:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15928, line : "That, taught by great examples, all may try"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15929, line : "Like thee to vanquish, or like me to die.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15930, line : "He ceased; the Fates suppress'd his labouring breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15931, line : "And his eyes darken'd with the shades of death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15932, line : "The insulting victor with disdain bestrode"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15933, line : "The prostrate prince, and on his bosom trod;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15934, line : "Then drew the weapon from his panting heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15935, line : "The reeking fibres clinging to the dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15936, line : "From the wide wound gush'd out a stream of blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15937, line : "And the soul issued in the purple flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15938, line : "His flying steeds the Myrmidons detain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15939, line : "Unguided now, their mighty master slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15940, line : "All-impotent of aid, transfix'd with grief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15941, line : "Unhappy Glaucus heard the dying chief:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15942, line : "His painful arm, yet useless with the smart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15943, line : "Inflicted late by Teucer's deadly dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15944, line : "Supported on his better hand he stay'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15945, line : "To Phoebus then ('twas all he could) he pray'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15947, line : "\"All-seeing monarch! whether Lycia's coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15948, line : "Or sacred Ilion, thy bright presence boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15949, line : "Powerful alike to ease the wretch's smart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15950, line : "O hear me! god of every healing art!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15951, line : "Lo! stiff with clotted blood, and pierced with pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15952, line : "That thrills my arm, and shoots through every vein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15953, line : "I stand unable to sustain the spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15954, line : "And sigh, at distance from the glorious war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15955, line : "Low in the dust is great Sarpedon laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15956, line : "Nor Jove vouchsafed his hapless offspring aid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15957, line : "But thou, O god of health! thy succour lend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15958, line : "To guard the relics of my slaughter'd friend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15959, line : "For thou, though distant, canst restore my might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15960, line : "To head my Lycians, and support the fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15962, line : "Apollo heard; and, suppliant as he stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15963, line : "His heavenly hand restrain'd the flux of blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15964, line : "He drew the dolours from the wounded part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15965, line : "And breathed a spirit in his rising heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15966, line : "Renew'd by art divine, the hero stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15967, line : "And owns the assistance of immortal hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15968, line : "First to the fight his native troops he warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15969, line : "Then loudly calls on Troy's vindictive arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15970, line : "With ample strides he stalks from place to place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15971, line : "Now fires Agenor, now Polydamas:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15972, line : "Ćneas next, and Hector he accosts;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15973, line : "Inflaming thus the rage of all their hosts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15975, line : "\"What thoughts, regardless chief! thy breast employ?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15976, line : "Oh too forgetful of the friends of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15977, line : "Those generous friends, who, from their country far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15978, line : "Breathe their brave souls out in another's war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15979, line : "See! where in dust the great Sarpedon lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15980, line : "In action valiant, and in council wise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15981, line : "Who guarded right, and kept his people free;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15982, line : "To all his Lycians lost, and lost to thee!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15983, line : "Stretch'd by Patroclus' arm on yonder plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15984, line : "O save from hostile rage his loved remains!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15985, line : "Ah let not Greece his conquer'd trophies boast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15986, line : "Nor on his corse revenge her heroes lost!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15988, line : "He spoke: each leader in his grief partook:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15989, line : "Troy, at the loss, through all her legions shook."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15990, line : "Transfix'd with deep regret, they view o'erthrown"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15991, line : "At once his country's pillar, and their own;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15992, line : "A chief, who led to Troy's beleaguer'd wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15993, line : "A host of heroes, and outshined them all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15994, line : "Fired, they rush on; first Hector seeks the foes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15995, line : "And with superior vengeance greatly glows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15997, line : "But o'er the dead the fierce Patroclus stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 15998, line : "And rousing Ajax, roused the listening bands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16000, line : "\"Heroes, be men; be what you were before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16001, line : "Or weigh the great occasion, and be more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16002, line : "The chief who taught our lofty walls to yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16003, line : "Lies pale in death, extended on the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16004, line : "To guard his body Troy in numbers flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16005, line : "Tis half the glory to maintain our prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16006, line : "Haste, strip his arms, the slaughter round him spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16007, line : "And send the living Lycians to the dead.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16009, line : "The heroes kindle at his fierce command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16010, line : "The martial squadrons close on either hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16011, line : "Here Troy and Lycia charge with loud alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16012, line : "Thessalia there, and Greece, oppose their arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16013, line : "With horrid shouts they circle round the slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16014, line : "The clash of armour rings o'er all the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16015, line : "Great Jove, to swell the horrors of the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16016, line : "O'er the fierce armies pours pernicious night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16017, line : "And round his son confounds the warring hosts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16018, line : "His fate ennobling with a crowd of ghosts."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16020, line : "Now Greece gives way, and great Epigeus falls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16021, line : "Agacleus' son, from Budium's lofty walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16022, line : "Who chased for murder thence a suppliant came"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16023, line : "To Peleus, and the silver-footed dame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16024, line : "Now sent to Troy, Achilles' arms to aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16025, line : "He pays due vengeance to his kinsman's shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16026, line : "Soon as his luckless hand had touch'd the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16027, line : "A rock's large fragment thunder'd on his head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16028, line : "Hurl'd by Hectorean force it cleft in twain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16029, line : "His shatter'd helm, and stretch'd him o'er the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16031, line : "Fierce to the van of fight Patroclus came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16032, line : "And, like an eagle darting at his game,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16033, line : "Sprung on the Trojan and the Lycian band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16034, line : "What grief thy heart, what fury urged thy hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16035, line : "O generous Greek! when with full vigour thrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16036, line : "At Sthenelaus flew the weighty stone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16037, line : "Which sunk him to the dead: when Troy, too near"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16038, line : "That arm, drew back; and Hector learn'd to fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16039, line : "Far as an able hand a lance can throw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16040, line : "Or at the lists, or at the fighting foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16041, line : "So far the Trojans from their lines retired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16042, line : "Till Glaucus, turning, all the rest inspired."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16043, line : "Then Bathyclaeus fell beneath his rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16044, line : "The only hope of Chalcon's trembling age;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16045, line : "Wide o'er the land was stretch'd his large domain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16046, line : "With stately seats, and riches blest in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16047, line : "Him, bold with youth, and eager to pursue"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16048, line : "The flying Lycians, Glaucus met and slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16049, line : "Pierced through the bosom with a sudden wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16050, line : "He fell, and falling made the fields resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16051, line : "The Achaians sorrow for their heroes slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16052, line : "With conquering shouts the Trojans shake the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16053, line : "And crowd to spoil the dead: the Greeks oppose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16054, line : "An iron circle round the carcase grows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16056, line : "Then brave Laogonus resign'd his breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16057, line : "Despatch'd by Merion to the shades of death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16058, line : "On Ida's holy hill he made abode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16059, line : "The priest of Jove, and honour'd like his god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16060, line : "Between the jaw and ear the javelin went;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16061, line : "The soul, exhaling, issued at the vent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16062, line : "His spear Aeneas at the victor threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16063, line : "Who stooping forward from the death withdrew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16064, line : "The lance hiss'd harmless o'er his covering shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16065, line : "And trembling struck, and rooted in the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16066, line : "There yet scarce spent, it quivers on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16067, line : "Sent by the great Aeneas' arm in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16068, line : "\"Swift as thou art (the raging hero cries)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16069, line : "And skill'd in dancing to dispute the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16070, line : "My spear, the destined passage had it found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16071, line : "Had fix'd thy active vigour to the ground.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16073, line : "\"O valiant leader of the Dardan host!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16074, line : "(Insulted Merion thus retorts the boast)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16075, line : "Strong as you are, 'tis mortal force you trust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16076, line : "An arm as strong may stretch thee in the dust."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16077, line : "And if to this my lance thy fate be given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16078, line : "Vain are thy vaunts; success is still from heaven:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16079, line : "This, instant, sends thee down to Pluto's coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16080, line : "Mine is the glory, his thy parting ghost.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16082, line : "\"O friend (Menoetius' son this answer gave)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16083, line : "With words to combat, ill befits the brave;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16084, line : "Not empty boasts the sons of Troy repel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16085, line : "Your swords must plunge them to the shades of hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16086, line : "To speak, beseems the council; but to dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16087, line : "In glorious action, is the task of war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16089, line : "This said, Patroclus to the battle flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16090, line : "Great Merion follows, and new shouts arise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16091, line : "Shields, helmets rattle, as the warriors close;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16092, line : "And thick and heavy sounds the storm of blows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16093, line : "As through the shrilling vale, or mountain ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16094, line : "The labours of the woodman's axe resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16095, line : "Blows following blows are heard re-echoing wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16096, line : "While crackling forests fall on every side:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16097, line : "Thus echoed all the fields with loud alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16098, line : "So fell the warriors, and so rung their arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16100, line : "Now great Sarpedon on the sandy shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16101, line : "His heavenly form defaced with dust and gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16102, line : "And stuck with darts by warring heroes shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16103, line : "Lies undistinguish'd from the vulgar dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16104, line : "His long-disputed corse the chiefs enclose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16105, line : "On every side the busy combat grows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16106, line : "Thick as beneath some shepherd's thatch'd abode"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16107, line : "(The pails high foaming with a milky flood)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16108, line : "The buzzing flies, a persevering train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16109, line : "Incessant swarm, and chased return again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16111, line : "Jove view'd the combat with a stern survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16112, line : "And eyes that flash'd intolerable day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16113, line : "Fix'd on the field his sight, his breast debates"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16114, line : "The vengeance due, and meditates the fates:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16115, line : "Whether to urge their prompt effect, and call"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16116, line : "The force of Hector to Patroclus' fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16117, line : "This instant see his short-lived trophies won,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16118, line : "And stretch him breathless on his slaughter'd son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16119, line : "Or yet, with many a soul's untimely flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16120, line : "Augment the fame and horror of the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16121, line : "To crown Achilles' valiant friend with praise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16122, line : "At length he dooms; and, that his last of days"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16123, line : "Shall set in glory, bids him drive the foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16124, line : "Nor unattended see the shades below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16125, line : "Then Hector's mind he fills with dire dismay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16126, line : "He mounts his car, and calls his hosts away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16127, line : "Sunk with Troy's heavy fates, he sees decline"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16128, line : "The scales of Jove, and pants with awe divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16130, line : "Then, nor before, the hardy Lycians fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16131, line : "And left their monarch with the common dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16132, line : "Around, in heaps on heaps, a dreadful wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16133, line : "Of carnage rises, as the heroes fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16134, line : "(So Jove decreed!) At length the Greeks obtain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16135, line : "The prize contested, and despoil the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16136, line : "The radiant arms are by Patroclus borne;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16137, line : "Patroclus' ships the glorious spoils adorn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16139, line : "Then thus to Phoebus, in the realms above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16140, line : "Spoke from his throne the cloud-compelling Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16141, line : "\"Descend, my Phoebus! on the Phrygian plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16142, line : "And from the fight convey Sarpedon slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16143, line : "Then bathe his body in the crystal flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16144, line : "With dust dishonour'd, and deform'd with blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16145, line : "O'er all his limbs ambrosial odours shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16146, line : "And with celestial robes adorn the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16147, line : "Those rites discharged, his sacred corse bequeath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16148, line : "To the soft arms of silent Sleep and Death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16149, line : "They to his friends the immortal charge shall bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16150, line : "His friends a tomb and pyramid shall rear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16151, line : "What honour mortals after death receive,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16152, line : "Those unavailing honours we may give!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16154, line : "[Illustration: SLEEP AND DEATH CONVEYING THE BODY OF SARPEDON TO LYCIA.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16156, line : "SLEEP AND DEATH CONVEYING THE BODY OF SARPEDON TO LYCIA."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16159, line : "Apollo bows, and from mount Ida's height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16160, line : "Swift to the field precipitates his flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16161, line : "Thence from the war the breathless hero bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16162, line : "Veil'd in a cloud, to silver Simois' shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16163, line : "There bathed his honourable wounds, and dress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16164, line : "His manly members in the immortal vest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16165, line : "And with perfumes of sweet ambrosial dews"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16166, line : "Restores his freshness, and his form renews."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16167, line : "Then Sleep and Death, two twins of winged race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16168, line : "Of matchless swiftness, but of silent pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16169, line : "Received Sarpedon, at the god's command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16170, line : "And in a moment reach'd the Lycian land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16171, line : "The corse amidst his weeping friends they laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16172, line : "Where endless honours wait the sacred shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16174, line : "Meanwhile Patroclus pours along the plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16175, line : "With foaming coursers, and with loosen'd reins."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16176, line : "Fierce on the Trojan and the Lycian crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16177, line : "Ah blind to fate! thy headlong fury flew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16178, line : "Against what fate and powerful Jove ordain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16179, line : "Vain was thy friend's command, thy courage vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16180, line : "For he, the god, whose counsels uncontroll'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16181, line : "Dismay the mighty, and confound the bold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16182, line : "The god who gives, resumes, and orders all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16183, line : "He urged thee on, and urged thee on to fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16185, line : "Who first, brave hero! by that arm was slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16186, line : "Who last beneath thy vengeance press'd the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16187, line : "When heaven itself thy fatal fury led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16188, line : "And call'd to fill the number of the dead?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16189, line : "Adrestus first; Autonous then succeeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16190, line : "Echeclus follows; next young Megas bleeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16191, line : "Epistor, Melanippus, bite the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16192, line : "The slaughter, Elasus and Mulius crown'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16193, line : "Then sunk Pylartes to eternal night;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16194, line : "The rest, dispersing, trust their fates to flight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16196, line : "Now Troy had stoop'd beneath his matchless power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16197, line : "But flaming Phoebus kept the sacred tower"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16198, line : "Thrice at the battlements Patroclus strook;(246)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16199, line : "His blazing aegis thrice Apollo shook;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16200, line : "He tried the fourth; when, bursting from the cloud,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16201, line : "A more than mortal voice was heard aloud."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16203, line : "\"Patroclus! cease; this heaven-defended wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16204, line : "Defies thy lance; not fated yet to fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16205, line : "Thy friend, thy greater far, it shall withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16206, line : "Troy shall not stoop even to Achilles' hand.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16208, line : "So spoke the god who darts celestial fires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16209, line : "The Greek obeys him, and with awe retires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16210, line : "While Hector, checking at the Scaean gates"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16211, line : "His panting coursers, in his breast debates,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16212, line : "Or in the field his forces to employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16213, line : "Or draw the troops within the walls of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16214, line : "Thus while he thought, beside him Phoebus stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16215, line : "In Asius' shape, who reigned by Sangar's flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16216, line : "(Thy brother, Hecuba! from Dymas sprung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16217, line : "A valiant warrior, haughty, bold, and young;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16218, line : "Thus he accosts him. \"What a shameful sight!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16219, line : "God! is it Hector that forbears the fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16220, line : "Were thine my vigour this successful spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16221, line : "Should soon convince thee of so false a fear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16222, line : "Turn thee, ah turn thee to the field of fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16223, line : "And in Patroclus' blood efface thy shame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16224, line : "Perhaps Apollo shall thy arms succeed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16225, line : "And heaven ordains him by thy lance to bleed.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16227, line : "So spoke the inspiring god; then took his flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16228, line : "And plunged amidst the tumult of the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16229, line : "He bids Cebrion drive the rapid car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16230, line : "The lash resounds, the coursers rush to war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16231, line : "The god the Grecians' sinking souls depress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16232, line : "And pour'd swift spirits through each Trojan breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16233, line : "Patroclus lights, impatient for the fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16234, line : "A spear his left, a stone employs his right:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16235, line : "With all his nerves he drives it at the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16236, line : "Pointed above, and rough and gross below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16237, line : "The falling ruin crush'd Cebrion's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16238, line : "The lawless offspring of king Priam's bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16239, line : "His front, brows, eyes, one undistinguish'd wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16240, line : "The bursting balls drop sightless to the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16241, line : "The charioteer, while yet he held the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16242, line : "Struck from the car, falls headlong on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16243, line : "To the dark shades the soul unwilling glides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16244, line : "While the proud victor thus his fall derides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16246, line : "\"Good heaven! what active feats yon artist shows!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16247, line : "What skilful divers are our Phrygian foes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16248, line : "Mark with what ease they sink into the sand!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16249, line : "Pity that all their practice is by land!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16251, line : "Then rushing sudden on his prostrate prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16252, line : "To spoil the carcase fierce Patroclus flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16253, line : "Swift as a lion, terrible and bold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16254, line : "That sweeps the field, depopulates the fold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16255, line : "Pierced through the dauntless heart, then tumbles slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16256, line : "And from his fatal courage finds his bane."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16257, line : "At once bold Hector leaping from his car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16258, line : "Defends the body, and provokes the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16259, line : "Thus for some slaughter'd hind, with equal rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16260, line : "Two lordly rulers of the wood engage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16261, line : "Stung with fierce hunger, each the prey invades,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16262, line : "And echoing roars rebellow through the shades."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16263, line : "Stern Hector fastens on the warrior's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16264, line : "And by the foot Patroclus drags the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16265, line : "While all around, confusion, rage, and fright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16266, line : "Mix the contending hosts in mortal fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16267, line : "So pent by hills, the wild winds roar aloud"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16268, line : "In the deep bosom of some gloomy wood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16269, line : "Leaves, arms, and trees, aloft in air are blown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16270, line : "The broad oaks crackle, and the Sylvans groan;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16271, line : "This way and that, the rattling thicket bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16272, line : "And the whole forest in one crash descends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16273, line : "Not with less noise, with less tumultuous rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16274, line : "In dreadful shock the mingled hosts engage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16275, line : "Darts shower'd on darts, now round the carcase ring;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16276, line : "Now flights of arrows bounding from the string:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16277, line : "Stones follow stones; some clatter on the fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16278, line : "Some hard, and heavy, shake the sounding shields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16279, line : "But where the rising whirlwind clouds the plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16280, line : "Sunk in soft dust the mighty chief remains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16281, line : "And, stretch'd in death, forgets the guiding reins!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16283, line : "Now flaming from the zenith, Sol had driven"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16284, line : "His fervid orb through half the vault of heaven;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16285, line : "While on each host with equal tempests fell"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16286, line : "The showering darts, and numbers sank to hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16287, line : "But when his evening wheels o'erhung the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16288, line : "Glad conquest rested on the Grecian train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16289, line : "Then from amidst the tumult and alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16290, line : "They draw the conquer'd corse and radiant arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16291, line : "Then rash Patroclus with new fury glows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16292, line : "And breathing slaughter, pours amid the foes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16293, line : "Thrice on the press like Mars himself he flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16294, line : "And thrice three heroes at each onset slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16295, line : "There ends thy glory! there the Fates untwine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16296, line : "The last, black remnant of so bright a line:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16297, line : "Apollo dreadful stops thy middle way;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16298, line : "Death calls, and heaven allows no longer day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16300, line : "For lo! the god in dusky clouds enshrined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16301, line : "Approaching dealt a staggering blow behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16302, line : "The weighty shock his neck and shoulders feel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16303, line : "His eyes flash sparkles, his stunn'd senses reel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16304, line : "In giddy darkness; far to distance flung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16305, line : "His bounding helmet on the champaign rung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16306, line : "Achilles' plume is stain'd with dust and gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16307, line : "That plume which never stoop'd to earth before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16308, line : "Long used, untouch'd, in fighting fields to shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16309, line : "And shade the temples of the mad divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16310, line : "Jove dooms it now on Hector's helm to nod;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16311, line : "Not long--for fate pursues him, and the god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16313, line : "His spear in shivers falls; his ample shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16314, line : "Drops from his arm: his baldric strows the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16315, line : "The corslet his astonish'd breast forsakes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16316, line : "Loose is each joint; each nerve with horror shakes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16317, line : "Stupid he stares, and all-assistless stands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16318, line : "Such is the force of more than mortal hands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16320, line : "A Dardan youth there was, well known to fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16321, line : "From Panthus sprung, Euphorbus was his name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16322, line : "Famed for the manage of the foaming horse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16323, line : "Skill'd in the dart, and matchless in the course:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16324, line : "Full twenty knights he tumbled from the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16325, line : "While yet he learn'd his rudiments of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16326, line : "His venturous spear first drew the hero's gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16327, line : "He struck, he wounded, but he durst no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16328, line : "Nor, though disarm'd, Patroclus' fury stood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16329, line : "But swift withdrew the long-protended wood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16330, line : "And turn'd him short, and herded in the crowd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16331, line : "Thus, by an arm divine, and mortal spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16332, line : "Wounded, at once, Patroclus yields to fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16333, line : "Retires for succour to his social train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16334, line : "And flies the fate, which heaven decreed, in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16335, line : "Stern Hector, as the bleeding chief he views,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16336, line : "Breaks through the ranks, and his retreat pursues:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16337, line : "The lance arrests him with a mortal wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16338, line : "He falls, earth thunders, and his arms resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16339, line : "With him all Greece was sunk; that moment all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16340, line : "Her yet-surviving heroes seem'd to fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16341, line : "So, scorch'd with heat, along the desert score,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16342, line : "The roaming lion meets a bristly boar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16343, line : "Fast by the spring; they both dispute the flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16344, line : "With flaming eyes, and jaws besmear'd with blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16345, line : "At length the sovereign savage wins the strife;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16346, line : "And the torn boar resigns his thirst and life."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16347, line : "Patroclus thus, so many chiefs o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16348, line : "So many lives effused, expires his own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16349, line : "As dying now at Hector's feet he lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16350, line : "He sternly views him, and triumphant cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16352, line : "\"Lie there, Patroclus! and with thee, the joy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16353, line : "Thy pride once promised, of subverting Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16354, line : "The fancied scenes of Ilion wrapt in flames,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16355, line : "And thy soft pleasures served with captive dames."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16356, line : "Unthinking man! I fought those towers to free,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16357, line : "And guard that beauteous race from lords like thee:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16358, line : "But thou a prey to vultures shalt be made;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16359, line : "Thy own Achilles cannot lend thee aid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16360, line : "Though much at parting that great chief might say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16361, line : "And much enjoin thee, this important day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16363, line : "'Return not, my brave friend (perhaps he said),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16364, line : "Without the bloody arms of Hector dead.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16365, line : "He spoke, Patroclus march'd, and thus he sped.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16367, line : "Supine, and wildly gazing on the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16368, line : "With faint, expiring breath, the chief replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16370, line : "\"Vain boaster! cease, and know the powers divine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16371, line : "Jove's and Apollo's is this deed, not thine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16372, line : "To heaven is owed whate'er your own you call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16373, line : "And heaven itself disarm'd me ere my fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16374, line : "Had twenty mortals, each thy match in might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16375, line : "Opposed me fairly, they had sunk in fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16376, line : "By fate and Phoebus was I first o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16377, line : "Euphorbus next; the third mean part thy own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16378, line : "But thou, imperious! hear my latest breath;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16379, line : "The gods inspire it, and it sounds thy death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16380, line : "Insulting man, thou shalt be soon as I;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16381, line : "Black fate o'erhangs thee, and thy hour draws nigh;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16382, line : "Even now on life's last verge I see thee stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16383, line : "I see thee fall, and by Achilles' hand.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16385, line : "He faints: the soul unwilling wings her way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16386, line : "(The beauteous body left a load of clay)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16387, line : "Flits to the lone, uncomfortable coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16388, line : "A naked, wandering, melancholy ghost!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16390, line : "Then Hector pausing, as his eyes he fed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16391, line : "On the pale carcase, thus address'd the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16393, line : "\"From whence this boding speech, the stern decree"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16394, line : "Of death denounced, or why denounced to me?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16395, line : "Why not as well Achilles' fate be given"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16396, line : "To Hector's lance? Who knows the will of heaven?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16398, line : "Pensive he said; then pressing as he lay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16399, line : "His breathless bosom, tore the lance away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16400, line : "And upwards cast the corse: the reeking spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16401, line : "He shakes, and charges the bold charioteer."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16402, line : "But swift Automedon with loosen'd reins"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16403, line : "Rapt in the chariot o'er the distant plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16404, line : "Far from his rage the immortal coursers drove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16405, line : "The immortal coursers were the gift of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16407, line : "[Illustration: ĆSCULAPIUS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16409, line : "ĆSCULAPIUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16415, line : "BOOK XVII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16418, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16420, line : "THE SEVENTH BATTLE, FOR THE BODY OF PATROCLUS.--THE ACTS OF MENELAUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16422, line : "Menelaus, upon the death of Patroclus, defends his body from the enemy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16423, line : "Euphorbus, who attempts it, is slain. Hector advancing, Menelaus retires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16424, line : "but soon returns with Ajax, and drives him off. This, Glaucus objects to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16425, line : "Hector as a flight, who thereupon puts on the armour he had won from"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16426, line : "Patroclus, and renews the battle. The Greeks give way, till Ajax rallies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16427, line : "them: Aeneas sustains the Trojans. Aeneas and Hector Attempt the chariot"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16428, line : "of Achilles, which is borne off by Automedon. The horses of Achilles"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16429, line : "deplore the loss of Patroclus: Jupiter covers his body with a thick"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16430, line : "darkness: the noble prayer of Ajax on that occasion. Menelaus sends"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16431, line : "Antilochus to Achilles, with the news of Patroclus' death: then returns to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16432, line : "the fight, where, though attacked with the utmost fury, he and Meriones,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16433, line : "assisted by the Ajaces, bear off the body to the ships."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16435, line : "The time is the evening of the eight-and-twentieth day. The scene lies in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16436, line : "the fields before Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16438, line : "On the cold earth divine Patroclus spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16439, line : "Lies pierced with wounds among the vulgar dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16440, line : "Great Menelaus, touch'd with generous woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16441, line : "Springs to the front, and guards him from the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16442, line : "Thus round her new-fallen young the heifer moves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16443, line : "Fruit of her throes, and first-born of her loves;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16444, line : "And anxious (helpless as he lies, and bare)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16445, line : "Turns, and re-turns her, with a mother's care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16446, line : "Opposed to each that near the carcase came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16447, line : "His broad shield glimmers, and his lances flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16449, line : "The son of Panthus, skill'd the dart to send,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16450, line : "Eyes the dead hero, and insults the friend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16451, line : "\"This hand, Atrides, laid Patroclus low;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16452, line : "Warrior! desist, nor tempt an equal blow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16453, line : "To me the spoils my prowess won, resign:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16454, line : "Depart with life, and leave the glory mine\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16456, line : "The Trojan thus: the Spartan monarch burn'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16457, line : "With generous anguish, and in scorn return'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16458, line : "\"Laugh'st thou not, Jove! from thy superior throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16459, line : "When mortals boast of prowess not their own?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16460, line : "Not thus the lion glories in his might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16461, line : "Nor panther braves his spotted foe in fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16462, line : "Nor thus the boar (those terrors of the plain;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16463, line : "Man only vaunts his force, and vaunts in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16464, line : "But far the vainest of the boastful kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16465, line : "These sons of Panthus vent their haughty mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16466, line : "Yet 'twas but late, beneath my conquering steel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16467, line : "This boaster's brother, Hyperenor, fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16468, line : "Against our arm which rashly he defied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16469, line : "Vain was his vigour, and as vain his pride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16470, line : "These eyes beheld him on the dust expire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16471, line : "No more to cheer his spouse, or glad his sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16472, line : "Presumptuous youth! like his shall be thy doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16473, line : "Go, wait thy brother to the Stygian gloom;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16474, line : "Or, while thou may'st, avoid the threaten'd fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16475, line : "Fools stay to feel it, and are wise too late.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16477, line : "Unmoved, Euphorbus thus: \"That action known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16478, line : "Come, for my brother's blood repay thy own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16479, line : "His weeping father claims thy destined head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16480, line : "And spouse, a widow in her bridal bed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16481, line : "On these thy conquer'd spoils I shall bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16482, line : "To soothe a consort's and a parent's woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16483, line : "No longer then defer the glorious strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16484, line : "Let heaven decide our fortune, fame, and life.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16486, line : "Swift as the word the missile lance he flings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16487, line : "The well-aim'd weapon on the buckler rings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16488, line : "But blunted by the brass, innoxious falls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16489, line : "On Jove the father great Atrides calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16490, line : "Nor flies the javelin from his arm in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16491, line : "It pierced his throat, and bent him to the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16492, line : "Wide through the neck appears the grisly wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16493, line : "Prone sinks the warrior, and his arms resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16494, line : "The shining circlets of his golden hair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16495, line : "Which even the Graces might be proud to wear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16496, line : "Instarr'd with gems and gold, bestrow the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16497, line : "With dust dishonour'd, and deform'd with gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16499, line : "As the young olive, in some sylvan scene,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16500, line : "Crown'd by fresh fountains with eternal green,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16501, line : "Lifts the gay head, in snowy flowerets fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16502, line : "And plays and dances to the gentle air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16503, line : "When lo! a whirlwind from high heaven invades"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16504, line : "The tender plant, and withers all its shades;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16505, line : "It lies uprooted from its genial bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16506, line : "A lovely ruin now defaced and dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16507, line : "Thus young, thus beautiful, Euphorbus lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16508, line : "While the fierce Spartan tore his arms away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16509, line : "Proud of his deed, and glorious in the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16510, line : "Affrighted Troy the towering victor flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16511, line : "Flies, as before some mountain lion's ire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16512, line : "The village curs and trembling swains retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16513, line : "When o'er the slaughter'd bull they hear him roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16514, line : "And see his jaws distil with smoking gore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16515, line : "All pale with fear, at distance scatter'd round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16516, line : "They shout incessant, and the vales resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16518, line : "Meanwhile Apollo view'd with envious eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16519, line : "And urged great Hector to dispute the prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16520, line : "(In Mentes' shape, beneath whose martial care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16521, line : "The rough Ciconians learn'd the trade of war;)(247)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16522, line : "\"Forbear (he cried) with fruitless speed to chase"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16523, line : "Achilles' coursers, of ethereal race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16524, line : "They stoop not, these, to mortal man's command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16525, line : "Or stoop to none but great Achilles' hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16526, line : "Too long amused with a pursuit so vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16527, line : "Turn, and behold the brave Euphorbus slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16528, line : "By Sparta slain! for ever now suppress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16529, line : "The fire which burn'd in that undaunted breast!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16531, line : "Thus having spoke, Apollo wing'd his flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16532, line : "And mix'd with mortals in the toils of fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16533, line : "His words infix'd unutterable care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16534, line : "Deep in great Hector's soul: through all the war"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16535, line : "He darts his anxious eye; and, instant, view'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16536, line : "The breathless hero in his blood imbued,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16537, line : "(Forth welling from the wound, as prone he lay)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16538, line : "And in the victor's hands the shining prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16539, line : "Sheath'd in bright arms, through cleaving ranks he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16540, line : "And sends his voice in thunder to the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16541, line : "Fierce as a flood of flame by Vulcan sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16542, line : "It flew, and fired the nations as it went."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16543, line : "Atrides from the voice the storm divined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16544, line : "And thus explored his own unconquer'd mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16546, line : "\"Then shall I quit Patroclus on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16547, line : "Slain in my cause, and for my honour slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16548, line : "Desert the arms, the relics, of my friend?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16549, line : "Or singly, Hector and his troops attend?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16550, line : "Sure where such partial favour heaven bestow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16551, line : "To brave the hero were to brave the god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16552, line : "Forgive me, Greece, if once I quit the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16553, line : "'Tis not to Hector, but to heaven I yield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16554, line : "Yet, nor the god, nor heaven, should give me fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16555, line : "Did but the voice of Ajax reach my ear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16556, line : "Still would we turn, still battle on the plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16557, line : "And give Achilles all that yet remains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16558, line : "Of his and our Patroclus--\" This, no more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16559, line : "The time allow'd: Troy thicken'd on the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16560, line : "A sable scene! The terrors Hector led."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16561, line : "Slow he recedes, and sighing quits the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16563, line : "So from the fold the unwilling lion parts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16564, line : "Forced by loud clamours, and a storm of darts;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16565, line : "He flies indeed, but threatens as he flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16566, line : "With heart indignant and retorted eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16567, line : "Now enter'd in the Spartan ranks, he turn'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16568, line : "His manly breast, and with new fury burn'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16569, line : "O'er all the black battalions sent his view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16570, line : "And through the cloud the godlike Ajax knew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16571, line : "Where labouring on the left the warrior stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16572, line : "All grim in arms, and cover'd o'er with blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16573, line : "There breathing courage, where the god of day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16574, line : "Had sunk each heart with terror and dismay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16576, line : "To him the king: \"Oh Ajax, oh my friend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16577, line : "Haste, and Patroclus' loved remains defend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16578, line : "The body to Achilles to restore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16579, line : "Demands our care; alas, we can no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16580, line : "For naked now, despoiled of arms, he lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16581, line : "And Hector glories in the dazzling prize.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16582, line : "He said, and touch'd his heart. The raging pair"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16583, line : "Pierced the thick battle, and provoke the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16584, line : "Already had stern Hector seized his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16585, line : "And doom'd to Trojan gods the unhappy dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16586, line : "But soon as Ajax rear'd his tower-like shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16587, line : "Sprung to his car, and measured back the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16588, line : "His train to Troy the radiant armour bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16589, line : "To stand a trophy of his fame in war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16591, line : "Meanwhile great Ajax (his broad shield display'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16592, line : "Guards the dead hero with the dreadful shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16593, line : "And now before, and now behind he stood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16594, line : "Thus in the centre of some gloomy wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16595, line : "With many a step, the lioness surrounds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16596, line : "Her tawny young, beset by men and hounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16597, line : "Elate her heart, and rousing all her powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16598, line : "Dark o'er the fiery balls each hanging eyebrow lours."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16599, line : "Fast by his side the generous Spartan glows"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16600, line : "With great revenge, and feeds his inward woes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16602, line : "But Glaucus, leader of the Lycian aids,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16603, line : "On Hector frowning, thus his flight upbraids:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16605, line : "\"Where now in Hector shall we Hector find?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16606, line : "A manly form, without a manly mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16607, line : "Is this, O chief! a hero's boasted fame?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16608, line : "How vain, without the merit, is the name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16609, line : "Since battle is renounced, thy thoughts employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16610, line : "What other methods may preserve thy Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16611, line : "'Tis time to try if Ilion's state can stand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16612, line : "By thee alone, nor ask a foreign hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16613, line : "Mean, empty boast! but shall the Lycians stake"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16614, line : "Their lives for you? those Lycians you forsake?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16615, line : "What from thy thankless arms can we expect?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16616, line : "Thy friend Sarpedon proves thy base neglect;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16617, line : "Say, shall our slaughter'd bodies guard your walls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16618, line : "While unreveng'd the great Sarpedon falls?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16619, line : "Even where he died for Troy, you left him there,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16620, line : "A feast for dogs, and all the fowls of air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16621, line : "On my command if any Lycian wait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16622, line : "Hence let him march, and give up Troy to fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16623, line : "Did such a spirit as the gods impart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16624, line : "Impel one Trojan hand or Trojan heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16625, line : "(Such as should burn in every soul that draws"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16626, line : "The sword for glory, and his country's cause)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16627, line : "Even yet our mutual arms we might employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16628, line : "And drag yon carcase to the walls of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16629, line : "Oh! were Patroclus ours, we might obtain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16630, line : "Sarpedon's arms and honour'd corse again!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16631, line : "Greece with Achilles' friend should be repaid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16632, line : "And thus due honours purchased to his shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16633, line : "But words are vain--Let Ajax once appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16634, line : "And Hector trembles and recedes with fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16635, line : "Thou dar'st not meet the terrors of his eye;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16636, line : "And lo! already thou prepar'st to fly.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16638, line : "The Trojan chief with fix'd resentment eyed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16639, line : "The Lycian leader, and sedate replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16641, line : "\"Say, is it just, my friend, that Hector's ear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16642, line : "From such a warrior such a speech should hear?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16643, line : "I deem'd thee once the wisest of thy kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16644, line : "But ill this insult suits a prudent mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16645, line : "I shun great Ajax? I desert my train?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16646, line : "'Tis mine to prove the rash assertion vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16647, line : "I joy to mingle where the battle bleeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16648, line : "And hear the thunder of the sounding steeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16649, line : "But Jove's high will is ever uncontroll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16650, line : "The strong he withers, and confounds the bold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16651, line : "Now crowns with fame the mighty man, and now"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16652, line : "Strikes the fresh garland from the victor's brow!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16653, line : "Come, through yon squadrons let us hew the way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16654, line : "And thou be witness, if I fear to-day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16655, line : "If yet a Greek the sight of Hector dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16656, line : "Or yet their hero dare defend the dead.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16658, line : "Then turning to the martial hosts, he cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16659, line : "\"Ye Trojans, Dardans, Lycians, and allies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16660, line : "Be men, my friends, in action as in name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16661, line : "And yet be mindful of your ancient fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16662, line : "Hector in proud Achilles' arms shall shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16663, line : "Torn from his friend, by right of conquest mine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16665, line : "He strode along the field, as thus he said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16666, line : "(The sable plumage nodded o'er his head:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16667, line : "Swift through the spacious plain he sent a look;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16668, line : "One instant saw, one instant overtook"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16669, line : "The distant band, that on the sandy shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16670, line : "The radiant spoils to sacred Ilion bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16671, line : "There his own mail unbraced the field bestrow'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16672, line : "His train to Troy convey'd the massy load."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16673, line : "Now blazing in the immortal arms he stands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16674, line : "The work and present of celestial hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16675, line : "By aged Peleus to Achilles given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16676, line : "As first to Peleus by the court of heaven:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16677, line : "His father's arms not long Achilles wears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16678, line : "Forbid by fate to reach his father's years."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16680, line : "Him, proud in triumph, glittering from afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16681, line : "The god whose thunder rends the troubled air"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16682, line : "Beheld with pity; as apart he sat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16683, line : "And, conscious, look'd through all the scene of fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16684, line : "He shook the sacred honours of his head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16685, line : "Olympus trembled, and the godhead said;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16686, line : "\"Ah, wretched man! unmindful of thy end!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16687, line : "A moment's glory; and what fates attend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16688, line : "In heavenly panoply divinely bright"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16689, line : "Thou stand'st, and armies tremble at thy sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16690, line : "As at Achilles' self! beneath thy dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16691, line : "Lies slain the great Achilles' dearer part."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16692, line : "Thou from the mighty dead those arms hast torn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16693, line : "Which once the greatest of mankind had worn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16694, line : "Yet live! I give thee one illustrious day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16695, line : "A blaze of glory ere thou fad'st away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16696, line : "For ah! no more Andromache shall come"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16697, line : "With joyful tears to welcome Hector home;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16698, line : "No more officious, with endearing charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16699, line : "From thy tired limbs unbrace Pelides' arms!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16701, line : "Then with his sable brow he gave the nod"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16702, line : "That seals his word; the sanction of the god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16703, line : "The stubborn arms (by Jove's command disposed)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16704, line : "Conform'd spontaneous, and around him closed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16705, line : "Fill'd with the god, enlarged his members grew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16706, line : "Through all his veins a sudden vigour flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16707, line : "The blood in brisker tides began to roll,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16708, line : "And Mars himself came rushing on his soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16709, line : "Exhorting loud through all the field he strode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16710, line : "And look'd, and moved, Achilles, or a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16711, line : "Now Mesthles, Glaucus, Medon, he inspires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16712, line : "Now Phorcys, Chromius, and Hippothous fires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16713, line : "The great Thersilochus like fury found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16714, line : "Asteropaeus kindled at the sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16715, line : "And Ennomus, in augury renown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16717, line : "\"Hear, all ye hosts, and hear, unnumber'd bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16718, line : "Of neighbouring nations, or of distant lands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16719, line : "'Twas not for state we summon'd you so far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16720, line : "To boast our numbers, and the pomp of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16721, line : "Ye came to fight; a valiant foe to chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16722, line : "To save our present, and our future race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16723, line : "Tor this, our wealth, our products, you enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16724, line : "And glean the relics of exhausted Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16725, line : "Now then, to conquer or to die prepare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16726, line : "To die or conquer are the terms of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16727, line : "Whatever hand shall win Patroclus slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16728, line : "Whoe'er shall drag him to the Trojan train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16729, line : "With Hector's self shall equal honours claim;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16730, line : "With Hector part the spoil, and share the fame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16732, line : "Fired by his words, the troops dismiss their fears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16733, line : "They join, they thicken, they protend their spears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16734, line : "Full on the Greeks they drive in firm array,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16735, line : "And each from Ajax hopes the glorious prey:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16736, line : "Vain hope! what numbers shall the field o'erspread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16737, line : "What victims perish round the mighty dead!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16739, line : "Great Ajax mark'd the growing storm from far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16740, line : "And thus bespoke his brother of the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16741, line : "\"Our fatal day, alas! is come, my friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16742, line : "And all our wars and glories at an end!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16743, line : "'Tis not this corse alone we guard in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16744, line : "Condemn'd to vultures on the Trojan plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16745, line : "We too must yield: the same sad fate must fall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16746, line : "On thee, on me, perhaps, my friend, on all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16747, line : "See what a tempest direful Hector spreads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16748, line : "And lo! it bursts, it thunders on our heads!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16749, line : "Call on our Greeks, if any hear the call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16750, line : "The bravest Greeks: this hour demands them all.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16752, line : "The warrior raised his voice, and wide around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16753, line : "The field re-echoed the distressful sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16754, line : "\"O chiefs! O princes, to whose hand is given"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16755, line : "The rule of men; whose glory is from heaven!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16756, line : "Whom with due honours both Atrides grace:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16757, line : "Ye guides and guardians of our Argive race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16758, line : "All, whom this well-known voice shall reach from far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16759, line : "All, whom I see not through this cloud of war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16760, line : "Come all! let generous rage your arms employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16761, line : "And save Patroclus from the dogs of Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16763, line : "Oilean Ajax first the voice obey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16764, line : "Swift was his pace, and ready was his aid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16765, line : "Next him Idomeneus, more slow with age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16766, line : "And Merion, burning with a hero's rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16767, line : "The long-succeeding numbers who can name?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16768, line : "But all were Greeks, and eager all for fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16769, line : "Fierce to the charge great Hector led the throng;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16770, line : "Whole Troy embodied rush'd with shouts along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16771, line : "Thus, when a mountain billow foams and raves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16772, line : "Where some swoln river disembogues his waves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16773, line : "Full in the mouth is stopp'd the rushing tide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16774, line : "The boiling ocean works from side to side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16775, line : "The river trembles to his utmost shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16776, line : "And distant rocks re-bellow to the roar."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16778, line : "Nor less resolved, the firm Achaian band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16779, line : "With brazen shields in horrid circle stand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16780, line : "Jove, pouring darkness o'er the mingled fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16781, line : "Conceals the warriors' shining helms in night:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16782, line : "To him, the chief for whom the hosts contend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16783, line : "Had lived not hateful, for he lived a friend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16784, line : "Dead he protects him with superior care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16785, line : "Nor dooms his carcase to the birds of air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16787, line : "[Illustration: FIGHT FOR THE BODY OF PATROCLUS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16789, line : "FIGHT FOR THE BODY OF PATROCLUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16792, line : "The first attack the Grecians scarce sustain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16793, line : "Repulsed, they yield; the Trojans seize the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16794, line : "Then fierce they rally, to revenge led on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16795, line : "By the swift rage of Ajax Telamon."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16796, line : "(Ajax to Peleus' son the second name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16797, line : "In graceful stature next, and next in fame)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16798, line : "With headlong force the foremost ranks he tore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16799, line : "So through the thicket bursts the mountain boar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16800, line : "And rudely scatters, for a distance round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16801, line : "The frighted hunter and the baying hound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16802, line : "The son of Lethus, brave Pelasgus' heir,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16803, line : "Hippothous, dragg'd the carcase through the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16804, line : "The sinewy ankles bored, the feet he bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16805, line : "With thongs inserted through the double wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16806, line : "Inevitable fate o'ertakes the deed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16807, line : "Doom'd by great Ajax' vengeful lance to bleed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16808, line : "It cleft the helmet's brazen cheeks in twain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16809, line : "The shatter'd crest and horse-hair strow the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16810, line : "With nerves relax'd he tumbles to the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16811, line : "The brain comes gushing through the ghastly wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16812, line : "He drops Patroclus' foot, and o'er him spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16813, line : "Now lies a sad companion of the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16814, line : "Far from Larissa lies, his native air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16815, line : "And ill requites his parents' tender care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16816, line : "Lamented youth! in life's first bloom he fell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16817, line : "Sent by great Ajax to the shades of hell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16819, line : "Once more at Ajax Hector's javelin flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16820, line : "The Grecian marking, as it cut the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16821, line : "Shunn'd the descending death; which hissing on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16822, line : "Stretch'd in the dust the great Iphytus' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16823, line : "Schedius the brave, of all the Phocian kind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16824, line : "The boldest warrior and the noblest mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16825, line : "In little Panope, for strength renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16826, line : "He held his seat, and ruled the realms around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16827, line : "Plunged in his throat, the weapon drank his blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16828, line : "And deep transpiercing through the shoulder stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16829, line : "In clanging arms the hero fell and all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16830, line : "The fields resounded with his weighty fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16832, line : "Phorcys, as slain Hippothous he defends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16833, line : "The Telamonian lance his belly rends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16834, line : "The hollow armour burst before the stroke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16835, line : "And through the wound the rushing entrails broke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16836, line : "In strong convulsions panting on the sands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16837, line : "He lies, and grasps the dust with dying hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16839, line : "Struck at the sight, recede the Trojan train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16840, line : "The shouting Argives strip the heroes slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16841, line : "And now had Troy, by Greece compell'd to yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16842, line : "Fled to her ramparts, and resign'd the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16843, line : "Greece, in her native fortitude elate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16844, line : "With Jove averse, had turn'd the scale of fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16845, line : "But Phoebus urged Ćneas to the fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16846, line : "He seem'd like aged Periphas to sight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16847, line : "(A herald in Anchises' love grown old,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16848, line : "Revered for prudence, and with prudence bold.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16850, line : "Thus he--\"What methods yet, O chief! remain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16851, line : "To save your Troy, though heaven its fall ordain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16852, line : "There have been heroes, who, by virtuous care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16853, line : "By valour, numbers, and by arts of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16854, line : "Have forced the powers to spare a sinking state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16855, line : "And gain'd at length the glorious odds of fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16856, line : "But you, when fortune smiles, when Jove declares"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16857, line : "His partial favour, and assists your wars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16858, line : "Your shameful efforts 'gainst yourselves employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16859, line : "And force the unwilling god to ruin Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16861, line : "Ćneas through the form assumed descries"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16862, line : "The power conceal'd, and thus to Hector cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16863, line : "\"Oh lasting shame! to our own fears a prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16864, line : "We seek our ramparts, and desert the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16865, line : "A god, nor is he less, my bosom warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16866, line : "And tells me, Jove asserts the Trojan arms.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16868, line : "He spoke, and foremost to the combat flew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16869, line : "The bold example all his hosts pursue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16870, line : "Then, first, Leocritus beneath him bled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16871, line : "In vain beloved by valiant Lycomede;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16872, line : "Who view'd his fall, and, grieving at the chance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16873, line : "Swift to revenge it sent his angry lance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16874, line : "The whirling lance, with vigorous force address'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16875, line : "Descends, and pants in Apisaon's breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16876, line : "From rich Paeonia's vales the warrior came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16877, line : "Next thee, Asteropeus! in place and fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16878, line : "Asteropeus with grief beheld the slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16879, line : "And rush'd to combat, but he rush'd in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16880, line : "Indissolubly firm, around the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16881, line : "Rank within rank, on buckler buckler spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16882, line : "And hemm'd with bristled spears, the Grecians stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16883, line : "A brazen bulwark, and an iron wood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16884, line : "Great Ajax eyes them with incessant care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16885, line : "And in an orb contracts the crowded war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16886, line : "Close in their ranks commands to fight or fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16887, line : "And stands the centre and the soul of all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16888, line : "Fix'd on the spot they war, and wounded, wound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16889, line : "A sanguine torrent steeps the reeking ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16890, line : "On heaps the Greeks, on heaps the Trojans bled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16891, line : "And, thickening round them, rise the hills of dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16893, line : "Greece, in close order, and collected might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16894, line : "Yet suffers least, and sways the wavering fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16895, line : "Fierce as conflicting fires the combat burns,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16896, line : "And now it rises, now it sinks by turns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16897, line : "In one thick darkness all the fight was lost;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16898, line : "The sun, the moon, and all the ethereal host"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16899, line : "Seem'd as extinct: day ravish'd from their eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16900, line : "And all heaven's splendours blotted from the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16901, line : "Such o'er Patroclus' body hung the night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16902, line : "The rest in sunshine fought, and open light;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16903, line : "Unclouded there, the aerial azure spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16904, line : "No vapour rested on the mountain's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16905, line : "The golden sun pour'd forth a stronger ray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16906, line : "And all the broad expansion flamed with day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16907, line : "Dispersed around the plain, by fits they fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16908, line : "And here and there their scatter'd arrows light:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16909, line : "But death and darkness o'er the carcase spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16910, line : "There burn'd the war, and there the mighty bled."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16912, line : "Meanwhile the sons of Nestor, in the rear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16913, line : "(Their fellows routed,) toss the distant spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16914, line : "And skirmish wide: so Nestor gave command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16915, line : "When from the ships he sent the Pylian band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16916, line : "The youthful brothers thus for fame contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16917, line : "Nor knew the fortune of Achilles' friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16918, line : "In thought they view'd him still, with martial joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16919, line : "Glorious in arms, and dealing death to Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16921, line : "But round the corse the heroes pant for breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16922, line : "And thick and heavy grows the work of death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16923, line : "O'erlabour'd now, with dust, and sweat, and gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16924, line : "Their knees, their legs, their feet, are covered o'er;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16925, line : "Drops follow drops, the clouds on clouds arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16926, line : "And carnage clogs their hands, and darkness fills their eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16927, line : "As when a slaughter'd bull's yet reeking hide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16928, line : "Strain'd with full force, and tugg'd from side to side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16929, line : "The brawny curriers stretch; and labour o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16930, line : "The extended surface, drunk with fat and gore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16931, line : "So tugging round the corse both armies stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16932, line : "The mangled body bathed in sweat and blood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16933, line : "While Greeks and Ilians equal strength employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16934, line : "Now to the ships to force it, now to Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16935, line : "Not Pallas' self, her breast when fury warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16936, line : "Nor he whose anger sets the world in arms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16937, line : "Could blame this scene; such rage, such horror reign'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16938, line : "Such, Jove to honour the great dead ordain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16940, line : "Achilles in his ships at distance lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16941, line : "Nor knew the fatal fortune of the day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16942, line : "He, yet unconscious of Patroclus' fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16943, line : "In dust extended under Ilion's wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16944, line : "Expects him glorious from the conquered plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16945, line : "And for his wish'd return prepares in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16946, line : "Though well he knew, to make proud Ilion bend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16947, line : "Was more than heaven had destined to his friend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16948, line : "Perhaps to him: this Thetis had reveal'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16949, line : "The rest, in pity to her son, conceal'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16951, line : "Still raged the conflict round the hero dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16952, line : "And heaps on heaps by mutual wounds they bled."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16953, line : "\"Cursed be the man (even private Greeks would say)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16954, line : "Who dares desert this well-disputed day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16955, line : "First may the cleaving earth before our eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16956, line : "Gape wide, and drink our blood for sacrifice;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16957, line : "First perish all, ere haughty Troy shall boast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16958, line : "We lost Patroclus, and our glory lost!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16960, line : "Thus they: while with one voice the Trojans said,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16961, line : "\"Grant this day, Jove! or heap us on the dead!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16963, line : "Then clash their sounding arms; the clangours rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16964, line : "And shake the brazen concave of the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16966, line : "Meantime, at distance from the scene of blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16967, line : "The pensive steeds of great Achilles stood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16968, line : "Their godlike master slain before their eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16969, line : "They wept, and shared in human miseries.(248)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16970, line : "In vain Automedon now shakes the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16971, line : "Now plies the lash, and soothes and threats in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16972, line : "Nor to the fight nor Hellespont they go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16973, line : "Restive they stood, and obstinate in woe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16974, line : "Still as a tombstone, never to be moved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16975, line : "On some good man or woman unreproved"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16976, line : "Lays its eternal weight; or fix'd, as stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16977, line : "A marble courser by the sculptor's hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16978, line : "Placed on the hero's grave. Along their face"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16979, line : "The big round drops coursed down with silent pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16980, line : "Conglobing on the dust. Their manes, that late"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16981, line : "Circled their arched necks, and waved in state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16982, line : "Trail'd on the dust beneath the yoke were spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16983, line : "And prone to earth was hung their languid head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16984, line : "Nor Jove disdain'd to cast a pitying look,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16985, line : "While thus relenting to the steeds he spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16987, line : "\"Unhappy coursers of immortal strain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16988, line : "Exempt from age, and deathless, now in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16989, line : "Did we your race on mortal man bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16990, line : "Only, alas! to share in mortal woe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16991, line : "For ah! what is there of inferior birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16992, line : "That breathes or creeps upon the dust of earth;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16993, line : "What wretched creature of what wretched kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16994, line : "Than man more weak, calamitous, and blind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16995, line : "A miserable race! but cease to mourn:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16996, line : "For not by you shall Priam's son be borne"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16997, line : "High on the splendid car: one glorious prize"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16998, line : "He rashly boasts: the rest our will denies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 16999, line : "Ourself will swiftness to your nerves impart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17000, line : "Ourself with rising spirits swell your heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17001, line : "Automedon your rapid flight shall bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17002, line : "Safe to the navy through the storm of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17003, line : "For yet 'tis given to Troy to ravage o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17004, line : "The field, and spread her slaughters to the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17005, line : "The sun shall see her conquer, till his fall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17006, line : "With sacred darkness shades the face of all.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17008, line : "He said; and breathing in the immortal horse"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17009, line : "Excessive spirit, urged them to the course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17010, line : "From their high manes they shake the dust, and bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17011, line : "The kindling chariot through the parted war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17012, line : "So flies a vulture through the clamorous train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17013, line : "Of geese, that scream, and scatter round the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17014, line : "From danger now with swiftest speed they flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17015, line : "And now to conquest with like speed pursue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17016, line : "Sole in the seat the charioteer remains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17017, line : "Now plies the javelin, now directs the reins:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17018, line : "Him brave Alcimedon beheld distress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17019, line : "Approach'd the chariot, and the chief address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17021, line : "\"What god provokes thee rashly thus to dare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17022, line : "Alone, unaided, in the thickest war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17023, line : "Alas! thy friend is slain, and Hector wields"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17024, line : "Achilles' arms triumphant in the fields.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17026, line : "\"In happy time (the charioteer replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17027, line : "The bold Alcimedon now greets my eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17028, line : "No Greek like him the heavenly steeds restrains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17029, line : "Or holds their fury in suspended reins:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17030, line : "Patroclus, while he lived, their rage could tame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17031, line : "But now Patroclus is an empty name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17032, line : "To thee I yield the seat, to thee resign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17033, line : "The ruling charge: the task of fight be mine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17035, line : "He said. Alcimedon, with active heat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17036, line : "Snatches the reins, and vaults into the seat."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17037, line : "His friend descends. The chief of Troy descried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17038, line : "And call'd Ćneas fighting near his side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17040, line : "\"Lo, to my sight, beyond our hope restored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17041, line : "Achilles' car, deserted of its lord!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17042, line : "The glorious steeds our ready arms invite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17043, line : "Scarce their weak drivers guide them through the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17044, line : "Can such opponents stand when we assail?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17045, line : "Unite thy force, my friend, and we prevail.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17047, line : "The son of Venus to the counsel yields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17048, line : "Then o'er their backs they spread their solid shields:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17049, line : "With brass refulgent the broad surface shined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17050, line : "And thick bull-hides the spacious concave lined."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17051, line : "Them Chromius follows, Aretus succeeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17052, line : "Each hopes the conquest of the lofty steeds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17053, line : "In vain, brave youths, with glorious hopes ye burn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17054, line : "In vain advance! not fated to return."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17056, line : "Unmov'd, Automedon attends the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17057, line : "Implores the Eternal, and collects his might."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17058, line : "Then turning to his friend, with dauntless mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17059, line : "\"Oh keep the foaming coursers close behind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17060, line : "Full on my shoulders let their nostrils blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17061, line : "For hard the fight, determined is the foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17062, line : "'Tis Hector comes: and when he seeks the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17063, line : "War knows no mean; he wins it or he dies.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17065, line : "Then through the field he sends his voice aloud,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17066, line : "And calls the Ajaces from the warring crowd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17067, line : "With great Atrides. \"Hither turn, (he said,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17068, line : "Turn where distress demands immediate aid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17069, line : "The dead, encircled by his friends, forego,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17070, line : "And save the living from a fiercer foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17071, line : "Unhelp'd we stand, unequal to engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17072, line : "The force of Hector, and Ćneas' rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17073, line : "Yet mighty as they are, my force to prove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17074, line : "Is only mine: the event belongs to Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17076, line : "He spoke, and high the sounding javelin flung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17077, line : "Which pass'd the shield of Aretus the young:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17078, line : "It pierced his belt, emboss'd with curious art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17079, line : "Then in the lower belly struck the dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17080, line : "As when a ponderous axe, descending full,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17081, line : "Cleaves the broad forehead of some brawny bull:(249)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17082, line : "Struck 'twixt the horns, he springs with many a bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17083, line : "Then tumbling rolls enormous on the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17084, line : "Thus fell the youth; the air his soul received,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17085, line : "And the spear trembled as his entrails heaved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17087, line : "Now at Automedon the Trojan foe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17088, line : "Discharged his lance; the meditated blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17089, line : "Stooping, he shunn'd; the javelin idly fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17090, line : "And hiss'd innoxious o'er the hero's head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17091, line : "Deep rooted in the ground, the forceful spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17092, line : "In long vibrations spent its fury there."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17093, line : "With clashing falchions now the chiefs had closed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17094, line : "But each brave Ajax heard, and interposed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17095, line : "Nor longer Hector with his Trojans stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17096, line : "But left their slain companion in his blood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17097, line : "His arms Automedon divests, and cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17098, line : "\"Accept, Patroclus, this mean sacrifice:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17099, line : "Thus have I soothed my griefs, and thus have paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17100, line : "Poor as it is, some offering to thy shade.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17102, line : "So looks the lion o'er a mangled boar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17103, line : "All grim with rage, and horrible with gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17104, line : "High on the chariot at one bound he sprung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17105, line : "And o'er his seat the bloody trophies hung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17107, line : "And now Minerva from the realms of air"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17108, line : "Descends impetuous, and renews the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17109, line : "For, pleased at length the Grecian arms to aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17110, line : "The lord of thunders sent the blue-eyed maid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17111, line : "As when high Jove denouncing future woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17112, line : "O'er the dark clouds extends his purple bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17113, line : "(In sign of tempests from the troubled air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17114, line : "Or from the rage of man, destructive war,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17115, line : "The drooping cattle dread the impending skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17116, line : "And from his half-till'd field the labourer flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17117, line : "In such a form the goddess round her drew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17118, line : "A livid cloud, and to the battle flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17119, line : "Assuming Phoenix' shape on earth she falls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17120, line : "And in his well-known voice to Sparta calls:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17121, line : "\"And lies Achilles' friend, beloved by all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17122, line : "A prey to dogs beneath the Trojan wall?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17123, line : "What shame 'o Greece for future times to tell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17124, line : "To thee the greatest in whose cause he fell!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17125, line : "\"O chief, O father! (Atreus' son replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17126, line : "O full of days! by long experience wise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17127, line : "What more desires my soul, than here unmoved"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17128, line : "To guard the body of the man I loved?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17129, line : "Ah, would Minerva send me strength to rear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17130, line : "This wearied arm, and ward the storm of war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17131, line : "But Hector, like the rage of fire, we dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17132, line : "And Jove's own glories blaze around his head!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17134, line : "Pleased to be first of all the powers address'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17135, line : "She breathes new vigour in her hero's breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17136, line : "And fills with keen revenge, with fell despite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17137, line : "Desire of blood, and rage, and lust of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17138, line : "So burns the vengeful hornet (soul all o'er),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17139, line : "Repulsed in vain, and thirsty still of gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17140, line : "(Bold son of air and heat) on angry wings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17141, line : "Untamed, untired, he turns, attacks, and stings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17142, line : "Fired with like ardour fierce Atrides flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17143, line : "And sent his soul with every lance he threw."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17145, line : "There stood a Trojan, not unknown to fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17146, line : "Aetion's son, and Podes was his name:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17147, line : "With riches honour'd, and with courage bless'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17148, line : "By Hector loved, his comrade, and his guest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17149, line : "Through his broad belt the spear a passage found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17150, line : "And, ponderous as he falls, his arms resound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17151, line : "Sudden at Hector's side Apollo stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17152, line : "Like Phaenops, Asius' son, appear'd the god;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17153, line : "(Asius the great, who held his wealthy reign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17154, line : "In fair Abydos, by the rolling main.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17156, line : "\"Oh prince! (he cried) Oh foremost once in fame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17157, line : "What Grecian now shall tremble at thy name?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17158, line : "Dost thou at length to Menelaus yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17159, line : "A chief once thought no terror of the field?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17160, line : "Yet singly, now, the long-disputed prize"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17161, line : "He bears victorious, while our army flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17162, line : "By the same arm illustrious Podes bled;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17163, line : "The friend of Hector, unrevenged, is dead!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17164, line : "This heard, o'er Hector spreads a cloud of woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17165, line : "Rage lifts his lance, and drives him on the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17167, line : "But now the Eternal shook his sable shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17168, line : "That shaded Ide and all the subject field"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17169, line : "Beneath its ample verge. A rolling cloud"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17170, line : "Involved the mount; the thunder roar'd aloud;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17171, line : "The affrighted hills from their foundations nod,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17172, line : "And blaze beneath the lightnings of the god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17173, line : "At one regard of his all-seeing eye"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17174, line : "The vanquish'd triumph, and the victors fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17176, line : "Then trembled Greece: the flight Peneleus led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17177, line : "For as the brave Boeotian turn'd his head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17178, line : "To face the foe, Polydamas drew near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17179, line : "And razed his shoulder with a shorten'd spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17180, line : "By Hector wounded, Leitus quits the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17181, line : "Pierced through the wrist; and raging with the pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17182, line : "Grasps his once formidable lance in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17184, line : "As Hector follow'd, Idomen address'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17185, line : "The flaming javelin to his manly breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17186, line : "The brittle point before his corslet yields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17187, line : "Exulting Troy with clamour fills the fields:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17188, line : "High on his chariots the Cretan stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17189, line : "The son of Priam whirl'd the massive wood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17190, line : "But erring from its aim, the impetuous spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17191, line : "Struck to the dust the squire and charioteer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17192, line : "Of martial Merion: Coeranus his name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17193, line : "Who left fair Lyctus for the fields of fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17194, line : "On foot bold Merion fought; and now laid low,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17195, line : "Had graced the triumphs of his Trojan foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17196, line : "But the brave squire the ready coursers brought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17197, line : "And with his life his master's safety bought."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17198, line : "Between his cheek and ear the weapon went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17199, line : "The teeth it shatter'd, and the tongue it rent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17200, line : "Prone from the seat he tumbles to the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17201, line : "His dying hand forgets the falling rein:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17202, line : "This Merion reaches, bending from the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17203, line : "And urges to desert the hopeless war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17204, line : "Idomeneus consents; the lash applies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17205, line : "And the swift chariot to the navy flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17207, line : "Not Ajax less the will of heaven descried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17208, line : "And conquest shifting to the Trojan side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17209, line : "Turn'd by the hand of Jove. Then thus begun,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17210, line : "To Atreus's seed, the godlike Telamon:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17212, line : "\"Alas! who sees not Jove's almighty hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17213, line : "Transfers the glory to the Trojan band?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17214, line : "Whether the weak or strong discharge the dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17215, line : "He guides each arrow to a Grecian heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17216, line : "Not so our spears; incessant though they rain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17217, line : "He suffers every lance to fall in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17218, line : "Deserted of the god, yet let us try"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17219, line : "What human strength and prudence can supply;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17220, line : "If yet this honour'd corse, in triumph borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17221, line : "May glad the fleets that hope not our return,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17222, line : "Who tremble yet, scarce rescued from their fates,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17223, line : "And still hear Hector thundering at their gates."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17224, line : "Some hero too must be despatch'd to bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17225, line : "The mournful message to Pelides' ear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17226, line : "For sure he knows not, distant on the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17227, line : "His friend, his loved Patroclus, is no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17228, line : "But such a chief I spy not through the host:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17229, line : "The men, the steeds, the armies, all are lost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17230, line : "In general darkness--Lord of earth and air!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17231, line : "Oh king! Oh father! hear my humble prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17232, line : "Dispel this cloud, the light of heaven restore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17233, line : "Give me to see, and Ajax asks no more:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17234, line : "If Greece must perish, we thy will obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17235, line : "But let us perish in the face of day!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17237, line : "With tears the hero spoke, and at his prayer"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17238, line : "The god relenting clear'd the clouded air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17239, line : "Forth burst the sun with all-enlightening ray;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17240, line : "The blaze of armour flash'd against the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17241, line : "\"Now, now, Atrides! cast around thy sight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17242, line : "If yet Antilochus survives the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17243, line : "Let him to great Achilles' ear convey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17244, line : "The fatal news\"--Atrides hastes away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17246, line : "So turns the lion from the nightly fold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17247, line : "Though high in courage, and with hunger bold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17248, line : "Long gall'd by herdsmen, and long vex'd by hounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17249, line : "Stiff with fatigue, and fretted sore with wounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17250, line : "The darts fly round him from a hundred hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17251, line : "And the red terrors of the blazing brands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17252, line : "Till late, reluctant, at the dawn of day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17253, line : "Sour he departs, and quits the untasted prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17254, line : "So moved Atrides from his dangerous place"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17255, line : "With weary limbs, but with unwilling pace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17256, line : "The foe, he fear'd, might yet Patroclus gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17257, line : "And much admonish'd, much adjured his train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17259, line : "\"O guard these relics to your charge consign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17260, line : "And bear the merits of the dead in mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17261, line : "How skill'd he was in each obliging art;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17262, line : "The mildest manners, and the gentlest heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17263, line : "He was, alas! but fate decreed his end,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17264, line : "In death a hero, as in life a friend!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17266, line : "So parts the chief; from rank to rank he flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17267, line : "And round on all sides sent his piercing view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17268, line : "As the bold bird, endued with sharpest eye"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17269, line : "Of all that wings the mid aerial sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17270, line : "The sacred eagle, from his walks above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17271, line : "Looks down, and sees the distant thicket move;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17272, line : "Then stoops, and sousing on the quivering hare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17273, line : "Snatches his life amid the clouds of air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17274, line : "Not with less quickness, his exerted sight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17275, line : "Pass'd this and that way, through the ranks of fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17276, line : "Till on the left the chief he sought, he found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17277, line : "Cheering his men, and spreading deaths around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17279, line : "To him the king: \"Beloved of Jove! draw near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17280, line : "For sadder tidings never touch'd thy ear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17281, line : "Thy eyes have witness'd what a fatal turn!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17282, line : "How Ilion triumphs, and the Achaians mourn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17283, line : "This is not all: Patroclus, on the shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17284, line : "Now pale and dead, shall succour Greece no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17285, line : "Fly to the fleet, this instant fly, and tell"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17286, line : "The sad Achilles, how his loved-one fell:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17287, line : "He too may haste the naked corse to gain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17288, line : "The arms are Hector's, who despoil'd the slain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17290, line : "The youthful warrior heard with silent woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17291, line : "From his fair eyes the tears began to flow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17292, line : "Big with the mighty grief, he strove to say"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17293, line : "What sorrow dictates, but no word found way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17294, line : "To brave Laodocus his arms he flung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17295, line : "Who, near him wheeling, drove his steeds along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17296, line : "Then ran the mournful message to impart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17297, line : "With tearful eyes, and with dejected heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17299, line : "Swift fled the youth: nor Menelaus stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17300, line : "(Though sore distress'd) to aid the Pylian bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17301, line : "But bids bold Thrasymede those troops sustain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17302, line : "Himself returns to his Patroclus slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17303, line : "\"Gone is Antilochus (the hero said);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17304, line : "But hope not, warriors, for Achilles' aid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17305, line : "Though fierce his rage, unbounded be his woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17306, line : "Unarm'd, he fights not with the Trojan foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17307, line : "'Tis in our hands alone our hopes remain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17308, line : "'Tis our own vigour must the dead regain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17309, line : "And save ourselves, while with impetuous hate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17310, line : "Troy pours along, and this way rolls our fate.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17312, line : "\"'Tis well (said Ajax), be it then thy care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17313, line : "With Merion's aid, the weighty corse to rear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17314, line : "Myself, and my bold brother will sustain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17315, line : "The shock of Hector and his charging train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17316, line : "Nor fear we armies, fighting side by side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17317, line : "What Troy can dare, we have already tried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17318, line : "Have tried it, and have stood.\" The hero said."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17319, line : "High from the ground the warriors heave the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17320, line : "A general clamour rises at the sight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17321, line : "Loud shout the Trojans, and renew the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17322, line : "Not fiercer rush along the gloomy wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17323, line : "With rage insatiate, and with thirst of blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17324, line : "Voracious hounds, that many a length before"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17325, line : "Their furious hunters, drive the wounded boar;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17326, line : "But if the savage turns his glaring eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17327, line : "They howl aloof, and round the forest fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17328, line : "Thus on retreating Greece the Trojans pour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17329, line : "Wave their thick falchions, and their javelins shower:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17330, line : "But Ajax turning, to their fears they yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17331, line : "All pale they tremble and forsake the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17333, line : "While thus aloft the hero's corse they bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17334, line : "Behind them rages all the storm of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17335, line : "Confusion, tumult, horror, o'er the throng"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17336, line : "Of men, steeds, chariots, urged the rout along:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17337, line : "Less fierce the winds with rising flames conspire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17338, line : "To whelm some city under waves of fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17339, line : "Now sink in gloomy clouds the proud abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17340, line : "Now crack the blazing temples of the gods;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17341, line : "The rumbling torrent through the ruin rolls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17342, line : "And sheets of smoke mount heavy to the poles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17343, line : "The heroes sweat beneath their honour'd load:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17344, line : "As when two mules, along the rugged road,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17345, line : "From the steep mountain with exerted strength"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17346, line : "Drag some vast beam, or mast's unwieldy length;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17347, line : "Inly they groan, big drops of sweat distil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17348, line : "The enormous timber lumbering down the hill:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17349, line : "So these--Behind, the bulk of Ajax stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17350, line : "And breaks the torrent of the rushing bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17351, line : "Thus when a river swell'd with sudden rains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17352, line : "Spreads his broad waters o'er the level plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17353, line : "Some interposing hill the stream divides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17354, line : "And breaks its force, and turns the winding tides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17355, line : "Still close they follow, close the rear engage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17356, line : "Aeneas storms, and Hector foams with rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17357, line : "While Greece a heavy, thick retreat maintains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17358, line : "Wedged in one body, like a flight of cranes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17359, line : "That shriek incessant, while the falcon, hung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17360, line : "High on poised pinions, threats their callow young."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17361, line : "So from the Trojan chiefs the Grecians fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17362, line : "Such the wild terror, and the mingled cry:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17363, line : "Within, without the trench, and all the way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17364, line : "Strow'd in bright heaps, their arms and armour lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17365, line : "Such horror Jove impress'd! yet still proceeds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17366, line : "The work of death, and still the battle bleeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17368, line : "[Illustration: VULCAN FROM AN ANTIQUE GEM.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17370, line : "VULCAN FROM AN ANTIQUE GEM."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17376, line : "BOOK XVIII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17379, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17381, line : "THE GRIEF OF ACHILLES, AND NEW ARMOUR MADE HIM BY VULCAN."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17383, line : "The news of the death of Patroclus is brought to Achilles by Antilochus."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17384, line : "Thetis, hearing his lamentations, comes with all her sea- nymphs to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17385, line : "comfort him. The speeches of the mother and son on this occasion. Iris"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17386, line : "appears to Achilles by the command of Juno, and orders him to show himself"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17387, line : "at the head of the intrenchments. The sight of him turns the fortunes of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17388, line : "the day, and the body of Patroclus is carried off by the Greeks. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17389, line : "Trojans call a council, where Hector and Polydamas disagree in their"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17390, line : "opinions: but the advice of the former prevails, to remain encamped in the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17391, line : "field. The grief of Achilles over the body of Patroclus."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17393, line : "Thetis goes to the palace of Vulcan to obtain new arms for her son. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17394, line : "description of the wonderful works of Vulcan: and, lastly, that noble one"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17395, line : "of the shield of Achilles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17397, line : "The latter part of the nine-and-twentieth day, and the night ensuing, take"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17398, line : "up this book: the scene is at Achilles' tent on the sea-shore, from whence"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17399, line : "it changes to the palace of Vulcan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17401, line : "Thus like the rage of fire the combat burns,(250)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17402, line : "And now it rises, now it sinks by turns."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17403, line : "Meanwhile, where Hellespont's broad waters flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17404, line : "Stood Nestor's son, the messenger of woe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17405, line : "There sat Achilles, shaded by his sails,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17406, line : "On hoisted yards extended to the gales;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17407, line : "Pensive he sat; for all that fate design'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17408, line : "Rose in sad prospect to his boding mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17409, line : "Thus to his soul he said: \"Ah! what constrains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17410, line : "The Greeks, late victors, now to quit the plains?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17411, line : "Is this the day, which heaven so long ago"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17412, line : "Ordain'd, to sink me with the weight of woe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17413, line : "(So Thetis warn'd;) when by a Trojan hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17414, line : "The bravest of the Myrmidonian band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17415, line : "Should lose the light! Fulfilled is that decree;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17416, line : "Fallen is the warrior, and Patroclus he!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17417, line : "In vain I charged him soon to quit the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17418, line : "And warn'd to shun Hectorean force in vain!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17420, line : "Thus while he thinks, Antilochus appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17421, line : "And tells the melancholy tale with tears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17422, line : "\"Sad tidings, son of Peleus! thou must hear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17423, line : "And wretched I, the unwilling messenger!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17424, line : "Dead is Patroclus! For his corse they fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17425, line : "His naked corse: his arms are Hector's right.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17427, line : "A sudden horror shot through all the chief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17428, line : "And wrapp'd his senses in the cloud of grief;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17429, line : "Cast on the ground, with furious hands he spread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17430, line : "The scorching ashes o'er his graceful head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17431, line : "His purple garments, and his golden hairs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17432, line : "Those he deforms with dust, and these he tears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17433, line : "On the hard soil his groaning breast he threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17434, line : "And roll'd and grovell'd, as to earth he grew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17435, line : "The virgin captives, with disorder'd charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17436, line : "(Won by his own, or by Patroclus' arms,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17437, line : "Rush'd from their tents with cries; and gathering round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17438, line : "Beat their white breasts, and fainted on the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17439, line : "While Nestor's son sustains a manlier part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17440, line : "And mourns the warrior with a warrior's heart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17441, line : "Hangs on his arms, amidst his frantic woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17442, line : "And oft prevents the meditated blow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17444, line : "Far in the deep abysses of the main,(251)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17445, line : "With hoary Nereus, and the watery train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17446, line : "The mother-goddess from her crystal throne"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17447, line : "Heard his loud cries, and answer'd groan for groan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17448, line : "The circling Nereids with their mistress weep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17449, line : "And all the sea-green sisters of the deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17450, line : "Thalia, Glauce (every watery name),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17451, line : "Nesaea mild, and silver Spio came:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17452, line : "Cymothoe and Cymodoce were nigh,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17453, line : "And the blue languish of soft Alia's eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17454, line : "Their locks Actaea and Limnoria rear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17455, line : "Then Proto, Doris, Panope appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17456, line : "Thoa, Pherusa, Doto, Melita;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17457, line : "Agave gentle, and Amphithoe gay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17458, line : "Next Callianira, Callianassa show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17459, line : "Their sister looks; Dexamene the slow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17460, line : "And swift Dynamene, now cut the tides:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17461, line : "Iaera now the verdant wave divides:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17462, line : "Nemertes with Apseudes lifts the head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17463, line : "Bright Galatea quits her pearly bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17464, line : "These Orythia, Clymene, attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17465, line : "Maera, Amphinome, the train extend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17466, line : "And black Janira, and Janassa fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17467, line : "And Amatheia with her amber hair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17468, line : "All these, and all that deep in ocean held"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17469, line : "Their sacred seats, the glimmering grotto fill'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17470, line : "Each beat her ivory breast with silent woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17471, line : "Till Thetis' sorrows thus began to flow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17473, line : "\"Hear me, and judge, ye sisters of the main!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17474, line : "How just a cause has Thetis to complain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17475, line : "How wretched, were I mortal, were my fate!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17476, line : "How more than wretched in the immortal state!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17477, line : "Sprung from my bed a godlike hero came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17478, line : "The bravest far that ever bore the name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17479, line : "Like some fair olive, by my careful hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17480, line : "He grew, he flourish'd and adorn'd the land"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17481, line : "To Troy I sent him: but the fates ordain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17482, line : "He never, never must return again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17483, line : "So short a space the light of heaven to view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17484, line : "So short, alas! and fill'd with anguish too!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17485, line : "Hear how his sorrows echo through the shore!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17486, line : "I cannot ease them, but I must deplore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17487, line : "I go at least to bear a tender part,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17488, line : "And mourn my loved-one with a mother's heart.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17490, line : "She said, and left the caverns of the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17491, line : "All bathed in tears; the melancholy train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17492, line : "Attend her way. Wide-opening part the tides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17493, line : "While the long pomp the silver wave divides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17494, line : "Approaching now, they touch'd the Trojan land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17495, line : "Then, two by two, ascended up the strand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17496, line : "The immortal mother, standing close beside"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17497, line : "Her mournful offspring, to his sighs replied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17498, line : "Along the coast their mingled clamours ran,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17499, line : "And thus the silver-footed dame began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17501, line : "\"Why mourns my son? thy late preferr'd request"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17502, line : "The god has granted, and the Greeks distress'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17503, line : "Why mourns my son? thy anguish let me share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17504, line : "Reveal the cause, and trust a parent's care.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17506, line : "He, deeply groaning--\"To this cureless grief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17507, line : "Not even the Thunderer's favour brings relief."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17508, line : "Patroclus--Ah!--say, goddess, can I boast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17509, line : "A pleasure now? revenge itself is lost;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17510, line : "Patroclus, loved of all my martial train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17511, line : "Beyond mankind, beyond myself is slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17512, line : "Lost are those arms the gods themselves bestow'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17513, line : "On Peleus; Hector bears the glorious load."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17514, line : "Cursed be that day, when all the powers above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17515, line : "Thy charms submitted to a mortal love:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17516, line : "O hadst thou still, a sister of the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17517, line : "Pursued the pleasures of the watery reign:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17518, line : "And happier Peleus, less ambitious, led"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17519, line : "A mortal beauty to his equal bed!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17520, line : "Ere the sad fruit of thy unhappy womb"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17521, line : "Had caused such sorrows past, and woes to come."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17522, line : "For soon, alas! that wretched offspring slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17523, line : "New woes, new sorrows, shall create again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17524, line : "'Tis not in fate the alternate now to give;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17525, line : "Patroclus dead, Achilles hates to live."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17526, line : "Let me revenge it on proud Hector's heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17527, line : "Let his last spirit smoke upon my dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17528, line : "On these conditions will I breathe: till then,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17529, line : "I blush to walk among the race of men.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17531, line : "A flood of tears, at this, the goddess shed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17532, line : "\"Ah then, I see thee dying, see thee dead!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17533, line : "When Hector falls, thou diest.\"--\"Let Hector die,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17534, line : "And let me fall! (Achilles made reply)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17535, line : "Far lies Patroclus from his native plain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17536, line : "He fell, and falling, wish'd my aid in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17537, line : "Ah then, since from this miserable day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17538, line : "I cast all hope of my return away;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17539, line : "Since, unrevenged, a hundred ghosts demand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17540, line : "The fate of Hector from Achilles' hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17541, line : "Since here, for brutal courage far renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17542, line : "I live an idle burden to the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17543, line : "(Others in council famed for nobler skill,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17544, line : "More useful to preserve, than I to kill,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17545, line : "Let me--But oh! ye gracious powers above!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17546, line : "Wrath and revenge from men and gods remove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17547, line : "Far, far too dear to every mortal breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17548, line : "Sweet to the soul, as honey to the taste:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17549, line : "Gathering like vapours of a noxious kind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17550, line : "From fiery blood, and darkening all the mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17551, line : "Me Agamemnon urged to deadly hate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17552, line : "'Tis past--I quell it; I resign to fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17553, line : "Yes--I will meet the murderer of my friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17554, line : "Or (if the gods ordain it) meet my end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17555, line : "The stroke of fate the strongest cannot shun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17556, line : "The great Alcides, Jove's unequall'd son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17557, line : "To Juno's hate, at length resign'd his breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17558, line : "And sunk the victim of all-conquering death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17559, line : "So shall Achilles fall! stretch'd pale and dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17560, line : "No more the Grecian hope, or Trojan dread!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17561, line : "Let me, this instant, rush into the fields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17562, line : "And reap what glory life's short harvest yields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17563, line : "Shall I not force some widow'd dame to tear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17564, line : "With frantic hands her long dishevell'd hair?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17565, line : "Shall I not force her breast to heave with sighs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17566, line : "And the soft tears to trickle from her eyes?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17567, line : "Yes, I shall give the fair those mournful charms--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17568, line : "In vain you hold me--Hence! my arms! my arms!--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17569, line : "Soon shall the sanguine torrent spread so wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17570, line : "That all shall know Achilles swells the tide.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17572, line : "\"My son (coerulean Thetis made reply,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17573, line : "To fate submitting with a secret sigh,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17574, line : "The host to succour, and thy friends to save,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17575, line : "Is worthy thee; the duty of the brave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17576, line : "But canst thou, naked, issue to the plains?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17577, line : "Thy radiant arms the Trojan foe detains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17578, line : "Insulting Hector bears the spoils on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17579, line : "But vainly glories, for his fate is nigh."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17580, line : "Yet, yet awhile thy generous ardour stay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17581, line : "Assured, I meet thee at the dawn of day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17582, line : "Charged with refulgent arms (a glorious load),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17583, line : "Vulcanian arms, the labour of a god.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17585, line : "Then turning to the daughters of the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17586, line : "The goddess thus dismiss'd her azure train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17588, line : "\"Ye sister Nereids! to your deeps descend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17589, line : "Haste, and our father's sacred seat attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17590, line : "I go to find the architect divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17591, line : "Where vast Olympus' starry summits shine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17592, line : "So tell our hoary sire\"--This charge she gave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17593, line : "The sea-green sisters plunge beneath the wave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17594, line : "Thetis once more ascends the bless'd abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17595, line : "And treads the brazen threshold of the gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17597, line : "[Illustration: THETIS ORDERING THE NEREIDS TO DESCEND INTO THE SEA.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17599, line : "THETIS ORDERING THE NEREIDS TO DESCEND INTO THE SEA."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17602, line : "And now the Greeks from furious Hector's force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17603, line : "Urge to broad Hellespont their headlong course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17604, line : "Nor yet their chiefs Patroclus' body bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17605, line : "Safe through the tempest to the tented shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17606, line : "The horse, the foot, with equal fury join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17607, line : "Pour'd on the rear, and thunder'd close behind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17608, line : "And like a flame through fields of ripen'd corn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17609, line : "The rage of Hector o'er the ranks was borne."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17610, line : "Thrice the slain hero by the foot he drew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17611, line : "Thrice to the skies the Trojan clamours flew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17612, line : "As oft the Ajaces his assault sustain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17613, line : "But check'd, he turns; repuls'd, attacks again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17614, line : "With fiercer shouts his lingering troops he fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17615, line : "Nor yields a step, nor from his post retires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17616, line : "So watchful shepherds strive to force, in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17617, line : "The hungry lion from a carcase slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17618, line : "Even yet Patroclus had he borne away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17619, line : "And all the glories of the extended day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17620, line : "Had not high Juno from the realms of air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17621, line : "Secret, despatch'd her trusty messenger."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17622, line : "The various goddess of the showery bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17623, line : "Shot in a whirlwind to the shore below;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17624, line : "To great Achilles at his ships she came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17625, line : "And thus began the many-colour'd dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17627, line : "\"Rise, son of Peleus! rise, divinely brave!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17628, line : "Assist the combat, and Patroclus save:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17629, line : "For him the slaughter to the fleet they spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17630, line : "And fall by mutual wounds around the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17631, line : "To drag him back to Troy the foe contends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17632, line : "Nor with his death the rage of Hector ends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17633, line : "A prey to dogs he dooms the corse to lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17634, line : "And marks the place to fix his head on high."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17635, line : "Rise, and prevent (if yet you think of fame)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17636, line : "Thy friend's disgrace, thy own eternal shame!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17638, line : "\"Who sends thee, goddess, from the ethereal skies?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17639, line : "Achilles thus. And Iris thus replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17641, line : "\"I come, Pelides! from the queen of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17642, line : "The immortal empress of the realms above;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17643, line : "Unknown to him who sits remote on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17644, line : "Unknown to all the synod of the sky.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17645, line : "\"Thou comest in vain (he cries, with fury warm'd);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17646, line : "Arms I have none, and can I fight unarm'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17647, line : "Unwilling as I am, of force I stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17648, line : "Till Thetis bring me at the dawn of day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17649, line : "Vulcanian arms: what other can I wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17650, line : "Except the mighty Telamonian shield?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17651, line : "That, in my friend's defence, has Ajax spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17652, line : "While his strong lance around him heaps the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17653, line : "The gallant chief defends Menoetius' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17654, line : "And does what his Achilles should have done.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17656, line : "\"Thy want of arms (said Iris) well we know;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17657, line : "But though unarm'd, yet clad in terrors, go!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17658, line : "Let but Achilles o'er yon trench appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17659, line : "Proud Troy shall tremble, and consent to fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17660, line : "Greece from one glance of that tremendous eye"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17661, line : "Shall take new courage, and disdain to fly.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17663, line : "She spoke, and pass'd in air. The hero rose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17664, line : "Her aegis Pallas o'er his shoulder throws;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17665, line : "Around his brows a golden cloud she spread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17666, line : "A stream of glory flamed above his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17667, line : "As when from some beleaguer'd town arise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17668, line : "The smokes, high curling to the shaded skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17669, line : "(Seen from some island, o'er the main afar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17670, line : "When men distress'd hang out the sign of war;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17671, line : "Soon as the sun in ocean hides his rays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17672, line : "Thick on the hills the flaming beacons blaze;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17673, line : "With long-projected beams the seas are bright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17674, line : "And heaven's high arch reflects the ruddy light:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17675, line : "So from Achilles' head the splendours rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17676, line : "Reflecting blaze on blaze against the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17677, line : "Forth march'd the chief, and distant from the crowd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17678, line : "High on the rampart raised his voice aloud;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17679, line : "With her own shout Minerva swells the sound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17680, line : "Troy starts astonish'd, and the shores rebound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17681, line : "As the loud trumpet's brazen mouth from far"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17682, line : "With shrilling clangour sounds the alarm of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17683, line : "Struck from the walls, the echoes float on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17684, line : "And the round bulwarks and thick towers reply;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17685, line : "So high his brazen voice the hero rear'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17686, line : "Hosts dropp'd their arms, and trembled as they heard:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17687, line : "And back the chariots roll, and coursers bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17688, line : "And steeds and men lie mingled on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17689, line : "Aghast they see the living lightnings play,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17690, line : "And turn their eyeballs from the flashing ray."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17691, line : "Thrice from the trench his dreadful voice he raised,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17692, line : "And thrice they fled, confounded and amazed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17693, line : "Twelve in the tumult wedged, untimely rush'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17694, line : "On their own spears, by their own chariots crush'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17695, line : "While, shielded from the darts, the Greeks obtain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17696, line : "The long-contended carcase of the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17698, line : "A lofty bier the breathless warrior bears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17699, line : "Around, his sad companions melt in tears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17700, line : "But chief Achilles, bending down his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17701, line : "Pours unavailing sorrows o'er the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17702, line : "Whom late triumphant, with his steeds and car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17703, line : "He sent refulgent to the field of war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17704, line : "(Unhappy change!) now senseless, pale, he found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17705, line : "Stretch'd forth, and gash'd with many a gaping wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17707, line : "Meantime, unwearied with his heavenly way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17708, line : "In ocean's waves the unwilling light of day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17709, line : "Quench'd his red orb, at Juno's high command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17710, line : "And from their labours eased the Achaian band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17711, line : "The frighted Trojans (panting from the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17712, line : "Their steeds unharness'd from the weary car)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17713, line : "A sudden council call'd: each chief appear'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17714, line : "In haste, and standing; for to sit they fear'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17715, line : "'Twas now no season for prolong'd debate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17716, line : "They saw Achilles, and in him their fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17717, line : "Silent they stood: Polydamas at last,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17718, line : "Skill'd to discern the future by the past,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17719, line : "The son of Panthus, thus express'd his fears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17720, line : "(The friend of Hector, and of equal years;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17721, line : "The self-same night to both a being gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17722, line : "One wise in council, one in action brave):"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17724, line : "[Illustration: JUNO COMMANDING THE SUN TO SET.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17726, line : "JUNO COMMANDING THE SUN TO SET."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17729, line : "\"In free debate, my friends, your sentence speak;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17730, line : "For me, I move, before the morning break,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17731, line : "To raise our camp: too dangerous here our post,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17732, line : "Far from Troy walls, and on a naked coast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17733, line : "I deem'd not Greece so dreadful, while engaged"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17734, line : "In mutual feuds her king and hero raged;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17735, line : "Then, while we hoped our armies might prevail"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17736, line : "We boldly camp'd beside a thousand sail."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17737, line : "I dread Pelides now: his rage of mind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17738, line : "Not long continues to the shores confined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17739, line : "Nor to the fields, where long in equal fray"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17740, line : "Contending nations won and lost the day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17741, line : "For Troy, for Troy, shall henceforth be the strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17742, line : "And the hard contest not for fame, but life."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17743, line : "Haste then to Ilion, while the favouring night"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17744, line : "Detains these terrors, keeps that arm from fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17745, line : "If but the morrow's sun behold us here,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17746, line : "That arm, those terrors, we shall feel, not fear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17747, line : "And hearts that now disdain, shall leap with joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17748, line : "If heaven permit them then to enter Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17749, line : "Let not my fatal prophecy be true,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17750, line : "Nor what I tremble but to think, ensue."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17751, line : "Whatever be our fate, yet let us try"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17752, line : "What force of thought and reason can supply;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17753, line : "Let us on counsel for our guard depend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17754, line : "The town her gates and bulwarks shall defend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17755, line : "When morning dawns, our well-appointed powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17756, line : "Array'd in arms, shall line the lofty towers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17757, line : "Let the fierce hero, then, when fury calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17758, line : "Vent his mad vengeance on our rocky walls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17759, line : "Or fetch a thousand circles round the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17760, line : "Till his spent coursers seek the fleet again:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17761, line : "So may his rage be tired, and labour'd down!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17762, line : "And dogs shall tear him ere he sack the town.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17764, line : "\"Return! (said Hector, fired with stern disdain)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17765, line : "What! coop whole armies in our walls again?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17766, line : "Was't not enough, ye valiant warriors, say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17767, line : "Nine years imprison'd in those towers ye lay?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17768, line : "Wide o'er the world was Ilion famed of old"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17769, line : "For brass exhaustless, and for mines of gold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17770, line : "But while inglorious in her walls we stay'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17771, line : "Sunk were her treasures, and her stores decay'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17772, line : "The Phrygians now her scatter'd spoils enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17773, line : "And proud Maeonia wastes the fruits of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17774, line : "Great Jove at length my arms to conquest calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17775, line : "And shuts the Grecians in their wooden walls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17776, line : "Darest thou dispirit whom the gods incite?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17777, line : "Flies any Trojan? I shall stop his flight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17778, line : "To better counsel then attention lend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17779, line : "Take due refreshment, and the watch attend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17780, line : "If there be one whose riches cost him care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17781, line : "Forth let him bring them for the troops to share;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17782, line : "'Tis better generously bestow'd on those,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17783, line : "Than left the plunder of our country's foes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17784, line : "Soon as the morn the purple orient warms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17785, line : "Fierce on yon navy will we pour our arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17786, line : "If great Achilles rise in all his might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17787, line : "His be the danger: I shall stand the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17788, line : "Honour, ye gods! or let me gain or give;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17789, line : "And live he glorious, whosoe'er shall live!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17790, line : "Mars is our common lord, alike to all;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17791, line : "And oft the victor triumphs, but to fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17793, line : "The shouting host in loud applauses join'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17794, line : "So Pallas robb'd the many of their mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17795, line : "To their own sense condemn'd, and left to choose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17796, line : "The worst advice, the better to refuse."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17798, line : "While the long night extends her sable reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17799, line : "Around Patroclus mourn'd the Grecian train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17800, line : "Stern in superior grief Pelides stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17801, line : "Those slaughtering arms, so used to bathe in blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17802, line : "Now clasp his clay-cold limbs: then gushing start"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17803, line : "The tears, and sighs burst from his swelling heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17804, line : "The lion thus, with dreadful anguish stung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17805, line : "Roars through the desert, and demands his young;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17806, line : "When the grim savage, to his rifled den"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17807, line : "Too late returning, snuffs the track of men,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17808, line : "And o'er the vales and o'er the forest bounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17809, line : "His clamorous grief the bellowing wood resounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17810, line : "So grieves Achilles; and, impetuous, vents"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17811, line : "To all his Myrmidons his loud laments."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17813, line : "\"In what vain promise, gods! did I engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17814, line : "When to console Menoetius' feeble age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17815, line : "I vowed his much-loved offspring to restore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17816, line : "Charged with rich spoils, to fair Opuntia's shore?(252)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17817, line : "But mighty Jove cuts short, with just disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17818, line : "The long, long views of poor designing man!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17819, line : "One fate the warrior and the friend shall strike,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17820, line : "And Troy's black sands must drink our blood alike:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17821, line : "Me too a wretched mother shall deplore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17822, line : "An aged father never see me more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17823, line : "Yet, my Patroclus! yet a space I stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17824, line : "Then swift pursue thee on the darksome way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17825, line : "Ere thy dear relics in the grave are laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17826, line : "Shall Hector's head be offer'd to thy shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17827, line : "That, with his arms, shall hang before thy shrine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17828, line : "And twelve, the noblest of the Trojan line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17829, line : "Sacred to vengeance, by this hand expire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17830, line : "Their lives effused around thy flaming pyre."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17831, line : "Thus let me lie till then! thus, closely press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17832, line : "Bathe thy cold face, and sob upon thy breast!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17833, line : "While Trojan captives here thy mourners stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17834, line : "Weep all the night and murmur all the day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17835, line : "Spoils of my arms, and thine; when, wasting wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17836, line : "Our swords kept time, and conquer'd side by side.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17838, line : "He spoke, and bade the sad attendants round"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17839, line : "Cleanse the pale corse, and wash each honour'd wound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17840, line : "A massy caldron of stupendous frame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17841, line : "They brought, and placed it o'er the rising flame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17842, line : "Then heap'd the lighted wood; the flame divides"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17843, line : "Beneath the vase, and climbs around the sides:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17844, line : "In its wide womb they pour the rushing stream;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17845, line : "The boiling water bubbles to the brim."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17846, line : "The body then they bathe with pious toil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17847, line : "Embalm the wounds, anoint the limbs with oil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17848, line : "High on a bed of state extended laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17849, line : "And decent cover'd with a linen shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17850, line : "Last o'er the dead the milk-white veil they threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17851, line : "That done, their sorrows and their sighs renew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17853, line : "Meanwhile to Juno, in the realms above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17854, line : "(His wife and sister,) spoke almighty Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17855, line : "\"At last thy will prevails: great Peleus' son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17856, line : "Rises in arms: such grace thy Greeks have won."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17857, line : "Say (for I know not), is their race divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17858, line : "And thou the mother of that martial line?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17860, line : "\"What words are these? (the imperial dame replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17861, line : "While anger flash'd from her majestic eyes)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17862, line : "Succour like this a mortal arm might lend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17863, line : "And such success mere human wit attend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17864, line : "And shall not I, the second power above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17865, line : "Heaven's queen, and consort of the thundering Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17866, line : "Say, shall not I one nation's fate command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17867, line : "Not wreak my vengeance on one guilty land?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17869, line : "[Illustration: TRIPOD.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17871, line : "TRIPOD."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17874, line : "So they. Meanwhile the silver-footed dame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17875, line : "Reach'd the Vulcanian dome, eternal frame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17876, line : "High-eminent amid the works divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17877, line : "Where heaven's far-beaming brazen mansions shine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17878, line : "There the lame architect the goddess found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17879, line : "Obscure in smoke, his forges flaming round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17880, line : "While bathed in sweat from fire to fire he flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17881, line : "And puffing loud, the roaring billows blew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17882, line : "That day no common task his labour claim'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17883, line : "Full twenty tripods for his hall he framed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17884, line : "That placed on living wheels of massy gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17885, line : "(Wondrous to tell,) instinct with spirit roll'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17886, line : "From place to place, around the bless'd abodes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17887, line : "Self-moved, obedient to the beck of gods:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17888, line : "For their fair handles now, o'erwrought with flowers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17889, line : "In moulds prepared, the glowing ore he pours."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17890, line : "Just as responsive to his thought the frame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17891, line : "Stood prompt to move, the azure goddess came:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17892, line : "Charis, his spouse, a grace divinely fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17893, line : "(With purple fillets round her braided hair,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17894, line : "Observed her entering; her soft hand she press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17895, line : "And, smiling, thus the watery queen address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17897, line : "\"What, goddess! this unusual favour draws?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17898, line : "All hail, and welcome! whatsoe'er the cause;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17899, line : "Till now a stranger, in a happy hour"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17900, line : "Approach, and taste the dainties of the bower.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17902, line : "[Illustration: THETIS AND EURYNOME RECEIVING THE INFANT VULCAN.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17904, line : "THETIS AND EURYNOME RECEIVING THE INFANT VULCAN."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17907, line : "High on a throne, with stars of silver graced,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17908, line : "And various artifice, the queen she placed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17909, line : "A footstool at her feet: then calling, said,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17910, line : "\"Vulcan, draw near, 'tis Thetis asks your aid.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17911, line : "\"Thetis (replied the god) our powers may claim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17912, line : "An ever-dear, an ever-honour'd name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17913, line : "When my proud mother hurl'd me from the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17914, line : "(My awkward form, it seems, displeased her eye,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17915, line : "She, and Eurynome, my griefs redress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17916, line : "And soft received me on their silver breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17917, line : "Even then these arts employ'd my infant thought:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17918, line : "Chains, bracelets, pendants, all their toys, I wrought."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17919, line : "Nine years kept secret in the dark abode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17920, line : "Secure I lay, conceal'd from man and god:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17921, line : "Deep in a cavern'd rock my days were led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17922, line : "The rushing ocean murmur'd o'er my head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17923, line : "Now, since her presence glads our mansion, say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17924, line : "For such desert what service can I pay?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17925, line : "Vouchsafe, O Thetis! at our board to share"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17926, line : "The genial rites, and hospitable fare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17927, line : "While I the labours of the forge forego,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17928, line : "And bid the roaring bellows cease to blow.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17930, line : "Then from his anvil the lame artist rose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17931, line : "Wide with distorted legs oblique he goes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17932, line : "And stills the bellows, and (in order laid)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17933, line : "Locks in their chests his instruments of trade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17934, line : "Then with a sponge the sooty workman dress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17935, line : "His brawny arms embrown'd, and hairy breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17936, line : "With his huge sceptre graced, and red attire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17937, line : "Came halting forth the sovereign of the fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17938, line : "The monarch's steps two female forms uphold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17939, line : "That moved and breathed in animated gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17940, line : "To whom was voice, and sense, and science given"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17941, line : "Of works divine (such wonders are in heaven!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17942, line : "On these supported, with unequal gait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17943, line : "He reach'd the throne where pensive Thetis sate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17944, line : "There placed beside her on the shining frame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17945, line : "He thus address'd the silver-footed dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17947, line : "\"Thee, welcome, goddess! what occasion calls"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17948, line : "(So long a stranger) to these honour'd walls?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17949, line : "'Tis thine, fair Thetis, the command to lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17950, line : "And Vulcan's joy and duty to obey.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17952, line : "[Illustration: VULCAN AND CHARIS RECEIVING THETIS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17954, line : "VULCAN AND CHARIS RECEIVING THETIS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17957, line : "To whom the mournful mother thus replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17958, line : "(The crystal drops stood trembling in her eyes:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17959, line : "\"O Vulcan! say, was ever breast divine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17960, line : "So pierced with sorrows, so o'erwhelm'd as mine?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17961, line : "Of all the goddesses, did Jove prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17962, line : "For Thetis only such a weight of care?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17963, line : "I, only I, of all the watery race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17964, line : "By force subjected to a man's embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17965, line : "Who, sinking now with age and sorrow, pays"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17966, line : "The mighty fine imposed on length of days."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17967, line : "Sprung from my bed, a godlike hero came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17968, line : "The bravest sure that ever bore the name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17969, line : "Like some fair plant beneath my careful hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17970, line : "He grew, he flourish'd, and he graced the land:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17971, line : "To Troy I sent him! but his native shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17972, line : "Never, ah never, shall receive him more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17973, line : "(Even while he lives, he wastes with secret woe;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17974, line : "Nor I, a goddess, can retard the blow!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17975, line : "Robb'd of the prize the Grecian suffrage gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17976, line : "The king of nations forced his royal slave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17977, line : "For this he grieved; and, till the Greeks oppress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17978, line : "Required his arm, he sorrow'd unredress'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17979, line : "Large gifts they promise, and their elders send;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17980, line : "In vain--he arms not, but permits his friend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17981, line : "His arms, his steeds, his forces to employ:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17982, line : "He marches, combats, almost conquers Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17983, line : "Then slain by Phoebus (Hector had the name)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17984, line : "At once resigns his armour, life, and fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17985, line : "But thou, in pity, by my prayer be won:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17986, line : "Grace with immortal arms this short-lived son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17987, line : "And to the field in martial pomp restore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17988, line : "To shine with glory, till he shines no more!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17990, line : "To her the artist-god: \"Thy griefs resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17991, line : "Secure, what Vulcan can, is ever thine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17992, line : "O could I hide him from the Fates, as well,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17993, line : "Or with these hands the cruel stroke repel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17994, line : "As I shall forge most envied arms, the gaze"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17995, line : "Of wondering ages, and the world's amaze!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17997, line : "Thus having said, the father of the fires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17998, line : "To the black labours of his forge retires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 17999, line : "Soon as he bade them blow, the bellows turn'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18000, line : "Their iron mouths; and where the furnace burn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18001, line : "Resounding breathed: at once the blast expires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18002, line : "And twenty forges catch at once the fires;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18003, line : "Just as the god directs, now loud, now low,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18004, line : "They raise a tempest, or they gently blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18005, line : "In hissing flames huge silver bars are roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18006, line : "And stubborn brass, and tin, and solid gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18007, line : "Before, deep fix'd, the eternal anvils stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18008, line : "The ponderous hammer loads his better hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18009, line : "His left with tongs turns the vex'd metal round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18010, line : "And thick, strong strokes, the doubling vaults rebound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18012, line : "Then first he form'd the immense and solid shield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18013, line : "Rich various artifice emblazed the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18014, line : "Its utmost verge a threefold circle bound;(253)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18015, line : "A silver chain suspends the massy round;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18016, line : "Five ample plates the broad expanse compose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18017, line : "And godlike labours on the surface rose."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18018, line : "There shone the image of the master-mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18019, line : "There earth, there heaven, there ocean he design'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18020, line : "The unwearied sun, the moon completely round;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18021, line : "The starry lights that heaven's high convex crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18022, line : "The Pleiads, Hyads, with the northern team;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18023, line : "And great Orion's more refulgent beam;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18024, line : "To which, around the axle of the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18025, line : "The Bear, revolving, points his golden eye,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18026, line : "Still shines exalted on the ethereal plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18027, line : "Nor bathes his blazing forehead in the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18029, line : "Two cities radiant on the shield appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18030, line : "The image one of peace, and one of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18031, line : "Here sacred pomp and genial feast delight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18032, line : "And solemn dance, and hymeneal rite;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18033, line : "Along the street the new-made brides are led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18034, line : "With torches flaming, to the nuptial bed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18035, line : "The youthful dancers in a circle bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18036, line : "To the soft flute, and cithern's silver sound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18037, line : "Through the fair streets the matrons in a row"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18038, line : "Stand in their porches, and enjoy the show."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18040, line : "There in the forum swarm a numerous train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18041, line : "The subject of debate, a townsman slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18042, line : "One pleads the fine discharged, which one denied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18043, line : "And bade the public and the laws decide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18044, line : "The witness is produced on either hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18045, line : "For this, or that, the partial people stand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18046, line : "The appointed heralds still the noisy bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18047, line : "And form a ring, with sceptres in their hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18048, line : "On seats of stone, within the sacred place,(254)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18049, line : "The reverend elders nodded o'er the case;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18050, line : "Alternate, each the attesting sceptre took,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18051, line : "And rising solemn, each his sentence spoke"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18052, line : "Two golden talents lay amidst, in sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18053, line : "The prize of him who best adjudged the right."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18055, line : "Another part (a prospect differing far)(255)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18056, line : "Glow'd with refulgent arms, and horrid war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18057, line : "Two mighty hosts a leaguer'd town embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18058, line : "And one would pillage, one would burn the place."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18059, line : "Meantime the townsmen, arm'd with silent care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18060, line : "A secret ambush on the foe prepare:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18061, line : "Their wives, their children, and the watchful band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18062, line : "Of trembling parents, on the turrets stand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18063, line : "They march; by Pallas and by Mars made bold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18064, line : "Gold were the gods, their radiant garments gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18065, line : "And gold their armour: these the squadron led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18066, line : "August, divine, superior by the head!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18067, line : "A place for ambush fit they found, and stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18068, line : "Cover'd with shields, beside a silver flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18069, line : "Two spies at distance lurk, and watchful seem"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18070, line : "If sheep or oxen seek the winding stream."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18071, line : "Soon the white flocks proceeded o'er the plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18072, line : "And steers slow-moving, and two shepherd swains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18073, line : "Behind them piping on their reeds they go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18074, line : "Nor fear an ambush, nor suspect a foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18075, line : "In arms the glittering squadron rising round"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18076, line : "Rush sudden; hills of slaughter heap the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18077, line : "Whole flocks and herds lie bleeding on the plains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18078, line : "And, all amidst them, dead, the shepherd swains!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18079, line : "The bellowing oxen the besiegers hear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18080, line : "They rise, take horse, approach, and meet the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18081, line : "They fight, they fall, beside the silver flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18082, line : "The waving silver seem'd to blush with blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18083, line : "There Tumult, there Contention stood confess'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18084, line : "One rear'd a dagger at a captive's breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18085, line : "One held a living foe, that freshly bled"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18086, line : "With new-made wounds; another dragg'd a dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18087, line : "Now here, now there, the carcases they tore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18088, line : "Fate stalk'd amidst them, grim with human gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18089, line : "And the whole war came out, and met the eye;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18090, line : "And each bold figure seem'd to live or die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18092, line : "A field deep furrow'd next the god design'd,(256)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18093, line : "The third time labour'd by the sweating hind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18094, line : "The shining shares full many ploughmen guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18095, line : "And turn their crooked yokes on every side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18096, line : "Still as at either end they wheel around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18097, line : "The master meets them with his goblet crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18098, line : "The hearty draught rewards, renews their toil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18099, line : "Then back the turning ploughshares cleave the soil:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18100, line : "Behind, the rising earth in ridges roll'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18101, line : "And sable look'd, though form'd of molten gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18103, line : "Another field rose high with waving grain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18104, line : "With bended sickles stand the reaper train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18105, line : "Here stretched in ranks the levell'd swarths are found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18106, line : "Sheaves heap'd on sheaves here thicken up the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18107, line : "With sweeping stroke the mowers strow the lands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18108, line : "The gatherers follow, and collect in bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18109, line : "And last the children, in whose arms are borne"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18110, line : "(Too short to gripe them) the brown sheaves of corn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18111, line : "The rustic monarch of the field descries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18112, line : "With silent glee, the heaps around him rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18113, line : "A ready banquet on the turf is laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18114, line : "Beneath an ample oak's expanded shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18115, line : "The victim ox the sturdy youth prepare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18116, line : "The reaper's due repast, the woman's care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18118, line : "Next, ripe in yellow gold, a vineyard shines,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18119, line : "Bent with the ponderous harvest of its vines;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18120, line : "A deeper dye the dangling clusters show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18121, line : "And curl'd on silver props, in order glow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18122, line : "A darker metal mix'd intrench'd the place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18123, line : "And pales of glittering tin the inclosure grace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18124, line : "To this, one pathway gently winding leads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18125, line : "Where march a train with baskets on their heads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18126, line : "(Fair maids and blooming youths,) that smiling bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18127, line : "The purple product of the autumnal year."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18128, line : "To these a youth awakes the warbling strings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18129, line : "Whose tender lay the fate of Linus sings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18130, line : "In measured dance behind him move the train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18131, line : "Tune soft the voice, and answer to the strain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18133, line : "Here herds of oxen march, erect and bold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18134, line : "Rear high their horns, and seem to low in gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18135, line : "And speed to meadows on whose sounding shores"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18136, line : "A rapid torrent through the rushes roars:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18137, line : "Four golden herdsmen as their guardians stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18138, line : "And nine sour dogs complete the rustic band."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18139, line : "Two lions rushing from the wood appear'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18140, line : "And seized a bull, the master of the herd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18141, line : "He roar'd: in vain the dogs, the men withstood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18142, line : "They tore his flesh, and drank his sable blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18143, line : "The dogs (oft cheer'd in vain) desert the prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18144, line : "Dread the grim terrors, and at distance bay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18146, line : "Next this, the eye the art of Vulcan leads"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18147, line : "Deep through fair forests, and a length of meads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18148, line : "And stalls, and folds, and scatter'd cots between;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18149, line : "And fleecy flocks, that whiten all the scene."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18151, line : "A figured dance succeeds; such once was seen"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18152, line : "In lofty Gnossus for the Cretan queen,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18153, line : "Form'd by Daedalean art; a comely band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18154, line : "Of youths and maidens, bounding hand in hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18155, line : "The maids in soft simars of linen dress'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18156, line : "The youths all graceful in the glossy vest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18157, line : "Of those the locks with flowery wreath inroll'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18158, line : "Of these the sides adorn'd with swords of gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18159, line : "That glittering gay, from silver belts depend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18160, line : "Now all at once they rise, at once descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18161, line : "With well-taught feet: now shape in oblique ways,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18162, line : "Confusedly regular, the moving maze:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18163, line : "Now forth at once, too swift for sight, they spring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18164, line : "And undistinguish'd blend the flying ring:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18165, line : "So whirls a wheel, in giddy circle toss'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18166, line : "And, rapid as it runs, the single spokes are lost."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18167, line : "The gazing multitudes admire around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18168, line : "Two active tumblers in the centre bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18169, line : "Now high, now low, their pliant limbs they bend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18170, line : "And general songs the sprightly revel end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18172, line : "Thus the broad shield complete the artist crown'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18173, line : "With his last hand, and pour'd the ocean round:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18174, line : "In living silver seem'd the waves to roll,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18175, line : "And beat the buckler's verge, and bound the whole."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18177, line : "This done, whate'er a warrior's use requires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18178, line : "He forged; the cuirass that outshone the fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18179, line : "The greaves of ductile tin, the helm impress'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18180, line : "With various sculpture, and the golden crest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18181, line : "At Thetis' feet the finished labour lay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18182, line : "She, as a falcon cuts the aerial way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18183, line : "Swift from Olympus' snowy summit flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18184, line : "And bears the blazing present through the skies.(257)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18190, line : "BOOK XIX."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18193, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18195, line : "THE RECONCILIATION OF ACHILLES AND AGAMEMNON."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18197, line : "Thetis brings to her son the armour made by Vulcan. She preserves the body"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18198, line : "of his friend from corruption, and commands him to assemble the army, to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18199, line : "declare his resentment at an end. Agamemnon and Achilles are solemnly"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18200, line : "reconciled: the speeches, presents, and ceremonies on that occasion."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18201, line : "Achilles is with great difficulty persuaded to refrain from the battle"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18202, line : "till the troops have refreshed themselves by the advice of Ulysses. The"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18203, line : "presents are conveyed to the tent of Achilles, where Briseis laments over"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18204, line : "the body of Patroclus. The hero obstinately refuses all repast, and gives"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18205, line : "himself up to lamentations for his friend. Minerva descends to strengthen"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18206, line : "him, by the order of Jupiter. He arms for the fight: his appearance"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18207, line : "described. He addresses himself to his horses, and reproaches them with"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18208, line : "the death of Patroclus. One of them is miraculously endued with voice, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18209, line : "inspired to prophesy his fate: but the hero, not astonished by that"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18210, line : "prodigy, rushes with fury to the combat."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18212, line : "The thirteenth day. The scene is on the sea-shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18214, line : "Soon as Aurora heaved her Orient head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18215, line : "Above the waves, that blush'd with early red,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18216, line : "(With new-born day to gladden mortal sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18217, line : "And gild the courts of heaven with sacred light,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18218, line : "The immortal arms the goddess-mother bears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18219, line : "Swift to her son: her son she finds in tears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18220, line : "Stretch'd o'er Patroclus' corse; while all the rest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18221, line : "Their sovereign's sorrows in their own express'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18222, line : "A ray divine her heavenly presence shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18223, line : "And thus, his hand soft touching, Thetis said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18225, line : "\"Suppress, my son, this rage of grief, and know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18226, line : "It was not man, but heaven, that gave the blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18227, line : "Behold what arms by Vulcan are bestow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18228, line : "Arms worthy thee, or fit to grace a god.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18230, line : "Then drops the radiant burden on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18231, line : "Clang the strong arms, and ring the shores around;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18232, line : "Back shrink the Myrmidons with dread surprise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18233, line : "And from the broad effulgence turn their eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18234, line : "Unmoved the hero kindles at the show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18235, line : "And feels with rage divine his bosom glow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18236, line : "From his fierce eyeballs living flames expire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18237, line : "And flash incessant like a stream of fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18238, line : "He turns the radiant gift: and feeds his mind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18239, line : "On all the immortal artist had design'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18241, line : "\"Goddess! (he cried,) these glorious arms, that shine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18242, line : "With matchless art, confess the hand divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18243, line : "Now to the bloody battle let me bend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18244, line : "But ah! the relics of my slaughter'd friend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18245, line : "In those wide wounds through which his spirit fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18246, line : "Shall flies, and worms obscene, pollute the dead?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18248, line : "\"That unavailing care be laid aside,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18249, line : "(The azure goddess to her son replied,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18250, line : "Whole years untouch'd, uninjured shall remain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18251, line : "Fresh as in life, the carcase of the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18252, line : "But go, Achilles, as affairs require,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18253, line : "Before the Grecian peers renounce thine ire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18254, line : "Then uncontroll'd in boundless war engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18255, line : "And heaven with strength supply the mighty rage!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18257, line : "[Illustration: THETIS BRINGING THE ARMOUR TO ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18259, line : "THETIS BRINGING THE ARMOUR TO ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18262, line : "Then in the nostrils of the slain she pour'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18263, line : "Nectareous drops, and rich ambrosia shower'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18264, line : "O'er all the corse. The flies forbid their prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18265, line : "Untouch'd it rests, and sacred from decay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18266, line : "Achilles to the strand obedient went:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18267, line : "The shores resounded with the voice he sent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18268, line : "The heroes heard, and all the naval train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18269, line : "That tend the ships, or guide them o'er the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18270, line : "Alarm'd, transported, at the well-known sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18271, line : "Frequent and full, the great assembly crown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18272, line : "Studious to see the terror of the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18273, line : "Long lost to battle, shine in arms again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18274, line : "Tydides and Ulysses first appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18275, line : "Lame with their wounds, and leaning on the spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18276, line : "These on the sacred seats of council placed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18277, line : "The king of men, Atrides, came the last:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18278, line : "He too sore wounded by Agenor's son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18279, line : "Achilles (rising in the midst) begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18281, line : "\"O monarch! better far had been the fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18282, line : "Of thee, of me, of all the Grecian state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18283, line : "If (ere the day when by mad passion sway'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18284, line : "Rash we contended for the black-eyed maid)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18285, line : "Preventing Dian had despatch'd her dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18286, line : "And shot the shining mischief to the heart!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18287, line : "Then many a hero had not press'd the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18288, line : "Nor Troy's glad fields been fatten'd with our gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18289, line : "Long, long shall Greece the woes we caused bewail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18290, line : "And sad posterity repeat the tale."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18291, line : "But this, no more the subject of debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18292, line : "Is past, forgotten, and resign'd to fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18293, line : "Why should, alas, a mortal man, as I,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18294, line : "Burn with a fury that can never die?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18295, line : "Here then my anger ends: let war succeed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18296, line : "And even as Greece has bled, let Ilion bleed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18297, line : "Now call the hosts, and try if in our sight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18298, line : "Troy yet shall dare to camp a second night!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18299, line : "I deem, their mightiest, when this arm he knows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18300, line : "Shall 'scape with transport, and with joy repose.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18302, line : "He said: his finish'd wrath with loud acclaim"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18303, line : "The Greeks accept, and shout Pelides' name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18304, line : "When thus, not rising from his lofty throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18305, line : "In state unmoved, the king of men begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18307, line : "\"Hear me, ye sons of Greece! with silence hear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18308, line : "And grant your monarch an impartial ear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18309, line : "Awhile your loud, untimely joy suspend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18310, line : "And let your rash, injurious clamours end:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18311, line : "Unruly murmurs, or ill-timed applause,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18312, line : "Wrong the best speaker, and the justest cause."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18313, line : "Nor charge on me, ye Greeks, the dire debate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18314, line : "Know, angry Jove, and all-compelling Fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18315, line : "With fell Erinnys, urged my wrath that day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18316, line : "When from Achilles' arms I forced the prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18317, line : "What then could I against the will of heaven?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18318, line : "Not by myself, but vengeful Ate driven;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18319, line : "She, Jove's dread daughter, fated to infest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18320, line : "The race of mortals, enter'd in my breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18321, line : "Not on the ground that haughty fury treads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18322, line : "But prints her lofty footsteps on the heads"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18323, line : "Of mighty men; inflicting as she goes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18324, line : "Long-festering wounds, inextricable woes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18325, line : "Of old, she stalk'd amid the bright abodes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18326, line : "And Jove himself, the sire of men and gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18327, line : "The world's great ruler, felt her venom'd dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18328, line : "Deceived by Juno's wiles, and female art:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18329, line : "For when Alcmena's nine long months were run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18330, line : "And Jove expected his immortal son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18331, line : "To gods and goddesses the unruly joy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18332, line : "He show'd, and vaunted of his matchless boy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18333, line : "'From us, (he said) this day an infant springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18334, line : "Fated to rule, and born a king of kings.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18335, line : "Saturnia ask'd an oath, to vouch the truth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18336, line : "And fix dominion on the favour'd youth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18337, line : "The Thunderer, unsuspicious of the fraud,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18338, line : "Pronounced those solemn words that bind a god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18339, line : "The joyful goddess, from Olympus' height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18340, line : "Swift to Achaian Argos bent her flight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18341, line : "Scarce seven moons gone, lay Sthenelus's wife;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18342, line : "She push'd her lingering infant into life:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18343, line : "Her charms Alcmena's coming labours stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18344, line : "And stop the babe, just issuing to the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18345, line : "Then bids Saturnius bear his oath in mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18346, line : "'A youth (said she) of Jove's immortal kind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18347, line : "Is this day born: from Sthenelus he springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18348, line : "And claims thy promise to be king of kings.'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18349, line : "Grief seized the Thunderer, by his oath engaged;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18350, line : "Stung to the soul, he sorrow'd, and he raged."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18351, line : "From his ambrosial head, where perch'd she sate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18352, line : "He snatch'd the fury-goddess of debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18353, line : "The dread, the irrevocable oath he swore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18354, line : "The immortal seats should ne'er behold her more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18355, line : "And whirl'd her headlong down, for ever driven"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18356, line : "From bright Olympus and the starry heaven:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18357, line : "Thence on the nether world the fury fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18358, line : "Ordain'd with man's contentious race to dwell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18359, line : "Full oft the god his son's hard toils bemoan'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18360, line : "Cursed the dire fury, and in secret groan'd.(258)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18361, line : "Even thus, like Jove himself, was I misled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18362, line : "While raging Hector heap'd our camps with dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18363, line : "What can the errors of my rage atone?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18364, line : "My martial troops, my treasures are thy own:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18365, line : "This instant from the navy shall be sent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18366, line : "Whate'er Ulysses promised at thy tent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18367, line : "But thou! appeased, propitious to our prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18368, line : "Resume thy arms, and shine again in war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18370, line : "\" O king of nations! whose superior sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18371, line : "(Returns Achilles) all our hosts obey!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18372, line : "To keep or send the presents, be thy care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18373, line : "To us, 'tis equal: all we ask is war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18374, line : "While yet we talk, or but an instant shun"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18375, line : "The fight, our glorious work remains undone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18376, line : "Let every Greek, who sees my spear confound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18377, line : "The Trojan ranks, and deal destruction round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18378, line : "With emulation, what I act survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18379, line : "And learn from thence the business of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18381, line : "The son of Peleus thus; and thus replies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18382, line : "The great in councils, Ithacus the wise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18383, line : "\"Though, godlike, thou art by no toils oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18384, line : "At least our armies claim repast and rest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18385, line : "Long and laborious must the combat be,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18386, line : "When by the gods inspired, and led by thee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18387, line : "Strength is derived from spirits and from blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18388, line : "And those augment by generous wine and food:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18389, line : "What boastful son of war, without that stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18390, line : "Can last a hero through a single day?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18391, line : "Courage may prompt; but, ebbing out his strength,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18392, line : "Mere unsupported man must yield at length;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18393, line : "Shrunk with dry famine, and with toils declined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18394, line : "The drooping body will desert the mind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18395, line : "But built anew with strength-conferring fare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18396, line : "With limbs and soul untamed, he tires a war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18397, line : "Dismiss the people, then, and give command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18398, line : "With strong repast to hearten every band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18399, line : "But let the presents to Achilles made,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18400, line : "In full assembly of all Greece be laid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18401, line : "The king of men shall rise in public sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18402, line : "And solemn swear (observant of the rite)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18403, line : "That, spotless, as she came, the maid removes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18404, line : "Pure from his arms, and guiltless of his loves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18405, line : "That done, a sumptuous banquet shall be made,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18406, line : "And the full price of injured honour paid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18407, line : "Stretch not henceforth, O prince.! thy sovereign might"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18408, line : "Beyond the bounds of reason and of right;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18409, line : "'Tis the chief praise that e'er to kings belong'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18410, line : "To right with justice whom with power they wrong'd.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18412, line : "To him the monarch: \"Just is thy decree,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18413, line : "Thy words give joy, and wisdom breathes in thee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18414, line : "Each due atonement gladly I prepare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18415, line : "And heaven regard me as I justly swear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18416, line : "Here then awhile let Greece assembled stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18417, line : "Nor great Achilles grudge this short delay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18418, line : "Till from the fleet our presents be convey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18419, line : "And Jove attesting, the firm compact made."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18420, line : "A train of noble youths the charge shall bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18421, line : "These to select, Ulysses, be thy care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18422, line : "In order rank'd let all our gifts appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18423, line : "And the fair train of captives close the rear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18424, line : "Talthybius shall the victim boar convey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18425, line : "Sacred to Jove, and yon bright orb of day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18427, line : "\"For this (the stern Ćacides replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18428, line : "Some less important season may suffice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18429, line : "When the stern fury of the war is o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18430, line : "And wrath, extinguish'd, burns my breast no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18431, line : "By Hector slain, their faces to the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18432, line : "All grim with gaping wounds, our heroes lie:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18433, line : "Those call to war! and might my voice incite,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18434, line : "Now, now, this instant, shall commence the fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18435, line : "Then, when the day's complete, let generous bowls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18436, line : "And copious banquets, glad your weary souls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18437, line : "Let not my palate know the taste of food,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18438, line : "Till my insatiate rage be cloy'd with blood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18439, line : "Pale lies my friend, with wounds disfigured o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18440, line : "And his cold feet are pointed to the door."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18441, line : "Revenge is all my soul! no meaner care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18442, line : "Interest, or thought, has room to harbour there;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18443, line : "Destruction be my feast, and mortal wounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18444, line : "And scenes of blood, and agonizing sounds.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18446, line : "\"O first of Greeks, (Ulysses thus rejoin'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18447, line : "The best and bravest of the warrior kind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18448, line : "Thy praise it is in dreadful camps to shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18449, line : "But old experience and calm wisdom mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18450, line : "Then hear my counsel, and to reason yield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18451, line : "The bravest soon are satiate of the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18452, line : "Though vast the heaps that strow the crimson plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18453, line : "The bloody harvest brings but little gain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18454, line : "The scale of conquest ever wavering lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18455, line : "Great Jove but turns it, and the victor dies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18456, line : "The great, the bold, by thousands daily fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18457, line : "And endless were the grief, to weep for all."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18458, line : "Eternal sorrows what avails to shed?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18459, line : "Greece honours not with solemn fasts the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18460, line : "Enough, when death demands the brave, to pay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18461, line : "The tribute of a melancholy day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18462, line : "One chief with patience to the grave resign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18463, line : "Our care devolves on others left behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18464, line : "Let generous food supplies of strength produce,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18465, line : "Let rising spirits flow from sprightly juice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18466, line : "Let their warm heads with scenes of battle glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18467, line : "And pour new furies on the feebler foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18468, line : "Yet a short interval, and none shall dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18469, line : "Expect a second summons to the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18470, line : "Who waits for that, the dire effects shall find,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18471, line : "If trembling in the ships he lags behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18472, line : "Embodied, to the battle let us bend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18473, line : "And all at once on haughty Troy descend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18475, line : "And now the delegates Ulysses sent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18476, line : "To bear the presents from the royal tent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18477, line : "The sons of Nestor, Phyleus' valiant heir,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18478, line : "Thias and Merion, thunderbolts of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18479, line : "With Lycomedes of Creiontian strain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18480, line : "And Melanippus, form'd the chosen train."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18481, line : "Swift as the word was given, the youths obey'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18482, line : "Twice ten bright vases in the midst they laid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18483, line : "A row of six fair tripods then succeeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18484, line : "And twice the number of high-bounding steeds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18485, line : "Seven captives next a lovely line compose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18486, line : "The eighth Briseis, like the blooming rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18487, line : "Closed the bright band: great Ithacus, before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18488, line : "First of the train, the golden talents bore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18489, line : "The rest in public view the chiefs dispose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18490, line : "A splendid scene! then Agamemnon rose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18491, line : "The boar Talthybius held: the Grecian lord"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18492, line : "Drew the broad cutlass sheath'd beside his sword:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18493, line : "The stubborn bristles from the victim's brow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18494, line : "He crops, and offering meditates his vow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18495, line : "His hands uplifted to the attesting skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18496, line : "On heaven's broad marble roof were fixed his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18497, line : "The solemn words a deep attention draw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18498, line : "And Greece around sat thrill'd with sacred awe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18500, line : "\"Witness thou first! thou greatest power above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18501, line : "All-good, all-wise, and all-surveying Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18502, line : "And mother-earth, and heaven's revolving light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18503, line : "And ye, fell furies of the realms of night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18504, line : "Who rule the dead, and horrid woes prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18505, line : "For perjured kings, and all who falsely swear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18506, line : "The black-eyed maid inviolate removes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18507, line : "Pure and unconscious of my manly loves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18508, line : "If this be false, heaven all its vengeance shed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18509, line : "And levell'd thunder strike my guilty head!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18511, line : "With that, his weapon deep inflicts the wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18512, line : "The bleeding savage tumbles to the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18513, line : "The sacred herald rolls the victim slain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18514, line : "(A feast for fish) into the foaming main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18516, line : "Then thus Achilles: \"Hear, ye Greeks! and know"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18517, line : "Whate'er we feel, 'tis Jove inflicts the woe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18518, line : "Not else Atrides could our rage inflame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18519, line : "Nor from my arms, unwilling, force the dame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18520, line : "'Twas Jove's high will alone, o'erruling all,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18521, line : "That doom'd our strife, and doom'd the Greeks to fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18522, line : "Go then, ye chiefs! indulge the genial rite;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18523, line : "Achilles waits ye, and expects the fight.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18525, line : "The speedy council at his word adjourn'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18526, line : "To their black vessels all the Greeks return'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18527, line : "Achilles sought his tent. His train before"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18528, line : "March'd onward, bending with the gifts they bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18529, line : "Those in the tents the squires industrious spread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18530, line : "The foaming coursers to the stalls they led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18531, line : "To their new seats the female captives move"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18532, line : "Briseis, radiant as the queen of love,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18533, line : "Slow as she pass'd, beheld with sad survey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18534, line : "Where, gash'd with cruel wounds, Patroclus lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18535, line : "Prone on the body fell the heavenly fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18536, line : "Beat her sad breast, and tore her golden hair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18537, line : "All beautiful in grief, her humid eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18538, line : "Shining with tears she lifts, and thus she cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18540, line : "\"Ah, youth for ever dear, for ever kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18541, line : "Once tender friend of my distracted mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18542, line : "I left thee fresh in life, in beauty gay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18543, line : "Now find thee cold, inanimated clay!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18544, line : "What woes my wretched race of life attend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18545, line : "Sorrows on sorrows, never doom'd to end!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18546, line : "The first loved consort of my virgin bed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18547, line : "Before these eyes in fatal battle bled:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18548, line : "My three brave brothers in one mournful day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18549, line : "All trod the dark, irremeable way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18550, line : "Thy friendly hand uprear'd me from the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18551, line : "And dried my sorrows for a husband slain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18552, line : "Achilles' care you promised I should prove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18553, line : "The first, the dearest partner of his love;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18554, line : "That rites divine should ratify the band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18555, line : "And make me empress in his native land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18556, line : "Accept these grateful tears! for thee they flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18557, line : "For thee, that ever felt another's woe!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18559, line : "Her sister captives echoed groan for groan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18560, line : "Nor mourn'd Patroclus' fortunes, but their own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18561, line : "The leaders press'd the chief on every side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18562, line : "Unmoved he heard them, and with sighs denied."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18564, line : "\"If yet Achilles have a friend, whose care"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18565, line : "Is bent to please him, this request forbear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18566, line : "Till yonder sun descend, ah, let me pay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18567, line : "To grief and anguish one abstemious day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18569, line : "He spoke, and from the warriors turn'd his face:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18570, line : "Yet still the brother-kings of Atreus' race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18571, line : "Nestor, Idomeneus, Ulysses sage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18572, line : "And Phoenix, strive to calm his grief and rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18573, line : "His rage they calm not, nor his grief control;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18574, line : "He groans, he raves, he sorrows from his soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18576, line : "\"Thou too, Patroclus! (thus his heart he vents)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18577, line : "Once spread the inviting banquet in our tents:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18578, line : "Thy sweet society, thy winning care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18579, line : "Once stay'd Achilles, rushing to the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18580, line : "But now, alas! to death's cold arms resign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18581, line : "What banquet but revenge can glad my mind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18582, line : "What greater sorrow could afflict my breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18583, line : "What more if hoary Peleus were deceased?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18584, line : "Who now, perhaps, in Phthia dreads to hear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18585, line : "His son's sad fate, and drops a tender tear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18586, line : "What more, should Neoptolemus the brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18587, line : "My only offspring, sink into the grave?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18588, line : "If yet that offspring lives; (I distant far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18589, line : "Of all neglectful, wage a hateful war.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18590, line : "I could not this, this cruel stroke attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18591, line : "Fate claim'd Achilles, but might spare his friend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18592, line : "I hoped Patroclus might survive, to rear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18593, line : "My tender orphan with a parent's care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18594, line : "From Scyros' isle conduct him o'er the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18595, line : "And glad his eyes with his paternal reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18596, line : "The lofty palace, and the large domain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18597, line : "For Peleus breathes no more the vital air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18598, line : "Or drags a wretched life of age and care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18599, line : "But till the news of my sad fate invades"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18600, line : "His hastening soul, and sinks him to the shades.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18602, line : "Sighing he said: his grief the heroes join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18603, line : "Each stole a tear for what he left behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18604, line : "Their mingled grief the sire of heaven survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18605, line : "And thus with pity to his blue-eyed maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18607, line : "\"Is then Achilles now no more thy care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18608, line : "And dost thou thus desert the great in war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18609, line : "Lo, where yon sails their canvas wings extend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18610, line : "All comfortless he sits, and wails his friend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18611, line : "Ere thirst and want his forces have oppress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18612, line : "Haste and infuse ambrosia in his breast.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18614, line : "He spoke; and sudden, at the word of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18615, line : "Shot the descending goddess from above."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18616, line : "So swift through ether the shrill harpy springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18617, line : "The wide air floating to her ample wings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18618, line : "To great Achilles she her flight address'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18619, line : "And pour'd divine ambrosia in his breast,(259)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18620, line : "With nectar sweet, (refection of the gods!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18621, line : "Then, swift ascending, sought the bright abodes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18623, line : "Now issued from the ships the warrior-train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18624, line : "And like a deluge pour'd upon the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18625, line : "As when the piercing blasts of Boreas blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18626, line : "And scatter o'er the fields the driving snow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18627, line : "From dusky clouds the fleecy winter flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18628, line : "Whose dazzling lustre whitens all the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18629, line : "So helms succeeding helms, so shields from shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18630, line : "Catch the quick beams, and brighten all the fields;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18631, line : "Broad glittering breastplates, spears with pointed rays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18632, line : "Mix in one stream, reflecting blaze on blaze;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18633, line : "Thick beats the centre as the coursers bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18634, line : "With splendour flame the skies, and laugh the fields around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18636, line : "Full in the midst, high-towering o'er the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18637, line : "His limbs in arms divine Achilles dress'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18638, line : "Arms which the father of the fire bestow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18639, line : "Forged on the eternal anvils of the god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18640, line : "Grief and revenge his furious heart inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18641, line : "His glowing eyeballs roll with living fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18642, line : "He grinds his teeth, and furious with delay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18643, line : "O'erlooks the embattled host, and hopes the bloody day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18645, line : "The silver cuishes first his thighs infold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18646, line : "Then o'er his breast was braced the hollow gold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18647, line : "The brazen sword a various baldric tied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18648, line : "That, starr'd with gems, hung glittering at his side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18649, line : "And, like the moon, the broad refulgent shield"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18650, line : "Blazed with long rays, and gleam'd athwart the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18652, line : "So to night-wandering sailors, pale with fears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18653, line : "Wide o'er the watery waste, a light appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18654, line : "Which on the far-seen mountain blazing high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18655, line : "Streams from some lonely watch-tower to the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18656, line : "With mournful eyes they gaze, and gaze again;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18657, line : "Loud howls the storm, and drives them o'er the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18659, line : "Next, his high head the helmet graced; behind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18660, line : "The sweepy crest hung floating in the wind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18661, line : "Like the red star, that from his flaming hair"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18662, line : "Shakes down diseases, pestilence, and war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18663, line : "So stream'd the golden honours from his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18664, line : "Trembled the sparkling plumes, and the loose glories shed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18665, line : "The chief beholds himself with wondering eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18666, line : "His arms he poises, and his motions tries;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18667, line : "Buoy'd by some inward force, he seems to swim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18668, line : "And feels a pinion lifting every limb."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18670, line : "And now he shakes his great paternal spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18671, line : "Ponderous and huge, which not a Greek could rear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18672, line : "From Pelion's cloudy top an ash entire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18673, line : "Old Chiron fell'd, and shaped it for his sire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18674, line : "A spear which stern Achilles only wields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18675, line : "The death of heroes, and the dread of fields."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18677, line : "Automedon and Alcimus prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18678, line : "The immortal coursers, and the radiant car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18679, line : "(The silver traces sweeping at their side;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18680, line : "Their fiery mouths resplendent bridles tied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18681, line : "The ivory-studded reins, return'd behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18682, line : "Waved o'er their backs, and to the chariot join'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18683, line : "The charioteer then whirl'd the lash around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18684, line : "And swift ascended at one active bound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18685, line : "All bright in heavenly arms, above his squire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18686, line : "Achilles mounts, and sets the field on fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18687, line : "Not brighter Phoebus in the ethereal way"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18688, line : "Flames from his chariot, and restores the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18689, line : "High o'er the host, all terrible he stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18690, line : "And thunders to his steeds these dread commands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18692, line : "\"Xanthus and Balius! of Podarges' strain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18693, line : "(Unless ye boast that heavenly race in vain,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18694, line : "Be swift, be mindful of the load ye bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18695, line : "And learn to make your master more your care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18696, line : "Through falling squadrons bear my slaughtering sword,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18697, line : "Nor, as ye left Patroclus, leave your lord.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18699, line : "The generous Xanthus, as the words he said,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18700, line : "Seem'd sensible of woe, and droop'd his head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18701, line : "Trembling he stood before the golden wain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18702, line : "And bow'd to dust the honours of his mane."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18703, line : "When, strange to tell! (so Juno will'd) he broke"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18704, line : "Eternal silence, and portentous spoke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18705, line : "\"Achilles! yes! this day at least we bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18706, line : "Thy rage in safety through the files of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18707, line : "But come it will, the fatal time must come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18708, line : "Not ours the fault, but God decrees thy doom."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18709, line : "Not through our crime, or slowness in the course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18710, line : "Fell thy Patroclus, but by heavenly force;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18711, line : "The bright far-shooting god who gilds the day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18712, line : "(Confess'd we saw him) tore his arms way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18713, line : "No--could our swiftness o'er the winds prevail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18714, line : "Or beat the pinions of the western gale,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18715, line : "All were in vain--the Fates thy death demand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18716, line : "Due to a mortal and immortal hand.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18718, line : "Then ceased for ever, by the Furies tied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18719, line : "His fateful voice. The intrepid chief replied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18720, line : "With unabated rage--\"So let it be!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18721, line : "Portents and prodigies are lost on me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18722, line : "I know my fate: to die, to see no more"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18723, line : "My much-loved parents, and my native shore--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18724, line : "Enough--when heaven ordains, I sink in night:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18725, line : "Now perish Troy!\" He said, and rush'd to fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18727, line : "[Illustration: HERCULES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18729, line : "HERCULES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18735, line : "BOOK XX."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18738, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18740, line : "THE BATTLE OF THE GODS, AND THE ACTS OF ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18742, line : "Jupiter, upon Achilles' return to the battle, calls a council of the gods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18743, line : "and permits them to assist either party. The terrors of the combat"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18744, line : "described, when the deities are engaged. Apollo encourages Ćneas to meet"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18745, line : "Achilles. After a long conversation, these two heroes encounter; but Ćneas"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18746, line : "is preserved by the assistance of Neptune. Achilles falls upon the rest of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18747, line : "the Trojans, and is upon the point of killing Hector, but Apollo conveys"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18748, line : "him away in a cloud. Achilles pursues the Trojans with a great slaughter."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18750, line : "The same day continues. The scene is in the field before Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18752, line : "Thus round Pelides breathing war and blood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18753, line : "Greece, sheathed in arms, beside her vessels stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18754, line : "While near impending from a neighbouring height,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18755, line : "Troy's black battalions wait the shock of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18756, line : "Then Jove to Themis gives command, to call"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18757, line : "The gods to council in the starry hall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18758, line : "Swift o'er Olympus' hundred hills she flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18759, line : "And summons all the senate of the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18760, line : "These shining on, in long procession come"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18761, line : "To Jove's eternal adamantine dome."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18762, line : "Not one was absent, not a rural power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18763, line : "That haunts the verdant gloom, or rosy bower;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18764, line : "Each fair-hair'd dryad of the shady wood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18765, line : "Each azure sister of the silver flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18766, line : "All but old Ocean, hoary sire! who keeps"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18767, line : "His ancient seat beneath the sacred deeps."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18768, line : "On marble thrones, with lucid columns crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18769, line : "(The work of Vulcan,) sat the powers around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18770, line : "Even he whose trident sways the watery reign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18771, line : "Heard the loud summons, and forsook the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18772, line : "Assumed his throne amid the bright abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18773, line : "And question'd thus the sire of men and gods:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18775, line : "\"What moves the god who heaven and earth commands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18776, line : "And grasps the thunder in his awful hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18777, line : "Thus to convene the whole ethereal state?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18778, line : "Is Greece and Troy the subject in debate?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18779, line : "Already met, the louring hosts appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18780, line : "And death stands ardent on the edge of war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18782, line : "\"'Tis true (the cloud-compelling power replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18783, line : "This day we call the council of the skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18784, line : "In care of human race; even Jove's own eye"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18785, line : "Sees with regret unhappy mortals die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18786, line : "Far on Olympus' top in secret state"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18787, line : "Ourself will sit, and see the hand of fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18788, line : "Work out our will. Celestial powers! descend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18789, line : "And as your minds direct, your succour lend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18790, line : "To either host. Troy soon must lie o'erthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18791, line : "If uncontroll'd Achilles fights alone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18792, line : "Their troops but lately durst not meet his eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18793, line : "What can they now, if in his rage he rise?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18794, line : "Assist them, gods! or Ilion's sacred wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18795, line : "May fall this day, though fate forbids the fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18797, line : "He said, and fired their heavenly breasts with rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18798, line : "On adverse parts the warring gods engage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18799, line : "Heaven's awful queen; and he whose azure round"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18800, line : "Girds the vast globe; the maid in arms renown'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18801, line : "Hermes, of profitable arts the sire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18802, line : "And Vulcan, the black sovereign of the fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18803, line : "These to the fleet repair with instant flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18804, line : "The vessels tremble as the gods alight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18805, line : "In aid of Troy, Latona, Phoebus came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18806, line : "Mars fiery-helm'd, the laughter-loving dame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18807, line : "Xanthus, whose streams in golden currents flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18808, line : "And the chaste huntress of the silver bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18809, line : "Ere yet the gods their various aid employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18810, line : "Each Argive bosom swell'd with manly joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18811, line : "While great Achilles (terror of the plain),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18812, line : "Long lost to battle, shone in arms again."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18813, line : "Dreadful he stood in front of all his host;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18814, line : "Pale Troy beheld, and seem'd already lost;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18815, line : "Her bravest heroes pant with inward fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18816, line : "And trembling see another god of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18818, line : "But when the powers descending swell'd the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18819, line : "Then tumult rose: fierce rage and pale affright"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18820, line : "Varied each face: then Discord sounds alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18821, line : "Earth echoes, and the nations rush to arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18822, line : "Now through the trembling shores Minerva calls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18823, line : "And now she thunders from the Grecian walls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18824, line : "Mars hovering o'er his Troy, his terror shrouds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18825, line : "In gloomy tempests, and a night of clouds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18826, line : "Now through each Trojan heart he fury pours"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18827, line : "With voice divine, from Ilion's topmost towers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18828, line : "Now shouts to Simois, from her beauteous hill;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18829, line : "The mountain shook, the rapid stream stood still."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18831, line : "Above, the sire of gods his thunder rolls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18832, line : "And peals on peals redoubled rend the poles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18833, line : "Beneath, stern Neptune shakes the solid ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18834, line : "The forests wave, the mountains nod around;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18835, line : "Through all their summits tremble Ida's woods,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18836, line : "And from their sources boil her hundred floods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18837, line : "Troy's turrets totter on the rocking plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18838, line : "And the toss'd navies beat the heaving main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18839, line : "Deep in the dismal regions of the dead,(260)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18840, line : "The infernal monarch rear'd his horrid head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18841, line : "Leap'd from his throne, lest Neptune's arm should lay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18842, line : "His dark dominions open to the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18843, line : "And pour in light on Pluto's drear abodes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18844, line : "Abhorr'd by men, and dreadful even to gods.(261)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18846, line : "[Illustration: THE GODS DESCENDING TO BATTLE.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18848, line : "THE GODS DESCENDING TO BATTLE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18851, line : "Such war the immortals wage; such horrors rend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18852, line : "The world's vast concave, when the gods contend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18853, line : "First silver-shafted Phoebus took the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18854, line : "Against blue Neptune, monarch of the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18855, line : "The god of arms his giant bulk display'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18856, line : "Opposed to Pallas, war's triumphant maid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18857, line : "Against Latona march'd the son of May."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18858, line : "The quiver'd Dian, sister of the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18859, line : "(Her golden arrows sounding at her side,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18860, line : "Saturnia, majesty of heaven, defied."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18861, line : "With fiery Vulcan last in battle stands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18862, line : "The sacred flood that rolls on golden sands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18863, line : "Xanthus his name with those of heavenly birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18864, line : "But called Scamander by the sons of earth."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18866, line : "While thus the gods in various league engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18867, line : "Achilles glow'd with more than mortal rage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18868, line : "Hector he sought; in search of Hector turn'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18869, line : "His eyes around, for Hector only burn'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18870, line : "And burst like lightning through the ranks, and vow'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18871, line : "To glut the god of battles with his blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18873, line : "Ćneas was the first who dared to stay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18874, line : "Apollo wedged him in the warrior's way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18875, line : "But swell'd his bosom with undaunted might,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18876, line : "Half-forced and half-persuaded to the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18877, line : "Like young Lycaon, of the royal line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18878, line : "In voice and aspect, seem'd the power divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18879, line : "And bade the chief reflect, how late with scorn"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18880, line : "In distant threats he braved the goddess-born."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18882, line : "Then thus the hero of Anchises' strain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18883, line : "\"To meet Pelides you persuade in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18884, line : "Already have I met, nor void of fear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18885, line : "Observed the fury of his flying spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18886, line : "From Ida's woods he chased us to the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18887, line : "Our force he scattered, and our herds he kill'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18888, line : "Lyrnessus, Pedasus in ashes lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18889, line : "But (Jove assisting) I survived the day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18890, line : "Else had I sunk oppress'd in fatal fight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18891, line : "By fierce Achilles and Minerva's might."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18892, line : "Where'er he moved, the goddess shone before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18893, line : "And bathed his brazen lance in hostile gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18894, line : "What mortal man Achilles can sustain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18895, line : "The immortals guard him through the dreadful plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18896, line : "And suffer not his dart to fall in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18897, line : "Were God my aid, this arm should check his power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18898, line : "Though strong in battle as a brazen tower.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18900, line : "To whom the son of Jove: \"That god implore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18901, line : "And be what great Achilles was before."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18902, line : "From heavenly Venus thou deriv'st thy strain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18903, line : "And he but from a sister of the main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18904, line : "An aged sea-god father of his line;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18905, line : "But Jove himself the sacred source of thine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18906, line : "Then lift thy weapon for a noble blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18907, line : "Nor fear the vaunting of a mortal foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18909, line : "This said, and spirit breathed into his breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18910, line : "Through the thick troops the embolden'd hero press'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18911, line : "His venturous act the white-arm'd queen survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18912, line : "And thus, assembling all the powers, she said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18914, line : "\"Behold an action, gods! that claims your care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18915, line : "Lo great Ćneas rushing to the war!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18916, line : "Against Pelides he directs his course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18917, line : "Phoebus impels, and Phoebus gives him force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18918, line : "Restrain his bold career; at least, to attend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18919, line : "Our favour'd hero, let some power descend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18920, line : "To guard his life, and add to his renown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18921, line : "We, the great armament of heaven, came down."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18922, line : "Hereafter let him fall, as Fates design,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18923, line : "That spun so short his life's illustrious line:(262)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18924, line : "But lest some adverse god now cross his way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18925, line : "Give him to know what powers assist this day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18926, line : "For how shall mortal stand the dire alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18927, line : "When heaven's refulgent host appear in arms?\"(263)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18929, line : "Thus she; and thus the god whose force can make"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18930, line : "The solid globe's eternal basis shake:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18931, line : "\"Against the might of man, so feeble known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18932, line : "Why should celestial powers exert their own?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18933, line : "Suffice from yonder mount to view the scene,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18934, line : "And leave to war the fates of mortal men."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18935, line : "But if the armipotent, or god of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18936, line : "Obstruct Achilles, or commence the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18937, line : "Thence on the gods of Troy we swift descend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18938, line : "Full soon, I doubt not, shall the conflict end;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18939, line : "And these, in ruin and confusion hurl'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18940, line : "Yield to our conquering arms the lower world.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18942, line : "Thus having said, the tyrant of the sea,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18943, line : "Coerulean Neptune, rose, and led the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18944, line : "Advanced upon the field there stood a mound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18945, line : "Of earth congested, wall'd, and trench'd around;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18946, line : "In elder times to guard Alcides made,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18947, line : "(The work of Trojans, with Minerva's aid,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18948, line : "What time a vengeful monster of the main"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18949, line : "Swept the wide shore, and drove him to the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18951, line : "Here Neptune and the gods of Greece repair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18952, line : "With clouds encompass'd, and a veil of air:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18953, line : "The adverse powers, around Apollo laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18954, line : "Crown the fair hills that silver Simois shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18955, line : "In circle close each heavenly party sat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18956, line : "Intent to form the future scheme of fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18957, line : "But mix not yet in fight, though Jove on high"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18958, line : "Gives the loud signal, and the heavens reply."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18960, line : "Meanwhile the rushing armies hide the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18961, line : "The trampled centre yields a hollow sound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18962, line : "Steeds cased in mail, and chiefs in armour bright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18963, line : "The gleaming champaign glows with brazen light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18964, line : "Amid both hosts (a dreadful space) appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18965, line : "There great Achilles; bold Ćneas, here."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18966, line : "With towering strides Aeneas first advanced;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18967, line : "The nodding plumage on his helmet danced:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18968, line : "Spread o'er his breast the fencing shield he bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18969, line : "And, so he moved, his javelin flamed before."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18970, line : "Not so Pelides; furious to engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18971, line : "He rush'd impetuous. Such the lion's rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18972, line : "Who viewing first his foes with scornful eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18973, line : "Though all in arms the peopled city rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18974, line : "Stalks careless on, with unregarding pride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18975, line : "Till at the length, by some brave youth defied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18976, line : "To his bold spear the savage turns alone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18977, line : "He murmurs fury with a hollow groan;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18978, line : "He grins, he foams, he rolls his eyes around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18979, line : "Lash'd by his tail his heaving sides resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18980, line : "He calls up all his rage; he grinds his teeth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18981, line : "Resolved on vengeance, or resolved on death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18982, line : "So fierce Achilles on Ćneas flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18983, line : "So stands Ćneas, and his force defies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18984, line : "Ere yet the stern encounter join'd, begun"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18985, line : "The seed of Thetis thus to Venus' son:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18987, line : "\"Why comes Ćneas through the ranks so far?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18988, line : "Seeks he to meet Achilles' arm in war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18989, line : "In hope the realms of Priam to enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18990, line : "And prove his merits to the throne of Troy?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18991, line : "Grant that beneath thy lance Achilles dies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18992, line : "The partial monarch may refuse the prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18993, line : "Sons he has many; those thy pride may quell:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18994, line : "And 'tis his fault to love those sons too well,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18995, line : "Or, in reward of thy victorious hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18996, line : "Has Troy proposed some spacious tract of land"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18997, line : "An ample forest, or a fair domain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18998, line : "Of hills for vines, and arable for grain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 18999, line : "Even this, perhaps, will hardly prove thy lot."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19000, line : "But can Achilles be so soon forgot?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19001, line : "Once (as I think) you saw this brandish'd spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19002, line : "And then the great Ćneas seem'd to fear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19003, line : "With hearty haste from Ida's mount he fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19004, line : "Nor, till he reach'd Lyrnessus, turn'd his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19005, line : "Her lofty walls not long our progress stay'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19006, line : "Those, Pallas, Jove, and we, in ruins laid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19007, line : "In Grecian chains her captive race were cast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19008, line : "'Tis true, the great Aeneas fled too fast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19009, line : "Defrauded of my conquest once before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19010, line : "What then I lost, the gods this day restore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19011, line : "Go; while thou may'st, avoid the threaten'd fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19012, line : "Fools stay to feel it, and are wise too late.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19014, line : "To this Anchises' son: \"Such words employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19015, line : "To one that fears thee, some unwarlike boy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19016, line : "Such we disdain; the best may be defied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19017, line : "With mean reproaches, and unmanly pride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19018, line : "Unworthy the high race from which we came"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19019, line : "Proclaim'd so loudly by the voice of fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19020, line : "Each from illustrious fathers draws his line;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19021, line : "Each goddess-born; half human, half divine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19022, line : "Thetis' this day, or Venus' offspring dies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19023, line : "And tears shall trickle from celestial eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19024, line : "For when two heroes, thus derived, contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19025, line : "'Tis not in words the glorious strife can end."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19026, line : "If yet thou further seek to learn my birth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19027, line : "(A tale resounded through the spacious earth)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19028, line : "Hear how the glorious origin we prove"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19029, line : "From ancient Dardanus, the first from Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19030, line : "Dardania's walls he raised; for Ilion, then,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19031, line : "(The city since of many-languaged men,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19032, line : "Was not. The natives were content to till"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19033, line : "The shady foot of Ida's fountful hill.(264)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19034, line : "From Dardanus great Erichthonius springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19035, line : "The richest, once, of Asia's wealthy kings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19036, line : "Three thousand mares his spacious pastures bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19037, line : "Three thousand foals beside their mothers fed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19038, line : "Boreas, enamour'd of the sprightly train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19039, line : "Conceal'd his godhead in a flowing mane,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19040, line : "With voice dissembled to his loves he neigh'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19041, line : "And coursed the dappled beauties o'er the mead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19042, line : "Hence sprung twelve others of unrivall'd kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19043, line : "Swift as their mother mares, and father wind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19044, line : "These lightly skimming, when they swept the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19045, line : "Nor plied the grass, nor bent the tender grain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19046, line : "And when along the level seas they flew,(265)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19047, line : "Scarce on the surface curl'd the briny dew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19048, line : "Such Erichthonius was: from him there came"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19049, line : "The sacred Tros, of whom the Trojan name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19050, line : "Three sons renown'd adorn'd his nuptial bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19051, line : "Ilus, Assaracus, and Ganymed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19052, line : "The matchless Ganymed, divinely fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19053, line : "Whom heaven, enamour'd, snatch'd to upper air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19054, line : "To bear the cup of Jove (ethereal guest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19055, line : "The grace and glory of the ambrosial feast)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19056, line : "The two remaining sons the line divide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19057, line : "First rose Laomedon from Ilus' side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19058, line : "From him Tithonus, now in cares grown old,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19059, line : "And Priam, bless'd with Hector, brave and bold;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19060, line : "Clytius and Lampus, ever-honour'd pair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19061, line : "And Hicetaon, thunderbolt of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19062, line : "From great Assaracus sprang Capys, he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19063, line : "Begat Anchises, and Anchises me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19064, line : "Such is our race: 'tis fortune gives us birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19065, line : "But Jove alone endues the soul with worth:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19066, line : "He, source of power and might! with boundless sway,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19067, line : "All human courage gives, or takes away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19068, line : "Long in the field of words we may contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19069, line : "Reproach is infinite, and knows no end,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19070, line : "Arm'd or with truth or falsehood, right or wrong;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19071, line : "So voluble a weapon is the tongue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19072, line : "Wounded, we wound; and neither side can fail,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19073, line : "For every man has equal strength to rail:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19074, line : "Women alone, when in the streets they jar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19075, line : "Perhaps excel us in this wordy war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19076, line : "Like us they stand, encompass'd with the crowd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19077, line : "And vent their anger impotent and loud."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19078, line : "Cease then--Our business in the field of fight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19079, line : "Is not to question, but to prove our might."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19080, line : "To all those insults thou hast offer'd here,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19081, line : "Receive this answer: 'tis my flying spear.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19083, line : "He spoke. With all his force the javelin flung,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19084, line : "Fix'd deep, and loudly in the buckler rung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19085, line : "Far on his outstretch'd arm, Pelides held"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19086, line : "(To meet the thundering lance) his dreadful shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19087, line : "That trembled as it stuck; nor void of fear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19088, line : "Saw, ere it fell, the immeasurable spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19089, line : "His fears were vain; impenetrable charms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19090, line : "Secured the temper of the ethereal arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19091, line : "Through two strong plates the point its passage held,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19092, line : "But stopp'd, and rested, by the third repell'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19093, line : "Five plates of various metal, various mould,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19094, line : "Composed the shield; of brass each outward fold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19095, line : "Of tin each inward, and the middle gold:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19096, line : "There stuck the lance. Then rising ere he threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19097, line : "The forceful spear of great Achilles flew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19098, line : "And pierced the Dardan shield's extremest bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19099, line : "Where the shrill brass return'd a sharper sound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19100, line : "Through the thin verge the Pelean weapon glides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19101, line : "And the slight covering of expanded hides."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19102, line : "Ćneas his contracted body bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19103, line : "And o'er him high the riven targe extends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19104, line : "Sees, through its parting plates, the upper air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19105, line : "And at his back perceives the quivering spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19106, line : "A fate so near him, chills his soul with fright;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19107, line : "And swims before his eyes the many-colour'd light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19108, line : "Achilles, rushing in with dreadful cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19109, line : "Draws his broad blade, and at Ćneas flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19110, line : "Ćneas rousing as the foe came on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19111, line : "With force collected, heaves a mighty stone:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19112, line : "A mass enormous! which in modern days"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19113, line : "No two of earth's degenerate sons could raise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19114, line : "But ocean's god, whose earthquakes rock the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19115, line : "Saw the distress, and moved the powers around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19117, line : "\"Lo! on the brink of fate Ćneas stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19118, line : "An instant victim to Achilles' hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19119, line : "By Phoebus urged; but Phoebus has bestow'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19120, line : "His aid in vain: the man o'erpowers the god."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19121, line : "And can ye see this righteous chief atone"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19122, line : "With guiltless blood for vices not his own?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19123, line : "To all the gods his constant vows were paid;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19124, line : "Sure, though he wars for Troy, he claims our aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19125, line : "Fate wills not this; nor thus can Jove resign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19126, line : "The future father of the Dardan line:(266)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19127, line : "The first great ancestor obtain'd his grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19128, line : "And still his love descends on all the race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19129, line : "For Priam now, and Priam's faithless kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19130, line : "At length are odious to the all-seeing mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19131, line : "On great Ćneas shall devolve the reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19132, line : "And sons succeeding sons the lasting line sustain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19134, line : "The great earth-shaker thus: to whom replies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19135, line : "The imperial goddess with the radiant eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19136, line : "\"Good as he is, to immolate or spare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19137, line : "The Dardan prince, O Neptune! be thy care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19138, line : "Pallas and I, by all that gods can bind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19139, line : "Have sworn destruction to the Trojan kind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19140, line : "Not even an instant to protract their fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19141, line : "Or save one member of the sinking state;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19142, line : "Till her last flame be quench'd with her last gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19143, line : "And even her crumbling ruins are no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19145, line : "The king of ocean to the fight descends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19146, line : "Through all the whistling darts his course he bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19147, line : "Swift interposed between the warrior flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19148, line : "And casts thick darkness o'er Achilles' eyes.(267)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19149, line : "From great Ćneas' shield the spear he drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19150, line : "And at his master's feet the weapon threw."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19151, line : "That done, with force divine he snatch'd on high"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19152, line : "The Dardan prince, and bore him through the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19153, line : "Smooth-gliding without step, above the heads"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19154, line : "Of warring heroes, and of bounding steeds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19155, line : "Till at the battle's utmost verge they light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19156, line : "Where the slow Caucans close the rear of fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19157, line : "The godhead there (his heavenly form confess'd)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19158, line : "With words like these the panting chief address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19160, line : "\"What power, O prince! with force inferior far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19161, line : "Urged thee to meet Achilles' arm in war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19162, line : "Henceforth beware, nor antedate thy doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19163, line : "Defrauding fate of all thy fame to come."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19164, line : "But when the day decreed (for come it must)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19165, line : "Shall lay this dreadful hero in the dust,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19166, line : "Let then the furies of that arm be known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19167, line : "Secure no Grecian force transcends thy own.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19169, line : "With that, he left him wondering as he lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19170, line : "Then from Achilles chased the mist away:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19171, line : "Sudden, returning with a stream of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19172, line : "The scene of war came rushing on his sight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19173, line : "Then thus, amazed; \"What wonders strike my mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19174, line : "My spear, that parted on the wings of wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19175, line : "Laid here before me! and the Dardan lord,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19176, line : "That fell this instant, vanish'd from my sword!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19177, line : "I thought alone with mortals to contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19178, line : "But powers celestial sure this foe defend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19179, line : "Great as he is, our arms he scarce will try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19180, line : "Content for once, with all his gods, to fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19181, line : "Now then let others bleed.\" This said, aloud"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19182, line : "He vents his fury and inflames the crowd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19183, line : "\"O Greeks! (he cries, and every rank alarms)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19184, line : "Join battle, man to man, and arms to arms!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19185, line : "'Tis not in me, though favour'd by the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19186, line : "To mow whole troops, and make whole armies fly:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19187, line : "No god can singly such a host engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19188, line : "Not Mars himself, nor great Minerva's rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19189, line : "But whatsoe'er Achilles can inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19190, line : "Whate'er of active force, or acting fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19191, line : "Whate'er this heart can prompt, or hand obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19192, line : "All, all Achilles, Greeks! is yours to-day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19193, line : "Through yon wide host this arm shall scatter fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19194, line : "And thin the squadrons with my single spear.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19196, line : "He said: nor less elate with martial joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19197, line : "The godlike Hector warm'd the troops of Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19198, line : "\"Trojans, to war! Think, Hector leads you on;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19199, line : "Nor dread the vaunts of Peleus' haughty son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19200, line : "Deeds must decide our fate. E'en these with words"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19201, line : "Insult the brave, who tremble at their swords:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19202, line : "The weakest atheist-wretch all heaven defies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19203, line : "But shrinks and shudders when the thunder flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19204, line : "Nor from yon boaster shall your chief retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19205, line : "Not though his heart were steel, his hands were fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19206, line : "That fire, that steel, your Hector should withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19207, line : "And brave that vengeful heart, that dreadful hand.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19209, line : "Thus (breathing rage through all) the hero said;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19210, line : "A wood of lances rises round his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19211, line : "Clamours on clamours tempest all the air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19212, line : "They join, they throng, they thicken to the war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19213, line : "But Phoebus warns him from high heaven to shun"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19214, line : "The single fight with Thetis' godlike son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19215, line : "More safe to combat in the mingled band,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19216, line : "Nor tempt too near the terrors of his hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19217, line : "He hears, obedient to the god of light,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19218, line : "And, plunged within the ranks, awaits the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19220, line : "Then fierce Achilles, shouting to the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19221, line : "On Troy's whole force with boundless fury flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19222, line : "First falls Iphytion, at his army's head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19223, line : "Brave was the chief, and brave the host he led;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19224, line : "From great Otrynteus he derived his blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19225, line : "His mother was a Nais, of the flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19226, line : "Beneath the shades of Tmolus, crown'd with snow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19227, line : "From Hyde's walls he ruled the lands below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19228, line : "Fierce as he springs, the sword his head divides:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19229, line : "The parted visage falls on equal sides:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19230, line : "With loud-resounding arms he strikes the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19231, line : "While thus Achilles glories o'er the slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19233, line : "\"Lie there, Otryntides! the Trojan earth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19234, line : "Receives thee dead, though Gygae boast thy birth;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19235, line : "Those beauteous fields where Hyllus' waves are roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19236, line : "And plenteous Hermus swells with tides of gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19237, line : "Are thine no more.\"--The insulting hero said,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19238, line : "And left him sleeping in eternal shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19239, line : "The rolling wheels of Greece the body tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19240, line : "And dash'd their axles with no vulgar gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19242, line : "Demoleon next, Antenor's offspring, laid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19243, line : "Breathless in dust, the price of rashness paid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19244, line : "The impatient steel with full-descending sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19245, line : "Forced through his brazen helm its furious way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19246, line : "Resistless drove the batter'd skull before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19247, line : "And dash'd and mingled all the brains with gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19248, line : "This sees Hippodamas, and seized with fright,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19249, line : "Deserts his chariot for a swifter flight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19250, line : "The lance arrests him: an ignoble wound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19251, line : "The panting Trojan rivets to the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19252, line : "He groans away his soul: not louder roars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19253, line : "At Neptune's shrine on Helice's high shores,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19254, line : "The victim bull; the rocks re-bellow round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19255, line : "And ocean listens to the grateful sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19256, line : "Then fell on Polydore his vengeful rage,(268)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19257, line : "The youngest hope of Priam's stooping age:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19258, line : "(Whose feet for swiftness in the race surpass'd:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19259, line : "Of all his sons, the dearest, and the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19260, line : "To the forbidden field he takes his flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19261, line : "In the first folly of a youthful knight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19262, line : "To vaunt his swiftness wheels around the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19263, line : "But vaunts not long, with all his swiftness slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19264, line : "Struck where the crossing belts unite behind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19265, line : "And golden rings the double back-plate join'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19266, line : "Forth through the navel burst the thrilling steel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19267, line : "And on his knees with piercing shrieks he fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19268, line : "The rushing entrails pour'd upon the ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19269, line : "His hands collect; and darkness wraps him round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19270, line : "When Hector view'd, all ghastly in his gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19271, line : "Thus sadly slain the unhappy Polydore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19272, line : "A cloud of sorrow overcast his sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19273, line : "His soul no longer brook'd the distant fight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19274, line : "Full in Achilles' dreadful front he came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19275, line : "And shook his javelin like a waving flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19276, line : "The son of Peleus sees, with joy possess'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19277, line : "His heart high-bounding in his rising breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19278, line : "\"And, lo! the man on whom black fates attend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19279, line : "The man, that slew Achilles, is his friend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19280, line : "No more shall Hector's and Pelides' spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19281, line : "Turn from each other in the walks of war.\"--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19282, line : "Then with revengeful eyes he scann'd him o'er:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19283, line : "\"Come, and receive thy fate!\" He spake no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19285, line : "Hector, undaunted, thus: \"Such words employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19286, line : "To one that dreads thee, some unwarlike boy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19287, line : "Such we could give, defying and defied,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19288, line : "Mean intercourse of obloquy and pride!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19289, line : "I know thy force to mine superior far;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19290, line : "But heaven alone confers success in war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19291, line : "Mean as I am, the gods may guide my dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19292, line : "And give it entrance in a braver heart.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19294, line : "Then parts the lance: but Pallas' heavenly breath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19295, line : "Far from Achilles wafts the winged death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19296, line : "The bidden dart again to Hector flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19297, line : "And at the feet of its great master lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19298, line : "Achilles closes with his hated foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19299, line : "His heart and eyes with flaming fury glow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19300, line : "But present to his aid, Apollo shrouds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19301, line : "The favour'd hero in a veil of clouds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19302, line : "Thrice struck Pelides with indignant heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19303, line : "Thrice in impassive air he plunged the dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19304, line : "The spear a fourth time buried in the cloud."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19305, line : "He foams with fury, and exclaims aloud:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19307, line : "\"Wretch! thou hast 'scaped again; once more thy flight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19308, line : "Has saved thee, and the partial god of light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19309, line : "But long thou shalt not thy just fate withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19310, line : "If any power assist Achilles' hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19311, line : "Fly then inglorious! but thy flight this day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19312, line : "Whole hecatombs of Trojan ghosts shall pay.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19314, line : "With that, he gluts his rage on numbers slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19315, line : "Then Dryops tumbled to the ensanguined plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19316, line : "Pierced through the neck: he left him panting there,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19317, line : "And stopp'd Demuchus, great Philetor's heir."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19318, line : "Gigantic chief! deep gash'd the enormous blade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19319, line : "And for the soul an ample passage made."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19320, line : "Laoganus and Dardanus expire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19321, line : "The valiant sons of an unhappy sire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19322, line : "Both in one instant from the chariot hurl'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19323, line : "Sunk in one instant to the nether world:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19324, line : "This difference only their sad fates afford"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19325, line : "That one the spear destroy'd, and one the sword."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19327, line : "Nor less unpitied, young Alastor bleeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19328, line : "In vain his youth, in vain his beauty pleads;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19329, line : "In vain he begs thee, with a suppliant's moan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19330, line : "To spare a form, an age so like thy own!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19331, line : "Unhappy boy! no prayer, no moving art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19332, line : "E'er bent that fierce, inexorable heart!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19333, line : "While yet he trembled at his knees, and cried,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19334, line : "The ruthless falchion oped his tender side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19335, line : "The panting liver pours a flood of gore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19336, line : "That drowns his bosom till he pants no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19338, line : "Through Mulius' head then drove the impetuous spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19339, line : "The warrior falls, transfix'd from ear to ear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19340, line : "Thy life, Echeclus! next the sword bereaves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19341, line : "Deep though the front the ponderous falchion cleaves;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19342, line : "Warm'd in the brain the smoking weapon lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19343, line : "The purple death comes floating o'er his eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19344, line : "Then brave Deucalion died: the dart was flung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19345, line : "Where the knit nerves the pliant elbow strung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19346, line : "He dropp'd his arm, an unassisting weight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19347, line : "And stood all impotent, expecting fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19348, line : "Full on his neck the falling falchion sped,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19349, line : "From his broad shoulders hew'd his crested head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19350, line : "Forth from the bone the spinal marrow flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19351, line : "And, sunk in dust, the corpse extended lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19352, line : "Rhigmas, whose race from fruitful Thracia came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19353, line : "(The son of Pierus, an illustrious name,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19354, line : "Succeeds to fate: the spear his belly rends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19355, line : "Prone from his car the thundering chief descends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19356, line : "The squire, who saw expiring on the ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19357, line : "His prostrate master, rein'd the steeds around;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19358, line : "His back, scarce turn'd, the Pelian javelin gored,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19359, line : "And stretch'd the servant o'er his dying lord."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19360, line : "As when a flame the winding valley fills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19361, line : "And runs on crackling shrubs between the hills;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19362, line : "Then o'er the stubble up the mountain flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19363, line : "Fires the high woods, and blazes to the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19364, line : "This way and that, the spreading torrent roars:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19365, line : "So sweeps the hero through the wasted shores;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19366, line : "Around him wide, immense destruction pours"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19367, line : "And earth is deluged with the sanguine showers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19368, line : "As with autumnal harvests cover'd o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19369, line : "And thick bestrewn, lies Ceres' sacred floor;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19370, line : "When round and round, with never-wearied pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19371, line : "The trampling steers beat out the unnumber'd grain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19372, line : "So the fierce coursers, as the chariot rolls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19373, line : "Tread down whole ranks, and crush out heroes' souls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19374, line : "Dash'd from their hoofs while o'er the dead they fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19375, line : "Black, bloody drops the smoking chariot dye:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19376, line : "The spiky wheels through heaps of carnage tore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19377, line : "And thick the groaning axles dropp'd with gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19378, line : "High o'er the scene of death Achilles stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19379, line : "All grim with dust, all horrible in blood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19380, line : "Yet still insatiate, still with rage on flame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19381, line : "Such is the lust of never-dying fame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19383, line : "[Illustration: CENTAUR.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19385, line : "CENTAUR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19391, line : "BOOK XXI."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19394, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19396, line : "THE BATTLE IN THE RIVER SCAMANDER.(269)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19398, line : "The Trojans fly before Achilles, some towards the town, others to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19399, line : "river Scamander: he falls upon the latter with great slaughter: takes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19400, line : "twelve captives alive, to sacrifice to the shade of Patroclus; and kills"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19401, line : "Lycaon and Asteropeus. Scamander attacks him with all his waves: Neptune"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19402, line : "and Pallas assist the hero: Simois joins Scamander: at length Vulcan, by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19403, line : "the instigation of Juno, almost dries up the river. This Combat ended, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19404, line : "other gods engage each other. Meanwhile Achilles continues the slaughter,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19405, line : "drives the rest into Troy: Agenor only makes a stand, and is conveyed away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19406, line : "in a cloud by Apollo; who (to delude Achilles) takes upon him Agenor's"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19407, line : "shape, and while he pursues him in that disguise, gives the Trojans an"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19408, line : "opportunity of retiring into their city."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19410, line : "The same day continues. The scene is on the banks and in the stream of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19411, line : "Scamander."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19413, line : "And now to Xanthus' gliding stream they drove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19414, line : "Xanthus, immortal progeny of Jove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19415, line : "The river here divides the flying train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19416, line : "Part to the town fly diverse o'er the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19417, line : "Where late their troops triumphant bore the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19418, line : "Now chased, and trembling in ignoble flight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19419, line : "(These with a gathered mist Saturnia shrouds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19420, line : "And rolls behind the rout a heap of clouds:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19421, line : "Part plunge into the stream: old Xanthus roars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19422, line : "The flashing billows beat the whiten'd shores:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19423, line : "With cries promiscuous all the banks resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19424, line : "And here, and there, in eddies whirling round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19425, line : "The flouncing steeds and shrieking warriors drown'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19426, line : "As the scorch'd locusts from their fields retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19427, line : "While fast behind them runs the blaze of fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19428, line : "Driven from the land before the smoky cloud,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19429, line : "The clustering legions rush into the flood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19430, line : "So, plunged in Xanthus by Achilles' force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19431, line : "Roars the resounding surge with men and horse."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19432, line : "His bloody lance the hero casts aside,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19433, line : "(Which spreading tamarisks on the margin hide,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19434, line : "Then, like a god, the rapid billows braves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19435, line : "Arm'd with his sword, high brandish'd o'er the waves:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19436, line : "Now down he plunges, now he whirls it round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19437, line : "Deep groan'd the waters with the dying sound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19438, line : "Repeated wounds the reddening river dyed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19439, line : "And the warm purple circled on the tide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19440, line : "Swift through the foamy flood the Trojans fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19441, line : "And close in rocks or winding caverns lie:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19442, line : "So the huge dolphin tempesting the main,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19443, line : "In shoals before him fly the scaly train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19444, line : "Confusedly heap'd they seek their inmost caves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19445, line : "Or pant and heave beneath the floating waves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19446, line : "Now, tired with slaughter, from the Trojan band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19447, line : "Twelve chosen youths he drags alive to land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19448, line : "With their rich belts their captive arms restrains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19449, line : "(Late their proud ornaments, but now their chains)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19450, line : "These his attendants to the ships convey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19451, line : "Sad victims destined to Patroclus' shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19453, line : "Then, as once more he plunged amid the flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19454, line : "The young Lycaon in his passage stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19455, line : "The son of Priam; whom the hero's hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19456, line : "But late made captive in his father's land"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19457, line : "(As from a sycamore, his sounding steel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19458, line : "Lopp'd the green arms to spoke a chariot wheel)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19459, line : "To Lemnos' isle he sold the royal slave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19460, line : "Where Jason's son the price demanded gave;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19461, line : "But kind Eetion, touching on the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19462, line : "The ransom'd prince to fair Arisbe bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19463, line : "Ten days were past, since in his father's reign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19464, line : "He felt the sweets of liberty again;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19465, line : "The next, that god whom men in vain withstand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19466, line : "Gives the same youth to the same conquering hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19467, line : "Now never to return! and doom'd to go"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19468, line : "A sadder journey to the shades below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19469, line : "His well-known face when great Achilles eyed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19470, line : "(The helm and visor he had cast aside"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19471, line : "With wild affright, and dropp'd upon the field"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19472, line : "His useless lance and unavailing shield,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19473, line : "As trembling, panting, from the stream he fled,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19474, line : "And knock'd his faltering knees, the hero said."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19475, line : "\"Ye mighty gods! what wonders strike my view!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19476, line : "Is it in vain our conquering arms subdue?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19477, line : "Sure I shall see yon heaps of Trojans kill'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19478, line : "Rise from the shades, and brave me on the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19479, line : "As now the captive, whom so late I bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19480, line : "And sold to Lemnos, stalks on Trojan ground!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19481, line : "Not him the sea's unmeasured deeps detain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19482, line : "That bar such numbers from their native plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19483, line : "Lo! he returns. Try, then, my flying spear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19484, line : "Try, if the grave can hold the wanderer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19485, line : "If earth, at length this active prince can seize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19486, line : "Earth, whose strong grasp has held down Hercules.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19488, line : "Thus while he spoke, the Trojan pale with fears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19489, line : "Approach'd, and sought his knees with suppliant tears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19490, line : "Loth as he was to yield his youthful breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19491, line : "And his soul shivering at the approach of death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19492, line : "Achilles raised the spear, prepared to wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19493, line : "He kiss'd his feet, extended on the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19494, line : "And while, above, the spear suspended stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19495, line : "Longing to dip its thirsty point in blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19496, line : "One hand embraced them close, one stopp'd the dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19497, line : "While thus these melting words attempt his heart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19499, line : "\"Thy well-known captive, great Achilles! see,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19500, line : "Once more Lycaon trembles at thy knee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19501, line : "Some pity to a suppliant's name afford,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19502, line : "Who shared the gifts of Ceres at thy board;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19503, line : "Whom late thy conquering arm to Lemnos bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19504, line : "Far from his father, friends, and native shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19505, line : "A hundred oxen were his price that day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19506, line : "Now sums immense thy mercy shall repay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19507, line : "Scarce respited from woes I yet appear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19508, line : "And scarce twelve morning suns have seen me here;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19509, line : "Lo! Jove again submits me to thy hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19510, line : "Again, her victim cruel Fate demands!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19511, line : "I sprang from Priam, and Laothoe fair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19512, line : "(Old Altes' daughter, and Lelegia's heir;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19513, line : "Who held in Pedasus his famed abode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19514, line : "And ruled the fields where silver Satnio flow'd,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19515, line : "Two sons (alas! unhappy sons) she bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19516, line : "For ah! one spear shall drink each brother's gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19517, line : "And I succeed to slaughter'd Polydore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19518, line : "How from that arm of terror shall I fly?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19519, line : "Some demon urges! 'tis my doom to die!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19520, line : "If ever yet soft pity touch'd thy mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19521, line : "Ah! think not me too much of Hector's kind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19522, line : "Not the same mother gave thy suppliant breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19523, line : "With his, who wrought thy loved Patroclus' death.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19525, line : "These words, attended with a shower of tears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19526, line : "The youth address'd to unrelenting ears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19527, line : "\"Talk not of life, or ransom (he replies):"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19528, line : "Patroclus dead, whoever meets me, dies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19529, line : "In vain a single Trojan sues for grace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19530, line : "But least, the sons of Priam's hateful race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19531, line : "Die then, my friend! what boots it to deplore?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19532, line : "The great, the good Patroclus is no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19533, line : "He, far thy better, was foredoom'd to die,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19534, line : "And thou, dost thou bewail mortality?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19535, line : "Seest thou not me, whom nature's gifts adorn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19536, line : "Sprung from a hero, from a goddess born?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19537, line : "The day shall come (which nothing can avert)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19538, line : "When by the spear, the arrow, or the dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19539, line : "By night, or day, by force, or by design,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19540, line : "Impending death and certain fate are mine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19541, line : "Die then,\"--He said; and as the word he spoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19542, line : "The fainting stripling sank before the stroke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19543, line : "His hand forgot its grasp, and left the spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19544, line : "While all his trembling frame confess'd his fear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19545, line : "Sudden, Achilles his broad sword display'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19546, line : "And buried in his neck the reeking blade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19547, line : "Prone fell the youth; and panting on the land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19548, line : "The gushing purple dyed the thirsty sand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19549, line : "The victor to the stream the carcase gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19550, line : "And thus insults him, floating on the wave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19552, line : "\"Lie there, Lycaon! let the fish surround"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19553, line : "Thy bloated corpse, and suck thy gory wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19554, line : "There no sad mother shall thy funerals weep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19555, line : "But swift Scamander roll thee to the deep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19556, line : "Whose every wave some watery monster brings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19557, line : "To feast unpunish'd on the fat of kings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19558, line : "So perish Troy, and all the Trojan line!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19559, line : "Such ruin theirs, and such compassion mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19560, line : "What boots ye now Scamander's worshipp'd stream,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19561, line : "His earthly honours, and immortal name?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19562, line : "In vain your immolated bulls are slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19563, line : "Your living coursers glut his gulfs in vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19564, line : "Thus he rewards you, with this bitter fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19565, line : "Thus, till the Grecian vengeance is complete:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19566, line : "Thus is atoned Patroclus' honour'd shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19567, line : "And the short absence of Achilles paid.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19569, line : "These boastful words provoked the raging god;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19570, line : "With fury swells the violated flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19571, line : "What means divine may yet the power employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19572, line : "To check Achilles, and to rescue Troy?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19573, line : "Meanwhile the hero springs in arms, to dare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19574, line : "The great Asteropeus to mortal war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19575, line : "The son of Pelagon, whose lofty line"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19576, line : "Flows from the source of Axius, stream divine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19577, line : "(Fair Peribaea's love the god had crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19578, line : "With all his refluent waters circled round:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19579, line : "On him Achilles rush'd; he fearless stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19580, line : "And shook two spears, advancing from the flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19581, line : "The flood impell'd him, on Pelides' head"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19582, line : "To avenge his waters choked with heaps of dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19583, line : "Near as they drew, Achilles thus began:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19585, line : "\"What art thou, boldest of the race of man?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19586, line : "Who, or from whence? Unhappy is the sire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19587, line : "Whose son encounters our resistless ire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19589, line : "\"O son of Peleus! what avails to trace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19590, line : "(Replied the warrior) our illustrious race?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19591, line : "From rich Paeonia's valleys I command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19592, line : "Arm'd with protended spears, my native band;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19593, line : "Now shines the tenth bright morning since I came"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19594, line : "In aid of Ilion to the fields of fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19595, line : "Axius, who swells with all the neighbouring rills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19596, line : "And wide around the floated region fills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19597, line : "Begot my sire, whose spear much glory won:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19598, line : "Now lift thy arm, and try that hero's son!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19600, line : "Threatening he said: the hostile chiefs advance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19601, line : "At once Asteropeus discharged each lance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19602, line : "(For both his dexterous hands the lance could wield,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19603, line : "One struck, but pierced not, the Vulcanian shield;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19604, line : "One razed Achilles' hand; the spouting blood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19605, line : "Spun forth; in earth the fasten'd weapon stood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19606, line : "Like lightning next the Pelean javelin flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19607, line : "Its erring fury hiss'd along the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19608, line : "Deep in the swelling bank was driven the spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19609, line : "Even to the middle earth; and quiver'd there."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19610, line : "Then from his side the sword Pelides drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19611, line : "And on his foe with double fury flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19612, line : "The foe thrice tugg'd, and shook the rooted wood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19613, line : "Repulsive of his might the weapon stood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19614, line : "The fourth, he tries to break the spear in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19615, line : "Bent as he stands, he tumbles to the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19616, line : "His belly open'd with a ghastly wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19617, line : "The reeking entrails pour upon the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19618, line : "Beneath the hero's feet he panting lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19619, line : "And his eye darkens, and his spirit flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19620, line : "While the proud victor thus triumphing said,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19621, line : "His radiant armour tearing from the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19623, line : "\"So ends thy glory! Such the fate they prove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19624, line : "Who strive presumptuous with the sons of Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19625, line : "Sprung from a river, didst thou boast thy line?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19626, line : "But great Saturnius is the source of mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19627, line : "How durst thou vaunt thy watery progeny?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19628, line : "Of Peleus, Ćacus, and Jove, am I."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19629, line : "The race of these superior far to those,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19630, line : "As he that thunders to the stream that flows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19631, line : "What rivers can, Scamander might have shown;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19632, line : "But Jove he dreads, nor wars against his son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19633, line : "Even Achelous might contend in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19634, line : "And all the roaring billows of the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19635, line : "The eternal ocean, from whose fountains flow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19636, line : "The seas, the rivers, and the springs below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19637, line : "The thundering voice of Jove abhors to hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19638, line : "And in his deep abysses shakes with fear.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19640, line : "He said: then from the bank his javelin tore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19641, line : "And left the breathless warrior in his gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19642, line : "The floating tides the bloody carcase lave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19643, line : "And beat against it, wave succeeding wave;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19644, line : "Till, roll'd between the banks, it lies the food"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19645, line : "Of curling eels, and fishes of the flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19646, line : "All scatter'd round the stream (their mightiest slain)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19647, line : "The amazed Paeonians scour along the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19648, line : "He vents his fury on the flying crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19649, line : "Thrasius, Astyplus, and Mnesus slew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19650, line : "Mydon, Thersilochus, with Ćnius, fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19651, line : "And numbers more his lance had plunged to hell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19652, line : "But from the bottom of his gulfs profound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19653, line : "Scamander spoke; the shores return'd the sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19655, line : "\"O first of mortals! (for the gods are thine)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19656, line : "In valour matchless, and in force divine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19657, line : "If Jove have given thee every Trojan head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19658, line : "'Tis not on me thy rage should heap the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19659, line : "See! my choked streams no more their course can keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19660, line : "Nor roll their wonted tribute to the deep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19661, line : "Turn then, impetuous! from our injured flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19662, line : "Content, thy slaughters could amaze a god.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19664, line : "In human form, confess'd before his eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19665, line : "The river thus; and thus the chief replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19666, line : "\"O sacred stream! thy word we shall obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19667, line : "But not till Troy the destined vengeance pay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19668, line : "Not till within her towers the perjured train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19669, line : "Shall pant, and tremble at our arms again;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19670, line : "Not till proud Hector, guardian of her wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19671, line : "Or stain this lance, or see Achilles fall.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19673, line : "He said; and drove with fury on the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19674, line : "Then to the godhead of the silver bow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19675, line : "The yellow flood began: \"O son of Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19676, line : "Was not the mandate of the sire above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19677, line : "Full and express, that Phoebus should employ"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19678, line : "His sacred arrows in defence of Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19679, line : "And make her conquer, till Hyperion's fall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19680, line : "In awful darkness hide the face of all?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19682, line : "He spoke in vain--The chief without dismay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19683, line : "Ploughs through the boiling surge his desperate way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19684, line : "Then rising in his rage above the shores,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19685, line : "From all his deep the bellowing river roars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19686, line : "Huge heaps of slain disgorges on the coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19687, line : "And round the banks the ghastly dead are toss'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19688, line : "While all before, the billows ranged on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19689, line : "(A watery bulwark,) screen the bands who fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19690, line : "Now bursting on his head with thundering sound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19691, line : "The falling deluge whelms the hero round:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19692, line : "His loaded shield bends to the rushing tide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19693, line : "His feet, upborne, scarce the strong flood divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19694, line : "Sliddering, and staggering. On the border stood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19695, line : "A spreading elm, that overhung the flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19696, line : "He seized a bending bough, his steps to stay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19697, line : "The plant uprooted to his weight gave way.(270)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19698, line : "Heaving the bank, and undermining all;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19699, line : "Loud flash the waters to the rushing fall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19700, line : "Of the thick foliage. The large trunk display'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19701, line : "Bridged the rough flood across: the hero stay'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19702, line : "On this his weight, and raised upon his hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19703, line : "Leap'd from the channel, and regain'd the land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19704, line : "Then blacken'd the wild waves: the murmur rose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19705, line : "The god pursues, a huger billow throws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19706, line : "And bursts the bank, ambitious to destroy"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19707, line : "The man whose fury is the fate of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19708, line : "He like the warlike eagle speeds his pace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19709, line : "(Swiftest and strongest of the aerial race);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19710, line : "Far as a spear can fly, Achilles springs;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19711, line : "At every bound his clanging armour rings:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19712, line : "Now here, now there, he turns on every side,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19713, line : "And winds his course before the following tide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19714, line : "The waves flow after, wheresoe'er he wheels,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19715, line : "And gather fast, and murmur at his heels."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19716, line : "So when a peasant to his garden brings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19717, line : "Soft rills of water from the bubbling springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19718, line : "And calls the floods from high, to bless his bowers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19719, line : "And feed with pregnant streams the plants and flowers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19720, line : "Soon as he clears whate'er their passage stay'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19721, line : "And marks the future current with his spade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19722, line : "Swift o'er the rolling pebbles, down the hills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19723, line : "Louder and louder purl the falling rills;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19724, line : "Before him scattering, they prevent his pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19725, line : "And shine in mazy wanderings o'er the plains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19727, line : "Still flies Achilles, but before his eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19728, line : "Still swift Scamander rolls where'er he flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19729, line : "Not all his speed escapes the rapid floods;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19730, line : "The first of men, but not a match for gods."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19731, line : "Oft as he turn'd the torrent to oppose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19732, line : "And bravely try if all the powers were foes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19733, line : "So oft the surge, in watery mountains spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19734, line : "Beats on his back, or bursts upon his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19735, line : "Yet dauntless still the adverse flood he braves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19736, line : "And still indignant bounds above the waves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19737, line : "Tired by the tides, his knees relax with toil;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19738, line : "Wash'd from beneath him slides the slimy soil;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19739, line : "When thus (his eyes on heaven's expansion thrown)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19740, line : "Forth bursts the hero with an angry groan:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19742, line : "\"Is there no god Achilles to befriend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19743, line : "No power to avert his miserable end?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19744, line : "Prevent, O Jove! this ignominious date,(271)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19745, line : "And make my future life the sport of fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19746, line : "Of all heaven's oracles believed in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19747, line : "But most of Thetis must her son complain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19748, line : "By Phoebus' darts she prophesied my fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19749, line : "In glorious arms before the Trojan wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19750, line : "Oh! had I died in fields of battle warm,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19751, line : "Stretch'd like a hero, by a hero's arm!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19752, line : "Might Hector's spear this dauntless bosom rend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19753, line : "And my swift soul o'ertake my slaughter'd friend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19754, line : "Ah no! Achilles meets a shameful fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19755, line : "Oh how unworthy of the brave and great!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19756, line : "Like some vile swain, whom on a rainy day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19757, line : "Crossing a ford, the torrent sweeps away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19758, line : "An unregarded carcase to the sea.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19760, line : "Neptune and Pallas haste to his relief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19761, line : "And thus in human form address'd the chief:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19762, line : "The power of ocean first: \"Forbear thy fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19763, line : "O son of Peleus! Lo, thy gods appear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19764, line : "Behold! from Jove descending to thy aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19765, line : "Propitious Neptune, and the blue-eyed maid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19766, line : "Stay, and the furious flood shall cease to rave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19767, line : "'Tis not thy fate to glut his angry wave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19768, line : "But thou, the counsel heaven suggests, attend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19769, line : "Nor breathe from combat, nor thy sword suspend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19770, line : "Till Troy receive her flying sons, till all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19771, line : "Her routed squadrons pant behind their wall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19772, line : "Hector alone shall stand his fatal chance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19773, line : "And Hector's blood shall smoke upon thy lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19774, line : "Thine is the glory doom'd.\" Thus spake the gods:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19775, line : "Then swift ascended to the bright abodes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19777, line : "Stung with new ardour, thus by heaven impell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19778, line : "He springs impetuous, and invades the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19779, line : "O'er all the expanded plain the waters spread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19780, line : "Heaved on the bounding billows danced the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19781, line : "Floating 'midst scatter'd arms; while casques of gold"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19782, line : "And turn'd-up bucklers glitter'd as they roll'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19783, line : "High o'er the surging tide, by leaps and bounds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19784, line : "He wades, and mounts; the parted wave resounds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19785, line : "Not a whole river stops the hero's course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19786, line : "While Pallas fills him with immortal force."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19787, line : "With equal rage, indignant Xanthus roars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19788, line : "And lifts his billows, and o'erwhelms his shores."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19790, line : "Then thus to Simois! \"Haste, my brother flood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19791, line : "And check this mortal that controls a god;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19792, line : "Our bravest heroes else shall quit the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19793, line : "And Ilion tumble from her towery height."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19794, line : "Call then thy subject streams, and bid them roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19795, line : "From all thy fountains swell thy watery store,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19796, line : "With broken rocks, and with a load of dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19797, line : "Charge the black surge, and pour it on his head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19798, line : "Mark how resistless through the floods he goes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19799, line : "And boldly bids the warring gods be foes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19800, line : "But nor that force, nor form divine to sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19801, line : "Shall aught avail him, if our rage unite:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19802, line : "Whelm'd under our dark gulfs those arms shall lie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19803, line : "That blaze so dreadful in each Trojan eye;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19804, line : "And deep beneath a sandy mountain hurl'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19805, line : "Immersed remain this terror of the world."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19806, line : "Such ponderous ruin shall confound the place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19807, line : "No Greeks shall e'er his perish'd relics grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19808, line : "No hand his bones shall gather, or inhume;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19809, line : "These his cold rites, and this his watery tomb.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19811, line : "[Illustration: ACHILLES CONTENDING WITH THE RIVERS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19813, line : "ACHILLES CONTENDING WITH THE RIVERS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19816, line : "He said; and on the chief descends amain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19817, line : "Increased with gore, and swelling with the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19818, line : "Then, murmuring from his beds, he boils, he raves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19819, line : "And a foam whitens on the purple waves:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19820, line : "At every step, before Achilles stood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19821, line : "The crimson surge, and deluged him with blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19822, line : "Fear touch'd the queen of heaven: she saw dismay'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19823, line : "She call'd aloud, and summon'd Vulcan's aid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19825, line : "\"Rise to the war! the insulting flood requires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19826, line : "Thy wasteful arm! assemble all thy fires!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19827, line : "While to their aid, by our command enjoin'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19828, line : "Rush the swift eastern and the western wind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19829, line : "These from old ocean at my word shall blow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19830, line : "Pour the red torrent on the watery foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19831, line : "Corses and arms to one bright ruin turn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19832, line : "And hissing rivers to their bottoms burn."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19833, line : "Go, mighty in thy rage! display thy power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19834, line : "Drink the whole flood, the crackling trees devour."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19835, line : "Scorch all the banks! and (till our voice reclaim)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19836, line : "Exert the unwearied furies of the flame!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19838, line : "The power ignipotent her word obeys:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19839, line : "Wide o'er the plain he pours the boundless blaze;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19840, line : "At once consumes the dead, and dries the soil"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19841, line : "And the shrunk waters in their channel boil."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19842, line : "As when autumnal Boreas sweeps the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19843, line : "And instant blows the water'd gardens dry:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19844, line : "So look'd the field, so whiten'd was the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19845, line : "While Vulcan breathed the fiery blast around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19846, line : "Swift on the sedgy reeds the ruin preys;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19847, line : "Along the margin winds the running blaze:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19848, line : "The trees in flaming rows to ashes turn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19849, line : "The flowering lotos and the tamarisk burn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19850, line : "Broad elm, and cypress rising in a spire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19851, line : "The watery willows hiss before the fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19852, line : "Now glow the waves, the fishes pant for breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19853, line : "The eels lie twisting in the pangs of death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19854, line : "Now flounce aloft, now dive the scaly fry,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19855, line : "Or, gasping, turn their bellies to the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19856, line : "At length the river rear'd his languid head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19857, line : "And thus, short-panting, to the god he said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19859, line : "\"Oh Vulcan! oh! what power resists thy might?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19860, line : "I faint, I sink, unequal to the fight--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19861, line : "I yield--Let Ilion fall; if fate decree--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19862, line : "Ah--bend no more thy fiery arms on me!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19864, line : "He ceased; wide conflagration blazing round;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19865, line : "The bubbling waters yield a hissing sound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19866, line : "As when the flames beneath a cauldron rise,(272)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19867, line : "To melt the fat of some rich sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19868, line : "Amid the fierce embrace of circling fires"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19869, line : "The waters foam, the heavy smoke aspires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19870, line : "So boils the imprison'd flood, forbid to flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19871, line : "And choked with vapours feels his bottom glow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19872, line : "To Juno then, imperial queen of air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19873, line : "The burning river sends his earnest prayer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19875, line : "\"Ah why, Saturnia; must thy son engage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19876, line : "Me, only me, with all his wasteful rage?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19877, line : "On other gods his dreadful arm employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19878, line : "For mightier gods assert the cause of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19879, line : "Submissive I desist, if thou command;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19880, line : "But ah! withdraw this all-destroying hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19881, line : "Hear then my solemn oath, to yield to fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19882, line : "Unaided Ilion, and her destined state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19883, line : "Till Greece shall gird her with destructive flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19884, line : "And in one ruin sink the Trojan name.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19886, line : "His warm entreaty touch'd Saturnia's ear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19887, line : "She bade the ignipotent his rage forbear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19888, line : "Recall the flame, nor in a mortal cause"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19889, line : "Infest a god: the obedient flame withdraws:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19890, line : "Again the branching streams begin to spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19891, line : "And soft remurmur in their wonted bed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19893, line : "While these by Juno's will the strife resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19894, line : "The warring gods in fierce contention join:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19895, line : "Rekindling rage each heavenly breast alarms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19896, line : "With horrid clangour shock the ethereal arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19897, line : "Heaven in loud thunder bids the trumpet sound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19898, line : "And wide beneath them groans the rending ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19899, line : "Jove, as his sport, the dreadful scene descries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19900, line : "And views contending gods with careless eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19901, line : "The power of battles lifts his brazen spear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19902, line : "And first assaults the radiant queen of war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19904, line : "\"What moved thy madness, thus to disunite"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19905, line : "Ethereal minds, and mix all heaven in fight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19906, line : "What wonder this, when in thy frantic mood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19907, line : "Thou drovest a mortal to insult a god?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19908, line : "Thy impious hand Tydides' javelin bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19909, line : "And madly bathed it in celestial gore.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19911, line : "He spoke, and smote the long-resounding shield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19912, line : "Which bears Jove's thunder on its dreadful field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19913, line : "The adamantine aegis of her sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19914, line : "That turns the glancing bolt and forked fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19916, line : "Then heaved the goddess in her mighty hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19917, line : "A stone, the limit of the neighbouring land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19918, line : "There fix'd from eldest times; black, craggy, vast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19919, line : "This at the heavenly homicide she cast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19920, line : "Thundering he falls, a mass of monstrous size:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19921, line : "And seven broad acres covers as he lies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19922, line : "The stunning stroke his stubborn nerves unbound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19923, line : "Loud o'er the fields his ringing arms resound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19924, line : "The scornful dame her conquest views with smiles,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19925, line : "And, glorying, thus the prostrate god reviles:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19927, line : "\"Hast thou not yet, insatiate fury! known"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19928, line : "How far Minerva's force transcends thy own?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19929, line : "Juno, whom thou rebellious darest withstand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19930, line : "Corrects thy folly thus by Pallas' hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19931, line : "Thus meets thy broken faith with just disgrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19932, line : "And partial aid to Troy's perfidious race.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19934, line : "The goddess spoke, and turn'd her eyes away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19935, line : "That, beaming round, diffused celestial day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19936, line : "Jove's Cyprian daughter, stooping on the land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19937, line : "Lent to the wounded god her tender hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19938, line : "Slowly he rises, scarcely breathes with pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19939, line : "And, propp'd on her fair arm, forsakes the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19940, line : "This the bright empress of the heavens survey'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19941, line : "And, scoffing, thus to war's victorious maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19943, line : "\"Lo! what an aid on Mars's side is seen!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19944, line : "The smiles' and loves' unconquerable queen!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19945, line : "Mark with what insolence, in open view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19946, line : "She moves: let Pallas, if she dares, pursue.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19948, line : "Minerva smiling heard, the pair o'ertook,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19949, line : "And slightly on her breast the wanton strook:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19950, line : "She, unresisting, fell (her spirits fled);"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19951, line : "On earth together lay the lovers spread."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19952, line : "\"And like these heroes be the fate of all"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19953, line : "(Minerva cries) who guard the Trojan wall!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19954, line : "To Grecian gods such let the Phrygian be,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19955, line : "So dread, so fierce, as Venus is to me;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19956, line : "Then from the lowest stone shall Troy be moved.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19957, line : "Thus she, and Juno with a smile approved."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19959, line : "Meantime, to mix in more than mortal fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19960, line : "The god of ocean dares the god of light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19961, line : "\"What sloth has seized us, when the fields around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19962, line : "Ring with conflicting powers, and heaven returns the sound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19963, line : "Shall, ignominious, we with shame retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19964, line : "No deed perform'd, to our Olympian sire?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19965, line : "Come, prove thy arm! for first the war to wage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19966, line : "Suits not my greatness, or superior age:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19967, line : "Rash as thou art to prop the Trojan throne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19968, line : "(Forgetful of my wrongs, and of thy own,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19969, line : "And guard the race of proud Laomedon!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19970, line : "Hast thou forgot, how, at the monarch's prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19971, line : "We shared the lengthen'd labours of a year?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19972, line : "Troy walls I raised (for such were Jove's commands),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19973, line : "And yon proud bulwarks grew beneath my hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19974, line : "Thy task it was to feed the bellowing droves"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19975, line : "Along fair Ida's vales and pendant groves."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19976, line : "But when the circling seasons in their train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19977, line : "Brought back the grateful day that crown'd our pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19978, line : "With menace stern the fraudful king defied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19979, line : "Our latent godhead, and the prize denied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19980, line : "Mad as he was, he threaten'd servile bands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19981, line : "And doom'd us exiles far in barbarous lands.(273)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19982, line : "Incensed, we heavenward fled with swiftest wing,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19983, line : "And destined vengeance on the perjured king."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19984, line : "Dost thou, for this, afford proud Ilion grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19985, line : "And not, like us, infest the faithless race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19986, line : "Like us, their present, future sons destroy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19987, line : "And from its deep foundations heave their Troy?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19989, line : "Apollo thus: \"To combat for mankind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19990, line : "Ill suits the wisdom of celestial mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19991, line : "For what is man? Calamitous by birth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19992, line : "They owe their life and nourishment to earth;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19993, line : "Like yearly leaves, that now, with beauty crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19994, line : "Smile on the sun; now, wither on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19995, line : "To their own hands commit the frantic scene,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19996, line : "Nor mix immortals in a cause so mean.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19998, line : "Then turns his face, far-beaming heavenly fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 19999, line : "And from the senior power submiss retires:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20000, line : "Him thus retreating, Artemis upbraids,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20001, line : "The quiver'd huntress of the sylvan shades:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20003, line : "\"And is it thus the youthful Phoebus flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20004, line : "And yields to ocean's hoary sire the prize?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20005, line : "How vain that martial pomp, and dreadful show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20006, line : "Of pointed arrows and the silver bow!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20007, line : "Now boast no more in yon celestial bower,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20008, line : "Thy force can match the great earth-shaking power.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20010, line : "Silent he heard the queen of woods upbraid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20011, line : "Not so Saturnia bore the vaunting maid:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20012, line : "But furious thus: \"What insolence has driven"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20013, line : "Thy pride to face the majesty of heaven?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20014, line : "What though by Jove the female plague design'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20015, line : "Fierce to the feeble race of womankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20016, line : "The wretched matron feels thy piercing dart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20017, line : "Thy sex's tyrant, with a tiger's heart?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20018, line : "What though tremendous in the woodland chase"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20019, line : "Thy certain arrows pierce the savage race?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20020, line : "How dares thy rashness on the powers divine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20021, line : "Employ those arms, or match thy force with mine?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20022, line : "Learn hence, no more unequal war to wage--\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20023, line : "She said, and seized her wrists with eager rage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20024, line : "These in her left hand lock'd, her right untied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20025, line : "The bow, the quiver, and its plumy pride."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20026, line : "About her temples flies the busy bow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20027, line : "Now here, now there, she winds her from the blow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20028, line : "The scattering arrows, rattling from the case,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20029, line : "Drop round, and idly mark the dusty place."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20030, line : "Swift from the field the baffled huntress flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20031, line : "And scarce restrains the torrent in her eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20032, line : "So, when the falcon wings her way above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20033, line : "To the cleft cavern speeds the gentle dove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20034, line : "(Not fated yet to die;) there safe retreats,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20035, line : "Yet still her heart against the marble beats."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20037, line : "To her Latona hastes with tender care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20038, line : "Whom Hermes viewing, thus declines the war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20039, line : "\"How shall I face the dame, who gives delight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20040, line : "To him whose thunders blacken heaven with night?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20041, line : "Go, matchless goddess! triumph in the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20042, line : "And boast my conquest, while I yield the prize.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20044, line : "He spoke; and pass'd: Latona, stooping low,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20045, line : "Collects the scatter'd shafts and fallen bow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20046, line : "That, glittering on the dust, lay here and there"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20047, line : "Dishonour'd relics of Diana's war:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20048, line : "Then swift pursued her to her blest abode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20049, line : "Where, all confused, she sought the sovereign god;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20050, line : "Weeping, she grasp'd his knees: the ambrosial vest"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20051, line : "Shook with her sighs, and panted on her breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20053, line : "The sire superior smiled, and bade her show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20054, line : "What heavenly hand had caused his daughter's woe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20055, line : "Abash'd, she names his own imperial spouse;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20056, line : "And the pale crescent fades upon her brows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20058, line : "Thus they above: while, swiftly gliding down,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20059, line : "Apollo enters Ilion's sacred town;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20060, line : "The guardian-god now trembled for her wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20061, line : "And fear'd the Greeks, though fate forbade her fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20062, line : "Back to Olympus, from the war's alarms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20063, line : "Return the shining bands of gods in arms;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20064, line : "Some proud in triumph, some with rage on fire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20065, line : "And take their thrones around the ethereal sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20067, line : "Through blood, through death, Achilles still proceeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20068, line : "O'er slaughter'd heroes, and o'er rolling steeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20069, line : "As when avenging flames with fury driven"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20070, line : "On guilty towns exert the wrath of heaven;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20071, line : "The pale inhabitants, some fall, some fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20072, line : "And the red vapours purple all the sky:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20073, line : "So raged Achilles: death and dire dismay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20074, line : "And toils, and terrors, fill'd the dreadful day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20076, line : "High on a turret hoary Priam stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20077, line : "And marks the waste of his destructive hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20078, line : "Views, from his arm, the Trojans' scatter'd flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20079, line : "And the near hero rising on his sight!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20080, line : "No stop, no check, no aid! With feeble pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20081, line : "And settled sorrow on his aged face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20082, line : "Fast as he could, he sighing quits the walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20083, line : "And thus descending, on the guards he calls:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20085, line : "\"You to whose care our city-gates belong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20086, line : "Set wide your portals to the flying throng:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20087, line : "For lo! he comes, with unresisted sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20088, line : "He comes, and desolation marks his way!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20089, line : "But when within the walls our troops take breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20090, line : "Lock fast the brazen bars, and shut out death.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20091, line : "Thus charged the reverend monarch: wide were flung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20092, line : "The opening folds; the sounding hinges rung."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20093, line : "Phoebus rush'd forth, the flying bands to meet;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20094, line : "Struck slaughter back, and cover'd the retreat,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20095, line : "On heaps the Trojans crowd to gain the gate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20096, line : "And gladsome see their last escape from fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20097, line : "Thither, all parch'd with thirst, a heartless train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20098, line : "Hoary with dust, they beat the hollow plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20099, line : "And gasping, panting, fainting, labour on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20100, line : "With heavier strides, that lengthen toward the town."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20101, line : "Enraged Achilles follows with his spear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20102, line : "Wild with revenge, insatiable of war."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20104, line : "Then had the Greeks eternal praise acquired,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20105, line : "And Troy inglorious to her walls retired;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20106, line : "But he, the god who darts ethereal flame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20107, line : "Shot down to save her, and redeem her fame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20108, line : "To young Agenor force divine he gave;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20109, line : "(Antenor's offspring, haughty, bold, and brave;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20110, line : "In aid of him, beside the beech he sate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20111, line : "And wrapt in clouds, restrain'd the hand of fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20112, line : "When now the generous youth Achilles spies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20113, line : "Thick beats his heart, the troubled motions rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20114, line : "(So, ere a storm, the waters heave and roll.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20115, line : "He stops, and questions thus his mighty soul;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20117, line : "\"What, shall I fly this terror of the plain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20118, line : "Like others fly, and be like others slain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20119, line : "Vain hope! to shun him by the self-same road"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20120, line : "Yon line of slaughter'd Trojans lately trod."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20121, line : "No: with the common heap I scorn to fall--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20122, line : "What if they pass'd me to the Trojan wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20123, line : "While I decline to yonder path, that leads"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20124, line : "To Ida's forests and surrounding shades?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20125, line : "So may I reach, conceal'd, the cooling flood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20126, line : "From my tired body wash the dirt and blood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20127, line : "As soon as night her dusky veil extends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20128, line : "Return in safety to my Trojan friends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20129, line : "What if?--But wherefore all this vain debate?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20130, line : "Stand I to doubt, within the reach of fate?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20131, line : "Even now perhaps, ere yet I turn the wall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20132, line : "The fierce Achilles sees me, and I fall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20133, line : "Such is his swiftness, 'tis in vain to fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20134, line : "And such his valour, that who stands must die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20135, line : "Howe'er 'tis better, fighting for the state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20136, line : "Here, and in public view, to meet my fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20137, line : "Yet sure he too is mortal; he may feel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20138, line : "(Like all the sons of earth) the force of steel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20139, line : "One only soul informs that dreadful frame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20140, line : "And Jove's sole favour gives him all his fame.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20142, line : "He said, and stood, collected, in his might;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20143, line : "And all his beating bosom claim'd the fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20144, line : "So from some deep-grown wood a panther starts,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20145, line : "Roused from his thicket by a storm of darts:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20146, line : "Untaught to fear or fly, he hears the sounds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20147, line : "Of shouting hunters, and of clamorous hounds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20148, line : "Though struck, though wounded, scarce perceives the pain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20149, line : "And the barb'd javelin stings his breast in vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20150, line : "On their whole war, untamed, the savage flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20151, line : "And tears his hunter, or beneath him dies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20152, line : "Not less resolved, Antenor's valiant heir"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20153, line : "Confronts Achilles, and awaits the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20154, line : "Disdainful of retreat: high held before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20155, line : "His shield (a broad circumference) he bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20156, line : "Then graceful as he stood, in act to throw"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20157, line : "The lifted javelin, thus bespoke the foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20159, line : "\"How proud Achilles glories in his fame!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20160, line : "And hopes this day to sink the Trojan name"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20161, line : "Beneath her ruins! Know, that hope is vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20162, line : "A thousand woes, a thousand toils remain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20163, line : "Parents and children our just arms employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20164, line : "And strong and many are the sons of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20165, line : "Great as thou art, even thou may'st stain with gore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20166, line : "These Phrygian fields, and press a foreign shore.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20168, line : "He said: with matchless force the javelin flung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20169, line : "Smote on his knee; the hollow cuishes rung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20170, line : "Beneath the pointed steel; but safe from harms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20171, line : "He stands impassive in the ethereal arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20172, line : "Then fiercely rushing on the daring foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20173, line : "His lifted arm prepares the fatal blow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20174, line : "But, jealous of his fame, Apollo shrouds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20175, line : "The god-like Trojan in a veil of clouds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20176, line : "Safe from pursuit, and shut from mortal view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20177, line : "Dismiss'd with fame, the favoured youth withdrew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20178, line : "Meanwhile the god, to cover their escape,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20179, line : "Assumes Agenor's habit, voice and shape,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20180, line : "Flies from the furious chief in this disguise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20181, line : "The furious chief still follows where he flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20182, line : "Now o'er the fields they stretch with lengthen'd strides,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20183, line : "Now urge the course where swift Scamander glides:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20184, line : "The god, now distant scarce a stride before,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20185, line : "Tempts his pursuit, and wheels about the shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20186, line : "While all the flying troops their speed employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20187, line : "And pour on heaps into the walls of Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20188, line : "No stop, no stay; no thought to ask, or tell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20189, line : "Who 'scaped by flight, or who by battle fell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20190, line : "'Twas tumult all, and violence of flight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20191, line : "And sudden joy confused, and mix'd affright."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20192, line : "Pale Troy against Achilles shuts her gate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20193, line : "And nations breathe, deliver'd from their fate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20199, line : "BOOK XXII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20202, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20204, line : "THE DEATH OF HECTOR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20206, line : "The Trojans being safe within the walls, Hector only stays to oppose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20207, line : "Achilles. Priam is struck at his approach, and tries to persuade his son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20208, line : "to re-enter the town. Hecuba joins her entreaties, but in vain. Hector"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20209, line : "consults within himself what measures to take; but at the advance of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20210, line : "Achilles, his resolution fails him, and he flies. Achilles pursues him"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20211, line : "thrice round the walls of Troy. The gods debate concerning the fate of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20212, line : "Hector; at length Minerva descends to the aid of Achilles. She deludes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20213, line : "Hector in the shape of Deiphobus; he stands the combat, and is slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20214, line : "Achilles drags the dead body at his chariot in the sight of Priam and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20215, line : "Hecuba. Their lamentations, tears, and despair. Their cries reach the ears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20216, line : "of Andromache, who, ignorant of this, was retired into the inner part of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20217, line : "the palace: she mounts up to the walls, and beholds her dead husband. She"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20218, line : "swoons at the spectacle. Her excess of grief and lamentation."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20220, line : "The thirtieth day still continues. The scene lies under the walls, and on"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20221, line : "the battlements of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20223, line : "Thus to their bulwarks, smit with panic fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20224, line : "The herded Ilians rush like driven deer:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20225, line : "There safe they wipe the briny drops away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20226, line : "And drown in bowls the labours of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20227, line : "Close to the walls, advancing o'er the fields"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20228, line : "Beneath one roof of well-compacted shields,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20229, line : "March, bending on, the Greeks' embodied powers,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20230, line : "Far stretching in the shade of Trojan towers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20231, line : "Great Hector singly stay'd: chain'd down by fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20232, line : "There fix'd he stood before the Scaean gate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20233, line : "Still his bold arms determined to employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20234, line : "The guardian still of long-defended Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20236, line : "Apollo now to tired Achilles turns:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20237, line : "(The power confess'd in all his glory burns:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20238, line : "\"And what (he cries) has Peleus' son in view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20239, line : "With mortal speed a godhead to pursue?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20240, line : "For not to thee to know the gods is given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20241, line : "Unskill'd to trace the latent marks of heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20242, line : "What boots thee now, that Troy forsook the plain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20243, line : "Vain thy past labour, and thy present vain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20244, line : "Safe in their walls are now her troops bestow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20245, line : "While here thy frantic rage attacks a god.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20247, line : "The chief incensed--\"Too partial god of day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20248, line : "To check my conquests in the middle way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20249, line : "How few in Ilion else had refuge found!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20250, line : "What gasping numbers now had bit the ground!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20251, line : "Thou robb'st me of a glory justly mine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20252, line : "Powerful of godhead, and of fraud divine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20253, line : "Mean fame, alas! for one of heavenly strain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20254, line : "To cheat a mortal who repines in vain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20256, line : "Then to the city, terrible and strong,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20257, line : "With high and haughty steps he tower'd along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20258, line : "So the proud courser, victor of the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20259, line : "To the near goal with double ardour flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20260, line : "Him, as he blazing shot across the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20261, line : "The careful eyes of Priam first beheld."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20262, line : "Not half so dreadful rises to the sight,(274)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20263, line : "Through the thick gloom of some tempestuous night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20264, line : "Orion's dog (the year when autumn weighs),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20265, line : "And o'er the feebler stars exerts his rays;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20266, line : "Terrific glory! for his burning breath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20267, line : "Taints the red air with fevers, plagues, and death."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20268, line : "So flamed his fiery mail. Then wept the sage:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20269, line : "He strikes his reverend head, now white with age;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20270, line : "He lifts his wither'd arms; obtests the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20271, line : "He calls his much-loved son with feeble cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20272, line : "The son, resolved Achilles' force to dare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20273, line : "Full at the Scaean gates expects the war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20274, line : "While the sad father on the rampart stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20275, line : "And thus adjures him with extended hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20277, line : "\"Ah stay not, stay not! guardless and alone;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20278, line : "Hector! my loved, my dearest, bravest son!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20279, line : "Methinks already I behold thee slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20280, line : "And stretch'd beneath that fury of the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20281, line : "Implacable Achilles! might'st thou be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20282, line : "To all the gods no dearer than to me!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20283, line : "Thee, vultures wild should scatter round the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20284, line : "And bloody dogs grow fiercer from thy gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20285, line : "How many valiant sons I late enjoy'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20286, line : "Valiant in vain! by thy cursed arm destroy'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20287, line : "Or, worse than slaughtered, sold in distant isles"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20288, line : "To shameful bondage, and unworthy toils."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20289, line : "Two, while I speak, my eyes in vain explore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20290, line : "Two from one mother sprung, my Polydore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20291, line : "And loved Lycaon; now perhaps no more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20292, line : "Oh! if in yonder hostile camp they live,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20293, line : "What heaps of gold, what treasures would I give!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20294, line : "(Their grandsire's wealth, by right of birth their own,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20295, line : "Consign'd his daughter with Lelegia's throne:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20296, line : "But if (which Heaven forbid) already lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20297, line : "All pale they wander on the Stygian coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20298, line : "What sorrows then must their sad mother know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20299, line : "What anguish I? unutterable woe!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20300, line : "Yet less that anguish, less to her, to me,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20301, line : "Less to all Troy, if not deprived of thee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20302, line : "Yet shun Achilles! enter yet the wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20303, line : "And spare thyself, thy father, spare us all!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20304, line : "Save thy dear life; or, if a soul so brave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20305, line : "Neglect that thought, thy dearer glory save."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20306, line : "Pity, while yet I live, these silver hairs;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20307, line : "While yet thy father feels the woes he bears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20308, line : "Yet cursed with sense! a wretch, whom in his rage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20309, line : "(All trembling on the verge of helpless age)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20310, line : "Great Jove has placed, sad spectacle of pain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20311, line : "The bitter dregs of fortune's cup to drain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20312, line : "To fill with scenes of death his closing eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20313, line : "And number all his days by miseries!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20314, line : "My heroes slain, my bridal bed o'erturn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20315, line : "My daughters ravish'd, and my city burn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20316, line : "My bleeding infants dash'd against the floor;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20317, line : "These I have yet to see, perhaps yet more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20318, line : "Perhaps even I, reserved by angry fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20319, line : "The last sad relic of my ruin'd state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20320, line : "(Dire pomp of sovereign wretchedness!) must fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20321, line : "And stain the pavement of my regal hall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20322, line : "Where famish'd dogs, late guardians of my door,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20323, line : "Shall lick their mangled master's spatter'd gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20324, line : "Yet for my sons I thank ye, gods! 'tis well;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20325, line : "Well have they perish'd, for in fight they fell."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20326, line : "Who dies in youth and vigour, dies the best,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20327, line : "Struck through with wounds, all honest on the breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20328, line : "But when the fates, in fulness of their rage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20329, line : "Spurn the hoar head of unresisting age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20330, line : "In dust the reverend lineaments deform,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20331, line : "And pour to dogs the life-blood scarcely warm:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20332, line : "This, this is misery! the last, the worse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20333, line : "That man can feel! man, fated to be cursed!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20335, line : "He said, and acting what no words could say,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20336, line : "Rent from his head the silver locks away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20337, line : "With him the mournful mother bears a part;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20338, line : "Yet all her sorrows turn not Hector's heart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20339, line : "The zone unbraced, her bosom she display'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20340, line : "And thus, fast-falling the salt tears, she said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20342, line : "\"Have mercy on me, O my son! revere"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20343, line : "The words of age; attend a parent's prayer!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20344, line : "If ever thee in these fond arms I press'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20345, line : "Or still'd thy infant clamours at this breast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20346, line : "Ah do not thus our helpless years forego,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20347, line : "But, by our walls secured, repel the foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20348, line : "Against his rage if singly thou proceed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20349, line : "Should'st thou, (but Heaven avert it!) should'st thou bleed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20350, line : "Nor must thy corse lie honour'd on the bier,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20351, line : "Nor spouse, nor mother, grace thee with a tear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20352, line : "Far from our pious rites those dear remains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20353, line : "Must feast the vultures on the naked plains.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20355, line : "So they, while down their cheeks the torrents roll;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20356, line : "But fix'd remains the purpose of his soul;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20357, line : "Resolved he stands, and with a fiery glance"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20358, line : "Expects the hero's terrible advance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20359, line : "So, roll'd up in his den, the swelling snake"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20360, line : "Beholds the traveller approach the brake;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20361, line : "When fed with noxious herbs his turgid veins"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20362, line : "Have gather'd half the poisons of the plains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20363, line : "He burns, he stiffens with collected ire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20364, line : "And his red eyeballs glare with living fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20365, line : "Beneath a turret, on his shield reclined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20366, line : "He stood, and question'd thus his mighty mind:(275)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20368, line : "\"Where lies my way? to enter in the wall?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20369, line : "Honour and shame the ungenerous thought recall:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20370, line : "Shall proud Polydamas before the gate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20371, line : "Proclaim, his counsels are obey'd too late,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20372, line : "Which timely follow'd but the former night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20373, line : "What numbers had been saved by Hector's flight?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20374, line : "That wise advice rejected with disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20375, line : "I feel my folly in my people slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20376, line : "Methinks my suffering country's voice I hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20377, line : "But most her worthless sons insult my ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20378, line : "On my rash courage charge the chance of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20379, line : "And blame those virtues which they cannot share."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20380, line : "No--if I e'er return, return I must"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20381, line : "Glorious, my country's terror laid in dust:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20382, line : "Or if I perish, let her see me fall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20383, line : "In field at least, and fighting for her wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20384, line : "And yet suppose these measures I forego,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20385, line : "Approach unarm'd, and parley with the foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20386, line : "The warrior-shield, the helm, and lance, lay down."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20387, line : "And treat on terms of peace to save the town:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20388, line : "The wife withheld, the treasure ill-detain'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20389, line : "(Cause of the war, and grievance of the land)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20390, line : "With honourable justice to restore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20391, line : "And add half Ilion's yet remaining store,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20392, line : "Which Troy shall, sworn, produce; that injured Greece"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20393, line : "May share our wealth, and leave our walls in peace."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20394, line : "But why this thought? Unarm'd if I should go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20395, line : "What hope of mercy from this vengeful foe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20396, line : "But woman-like to fall, and fall without a blow?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20397, line : "We greet not here, as man conversing man,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20398, line : "Met at an oak, or journeying o'er a plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20399, line : "No season now for calm familiar talk,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20400, line : "Like youths and maidens in an evening walk:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20401, line : "War is our business, but to whom is given"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20402, line : "To die, or triumph, that, determine Heaven!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20404, line : "Thus pondering, like a god the Greek drew nigh;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20405, line : "His dreadful plumage nodded from on high;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20406, line : "The Pelian javelin, in his better hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20407, line : "Shot trembling rays that glitter'd o'er the land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20408, line : "And on his breast the beamy splendour shone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20409, line : "Like Jove's own lightning, or the rising sun."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20410, line : "As Hector sees, unusual terrors rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20411, line : "Struck by some god, he fears, recedes, and flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20412, line : "He leaves the gates, he leaves the wall behind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20413, line : "Achilles follows like the winged wind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20414, line : "Thus at the panting dove a falcon flies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20415, line : "(The swiftest racer of the liquid skies),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20416, line : "Just when he holds, or thinks he holds his prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20417, line : "Obliquely wheeling through the aerial way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20418, line : "With open beak and shrilling cries he springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20419, line : "And aims his claws, and shoots upon his wings:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20420, line : "No less fore-right the rapid chase they held,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20421, line : "One urged by fury, one by fear impell'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20422, line : "Now circling round the walls their course maintain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20423, line : "Where the high watch-tower overlooks the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20424, line : "Now where the fig-trees spread their umbrage broad,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20425, line : "(A wider compass,) smoke along the road."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20426, line : "Next by Scamander's double source they bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20427, line : "Where two famed fountains burst the parted ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20428, line : "This hot through scorching clefts is seen to rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20429, line : "With exhalations steaming to the skies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20430, line : "That the green banks in summer's heat o'erflows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20431, line : "Like crystal clear, and cold as winter snows:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20432, line : "Each gushing fount a marble cistern fills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20433, line : "Whose polish'd bed receives the falling rills;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20434, line : "Where Trojan dames (ere yet alarm'd by Greece)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20435, line : "Wash'd their fair garments in the days of peace.(276)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20436, line : "By these they pass'd, one chasing, one in flight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20437, line : "(The mighty fled, pursued by stronger might:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20438, line : "Swift was the course; no vulgar prize they play,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20439, line : "No vulgar victim must reward the day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20440, line : "(Such as in races crown the speedy strife:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20441, line : "The prize contended was great Hector's life."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20442, line : "As when some hero's funerals are decreed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20443, line : "In grateful honour of the mighty dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20444, line : "Where high rewards the vigorous youth inflame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20445, line : "(Some golden tripod, or some lovely dame)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20446, line : "The panting coursers swiftly turn the goal,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20447, line : "And with them turns the raised spectator's soul:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20448, line : "Thus three times round the Trojan wall they fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20449, line : "The gazing gods lean forward from the sky;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20450, line : "To whom, while eager on the chase they look,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20451, line : "The sire of mortals and immortals spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20453, line : "\"Unworthy sight! the man beloved of heaven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20454, line : "Behold, inglorious round yon city driven!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20455, line : "My heart partakes the generous Hector's pain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20456, line : "Hector, whose zeal whole hecatombs has slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20457, line : "Whose grateful fumes the gods received with joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20458, line : "From Ida's summits, and the towers of Troy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20459, line : "Now see him flying; to his fears resign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20460, line : "And fate, and fierce Achilles, close behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20461, line : "Consult, ye powers! ('tis worthy your debate)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20462, line : "Whether to snatch him from impending fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20463, line : "Or let him bear, by stern Pelides slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20464, line : "(Good as he is) the lot imposed on man.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20466, line : "Then Pallas thus: \"Shall he whose vengeance forms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20467, line : "The forky bolt, and blackens heaven with storms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20468, line : "Shall he prolong one Trojan's forfeit breath?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20469, line : "A man, a mortal, pre-ordain'd to death!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20470, line : "And will no murmurs fill the courts above?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20471, line : "No gods indignant blame their partial Jove?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20473, line : "\"Go then (return'd the sire) without delay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20474, line : "Exert thy will: I give the Fates their way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20475, line : "Swift at the mandate pleased Tritonia flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20476, line : "And stoops impetuous from the cleaving skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20478, line : "As through the forest, o'er the vale and lawn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20479, line : "The well-breath'd beagle drives the flying fawn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20480, line : "In vain he tries the covert of the brakes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20481, line : "Or deep beneath the trembling thicket shakes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20482, line : "Sure of the vapour in the tainted dews,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20483, line : "The certain hound his various maze pursues."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20484, line : "Thus step by step, where'er the Trojan wheel'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20485, line : "There swift Achilles compass'd round the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20486, line : "Oft as to reach the Dardan gates he bends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20487, line : "And hopes the assistance of his pitying friends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20488, line : "(Whose showering arrows, as he coursed below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20489, line : "From the high turrets might oppress the foe,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20490, line : "So oft Achilles turns him to the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20491, line : "He eyes the city, but he eyes in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20492, line : "As men in slumbers seem with speedy pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20493, line : "One to pursue, and one to lead the chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20494, line : "Their sinking limbs the fancied course forsake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20495, line : "Nor this can fly, nor that can overtake:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20496, line : "No less the labouring heroes pant and strain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20497, line : "While that but flies, and this pursues in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20499, line : "What god, O muse, assisted Hector's force"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20500, line : "With fate itself so long to hold the course?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20501, line : "Phoebus it was; who, in his latest hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20502, line : "Endued his knees with strength, his nerves with power:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20503, line : "And great Achilles, lest some Greek's advance"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20504, line : "Should snatch the glory from his lifted lance,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20505, line : "Sign'd to the troops to yield his foe the way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20506, line : "And leave untouch'd the honours of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20508, line : "Jove lifts the golden balances, that show"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20509, line : "The fates of mortal men, and things below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20510, line : "Here each contending hero's lot he tries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20511, line : "And weighs, with equal hand, their destinies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20512, line : "Low sinks the scale surcharged with Hector's fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20513, line : "Heavy with death it sinks, and hell receives the weight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20515, line : "Then Phoebus left him. Fierce Minerva flies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20516, line : "To stern Pelides, and triumphing, cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20517, line : "\"O loved of Jove! this day our labours cease,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20518, line : "And conquest blazes with full beams on Greece."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20519, line : "Great Hector falls; that Hector famed so far,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20520, line : "Drunk with renown, insatiable of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20521, line : "Falls by thy hand, and mine! nor force, nor flight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20522, line : "Shall more avail him, nor his god of light."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20523, line : "See, where in vain he supplicates above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20524, line : "Roll'd at the feet of unrelenting Jove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20525, line : "Rest here: myself will lead the Trojan on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20526, line : "And urge to meet the fate he cannot shun.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20528, line : "Her voice divine the chief with joyful mind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20529, line : "Obey'd; and rested, on his lance reclined"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20530, line : "While like Deiphobus the martial dame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20531, line : "(Her face, her gesture, and her arms the same),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20532, line : "In show an aid, by hapless Hector's side"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20533, line : "Approach'd, and greets him thus with voice belied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20535, line : "\"Too long, O Hector! have I borne the sight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20536, line : "Of this distress, and sorrow'd in thy flight:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20537, line : "It fits us now a noble stand to make,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20538, line : "And here, as brothers, equal fates partake.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20540, line : "Then he: \"O prince! allied in blood and fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20541, line : "Dearer than all that own a brother's name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20542, line : "Of all that Hecuba to Priam bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20543, line : "Long tried, long loved: much loved, but honoured more!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20544, line : "Since you, of all our numerous race alone"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20545, line : "Defend my life, regardless of your own.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20547, line : "Again the goddess: \"Much my father's prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20548, line : "And much my mother's, press'd me to forbear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20549, line : "My friends embraced my knees, adjured my stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20550, line : "But stronger love impell'd, and I obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20551, line : "Come then, the glorious conflict let us try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20552, line : "Let the steel sparkle, and the javelin fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20553, line : "Or let us stretch Achilles on the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20554, line : "Or to his arm our bloody trophies yield.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20556, line : "Fraudful she said; then swiftly march'd before:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20557, line : "The Dardan hero shuns his foe no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20558, line : "Sternly they met. The silence Hector broke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20559, line : "His dreadful plumage nodded as he spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20561, line : "\"Enough, O son of Peleus! Troy has view'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20562, line : "Her walls thrice circled, and her chief pursued."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20563, line : "But now some god within me bids me try"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20564, line : "Thine, or my fate: I kill thee, or I die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20565, line : "Yet on the verge of battle let us stay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20566, line : "And for a moment's space suspend the day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20567, line : "Let Heaven's high powers be call'd to arbitrate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20568, line : "The just conditions of this stern debate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20569, line : "(Eternal witnesses of all below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20570, line : "And faithful guardians of the treasured vow!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20571, line : "To them I swear; if, victor in the strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20572, line : "Jove by these hands shall shed thy noble life,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20573, line : "No vile dishonour shall thy corse pursue;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20574, line : "Stripp'd of its arms alone (the conqueror's due)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20575, line : "The rest to Greece uninjured I'll restore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20576, line : "Now plight thy mutual oath, I ask no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20578, line : "\"Talk not of oaths (the dreadful chief replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20579, line : "While anger flash'd from his disdainful eyes),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20580, line : "Detested as thou art, and ought to be,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20581, line : "Nor oath nor pact Achilles plights with thee:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20582, line : "Such pacts as lambs and rabid wolves combine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20583, line : "Such leagues as men and furious lions join,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20584, line : "To such I call the gods! one constant state"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20585, line : "Of lasting rancour and eternal hate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20586, line : "No thought but rage, and never-ceasing strife,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20587, line : "Till death extinguish rage, and thought, and life."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20588, line : "Rouse then thy forces this important hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20589, line : "Collect thy soul, and call forth all thy power."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20590, line : "No further subterfuge, no further chance;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20591, line : "'Tis Pallas, Pallas gives thee to my lance."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20592, line : "Each Grecian ghost, by thee deprived of breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20593, line : "Now hovers round, and calls thee to thy death.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20595, line : "He spoke, and launch'd his javelin at the foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20596, line : "But Hector shunn'd the meditated blow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20597, line : "He stoop'd, while o'er his head the flying spear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20598, line : "Sang innocent, and spent its force in air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20599, line : "Minerva watch'd it falling on the land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20600, line : "Then drew, and gave to great Achilles' hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20601, line : "Unseen of Hector, who, elate with joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20602, line : "Now shakes his lance, and braves the dread of Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20604, line : "\"The life you boasted to that javelin given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20605, line : "Prince! you have miss'd. My fate depends on Heaven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20606, line : "To thee, presumptuous as thou art, unknown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20607, line : "Or what must prove my fortune, or thy own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20608, line : "Boasting is but an art, our fears to blind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20609, line : "And with false terrors sink another's mind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20610, line : "But know, whatever fate I am to try,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20611, line : "By no dishonest wound shall Hector die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20612, line : "I shall not fall a fugitive at least,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20613, line : "My soul shall bravely issue from my breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20614, line : "But first, try thou my arm; and may this dart"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20615, line : "End all my country's woes, deep buried in thy heart.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20617, line : "The weapon flew, its course unerring held,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20618, line : "Unerring, but the heavenly shield repell'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20619, line : "The mortal dart; resulting with a bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20620, line : "From off the ringing orb, it struck the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20621, line : "Hector beheld his javelin fall in vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20622, line : "Nor other lance, nor other hope remain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20623, line : "He calls Deiphobus, demands a spear--"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20624, line : "In vain, for no Deiphobus was there."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20625, line : "All comfortless he stands: then, with a sigh;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20626, line : "\"'Tis so--Heaven wills it, and my hour is nigh!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20627, line : "I deem'd Deiphobus had heard my call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20628, line : "But he secure lies guarded in the wall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20629, line : "A god deceived me; Pallas, 'twas thy deed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20630, line : "Death and black fate approach! 'tis I must bleed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20631, line : "No refuge now, no succour from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20632, line : "Great Jove deserts me, and the son of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20633, line : "Propitious once, and kind! Then welcome fate!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20634, line : "'Tis true I perish, yet I perish great:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20635, line : "Yet in a mighty deed I shall expire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20636, line : "Let future ages hear it, and admire!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20638, line : "Fierce, at the word, his weighty sword he drew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20639, line : "And, all collected, on Achilles flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20640, line : "So Jove's bold bird, high balanced in the air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20641, line : "Stoops from the clouds to truss the quivering hare."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20642, line : "Nor less Achilles his fierce soul prepares:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20643, line : "Before his breast the flaming shield he bears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20644, line : "Refulgent orb! above his fourfold cone"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20645, line : "The gilded horse-hair sparkled in the sun."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20646, line : "Nodding at every step: (Vulcanian frame!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20647, line : "And as he moved, his figure seem'd on flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20648, line : "As radiant Hesper shines with keener light,(277)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20649, line : "Far-beaming o'er the silver host of night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20650, line : "When all the starry train emblaze the sphere:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20651, line : "So shone the point of great Achilles' spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20652, line : "In his right hand he waves the weapon round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20653, line : "Eyes the whole man, and meditates the wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20654, line : "But the rich mail Patroclus lately wore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20655, line : "Securely cased the warrior's body o'er."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20656, line : "One space at length he spies, to let in fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20657, line : "Where 'twixt the neck and throat the jointed plate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20658, line : "Gave entrance: through that penetrable part"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20659, line : "Furious he drove the well-directed dart:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20660, line : "Nor pierced the windpipe yet, nor took the power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20661, line : "Of speech, unhappy! from thy dying hour."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20662, line : "Prone on the field the bleeding warrior lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20663, line : "While, thus triumphing, stern Achilles cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20665, line : "\"At last is Hector stretch'd upon the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20666, line : "Who fear'd no vengeance for Patroclus slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20667, line : "Then, prince! you should have fear'd, what now you feel;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20668, line : "Achilles absent was Achilles still:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20669, line : "Yet a short space the great avenger stayed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20670, line : "Then low in dust thy strength and glory laid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20671, line : "Peaceful he sleeps, with all our rites adorn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20672, line : "For ever honour'd, and for ever mourn'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20673, line : "While cast to all the rage of hostile power,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20674, line : "Thee birds shall mangle, and the gods devour.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20676, line : "Then Hector, fainting at the approach of death:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20677, line : "\"By thy own soul! by those who gave thee breath!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20678, line : "By all the sacred prevalence of prayer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20679, line : "Ah, leave me not for Grecian dogs to tear!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20680, line : "The common rites of sepulture bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20681, line : "To soothe a father's and a mother's woe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20682, line : "Let their large gifts procure an urn at least,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20683, line : "And Hector's ashes in his country rest.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20685, line : "\"No, wretch accursed! relentless he replies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20686, line : "(Flames, as he spoke, shot flashing from his eyes;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20687, line : "Not those who gave me breath should bid me spare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20688, line : "Nor all the sacred prevalence of prayer."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20689, line : "Could I myself the bloody banquet join!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20690, line : "No--to the dogs that carcase I resign."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20691, line : "Should Troy, to bribe me, bring forth all her store,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20692, line : "And giving thousands, offer thousands more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20693, line : "Should Dardan Priam, and his weeping dame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20694, line : "Drain their whole realm to buy one funeral flame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20695, line : "Their Hector on the pile they should not see,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20696, line : "Nor rob the vultures of one limb of thee.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20698, line : "Then thus the chief his dying accents drew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20699, line : "\"Thy rage, implacable! too well I knew:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20700, line : "The Furies that relentless breast have steel'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20701, line : "And cursed thee with a heart that cannot yield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20702, line : "Yet think, a day will come, when fate's decree"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20703, line : "And angry gods shall wreak this wrong on thee;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20704, line : "Phoebus and Paris shall avenge my fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20705, line : "And stretch thee here before the Scaean gate.\"(278)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20707, line : "He ceased. The Fates suppress'd his labouring breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20708, line : "And his eyes stiffen'd at the hand of death;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20709, line : "To the dark realm the spirit wings its way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20710, line : "(The manly body left a load of clay,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20711, line : "And plaintive glides along the dreary coast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20712, line : "A naked, wandering, melancholy ghost!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20714, line : "Achilles, musing as he roll'd his eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20715, line : "O'er the dead hero, thus unheard, replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20716, line : "\"Die thou the first! When Jove and heaven ordain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20717, line : "I follow thee\"--He said, and stripp'd the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20718, line : "Then forcing backward from the gaping wound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20719, line : "The reeking javelin, cast it on the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20720, line : "The thronging Greeks behold with wondering eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20721, line : "His manly beauty and superior size;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20722, line : "While some, ignobler, the great dead deface"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20723, line : "With wounds ungenerous, or with taunts disgrace:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20725, line : "\"How changed that Hector, who like Jove of late"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20726, line : "Sent lightning on our fleets, and scatter'd fate!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20728, line : "High o'er the slain the great Achilles stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20729, line : "Begirt with heroes and surrounding bands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20730, line : "And thus aloud, while all the host attends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20731, line : "\"Princes and leaders! countrymen and friends!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20732, line : "Since now at length the powerful will of heaven"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20733, line : "The dire destroyer to our arm has given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20734, line : "Is not Troy fallen already? Haste, ye powers!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20735, line : "See, if already their deserted towers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20736, line : "Are left unmann'd; or if they yet retain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20737, line : "The souls of heroes, their great Hector slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20738, line : "But what is Troy, or glory what to me?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20739, line : "Or why reflects my mind on aught but thee,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20740, line : "Divine Patroclus! Death hath seal'd his eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20741, line : "Unwept, unhonour'd, uninterr'd he lies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20742, line : "Can his dear image from my soul depart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20743, line : "Long as the vital spirit moves my heart?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20744, line : "If in the melancholy shades below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20745, line : "The flames of friends and lovers cease to glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20746, line : "Yet mine shall sacred last; mine, undecay'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20747, line : "Burn on through death, and animate my shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20748, line : "Meanwhile, ye sons of Greece, in triumph bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20749, line : "The corpse of Hector, and your paeans sing."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20750, line : "Be this the song, slow-moving toward the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20751, line : "\"Hector is dead, and Ilion is no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20753, line : "Then his fell soul a thought of vengeance bred;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20754, line : "(Unworthy of himself, and of the dead;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20755, line : "The nervous ancles bored, his feet he bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20756, line : "With thongs inserted through the double wound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20757, line : "These fix'd up high behind the rolling wain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20758, line : "His graceful head was trail'd along the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20759, line : "Proud on his car the insulting victor stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20760, line : "And bore aloft his arms, distilling blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20761, line : "He smites the steeds; the rapid chariot flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20762, line : "The sudden clouds of circling dust arise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20763, line : "Now lost is all that formidable air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20764, line : "The face divine, and long-descending hair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20765, line : "Purple the ground, and streak the sable sand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20766, line : "Deform'd, dishonour'd, in his native land,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20767, line : "Given to the rage of an insulting throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20768, line : "And, in his parents' sight, now dragg'd along!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20770, line : "The mother first beheld with sad survey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20771, line : "She rent her tresses, venerable grey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20772, line : "And cast, far off, the regal veils away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20773, line : "With piercing shrieks his bitter fate she moans,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20774, line : "While the sad father answers groans with groans"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20775, line : "Tears after tears his mournful cheeks o'erflow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20776, line : "And the whole city wears one face of woe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20777, line : "No less than if the rage of hostile fires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20778, line : "From her foundations curling to her spires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20779, line : "O'er the proud citadel at length should rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20780, line : "And the last blaze send Ilion to the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20781, line : "The wretched monarch of the falling state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20782, line : "Distracted, presses to the Dardan gate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20783, line : "Scarce the whole people stop his desperate course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20784, line : "While strong affliction gives the feeble force:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20785, line : "Grief tears his heart, and drives him to and fro,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20786, line : "In all the raging impotence of woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20787, line : "At length he roll'd in dust, and thus begun,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20788, line : "Imploring all, and naming one by one:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20789, line : "\"Ah! let me, let me go where sorrow calls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20790, line : "I, only I, will issue from your walls"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20791, line : "(Guide or companion, friends! I ask ye none),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20792, line : "And bow before the murderer of my son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20793, line : "My grief perhaps his pity may engage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20794, line : "Perhaps at least he may respect my age."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20795, line : "He has a father too; a man like me;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20796, line : "One, not exempt from age and misery"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20797, line : "(Vigorous no more, as when his young embrace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20798, line : "Begot this pest of me, and all my race)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20799, line : "How many valiant sons, in early bloom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20800, line : "Has that cursed hand send headlong to the tomb!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20801, line : "Thee, Hector! last: thy loss (divinely brave)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20802, line : "Sinks my sad soul with sorrow to the grave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20803, line : "O had thy gentle spirit pass'd in peace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20804, line : "The son expiring in the sire's embrace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20805, line : "While both thy parents wept the fatal hour,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20806, line : "And, bending o'er thee, mix'd the tender shower!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20807, line : "Some comfort that had been, some sad relief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20808, line : "To melt in full satiety of grief!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20810, line : "Thus wail'd the father, grovelling on the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20811, line : "And all the eyes of Ilion stream'd around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20813, line : "Amidst her matrons Hecuba appears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20814, line : "(A mourning princess, and a train in tears;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20815, line : "\"Ah why has Heaven prolong'd this hated breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20816, line : "Patient of horrors, to behold thy death?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20817, line : "O Hector! late thy parents' pride and joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20818, line : "The boast of nations! the defence of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20819, line : "To whom her safety and her fame she owed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20820, line : "Her chief, her hero, and almost her god!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20821, line : "O fatal change! become in one sad day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20822, line : "A senseless corse! inanimated clay!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20824, line : "But not as yet the fatal news had spread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20825, line : "To fair Andromache, of Hector dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20826, line : "As yet no messenger had told his fate,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20827, line : "Not e'en his stay without the Scaean gate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20828, line : "Far in the close recesses of the dome,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20829, line : "Pensive she plied the melancholy loom;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20830, line : "A growing work employ'd her secret hours,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20831, line : "Confusedly gay with intermingled flowers."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20832, line : "Her fair-haired handmaids heat the brazen urn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20833, line : "The bath preparing for her lord's return"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20834, line : "In vain; alas! her lord returns no more;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20835, line : "Unbathed he lies, and bleeds along the shore!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20836, line : "Now from the walls the clamours reach her ear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20837, line : "And all her members shake with sudden fear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20838, line : "Forth from her ivory hand the shuttle falls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20839, line : "And thus, astonish'd, to her maids she calls:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20841, line : "[Illustration: THE BATH.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20843, line : "THE BATH."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20846, line : "\"Ah follow me! (she cried) what plaintive noise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20847, line : "Invades my ear? 'Tis sure my mother's voice."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20848, line : "My faltering knees their trembling frame desert,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20849, line : "A pulse unusual flutters at my heart;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20850, line : "Some strange disaster, some reverse of fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20851, line : "(Ye gods avert it!) threats the Trojan state."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20852, line : "Far be the omen which my thoughts suggest!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20853, line : "But much I fear my Hector's dauntless breast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20854, line : "Confronts Achilles; chased along the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20855, line : "Shut from our walls! I fear, I fear him slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20856, line : "Safe in the crowd he ever scorn'd to wait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20857, line : "And sought for glory in the jaws of fate:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20858, line : "Perhaps that noble heat has cost his breath,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20859, line : "Now quench'd for ever in the arms of death.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20861, line : "She spoke: and furious, with distracted pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20862, line : "Fears in her heart, and anguish in her face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20863, line : "Flies through the dome (the maids her steps pursue),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20864, line : "And mounts the walls, and sends around her view."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20865, line : "Too soon her eyes the killing object found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20866, line : "The godlike Hector dragg'd along the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20867, line : "A sudden darkness shades her swimming eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20868, line : "She faints, she falls; her breath, her colour flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20869, line : "Her hair's fair ornaments, the braids that bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20870, line : "The net that held them, and the wreath that crown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20871, line : "The veil and diadem flew far away"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20872, line : "(The gift of Venus on her bridal day)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20873, line : "Around a train of weeping sisters stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20874, line : "To raise her sinking with assistant hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20875, line : "Scarce from the verge of death recall'd, again"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20876, line : "She faints, or but recovers to complain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20878, line : "[Illustration: ANDROMACHE FAINTING ON THE WALL.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20880, line : "ANDROMACHE FAINTING ON THE WALL."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20883, line : "\"O wretched husband of a wretched wife!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20884, line : "Born with one fate, to one unhappy life!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20885, line : "For sure one star its baneful beam display'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20886, line : "On Priam's roof, and Hippoplacia's shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20887, line : "From different parents, different climes we came."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20888, line : "At different periods, yet our fate the same!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20889, line : "Why was my birth to great Aetion owed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20890, line : "And why was all that tender care bestow'd?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20891, line : "Would I had never been!--O thou, the ghost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20892, line : "Of my dead husband! miserably lost!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20893, line : "Thou to the dismal realms for ever gone!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20894, line : "And I abandon'd, desolate, alone!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20895, line : "An only child, once comfort of my pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20896, line : "Sad product now of hapless love, remains!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20897, line : "No more to smile upon his sire; no friend"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20898, line : "To help him now! no father to defend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20899, line : "For should he 'scape the sword, the common doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20900, line : "What wrongs attend him, and what griefs to come!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20901, line : "Even from his own paternal roof expell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20902, line : "Some stranger ploughs his patrimonial field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20903, line : "The day, that to the shades the father sends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20904, line : "Robs the sad orphan of his father's friends:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20905, line : "He, wretched outcast of mankind! appears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20906, line : "For ever sad, for ever bathed in tears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20907, line : "Amongst the happy, unregarded, he"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20908, line : "Hangs on the robe, or trembles at the knee,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20909, line : "While those his father's former bounty fed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20910, line : "Nor reach the goblet, nor divide the bread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20911, line : "The kindest but his present wants allay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20912, line : "To leave him wretched the succeeding day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20913, line : "Frugal compassion! Heedless, they who boast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20914, line : "Both parents still, nor feel what he has lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20915, line : "Shall cry, 'Begone! thy father feasts not here:'"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20916, line : "The wretch obeys, retiring with a tear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20917, line : "Thus wretched, thus retiring all in tears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20918, line : "To my sad soul Astyanax appears!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20919, line : "Forced by repeated insults to return,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20920, line : "And to his widow'd mother vainly mourn:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20921, line : "He, who, with tender delicacy bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20922, line : "With princes sported, and on dainties fed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20923, line : "And when still evening gave him up to rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20924, line : "Sunk soft in down upon the nurse's breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20925, line : "Must--ah what must he not? Whom Ilion calls"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20926, line : "Astyanax, from her well-guarded walls,(279)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20927, line : "Is now that name no more, unhappy boy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20928, line : "Since now no more thy father guards his Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20929, line : "But thou, my Hector, liest exposed in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20930, line : "Far from thy parents' and thy consort's care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20931, line : "Whose hand in vain, directed by her love,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20932, line : "The martial scarf and robe of triumph wove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20933, line : "Now to devouring flames be these a prey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20934, line : "Useless to thee, from this accursed day!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20935, line : "Yet let the sacrifice at least be paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20936, line : "An honour to the living, not the dead!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20938, line : "So spake the mournful dame: her matrons hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20939, line : "Sigh back her sighs, and answer tear with tear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20945, line : "BOOK XXIII."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20948, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20950, line : "FUNERAL GAMES IN HONOUR OF PATROCLUS.(280)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20952, line : "Achilles and the Myrmidons do honours to the body of Patroclus. After the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20953, line : "funeral feast he retires to the sea-shore, where, falling asleep, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20954, line : "ghost of his friend appears to him, and demands the rites of burial; the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20955, line : "next morning the soldiers are sent with mules and waggons to fetch wood"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20956, line : "for the pyre. The funeral procession, and the offering their hair to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20957, line : "dead. Achilles sacrifices several animals, and lastly twelve Trojan"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20958, line : "captives, at the pile; then sets fire to it. He pays libations to the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20959, line : "Winds, which (at the instance of Iris) rise, and raise the flames. When"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20960, line : "the pile has burned all night, they gather the bones, place them in an urn"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20961, line : "of gold, and raise the tomb. Achilles institutes the funeral games: the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20962, line : "chariot-race, the fight of the caestus, the wrestling, the foot-race, the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20963, line : "single combat, the discus, the shooting with arrows, the darting the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20964, line : "javelin: the various descriptions of which, and the various success of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20965, line : "several antagonists, make the greatest part of the book."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20967, line : "In this book ends the thirtieth day. The night following, the ghost of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20968, line : "Patroclus appears to Achilles: the one-and-thirtieth day is employed in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20969, line : "felling the timber for the pile: the two-and-thirtieth in burning it; and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20970, line : "the three-and-thirtieth in the games. The scene is generally on the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20971, line : "sea-shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20973, line : "Thus humbled in the dust, the pensive train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20974, line : "Through the sad city mourn'd her hero slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20975, line : "The body soil'd with dust, and black with gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20976, line : "Lies on broad Hellespont's resounding shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20977, line : "The Grecians seek their ships, and clear the strand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20978, line : "All, but the martial Myrmidonian band:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20979, line : "These yet assembled great Achilles holds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20980, line : "And the stern purpose of his mind unfolds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20982, line : "\"Not yet, my brave companions of the war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20983, line : "Release your smoking coursers from the car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20984, line : "But, with his chariot each in order led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20985, line : "Perform due honours to Patroclus dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20986, line : "Ere yet from rest or food we seek relief,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20987, line : "Some rites remain, to glut our rage of grief.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20989, line : "The troops obey'd; and thrice in order led(281)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20990, line : "(Achilles first) their coursers round the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20991, line : "And thrice their sorrows and laments renew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20992, line : "Tears bathe their arms, and tears the sands bedew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20993, line : "For such a warrior Thetis aids their woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20994, line : "Melts their strong hearts, and bids their eyes to flow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20995, line : "But chief, Pelides: thick-succeeding sighs"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20996, line : "Burst from his heart, and torrents from his eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20997, line : "His slaughtering hands, yet red with blood, he laid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 20998, line : "On his dead friend's cold breast, and thus he said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21000, line : "\"All hail, Patroclus! let thy honour'd ghost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21001, line : "Hear, and rejoice on Pluto's dreary coast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21002, line : "Behold! Achilles' promise is complete;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21003, line : "The bloody Hector stretch'd before thy feet."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21004, line : "Lo! to the dogs his carcase I resign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21005, line : "And twelve sad victims, of the Trojan line,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21006, line : "Sacred to vengeance, instant shall expire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21007, line : "Their lives effused around thy funeral pyre.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21009, line : "Gloomy he said, and (horrible to view)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21010, line : "Before the bier the bleeding Hector threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21011, line : "Prone on the dust. The Myrmidons around"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21012, line : "Unbraced their armour, and the steeds unbound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21013, line : "All to Achilles' sable ship repair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21014, line : "Frequent and full, the genial feast to share."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21015, line : "Now from the well-fed swine black smokes aspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21016, line : "The bristly victims hissing o'er the fire:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21017, line : "The huge ox bellowing falls; with feebler cries"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21018, line : "Expires the goat; the sheep in silence dies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21019, line : "Around the hero's prostrate body flow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21020, line : "In one promiscuous stream, the reeking blood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21021, line : "And now a band of Argive monarchs brings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21022, line : "The glorious victor to the king of kings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21023, line : "From his dead friend the pensive warrior went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21024, line : "With steps unwilling, to the regal tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21025, line : "The attending heralds, as by office bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21026, line : "With kindled flames the tripod-vase surround:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21027, line : "To cleanse his conquering hands from hostile gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21028, line : "They urged in vain; the chief refused, and swore:(282)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21030, line : "\"No drop shall touch me, by almighty Jove!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21031, line : "The first and greatest of the gods above!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21032, line : "Till on the pyre I place thee; till I rear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21033, line : "The grassy mound, and clip thy sacred hair."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21034, line : "Some ease at least those pious rites may give,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21035, line : "And soothe my sorrows, while I bear to live."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21036, line : "Howe'er, reluctant as I am, I stay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21037, line : "And share your feast; but with the dawn of day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21038, line : "(O king of men!) it claims thy royal care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21039, line : "That Greece the warrior's funeral pile prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21040, line : "And bid the forests fall: (such rites are paid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21041, line : "To heroes slumbering in eternal shade:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21042, line : "Then, when his earthly part shall mount in fire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21043, line : "Let the leagued squadrons to their posts retire.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21045, line : "He spoke: they hear him, and the word obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21046, line : "The rage of hunger and of thirst allay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21047, line : "Then ease in sleep the labours of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21048, line : "But great Pelides, stretch'd along the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21049, line : "Where, dash'd on rocks, the broken billows roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21050, line : "Lies inly groaning; while on either hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21051, line : "The martial Myrmidons confusedly stand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21052, line : "Along the grass his languid members fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21053, line : "Tired with his chase around the Trojan wall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21054, line : "Hush'd by the murmurs of the rolling deep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21055, line : "At length he sinks in the soft arms of sleep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21056, line : "When lo! the shade, before his closing eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21057, line : "Of sad Patroclus rose, or seem'd to rise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21058, line : "In the same robe he living wore, he came:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21059, line : "In stature, voice, and pleasing look, the same."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21060, line : "The form familiar hover'd o'er his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21061, line : "\"And sleeps Achilles? (thus the phantom said:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21062, line : "Sleeps my Achilles, his Patroclus dead?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21063, line : "Living, I seem'd his dearest, tenderest care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21064, line : "But now forgot, I wander in the air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21065, line : "Let my pale corse the rites of burial know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21066, line : "And give me entrance in the realms below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21067, line : "Till then the spirit finds no resting-place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21068, line : "But here and there the unbodied spectres chase"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21069, line : "The vagrant dead around the dark abode,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21070, line : "Forbid to cross the irremeable flood."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21071, line : "Now give thy hand; for to the farther shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21072, line : "When once we pass, the soul returns no more:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21073, line : "When once the last funereal flames ascend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21074, line : "No more shall meet Achilles and his friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21075, line : "No more our thoughts to those we loved make known;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21076, line : "Or quit the dearest, to converse alone."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21077, line : "Me fate has sever'd from the sons of earth,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21078, line : "The fate fore-doom'd that waited from my birth:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21079, line : "Thee too it waits; before the Trojan wall"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21080, line : "Even great and godlike thou art doom'd to fall."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21081, line : "Hear then; and as in fate and love we join,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21082, line : "Ah suffer that my bones may rest with thine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21083, line : "Together have we lived; together bred,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21084, line : "One house received us, and one table fed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21085, line : "That golden urn, thy goddess-mother gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21086, line : "May mix our ashes in one common grave.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21088, line : "\"And is it thou? (he answers) To my sight(283)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21089, line : "Once more return'st thou from the realms of night?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21090, line : "O more than brother! Think each office paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21091, line : "Whate'er can rest a discontented shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21092, line : "But grant one last embrace, unhappy boy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21093, line : "Afford at least that melancholy joy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21095, line : "He said, and with his longing arms essay'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21096, line : "In vain to grasp the visionary shade!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21097, line : "Like a thin smoke he sees the spirit fly,(284)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21098, line : "And hears a feeble, lamentable cry."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21099, line : "Confused he wakes; amazement breaks the bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21100, line : "Of golden sleep, and starting from the sands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21101, line : "Pensive he muses with uplifted hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21103, line : "\"'Tis true, 'tis certain; man, though dead, retains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21104, line : "Part of himself; the immortal mind remains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21105, line : "The form subsists without the body's aid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21106, line : "Aerial semblance, and an empty shade!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21107, line : "This night my friend, so late in battle lost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21108, line : "Stood at my side, a pensive, plaintive ghost:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21109, line : "Even now familiar, as in life, he came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21110, line : "Alas! how different! yet how like the same!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21112, line : "Thus while he spoke, each eye grew big with tears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21113, line : "And now the rosy-finger'd morn appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21114, line : "Shows every mournful face with tears o'erspread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21115, line : "And glares on the pale visage of the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21116, line : "But Agamemnon, as the rites demand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21117, line : "With mules and waggons sends a chosen band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21118, line : "To load the timber, and the pile to rear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21119, line : "A charge consign'd to Merion's faithful care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21120, line : "With proper instruments they take the road,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21121, line : "Axes to cut, and ropes to sling the load."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21122, line : "First march the heavy mules, securely slow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21123, line : "O'er hills, o'er dales, o'er crags, o'er rocks they go:(285)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21124, line : "Jumping, high o'er the shrubs of the rough ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21125, line : "Rattle the clattering cars, and the shock'd axles bound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21126, line : "But when arrived at Ida's spreading woods,(286)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21127, line : "(Fair Ida, water'd with descending floods,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21128, line : "Loud sounds the axe, redoubling strokes on strokes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21129, line : "On all sides round the forest hurls her oaks"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21130, line : "Headlong. Deep echoing groan the thickets brown;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21131, line : "Then rustling, crackling, crashing, thunder down."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21132, line : "The wood the Grecians cleave, prepared to burn;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21133, line : "And the slow mules the same rough road return"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21134, line : "The sturdy woodmen equal burdens bore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21135, line : "(Such charge was given them) to the sandy shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21136, line : "There on the spot which great Achilles show'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21137, line : "They eased their shoulders, and disposed the load;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21138, line : "Circling around the place, where times to come"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21139, line : "Shall view Patroclus' and Achilles' tomb."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21140, line : "The hero bids his martial troops appear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21141, line : "High on their cars in all the pomp of war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21142, line : "Each in refulgent arms his limbs attires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21143, line : "All mount their chariots, combatants and squires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21144, line : "The chariots first proceed, a shining train;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21145, line : "Then clouds of foot that smoke along the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21146, line : "Next these the melancholy band appear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21147, line : "Amidst, lay dead Patroclus on the bier;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21148, line : "O'er all the corse their scattered locks they throw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21149, line : "Achilles next, oppress'd with mighty woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21150, line : "Supporting with his hands the hero's head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21151, line : "Bends o'er the extended body of the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21152, line : "Patroclus decent on the appointed ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21153, line : "They place, and heap the sylvan pile around."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21154, line : "But great Achilles stands apart in prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21155, line : "And from his head divides the yellow hair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21156, line : "Those curling locks which from his youth he vow'd,(287)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21157, line : "And sacred grew, to Sperchius' honour'd flood:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21158, line : "Then sighing, to the deep his locks he cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21159, line : "And roll'd his eyes around the watery waste:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21161, line : "\"Sperchius! whose waves in mazy errors lost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21162, line : "Delightful roll along my native coast!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21163, line : "To whom we vainly vow'd, at our return,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21164, line : "These locks to fall, and hecatombs to burn:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21165, line : "Full fifty rams to bleed in sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21166, line : "Where to the day thy silver fountains rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21167, line : "And where in shade of consecrated bowers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21168, line : "Thy altars stand, perfumed with native flowers!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21169, line : "So vow'd my father, but he vow'd in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21170, line : "No more Achilles sees his native plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21171, line : "In that vain hope these hairs no longer grow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21172, line : "Patroclus bears them to the shades below.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21174, line : "Thus o'er Patroclus while the hero pray'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21175, line : "On his cold hand the sacred lock he laid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21176, line : "Once more afresh the Grecian sorrows flow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21177, line : "And now the sun had set upon their woe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21178, line : "But to the king of men thus spoke the chief:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21179, line : "\"Enough, Atrides! give the troops relief:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21180, line : "Permit the mourning legions to retire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21181, line : "And let the chiefs alone attend the pyre;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21182, line : "The pious care be ours, the dead to burn--\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21183, line : "He said: the people to their ships return:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21184, line : "While those deputed to inter the slain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21185, line : "Heap with a rising pyramid the plain.(288)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21186, line : "A hundred foot in length, a hundred wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21187, line : "The growing structure spreads on every side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21188, line : "High on the top the manly corse they lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21189, line : "And well-fed sheep and sable oxen slay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21190, line : "Achilles covered with their fat the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21191, line : "And the piled victims round the body spread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21192, line : "Then jars of honey, and of fragrant oil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21193, line : "Suspends around, low-bending o'er the pile."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21194, line : "Four sprightly coursers, with a deadly groan"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21195, line : "Pour forth their lives, and on the pyre are thrown."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21196, line : "Of nine large dogs, domestic at his board,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21197, line : "Fall two, selected to attend their lord,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21198, line : "Then last of all, and horrible to tell,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21199, line : "Sad sacrifice! twelve Trojan captives fell.(289)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21200, line : "On these the rage of fire victorious preys,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21201, line : "Involves and joins them in one common blaze."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21202, line : "Smear'd with the bloody rites, he stands on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21203, line : "And calls the spirit with a dreadful cry:(290)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21205, line : "\"All hail, Patroclus! let thy vengeful ghost"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21206, line : "Hear, and exult, on Pluto's dreary coast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21207, line : "Behold Achilles' promise fully paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21208, line : "Twelve Trojan heroes offer'd to thy shade;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21209, line : "But heavier fates on Hector's corse attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21210, line : "Saved from the flames, for hungry dogs to rend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21212, line : "So spake he, threatening: but the gods made vain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21213, line : "His threat, and guard inviolate the slain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21214, line : "Celestial Venus hover'd o'er his head,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21215, line : "And roseate unguents, heavenly fragrance! shed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21216, line : "She watch'd him all the night and all the day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21217, line : "And drove the bloodhounds from their destined prey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21218, line : "Nor sacred Phoebus less employ'd his care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21219, line : "He pour'd around a veil of gather'd air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21220, line : "And kept the nerves undried, the flesh entire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21221, line : "Against the solar beam and Sirian fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21223, line : "[Illustration: THE FUNERAL PILE OF PATROCLUS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21225, line : "THE FUNERAL PILE OF PATROCLUS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21228, line : "Nor yet the pile, where dead Patroclus lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21229, line : "Smokes, nor as yet the sullen flames arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21230, line : "But, fast beside, Achilles stood in prayer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21231, line : "Invoked the gods whose spirit moves the air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21232, line : "And victims promised, and libations cast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21233, line : "To gentle Zephyr and the Boreal blast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21234, line : "He call'd the aerial powers, along the skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21235, line : "To breathe, and whisper to the fires to rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21236, line : "The winged Iris heard the hero's call,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21237, line : "And instant hasten'd to their airy hall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21238, line : "Where in old Zephyr's open courts on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21239, line : "Sat all the blustering brethren of the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21240, line : "She shone amidst them, on her painted bow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21241, line : "The rocky pavement glitter'd with the show."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21242, line : "All from the banquet rise, and each invites"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21243, line : "The various goddess to partake the rites."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21244, line : "\"Not so (the dame replied), I haste to go"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21245, line : "To sacred Ocean, and the floods below:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21246, line : "Even now our solemn hecatombs attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21247, line : "And heaven is feasting on the world's green end"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21248, line : "With righteous Ethiops (uncorrupted train!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21249, line : "Far on the extremest limits of the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21250, line : "But Peleus' son entreats, with sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21251, line : "The western spirit, and the north, to rise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21252, line : "Let on Patroclus' pile your blast be driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21253, line : "And bear the blazing honours high to heaven.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21255, line : "Swift as the word she vanish'd from their view;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21256, line : "Swift as the word the winds tumultuous flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21257, line : "Forth burst the stormy band with thundering roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21258, line : "And heaps on heaps the clouds are toss'd before."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21259, line : "To the wide main then stooping from the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21260, line : "The heaving deeps in watery mountains rise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21261, line : "Troy feels the blast along her shaking walls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21262, line : "Till on the pile the gather'd tempest falls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21263, line : "The structure crackles in the roaring fires,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21264, line : "And all the night the plenteous flame aspires."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21265, line : "All night Achilles hails Patroclus' soul,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21266, line : "With large libations from the golden bowl."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21267, line : "As a poor father, helpless and undone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21268, line : "Mourns o'er the ashes of an only son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21269, line : "Takes a sad pleasure the last bones to burn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21270, line : "And pours in tears, ere yet they close the urn:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21271, line : "So stay'd Achilles, circling round the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21272, line : "So watch'd the flames, till now they flame no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21273, line : "'Twas when, emerging through the shades of night."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21274, line : "The morning planet told the approach of light;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21275, line : "And, fast behind, Aurora's warmer ray"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21276, line : "O'er the broad ocean pour'd the golden day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21277, line : "Then sank the blaze, the pile no longer burn'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21278, line : "And to their caves the whistling winds return'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21279, line : "Across the Thracian seas their course they bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21280, line : "The ruffled seas beneath their passage roar."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21282, line : "Then parting from the pile he ceased to weep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21283, line : "And sank to quiet in the embrace of sleep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21284, line : "Exhausted with his grief: meanwhile the crowd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21285, line : "Of thronging Grecians round Achilles stood;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21286, line : "The tumult waked him: from his eyes he shook"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21287, line : "Unwilling slumber, and the chiefs bespoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21289, line : "\"Ye kings and princes of the Achaian name!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21290, line : "First let us quench the yet remaining flame"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21291, line : "With sable wine; then, as the rites direct,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21292, line : "The hero's bones with careful view select:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21293, line : "(Apart, and easy to be known they lie"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21294, line : "Amidst the heap, and obvious to the eye:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21295, line : "The rest around the margin will be seen"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21296, line : "Promiscuous, steeds and immolated men:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21297, line : "These wrapp'd in double cauls of fat, prepare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21298, line : "And in the golden vase dispose with care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21299, line : "There let them rest with decent honour laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21300, line : "Till I shall follow to the infernal shade."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21301, line : "Meantime erect the tomb with pious hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21302, line : "A common structure on the humble sands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21303, line : "Hereafter Greece some nobler work may raise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21304, line : "And late posterity record our praise!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21306, line : "The Greeks obey; where yet the embers glow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21307, line : "Wide o'er the pile the sable wine they throw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21308, line : "And deep subsides the ashy heap below."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21309, line : "Next the white bones his sad companions place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21310, line : "With tears collected, in the golden vase."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21311, line : "The sacred relics to the tent they bore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21312, line : "The urn a veil of linen covered o'er."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21313, line : "That done, they bid the sepulchre aspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21314, line : "And cast the deep foundations round the pyre;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21315, line : "High in the midst they heap the swelling bed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21316, line : "Of rising earth, memorial of the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21318, line : "The swarming populace the chief detains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21319, line : "And leads amidst a wide extent of plains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21320, line : "There placed them round: then from the ships proceeds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21321, line : "A train of oxen, mules, and stately steeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21322, line : "Vases and tripods (for the funeral games),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21323, line : "Resplendent brass, and more resplendent dames."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21324, line : "First stood the prizes to reward the force"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21325, line : "Of rapid racers in the dusty course:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21326, line : "A woman for the first, in beauty's bloom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21327, line : "Skill'd in the needle, and the labouring loom;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21328, line : "And a large vase, where two bright handles rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21329, line : "Of twenty measures its capacious size."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21330, line : "The second victor claims a mare unbroke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21331, line : "Big with a mule, unknowing of the yoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21332, line : "The third, a charger yet untouch'd by flame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21333, line : "Four ample measures held the shining frame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21334, line : "Two golden talents for the fourth were placed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21335, line : "An ample double bowl contents the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21336, line : "These in fair order ranged upon the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21337, line : "The hero, rising, thus address'd the train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21339, line : "\"Behold the prizes, valiant Greeks! decreed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21340, line : "To the brave rulers of the racing steed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21341, line : "Prizes which none beside ourself could gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21342, line : "Should our immortal coursers take the plain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21343, line : "(A race unrivall'd, which from ocean's god"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21344, line : "Peleus received, and on his son bestow'd.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21345, line : "But this no time our vigour to display;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21346, line : "Nor suit, with them, the games of this sad day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21347, line : "Lost is Patroclus now, that wont to deck"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21348, line : "Their flowing manes, and sleek their glossy neck."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21349, line : "Sad, as they shared in human grief, they stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21350, line : "And trail those graceful honours on the sand!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21351, line : "Let others for the noble task prepare,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21352, line : "Who trust the courser and the flying car.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21354, line : "Fired at his word the rival racers rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21355, line : "But far the first Eumelus hopes the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21356, line : "Famed though Pieria for the fleetest breed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21357, line : "And skill'd to manage the high-bounding steed."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21358, line : "With equal ardour bold Tydides swell'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21359, line : "The steeds of Tros beneath his yoke compell'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21360, line : "(Which late obey'd the Dardan chiefs command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21361, line : "When scarce a god redeem'd him from his hand)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21362, line : "Then Menelaus his Podargus brings,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21363, line : "And the famed courser of the king of kings:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21364, line : "Whom rich Echepolus (more rich than brave),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21365, line : "To 'scape the wars, to Agamemnon gave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21366, line : "(Ćthe her name) at home to end his days;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21367, line : "Base wealth preferring to eternal praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21368, line : "Next him Antilochus demands the course"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21369, line : "With beating heart, and cheers his Pylian horse."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21370, line : "Experienced Nestor gives his son the reins,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21371, line : "Directs his judgment, and his heat restrains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21372, line : "Nor idly warns the hoary sire, nor hears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21373, line : "The prudent son with unattending ears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21375, line : "\"My son! though youthful ardour fire thy breast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21376, line : "The gods have loved thee, and with arts have bless'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21377, line : "Neptune and Jove on thee conferr'd the skill"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21378, line : "Swift round the goal to turn the flying wheel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21379, line : "To guide thy conduct little precept needs;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21380, line : "But slow, and past their vigour, are my steeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21381, line : "Fear not thy rivals, though for swiftness known;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21382, line : "Compare those rivals' judgment and thy own:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21383, line : "It is not strength, but art, obtains the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21384, line : "And to be swift is less than to be wise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21385, line : "'Tis more by art than force of numerous strokes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21386, line : "The dexterous woodman shapes the stubborn oaks;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21387, line : "By art the pilot, through the boiling deep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21388, line : "And howling tempest, steers the fearless ship;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21389, line : "And 'tis the artist wins the glorious course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21390, line : "Not those who trust in chariots and in horse."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21391, line : "In vain, unskilful to the goal they strive,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21392, line : "And short, or wide, the ungovern'd courser drive:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21393, line : "While with sure skill, though with inferior steeds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21394, line : "The knowing racer to his end proceeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21395, line : "Fix'd on the goal his eye foreruns the course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21396, line : "His hand unerring steers the steady horse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21397, line : "And now contracts, or now extends the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21398, line : "Observing still the foremost on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21399, line : "Mark then the goal, 'tis easy to be found;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21400, line : "Yon aged trunk, a cubit from the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21401, line : "Of some once stately oak the last remains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21402, line : "Or hardy fir, unperish'd with the rains:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21403, line : "Inclosed with stones, conspicuous from afar;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21404, line : "And round, a circle for the wheeling car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21405, line : "(Some tomb perhaps of old, the dead to grace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21406, line : "Or then, as now, the limit of a race.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21407, line : "Bear close to this, and warily proceed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21408, line : "A little bending to the left-hand steed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21409, line : "But urge the right, and give him all the reins;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21410, line : "While thy strict hand his fellow's head restrains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21411, line : "And turns him short; till, doubling as they roll,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21412, line : "The wheel's round naves appear to brush the goal."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21413, line : "Yet (not to break the car, or lame the horse)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21414, line : "Clear of the stony heap direct the course;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21415, line : "Lest through incaution failing, thou mayst be"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21416, line : "A joy to others, a reproach to me."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21417, line : "So shalt thou pass the goal, secure of mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21418, line : "And leave unskilful swiftness far behind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21419, line : "Though thy fierce rival drove the matchless steed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21420, line : "Which bore Adrastus, of celestial breed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21421, line : "Or the famed race, through all the regions known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21422, line : "That whirl'd the car of proud Laomedon.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21424, line : "Thus (nought unsaid) the much-advising sage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21425, line : "Concludes; then sat, stiff with unwieldy age."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21426, line : "Next bold Meriones was seen to rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21427, line : "The last, but not least ardent for the prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21428, line : "They mount their seats; the lots their place dispose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21429, line : "(Roll'd in his helmet, these Achilles throws)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21430, line : "Young Nestor leads the race: Eumelus then;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21431, line : "And next the brother of the king of men:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21432, line : "Thy lot, Meriones, the fourth was cast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21433, line : "And, far the bravest, Diomed, was last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21434, line : "They stand in order, an impatient train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21435, line : "Pelides points the barrier on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21436, line : "And sends before old Phoenix to the place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21437, line : "To mark the racers, and to judge the race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21438, line : "At once the coursers from the barrier bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21439, line : "The lifted scourges all at once resound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21440, line : "Their heart, their eyes, their voice, they send before;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21441, line : "And up the champaign thunder from the shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21442, line : "Thick, where they drive, the dusty clouds arise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21443, line : "And the lost courser in the whirlwind flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21444, line : "Loose on their shoulders the long manes reclined,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21445, line : "Float in their speed, and dance upon the wind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21446, line : "The smoking chariots, rapid as they bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21447, line : "Now seem to touch the sky, and now the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21448, line : "While hot for fame, and conquest all their care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21449, line : "(Each o'er his flying courser hung in air,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21450, line : "Erect with ardour, poised upon the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21451, line : "They pant, they stretch, they shout along the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21452, line : "Now (the last compass fetch'd around the goal)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21453, line : "At the near prize each gathers all his soul,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21454, line : "Each burns with double hope, with double pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21455, line : "Tears up the shore, and thunders toward the main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21456, line : "First flew Eumelus on Pheretian steeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21457, line : "With those of Tros bold Diomed succeeds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21458, line : "Close on Eumelus' back they puff the wind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21459, line : "And seem just mounting on his car behind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21460, line : "Full on his neck he feels the sultry breeze,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21461, line : "And, hovering o'er, their stretching shadows sees."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21462, line : "Then had he lost, or left a doubtful prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21463, line : "But angry Phoebus to Tydides flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21464, line : "Strikes from his hand the scourge, and renders vain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21465, line : "His matchless horses' labour on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21466, line : "Rage fills his eye with anguish, to survey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21467, line : "Snatch'd from his hope the glories of the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21468, line : "The fraud celestial Pallas sees with pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21469, line : "Springs to her knight, and gives the scourge again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21470, line : "And fills his steeds with vigour. At a stroke"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21471, line : "She breaks his rival's chariot from the yoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21472, line : "No more their way the startled horses held;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21473, line : "The car reversed came rattling on the field;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21474, line : "Shot headlong from his seat, beside the wheel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21475, line : "Prone on the dust the unhappy master fell;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21476, line : "His batter'd face and elbows strike the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21477, line : "Nose, mouth, and front, one undistinguish'd wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21478, line : "Grief stops his voice, a torrent drowns his eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21479, line : "Before him far the glad Tydides flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21480, line : "Minerva's spirit drives his matchless pace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21481, line : "And crowns him victor of the labour'd race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21483, line : "The next, though distant, Menelaus succeeds;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21484, line : "While thus young Nestor animates his steeds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21485, line : "\"Now, now, my generous pair, exert your force;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21486, line : "Not that we hope to match Tydides' horse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21487, line : "Since great Minerva wings their rapid way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21488, line : "And gives their lord the honours of the day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21489, line : "But reach Atrides! shall his mare outgo"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21490, line : "Your swiftness? vanquish'd by a female foe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21491, line : "Through your neglect, if lagging on the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21492, line : "The last ignoble gift be all we gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21493, line : "No more shall Nestor's hand your food supply,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21494, line : "The old man's fury rises, and ye die."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21495, line : "Haste then: yon narrow road, before our sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21496, line : "Presents the occasion, could we use it right.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21498, line : "Thus he. The coursers at their master's threat"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21499, line : "With quicker steps the sounding champaign beat."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21500, line : "And now Antilochus with nice survey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21501, line : "Observes the compass of the hollow way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21502, line : "'Twas where, by force of wintry torrents torn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21503, line : "Fast by the road a precipice was worn:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21504, line : "Here, where but one could pass, to shun the throng"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21505, line : "The Spartan hero's chariot smoked along."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21506, line : "Close up the venturous youth resolves to keep,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21507, line : "Still edging near, and bears him toward the steep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21508, line : "Atrides, trembling, casts his eye below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21509, line : "And wonders at the rashness of his foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21510, line : "\"Hold, stay your steeds--What madness thus to ride"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21511, line : "This narrow way! take larger field (he cried),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21512, line : "Or both must fall.\"--Atrides cried in vain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21513, line : "He flies more fast, and throws up all the rein."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21514, line : "Far as an able arm the disk can send,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21515, line : "When youthful rivals their full force extend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21516, line : "So far, Antilochus! thy chariot flew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21517, line : "Before the king: he, cautious, backward drew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21518, line : "His horse compell'd; foreboding in his fears"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21519, line : "The rattling ruin of the clashing cars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21520, line : "The floundering coursers rolling on the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21521, line : "And conquest lost through frantic haste to gain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21522, line : "But thus upbraids his rival as he flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21523, line : "\"Go, furious youth! ungenerous and unwise!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21524, line : "Go, but expect not I'll the prize resign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21525, line : "Add perjury to fraud, and make it thine--\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21526, line : "Then to his steeds with all his force he cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21527, line : "\"Be swift, be vigorous, and regain the prize!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21528, line : "Your rivals, destitute of youthful force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21529, line : "With fainting knees shall labour in the course,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21530, line : "And yield the glory yours.\"--The steeds obey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21531, line : "Already at their heels they wing their way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21532, line : "And seem already to retrieve the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21534, line : "Meantime the Grecians in a ring beheld"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21535, line : "The coursers bounding o'er the dusty field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21536, line : "The first who mark'd them was the Cretan king;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21537, line : "High on a rising ground, above the ring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21538, line : "The monarch sat: from whence with sure survey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21539, line : "He well observed the chief who led the way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21540, line : "And heard from far his animating cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21541, line : "And saw the foremost steed with sharpen'd eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21542, line : "On whose broad front a blaze of shining white,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21543, line : "Like the full moon, stood obvious to the sight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21544, line : "He saw; and rising, to the Greeks begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21545, line : "\"Are yonder horse discern'd by me alone?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21546, line : "Or can ye, all, another chief survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21547, line : "And other steeds than lately led the way?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21548, line : "Those, though the swiftest, by some god withheld,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21549, line : "Lie sure disabled in the middle field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21550, line : "For, since the goal they doubled, round the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21551, line : "I search to find them, but I search in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21552, line : "Perchance the reins forsook the driver's hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21553, line : "And, turn'd too short, he tumbled on the strand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21554, line : "Shot from the chariot; while his coursers stray"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21555, line : "With frantic fury from the destined way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21556, line : "Rise then some other, and inform my sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21557, line : "For these dim eyes, perhaps, discern not right;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21558, line : "Yet sure he seems, to judge by shape and air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21559, line : "The great Ćtolian chief, renown'd in war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21561, line : "\"Old man! (Oileus rashly thus replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21562, line : "Thy tongue too hastily confers the prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21563, line : "Of those who view the course, nor sharpest eyed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21564, line : "Nor youngest, yet the readiest to decide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21565, line : "Eumelus' steeds, high bounding in the chase,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21566, line : "Still, as at first, unrivall'd lead the race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21567, line : "I well discern him, as he shakes the rein,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21568, line : "And hear his shouts victorious o'er the plain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21570, line : "Thus he. Idomeneus, incensed, rejoin'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21571, line : "\"Barbarous of words! and arrogant of mind!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21572, line : "Contentious prince, of all the Greeks beside"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21573, line : "The last in merit, as the first in pride!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21574, line : "To vile reproach what answer can we make?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21575, line : "A goblet or a tripod let us stake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21576, line : "And be the king the judge. The most unwise"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21577, line : "Will learn their rashness, when they pay the price.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21579, line : "He said: and Ajax, by mad passion borne,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21580, line : "Stern had replied; fierce scorn enhancing scorn"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21581, line : "To fell extremes. But Thetis' godlike son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21582, line : "Awful amidst them rose, and thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21584, line : "\"Forbear, ye chiefs! reproachful to contend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21585, line : "Much would ye blame, should others thus offend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21586, line : "And lo! the approaching steeds your contest end.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21587, line : "No sooner had he spoke, but thundering near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21588, line : "Drives, through a stream of dust, the charioteer."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21589, line : "High o'er his head the circling lash he wields:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21590, line : "His bounding horses scarcely touch the fields:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21591, line : "His car amidst the dusty whirlwind roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21592, line : "Bright with the mingled blaze of tin and gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21593, line : "Refulgent through the cloud: no eye could find"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21594, line : "The track his flying wheels had left behind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21595, line : "And the fierce coursers urged their rapid pace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21596, line : "So swift, it seem'd a flight, and not a race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21597, line : "Now victor at the goal Tydides stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21598, line : "Quits his bright car, and springs upon the sands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21599, line : "From the hot steeds the sweaty torrents stream;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21600, line : "The well-plied whip is hung athwart the beam:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21601, line : "With joy brave Sthenelus receives the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21602, line : "The tripod-vase, and dame with radiant eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21603, line : "These to the ships his train triumphant leads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21604, line : "The chief himself unyokes the panting steeds."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21606, line : "Young Nestor follows (who by art, not force,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21607, line : "O'erpass'd Atrides) second in the course."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21608, line : "Behind, Atrides urged the race, more near"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21609, line : "Than to the courser in his swift career"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21610, line : "The following car, just touching with his heel"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21611, line : "And brushing with his tail the whirling wheel:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21612, line : "Such, and so narrow now the space between"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21613, line : "The rivals, late so distant on the green;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21614, line : "So soon swift Ćthe her lost ground regain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21615, line : "One length, one moment, had the race obtain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21617, line : "Merion pursued, at greater distance still,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21618, line : "With tardier coursers, and inferior skill."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21619, line : "Last came, Admetus! thy unhappy son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21620, line : "Slow dragged the steeds his batter'd chariot on:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21621, line : "Achilles saw, and pitying thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21623, line : "\"Behold! the man whose matchless art surpass'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21624, line : "The sons of Greece! the ablest, yet the last!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21625, line : "Fortune denies, but justice bids us pay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21626, line : "(Since great Tydides bears the first away)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21627, line : "To him the second honours of the day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21629, line : "The Greeks consent with loud-applauding cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21630, line : "And then Eumelus had received the prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21631, line : "But youthful Nestor, jealous of his fame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21632, line : "The award opposes, and asserts his claim."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21633, line : "\"Think not (he cries) I tamely will resign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21634, line : "O Peleus' son! the mare so justly mine."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21635, line : "What if the gods, the skilful to confound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21636, line : "Have thrown the horse and horseman to the ground?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21637, line : "Perhaps he sought not heaven by sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21638, line : "And vows omitted forfeited the prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21639, line : "If yet (distinction to thy friend to show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21640, line : "And please a soul desirous to bestow)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21641, line : "Some gift must grace Eumelus, view thy store"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21642, line : "Of beauteous handmaids, steeds, and shining ore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21643, line : "An ample present let him thence receive,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21644, line : "And Greece shall praise thy generous thirst to give."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21645, line : "But this my prize I never shall forego;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21646, line : "This, who but touches, warriors! is my foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21648, line : "Thus spake the youth; nor did his words offend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21649, line : "Pleased with the well-turn'd flattery of a friend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21650, line : "Achilles smiled: \"The gift proposed (he cried),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21651, line : "Antilochus! we shall ourself provide."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21652, line : "With plates of brass the corslet cover'd o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21653, line : "(The same renown'd Asteropaeus wore,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21654, line : "Whose glittering margins raised with silver shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21655, line : "(No vulgar gift,) Eumelus! shall be thine.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21657, line : "He said: Automedon at his command"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21658, line : "The corslet brought, and gave it to his hand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21659, line : "Distinguish'd by his friend, his bosom glows"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21660, line : "With generous joy: then Menelaus rose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21661, line : "The herald placed the sceptre in his hands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21662, line : "And still'd the clamour of the shouting bands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21663, line : "Not without cause incensed at Nestor's son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21664, line : "And inly grieving, thus the king begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21666, line : "\"The praise of wisdom, in thy youth obtain'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21667, line : "An act so rash, Antilochus! has stain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21668, line : "Robb'd of my glory and my just reward,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21669, line : "To you, O Grecians! be my wrong declared:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21670, line : "So not a leader shall our conduct blame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21671, line : "Or judge me envious of a rival's fame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21672, line : "But shall not we, ourselves, the truth maintain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21673, line : "What needs appealing in a fact so plain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21674, line : "What Greek shall blame me, if I bid thee rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21675, line : "And vindicate by oath th' ill-gotten prize?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21676, line : "Rise if thou darest, before thy chariot stand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21677, line : "The driving scourge high-lifted in thy hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21678, line : "And touch thy steeds, and swear thy whole intent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21679, line : "Was but to conquer, not to circumvent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21680, line : "Swear by that god whose liquid arms surround"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21681, line : "The globe, and whose dread earthquakes heave the ground!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21683, line : "The prudent chief with calm attention heard;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21684, line : "Then mildly thus: \"Excuse, if youth have err'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21685, line : "Superior as thou art, forgive the offence,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21686, line : "Nor I thy equal, or in years, or sense."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21687, line : "Thou know'st the errors of unripen'd age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21688, line : "Weak are its counsels, headlong is its rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21689, line : "The prize I quit, if thou thy wrath resign;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21690, line : "The mare, or aught thou ask'st, be freely thine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21691, line : "Ere I become (from thy dear friendship torn)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21692, line : "Hateful to thee, and to the gods forsworn.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21694, line : "So spoke Antilochus; and at the word"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21695, line : "The mare contested to the king restored."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21696, line : "Joy swells his soul: as when the vernal grain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21697, line : "Lifts the green ear above the springing plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21698, line : "The fields their vegetable life renew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21699, line : "And laugh and glitter with the morning dew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21700, line : "Such joy the Spartan's shining face o'erspread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21701, line : "And lifted his gay heart, while thus he said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21703, line : "\"Still may our souls, O generous youth! agree"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21704, line : "'Tis now Atrides' turn to yield to thee."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21705, line : "Rash heat perhaps a moment might control,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21706, line : "Not break, the settled temper of thy soul."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21707, line : "Not but (my friend) 'tis still the wiser way"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21708, line : "To waive contention with superior sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21709, line : "For ah! how few, who should like thee offend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21710, line : "Like thee, have talents to regain the friend!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21711, line : "To plead indulgence, and thy fault atone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21712, line : "Suffice thy father's merit and thy own:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21713, line : "Generous alike, for me, the sire and son"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21714, line : "Have greatly suffer'd, and have greatly done."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21715, line : "I yield; that all may know, my soul can bend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21716, line : "Nor is my pride preferr'd before my friend.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21718, line : "He said; and pleased his passion to command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21719, line : "Resign'd the courser to Noemon's hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21720, line : "Friend of the youthful chief: himself content,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21721, line : "The shining charger to his vessel sent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21722, line : "The golden talents Merion next obtain'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21723, line : "The fifth reward, the double bowl, remain'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21724, line : "Achilles this to reverend Nestor bears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21725, line : "And thus the purpose of his gift declares:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21726, line : "\"Accept thou this, O sacred sire! (he said)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21727, line : "In dear memorial of Patroclus dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21728, line : "Dead and for ever lost Patroclus lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21729, line : "For ever snatch'd from our desiring eyes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21730, line : "Take thou this token of a grateful heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21731, line : "Though 'tis not thine to hurl the distant dart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21732, line : "The quoit to toss, the ponderous mace to wield,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21733, line : "Or urge the race, or wrestle on the field:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21734, line : "Thy pristine vigour age has overthrown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21735, line : "But left the glory of the past thy own.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21737, line : "He said, and placed the goblet at his side;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21738, line : "With joy the venerable king replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21740, line : "\"Wisely and well, my son, thy words have proved"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21741, line : "A senior honour'd, and a friend beloved!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21742, line : "Too true it is, deserted of my strength,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21743, line : "These wither'd arms and limbs have fail'd at length."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21744, line : "Oh! had I now that force I felt of yore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21745, line : "Known through Buprasium and the Pylian shore!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21746, line : "Victorious then in every solemn game,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21747, line : "Ordain'd to Amarynces' mighty name;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21748, line : "The brave Epeians gave my glory way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21749, line : "Ćtolians, Pylians, all resign'd the day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21750, line : "I quell'd Clytomedes in fights of hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21751, line : "And backward hurl'd Ancaeus on the sand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21752, line : "Surpass'd Iphyclus in the swift career,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21753, line : "Phyleus and Polydorus with the spear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21754, line : "The sons of Actor won the prize of horse,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21755, line : "But won by numbers, not by art or force:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21756, line : "For the famed twins, impatient to survey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21757, line : "Prize after prize by Nestor borne away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21758, line : "Sprung to their car; and with united pains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21759, line : "One lash'd the coursers, while one ruled the reins."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21760, line : "Such once I was! Now to these tasks succeeds"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21761, line : "A younger race, that emulate our deeds:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21762, line : "I yield, alas! (to age who must not yield?)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21763, line : "Though once the foremost hero of the field."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21764, line : "Go thou, my son! by generous friendship led,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21765, line : "With martial honours decorate the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21766, line : "While pleased I take the gift thy hands present,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21767, line : "(Pledge of benevolence, and kind intent,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21768, line : "Rejoiced, of all the numerous Greeks, to see"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21769, line : "Not one but honours sacred age and me:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21770, line : "Those due distinctions thou so well canst pay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21771, line : "May the just gods return another day!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21773, line : "Proud of the gift, thus spake the full of days:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21774, line : "Achilles heard him, prouder of the praise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21776, line : "The prizes next are order'd to the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21777, line : "For the bold champions who the caestus wield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21778, line : "A stately mule, as yet by toils unbroke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21779, line : "Of six years' age, unconscious of the yoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21780, line : "Is to the circus led, and firmly bound;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21781, line : "Next stands a goblet, massy, large, and round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21782, line : "Achilles rising, thus: \"Let Greece excite"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21783, line : "Two heroes equal to this hardy fight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21784, line : "Who dare the foe with lifted arms provoke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21785, line : "And rush beneath the long-descending stroke."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21786, line : "On whom Apollo shall the palm bestow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21787, line : "And whom the Greeks supreme by conquest know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21788, line : "This mule his dauntless labours shall repay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21789, line : "The vanquish'd bear the massy bowl away.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21791, line : "This dreadful combat great Epeus chose;(291)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21792, line : "High o'er the crowd, enormous bulk! he rose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21793, line : "And seized the beast, and thus began to say:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21794, line : "\"Stand forth some man, to bear the bowl away!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21795, line : "(Price of his ruin: for who dares deny"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21796, line : "This mule my right; the undoubted victor I)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21797, line : "Others, 'tis own'd, in fields of battle shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21798, line : "But the first honours of this fight are mine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21799, line : "For who excels in all? Then let my foe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21800, line : "Draw near, but first his certain fortune know;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21801, line : "Secure this hand shall his whole frame confound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21802, line : "Mash all his bones, and all his body pound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21803, line : "So let his friends be nigh, a needful train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21804, line : "To heave the batter'd carcase off the plain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21806, line : "The giant spoke; and in a stupid gaze"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21807, line : "The host beheld him, silent with amaze!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21808, line : "'Twas thou, Euryalus! who durst aspire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21809, line : "To meet his might, and emulate thy sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21810, line : "The great Mecistheus; who in days of yore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21811, line : "In Theban games the noblest trophy bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21812, line : "(The games ordain'd dead OEdipus to grace,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21813, line : "And singly vanquish the Cadmean race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21814, line : "Him great Tydides urges to contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21815, line : "Warm with the hopes of conquest for his friend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21816, line : "Officious with the cincture girds him round;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21817, line : "And to his wrist the gloves of death are bound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21818, line : "Amid the circle now each champion stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21819, line : "And poises high in air his iron hands;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21820, line : "With clashing gauntlets now they fiercely close,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21821, line : "Their crackling jaws re-echo to the blows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21822, line : "And painful sweat from all their members flows."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21823, line : "At length Epeus dealt a weighty blow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21824, line : "Full on the cheek of his unwary foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21825, line : "Beneath that ponderous arm's resistless sway"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21826, line : "Down dropp'd he, nerveless, and extended lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21827, line : "As a large fish, when winds and waters roar,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21828, line : "By some huge billow dash'd against the shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21829, line : "Lies panting; not less batter'd with his wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21830, line : "The bleeding hero pants upon the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21831, line : "To rear his fallen foe, the victor lends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21832, line : "Scornful, his hand; and gives him to his friends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21833, line : "Whose arms support him, reeling through the throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21834, line : "And dragging his disabled legs along;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21835, line : "Nodding, his head hangs down his shoulder o'er;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21836, line : "His mouth and nostrils pour the clotted gore;(292)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21837, line : "Wrapp'd round in mists he lies, and lost to thought;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21838, line : "His friends receive the bowl, too dearly bought."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21840, line : "The third bold game Achilles next demands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21841, line : "And calls the wrestlers to the level sands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21842, line : "A massy tripod for the victor lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21843, line : "Of twice six oxen its reputed price;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21844, line : "And next, the loser's spirits to restore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21845, line : "A female captive, valued but at four."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21846, line : "Scarce did the chief the vigorous strife prop"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21847, line : "When tower-like Ajax and Ulysses rose."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21848, line : "Amid the ring each nervous rival stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21849, line : "Embracing rigid with implicit hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21850, line : "Close lock'd above, their heads and arms are mix'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21851, line : "Below, their planted feet at distance fix'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21852, line : "Like two strong rafters which the builder forms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21853, line : "Proof to the wintry winds and howling storms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21854, line : "Their tops connected, but at wider space"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21855, line : "Fix'd on the centre stands their solid base."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21856, line : "Now to the grasp each manly body bends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21857, line : "The humid sweat from every pore descends;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21858, line : "Their bones resound with blows: sides, shoulders, thighs"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21859, line : "Swell to each gripe, and bloody tumours rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21860, line : "Nor could Ulysses, for his art renown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21861, line : "O'erturn the strength of Ajax on the ground;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21862, line : "Nor could the strength of Ajax overthrow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21863, line : "The watchful caution of his artful foe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21864, line : "While the long strife even tired the lookers on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21865, line : "Thus to Ulysses spoke great Telamon:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21866, line : "\"Or let me lift thee, chief, or lift thou me:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21867, line : "Prove we our force, and Jove the rest decree.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21869, line : "He said; and, straining, heaved him off the ground"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21870, line : "With matchless strength; that time Ulysses found"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21871, line : "The strength to evade, and where the nerves combine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21872, line : "His ankle struck: the giant fell supine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21873, line : "Ulysses, following, on his bosom lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21874, line : "Shouts of applause run rattling through the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21875, line : "Ajax to lift Ulysses next essays;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21876, line : "He barely stirr'd him, but he could not raise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21877, line : "His knee lock'd fast, the foe's attempt denied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21878, line : "And grappling close, they tumbled side by side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21879, line : "Defiled with honourable dust they roll,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21880, line : "Still breathing strife, and unsubdued of soul:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21881, line : "Again they rage, again to combat rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21882, line : "When great Achilles thus divides the prize:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21884, line : "\"Your noble vigour, O my friends, restrain;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21885, line : "Nor weary out your generous strength in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21886, line : "Ye both have won: let others who excel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21887, line : "Now prove that prowess you have proved so well.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21889, line : "The hero's words the willing chiefs obey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21890, line : "From their tired bodies wipe the dust away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21891, line : "And, clothed anew, the following games survey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21893, line : "And now succeed the gifts ordain'd to grace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21894, line : "The youths contending in the rapid race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21895, line : "A silver urn that full six measures held,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21896, line : "By none in weight or workmanship excell'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21897, line : "Sidonian artists taught the frame to shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21898, line : "Elaborate, with artifice divine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21899, line : "Whence Tyrian sailors did the prize transport,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21900, line : "And gave to Thoas at the Lemnian port:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21901, line : "From him descended, good Eunaeus heir'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21902, line : "The glorious gift; and, for Lycaon spared,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21903, line : "To brave Patroclus gave the rich reward:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21904, line : "Now, the same hero's funeral rites to grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21905, line : "It stands the prize of swiftness in the race."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21906, line : "A well-fed ox was for the second placed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21907, line : "And half a talent must content the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21908, line : "Achilles rising then bespoke the train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21909, line : "\"Who hope the palm of swiftness to obtain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21910, line : "Stand forth, and bear these prizes from the plain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21912, line : "The hero said, and starting from his place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21913, line : "Oilean Ajax rises to the race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21914, line : "Ulysses next; and he whose speed surpass'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21915, line : "His youthful equals, Nestor's son, the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21916, line : "Ranged in a line the ready racers stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21917, line : "Pelides points the barrier with his hand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21918, line : "All start at once; Oileus led the race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21919, line : "The next Ulysses, measuring pace with pace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21920, line : "Behind him, diligently close, he sped,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21921, line : "As closely following as the running thread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21922, line : "The spindle follows, and displays the charms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21923, line : "Of the fair spinster's breast and moving arms:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21924, line : "Graceful in motion thus, his foe he plies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21925, line : "And treads each footstep ere the dust can rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21926, line : "His glowing breath upon his shoulders plays:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21927, line : "The admiring Greeks loud acclamations raise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21928, line : "To him they give their wishes, hearts, and eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21929, line : "And send their souls before him as he flies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21930, line : "Now three times turn'd in prospect of the goal,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21931, line : "The panting chief to Pallas lifts his soul:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21932, line : "\"Assist, O goddess!\" thus in thought he pray'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21933, line : "And present at his thought descends the maid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21934, line : "Buoy'd by her heavenly force, he seems to swim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21935, line : "And feels a pinion lifting every limb."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21936, line : "All fierce, and ready now the prize to gain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21937, line : "Unhappy Ajax stumbles on the plain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21938, line : "(O'erturn'd by Pallas), where the slippery shore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21939, line : "Was clogg'd with slimy dung and mingled gore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21940, line : "(The self-same place beside Patroclus' pyre,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21941, line : "Where late the slaughter'd victims fed the fire.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21942, line : "Besmear'd with filth, and blotted o'er with clay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21943, line : "Obscene to sight, the rueful racer lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21944, line : "The well-fed bull (the second prize) he shared,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21945, line : "And left the urn Ulysses' rich reward."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21946, line : "Then, grasping by the horn the mighty beast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21947, line : "The baffled hero thus the Greeks address'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21949, line : "\"Accursed fate! the conquest I forego;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21950, line : "A mortal I, a goddess was my foe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21951, line : "She urged her favourite on the rapid way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21952, line : "And Pallas, not Ulysses, won the day.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21954, line : "Thus sourly wail'd he, sputtering dirt and gore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21955, line : "A burst of laughter echoed through the shore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21956, line : "Antilochus, more humorous than the rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21957, line : "Takes the last prize, and takes it with a jest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21959, line : "\"Why with our wiser elders should we strive?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21960, line : "The gods still love them, and they always thrive."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21961, line : "Ye see, to Ajax I must yield the prize:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21962, line : "He to Ulysses, still more aged and wise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21963, line : "(A green old age unconscious of decays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21964, line : "That proves the hero born in better days!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21965, line : "Behold his vigour in this active race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21966, line : "Achilles only boasts a swifter pace:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21967, line : "For who can match Achilles? He who can,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21968, line : "Must yet be more than hero, more than man.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21970, line : "The effect succeeds the speech. Pelides cries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21971, line : "\"Thy artful praise deserves a better prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21972, line : "Nor Greece in vain shall hear thy friend extoll'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21973, line : "Receive a talent of the purest gold.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21974, line : "The youth departs content. The host admire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21975, line : "The son of Nestor, worthy of his sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21977, line : "Next these a buckler, spear, and helm, he brings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21978, line : "Cast on the plain, the brazen burden rings:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21979, line : "Arms which of late divine Sarpedon wore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21980, line : "And great Patroclus in short triumph bore."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21981, line : "\"Stand forth the bravest of our host! (he cries)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21982, line : "Whoever dares deserve so rich a prize,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21983, line : "Now grace the lists before our army's sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21984, line : "And sheathed in steel, provoke his foe to fight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21985, line : "Who first the jointed armour shall explore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21986, line : "And stain his rival's mail with issuing gore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21987, line : "The sword Asteropaeus possess'd of old,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21988, line : "(A Thracian blade, distinct with studs of gold,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21989, line : "Shall pay the stroke, and grace the striker's side:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21990, line : "These arms in common let the chiefs divide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21991, line : "For each brave champion, when the combat ends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21992, line : "A sumptuous banquet at our tents attends.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21994, line : "Fierce at the word uprose great Tydeus' son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21995, line : "And the huge bulk of Ajax Telamon."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21996, line : "Clad in refulgent steel, on either hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21997, line : "The dreadful chiefs amid the circle stand;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21998, line : "Louring they meet, tremendous to the sight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 21999, line : "Each Argive bosom beats with fierce delight."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22000, line : "Opposed in arms not long they idly stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22001, line : "But thrice they closed, and thrice the charge renew'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22002, line : "A furious pass the spear of Ajax made"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22003, line : "Through the broad shield, but at the corslet stay'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22004, line : "Not thus the foe: his javelin aim'd above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22005, line : "The buckler's margin, at the neck he drove."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22006, line : "But Greece, now trembling for her hero's life,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22007, line : "Bade share the honours, and surcease the strife."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22008, line : "Yet still the victor's due Tydides gains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22009, line : "With him the sword and studded belt remains."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22011, line : "Then hurl'd the hero, thundering on the ground,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22012, line : "A mass of iron (an enormous round),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22013, line : "Whose weight and size the circling Greeks admire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22014, line : "Rude from the furnace, and but shaped by fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22015, line : "This mighty quoit Aetion wont to rear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22016, line : "And from his whirling arm dismiss in air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22017, line : "The giant by Achilles slain, he stow'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22018, line : "Among his spoils this memorable load."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22019, line : "For this, he bids those nervous artists vie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22020, line : "That teach the disk to sound along the sky."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22021, line : "\"Let him, whose might can hurl this bowl, arise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22022, line : "Who farthest hurls it, take it as his prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22023, line : "If he be one enrich'd with large domain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22024, line : "Of downs for flocks, and arable for grain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22025, line : "Small stock of iron needs that man provide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22026, line : "His hinds and swains whole years shall be supplied"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22027, line : "From hence; nor ask the neighbouring city's aid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22028, line : "For ploughshares, wheels, and all the rural trade.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22030, line : "Stern Polypoetes stepp'd before the throng,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22031, line : "And great Leonteus, more than mortal strong;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22032, line : "Whose force with rival forces to oppose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22033, line : "Uprose great Ajax; up Epeus rose."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22034, line : "Each stood in order: first Epeus threw;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22035, line : "High o'er the wondering crowds the whirling circle flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22036, line : "Leonteus next a little space surpass'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22037, line : "And third, the strength of godlike Ajax cast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22038, line : "O'er both their marks it flew; till fiercely flung"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22039, line : "From Polypoetes' arm the discus sung:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22040, line : "Far as a swain his whirling sheephook throws,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22041, line : "That distant falls among the grazing cows,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22042, line : "So past them all the rapid circle flies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22043, line : "His friends, while loud applauses shake the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22044, line : "With force conjoin'd heave off the weighty prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22046, line : "Those, who in skilful archery contend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22047, line : "He next invites the twanging bow to bend;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22048, line : "And twice ten axes casts amidst the round,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22049, line : "Ten double-edged, and ten that singly wound"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22050, line : "The mast, which late a first-rate galley bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22051, line : "The hero fixes in the sandy shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22052, line : "To the tall top a milk-white dove they tie,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22053, line : "The trembling mark at which their arrows fly."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22055, line : "\"Whose weapon strikes yon fluttering bird, shall bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22056, line : "These two-edged axes, terrible in war;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22057, line : "The single, he whose shaft divides the cord.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22058, line : "He said: experienced Merion took the word;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22059, line : "And skilful Teucer: in the helm they threw"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22060, line : "Their lots inscribed, and forth the latter flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22061, line : "Swift from the string the sounding arrow flies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22062, line : "But flies unbless'd! No grateful sacrifice,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22063, line : "No firstling lambs, unheedful! didst thou vow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22064, line : "To Phoebus, patron of the shaft and bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22065, line : "For this, thy well-aim'd arrow turn'd aside,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22066, line : "Err'd from the dove, yet cut the cord that tied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22067, line : "Adown the mainmast fell the parted string,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22068, line : "And the free bird to heaven displays her wing:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22069, line : "Sea, shores, and skies, with loud applause resound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22070, line : "And Merion eager meditates the wound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22071, line : "He takes the bow, directs the shaft above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22072, line : "And following with his eye the soaring dove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22073, line : "Implores the god to speed it through the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22074, line : "With vows of firstling lambs, and grateful sacrific"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22075, line : "The dove, in airy circles as she wheels,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22076, line : "Amid the clouds the piercing arrow feels;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22077, line : "Quite through and through the point its passage found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22078, line : "And at his feet fell bloody to the ground."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22079, line : "The wounded bird, ere yet she breathed her last,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22080, line : "With flagging wings alighted on the mast,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22081, line : "A moment hung, and spread her pinions there,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22082, line : "Then sudden dropp'd, and left her life in air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22083, line : "From the pleased crowd new peals of thunder rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22084, line : "And to the ships brave Merion bears the prize."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22086, line : "To close the funeral games, Achilles last"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22087, line : "A massy spear amid the circle placed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22088, line : "And ample charger of unsullied frame,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22089, line : "With flowers high-wrought, not blacken'd yet by flame."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22090, line : "For these he bids the heroes prove their art,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22091, line : "Whose dexterous skill directs the flying dart."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22092, line : "Here too great Merion hopes the noble prize;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22093, line : "Nor here disdain'd the king of men to rise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22094, line : "With joy Pelides saw the honour paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22095, line : "Rose to the monarch, and respectful said:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22097, line : "\"Thee first in virtue, as in power supreme,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22098, line : "O king of nations! all thy Greeks proclaim;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22099, line : "In every martial game thy worth attest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22100, line : "And know thee both their greatest and their best."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22101, line : "Take then the prize, but let brave Merion bear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22102, line : "This beamy javelin in thy brother's war.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22104, line : "Pleased from the hero's lips his praise to hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22105, line : "The king to Merion gives the brazen spear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22106, line : "But, set apart for sacred use, commands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22107, line : "The glittering charger to Talthybius' hands."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22109, line : "[Illustration: CERES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22111, line : "CERES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22117, line : "BOOK XXIV."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22120, line : "ARGUMENT."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22122, line : "THE REDEMPTION OF THE BODY OF HECTOR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22124, line : "The gods deliberate about the redemption of Hector's body. Jupiter sends"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22125, line : "Thetis to Achilles, to dispose him for the restoring it, and Iris to"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22126, line : "Priam, to encourage him to go in person and treat for it. The old king,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22127, line : "notwithstanding the remonstrances of his queen, makes ready for the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22128, line : "journey, to which he is encouraged by an omen from Jupiter. He sets forth"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22129, line : "in his chariot, with a waggon loaded with presents, under the charge of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22130, line : "Idaeus the herald. Mercury descends in the shape of a young man, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22131, line : "conducts him to the pavilion of Achilles. Their conversation on the way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22132, line : "Priam finds Achilles at his table, casts himself at his feet, and begs for"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22133, line : "the body of his son: Achilles, moved with compassion, grants his request,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22134, line : "detains him one night in his tent, and the next morning sends him home"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22135, line : "with the body: the Trojans run out to meet him. The lamentations of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22136, line : "Andromache, Hecuba, and Helen, with the solemnities of the funeral."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22138, line : "The time of twelve days is employed in this book, while the body of Hector"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22139, line : "lies in the tent of Achilles; and as many more are spent in the truce"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22140, line : "allowed for his interment. The scene is partly in Achilles' camp, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22141, line : "partly in Troy."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22143, line : "Now from the finish'd games the Grecian band"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22144, line : "Seek their black ships, and clear the crowded strand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22145, line : "All stretch'd at ease the genial banquet share,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22146, line : "And pleasing slumbers quiet all their care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22147, line : "Not so Achilles: he, to grief resign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22148, line : "His friend's dear image present to his mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22149, line : "Takes his sad couch, more unobserved to weep;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22150, line : "Nor tastes the gifts of all-composing sleep."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22151, line : "Restless he roll'd around his weary bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22152, line : "And all his soul on his Patroclus fed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22153, line : "The form so pleasing, and the heart so kind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22154, line : "That youthful vigour, and that manly mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22155, line : "What toils they shared, what martial works they wrought,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22156, line : "What seas they measured, and what fields they fought;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22157, line : "All pass'd before him in remembrance dear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22158, line : "Thought follows thought, and tear succeeds to tear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22159, line : "And now supine, now prone, the hero lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22160, line : "Now shifts his side, impatient for the day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22161, line : "Then starting up, disconsolate he goes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22162, line : "Wide on the lonely beach to vent his woes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22163, line : "There as the solitary mourner raves,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22164, line : "The ruddy morning rises o'er the waves:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22165, line : "Soon as it rose, his furious steeds he join'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22166, line : "The chariot flies, and Hector trails behind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22167, line : "And thrice, Patroclus! round thy monument"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22168, line : "Was Hector dragg'd, then hurried to the tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22169, line : "There sleep at last o'ercomes the hero's eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22170, line : "While foul in dust the unhonour'd carcase lies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22171, line : "But not deserted by the pitying skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22172, line : "For Phoebus watch'd it with superior care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22173, line : "Preserved from gaping wounds and tainting air;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22174, line : "And, ignominious as it swept the field,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22175, line : "Spread o'er the sacred corse his golden shield."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22176, line : "All heaven was moved, and Hermes will'd to go"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22177, line : "By stealth to snatch him from the insulting foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22178, line : "But Neptune this, and Pallas this denies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22179, line : "And th' unrelenting empress of the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22180, line : "E'er since that day implacable to Troy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22181, line : "What time young Paris, simple shepherd boy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22182, line : "Won by destructive lust (reward obscene),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22183, line : "Their charms rejected for the Cyprian queen."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22184, line : "But when the tenth celestial morning broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22185, line : "To heaven assembled, thus Apollo spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22187, line : "[Illustration: HECTOR'S BODY AT THE CAR OF ACHILLES.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22189, line : "HECTOR'S BODY AT THE CAR OF ACHILLES."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22192, line : "\"Unpitying powers! how oft each holy fane"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22193, line : "Has Hector tinged with blood of victims slain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22194, line : "And can ye still his cold remains pursue?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22195, line : "Still grudge his body to the Trojans' view?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22196, line : "Deny to consort, mother, son, and sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22197, line : "The last sad honours of a funeral fire?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22198, line : "Is then the dire Achilles all your care?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22199, line : "That iron heart, inflexibly severe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22200, line : "A lion, not a man, who slaughters wide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22201, line : "In strength of rage, and impotence of pride;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22202, line : "Who hastes to murder with a savage joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22203, line : "Invades around, and breathes but to destroy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22204, line : "Shame is not of his soul; nor understood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22205, line : "The greatest evil and the greatest good."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22206, line : "Still for one loss he rages unresign'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22207, line : "Repugnant to the lot of all mankind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22208, line : "To lose a friend, a brother, or a son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22209, line : "Heaven dooms each mortal, and its will is done:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22210, line : "Awhile they sorrow, then dismiss their care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22211, line : "Fate gives the wound, and man is born to bear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22212, line : "But this insatiate, the commission given"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22213, line : "By fate exceeds, and tempts the wrath of heaven:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22214, line : "Lo, how his rage dishonest drags along"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22215, line : "Hector's dead earth, insensible of wrong!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22216, line : "Brave though he be, yet by no reason awed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22217, line : "He violates the laws of man and god.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22219, line : "[Illustration: THE JUDGMENT OF PARIS.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22221, line : "THE JUDGMENT OF PARIS."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22224, line : "\"If equal honours by the partial skies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22225, line : "Are doom'd both heroes, (Juno thus replies,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22226, line : "If Thetis' son must no distinction know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22227, line : "Then hear, ye gods! the patron of the bow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22228, line : "But Hector only boasts a mortal claim,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22229, line : "His birth deriving from a mortal dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22230, line : "Achilles, of your own ethereal race,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22231, line : "Springs from a goddess by a man's embrace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22232, line : "(A goddess by ourself to Peleus given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22233, line : "A man divine, and chosen friend of heaven)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22234, line : "To grace those nuptials, from the bright abode"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22235, line : "Yourselves were present; where this minstrel-god,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22236, line : "Well pleased to share the feast, amid the quire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22237, line : "Stood proud to hymn, and tune his youthful lyre.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22239, line : "Then thus the Thunderer checks the imperial dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22240, line : "\"Let not thy wrath the court of heaven inflame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22241, line : "Their merits, nor their honours, are the same."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22242, line : "But mine, and every god's peculiar grace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22243, line : "Hector deserves, of all the Trojan race:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22244, line : "Still on our shrines his grateful offerings lay,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22245, line : "(The only honours men to gods can pay,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22246, line : "Nor ever from our smoking altar ceased"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22247, line : "The pure libation, and the holy feast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22248, line : "Howe'er by stealth to snatch the corse away,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22249, line : "We will not: Thetis guards it night and day."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22250, line : "But haste, and summon to our courts above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22251, line : "The azure queen; let her persuasion move"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22252, line : "Her furious son from Priam to receive"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22253, line : "The proffer'd ransom, and the corse to leave.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22255, line : "He added not: and Iris from the skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22256, line : "Swift as a whirlwind, on the message flies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22257, line : "Meteorous the face of ocean sweeps,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22258, line : "Refulgent gliding o'er the sable deeps."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22259, line : "Between where Samos wide his forests spreads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22260, line : "And rocky Imbrus lifts its pointed heads,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22261, line : "Down plunged the maid; (the parted waves resound;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22262, line : "She plunged and instant shot the dark profound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22263, line : "As bearing death in the fallacious bait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22264, line : "From the bent angle sinks the leaden weight;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22265, line : "So pass'd the goddess through the closing wave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22266, line : "Where Thetis sorrow'd in her secret cave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22267, line : "There placed amidst her melancholy train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22268, line : "(The blue-hair'd sisters of the sacred main)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22269, line : "Pensive she sat, revolving fates to come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22270, line : "And wept her godlike son's approaching doom."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22271, line : "Then thus the goddess of the painted bow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22272, line : "\"Arise, O Thetis! from thy seats below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22273, line : "'Tis Jove that calls.\"--\"And why (the dame replies)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22274, line : "Calls Jove his Thetis to the hated skies?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22275, line : "Sad object as I am for heavenly sight!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22276, line : "Ah may my sorrows ever shun the light!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22277, line : "Howe'er, be heaven's almighty sire obey'd--\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22278, line : "She spake, and veil'd her head in sable shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22279, line : "Which, flowing long, her graceful person clad;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22280, line : "And forth she paced, majestically sad."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22282, line : "Then through the world of waters they repair"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22283, line : "(The way fair Iris led) to upper air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22284, line : "The deeps dividing, o'er the coast they rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22285, line : "And touch with momentary flight the skies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22286, line : "There in the lightning's blaze the sire they found,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22287, line : "And all the gods in shining synod round."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22288, line : "Thetis approach'd with anguish in her face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22289, line : "(Minerva rising, gave the mourner place,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22290, line : "Even Juno sought her sorrows to console,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22291, line : "And offer'd from her hand the nectar-bowl:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22292, line : "She tasted, and resign'd it: then began"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22293, line : "The sacred sire of gods and mortal man:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22295, line : "\"Thou comest, fair Thetis, but with grief o'ercast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22296, line : "Maternal sorrows; long, ah, long to last!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22297, line : "Suffice, we know and we partake thy cares;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22298, line : "But yield to fate, and hear what Jove declares"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22299, line : "Nine days are past since all the court above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22300, line : "In Hector's cause have moved the ear of Jove;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22301, line : "'Twas voted, Hermes from his godlike foe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22302, line : "By stealth should bear him, but we will'd not so:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22303, line : "We will, thy son himself the corse restore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22304, line : "And to his conquest add this glory more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22305, line : "Then hie thee to him, and our mandate bear:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22306, line : "Tell him he tempts the wrath of heaven too far;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22307, line : "Nor let him more (our anger if he dread)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22308, line : "Vent his mad vengeance on the sacred dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22309, line : "But yield to ransom and the father's prayer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22310, line : "The mournful father, Iris shall prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22311, line : "With gifts to sue; and offer to his hands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22312, line : "Whate'er his honour asks, or heart demands.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22314, line : "His word the silver-footed queen attends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22315, line : "And from Olympus' snowy tops descends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22316, line : "Arrived, she heard the voice of loud lament,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22317, line : "And echoing groans that shook the lofty tent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22318, line : "His friends prepare the victim, and dispose"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22319, line : "Repast unheeded, while he vents his woes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22320, line : "The goddess seats her by her pensive son,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22321, line : "She press'd his hand, and tender thus begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22323, line : "\"How long, unhappy! shall thy sorrows flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22324, line : "And thy heart waste with life-consuming woe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22325, line : "Mindless of food, or love, whose pleasing reign"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22326, line : "Soothes weary life, and softens human pain?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22327, line : "O snatch the moments yet within thy power;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22328, line : "Not long to live, indulge the amorous hour!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22329, line : "Lo! Jove himself (for Jove's command I bear)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22330, line : "Forbids to tempt the wrath of heaven too far."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22331, line : "No longer then (his fury if thou dread)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22332, line : "Detain the relics of great Hector dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22333, line : "Nor vent on senseless earth thy vengeance vain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22334, line : "But yield to ransom, and restore the slain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22336, line : "To whom Achilles: \"Be the ransom given,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22337, line : "And we submit, since such the will of heaven.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22339, line : "While thus they communed, from the Olympian bowers"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22340, line : "Jove orders Iris to the Trojan towers:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22341, line : "\"Haste, winged goddess! to the sacred town,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22342, line : "And urge her monarch to redeem his son."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22343, line : "Alone the Ilian ramparts let him leave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22344, line : "And bear what stern Achilles may receive:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22345, line : "Alone, for so we will; no Trojan near"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22346, line : "Except, to place the dead with decent care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22347, line : "Some aged herald, who with gentle hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22348, line : "May the slow mules and funeral car command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22349, line : "Nor let him death, nor let him danger dread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22350, line : "Safe through the foe by our protection led:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22351, line : "Him Hermes to Achilles shall convey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22352, line : "Guard of his life, and partner of his way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22353, line : "Fierce as he is, Achilles' self shall spare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22354, line : "His age, nor touch one venerable hair:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22355, line : "Some thought there must be in a soul so brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22356, line : "Some sense of duty, some desire to save.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22358, line : "[Illustration: IRIS ADVISES PRIAM TO OBTAIN THE BODY OF HECTOR.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22360, line : "IRIS ADVISES PRIAM TO OBTAIN THE BODY OF HECTOR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22363, line : "Then down her bow the winged Iris drives,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22364, line : "And swift at Priam's mournful court arrives:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22365, line : "Where the sad sons beside their father's throne"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22366, line : "Sat bathed in tears, and answer'd groan with groan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22367, line : "And all amidst them lay the hoary sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22368, line : "(Sad scene of woe!) his face his wrapp'd attire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22369, line : "Conceal'd from sight; with frantic hands he spread"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22370, line : "A shower of ashes o'er his neck and head."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22371, line : "From room to room his pensive daughters roam;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22372, line : "Whose shrieks and clamours fill the vaulted dome;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22373, line : "Mindful of those, who late their pride and joy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22374, line : "Lie pale and breathless round the fields of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22375, line : "Before the king Jove's messenger appears,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22376, line : "And thus in whispers greets his trembling ears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22378, line : "\"Fear not, O father! no ill news I bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22379, line : "From Jove I come, Jove makes thee still his care;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22380, line : "For Hector's sake these walls he bids thee leave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22381, line : "And bear what stern Achilles may receive;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22382, line : "Alone, for so he wills; no Trojan near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22383, line : "Except, to place the dead with decent care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22384, line : "Some aged herald, who with gentle hand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22385, line : "May the slow mules and funeral car command."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22386, line : "Nor shalt thou death, nor shall thou danger dread:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22387, line : "Safe through the foe by his protection led:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22388, line : "Thee Hermes to Pelides shall convey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22389, line : "Guard of thy life, and partner of thy way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22390, line : "Fierce as he is, Achilles' self shall spare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22391, line : "Thy age, nor touch one venerable hair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22392, line : "Some thought there must be in a soul so brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22393, line : "Some sense of duty, some desire to save.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22395, line : "She spoke, and vanish'd. Priam bids prepare"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22396, line : "His gentle mules and harness to the car;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22397, line : "There, for the gifts, a polish'd casket lay:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22398, line : "His pious sons the king's command obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22399, line : "Then pass'd the monarch to his bridal-room,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22400, line : "Where cedar-beams the lofty roofs perfume,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22401, line : "And where the treasures of his empire lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22402, line : "Then call'd his queen, and thus began to say:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22404, line : "\"Unhappy consort of a king distress'd!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22405, line : "Partake the troubles of thy husband's breast:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22406, line : "I saw descend the messenger of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22407, line : "Who bids me try Achilles' mind to move;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22408, line : "Forsake these ramparts, and with gifts obtain"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22409, line : "The corse of Hector, at yon navy slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22410, line : "Tell me thy thought: my heart impels to go"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22411, line : "Through hostile camps, and bears me to the foe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22413, line : "The hoary monarch thus. Her piercing cries"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22414, line : "Sad Hecuba renews, and then replies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22415, line : "\"Ah! whither wanders thy distemper'd mind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22416, line : "And where the prudence now that awed mankind?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22417, line : "Through Phrygia once and foreign regions known;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22418, line : "Now all confused, distracted, overthrown!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22419, line : "Singly to pass through hosts of foes! to face"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22420, line : "(O heart of steel!) the murderer of thy race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22421, line : "To view that deathful eye, and wander o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22422, line : "Those hands yet red with Hector's noble gore!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22423, line : "Alas! my lord! he knows not how to spare."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22424, line : "And what his mercy, thy slain sons declare;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22425, line : "So brave! so many fallen! To claim his rage"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22426, line : "Vain were thy dignity, and vain thy age."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22427, line : "No--pent in this sad palace, let us give"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22428, line : "To grief the wretched days we have to live."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22429, line : "Still, still for Hector let our sorrows flow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22430, line : "Born to his own, and to his parents' woe!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22431, line : "Doom'd from the hour his luckless life begun,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22432, line : "To dogs, to vultures, and to Peleus' son!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22433, line : "Oh! in his dearest blood might I allay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22434, line : "My rage, and these barbarities repay!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22435, line : "For ah! could Hector merit thus, whose breath"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22436, line : "Expired not meanly, in unactive death?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22437, line : "He poured his latest blood in manly fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22438, line : "And fell a hero in his country's right.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22440, line : "\"Seek not to stay me, nor my soul affright"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22441, line : "With words of omen, like a bird of night,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22442, line : "(Replied unmoved the venerable man;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22443, line : "'Tis heaven commands me, and you urge in vain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22444, line : "Had any mortal voice the injunction laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22445, line : "Nor augur, priest, nor seer, had been obey'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22446, line : "A present goddess brought the high command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22447, line : "I saw, I heard her, and the word shall stand."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22448, line : "I go, ye gods! obedient to your call:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22449, line : "If in yon camp your powers have doom'd my fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22450, line : "Content--By the same hand let me expire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22451, line : "Add to the slaughter'd son the wretched sire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22452, line : "One cold embrace at least may be allow'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22453, line : "And my last tears flow mingled with his blood!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22455, line : "From forth his open'd stores, this said, he drew"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22456, line : "Twelve costly carpets of refulgent hue,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22457, line : "As many vests, as many mantles told,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22458, line : "And twelve fair veils, and garments stiff with gold,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22459, line : "Two tripods next, and twice two chargers shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22460, line : "With ten pure talents from the richest mine;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22461, line : "And last a large well-labour'd bowl had place,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22462, line : "(The pledge of treaties once with friendly Thrace:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22463, line : "Seem'd all too mean the stores he could employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22464, line : "For one last look to buy him back to Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22466, line : "Lo! the sad father, frantic with his pain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22467, line : "Around him furious drives his menial train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22468, line : "In vain each slave with duteous care attends,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22469, line : "Each office hurts him, and each face offends."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22470, line : "\"What make ye here, officious crowds! (he cries)."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22471, line : "Hence! nor obtrude your anguish on my eyes."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22472, line : "Have ye no griefs at home, to fix ye there:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22473, line : "Am I the only object of despair?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22474, line : "Am I become my people's common show,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22475, line : "Set up by Jove your spectacle of woe?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22476, line : "No, you must feel him too; yourselves must fall;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22477, line : "The same stern god to ruin gives you all:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22478, line : "Nor is great Hector lost by me alone;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22479, line : "Your sole defence, your guardian power is gone!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22480, line : "I see your blood the fields of Phrygia drown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22481, line : "I see the ruins of your smoking town!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22482, line : "O send me, gods! ere that sad day shall come,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22483, line : "A willing ghost to Pluto's dreary dome!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22485, line : "He said, and feebly drives his friends away:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22486, line : "The sorrowing friends his frantic rage obey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22487, line : "Next on his sons his erring fury falls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22488, line : "Polites, Paris, Agathon, he calls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22489, line : "His threats Deiphobus and Dius hear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22490, line : "Hippothous, Pammon, Helenes the seer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22491, line : "And generous Antiphon: for yet these nine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22492, line : "Survived, sad relics of his numerous line."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22494, line : "\"Inglorious sons of an unhappy sire!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22495, line : "Why did not all in Hector's cause expire?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22496, line : "Wretch that I am! my bravest offspring slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22497, line : "You, the disgrace of Priam's house, remain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22498, line : "Mestor the brave, renown'd in ranks of war,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22499, line : "With Troilus, dreadful on his rushing car,(293)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22500, line : "And last great Hector, more than man divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22501, line : "For sure he seem'd not of terrestrial line!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22502, line : "All those relentless Mars untimely slew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22503, line : "And left me these, a soft and servile crew,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22504, line : "Whose days the feast and wanton dance employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22505, line : "Gluttons and flatterers, the contempt of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22506, line : "Why teach ye not my rapid wheels to run,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22507, line : "And speed my journey to redeem my son?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22509, line : "The sons their father's wretched age revere,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22510, line : "Forgive his anger, and produce the car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22511, line : "High on the seat the cabinet they bind:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22512, line : "The new-made car with solid beauty shined;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22513, line : "Box was the yoke, emboss'd with costly pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22514, line : "And hung with ringlets to receive the reins;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22515, line : "Nine cubits long, the traces swept the ground:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22516, line : "These to the chariot's polish'd pole they bound."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22517, line : "Then fix'd a ring the running reins to guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22518, line : "And close beneath the gather'd ends were tied."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22519, line : "Next with the gifts (the price of Hector slain)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22520, line : "The sad attendants load the groaning wain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22521, line : "Last to the yoke the well-matched mules they bring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22522, line : "(The gift of Mysia to the Trojan king.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22523, line : "But the fair horses, long his darling care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22524, line : "Himself received, and harness'd to his car:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22525, line : "Grieved as he was, he not this task denied;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22526, line : "The hoary herald help'd him, at his side."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22527, line : "While careful these the gentle coursers join'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22528, line : "Sad Hecuba approach'd with anxious mind;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22529, line : "A golden bowl that foam'd with fragrant wine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22530, line : "(Libation destined to the power divine,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22531, line : "Held in her right, before the steed she stands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22532, line : "And thus consigns it to the monarch's hands:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22534, line : "\"Take this, and pour to Jove; that safe from harms"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22535, line : "His grace restore thee to our roof and arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22536, line : "Since victor of thy fears, and slighting mine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22537, line : "Heaven, or thy soul, inspires this bold design;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22538, line : "Pray to that god, who high on Ida's brow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22539, line : "Surveys thy desolated realms below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22540, line : "His winged messenger to send from high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22541, line : "And lead thy way with heavenly augury:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22542, line : "Let the strong sovereign of the plumy race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22543, line : "Tower on the right of yon ethereal space."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22544, line : "That sign beheld, and strengthen'd from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22545, line : "Boldly pursue the journey mark'd by Jove:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22546, line : "But if the god his augury denies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22547, line : "Suppress thy impulse, nor reject advice.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22549, line : "\"'Tis just (said Priam) to the sire above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22550, line : "To raise our hands; for who so good as Jove?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22551, line : "He spoke, and bade the attendant handmaid bring"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22552, line : "The purest water of the living spring:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22553, line : "(Her ready hands the ewer and bason held:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22554, line : "Then took the golden cup his queen had fill'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22555, line : "On the mid pavement pours the rosy wine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22556, line : "Uplifts his eyes, and calls the power divine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22558, line : "\"O first and greatest! heaven's imperial lord!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22559, line : "On lofty Ida's holy hill adored!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22560, line : "To stern Achilles now direct my ways,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22561, line : "And teach him mercy when a father prays."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22562, line : "If such thy will, despatch from yonder sky"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22563, line : "Thy sacred bird, celestial augury!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22564, line : "Let the strong sovereign of the plumy race"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22565, line : "Tower on the right of yon ethereal space;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22566, line : "So shall thy suppliant, strengthen'd from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22567, line : "Fearless pursue the journey mark'd by Jove.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22569, line : "Jove heard his prayer, and from the throne on high,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22570, line : "Despatch'd his bird, celestial augury!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22571, line : "The swift-wing'd chaser of the feather'd game,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22572, line : "And known to gods by Percnos' lofty name."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22573, line : "Wide as appears some palace-gate display'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22574, line : "So broad, his pinions stretch'd their ample shade,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22575, line : "As stooping dexter with resounding wings"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22576, line : "The imperial bird descends in airy rings."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22577, line : "A dawn of joy in every face appears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22578, line : "The mourning matron dries her timorous tears:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22579, line : "Swift on his car the impatient monarch sprung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22580, line : "The brazen portal in his passage rung;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22581, line : "The mules preceding draw the loaded wain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22582, line : "Charged with the gifts: Idaeus holds the rein:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22583, line : "The king himself his gentle steeds controls,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22584, line : "And through surrounding friends the chariot rolls."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22585, line : "On his slow wheels the following people wait,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22586, line : "Mourn at each step, and give him up to fate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22587, line : "With hands uplifted eye him as he pass'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22588, line : "And gaze upon him as they gazed their last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22589, line : "Now forward fares the father on his way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22590, line : "Through the lone fields, and back to Ilion they."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22591, line : "Great Jove beheld him as he cross'd the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22592, line : "And felt the woes of miserable man."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22593, line : "Then thus to Hermes: \"Thou whose constant cares"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22594, line : "Still succour mortals, and attend their prayers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22595, line : "Behold an object to thy charge consign'd:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22596, line : "If ever pity touch'd thee for mankind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22597, line : "Go, guard the sire: the observing foe prevent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22598, line : "And safe conduct him to Achilles' tent.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22600, line : "The god obeys, his golden pinions binds,(294)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22601, line : "And mounts incumbent on the wings of winds,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22602, line : "That high, through fields of air, his flight sustain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22603, line : "O'er the wide earth, and o'er the boundless main;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22604, line : "Then grasps the wand that causes sleep to fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22605, line : "Or in soft slumbers seals the wakeful eye:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22606, line : "Thus arm'd, swift Hermes steers his airy way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22607, line : "And stoops on Hellespont's resounding sea."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22608, line : "A beauteous youth, majestic and divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22609, line : "He seem'd; fair offspring of some princely line!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22610, line : "Now twilight veil'd the glaring face of day,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22611, line : "And clad the dusky fields in sober grey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22612, line : "What time the herald and the hoary king"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22613, line : "(Their chariots stopping at the silver spring,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22614, line : "That circling Ilus' ancient marble flows)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22615, line : "Allow'd their mules and steeds a short repose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22616, line : "Through the dim shade the herald first espies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22617, line : "A man's approach, and thus to Priam cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22618, line : "\"I mark some foe's advance: O king! beware;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22619, line : "This hard adventure claims thy utmost care!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22620, line : "For much I fear destruction hovers nigh:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22621, line : "Our state asks counsel; is it best to fly?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22622, line : "Or old and helpless, at his feet to fall,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22623, line : "Two wretched suppliants, and for mercy call?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22625, line : "The afflicted monarch shiver'd with despair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22626, line : "Pale grew his face, and upright stood his hair;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22627, line : "Sunk was his heart; his colour went and came;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22628, line : "A sudden trembling shook his aged frame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22629, line : "When Hermes, greeting, touch'd his royal hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22630, line : "And, gentle, thus accosts with kind demand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22632, line : "\"Say whither, father! when each mortal sight"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22633, line : "Is seal'd in sleep, thou wanderest through the night?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22634, line : "Why roam thy mules and steeds the plains along,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22635, line : "Through Grecian foes, so numerous and so strong?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22636, line : "What couldst thou hope, should these thy treasures view;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22637, line : "These, who with endless hate thy race pursue?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22638, line : "For what defence, alas! could'st thou provide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22639, line : "Thyself not young, a weak old man thy guide?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22640, line : "Yet suffer not thy soul to sink with dread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22641, line : "From me no harm shall touch thy reverend head;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22642, line : "From Greece I'll guard thee too; for in those lines"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22643, line : "The living image of my father shines.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22645, line : "\"Thy words, that speak benevolence of mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22646, line : "Are true, my son! (the godlike sire rejoin'd:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22647, line : "Great are my hazards; but the gods survey"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22648, line : "My steps, and send thee, guardian of my way."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22649, line : "Hail, and be bless'd! For scarce of mortal kind"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22650, line : "Appear thy form, thy feature, and thy mind.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22652, line : "\"Nor true are all thy words, nor erring wide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22653, line : "(The sacred messenger of heaven replied;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22654, line : "But say, convey'st thou through the lonely plains"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22655, line : "What yet most precious of thy store remains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22656, line : "To lodge in safety with some friendly hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22657, line : "Prepared, perchance, to leave thy native land?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22658, line : "Or fliest thou now?--What hopes can Troy retain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22659, line : "Thy matchless son, her guard and glory, slain?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22661, line : "The king, alarm'd: \"Say what, and whence thou art"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22662, line : "Who search the sorrows of a parent's heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22663, line : "And know so well how godlike Hector died?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22664, line : "Thus Priam spoke, and Hermes thus replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22666, line : "\"You tempt me, father, and with pity touch:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22667, line : "On this sad subject you inquire too much."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22668, line : "Oft have these eyes that godlike Hector view'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22669, line : "In glorious fight, with Grecian blood embrued:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22670, line : "I saw him when, like Jove, his flames he toss'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22671, line : "On thousand ships, and wither'd half a host:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22672, line : "I saw, but help'd not: stern Achilles' ire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22673, line : "Forbade assistance, and enjoy'd the fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22674, line : "For him I serve, of Myrmidonian race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22675, line : "One ship convey'd us from our native place;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22676, line : "Polyctor is my sire, an honour'd name,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22677, line : "Old like thyself, and not unknown to fame;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22678, line : "Of seven his sons, by whom the lot was cast"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22679, line : "To serve our prince, it fell on me, the last."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22680, line : "To watch this quarter, my adventure falls:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22681, line : "For with the morn the Greeks attack your walls;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22682, line : "Sleepless they sit, impatient to engage,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22683, line : "And scarce their rulers check their martial rage.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22685, line : "\"If then thou art of stern Pelides' train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22686, line : "(The mournful monarch thus rejoin'd again,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22687, line : "Ah tell me truly, where, oh! where are laid"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22688, line : "My son's dear relics? what befals him dead?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22689, line : "Have dogs dismember'd (on the naked plains),"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22690, line : "Or yet unmangled rest, his cold remains?\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22692, line : "\"O favour'd of the skies! (thus answered then"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22693, line : "The power that mediates between god and men)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22694, line : "Nor dogs nor vultures have thy Hector rent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22695, line : "But whole he lies, neglected in the tent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22696, line : "This the twelfth evening since he rested there,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22697, line : "Untouch'd by worms, untainted by the air."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22698, line : "Still as Aurora's ruddy beam is spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22699, line : "Round his friend's tomb Achilles drags the dead:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22700, line : "Yet undisfigured, or in limb or face,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22701, line : "All fresh he lies, with every living grace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22702, line : "Majestical in death! No stains are found"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22703, line : "O'er all the corse, and closed is every wound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22704, line : "Though many a wound they gave. Some heavenly care,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22705, line : "Some hand divine, preserves him ever fair:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22706, line : "Or all the host of heaven, to whom he led"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22707, line : "A life so grateful, still regard him dead.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22709, line : "Thus spoke to Priam the celestial guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22710, line : "And joyful thus the royal sire replied:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22711, line : "\"Blest is the man who pays the gods above"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22712, line : "The constant tribute of respect and love!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22713, line : "Those who inhabit the Olympian bower"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22714, line : "My son forgot not, in exalted power;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22715, line : "And heaven, that every virtue bears in mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22716, line : "Even to the ashes of the just is kind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22717, line : "But thou, O generous youth! this goblet take,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22718, line : "A pledge of gratitude for Hector's sake;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22719, line : "And while the favouring gods our steps survey,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22720, line : "Safe to Pelides' tent conduct my way.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22722, line : "To whom the latent god: \"O king, forbear"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22723, line : "To tempt my youth, for apt is youth to err."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22724, line : "But can I, absent from my prince's sight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22725, line : "Take gifts in secret, that must shun the light?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22726, line : "What from our master's interest thus we draw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22727, line : "Is but a licensed theft that 'scapes the law."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22728, line : "Respecting him, my soul abjures the offence;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22729, line : "And as the crime, I dread the consequence."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22730, line : "Thee, far as Argos, pleased I could convey;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22731, line : "Guard of thy life, and partner of thy way:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22732, line : "On thee attend, thy safety to maintain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22733, line : "O'er pathless forests, or the roaring main.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22735, line : "He said, then took the chariot at a bound,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22736, line : "And snatch'd the reins, and whirl'd the lash around:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22737, line : "Before the inspiring god that urged them on,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22738, line : "The coursers fly with spirit not their own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22739, line : "And now they reach'd the naval walls, and found"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22740, line : "The guards repasting, while the bowls go round;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22741, line : "On these the virtue of his wand he tries,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22742, line : "And pours deep slumber on their watchful eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22743, line : "Then heaved the massy gates, removed the bars,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22744, line : "And o'er the trenches led the rolling cars."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22745, line : "Unseen, through all the hostile camp they went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22746, line : "And now approach'd Pelides' lofty tent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22747, line : "On firs the roof was raised, and cover'd o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22748, line : "With reeds collected from the marshy shore;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22749, line : "And, fenced with palisades, a hall of state,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22750, line : "(The work of soldiers,) where the hero sat."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22751, line : "Large was the door, whose well-compacted strength"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22752, line : "A solid pine-tree barr'd of wondrous length:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22753, line : "Scarce three strong Greeks could lift its mighty weight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22754, line : "But great Achilles singly closed the gate."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22755, line : "This Hermes (such the power of gods) set wide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22756, line : "Then swift alighted the celestial guide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22757, line : "And thus reveal'd--\"Hear, prince! and understand"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22758, line : "Thou ow'st thy guidance to no mortal hand:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22759, line : "Hermes I am, descended from above,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22760, line : "The king of arts, the messenger of Jove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22761, line : "Farewell: to shun Achilles' sight I fly;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22762, line : "Uncommon are such favours of the sky,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22763, line : "Nor stand confess'd to frail mortality."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22764, line : "Now fearless enter, and prefer thy prayers;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22765, line : "Adjure him by his father's silver hairs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22766, line : "His son, his mother! urge him to bestow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22767, line : "Whatever pity that stern heart can know.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22769, line : "Thus having said, he vanish'd from his eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22770, line : "And in a moment shot into the skies:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22771, line : "The king, confirm'd from heaven, alighted there,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22772, line : "And left his aged herald on the car,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22773, line : "With solemn pace through various rooms he went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22774, line : "And found Achilles in his inner tent:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22775, line : "There sat the hero: Alcimus the brave,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22776, line : "And great Automedon, attendance gave:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22777, line : "These served his person at the royal feast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22778, line : "Around, at awful distance, stood the rest."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22780, line : "Unseen by these, the king his entry made:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22781, line : "And, prostrate now before Achilles laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22782, line : "Sudden (a venerable sight!) appears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22783, line : "Embraced his knees, and bathed his hands in tears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22784, line : "Those direful hands his kisses press'd, embrued"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22785, line : "Even with the best, the dearest of his blood!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22787, line : "As when a wretch (who, conscious of his crime,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22788, line : "Pursued for murder, flies his native clime)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22789, line : "Just gains some frontier, breathless, pale, amazed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22790, line : "All gaze, all wonder: thus Achilles gazed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22791, line : "Thus stood the attendants stupid with surprise:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22792, line : "All mute, yet seem'd to question with their eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22793, line : "Each look'd on other, none the silence broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22794, line : "Till thus at last the kingly suppliant spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22796, line : "\"Ah think, thou favour'd of the powers divine!(295)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22797, line : "Think of thy father's age, and pity mine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22798, line : "In me that father's reverend image trace,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22799, line : "Those silver hairs, that venerable face;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22800, line : "His trembling limbs, his helpless person, see!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22801, line : "In all my equal, but in misery!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22802, line : "Yet now, perhaps, some turn of human fate"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22803, line : "Expels him helpless from his peaceful state;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22804, line : "Think, from some powerful foe thou seest him fly,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22805, line : "And beg protection with a feeble cry."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22806, line : "Yet still one comfort in his soul may rise;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22807, line : "He hears his son still lives to glad his eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22808, line : "And, hearing, still may hope a better day"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22809, line : "May send him thee, to chase that foe away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22810, line : "No comfort to my griefs, no hopes remain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22811, line : "The best, the bravest, of my sons are slain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22812, line : "Yet what a race! ere Greece to Ilion came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22813, line : "The pledge of many a loved and loving dame:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22814, line : "Nineteen one mother bore--Dead, all are dead!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22815, line : "How oft, alas! has wretched Priam bled!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22816, line : "Still one was left their loss to recompense;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22817, line : "His father's hope, his country's last defence."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22818, line : "Him too thy rage has slain! beneath thy steel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22819, line : "Unhappy in his country's cause he fell!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22821, line : "\"For him through hostile camps I bent my way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22822, line : "For him thus prostrate at thy feet I lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22823, line : "Large gifts proportion'd to thy wrath I bear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22824, line : "O hear the wretched, and the gods revere!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22826, line : "\"Think of thy father, and this face behold!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22827, line : "See him in me, as helpless and as old!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22828, line : "Though not so wretched: there he yields to me,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22829, line : "The first of men in sovereign misery!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22830, line : "Thus forced to kneel, thus grovelling to embrace"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22831, line : "The scourge and ruin of my realm and race;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22832, line : "Suppliant my children's murderer to implore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22833, line : "And kiss those hands yet reeking with their gore!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22835, line : "These words soft pity in the chief inspire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22836, line : "Touch'd with the dear remembrance of his sire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22837, line : "Then with his hand (as prostrate still he lay)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22838, line : "The old man's cheek he gently turn'd away."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22839, line : "Now each by turns indulged the gush of woe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22840, line : "And now the mingled tides together flow:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22841, line : "This low on earth, that gently bending o'er;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22842, line : "A father one, and one a son deplore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22843, line : "But great Achilles different passions rend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22844, line : "And now his sire he mourns, and now his friend."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22845, line : "The infectious softness through the heroes ran;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22846, line : "One universal solemn shower began;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22847, line : "They bore as heroes, but they felt as man."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22849, line : "Satiate at length with unavailing woes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22850, line : "From the high throne divine Achilles rose;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22851, line : "The reverend monarch by the hand he raised;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22852, line : "On his white beard and form majestic gazed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22853, line : "Not unrelenting; then serene began"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22854, line : "With words to soothe the miserable man:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22856, line : "\"Alas, what weight of anguish hast thou known,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22857, line : "Unhappy prince! thus guardless and alone"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22858, line : "Two pass through foes, and thus undaunted face"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22859, line : "The man whose fury has destroy'd thy race!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22860, line : "Heaven sure has arm'd thee with a heart of steel,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22861, line : "A strength proportion'd to the woes you feel."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22862, line : "Rise, then: let reason mitigate your care:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22863, line : "To mourn avails not: man is born to bear."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22864, line : "Such is, alas! the gods' severe decree:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22865, line : "They, only they are blest, and only free."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22866, line : "Two urns by Jove's high throne have ever stood,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22867, line : "The source of evil one, and one of good;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22868, line : "From thence the cup of mortal man he fills,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22869, line : "Blessings to these, to those distributes ill;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22870, line : "To most he mingles both: the wretch decreed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22871, line : "To taste the bad unmix'd, is cursed indeed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22872, line : "Pursued by wrongs, by meagre famine driven,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22873, line : "He wanders, outcast both of earth and heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22874, line : "The happiest taste not happiness sincere;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22875, line : "But find the cordial draught is dash'd with care."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22876, line : "Who more than Peleus shone in wealth and power"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22877, line : "What stars concurring bless'd his natal hour!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22878, line : "A realm, a goddess, to his wishes given;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22879, line : "Graced by the gods with all the gifts of heaven."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22880, line : "One evil yet o'ertakes his latest day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22881, line : "No race succeeding to imperial sway;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22882, line : "An only son; and he, alas! ordain'd"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22883, line : "To fall untimely in a foreign land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22884, line : "See him, in Troy, the pious care decline"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22885, line : "Of his weak age, to live the curse of thine!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22886, line : "Thou too, old man, hast happier days beheld;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22887, line : "In riches once, in children once excell'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22888, line : "Extended Phrygia own'd thy ample reign,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22889, line : "And all fair Lesbos' blissful seats contain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22890, line : "And all wide Hellespont's unmeasured main."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22891, line : "But since the god his hand has pleased to turn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22892, line : "And fill thy measure from his bitter urn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22893, line : "What sees the sun, but hapless heroes' falls?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22894, line : "War, and the blood of men, surround thy walls!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22895, line : "What must be, must be. Bear thy lot, nor shed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22896, line : "These unavailing sorrows o'er the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22897, line : "Thou canst not call him from the Stygian shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22898, line : "But thou, alas! may'st live to suffer more!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22900, line : "To whom the king: \"O favour'd of the skies!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22901, line : "Here let me grow to earth! since Hector lies"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22902, line : "On the bare beach deprived of obsequies."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22903, line : "O give me Hector! to my eyes restore"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22904, line : "His corse, and take the gifts: I ask no more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22905, line : "Thou, as thou may'st, these boundless stores enjoy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22906, line : "Safe may'st thou sail, and turn thy wrath from Troy;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22907, line : "So shall thy pity and forbearance give"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22908, line : "A weak old man to see the light and live!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22910, line : "\"Move me no more, (Achilles thus replies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22911, line : "While kindling anger sparkled in his eyes,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22912, line : "Nor seek by tears my steady soul to bend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22913, line : "To yield thy Hector I myself intend:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22914, line : "For know, from Jove my goddess-mother came,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22915, line : "(Old Ocean's daughter, silver-footed dame,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22916, line : "Nor comest thou but by heaven; nor comest alone,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22917, line : "Some god impels with courage not thy own:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22918, line : "No human hand the weighty gates unbarr'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22919, line : "Nor could the boldest of our youth have dared"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22920, line : "To pass our outworks, or elude the guard."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22921, line : "Cease; lest, neglectful of high Jove's command,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22922, line : "I show thee, king! thou tread'st on hostile land;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22923, line : "Release my knees, thy suppliant arts give o'er,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22924, line : "And shake the purpose of my soul no more.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22926, line : "The sire obey'd him, trembling and o'eraw'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22927, line : "Achilles, like a lion, rush'd abroad:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22928, line : "Automedon and Alcimus attend,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22929, line : "(Whom most he honour'd, since he lost his friend,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22930, line : "These to unyoke the mules and horses went,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22931, line : "And led the hoary herald to the tent;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22932, line : "Next, heap'd on high, the numerous presents bear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22933, line : "(Great Hector's ransom,) from the polish'd car."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22934, line : "Two splendid mantles, and a carpet spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22935, line : "They leave: to cover and enwrap the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22936, line : "Then call the handmaids, with assistant toil"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22937, line : "To wash the body and anoint with oil,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22938, line : "Apart from Priam: lest the unhappy sire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22939, line : "Provoked to passion, once more rouse to ire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22940, line : "The stern Pelides; and nor sacred age,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22941, line : "Nor Jove's command, should check the rising rage."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22942, line : "This done, the garments o'er the corse they spread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22943, line : "Achilles lifts it to the funeral bed:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22944, line : "Then, while the body on the car they laid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22945, line : "He groans, and calls on loved Patroclus' shade:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22947, line : "\"If, in that gloom which never light must know,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22948, line : "The deeds of mortals touch the ghosts below,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22949, line : "O friend! forgive me, that I thus fulfil"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22950, line : "(Restoring Hector) heaven's unquestion'd will."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22951, line : "The gifts the father gave, be ever thine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22952, line : "To grace thy manes, and adorn thy shrine.\"(296)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22954, line : "He said, and, entering, took his seat of state;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22955, line : "Where full before him reverend Priam sate;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22956, line : "To whom, composed, the godlike chief begun:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22957, line : "\"Lo! to thy prayer restored, thy breathless son;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22958, line : "Extended on the funeral couch he lies;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22959, line : "And soon as morning paints the eastern skies,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22960, line : "The sight is granted to thy longing eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22961, line : "But now the peaceful hours of sacred night"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22962, line : "Demand reflection, and to rest invite:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22963, line : "Nor thou, O father! thus consumed with woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22964, line : "The common cares that nourish life forego."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22965, line : "Not thus did Niobe, of form divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22966, line : "A parent once, whose sorrows equall'd thine:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22967, line : "Six youthful sons, as many blooming maids,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22968, line : "In one sad day beheld the Stygian shades;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22969, line : "Those by Apollo's silver bow were slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22970, line : "These, Cynthia's arrows stretch'd upon the plain:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22971, line : "So was her pride chastised by wrath divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22972, line : "Who match'd her own with bright Latona's line;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22973, line : "But two the goddess, twelve the queen enjoy'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22974, line : "Those boasted twelve, the avenging two destroy'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22975, line : "Steep'd in their blood, and in the dust outspread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22976, line : "Nine days, neglected, lay exposed the dead;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22977, line : "None by to weep them, to inhume them none;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22978, line : "(For Jove had turn'd the nation all to stone.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22979, line : "The gods themselves, at length relenting gave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22980, line : "The unhappy race the honours of a grave."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22981, line : "Herself a rock (for such was heaven's high will)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22982, line : "Through deserts wild now pours a weeping rill;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22983, line : "Where round the bed whence Achelous springs,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22984, line : "The watery fairies dance in mazy rings;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22985, line : "There high on Sipylus's shaggy brow,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22986, line : "She stands, her own sad monument of woe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22987, line : "The rock for ever lasts, the tears for ever flow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22989, line : "\"Such griefs, O king! have other parents known;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22990, line : "Remember theirs, and mitigate thy own."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22991, line : "The care of heaven thy Hector has appear'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22992, line : "Nor shall he lie unwept, and uninterr'd;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22993, line : "Soon may thy aged cheeks in tears be drown'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22994, line : "And all the eyes of Ilion stream around.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22996, line : "He said, and, rising, chose the victim ewe"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22997, line : "With silver fleece, which his attendants slew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22998, line : "The limbs they sever from the reeking hide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 22999, line : "With skill prepare them, and in parts divide:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23000, line : "Each on the coals the separate morsels lays,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23001, line : "And, hasty, snatches from the rising blaze."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23002, line : "With bread the glittering canisters they load,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23003, line : "Which round the board Automedon bestow'd."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23004, line : "The chief himself to each his portion placed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23005, line : "And each indulging shared in sweet repast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23006, line : "When now the rage of hunger was repress'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23007, line : "The wondering hero eyes his royal guest:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23008, line : "No less the royal guest the hero eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23009, line : "His godlike aspect and majestic size;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23010, line : "Here, youthful grace and noble fire engage;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23011, line : "And there, the mild benevolence of age."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23012, line : "Thus gazing long, the silence neither broke,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23013, line : "(A solemn scene!) at length the father spoke:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23015, line : "\"Permit me now, beloved of Jove! to steep"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23016, line : "My careful temples in the dew of sleep:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23017, line : "For, since the day that number'd with the dead"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23018, line : "My hapless son, the dust has been my bed;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23019, line : "Soft sleep a stranger to my weeping eyes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23020, line : "My only food, my sorrows and my sighs!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23021, line : "Till now, encouraged by the grace you give,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23022, line : "I share thy banquet, and consent to live.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23024, line : "With that, Achilles bade prepare the bed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23025, line : "With purple soft and shaggy carpets spread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23026, line : "Forth, by the flaming lights, they bend their way,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23027, line : "And place the couches, and the coverings lay."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23028, line : "Then he: \"Now, father, sleep, but sleep not here;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23029, line : "Consult thy safety, and forgive my fear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23030, line : "Lest any Argive, at this hour awake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23031, line : "To ask our counsel, or our orders take,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23032, line : "Approaching sudden to our open'd tent,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23033, line : "Perchance behold thee, and our grace prevent."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23034, line : "Should such report thy honour'd person here,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23035, line : "The king of men the ransom might defer;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23036, line : "But say with speed, if aught of thy desire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23037, line : "Remains unask'd; what time the rites require"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23038, line : "To inter thy Hector? For, so long we stay"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23039, line : "Our slaughtering arm, and bid the hosts obey.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23041, line : "\"If then thy will permit (the monarch said)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23042, line : "To finish all due honours to the dead,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23043, line : "This of thy grace accord: to thee are known"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23044, line : "The fears of Ilion, closed within her town;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23045, line : "And at what distance from our walls aspire"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23046, line : "The hills of Ide, and forests for the fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23047, line : "Nine days to vent our sorrows I request,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23048, line : "The tenth shall see the funeral and the feast;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23049, line : "The next, to raise his monument be given;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23050, line : "The twelfth we war, if war be doom'd by heaven!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23052, line : "\"This thy request (replied the chief) enjoy:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23053, line : "Till then our arms suspend the fall of Troy.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23055, line : "Then gave his hand at parting, to prevent"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23056, line : "The old man's fears, and turn'd within the tent;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23057, line : "Where fair Briseis, bright in blooming charms,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23058, line : "Expects her hero with desiring arms."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23059, line : "But in the porch the king and herald rest;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23060, line : "Sad dreams of care yet wandering in their breast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23061, line : "Now gods and men the gifts of sleep partake;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23062, line : "Industrious Hermes only was awake,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23063, line : "The king's return revolving in his mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23064, line : "To pass the ramparts, and the watch to blind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23065, line : "The power descending hover'd o'er his head:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23066, line : "\"And sleep'st thou, father! (thus the vision said:)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23067, line : "Now dost thou sleep, when Hector is restored?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23068, line : "Nor fear the Grecian foes, or Grecian lord?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23069, line : "Thy presence here should stern Atrides see,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23070, line : "Thy still surviving sons may sue for thee;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23071, line : "May offer all thy treasures yet contain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23072, line : "To spare thy age; and offer all in vain.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23074, line : "Waked with the word the trembling sire arose,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23075, line : "And raised his friend: the god before him goes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23076, line : "He joins the mules, directs them with his hand,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23077, line : "And moves in silence through the hostile land."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23078, line : "When now to Xanthus' yellow stream they drove,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23079, line : "(Xanthus, immortal progeny of Jove,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23080, line : "The winged deity forsook their view,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23081, line : "And in a moment to Olympus flew."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23082, line : "Now shed Aurora round her saffron ray,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23083, line : "Sprang through the gates of light, and gave the day:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23084, line : "Charged with the mournful load, to Ilion go"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23085, line : "The sage and king, majestically slow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23086, line : "Cassandra first beholds, from Ilion's spire,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23087, line : "The sad procession of her hoary sire;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23088, line : "Then, as the pensive pomp advanced more near,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23089, line : "(Her breathless brother stretched upon the bier,)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23090, line : "A shower of tears o'erflows her beauteous eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23091, line : "Alarming thus all Ilion with her cries:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23093, line : "\"Turn here your steps, and here your eyes employ,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23094, line : "Ye wretched daughters, and ye sons of Troy!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23095, line : "If e'er ye rush'd in crowds, with vast delight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23096, line : "To hail your hero glorious from the fight,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23097, line : "Now meet him dead, and let your sorrows flow;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23098, line : "Your common triumph, and your common woe.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23100, line : "In thronging crowds they issue to the plains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23101, line : "Nor man nor woman in the walls remains;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23102, line : "In every face the self-same grief is shown;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23103, line : "And Troy sends forth one universal groan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23104, line : "At Scaea's gates they meet the mourning wain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23105, line : "Hang on the wheels, and grovel round the slain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23106, line : "The wife and mother, frantic with despair,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23107, line : "Kiss his pale cheek, and rend their scatter'd hair:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23108, line : "Thus wildly wailing, at the gates they lay;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23109, line : "And there had sigh'd and sorrow'd out the day;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23110, line : "But godlike Priam from the chariot rose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23111, line : "\"Forbear (he cried) this violence of woes;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23112, line : "First to the palace let the car proceed,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23113, line : "Then pour your boundless sorrows o'er the dead.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23115, line : "The waves of people at his word divide,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23116, line : "Slow rolls the chariot through the following tide;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23117, line : "Even to the palace the sad pomp they wait:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23118, line : "They weep, and place him on the bed of state."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23119, line : "A melancholy choir attend around,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23120, line : "With plaintive sighs, and music's solemn sound:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23121, line : "Alternately they sing, alternate flow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23122, line : "The obedient tears, melodious in their woe."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23123, line : "While deeper sorrows groan from each full heart,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23124, line : "And nature speaks at every pause of art."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23126, line : "First to the corse the weeping consort flew;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23127, line : "Around his neck her milk-white arms she threw,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23128, line : "\"And oh, my Hector! Oh, my lord! (she cries)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23129, line : "Snatch'd in thy bloom from these desiring eyes!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23130, line : "Thou to the dismal realms for ever gone!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23131, line : "And I abandon'd, desolate, alone!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23132, line : "An only son, once comfort of our pains,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23133, line : "Sad product now of hapless love, remains!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23134, line : "Never to manly age that son shall rise,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23135, line : "Or with increasing graces glad my eyes:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23136, line : "For Ilion now (her great defender slain)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23137, line : "Shall sink a smoking ruin on the plain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23138, line : "Who now protects her wives with guardian care?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23139, line : "Who saves her infants from the rage of war?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23140, line : "Now hostile fleets must waft those infants o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23141, line : "(Those wives must wait them) to a foreign shore:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23142, line : "Thou too, my son, to barbarous climes shall go,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23143, line : "The sad companion of thy mother's woe;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23144, line : "Driven hence a slave before the victor's sword"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23145, line : "Condemn'd to toil for some inhuman lord:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23146, line : "Or else some Greek whose father press'd the plain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23147, line : "Or son, or brother, by great Hector slain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23148, line : "In Hector's blood his vengeance shall enjoy,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23149, line : "And hurl thee headlong from the towers of Troy.(297)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23150, line : "For thy stern father never spared a foe:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23151, line : "Thence all these tears, and all this scene of woe!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23152, line : "Thence many evils his sad parents bore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23153, line : "His parents many, but his consort more."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23154, line : "Why gav'st thou not to me thy dying hand?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23155, line : "And why received not I thy last command?"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23156, line : "Some word thou would'st have spoke, which, sadly dear,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23157, line : "My soul might keep, or utter with a tear;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23158, line : "Which never, never could be lost in air,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23159, line : "Fix'd in my heart, and oft repeated there!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23161, line : "Thus to her weeping maids she makes her moan,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23162, line : "Her weeping handmaids echo groan for groan."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23164, line : "The mournful mother next sustains her part:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23165, line : "\"O thou, the best, the dearest to my heart!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23166, line : "Of all my race thou most by heaven approved,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23167, line : "And by the immortals even in death beloved!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23168, line : "While all my other sons in barbarous bands"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23169, line : "Achilles bound, and sold to foreign lands,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23170, line : "This felt no chains, but went a glorious ghost,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23171, line : "Free, and a hero, to the Stygian coast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23172, line : "Sentenced, 'tis true, by his inhuman doom,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23173, line : "Thy noble corse was dragg'd around the tomb;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23174, line : "(The tomb of him thy warlike arm had slain;)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23175, line : "Ungenerous insult, impotent and vain!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23176, line : "Yet glow'st thou fresh with every living grace;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23177, line : "No mark of pain, or violence of face:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23178, line : "Rosy and fair! as Phoebus' silver bow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23179, line : "Dismiss'd thee gently to the shades below.\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23181, line : "Thus spoke the dame, and melted into tears."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23182, line : "Sad Helen next in pomp of grief appears;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23183, line : "Fast from the shining sluices of her eyes"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23184, line : "Fall the round crystal drops, while thus she cries."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23186, line : "\"Ah, dearest friend! in whom the gods had join'd(298)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23187, line : "Tne mildest manners with the bravest mind,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23188, line : "Now twice ten years (unhappy years) are o'er"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23189, line : "Since Paris brought me to the Trojan shore,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23190, line : "(O had I perish'd, ere that form divine"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23191, line : "Seduced this soft, this easy heart of mine!)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23192, line : "Yet was it ne'er my fate, from thee to find"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23193, line : "A deed ungentle, or a word unkind."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23194, line : "When others cursed the authoress of their woe,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23195, line : "Thy pity check'd my sorrows in their flow."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23196, line : "If some proud brother eyed me with disdain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23197, line : "Or scornful sister with her sweeping train,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23198, line : "Thy gentle accents soften'd all my pain."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23199, line : "For thee I mourn, and mourn myself in thee,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23200, line : "The wretched source of all this misery."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23201, line : "The fate I caused, for ever I bemoan;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23202, line : "Sad Helen has no friend, now thou art gone!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23203, line : "Through Troy's wide streets abandon'd shall I roam!"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23204, line : "In Troy deserted, as abhorr'd at home!\""});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23206, line : "So spoke the fair, with sorrow-streaming eye."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23207, line : "Distressful beauty melts each stander-by."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23208, line : "On all around the infectious sorrow grows;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23209, line : "But Priam check'd the torrent as it rose:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23210, line : "\"Perform, ye Trojans! what the rites require,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23211, line : "And fell the forests for a funeral pyre;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23212, line : "Twelve days, nor foes nor secret ambush dread;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23213, line : "Achilles grants these honours to the dead.\"(299)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23215, line : "[Illustration: FUNERAL OF HECTOR.]"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23217, line : "FUNERAL OF HECTOR."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23220, line : "He spoke, and, at his word, the Trojan train"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23221, line : "Their mules and oxen harness to the wain,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23222, line : "Pour through the gates, and fell'd from Ida's crown,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23223, line : "Roll back the gather'd forests to the town."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23224, line : "These toils continue nine succeeding days,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23225, line : "And high in air a sylvan structure raise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23226, line : "But when the tenth fair morn began to shine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23227, line : "Forth to the pile was borne the man divine,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23228, line : "And placed aloft; while all, with streaming eyes,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23229, line : "Beheld the flames and rolling smokes arise."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23230, line : "Soon as Aurora, daughter of the dawn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23231, line : "With rosy lustre streak'd the dewy lawn,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23232, line : "Again the mournful crowds surround the pyre,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23233, line : "And quench with wine the yet remaining fire."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23234, line : "The snowy bones his friends and brothers place"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23235, line : "(With tears collected) in a golden vase;"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23236, line : "The golden vase in purple palls they roll'd,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23237, line : "Of softest texture, and inwrought with gold."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23238, line : "Last o'er the urn the sacred earth they spread,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23239, line : "And raised the tomb, memorial of the dead."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23240, line : "(Strong guards and spies, till all the rites were done,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23241, line : "Watch'd from the rising to the setting sun.)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23242, line : "All Troy then moves to Priam's court again,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23243, line : "A solemn, silent, melancholy train:"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23244, line : "Assembled there, from pious toil they rest,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23245, line : "And sadly shared the last sepulchral feast."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23246, line : "Such honours Ilion to her hero paid,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23247, line : "And peaceful slept the mighty Hector's shade.(300)"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23253, line : "CONCLUDING NOTE."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23256, line : "We have now passed through the Iliad, and seen the anger of Achilles, and"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23257, line : "the terrible effects of it, at an end, as that only was the subject of the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23258, line : "poem, and the nature of epic poetry would not permit our author to proceed"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23259, line : "to the event of the war, it perhaps may be acceptable to the common reader"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23260, line : "to give a short account of what happened to Troy and the chief actors in"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23261, line : "this poem after the conclusion of it."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23263, line : "I need not mention that Troy was taken soon after the death of Hector by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23264, line : "the stratagem of the wooden horse, the particulars of which are described"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23265, line : "by Virgil in the second book of the Ćneid."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23267, line : "Achilles fell before Troy, by the hand of Paris, by the shot of an arrow"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23268, line : "in his heel, as Hector had prophesied at his death, lib. xxii."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23270, line : "The unfortunate Priam was killed by Pyrrhus, the son of Achilles."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23272, line : "Ajax, after the death of Achilles, had a contest with Ulysses for the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23273, line : "armour of Vulcan, but being defeated in his aim, he slew himself through"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23274, line : "indignation."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23276, line : "Helen, after the death of Paris, married Deiphobus his brother, and at the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23277, line : "taking of Troy betrayed him, in order to reconcile herself to Menelaus her"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23278, line : "first husband, who received her again into favour."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23280, line : "Agamemnon at his return was barbarously murdered by Ćgysthus, at the"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23281, line : "instigation of Clytemnestra his wife, who in his absence had dishonoured"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23282, line : "his bed with Ćgysthus."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23284, line : "Diomed, after the fall of Troy, was expelled his own country, and scarce"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23285, line : "escaped with his life from his adulterous wife Ćgiale; but at last was"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23286, line : "received by Daunus in Apulia, and shared his kingdom; it is uncertain how"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23287, line : "he died."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23289, line : "Nestor lived in peace with his children, in Pylos, his native country."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23291, line : "Ulysses also, after innumerable troubles by sea and land, at last returned"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23292, line : "in safety to Ithaca, which is the subject of Homer's Odyssey."});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23294, line : "For what remains, I beg to be excused from the ceremonies of taking leave"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23295, line : "at the end of my work, and from embarrassing myself, or others, with any"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23296, line : "defences or apologies about it. But instead of endeavouring to raise a"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23297, line : "vain monument to myself, of the merits or difficulties of it (which must"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23298, line : "be left to the world, to truth, and to posterity), let me leave behind me"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23299, line : "a memorial of my friendship with one of the most valuable of men, as well"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23300, line : "as finest writers, of my age and country, one who has tried, and knows by"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23301, line : "his own experience, how hard an undertaking it is to do justice to Homer,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23302, line : "and one whom (I am sure) sincerely rejoices with me at the period of my"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23303, line : "labours. To him, therefore, having brought this long work to a conclusion,"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23304, line : "I desire to dedicate it, and to have the honour and satisfaction of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23305, line : "placing together, in this manner, the names of Mr. CONGREVE, and of"});
db.iliad.insert({ pg : 23307, line : "March 25, 1720"});
